{"_id":"QBtYDU5Qp9Tn9x6y","name":"Red-hood / Iskra","pages":[{"_id":"iJKUO82K7mTDMwnt","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>Red-hood / Iskra</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> Core Book</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, pages 119-130.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/red-hood-iskra-p119-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513694282,"modifiedTime":1781513694282,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"2PAKjAoXwCa7bOQe","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Red-hood / Iskra - Setup</h2><p>118<br>Red-hood <br>Iskra Once upon a time…<br>The prosperous village of Durfort in <br>Gévaudan, France is being terrorized by <br>ferocious beasts. Gerard Dubois, the local <br>lord of the manor, is recently married to the <br>beautiful Elizaveta of Volhynia but finds <br>he cannot enjoy his honeymoon when his <br>desperate subjects are constantly pestering <br>him for help. Finding that the cause of <br>their fears are beyond his meager ability to <br>manage, Gerard has written a letter to the <br>Papacy, quietly begging for help. The letter, <br>written in Lord Gerard’s trembling hand, <br>reads, “The beasts that menace the Gévaudan <br>are unnatural, fashioned by something other <br>than God. ”<br>A group of the Order’s Hunters is sent to the <br>village of Durfort to find out what is really <br>going on...<br>A Scenario inspired by <br>Little Red Riding Hood <br>(Charles Perrault)<br>Safety Keywords:<br>  <br>Child neglect / Revenge</p><p>Play the official Red-Hood Iskra <br>soundtrack during your game <br>session!<br>119<br>The story that led us here…<br>Elizaveta of Volhynia has always been an attractive <br>woman, accustomed to the rich salons of the gentry, and <br>the pomp of nobles and courtiers. Becoming pregnant with <br>Iskra, her eldest daughter, was a curse for her.<br>Abandoned by her wealthy lover, Elizaveta was  <br>impoverished for years, with few skills, little work, and only <br>the help of her old mother Anastazia. A chance encounter <br>with Gerard, who is ignorant of her past, rekindled <br>Elizaveta’s ambition for a life of comfort and decadence as <br>the future wife of a nobleman. Elizaveta, determined not to <br>miss such an opportunity, sent her daughter Iskra alone to <br>visit her grandmother. Elizaveta knew that she was exposing <br>her to the dangers of the dense forest of Białowieża, a place <br>full of beasts and bandits, and deadly to the unwary. Ten-<br>year-old Iskra trusted her mother and disappeared forever <br>into the darkness of the forest. Anastazia had always treated <br>Iskra with love and kindness and, overwhelmed by the <br>grief of her granddaughter’s sad end, died soon after. Free <br>and unattached, Elizaveta fled to Gévaudan with her new <br>husband, unaware of her daughter’s real fate. In fact, Iskra <br>did not die, but joined Greskar’s wolf pack, becoming a wolf <br>herself...<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>Iskra didn’t die in the forest of Białowieża. Instead, she <br>faced every trial with fierce tenacity and eventually <br>prevailed, defeating Greskar. A huge, ferocious werewolf, <br>Greskar infected Iskra with the wolf ’s curse. Becoming a <br>member of the pack and the favorite of the alpha Greskar, <br>Iskra set off for the Gévaudan, following the scent of her <br>mother, determined to get her revenge. Thanks to the fury <br>of the wolf pack, Iskra has thrown the village of Durfort <br>into disarray. Now, she waits in the shadows for the right <br>opportunity to enter the palace and devour her unworthy <br>mother. <br>Elizaveta has realized what is happening, for Iskra left  <br>a pendant she had once made for her on the windowsill, <br>a memento of a rare moment of happiness. Elizaveta, a <br>cunning manipulator, got rid of the token and did not panic <br>or lose her temper. After convincing Gerard to turn to the <br>Order, she will seek to move the pieces on the chessboard, <br>using them to rid herself of her unwanted offspring once <br>and for all...</p><p>1<br>120</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513694284,"modifiedTime":1781513694284,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"dLr4VDqVZmcCITp6","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Red-hood / Iskra - Scene 1</h2><p>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  Our story opens as you are <br>being interviewed by a nervous Gerard Dubois, who, anxious <br>to get rid of the monsters infesting his lands, has organized a <br>dinner for his long-anticipated guests. A room has been booked <br>for you at the town’s finest inn, but even though it’s been a long <br>day’s journey, the urgency of the matter at hand demands that <br>no time be wasted. Next to the fireplace, a beautiful woman <br>is pouring wine from a goblet and smiling at you. She is Lady <br>Elizaveta, Gerard’s wife.  <br>Place: The ceremonial hall of the Dubois family’s grand <br>palace. A richly furnished room with an enormous painting of <br>Patrick Dubois, Gerard’s late father. Stern and sullen-looking, <br>Patrick seems to judge his son’s incompetence from beyond <br>the grave with ill-concealed contempt.<br>Time: The sun set more than two hours ago and after a long <br>journey, it is now dinnertime.<br>Initial situation: Gerard is anxious for the Hunters to get to <br>work. Elizaveta studies the situation in silence, trying to figure <br>out how she can turn the Hunters’ arrival to her advantage, <br>using them as tools for her own purposes. Choose one of the <br>villagers to be her dinner guest, or create one of your own. <br>Vincent, her trusted head of the guards, will also be present, <br>of course.<br>Information: The following information/clues can be <br>obtained from the interview with Gerard.<br> ◆ The monsters that scourge the Gévaudan are ferocious <br>beasts, as can be seen from the state of the victims’ bodies.<br> ◆ The first two victims were Guy and Ivette, two young <br>lovers who used to meet secretly in the old cemetery <br>just outside the city. It is there that what remains of their <br>bodies are buried.<br> ◆ It is strictly forbidden to leave the city after sunset. The fall <br>of night now brings with it the mournful song of howling <br>wolves.<br>The Dubois Palace<br>Descriptor: A great palace with more than a hundred rooms, <br>rich and opulent.<br>When the Hunters visit the palace, roll 1 die to determine a <br>special feature.<br>1-2: The palace cellars are filled with excellent wine and fine <br>game meat.<br>3-4: A secret passageway connects the large dining room to <br>the inner courtyard.<br>5-6: Every room in the palace is filled with flattering paintings <br>of Patrick Dubois, Gerard’s father.</p><p>121<br>Gerard Dubois the Incapable Noble<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am the noble baron of Durfort and my <br>word is law. I live in the shadow of my late father’s glory.<br>Agenda: Put an end to the menacing werewolves and <br>cover up any possible mischief.<br>Elizaveta – The cruel bride<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am skillful and charming. I’ll do whatever <br>is needed to get what I want.<br>Agenda: To maintain the comforts and luxuries I have <br>earned. That means ridding myself of my annoying daughter <br>Iskra.<br>Vincent Arn – Former Huntsman and Chief of <br>the Guards<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a skilled hunter. I have no qualms <br>about doing whatever is needed. I want to enjoy a good life <br>without working so hard.<br>Agenda: I understand how the world works and who <br>really runs the Dubois household. Pleasing Elizaveta is the <br>best way to maintain my status.<br>Gift - Veteran:  Vincent is skilled in taking advantage <br>of any situation. When he has the support of at least two <br>of his men, every action against him receives 1 Penalty <br>and Vincent can inflict 1 additional Wound.<br>The Guards of Gerard Dubois<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are duty-bound    -    as long as we get <br>paid.<br>Agenda: Vincent is the boss. We’ll follow his lead.</p><p>122<br>Durfort Village<br>Descriptor: A rich and prosperous place thanks largely to the <br>previous baron, Patrick Dubois.<br>When the Hunters roam Durfort, roll 1 die in each Scene to see <br>who they will meet:<br>1 Anne the Little Chatterer<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: Lady Elizaveta has instructed me to keep her <br>informed about what is being said in town. I do my job as a spy <br>because I don’t want her to stop giving me gifts.<br>2 Nicholas the Huntsman<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I know the ferocity of wolves and I can’t wait to <br>show off in front of Baron Gerard.<br>3 Genevieve the Chemist<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I escaped from a past full of witchcraft and deceit. <br>I know how to summon spirits and talk with them.<br>4 Marcel the Time-Waster<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I frequently wander the town and may be found <br>anywhere. Once, I saw a young girl at the Oak Glade, but no <br>one believed my story because I am too young.<br>5 Corinne the Housekeeper<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I know all rumors in the village, partly because <br>I start most of them myself. I’m easily offended and I love <br>receiving gifts.<br>6 Didier the Grumpy Old Man <br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I hate all foreigners and I miss the old baron. He <br>knew how to stand up for himself. Not like that lax Gerard who <br>even married a foreigner!</p><p>123<br>The Great Gévaudan Forest<br>Descriptor: A huge expanse of trees and natural ravines. Home to animals and fairy creatures.<br>The Old Cemetery<br>Descriptor: A small cemetery with rusty gates and stone tombs. A <br>small, abandoned church lends a gloomy aura to the place.<br>When Hunters wander through the cemetery, roll a die:<br>1-2: A small hidden path leads to an abandoned well, where <br>Elizaveta has thrown an old earthenware pendant that Iskra once <br>made for her as a gift.<br>3-4: Armand, an old, rich wine and spice merchant, arrives in a <br>hurry at the cemetery. The wolves are following him. Roll a die: <br>1-3: 8 Black wolves.<br>4-5: 8 Black wolves + Greskar. <br>6: 8 Black wolves + Iskra.<br>5-6: A group of bandits is traveling through Gévaudan, carrying <br>illegal game. Jozef, their leader, is a former lover of Elizaveta and <br>knows the woman’s past. The bandits want to stop in town to rest, <br>but without attracting attention from the authorities.<br>Descriptor: A small green area just over an hour from <br>Durfort. The glade is a place of arcane power in the middle <br>of the great Gévaudan forest.<br>Gift - Fairyland: Any action that has to do with magic <br>receives 1 extra Success within the small glade. This place <br>absorbs energy from living things. For every hour you stay <br>there you must spend 1 Soma or receive 1 fatigue Wound.<br>When the Hunters arrive at the glade, roll a die to see who <br>they will meet:<br>1-3: The glade is empty, but there are traces of wolves and <br>the bones of devoured prey. After ten minutes, 8 Black <br>Wolves arrive and ambush the Hunters.<br>4-5: A pack is at the glade: Greskar + 8 Black Wolves.<br>6: Iskra is at the glade, alone if it is daytime or with the <br>pack (4-5 result, but without Greskar) if it is nighttime.<br>As a modifier: if it is night, add 2 to the roll.<br>The Oaks Glade</p><p>IskraIskra<br>124<br>The Wolves’ Lair<br>Descriptor: A large, natural cave full of tunnels and <br>small chambers, less than three hours from Durfort. <br>During the day the den is full of resting wolves, but at <br>night it is almost always empty.<br>Gift - Defense Lair:  Moving into the lair without <br>masking your scent will cause the beasts to quickly <br>become alert. At the start of each Scene spent in this <br>place, you must pass a Medium OL Defense roll. If you <br>fail, 1d6 (2d6 if it is daytime) black wolves arrive.<br>As the Hunters explore the lair, roll a die at each Scene <br>to see what they will encounter, or present the rooms in <br>ascending order:<br>1-2: Iskra’s personal den. It is clear that this space is <br>occupied by a little girl. Drawings on the walls depict <br>a mother and daughter holding hands. They are drawn <br>in blood.<br>3-4: A prisoner that is too badly injured to move. <br>Depending on what has happened thus far, he may be <br>one of the inhabitants of Durfort (see the Village table) <br>or one of the encounters at the Old Cemetery that hasn’t <br>already been triggered.<br>5: A large cave full of bones and human corpses.<br>6: A long underground tunnel leading from the Den to <br>the old well in Dufort’s main square.<br>Anastazia the <br>Sorrowful Spirit<br>OL Hard 7 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a restless spirit, bound to the memory of <br>my granddaughter. My condition as a spirit does not allow <br>me to communicate with the living except through dreams, <br>whispers, and visions.<br>Agenda: Preventing further harm to Iskra and find a way to <br>save my granddaughter’s soul.<br>Gift - Spirit: Anastazia is a spirit and can only be damaged <br>by magic. She may appear in a dream to a target, who may <br>resist with a Defense Check or accept contact voluntarily. <br>The target suffers 1 Wound from stress but will receive from <br>Anastazia a vision of a present or past event with a barely <br>whispered phrase.<br>Gift - Loving Grandmother:  Anastazia always follows <br>Iskra and protects her from danger. Thanks to her strong <br>will, she can interact with the material world by moving <br>objects and manipulating the environment, even inflicting <br>a Wound on a target. If a subject is likely to help save her <br>granddaughter, Anastazia will simply fill their mind with <br>memories of her.</p><p>IskraIskra<br>125<br>Greskar the <br>Big Black <br>Wolf<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC  <br>(4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a huge, mighty <br>werewolf. I have to constantly prove my <br>strength to stay the alpha of the pack.<br>Agenda: Protect Iskra and devour as <br>many humans as possible.<br>Gift - Big Wolf: Greskar is an enormous <br>black wolf, as big as a horse. When he <br>grabs someone with his jaws, in addition <br>to inflicting a Wound, he can drag or <br>hurl them away as if they were a rag doll. <br>Once per Scene, Geskar’s bite can inflict <br>1 additional Wound.<br>Gift - The Wolf’s Smell:  Greskar’s <br>sense of smell is infallible. The big wolf <br>will always be able to identify someone if <br>he knows their scent, ignoring all kinds <br>of disguises and even magic.<br>Red-Hood Iskra<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I possess the strength and agility of a wolf. I <br>hide my face with a rudimentary wooden mask that I made <br>with my own hands. I wear a threadbare red cape, the <br>last gift from my mother.<br>Agenda: To unleash her animalistic fury <br>on Elizaveta and anyone who defends <br>her. Taking revenge on my mother has <br>become an obsession for me.<br>Gift - Wolf’s Blood:  Iskra is <br>moved by an animalistic fury <br>that allows her to act twice in <br>the course of an Exchange.<br>Gift - The Senses of a <br>Wolf: Iskra’s sense of smell <br>has become infallible. The <br>little girl will always be able to <br>identify someone if she knows <br>their scent, ignoring all kinds <br>of disguises and even magic.</p><p>126<br>Black Wolves of <br>Greskar’s Pack<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are fierce black wolves, we hate <br>humans and obey only our pack leader.<br>Agenda: Follow without hesitation every order <br>from the pack’s alpha.<br>Gift - The Power of the Pack:  Any action <br>taken while being engaged by two or more Wolves <br>receives 1 Penalty.<br>Story Events<br>In this Scenario, there are six main Events. As Storyteller, feel <br>free to create new ones in response to the actions of the Hunters.<br>If the raids of the wolves are not stopped in one day:  <br>many of Gerard’s soldiers will be eliminated, victims of a much <br>more intense attack than those that have occurred so far, taking <br>place at the gates of the palace. After the furious assault, the <br>city’s defenses will be reduced to a minimum and it will be very <br>easy for Iskra to break into the Dubois palace under the cover of <br>darkness.<br>If a Hunter finds Iskra’s pendant in the well:  Anastazia <br>will contact them, showing them a vision of Iskra as a child <br>drinking at the Oaks Glade. The spirit of Iskra’s grandmother, <br>while unable to communicate directly, will try to make the <br>Hunters understand that Iskra is not a monster.<br>If Elizaveta goes out of town for any reason:  Iskra will <br>immediately smell her scent and rush to eliminate her regardless <br>of any risk. Confronted with her mother, the little girl will lose all <br>restraint and refuse to listen to reason.<br>If Iskra is captured: the wolf pack led by a furious Greskar <br>will launch a tremendous attack on Durfort. Elizaveta will try to <br>eliminate her daughter with a powerful poison.<br>If Iskra is killed: Anastazia’s spirit will turn on her murderer, <br>sending visions of Elizaveta trying to wash the blood of a dead <br>child from her hands.<br>If someone accuses Elizaveta: Gerard will deny everything <br>out of fear and shame, invoking concrete and irrefutable <br>evidence. Elizaveta, for her part, will play the role of the victim, <br>always trying to highlight the danger posed by the wolves.</p><p>1<br>2<br>127<br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the <br>Red-Hood Iskra Scenario and can be acquired once the <br>conditions are met. A Hunter can only acquire one Scenario <br>Gift. If they buy a new one during an Interlude, they will <br>have to forgo the previous one.<br>Voice of the Spirits<br>Requirement:    You have come into contact with the Gift  <br>Spirit.<br>By calming your mind and concentrating, you can open <br>your mind to the spiritual world and communicate with <br>restless souls. Spend 1 Soma to contact a creature with the <br>Spirit Gift you’ve previously encountered. Y ou do not suffer <br>the Wound caused by the stress of spiritual connection.<br>Wolf-killer<br>Requirement: Having faced the wolves in a fight at least <br>once.<br>Y ou know how to deal with the fiercest of wolves and are <br>careful not to be surrounded. When you obtain at least a <br>Standard Outcome on a Position or Defense Check against <br>a pack of beasts, you can immediately eliminate 1 Minor <br>animal NPC with 1 Wound.<br>Where are you going all alone, <br>sweetie? (Special Gift for Garou the <br>Old Wolf)<br>Requirement: To meet Iskra alone in the forest.<br>Y ou are attracted to the little girl who pretends to be a wolf <br>and you dream of devouring her. Once per Scene, you can <br>spend 1 Soma to know exactly where she is. If you anticipate <br>her and arrive somewhere before her, you get 1 Additional <br>Success on every Check you make to hurt or devour that <br>little morsel. Y ou can’t wait to swallow that tidbit and it <br>makes you let your guard down. As long as she is present <br>in the Scene, you receive 1 Penalty in all Defense Checks.<br>The Scenario Red-Hood <br>Iskra in Scenes</p><p>FIRST SCENE – Dinner with <br>Gerard Dubois<br>It’s the same one you find on page 120.<br>End of Scene: Gerard asks the Hunters to look for traces <br>of the Wolves by sending them to the Old Cemetery, <br>where the first massacre took place. Continue to SECOND <br>SCENE - The old cemetery.</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513694284,"modifiedTime":1781513694284,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Jze3mkQvcRXLrYW1","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Red-hood / Iskra - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE – The old <br>cemetery<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: The old cemetery of Durfort <br>lies just over ten minutes’ walk from the town. With the <br>constant threat of wolves, it is now totally abandoned. Beyond <br>the old rusty gate, you can see many weathered gravestones, <br>a small church, and an old well whose wooden planks have <br>recently been dismantled.<br>Place: The old cemetery of Durfort in the middle of the <br>large Gévaudan forest. It is reached by a narrow, dirt path</p><p>3a<br>3b<br>128<br>that winds its way through the woods from the main road.<br>Time: It is early morning, the sun is high on a clear winter <br>sky.<br>Information: In the cemetery, there are many wolf <br>tracks. In the middle of them are the prints of two small <br>bare feet, almost certainly a little girl. At the bottom of <br>the old well can be found the pendant that Elizaveta tried <br>to make disappear. The wolves’ tracks lead deep into the <br>forest, to their den. Anastazia will contact the Hunter who <br>recovered the pendant, sending them a vision of Elizaveta <br>trying in vain to wash her bloodstained hands.<br>End of Scene:  Hunters can decide whether to return <br>to the town to report (THIRD SCENE OPTION A - <br>Reporting) or follow the trail to the wolves’ den (THIRD <br>SCENE OPTION B - On the Wolves’ Trail).</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513694284,"modifiedTime":1781513694284,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"yEIB38qV4Ji5M8kR","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Red-hood / Iskra - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION A – <br>Reporting<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: Now that you see Durfort in <br>broad daylight you realize how large the village is and how it <br>is slowly expanding, so much so that it could almost be called <br>a city. Trade flourished in Dufort under the old baron’s rule, <br>but now all that is threatened by the savage beasts lurking in <br>the nearby forest. <br>Place: Along the streets of the village, men and women go <br>about their daily business. Their somber glances betray the <br>fear that runs through the population.<br>Time: It is late morning, just over an hour until noon, and <br>the whole village will stop to have a frugal lunch.<br>Information: Along the streets of the village, two of the <br>inhabitants (see Durfort Village table) will approach the <br>Hunters to interact. At the palace, Vincent will greet the <br>characters by asking them how it went at the cemetery, <br>gathering information for a report to Elizaveta. Gerard, <br>once he hears the Hunters’ report, will hesitantly ask about <br>their next move. Elizaveta will try to learn what the Hunters <br>have discovered, showing excessive interest if the pendant <br>is shown.<br>End of Scene:  Hunters can either look for the wolves’ <br>lair (THIRD SCENE OPTION B - On the Wolves’ Trail) <br>or ambush Iskra while remaining in the city (FOURTH <br>SCENE - Surprise Attack).</p><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION B – <br>On the Wolves’ Trail<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  Following the tracks <br>in the forest is not easy and several times you risk getting <br>lost. Eventually, the tracks lead to a large natural cave that <br>disappears into the darkness underground.<br>Place: The lair of the Black Wolves. Traces of the pack are <br>clearly visible outside.<br>Time: Crossing the forest takes more than half a day.<br>Information: Depending on whether it is day or night, <br>consult The Wolves’ Lair to see who the Hunters will meet. <br>In the lair, it will be possible to discover traces of Iskra and <br>information about her. If freed, the village prisoner will tell <br>the Hunters, in great detail, of a little girl, masked and in <br>a threadbare red cloak, that is the leader of the wolf pack.<br>End of Scene:  While the Hunters are in the lair, Iskra, <br>Greskar, and the remaining wolves of the pack launch an</p><p>4 5<br>129<br>attack on Durfort, decimating Vincent’s men. The Hunters <br>may arrive in the middle of the battle or when the fight <br>is almost over. Continue to FOURTH SCENE - Surprise <br>Attack.</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513694284,"modifiedTime":1781513694284,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"LsqA8QzGav8H3UHP","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Red-hood / Iskra - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE – Surprise <br>Attack<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: The cries of the townspeople <br>mingle with the howls of the wolves, while large feral figures <br>dart through the alleyways in the moonlight. Using a secret <br>passageway, the pack launched a furious attack on the <br>Dubois mansion. <br>Place: The village of Durfort, doors barred and terrified <br>villagers fleeing through the streets.<br>Time: It is night, but a full moon high in the sky illuminates <br>the village with a gloomy white light.<br>Information: There’s no mercy in the wolves’ fury and <br>many villagers will be devoured alive if the Hunters don’t <br>save them. At the head of his men, Vincent tries to repel <br>Greskar and his wolves, but he will not fight to the death. <br>Iskra, meanwhile, has snuck into the palace in search of her <br>mother.<br>End of Scene: However the battle goes, the Hunters arrive <br>at the palace to find a terrified Gerard fleeing the scene. <br>The nobleman tells them that a small, furious creature <br>has broken into the palace and is now hunting down his <br>beloved bride. It’s time for a showdown. Go to FIFTH <br>SCENE - Which Side Are You On?</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513694284,"modifiedTime":1781513694284,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"TsD8QHMvQ1X635SL","name":"Scene 5","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Red-hood / Iskra - Scene 5</h2><p>FIFTH SCENE – Which Side <br>Are You On?<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  The Dubois palace is a <br>veritable slaughterhouse. It seems that a whole pack of wolves <br>has run rampant, destroying as they went. When you hear <br>Elizaveta’s cry, you rush into the great hall where you had <br>dinner when you first arrived. In front of you, a terrified <br>Elizaveta is confronting a little girl covered in mud and <br>blood. The little girl bares her teeth like a wolf, but she has the <br>crystal blue eyes of her mother.<br>Place: The ceremonial hall of the Dubois family’s grand <br>palace.<br>Time: Time for a showdown.<br>End of Scene:  Elizaveta will ask the Hunters for help. <br>Iskra, on the other hand, after a moment of surprise at the <br>newcomers, is ready to die in order to have her revenge. If <br>he is still alive, Greskar’s howling will hint that the big wolf <br>will arrive any moment. If someone has made a connection <br>with her, Anastazia will intervene with a vision to help the <br>Hunters realize who in the room is truly the monster.</p>"},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513694284,"modifiedTime":1781513694284,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"red-hood-iskra","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","pages":"119-130"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513694284,"modifiedTime":1781513694284,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"qi5c9LFPIcV1TSLD","name":"Of Flesh and Wood","pages":[{"_id":"zUCJuqMjK0EmMqkq","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>Of Flesh and Wood</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> Core Book</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, pages 131-144.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/of-flesh-and-wood-p131-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513695563,"modifiedTime":1781513695563,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"4qBUzxttmhc3u69e","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Of Flesh and Wood - Setup</h2><p>130<br>Once upon a <br>time…<br>The Hunters arrive in Sinalunga, a small <br>town in the Grand Duchy of Tuscany where <br>a gruesome discovery has been made. Not <br>far from the town, the mutilated corpses of <br>ten people were found in an old well,  solving <br>almost all of the many disappearances in <br>recent months that have made the area <br>the epicenter of macabre rumors and tales. <br>Of Flesh <br>and Wood<br>A Scenario inspired by <br>Pinocchio (Carlo Collodi)<br>Safety Keywords:  <br>Blood sacrifices / Mutilation / Body Horror<br>The Papacy, determined to clarify what <br>happened, fears that there is an ancient <br>esoteric practice behind the killings, one <br>that involves the sacrifice of innocent <br>souls. Once before Sinalunga had been <br>the setting of a terrible story: the noble <br>Azzurra De Baciocchi was accused of <br>witchcraft for sacrificing young women <br>in search of eternal youth, and burned at <br>the stake in 1513. The task of the Hunters <br>will therefore be to understand what lies <br>behind the many disappearances now <br>afflicting Sinalunga.</p><p>131<br>The story that led us here…<br>Two old alchemists, Antonio and Geppetto, have <br>worked on a magic oak tree, hoping to obtain the fantastic <br>ingredients required to uncover the secret of eternal life. <br>They were led to the supernatural discovery by an ancient <br>text in their possession, which revealed the alchemical <br>formula for unending life, the key component being a body <br>made of enchanted wood. <br>The mystical material would bestow immortality, but to live <br>among men without frightening them it must be covered in <br>flesh. In the course of their experiments, the two alchemists <br>were astonished to discover that the magical oak had a life <br>of its own. Animated by the power of fairy magic, whose <br>only purpose is to bedevil humans, this piece of wood <br>could bring lies to life.<br> <br>To prove it, the enchanted oak turned into a living, wooden <br>puppet named Carlo, who by his nature could not help but <br>deceive Geppetto and Antonio about the veracity of their <br>theories. Carlo, unable to speak even a single word of truth <br>to the two alchemists, convinced them that the rite they <br>searched for required harnessing a person’s soul inside a <br>wooden body. Antonio and Geppetto then began to kidnap <br>the poor and desperate around Sinalunga, torturing and <br>flaying them alive according to Carlo’s instructions. After a <br>few weeks, horrified by the situation he unwillingly created, <br>Carlo escaped to the city. <br>After the discovery of the well, Antonio and Geppetto fled <br>the old carpenter’s workshop they used as a laboratory and <br>took refuge in Villa Cilesterino, an old abandoned manor <br>house not far from Sinalunga. Here the two alchemists met <br>the spirit of Azzurra, the ancient owner of the villa, who <br>wanders in this world longing for past glories. The gullible <br>pair did not hesitate to tell her the whole story. Azzurra <br>deceived them in turn, animating the mannequins with her <br>powers and convincing Geppetto and Antonio that their <br>research was heading in the right direction. Azzura’s spirit <br>now needs to find Carlo and take advantage of the fairy <br>magic that animates him, using it to bring herself back to <br>life.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>Carlo escaped from the old carpenter’s shop and is now in <br>Sinalunga. Every morning, thanks to the power of his lies, <br>he disguises himself as a real child. Carlo has even begun <br>attending school, where he met Lucino, a loyal and studious <br>child who took a liking to the living puppet. At Villa <br>Cilesterino, Antonio continues his experiments, animating <br>more and more mannequins that he wraps in human flesh <br>to make them look like ordinary people. Azzurra’s magic <br>completes the “miracle” by combining flesh and wood, <br>thereby creating servants to do her will. Geppetto, tricked <br>by Azzurra, has instead returned to Sinalunga, where for <br>days he has been desperately trying to track down Carlo <br>and take him back to his mistress.</p><p>1<br>132</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513695563,"modifiedTime":1781513695563,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"dtgz2l0Tg6tKqbPJ","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Of Flesh and Wood - Scene 1</h2><p>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You have recently arrived <br>in Sinalunga. The small town is bustling with activity and <br>no one seems to have noticed your presence. However, in <br>the eyes of the city’s inhabitants you clearly see a darkness, <br>reflecting the horror that has recently been discovered... <br>You notice a man in military uniform, intent on talking to <br>a couple of peasants who are dragging a large pig with an <br>injured leg. The two townspeople look puzzled at the officer, <br>and from their disinterested expressions, you understand that <br>they can’t wait to get back on the road and leave the insistent <br>investigator behind. The Order is in close contact with the <br>Grand Duchy of Tuscany, so the officer should be aware that <br>a group of Hunters is arriving in town. Could he be an ally in <br>your investigation?<br>Place: The road that crosses the whole town of Sinalunga. <br>The townspeople are hard at work, trying to finish all their <br>chores before dinner.<br>Time: It is less than an hour before sunset and the low, <br>intensely red sun illuminates the surrounding hills, full of <br>vineyards.<br>Initial situation:  The Hunters have arrived in the <br>town of Sinalunga. They already have various pieces of <br>information regarding the incident and they know where <br>the old well, and makeshift morgue, is located. In front of <br>them, Vincenzo Carabiniere, the military officer, is also at <br>work to unravel the murder mystery.<br>Information: What the Hunters already know.<br> ◆ The well is a ten-minute walk from the town and was <br>part of an old manor estate called Villa Cilesterino.<br> ◆ The bodies found had their skin flayed off. It seems that <br>the killer wanted only the skin and muscles of their <br>victims, but not the organs and entrails.<br>Speaking with Vincenzo, the Hunters will discover that the <br>two farmers he was questioning are Lapo and Cino, the <br>ones who found the well. The two were reluctant to talk <br>because at the time of their discovery they were hiding at <br>the well to eat some bread they had stolen from the bakery. <br>The two know very little and Vincenzo will make it clear <br>that they are not the sharpest knives in the drawer.<br>Vincenzo Carabiniere<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a loyal soldier and I always try to do my <br>best to help others. Given my integrity, my superiors keep me <br>away from battlefields.<br>Agenda: Find out what lies behind the disappearances in <br>Sinalunga.<br>Sinalunga<br>Descriptor: A small town in the Tuscan hills. Thanks to its <br>famously delicious wine, many in the town manage to have a <br>good standard of living.<br>By wandering around town and talking to the inhabitants, <br>the Hunters can get some information. The fear that <br>an intervention by the Grand Duchy could upset life in <br>Sinalunga means the inhabitants are reluctant to speak to <br>anyone other than the authorities. Only Lapo and Cino, <br>who are not particularly bright, won’t hesitate to talk with <br>the Hunters, though only with the promise of a reward.</p><p>133<br>Threat - Distrustful Inhabitants<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: We don’t want to attract too much attention <br>to Sinalunga, so we’re reluctant to talk to foreigners. Nobody <br>here wants to lose what they have gained through years of <br>hard work.<br>Information from the townspeople: <br>Roll a die or pick from the list.<br> ◆ 1-2: 10 people have been found, but 11 went missing. <br>Nino’s body is still missing. He is Mastro Antonio’s <br>apprentice carpenter. Antonio is known as Mastro <br>“Cherry” Ciliegia because of his squat and red nose. <br> ◆ 3-4: Villa Cilesterino is haunted by the ghost of the <br>old owner, Azzurra. She was burned at the stake for <br>witchcraft.<br> ◆ 5-6: The high standard of living in Sinalunga led to the <br>opening of Villa Balocchi, a tavern on the edge of town <br>where one can find company as well as a comfortable <br>bed. The tavern is managed by Amabile Burromo and <br>is in open competition with the historic town inn, the <br>Gambero Rosso (meaning “the Red Prawn”).<br>The Old Well<br>Descriptor: An old abandoned well in the middle of a <br>dilapidated vineyard. A nauseating smell from the bottom of <br>the well reminds anyone who approaches of the horror that <br>it hides.<br>Information: <br> ◆ The bodies have already been removed and burned to <br>avoid infection and disease. <br> ◆ When going down into the well, however, there are still <br>some remains and traces of blood. <br> ◆ On the bottom, it is possible to find a carpenter’s chisel <br>that Geppetto lost while moving the corpses. <br>The Gambero Rosso Inn<br>Descriptor: A small and cozy tavern, full of bottles of good <br>wine.<br>Information: <br> ◆ Speaking with the innkeeper, a big fat man named <br>Duccio, the Hunters will learn that Villa Balocchi is a <br>place steeped in sin, where men and women gamble <br>and entertain themselves in shady encounters. <br>During the evening, Geppetto is at the Gambero Rosso and <br>will not hesitate to play out his little rehearsed spectacle of <br>the worried father for whoever shows up. Geppetto will <br>describe Carlo as an annoying child with a pair of old, <br>elegant shoes that Geppetto gave him for his first day of <br>school.</p><p>134<br>Geppetto Gullible Alchemist <br>Apprentice<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a poor man who has always been looking <br>for a way to make a living. I learned the basics of alchemy <br>from master Antonio.<br>Agenda: Pretend to be Carlo’s father and find him / Obtain <br>the secret of eternal life, thanks to alchemy.<br>Gift - Improvised Alchemist:  Geppetto can rely on <br>a series of alchemical compounds contained in vials that <br>he hides under a tacky yellow wig. When he throws a vial, <br>roll a die: 1-2 Explosive: The liquid explodes on contact <br>with the air, causing 1 Wound to everyone within thirty <br>feet. Thick black smoke will engulf the whole area; 3-4 <br>Stench: A nauseating odor fills the air giving 1 Penalty to <br>all actions within the area for the rest of the Scene; 5-6 Air <br>Bomb: All subjects in an area of thirty feet are knocked <br>back and fall to the ground. If they hit an obstacle they can <br>suffer 1 Wound. Geppetto is immune to the effects of his <br>alchemical concoctions.<br>The Old Carpenter’s Shop<br>Descriptor: Once the alchemical laboratory of Mastro <br>Antonio, the carpenter’s shop was abandoned after the <br>discovery of the corpses. <br>Information: <br> ◆ The place is a normal carpenter’s shop, abandoned for <br>some time. The only element that catches the Hunters’ <br>attention is a series of chisels on the wall, with one</p><p>135<br>missing from the set. If the Hunters have recovered the <br>chisel in the well they will see that it is the missing tool. <br> ◆ Among other things of interest, the Hunters can find <br>an old leather bag with some books for the local school.<br>At the back of the carpenter’s shop are the remains of a <br>hastily packed alchemical laboratory. On the wall, there <br>are two human-sized wooden mannequins, skillfully <br>made but stained with blood and decomposing skin. These <br>are Marionettes, the first two produced by Antonio and <br>Geppetto’s experiments, later animated by Azzurra’s magic. <br>The Marionettes will spring on the Hunters as soon as they <br>get close.<br>Marionette <br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: We are souls cursed by Azzurra in the wooden <br>bodies of marionettes. We hate all living beings and want to <br>be destroyed to be free again.<br>Agenda: Attacking every human we meet.<br>Gift - Boundless Rage:  Azzurra’s power animates and <br>forces the Marionettes to do evil acts. When a Marionette <br>suffers the last Wound it will immediately spring on the <br>enemy with incredible momentum as Azzurra’s power <br>compels them one last time. The Marionette can take a <br>final action with OL Hard 7. This action must be aimed at <br>harming a living being.<br>The School<br>Descriptor: A small school for the studious children of <br>Sinalunga. Jolly voices and shouts cover the lamentation of <br>a dispirited teacher.<br>Information: <br> ◆ The school is open in the morning and brings together <br>all the town’s children who want to learn something. <br>The situation is clearly out of control and the teacher, <br>a young academic from Florence, does not know what <br>to do. <br> ◆ The school is attended by Carlo who, however, appears <br>as an ordinary child. In fact, he does not correspond <br>to the description that Geppetto may have given. The <br>old shoes on his feet are the only clue that the Hunters <br>may notice.</p><p>136<br>Carlo The Living <br>Puppet<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a puppet animated by fairy magic. The <br>lies I tell become reality for a short time.<br>Agenda: Living a carefree life without responsibility / I don’t <br>want to abandon Sinalunga and my new friend Lucino, but <br>I’m always afraid that Geppetto and Antonio will catch me. <br>Gift - Lies: Carlo can bring the lies he tells to life <br>by creating a Descriptor that allows him to <br>perform incredible feats. All lies must be <br>centered on him. For example: I can walk <br>through walls or I am invisible to the human <br>eye. The effects of the lies’ power are literal. <br>For this reason, Carlo would not be able to <br>go through a closed door and he would be <br>seen by animals. The effect of Lies lasts for 1 <br>Scene or until a new lie is told.<br>Lucino - The Good Friend<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC  <br>(1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a dutiful and studious child <br>who can’t wait to learn a trade to help my family.<br>Agenda: Help Carlo become a responsible <br>child / Work to help adults who behave well <br>and follow the law.<br>Villa Balocchi<br>Descriptor: A beautiful and sumptuous inn, recently <br>refurbished.<br>Information: <br> ◆ Amabile hosts little Carlo, making him sleep in a small <br>back room. <br> ◆ The Puppet pays the greedy innkeeper with stones <br>which he temporarily turns into gold coins with his <br>powers. Throwing the coins into a safe in his room, the <br>innkeeper hasn’t yet noticed the Puppet’s trick. <br> ◆ During the afternoon and evening, Carlo is at Villa <br>Balocchi and can be found playing with Lucino or <br>pretending to study.<br>Amabile Burromo<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC  <br>(1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a skilled business owner <br>and I manage my inn without delegating <br>anything to anyone. I trust myself only.<br>Agenda: To make profitable deals, <br>without worrying about scruples.</p><p>137<br>Villa <br>Cilesterino<br>Descriptor: An old abandoned manor house. Weeds and <br>plants have covered everything, while the large garden is <br>abandoned to the passing of time.<br>Information: <br> ◆ Villa Cilesterino is divided into 3 environments: the <br>Garden, the Villa, and the Secret Laboratory. <br> ◆ Azzurra is connected to the whole place and will always <br>be aware of anyone who ventures onto her property.<br>The Garden<br>Descriptor: A large abandoned garden where flowers and <br>plants of all kinds grow. <br>Information: <br> ◆ The Garden is guarded by 4 Marionettes and by <br>old Medoro, a sick bear that Azzurra enslaved with <br>her powers. Wandering around the Garden will <br>immediately alert the guardians.<br>Medoro The Old Bear<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a deformed old bear that has lost all its <br>fur. Azzurra treats me like her faithful dog and I am happy to <br>serve her. I have retained most of my bestial strength, despite <br>my age.<br>The Villa<br>Descriptor: A large manor house, once flamboyant, but <br>now covered in dust and mold. <br>Information: <br> ◆ Azzurra is wandering around the Villa and will not <br>hesitate to appear and confront intruders.<br> ◆ In the dining room, there is a huge painting on the <br>north wall depicting a whale swallowing an entire <br>ship. By looking behind the painting, the Hunters can <br>activate the mechanism which opens the secret door to <br>access the Secret Laboratory.<br> ◆ The remaining 4 Marionettes covered in human skin <br>roam around the Villa, but they only act on Azzurra’s <br>orders.</p><p>138<br>Azzurra The Spirit of the Witch who <br>Spurns Death<br>OL Hard 7 - Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am the spirit of an old and powerful witch. My powers allow <br>me to summon the souls of the dead and bind them to my will. <br>Agenda: To come back to life thanks to Carlo’s power.<br>Gift - Ancient Spirit:  Azzurra’s body is immaterial and can only be <br>damaged by magic. Azzurra can interact with the world by evoking the souls <br>of the dead, choosing between various effects. 1. Poltergeist: Throw up to <br>3 objects at once. The force with which the objects are thrown is such that <br>they can cause a Wound. 2. Cacophony of the Dead: Frighten everyone <br>with the agonized voices of the damned. Anyone who hears the cacophony <br>must pass a Defense Check or lose 2 Soma points. 3. Possession: Take <br>possession of a target’s body and cause them to perform a single action, <br>albeit not a self-destructive one. Azzurra must change the spirits’ effect with <br>each action and must use all three before she can use an effect again.<br>The Secret Laboratory<br>Descriptor: The cellar of Villa Cilesterino, converted into an alchemical <br>laboratory by Antonio. The smell of wine and mold is unbearable.<br>Information: <br> ◆ Antonio continues his research under Azzurra’s guidance. This led him <br>to create a magical brazier in which Carlo is to be burned.<br> ◆ Nino, the carpenter’s apprentice, is tied to a table, alive but with his legs <br>now ruined by Antonio’s slow flaying. Azzurra wants him kept alive, as <br>she needs innocent blood for the rite.</p><p>139<br>Antonio Ciliegia <br>Gullible Alchemist<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am an old alchemist who has never discovered <br>anything concrete. Despite my skills and my experience, luck <br>is never on my side.<br>Agenda: Obtaining the secret of eternal life thanks to <br>alchemy. <br>Gift - Unlucky Alchemist: Antonio can rely on a series <br>of alchemical compounds contained in vials that he hides <br>in his tunic. When using a vial he rolls 1 die. On a 5 or <br>6 something goes wrong and Antonio suffers 1 Wound <br>due to his proverbial bad luck. 1. Fire: The target and the <br>surrounding area catch fire. All targets involved suffer 1 <br>Wound. If the fire is not extinguished, burning targets <br>suffer 1 Wound per action. 2. Thunder:  The target <br>is knocked over thirty feet away and ends up on the <br>ground. If they hit something they will suffer 1 <br>Wound. 3. Glue: an adhesive compound that <br>quickly solidifies in the air. The target will be <br>paralyzed until the compound is removed. <br>The Glue can take 2 Wounds.</p><p>140<br>Events of the Scenario<br>In this Scenario, there are six Events. As a Storyteller, feel <br>free to create new ones in response to the actions of the <br>Hunters.<br>If the Hunters put pressure on Carlo:  Lucino will <br>intervene to help his friend by giving him time to escape.<br>If the Hunters reveal their identity to Vincenzo:   <br>the officer will be at their disposal, trying to help them <br>whenever possible. <br>If the Hunters meet Geppetto: the man will attempt to <br>play on their sympathies with the made-up story of the lost <br>son. Geppetto is not a genius, but neither is he stupid. If <br>he understands who the Hunters really are, he will try to <br>follow them to see if they find Carlo.<br>If the Hunters gain Carlo’s trust:  the Puppet will <br>reveal the truth. Geppetto and Antonio are to blame for <br>everything. The Puppet ignores that it is now Azzurra who <br>runs things.<br>If Geppetto is captured by the Hunters:  he will lead <br>them to Villa Cilesterino, where his companion is. Geppetto <br>will pretend to know nothing, aware that once they arrive, <br>Azzurra will get rid of the Hunters.<br>When Azzurra meets the Hunters:  she will try to <br>deceive them by pretending to be a good spirit who tries <br>to watch over the inhabitants of Sinalunga. Azzurra will <br>ask the Hunters to help her recover a magical Puppet, <br>animated by a dark force that is devouring the souls of the <br>poor townsfolk.<br>Exclusive Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the Flesh and <br>Wood Scenario and can be acquired once the conditions <br>are met. A Hunter can only acquire one Scenario Gift. If <br>they buy a new one during an Interlude, they will have to <br>forgo the previous one.<br>Marionettes’ Destroyer<br>Requirement: Defeat any Marionette or understand that <br>they are souls imprisoned against their will.<br>Y ou know how to calm restless spirits by giving them <br>a proper greeting when their soul is freed. Y ou are not <br>affected by the Boundless Rage Gift. Receive 1 Additional <br>Success when defending against beings that are animated <br>or controlled by spirits or magic.<br>A True Friend <br>Requirement: Gain Carlo’s trust despite all his lies.<br>Carlo understands that he can trust you and will run to <br>your aid if you need it. Y ou can spend 1 Soma to have Carlo <br>appear in the Scene as your NPC ally. Carlo will use the <br>power of his lies to help you to the best of his ability.<br>The Field of Miracles (Special Gift for The Fox <br>and the Cat)<br>Requirement: Arrive in Sinalunga.<br>Y ou know Sinalunga well because it is where one of your <br>secret shelters is located. Once per Scene you can spend 1 <br>Soma so you or another subject can leave the Scene and <br>hide in the Field of Miracles. No one can find the exact <br>location of the shelter. When you are at the Field, once per <br>Session you can recover 1 Wound you have suffered.</p><p>2<br>1<br>3a<br>141<br>The Scenario of <br>Flesh and Wood in <br>Scenes</p><p>FIRST SCENE - Arrival In <br>Sinalunga <br>It’s the same one you find on page 132.<br>Information: <br> ◆ Speaking with Vincenzo or the citizens, the Hunters <br>will discover that Villa Cilesterino is a place considered <br>cursed. <br> ◆ They’ll also discover that the well where the corpses <br>were found is located on the edge of the same estate as <br>the villa.<br>End of Scene:  The Hunters leave in the direction of the <br>old well to better understand what happened. If they want, <br>Vincenzo will accompany them. Go to SECOND SCENE - <br>The Old Well.</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513695564,"modifiedTime":1781513695564,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"DjmRBuqz8JVLrdVC","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Of Flesh and Wood - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE - The Old <br>Well<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You find the old well after a <br>ten-minute walk from the town. On the nearby hill, the old, <br>shabby silhouette of Villa Cilesterino looms over you like a <br>dark shadow. The boards that closed the well are uprooted and <br>are now just laying across the top. The stench of death still <br>lingers in the air, still strong enough that it cannot be ignored.<br>Location: The old well on the edge of the Cilesterino estate. <br>Time: The sun is now setting and it won’t be light for much <br>longer.<br>Information: <br> ◆ By descending into the well, the Hunters will find <br>Geppetto’s chisel. <br> ◆ Around the well there are traces of people which then <br>lead towards the abandoned villa.<br>End of Scene:  The Hunters can decide to investigate the <br>Old Carpenter’s Shop from which the chisel surely comes <br>(THIRD SCENE OPTION A - At The Old Carpenter’s Shop) <br>or follow the tracks to Villa Cilesterino (THIRD SCENE <br>OPTION B - Villa Cilesterino).</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513695564,"modifiedTime":1781513695564,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"1TMPQmEhgH5y4RaS","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Of Flesh and Wood - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION A - <br>At The Old Carpenter’s Shop<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  From the outside, the <br>workshop seems abandoned. A large sign outside sways, blown <br>by the wind. It reads “Mastro Antonio Ciliegia, Carpenter. ” <br>Apparently what they told you in the town is true. It seems <br>that Antonio has left and closed up his business. <br>Place: Mastro Antonio’s carpenter’s shop, a well-kept place <br>that, on the inside, does not seem abandoned at all.<br>Time: It is night now and no inhabitants of Sinalunga <br>wander the streets. The shutters in the windows flutter as <br>prying eyes stare at the Hunters.<br>Information: <br> ◆ Upon entering the Old Carpenter’s Shop, the Hunters <br>will come across the Marionettes on guard. Once the</p><p>43b<br>142<br>clash is resolved, the Hunters will be able to verify that <br>the chisel found in the well is just what is missing from <br>the wall rack. <br> ◆ A school bag full of old books attracts their attention. <br>Among other things, they find an unsent letter <br>requesting enrollment for a boy named Carlo.<br>End of Scene:  Hunters can go to Villa Cilesterino <br>(THIRD SCENE OPTION B - Villa Cilesterino) or wait for <br>the morning to go to FOURTH SCENE - The School.</p><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION B - <br>Villa Cilesterino<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: As soon as you step into the <br>large garden of the abandoned villa you realize that what was <br>once a magnificent garden is now nothing more than a thick <br>mass of scrub and weathered stone statues. Your attention, <br>however, is attracted by a bestial verse, which materializes in <br>the grotesque figure of a bear, but one without fur, the hairless <br>skin pocked by who knows what disease. The creature sniffs <br>the air. After spotting you, it starts charging. <br>Time: It is night and a cloud-veiled moon illuminates the <br>old marble statues in the garden with a gloomy glow.<br>Information: <br> ◆ Medoro lashes out at the Hunters. Azzurra will <br>intervene at the end of the battle to ask the Hunters to <br>spare the unfortunate creature she uses as a guardian. <br>Then, she will show them the Marionettes in the <br>garden, saying that in the town someone is carrying out <br>atrocious experiments on the townsfolk. Azzurra will <br>tell the Hunters that everything started with a small <br>puppet animated by dark magic. Azzurra will ask for <br>the Hunters’ help. They should bring back the puppet <br>who hides among the townspeople pretending to be a <br>real child named Carlo. Once captured and brought <br>before her, Azzurra will use her power to banish the <br>evil spirit that animates him.<br> ◆ Azzurra’s intention is to deceive the Hunters, in the <br>hope that they will bring her little Carlo.<br>End of Scene: Hunters can also go to the Old Carpenter’s <br>Shop in search of clues (THIRD SCENE OPTION A - At <br>The Old Carpenter’s Shop) or wait for the morning to go to</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513695564,"modifiedTime":1781513695564,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"UrzoyiTQvgL2ZsYL","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Of Flesh and Wood - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE - The School if they have already obtained <br>the clues from the carpentry.</p><p>FOURTH SCENE - The School<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  The small school of <br>Sinalunga welcomes no more than thirty students. A young <br>teacher with the typical Florentine accent yells and gestures <br>in a vain attempt to get the unruly young scholars to settle <br>down. But children run everywhere like ferrets, ignoring the <br>disconsolate man’s calls. <br>Information: <br> ◆ Watching the children play, the Hunters will notice <br>that one of them has no school bag or books with him. <br>If asked about it, the teacher will say that the pupil is <br>called Carlo and that he is an orphan who comes to <br>school but has never been officially enrolled. The man <br>is not sure where he lives and what he does outside of <br>school.<br> ◆ If a Hunter knows magic, they will sense that there is <br>something strange about the child.<br> ◆ Carlo, sure of his disguise, plays with his friend Lucino, <br>but as soon as the Hunters corner him he will try to <br>escape using the power of his lies.</p><p>5<br>143<br> ◆ Once captured, Carlo will reveal the whole truth to <br>the Hunters. The Puppet doesn’t know about Azzurra <br>but will speak of Geppetto and Antonio as two <br>unscrupulous killers.<br>End of Scene:  The Hunters have managed to capture <br>Carlo. Whether they decide to believe him or not, it is clear <br>that Villa Cilesterino is hiding a secret. Go to the FIFTH <br>SCENE - Return to the Villa.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513695564,"modifiedTime":1781513695564,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Ohy35M3rhsz2nsdw","name":"Scene 5","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Of Flesh and Wood - Scene 5</h2><p>FIFTH SCENE - Return to the <br>Villa<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  When you arrive at the <br>Villa you perceive a strange tension in the air. The weeds that <br>had swallowed the garden are uprooted as if displaced by a <br>supernatural force that has created a path for you. The door <br>of the mansion is wide open, while from the broken windows, <br>the dim light of the candelabra suggests that some kind of <br>welcome is awaiting you.<br>Location: Villa Cilesterino and the Secret Laboratory in <br>the basement, where Antonio and Geppetto carry out their <br>grim experiments.<br>Time: It is just past noon, but the sky is full of clouds, <br>giving a gloomy atmosphere to the abandoned villa.<br>Information: At this point, the story can go in two <br>distinct directions.<br> ◆ If the Hunters trust Azzurra, the spirit will hand over <br>Carlo to Antonio and Geppetto. The two will take <br>refuge in the basement dragging the weeping puppet <br>with them. At this point, Azzurra will order the <br>Hunters to leave. If not listened to, she will try to get rid <br>of them with the help of the Marionettes and Medoro, <br>if it’s still alive.<br> ◆ If the Hunters believe Carlo, Azzurra will try to kill <br>them in order to capture the puppet but will not <br>hesitate to flee if the situation turns for the worse. <br>Antonio and Geppetto, abandoned by their mistress, <br>will take refuge in the Secret Laboratory, trying to put <br>up a last resistance to the Hunters.<br>End of Scene:  However it goes, the Hunters will have <br>Carlo’s fate in their hands and somehow, they will shed light <br>on the disappearances that took place in Sinalunga.</p>"},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513695564,"modifiedTime":1781513695564,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"of-flesh-and-wood","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","pages":"131-144"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513695564,"modifiedTime":1781513695564,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"cMxFaifd2Ix99QnB","name":"The Smile in the Darkness","pages":[{"_id":"WmmfmQ31UeAnHijy","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>The Smile in the Darkness</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> Core Book</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, pages 145-156.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/smile-in-the-darkness-p145-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513696468,"modifiedTime":1781513696468,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"eUQdVjbhB4qvI3Us","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The Smile in the Darkness - Setup</h2><p>144<br>The Smile in <br>the Darkness<br>Once upon a <br>time…<br>The Hunters are sent to Paris, where someone <br>has been setting fires in the city’s slums for <br>weeks. At first, some assumed the radicals and <br>agitators opposing the monarchy were to blame. <br>However, many of the fires’ victims have been <br>the poor and desperate living beneath the city <br>in the catacombs, suggesting a different cause <br>and drawing the interest of the Order. Father <br>Adrien, a humble servant of the Church in the <br>city, has reported rumors that speak of the eerie <br>laughter of children and glimpses of strange, <br>dark presences. Hidden in the shadows, these <br>entities grab all those who have a soul to lose...<br>A Scenario inspired by The Little Match Girl (Hans Christian Andersen)<br>Safety Keywords: Murder / Revenge / Corpses / Religion / Burning Flesh</p><p>145<br>The story that led us here…<br>Yvonne was a ragged, little orphan who sold <br>candles as a way of surviving on the streets. The girl was <br>scorned by all, even by the poor of the city who had always <br>considered her only to be a burden. Little Yvonne found <br>compassion only in Father Adrien, a young priest who <br>had always offered her a helping hand and a warm shelter <br>from the cold Parisian winter. Unfortunately, one evening <br>Yvonne discovered the laboratory where Adrien distills <br>absinthe. The man, his sin discovered, strangled the girl <br>into unconsciousness. To hide his deed, Adrien set the little <br>girl on fire and threw her remains in the catacombs. What <br>was found the following day was a small, charred body with <br>only one part left intact: the teeth, shining white and locked <br>in a deathly grin. Many poor people in the city who depend <br>on Adrien for a few pennies worth of work witnessed the <br>scene, but they kept quiet so as not to lose the priest’s favor. <br>Thrown into a mass grave without ceremony, Yvonne was <br>reborn the following night as a spirit. Her vengeful ghost <br>now wanders in the darkness of The Catacombs of Paris, <br>where she torments those who were silent at her murder <br>with maddening laughter and vicious whispers. When <br>her quarry sparks a light to discover who is hiding in the <br>darkness, the spirit feeds the flame to set the victim afire. <br>Yvonne is slowly burning alive all those who know her <br>murderer and yet say nothing, one by one, saving Adrien <br>for her grand finale.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>Yvonne is carrying out her revenge with methodical <br>determination, killing one person every night. Only a <br>young man named Olivier has escaped her attention and <br>then she can pour out all her hatred on Adrien. If left  <br>unchecked, Yvonne plans to burn all of Paris, igniting the <br>Cemetery of the Innocents, full of rotting flesh and slime <br>from the corpses crammed inside. With the wisdom of the <br>dead, Yvonne knows she will only be able to satisfy her need <br>for revenge during the passage of a comet called Morituris. <br>With the comet’s passage, the souls of the unquiet dead <br>will fill with mystical energy, which Yvonne will be able to <br>channel into an inferno. The passage of the long-tailed star <br>is scheduled for December 31, coincidentally the day the <br>Hunters arrive in Paris. Adrien understands that something <br>fearsome and dark is pursuing his flock of followers, which <br>is why he wrote to the Order. The priest is sure that it all <br>has to do with Yvonne’s death, as every night he dreams <br>and relives the moment he set the child on fire, before the <br>vision widens to reveal the whole of Paris burning. Olivier, <br>a barely eighteen-year-old boy in Adrien’s service, saw his <br>companion Thierry be burnt alive after Yvonne’s spirit <br>began to seek revenge. The young man confided in Adrien <br>but quickly realized that the priest would do nothing for <br>him. He is now desperately trying to leave the city in a <br>hurry. Olivier doesn’t know that he is the next one on <br>Yvonne’s list…<br>A historical note: The Catacombs of Paris were born as <br>gypsum and clay quarries and only began to be used as a <br>sepulcher starting in 1788. In our story, the government of <br>Paris has already begun to work out future plans for the <br>catacombs and this name has already spread among the <br>citizens of Paris. It is worth noting also that, in reality, the <br>Cemetery of the Innocents was closed in 1780 and emptied <br>in 1786.</p><p>1<br>146</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513696469,"modifiedTime":1781513696469,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"q1ah0R4rYbreKYKz","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The Smile in the Darkness - Scene 1</h2><p>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: Our story begins in the small <br>church of Saint Pierre, where Father Adrien welcomes you <br>tiredly. The young priest has been in the service of the city <br>of Paris for just over a year, but already wrinkles caused by <br>worry and stress are starting to show. Adrien has the swollen <br>eyes of someone who hasn’t slept for days and his fatigue is <br>obvious as he guides you into the small sacristy. “You have <br>finally arrived, Hunters. A hidden presence lurks beneath the <br>whole city and I fear there is no hope of salvation without the <br>intervention of the Order... ”<br>Place: The small church of Saint Pierre, one of the oldest <br>in the city.<br>Time: It is late afternoon and the Hunters have arrived <br>after a long journey.<br>Initial Situation:  Adrien will tell the Hunters that he <br>fears an evil spirit is haunting the catacombs. Many beggars <br>have been found burned alive. And, while in the wealthier <br>parts of the city not a finger is raised for the lowest of society, <br>Adrien has always welcomed and cared for them, and he <br>cannot allow this to go on. From interviewing the young <br>priest, the Hunters will learn the following information:<br> ◆ The denizens of the catacombs insist a spirit wanders <br>beneath the city, where many of the poor and desperate <br>sleep in the absence of a roof over their heads. The <br>presence manifests itself only at night, first with a <br>childish laugh and then by whispering in the shadows.<br> ◆ A certain Lorenzo Scannapecore settled in the city <br>cemetery. Lorenzo is an Italian doctor very famous for <br>his unorthodox practices on corpses and who is said <br>to be able to speak with the dead. Lorenzo was hired <br>by the cemetery manager to investigate strange noises <br>coming from the mass graves.<br> ◆ Adrien will be careful not to mention little Yvonne and <br>the fact that she was the first victim to be found.<br>The Church <br>Descriptor: One of the oldest churches in Paris. An old <br>passage directly connects the cellars where Adrien has his <br>workshop to the catacombs.<br>Information: The church is not well maintained, but <br>welcoming. In the basement, there is a large cellar that <br>Adrien has adapted into his laboratory. The smell of <br>absinthe is clearly recognizable to anyone who has the <br>slightest knowledge of distillation as soon as they set foot <br>in the laboratory. A heavy trap door connects the cellars to <br>the catacombs and from there Adrien passes his loads of <br>absinthe to his henchmen.<br>Father Adrien<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds) <br>Descriptor: I am a young priest who chose to take holy <br>vows to avoid a life of struggle. I am a scholar of alchemy and <br>distillation, but I do not shy away from the pleasures of life. <br>Agenda: Accumulate wealth through absinthe smuggling <br>and then flee across the ocean to rebuild my life in the new <br>world.</p><p>147<br>The Catacombs<br>Descriptor: A series of tunnels and galleries that extends <br>under most of Paris. Over time, they have become a refuge <br>for the poor and homeless.<br>Gift - A Tunnel for Everywhere:  Using the <br>catacombs, it is possible to reach many places in <br>the city through hidden openings or old buildings. <br>A Hunter who has a minimum of familiarity with <br>the place (that is, who has visited at least 1 of the <br>6 places presented below) can make a Position <br>Check against an OL Medium 5 to arrive at a <br>specific place in the city.<br>The catacombs are divided into environ-<br>ments that the Hunters can explore. Y ou <br>can roll a die to see where they arrive or <br>simply decide the place when needed.<br>1 - The Dormitories:  A <br>series of tunnels and galleries that make <br>up an old gypsum and clay quarry. <br>Connected to one of the city’s squares, <br>poor and homeless people take refuge <br>here to have a roof over their heads. By <br>exploring the dormitories it is possible <br>to gather some information:<br> ◆ In the catacombs, there are <br>many scoundrels who engage in <br>smuggling and illicit commerce. It <br>is quite easy, especially at night, to <br>come across one of these groups.<br> ◆ Spirits roam the catacombs, though <br>by the grace of God and with a <br>little luck, they rarely trouble good <br>folks. Recently, several burned bodies have been found <br>in the catacombs and for this reason, those who feel <br>they are being followed by a strange presence prefer to <br>douse torches and other flames.<br>The poor people of Paris<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are the poor and desperate who have <br>no other home but the catacombs.<br>When the Hunters interact with the poor, you can <br>decide or roll a die to learn their history and what <br>information they can give.<br>1. Marie lost all her children and her husband to <br>the war. She had grown fond of little Yvonne and <br>weeps for the end she met.<br>2. Claude is a soldier who lost a leg in the war. <br>He wanted to go into business with the Ravens <br>who live in the east side of the catacombs, but <br>they are all young and arrogant and have <br>turned down his offer.<br>3. Brigitte is a little girl who lost her parents <br>during the most recent plague. She knew <br>Yvonne and occasionally went to sell candles <br>with her. She knows that Adrien had taken <br>Yvonne into his service to do small jobs in the <br>sacristy.<br>4. Jerome is an old man who has almost <br>completely lost his sight. In the past, he was <br>a skilled goldsmith, until his blindness left <br>him without a job. He will say that he heard</p><p>148<br>the Ravens boast about the profits they made thanks <br>to an important customer. Their mysterious employer <br>is someone who will never be suspected and who can <br>therefore provide goods in defiance of any authority.<br>5. Bernadette is a youth who witnessed a murder and <br>is now wanted. She fears that the killer wants to make <br>her disappear and shut her mouth for good. The young <br>woman will tell of having encountered a strange <br>presence in the catacombs. In terror, Bernadette threw <br>her torch to the ground and fled into the darkness.<br>6. Bruno is an arrogant street boy, but he knows the <br>catacombs like the back of his hand. He’ll boast that he <br>can get anywhere, but he wants to get paid for it.<br>2 - Yvonne’s Alcove: A small stone alcove with <br>a bed of straw and rags. An old vase of withered flowers <br>indicates that no one has been using it for some time. If the <br>Hunters ask around, a poor old woman will tell them that <br>a foundling named Yvonne slept there. The girl hasn’t been <br>back for more than a week.<br>3 - The Tunnels: It’s easy to get lost in <br>the maze of intricate tunnels.<br>Threat OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: A dense network of tunnels <br>that all look alike.<br>Getting lost in the Tunnels will force <br>the Hunters to waste several hours <br>before finding the exit.<br>4 - The Ravens’ Hideout:  This part of <br>the catacombs is only frequented by scoundrels who had <br>business with Adrien. A couple of broken bottles of absinthe <br>are scattered among some makeshift beds. To those with a <br>sensitive sense of smell, the scent of alcohol is still strong. <br>An old dagger and a wooden crucifix are the only other <br>noteworthy details.<br>Information: If the Hunters arrive here before sunset, they <br>will find Olivier preparing his escape. When night falls, they <br>will find his charred corpse.<br>Olivier the Raven on the run<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I’m a thug always looking to fill my pockets with <br>coin, no matter how dirty the job.<br>Agenda: Collect the money I have hidden in the catacombs <br>and flee far from Paris before the fire spirit finds me.<br>5 - The Burns: Scattered through various tunnels, <br>large patches of ash indicate where the bodies of the burned-<br>alive victims were found. Under the ashes of Yvonne’s, it is <br>possible to find a small candle, miraculously untouched by <br>the flames. During the day, Yvonne remains near the place <br>where she burned, sadly absorbed in the memory of her <br>death.</p><p>149<br>Yvonne the Spirit who Longs for <br>Revenge<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a restless spirit who can manipulate fire.<br>Agenda: Get revenge on Adrien and all those who ignored <br>my death / Set Paris ablaze with the fires of the dead.<br>Gift - Spirit:  Yvonne is in a spirit form and can only <br>truly be damaged by magic. The touch of a Spirit absorbs <br>life energy and inflicts 1 Wound. Physical protection <br>and barriers cannot help against this Gift. If the Spirit <br>is harmed by non-magical means, she still will suffer a <br>Wound. However, when Yvonne has no Wounds left, she <br>disappears and rematerializes immediately. In doing so, all <br>her Wounds are healed, except those inflicted by magical <br>means. Once per Scene, Yvonne can call 3 Restless Spirits <br>to her who will obey her will.<br>Gift - Soul of Fire:  Yvonne can manipulate fire at will. <br>This Gift only affects a fire that is already lit. Manipulating <br>fire, for Yvonne, is considered an additional action. The fire <br>inflicts 1 Wound and if the Defense Check is an Outcome <br>with a Cost, the target will continue to burn. During the <br>following Exchange, if not put out, the fire will inflict <br>1 additional Wound. Thanks to her power, Yvonne can <br>multiply the width and size of a flame by up to ten times.</p><p>150<br>6 - The Halls of the Spirits: In the most <br>central part of the catacombs there is a great concentration <br>of restless souls, who will not hesitate to target the living.<br>Restless spirits<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are restless souls and yearn for the essence <br>of the living.<br>Agenda: We sense Yvonne’s wrath, driving us to prey on the <br>living.<br>Gift - Spirit: This NPC is in a spirit form and can only be <br>damaged by magic. The touch of a Spirit absorbs life energy <br>and inflicts 1 Wound. Physical protection and barriers <br>cannot help against this Gift. If the Spirit is harmed by <br>non-magical means, it still will suffer a Wound. However, <br>when the Spirit has no Wounds left, it disappears and <br>rematerializes immediately. In doing so, all its Wounds are <br>healed, except those inflicted by magical means. <br>Information: If a Hunter communicates with Spirits <br>through the Gift Voice of the Spirits, they will be able to <br>learn of Yvonne’s presence.<br>The Cemetery<br>Descriptor: The great cemetery of Paris, protected by <br>high walls and well-maintained thanks to the work of many <br>custodians. Strange noises and a strong smell of death come <br>from the mass graves.<br>Information: The cemetery is currently under the control <br>of Lorenzo Scannapecore, an Italian doctor hired by the city <br>of Paris to manage the excessive number of corpses inside <br>the mass graves. Lorenzo has sent the cemetery keepers <br>away with the excuse of requiring quiet for his studies. <br>However, that was only a ruse to secretly host Alizée, a nun <br>he has fallen in love with and whom he keeps safe from the <br>severe judgment of the Church. Lorenzo’s intent is to wait <br>until the new year to embark with his beloved towards the <br>New World.<br> ◆ Speaking with Lorenzo, the Hunters can learn about <br>the dire state of the mass graves of the cemetery, which <br>in fact is about to explode due to the excessive number <br>of decaying corpses. Lorenzo will appear strangely <br>nervous, looking wary. The man fears that the Hunters <br>may discover Alizée hidden among the tombstones.<br> ◆ Lorenzo is also a good astrologer and will be able to tell <br>the Hunters about the passage of Morituris and how, <br>according to the legend, this gives power to the spirits.<br> ◆ Alizée will observe the Hunters from behind some <br>tombstones, trying not to be discovered. However, she <br>will always remain nearby, ready to intervene to help <br>her beloved.<br> ◆ Alizée will try not to reveal her abilities. When cornered, <br>she may report that the spirits are very agitated, both <br>due to the presence of a very powerful and hateful <br>spirit among them, and due to the imminent passage <br>of the comet.<br> ◆ Strange smells and noises come from the mass graves. <br>Lorenzo will say that it is the dead bodies generating</p><p>151<br>gas during decomposition. By opening one of the large <br>hatches, it is possible to access the underground pit.<br> ◆ Lorenzo has all the keys to open the hatches to access the <br>underground pit.<br>Lorenzo Scannapecore the <br>Plague Doctor<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a skilled plague doctor. My attention to <br>detail is obsessive.<br>Agenda: Pretend to work in the cemetery to protect Alizée <br>from prying eyes.<br>Alizée the Fugitive<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a young nun who repudiated her vows out <br>of love. I have always been able to see spirits, though my ability <br>sometimes scares me.<br>Agenda: Escape with Lorenzo to a place where we don’t need <br>to fear the Church’s punishment.<br>Gift - Spiritualist:  Alizée can see and communicate with <br>spirits. If anyone has been in contact with spirits in the past <br>twenty-four hours, Alizée will sense the remaining spirit <br>energy. With each use of this Gift, the young woman can <br>obtain a single piece of information about the spirit aura she <br>has perceived. The Spiritualist Gift can also be used to remove <br>a Grudge Token from the Gift Mass of Restless Spirits.<br>The Underground Pit<br>Descriptor: A huge pit where the corpses of all those who <br>cannot afford a burial are thrown. Crowds of restless spirits <br>throng among the inert bodies, invisible to mundane eyes.<br>Gift - Mass of Restless Spirits:  The pit accumulates <br>spiritual energy thanks to the passage of the comet Morituris. <br>At the beginning of each Scene, there are 2 Grudge Tokens <br>in the pit. An NPC with the Gift Spirit, Alizée with the Gift  <br>Spiritualist, or a Hunter with a Descriptor associated with <br>magic or spirits, can use their action to add or remove 1 <br>Token from the mass. If at midnight on December 31st there <br>are 3 Tokens in the pit, all the accumulated energy will cause <br>a powerful explosion capable of wiping out half of Paris. <br>The passage of the comet will add 1 Token at the stroke of <br>midnight. There can never be more than 4 Grudge Tokens on <br>this Gift.<br>Threat - Grudge of the Dead<br>Descriptor: We are the spirits of those who are dead and <br>forgotten by all. We hate the living and their life energy, and we <br>attack anyone who dares to approach the underground pit.<br>OL Hard 7<br>Gift - Chorus of the Dead: A powerful spirit cacophony that <br>only those who perceive spirits or understand magic can hear. <br>For everyone else, the chorus is nothing more than a terrible, <br>overwhelming feeling that prompts you to walk away. Anyone <br>wishing to act in the area where the choir can be heard will <br>lose 1 Soma for each minute staying under its influence. If <br>they do not have Soma, a subject will suffer a Wound until <br>they faint. A Defense Check can shelter a subject for 1 minute <br>from the effect of this Gift.</p><p>152<br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the Smile <br>in the Darkness Scenario and can be acquired once the <br>requirements are met. A Hunter can only have one Scenario <br>Gift and if they acquire a new one, they will have to forgo <br>the previous one.<br>Voice of the Spirits<br>Requirement: You have been in contact with either the <br>Spirit or Spiritualist Gifts.<br>With the right peace and focus, you can open your mind <br>to the spirit world and communicate with restless souls. <br>Spend 1 Soma to contact any creature with the Spirit Gift  <br>that you’ve previously encountered. Y ou can communicate <br>with the Spirit and understand what it says.<br>Exorcist<br>Requirement: Have a Church or Magic-related Descriptor. <br>Talk to Adrien or Alizée about practices used against Spirits.<br>Y ou have learned how to use your skills against the Spirits. <br>All your actions can affect a target who has the Spirit Gift  <br>and all Wounds you inflict cannot be ignored by the Spirit <br>Gift.<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario, there are eight Events. As a Storyteller, feel <br>free to create new ones in response to the actions of the <br>Hunters.<br>If the Hunters encounter Olivier in the catacombs <br>before night falls:  Yvonne will arrive before the <br>scoundrel opens his mouth to try and silence him by taking <br>her revenge.<br>If the Hunters talk to more than two poor people <br>in the catacombs: Yvonne will notice their presence and <br>will come to spy on them, trying to stay hidden.<br>If Olivier is not found before sunset:  news of a new <br>charred body will spread in the catacombs shortly after 10 <br>pm.<br>If Olivier is saved by the Hunters:   he will tell of a <br>strange presence that has killed his companions. The <br>scoundrel won’t make mention of his connections with <br>Adrien and Yvonne unless put under pressure in some way.<br>If Adrien is confronted with his faults:   he will <br>collapse in tears and ask for forgiveness. At this point, <br>he will reveal the recurring dream in which he sees Paris <br>burning on New Y ear’s Eve.<br>If the Hunters attempt to mediate with Yvonne:  the <br>spirit will be willing to give up blowing up the graveyard, <br>but not her revenge on Adrien.</p><p>1<br>2 3<br>153<br>The Scenario <br>The Smile in the <br>Darkness in Scenes</p><p>FIRST SCENE – Father Adrien<br>It’s the same one you find on page 146.<br>End of Scene: Adrien will suggest to the Hunters to speak <br>to Lorenzo Scannapecore, as he is an expert on the dead <br>and ghosts. The doctor lives in the cemetery in Paris. Go to</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513696469,"modifiedTime":1781513696469,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"YfZesN1J0WbW1t9Y","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The Smile in the Darkness - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE - The Cemetery.</p><p>SECOND SCENE – The <br>Cemetery<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  The Cemetery of the <br>Innocents stretches as far as the eyes can see and is probably <br>one of the largest you have ever seen. As you wander through <br>tombstones and family mausoleums, a black-cloaked figure <br>is busy fumbling among the tombs. The typical beak mask <br>identifies him as a plague doctor. The figure had been <br>occupied exhuming a grave, but now he puts down his shovel <br>and approaches you.<br>Place: The great cemetery of Paris.<br>Time: It is late afternoon and the winter wind whistles <br>through the corridors of the cemetery.<br>Information: Lorenzo will prove helpful to the Hunters, <br>while Alizée will keep watch from behind a noble’s large <br>tomb. Lorenzo will be visibly nervous, however, often <br>looking over his shoulder at her. It’s simple to deduce that <br>someone is hiding nearby.<br> ◆ Having discovered Alizée, the Hunters will know <br>from her that the spirits are restless, due partly to the <br>passage of the comet, but above all from the presence <br>of a particularly angry spirit in the catacombs.<br> ◆ Lorenzo will confirm the passage of the comet <br>Morituris and how it charges the spiritual world with <br>energy.<br> ◆ Towards the end of the interview, Father Adrien will <br>arrive to warn the Hunters that another charred corpse <br>has been found in the catacombs.<br>End of Scene:  The Hunters rush to the <br>catacombs to find out what happened. Go to</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513696469,"modifiedTime":1781513696469,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"gQdlVP6LlruzKBZz","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The Smile in the Darkness - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE - The Catacombs.</p><p>THIRD SCENE – The <br>Catacombs<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You go <br>down in The Catacombs of Paris and what <br>you see is a maze of narrow tunnels that <br>open onto small chambers and dark alcoves. <br>The stale smell mixes with the stench of <br>unwashed, desperate people crowded into <br>the narrow spaces. Apparently, those who <br>do not have a roof over their head can find a <br>shadow of comfort under the city, effectively <br>disappearing from the sight and conscience of <br>“respectable” people.</p><p>4a<br>154<br>Place: The Catacombs of Paris.<br>Time: The sun has set and in the streets, the last workers <br>hurry to return to their homes. <br>Information: The Hunters explore the catacombs until <br>reaching the place where Olivier was found. The body is still <br>there, along with an intense burning smell. The expression <br>of sheer terror is still discernible on his charred features. If <br>the Hunters have Alizée with them, the woman will sense <br>Yvonne’s presence. Either way, the spirit will attack the <br>Hunters with the support of 3 Restless Spirits. Yvonne’s goal <br>is to drive the Hunters out of the catacombs.<br> ◆ Regardless of how the fight ends, the Hunters will be <br>approached by Marie, who witnessed the scene. The <br>woman will reveal that the spirit is little Yvonne, a <br>foundling who lived by selling candles Father Adrien <br>had given her. The little girl has been missing for more <br>than a week and Marie was convinced she had gone to <br>stay with Adrien, given the charming, almost paternal <br>relationship that was forged between the two. It will <br>be clear to the Hunters that Adrien has not told the <br>whole truth, but at the same moment, a roar from the <br>graveyard will cause the earth to shake.  <br>End of Scene:  The Hunters can go find Adrien at the <br>church (FOURTH SCENE OPTION A - Confession ) <br>or head to the cemetery to find the source of the roar <br>(FOURTH SCENE OPTION B - Return to the Cemetery).<br>Note: Given the obvious emergency of both situations, <br>advise the Hunters to split up to deal with both Scenes.</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513696469,"modifiedTime":1781513696469,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"XJVDoKPqNggwB9Tq","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The Smile in the Darkness - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE OPTION <br>A – The Confession<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: You arrive at the church <br>looking for answers when Adrien’s cry breaches the <br>stillness of the night. When you open the door, the priest is <br>kneeling in the center of the aisle, his face covered in tears <br>as he whispers, “Forgive me, please forgive me for what I <br>have done. ” In front of him, the spirit of the little girl you <br>faced in the catacombs floats ominously, while behind her, <br>the flames of the offering candles swell until they become <br>tongues of fire.<br>Place: Father Adrien’s church.<br>Time: It is almost midnight on December 31st and it is <br>possible to observe the passing comet, Morituris, in the <br>sky outside the church.<br>Information: Yvonne intends to kill Adrien. If <br>stopped by the Hunters, she will inform them that in <br>less than an hour the cemetery will explode thanks to <br>the anger of the spirits she has stirred up.<br> ◆ Cornered, Adrien will confess to what he did to <br>Yvonne and to his involvement in the absinthe <br>trade. The priest, however, will try to distract the <br>Hunters with the knowledge that now the little girl <br>is a spirit full of anger and, in fact, a hostile creature <br>of the sort that the Order would hunt down.</p><p>4b<br>5<br>155<br> ◆ Adrien will try to escape through the secret passage <br>in the cellar if he has the opportunity. The man is <br>absolutely not sorry for what he did.<br> ◆ Yvonne will be willing to help the Hunters if they don’t <br>interfere with her revenge and allow her to deal with <br>Adrien.<br>End of Scene: The Hunters must run to the graveyard to <br>avert the explosion. Go to the FIFTH SCENE - The Fire of <br>Revenge.</p><p>FOURTH SCENE OPTION B <br>– Return to the Cemetery<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You hurry back to the <br>cemetery and find Lorenzo passed out on the ground. When <br>he wakes, the doctor tells you that the reinforced trap doors of <br>the mass graves all exploded in unison, and now Alizée feels a <br>spirit force beyond comprehension. If something is not done, <br>the consequences for the city will be catastrophic.<br>Place: The Cemetery of the Innocents.<br>Time: It is almost midnight on December 31st and it is <br>possible to observe the passing comet Morituris in the sky.<br>Information: Hunters will have to approach the pit to <br>quell the Mass of Restless Spirits. After having retrieved <br>at least 1 Token (with Alizée’s help, if they have no other <br>resources), the Hunters will be aware that, until the comet’s <br>passage is complete, the graveyard is a potential bomb. <br>End of Scene:  When the Hunters reduce the Grudge <br>Tokens to zero, go to the FIFTH SCENE - The Fire of <br>Revenge.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513696469,"modifiedTime":1781513696469,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"avS85TySajaLcZfi","name":"Scene 5","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The Smile in the Darkness - Scene 5</h2><p>FIFTH SCENE –  The Fire of <br>Revenge<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  A long and heart-breaking <br>lament rises from the mass graves, deep enough to make your <br>skin crawl. Apparently, the dead have no intention of resting <br>forever.<br>Place: The Cemetery of Paris.<br>Time: The stroke of midnight on December 31st. In the <br>sky, the comet Morituris is as bright as a small sun.<br>Information: This Scene has two possible developments.<br> ◆ If the Hunters haven’t faced the FOURTH SCENE <br>OPTION A - Confession , Yvonne will appear in the <br>center of the mass grave with Adrien. The spirit intends <br>to throw the priest to the spirits and thus activate <br>the explosion of the cemetery. Yvonne will face the <br>Hunters backed by 4 Restless Spirits. If during the fight <br>the Grudge Tokens reach 3, there will be an explosion. <br> ◆ If the Hunters have Yvonne’s support, the pit spirits will <br>rebel against their own mistress. 9 Restless Spirits will <br>appear in the graveyard to face off against the Hunters <br>and Yvonne. During each Exchange, 1 Spirit will use its <br>action to add 1 Grudge Token.<br>End of Scene:  It will be time for the Hunters to judge <br>Adrien (if still alive) and decide what to do with little <br>Yvonne, condemned to eternal unlife.</p>"},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513696469,"modifiedTime":1781513696469,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"smile-in-the-darkness","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","pages":"145-156"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513696469,"modifiedTime":1781513696469,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"VNQFyPiNncmn0TAc","name":"A Soldier's Duty","pages":[{"_id":"txzI5hAaZCSooUKg","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>A Soldier's Duty</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> Core Book</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, pages 157-168.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/a-soldiers-duty-p157-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513697602,"modifiedTime":1781513697602,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"SyD3hZt5B233ru75","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>A Soldier's Duty - Setup</h2><p>156<br>A Soldier’s Duty<br>Once upon a <br>time…<br>The Hunters arrive in Borgholm, on the <br>beautiful island of Oland. The Hunters’ <br>intervention is ordered by the Papacy after <br>a request from the Riksråd, the great council <br>of the kingdom of Sweden. A former soldier <br>and war hero named Nils, also called the <br>Poor Devil, has sent a letter to the council, <br>imploring them to help him and his former <br>comrades. Six valiant soldiers were all that <br>remained of their company after the bloody <br>war between Sweden and Russia. Now, they <br>are being killed one by one by a monster that <br>seems able to take a bullet without batting an <br>eye. Two of the comrades have already fallen <br>to the monster’s fury. Those that still live <br>have barricaded themselves in the mansion <br>of their one-time commander, Andersen, who <br>now leads them in defense of their own lives <br>and those of his family.<br>A Scenario inspired by The Steadfast Tin Soldier <br>(Hans Christian Andersen)<br>Safety Keywords:<br>  <br>Rape / Revenge / Murder</p><p>157<br>The story that led us here…<br>Six years earlier, a company of Carolean soldiers was <br>stationed in Vaasa, a small town on the Finnish coast. Here <br>Private Enar fell in love with Satu, a young and beautiful <br>dancer. Enar deserted to remain near his beloved but was <br>discovered by his comrades. They judged him a sinner <br>according to the strict religious discipline of the Caroleans.<br>Led by Captain Andersen, the soldiers punished Enar by <br>cutting off his leg and throwing him into the sea. But in <br>reality, the true reason for Andersen’s ferocity arose from <br>the fact that the officer too had fallen in love with Satu and, <br>mad with jealousy, had punished Enar far beyond what the <br>rules dictated. After Enar’s execution, unknown even to his <br>own men, the Captain tried to romance Satu, who rejected <br>him. Unable to accept that refusal, Andersen raped her and <br>as a result of that terrible act, the girl became pregnant. <br>Six years later, the company disbanded and Andersen, a <br>wealthy war hero, paid his underlings handsomely to keep <br>the secret of Enar’s death. Having retired to private life, over <br>time, Andersen grew to regret his deplorable behavior. He <br>sought out the dancer and, after regaining contact with her, <br>discovered with great shame the existence of his son, Erik. <br>Ravaged by guilt for what he had done, Andersen managed <br>to earn Satu’s grudging forgiveness after months of effort. <br>He freed her from a life of hardship as an assistant cook and <br>took her with him to his mansion, together with his son. <br>But Enar’s fate did not end beneath the sea waves. Love for <br>Satu soon turned into blind hatred for Andersen and his <br>former comrades. Below the waves, Enar remained alive for <br>a long time while the fish slowly devoured his flesh. Of the <br>soldier’s body, only the heart was spared and, as it fell into <br>the abyss, it attracted the attention of a Sea Fairy. The Fairy <br>took pity on him and, seeing that heart so wounded, infused <br>it with new life. Enar’s body slowly began to regenerate, but <br>the young soldier’s mind was now lost. All the accumulated <br>hatred and resentment had driven him insane. Worse, in <br>the process of his rebirth, the soldier’s body began to absorb <br>everything it found. Algae, shells, and timbers from an old <br>wreck fused to his limbs, making him an immortal monster <br>bound to the world only by an infinite grudge...<br>Six years have passed, and Andersen managed to get closer <br>to Satu, who is now at least accepting him. At the same <br>time, Enar’s heart has started beating again. Now that his <br>greatest enemy, Andersen, has found something he truly <br>loves and would not want to lose, Enar is ready to return to <br>take it away from him.<br>Appearing every day an hour after sunset, Enar began his <br>personal war by killing his fellow soldiers, one by one, in a <br>heinous fashion. Six survived the war, and two have already <br>been murdered, with one gutted and another burned alive <br>after being flayed. Andersen soon understood the nature of <br>the threat and brought Hans and Christian, his remaining <br>former companions, to his mansion. Only Nils was not <br>called, being unable to move due to his war wounds. The <br>Poor Devil has many friends, however, and has gathered <br>information from his home in Sundsvall.</p><p>1<br>158<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>Enar is completely insane and fully intent on killing all his <br>former comrades, only to finally “merge” into one being <br>with his beloved Satu. Nils in his heart sensed that the <br>killer is Enar and, seized by a sense of guilt, he summoned <br>the Order to try and stop his former comrade in arms. <br>Andersen has found happiness with Satu and Erik, and <br>despite the shame he feels for what he has done in the past, <br>he is absolutely determined to destroy the revived Enar to <br>secure a future with his new family.<br>Satu has guessed who the monstrous being that appears <br>every night really is, but fear makes her hide from Enar’s <br>gaze. The woman now wants nothing more than the best <br>for her child, even to the detriment of her own happiness, <br>even if it means accepting a life alongside the one who took <br>away her true love six years earlier.<br>On this sad stage, all the actors have something to hide <br>while Enar represents the truth that, inescapably, will <br>destroy the wall of lies built with care by Andersen and his <br>men.</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513697603,"modifiedTime":1781513697603,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"iUvqxZW8R41HFLCo","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>A Soldier's Duty - Scene 1</h2><p>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: It is late afternoon when you <br>finally see the mansion of Andersen Olsson, the war veteran <br>who, according to the letters they’ve received, is the victim of <br>an attack by a monstrous creature. You notice immediately <br>that the mansion has been fortified. A wrought iron fence <br>and main gate, reinforced and strengthened by barricades, <br>form an improvised wall around the grounds. A smaller gate <br>that allows access to the garden has been bent in a way that <br>suggests some very violent force has acted there, knocking it <br>down and warping its hinges. A rudimentary watchtower <br>has been built in a large oak that rises beyond the makeshift  <br>palisades and, from the top, a figure beckons to you with his <br>hand before descending to the ground and running to meet <br>you. He wears a soldier’s uniform, and with every step, a <br>saber clatters in the scabbard at his side. The man arrives <br>at the gate with a grim and serious expression, asking who <br>goes there.<br>Place: Andersen’s large mansion just outside the town of <br>Borgholm.<br>Time: It is late afternoon and the sun begins its slow <br>descent. The salty air that comes from the sea teases the <br>nostrils.<br>Initial Situation: The soldier who welcomes the Hunters <br>is Christian, who will not allow the Hunters to enter the <br>estate without first understanding who they are. As soon <br>as it becomes clear they belong to the Order, Christian will <br>call Andersen to let him handle the situation.<br>Information: During the Scene, Andersen will make <br>no secret of his disappointment at seeing the Hunters. By <br>talking to him you can learn the following information.<br> ◆ Andersen disapproves of the fact that Nils sent a letter <br>to the Order. The creature attacking his property yearns <br>to take revenge on his men. The identities of the first <br>two victims, his former comrades-in-arms Jacob and <br>Wilhelm, were enough to convince him of that.<br> ◆ Andersen has called the survivors to him to deal with <br>this new threat, which he is sure is connected to the <br>many deaths his company caused during the war. <br>Andersen will make no secret of the fact that he and <br>his men had their souls soaked in so much blood they <br>were stained crimson. The monster is able to travel</p><p>159<br>great distances since the first two victims lived many <br>days’ travel from each other. That’s why Andersen has <br>gathered everyone on his estate to join forces.<br> ◆ Although Andersen despises Nils because he has <br>always been a coward, he has sent Hans to keep him <br>safe, as the Poor Devil has lost his legs in battle and is <br>unable to travel. Nils lives a day’s drive from the estate <br>in the village of Sundsvall and Hans left a few hours <br>before the Hunters arrived.<br> ◆ Andersen is a soldier and if the Hunters insist, he will <br>reluctantly welcome them into his home, respecting <br>the authority of the Order.<br>Note: This Scenario uses Events as timers for story <br>development. For this reason, the Storyteller must keep in <br>mind some factors.<br> ◆ There are only 3 places (the Andersen Estate, the town <br>of Sundsvall, and the cliff) that make up an equilateral <br>“triangle” . Moving from one place to another always <br>takes 1 day of travel on foot. <br> ◆ Some Events have an indicative day number in which <br>they occur: 1st day, 2nd day, and so on. In this way, <br>the Storyteller will always know where Enar will be and <br>who he will try to strike.<br> ◆ Since the action always occurs in two places at the same <br>time, the Storyteller must point out that all the former <br>soldiers are in danger, and that this mission requires <br>action on multiple fronts. For this reason, splitting <br>the Hunters into two groups is encouraged. However, <br>it is not an essential condition and the final decision <br>regarding what to do will always be up to the Players.<br> ◆ For better management of Events, given their <br>importance, they are shown below instead of at the end <br>of the Scenario as usual.<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario, there are eight Events. As Storyteller feel <br>free to create new ones in response to the actions of the <br>Hunters.<br>Day 1:  Enar will attack Andersen’s estate shortly after <br>sunset. If the Hunters are not present, Christian will be <br>killed.<br>Day 1: Hans arrives in Sundsvall to interrogate Nils, who <br>will no longer be willing to keep quiet about Enar’s murder. <br>If the Hunters are not present, the soldier will kill the Poor <br>Devil.<br>Day 2: Enar will arrive after sunset in Sundsvall to punish <br>Nils. If the latter is already dead, then he will find Hans <br>ready to ambush him. If the Hunters are not present, <br>Hans will die. If Nils is alive, however, Enar will attempt to <br>eliminate him unless the Hunters do something to prevent <br>it.<br>Day 2: Erik will recognize the shells that have fallen from <br>Enar’s body as those present on the cliff. If the Hunters <br>are present, Andersen will invite them to investigate. <br>Otherwise he will send Christian, who will be eliminated <br>by the Sea Fairy. <br>Day 3: Enar will arrive at the estate after sunset to eliminate <br>Andersen and possibly Christian. Once this is done, he will <br>try to reach Satu.<br>If Erik is put in danger:  Both Andersen and Satu will <br>put their lives at risk for him. Both are willing to confess if <br>this can save the child from danger.<br>If Enar discovers that Erik is Andersen’s son: The <br>child will become his new target, as killing him is the best <br>way to make Andersen feel the pain he has inflicted.</p><p>160<br>If the Hunters convince the Sea Fairy of their good <br>intentions: The Fairy will lead one of them to the bottom <br>of the sea where Enar’s heart is.<br>Andersen’s Estate<br>Descriptor: A large, lush estate ten minutes from the city <br>center.<br>Wandering around the estate, the Hunters may encounter <br>one or more of these NPCs. Roll a die:<br>1-2 Satu: With a sad and depressed air, the woman will try <br>to avoid any interaction with the Hunters. Her shy demeanor <br>will make it clear that something is bothering her.<br>3-4 Erik: Intrigued by the Hunters, he will approach them <br>brimming with questions. He is a lively child, and it will soon <br>become clear to the Hunters that he is not fully aware of the <br>danger he is in.<br>5-6 Adam the Chatty Servant:  A young man in his 20s <br>who can’t escape to the city, as he works on the estate to <br>pay off a debt to Andersen. Adam will speak without much <br>hesitation about the fact that there is a complex relationship <br>between his master and Satu, and that the woman comes <br>from the past of the former commander. Adam will add that <br>Andersen is also very considerate of Erik and it becomes <br>clear that he regards the boy as a son.<br>Information: Over twenty servants work on the estate, <br>but few are capable of wielding a weapon. The whole defense <br>rests on the shoulders of Andersen and Christian. It will be <br>clear to the Hunters, however, that Andersen’s abilities as a <br>commander allow him to keep everything under control and <br>to bring out the best even from inexperienced servants.<br>After the first encounter with Enar, Erik will recognize the <br>shells he collected when he lived with his mother in a small <br>cliffside village. According to some old stories, under the cliff <br>there is a dense network of caves where a Sea Fairy is said to <br>reside.<br>Andersen<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a war veteran with strong leadership skills. <br>In addition to being a good leader, I am also a capable fighter.<br>Agenda: Defend my new family from the danger that Enar <br>represents / Redeem myself in the eyes of Satu and make her <br>understand that I am now a different man / Prevent anyone <br>from discovering what I have done.<br>Gift - Commander:  Andersen is skilled at giving orders <br>and managing a battle. Up to 3 times per Scene, Andersen <br>can issue an order to an ally who will receive 1 Additional <br>Success (+1 to OL in the case of an NPC) while executing it.</p><p>161<br>Satu<br>OL Easy 3 – Main NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a former dancer who has lost everything. <br>I am but a shadow of my former self.<br>Agenda: Defend my son Erik, the only reason that I keep <br>going.<br>Erik<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a lively child who can never sit still. <br>Agenda: Understand who Andersen really is, and why he <br>took my mom and me out of the misery we lived in.<br>Christian<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a former soldier, called the Relentless <br>by all because of my cold determination. I act without any <br>qualms when it comes to executing an order.<br>Agenda: Help Andersen in memory of the old days and a <br>military life I can’t forget / Eliminate Enar to prove I am the <br>better man.<br>Gift - The Relentless: When he is carrying out an order, <br>Christian is immune to any effect that affects his behavior, <br>such as fear or charm. The soldier increases his Opposition <br>Level by 1 when he tries to eliminate an obstacle that stands <br>between him and the subject of an order he must carry out.<br>Enar<br>OL Hard 7 – Main NPC (4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am an immortal being, the result of all the <br>hatred I harbored in my exile into the abyss. I have the <br>strength of five men and my body feels no pain.<br>Agenda: Take revenge on Andersen, but not before I have <br>eliminated all my former companions / After eliminating <br>Andersen and his people, I want to meld with Satu so that <br>our bodies and souls are united for eternity.<br>Gift - The Eternal Soldier:  Enar’s body is the result of <br>powerful magic tainted by hatred. When Enar suffers his <br>final Wound, his body becomes seawater and soaks into <br>the ground. The following day, Enar completely regenerates <br>himself at the bottom of the sea, where his heart is, the very <br>focus of his existence. Only by recovering the heart and <br>destroying it can Enar be permanently eliminated. <br>Gift - Rage of the Sea:  Thanks to the magic granted by <br>the Sea Fairy, Enar has gained powers. When he acts, he <br>can always choose an additional effect. 1. Algae Whip: A <br>string of algae stretches from Enar’s body and can perform <br>a second independent action. 2. Wave:  Enar’s body <br>becomes seawater for a few moments, allowing him to slip <br>away and cover a distance of 30 feet before regrouping. <br>3. Shells: 3 large seashells are shot from Enar’s body in <br>different directions, which should be considered 3 attacks <br>with OL Medium 5. The shells must be aimed at 3 different <br>targets.</p><p>162<br>The Cliff<br>Descriptor: A steep cliff overlooking <br>the sea, riddled with many inlets. In <br>the most inaccessible part, there are <br>entrances that lead to underground <br>caves.<br>Going down the cliff, it is possible to <br>arrive at the caves’ entrance. In the <br>center of the tunnel network, there is a <br>pool where the Sea Fairy lives. Getting <br>to the pool may require you to deal <br>with one or more of these Threats. <br>Roll a die:<br>1-2 Landslide:  As they descend <br>along the cliffs, part of the rock path <br>collapses under the Hunters’ feet. <br>Descriptor: A sudden landslide. OL <br>Hard 7. <br>In the landslide, a Hunter can suffer <br>1 Wound or lose some of their <br>equipment to the sea.<br>3-4 Submerged tunnel:  To get <br>to the central pool you need to swim <br>through a narrow tunnel. <br>Descriptor: A long, narrow <br>submerged tunnel. OL Medium 5. <br>Failing the Check means not being <br>able to make it through the tunnel <br>successfully and returning to the <br>entrance.<br>5-6 Hook’s Crew: A dozen pirates <br>died here after a shipwreck and now <br>their souls are demanding vengeance <br>on the living.<br>Dead Pirates<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC  <br>(1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a lost soul who only <br>wishes for revenge on those who are still <br>alive. My body is a heap of swollen and <br>rotten flesh that moves slowly.<br>Special agenda (James the <br>Swordsman): We recognize James <br>as the one who killed our captain in <br>a duel! It is his fault that our ship was <br>wrecked, and we will taste his flesh <br>first!<br>Gift - Walking Dead:  The body <br>of the Dead Pirate is rotten and <br>putrescent, but it does not stop even if <br>dismembered. After suffering his only <br>Wound, a Dead Pirate can still take his <br>action before being eliminated, if he <br>has not already done so in the course <br>of the Exchange. If a Dead Pirate acts <br>against an outnumbered enemy, his <br>Opposition Level is increased by 1.</p><p>163<br>Sea Fairy<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a fairy of the sea and my magic allows me to <br>perform true miracles. My entire existence is tied to the sea and <br>leaving it would destroy me.<br>Agenda: I am sad because Enar has forsaken the love that kept <br>him alive in favor of blind hatred. I would like to do something <br>for him, but I cannot go to the mainland to stop his fury or find <br>his beloved.<br>Special Agenda (Marina the Sea Explorer):  I have <br>heard of Marina and know her reputation. She uses her powers <br>only to enrich herself at the expense of others. I will never agree <br>to help her unless she first shows me that she is also capable of <br>good deeds.<br>Gift – Sea Magic:  The Sea Fairy can always use one of <br>the following effects.  1. Water of Life:  A target recovers 1 <br>Wound and, if they have been dead for no more than a day, <br>they can even come back to life.  2. The Fury of the Sea:  <br>The water of the sea engulfs everything, sweeping away all <br>threats. Those who are within 30 feet must pass a Defense <br>Check against OL Hard 7 to avoid being overwhelmed by <br>the waves and being washed away, suffering 1 Wound. The <br>Sea Fairy can deliberately avoid hitting anyone in the area of <br>effect.  3. The Waves of the Sea: The Sea Fairy can travel to <br>any point of the sea within 6 miles. This shift is instantaneous, <br>and if she wants, the Fairy can take up to 2 subjects with her.<br>Sundsvall<br>Descriptor: A small coastal town, where the tranquillity of the <br>sea provides peace and serenity.<br>Information: It’s easy to find old Nils just by wandering <br>around the town. The Poor Devil has invested himself in <br>the community by donating part of his wealth to the <br>neediest, and he is well regarded by all in town. In Nils’ <br>house rests a diary where the former soldier wrote <br>down everything that happened six years earlier. From <br>the Poor Devil’s memories, it is possible to reconstruct <br>Enar’s identity and his relationship with Satu, but not <br>that Erik is Andersen’s son. The abuse perpetrated by <br>the officer was never discovered by his comrades in <br>arms. However, it will be clear from the writings that <br>the punishment reserved for Enar was beyond reason.<br>Nils the Poor Devil<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am an old soldier who lost his legs <br>in the war.<br>Agenda: The guilt for what we did to Enar <br>haunts me, I want to find a way to bring him <br>peace.<br>Hans<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC  <br>(4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a former soldier, once one <br>of the company’s best marksmen. I never miss <br>my mark and always have a loaded weapon <br>hidden under my heavy overcoat.<br>Agenda: Convince Nils to keep our <br>secret or remove him.<br>Gift - Gunslinger:  Hans owns a <br>pair of prized experimental pistols, <br>which he bought from an inventor</p><p>164<br>for more than half of his war earnings. <br>Hans’s guns can fire multiple shots <br>at the same time and with one attack, <br>the soldier can aim at 3 targets that are <br>within an area of 30 feet square. While <br>firing one pistol, Hans can reload the <br>other as an additional action. When <br>he draws a pistol from under his coat, <br>Hans can make an attack with OL Hard <br>7.  <br>Gift - Smoke Bombs:  Hans has <br>some smoke bombs, which he uses <br>to surprise the enemy. While firing <br>a pistol, Hans can drop a bomb as an <br>additional action. The thick smoke <br>will cover an area of 30 feet square and <br>inside it, everyone receives 1 Penalty <br>for every action that requires the use of <br>sight, except for Hans, who is immune <br>to the effect. Additionally, he can always <br>get away from opponents who engage <br>him without anyone preventing him.<br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities <br>related to the A Soldier’s Duty <br>Scenario and can be acquired once the <br>requirements are met. A Hunter can <br>only have one Scenario Gift and if they <br>acquire a new one, they will have to <br>forgo the previous one.<br>Blessing of the Sea<br>Requirement: Prove to the Sea Fairy <br>your intention to do something for poor <br>Enar.<br>Y ou are blessed by the mighty Sea <br>Fairy and therefore sea-related abilities <br>have no effect on you. Y ou receive 2 <br>Additional Successes on each Defense <br>Check you make to defend yourself <br>against a Gift, spell, or action made <br>using a Descriptor that includes the <br>word sea. <br>Art of Command<br>Requirement: Withstand an on -<br>slaught from Enar by fighting alongside <br>Andersen.<br>Y ou’ve observed a good leader and <br>figured out how to hone your strategies. <br>Once per Scene, you can give an <br>order to one of your allies and if they <br>try to carry it out, they will receive 2 <br>Additional Successes to any Check.<br>Coral of the Sea Fairy <br>(Special gift for Marina <br>the Sea Explorer)<br>Requirement: To kill the Sea Fairy.<br>Y ou dispatched that hateful fairy and <br>harnessed her soul in a lump of coral. <br>Now her power is yours. Y ou can use 1 <br>Treasure Token to unlock this Gift for <br>the duration of the Scenario. Spend <br>1 Soma to tap into the Coral’s power <br>and choose one of the following effects.   <br>1. Water of Life:  A target recovers <br>1 Wound.  2. The Fury of the Sea:  <br>The water of the sea engulfs everything, <br>sweeping away all threats. Those who <br>are within 30 feet must pass a Defense <br>Check against OL Hard 7 to avoid be-<br>ing overwhelmed by the waves and be-<br>ing thrown away, suffering 1 Wound.   <br>3. The Waves of the Sea:  Y ou can <br>travel to any point of the sea within 6 <br>miles. This shift is instantaneous and <br>you can take up to 2 subjects with you.<br>Sea creatures sense what you have done <br>and will attack you without hesitation <br>to try to free the soul of the Fairy.</p><p>1<br>2a<br>165<br>The Scenario <br>A Soldier’s <br>Duty in Scenes</p><p>FIRST SCENE – The Arrival at <br>the Estate<br>It’s the same one you find on page 158.<br>End of Scene:  After talking to Andersen, the Hunters <br>have a rough understanding of the situation. Given the <br>danger on several fronts, Andersen will ask half of the <br>Hunters to stay at the estate (SECOND SCENE OPTION <br>A - The Defense) and the other half to travel to Sundsvall to <br>help Hans protect Nils (SECOND SCENE OPTION B - The <br>Poor Devil).</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513697603,"modifiedTime":1781513697603,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"uHhUK7ZuissspOv2","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>A Soldier's Duty - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE OPTION A <br>– The Defense<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  The sun has just set, while <br>servants are nailing a last few planks across the windows <br>on the first floor. What should be a luxurious mansion <br>increasingly resembles a fortress under siege. Andersen and <br>Christian take the last few puffs on a pipe while setting up <br>their rifles, a ritual that probably formed during the days <br>they fought side-by-side on real battlefields. Then the pungent <br>smell of burnt tobacco fades, covered by that of salt and rotten <br>fish. A figure stands at the entrance to the garden, huge and <br>ungainly. It is a colossus of pale flesh, driftwood, rocks, shells, <br>and other debris from the sea. The being stares at the large <br>mansion for a moment, before roaring out its rage.<br>Place: Andersen’s fortified mansion.<br>Time: It is night, but a high moon and a cloudless sky <br>allow for good visibility.<br>Information: <br> ◆ Enar will attack without hesitation, ignoring any <br>mediation attempts by the Hunters. However, it will be <br>clear that Enar understands what he is told but simply <br>ignores it.<br> ◆ Andersen will give his best as a leader, using his <br>Commander Gift to lend a hand to the Hunters.<br> ◆ When Enar is left with 2 Wounds, little Erik will enter <br>the scene. Sneaking out of the mansion to get a better <br>look, he will find himself in the middle of the battle. <br>Satu will arrive soon after and the Hunters will be able <br>to observe the reactions of Enar and Andersen.<br> ◆ Enar will understand from their actions that Erik is the <br>couple’s son. When he does, he will roar in anger and <br>try to unleash his rage on the child.<br> ◆ When Enar is defeated, his body will fall apart, and <br>Erik will recognize some particular shells he has always <br>seen at the cliff.<br>End of Scene: Erik recognizes the cliff shells, which could <br>be a good clue to find out where Enar resides. Go to the</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513697604,"modifiedTime":1781513697604,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"6cLZhovHyAQ30C5p","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>A Soldier's Duty - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION A - The Cliff.</p><p>2b<br>3a<br>166</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513697604,"modifiedTime":1781513697604,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"uHhUK7ZuissspOv2","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>A Soldier's Duty - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE OPTION B – <br>The Poor Devil<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  Sundsvall is a charming <br>seaside town, with colorful houses and smiling people. Here, <br>it really seems that war and suffering have never happened. It <br>is easy to find Nils’ house. Apparently, the former soldier has <br>donated a lot of money to the poor of the city and these, given <br>his handicap, often give him a hand to thank him. When <br>you arrive at the small red brick house, you’re surprised to <br>find the front door open. Did Hans get there before you? The <br>sudden sound of a gunshot does not bode well.<br>Place: Nils the Poor Devil’s little house.<br>Time: It is late afternoon.<br>Information: When the Hunters arrive, Hans is trying <br>to execute Nils after the Poor Devil has expressed his <br>resolution to confess what happened six years ago. Hans <br>is ready to fight to the death against the Hunters while <br>keeping the elimination of Nils as his main goal.<br> ◆ If the Hunters kill Hans and Nils survives, the Poor <br>Devil will tell them everything he knows. From the <br>memories of the Poor Devil, it is possible to reconstruct <br>the identity of Enar and his relationship with Satu, <br>but not that Erik is the son of Andersen. The abuse <br>perpetrated by the officer was never discovered by his <br>comrades in arms. However, it will be clear that the <br>punishment reserved for Enar was beyond measure.<br> ◆ If Nils dies, it will be possible to find out the truth <br>regarding Enar’s punishment by reading his diary.<br> ◆ If Hans is captured, the soldier will not speak even <br>under torture and will try to give the Hunters a hard <br>time.<br>End of Scene:  It is now clear that Andersen is hiding a <br>secret linked to Enar’s revenge. The Hunters must return <br>to the estate, go to SCENE THREE OPTION B - Return to <br>the Estate.</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513697604,"modifiedTime":1781513697604,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"6cLZhovHyAQ30C5p","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>A Soldier's Duty - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION A – <br>The Cliff<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  Following the directions <br>of little Erik, you finally reach the coast. The sea is stormy <br>and crashes against a long cliff that acts as a promontory. <br>It doesn’t take long to find what looks like a natural path <br>between the rocks, exactly as Erik described to you.<br>Place: The cliff on the stretch of sea from which Enar <br>emerges.<br>Time: The setting sun is covered with rain clouds.<br>Information: Descending along the cliff will put the <br>Hunters to the test. Select or present in order the Threats on <br>page 162. Once on the bottom, they will be able to meet <br>the Sea Fairy and convince her to stop Enar. The Fairy will <br>reveal that Enar’s heart is darkened by great pain for the <br>injustice he has suffered and that it is safely laying on the <br>bottom of the sea. The Fairy can bring it to the Hunters, but <br>only if they first do justice to the memory of Enar, bringing <br>her Satu so that she can say a last goodbye to Enar’s heart. <br>The woman is Enar’s lost love and it is right that the <br>unfortunate soldier should have a chance to rest in peace.<br>End of Scene:  The Hunters must return to the estate <br>to retrieve Satu and join their other companions. Go to <br>SCENE FOUR - Destinies.</p><p>3b<br>4<br>167</p><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION B – <br>Return to the Estate<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: Tired from the long journey, <br>you arrive at Andersen’s estate as the sun goes down. You <br>are determined to untangle this story, but all your intentions <br>collide with a monster’s insane howl. Like every night, the <br>fearsome brute has come to carry out a massacre.<br>Place: Andersen’s Estate, marred by the previous night’s <br>clash.<br>Time: The sun is slowly setting, but the estate remains lit <br>thanks to lanterns expertly positioned by Andersen.<br>Information: As with the previous night, the clash with <br>Enar will be inevitable. With the monster down, the Hunters <br>will be able to ask Andersen why he tried to eliminate Nils. <br>The man will fall to his knees as he tells his entire story, <br>including his abuse of Satu. Wanting Erik to keep both a <br>father and mother, Andersen will ask the Hunters to end <br>Enar’s persecution.<br> ◆ As the Hunters sent to the cliff arrive, Erik will come <br>out of the barricaded mansion crying. Satu fled during <br>the fight, to head to the cliff. The woman reassured her <br>son that the monster will not harm her and that only <br>she can stop his fury.<br>End of Scene: It will be clear to the Hunters that Satu will <br>try to meet Enar at the cliff. Andersen will want to leave <br>immediately and nothing can stop him. Go to SCENE <br>FOUR - Destinies.</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513697604,"modifiedTime":1781513697604,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"6r2Tbo4Evno2MeeY","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>A Soldier's Duty - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE –  Destinies<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  By the time you get to the <br>cliff, night has fallen. The storm has passed, and a clear and <br>gloomy moon illuminates two figures on the edge of the rocks. <br>One is the graceful silhouette of Satu, the other the huge, <br>grotesque mass of Enar. The two observe each other for a <br>few moments. Then tentacles of seaweed emerge from Enar’s <br>body, reaching out to seize his lost love.<br>Place: The Cliff.<br>Time: It is night, but a clear moonlight illuminates the <br>epilogue of this sad story.<br>Information: Stopping Enar is a priority or he will <br>assimilate Satu by merging with her within the course of <br>one Exchange. The Hunters know that the only way to <br>permanently kill him is to call the Sea Fairy to bring the <br>monster’s heart.<br>End of Scene:  Enar, Satu, and Andersen’s fate will be in <br>the hands of the Hunters</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513697604,"modifiedTime":1781513697604,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"a-soldiers-duty","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","pages":"157-168"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513697604,"modifiedTime":1781513697604,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"b2ipz5XO5Tzf2bqO","name":"Wonderbedlam","pages":[{"_id":"avqmYFUOS4RRB43i","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>Wonderbedlam</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> Core Book</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, pages 169-182.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/wonderbedlam-p169-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513699481,"modifiedTime":1781513699481,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"aDasxbP09eJiAAiZ","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Wonderbedlam - Setup</h2><p>168<br>Wonderbedlam<br>Once upon a time…<br>No less than the Duke of Norfolk himself has approached <br>the Order with a request which must remain secret. Five <br>months ago, his daughter Alissa was taken to Wonder, <br>the bedlam of Y ork, the most renowned asylum in all of <br>England. Under the guidance of a mysterious Director, <br>the Duke hoped for the quick recovery of his daughter, <br>who possessed an attitude that was too rebellious and <br>unseemly for a young noblewoman. After the first <br>month, Alissa’s letters to her family became more and <br>more terrified and delusional, until they abruptly <br>ceased. According to Alissa’s words, Wonder is hell on <br>earth, where strange presences move in the dark rooms, <br>animated by an evil will. The Duke’s plea to the Hunters is <br>simple: save Alissa and shed a light on the dark dealings <br>happening in the asylum of Wonder.<br>A Scenario inspired by Alice’s Adventures in Wonderland (Lewis Carroll)<br>Safety Keywords: Mental illness / Imprisonment / Abuse / Cannibalism</p><p>169<br>The story that led us here…<br>Alice Liddell, daughter of an English aristocrat <br>in great favor with the Crown, developed a complex <br>mental illness as a child. From an early age, she suffered <br>from visions and delusions about a fantasy world hidden <br>in her dreams.<br>“Treated” in great secrecy by the family with drugs and <br>experimental therapies, Alice has learned to control <br>her madness enough to appear to be as sane as the next <br>person. At the age of twenty-seven, she graduated with <br>a degree in medicine, dedicating herself body and soul <br>to the treatment of mental illness. The culmination of <br>this dazzling career is Wonder, a “hospital” meant to <br>welcome children of wealthy families who want to avoid <br>patronizing one of the infamous asylums of England. <br>Little do they suspect that inside Wonder, Alice has <br>created a world of sheer madness, where unquestioning <br>patients must follow her every perverse idea to the letter, <br>in a physical and mental ordeal that she believes will bring <br>them back to sanity. Alice’s lucid madness has wrung <br>more and more strength from the patients’ suffering, <br>allowing her to shape reality itself. Wonder has become <br>a building out of space and time, where a door might <br>lead you anywhere unless you know the right words. To <br>control Wonder and not fall victim to her own creation, <br>Alice has hired the most skilled inventor in all of England, <br>Hatta Carter, famous for his theories on automatons. The <br>man has thoroughly researched Wonder in an attempt to <br>make sense of the physics-defying nature of the asylum. <br>Thanks to Hatta’s hard work, the structure now responds <br>to Alice’s will, and it has become a place from which it is <br>impossible to escape without the consent of its Director. <br>Thanks to her power, Alice controls a large, trained lynx <br>named Cheshire. By moving through the narrow conduits <br>of the asylum, she acts as the eyes of her mistress.<br> <br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>The young Alissa of Norfolk proved incredibly resistant to <br>Alice’s “cures, ” and for this reason the Director of Wonder <br>imprisoned the girl in the Hall of the Mind, disregarding <br>her normal procedure. Day after day, Alice invades <br>Alissa’s mind with nightmares in an attempt to quell her <br>rebellious spirit. Alice manages Wonder completely by <br>herself, taking advantage of her control over the building <br>and rooms, which can only be accessed with the right <br>passwords. Hatta Carter is the only other person able <br>to solve the Wonder puzzle. For this reason, Alice has <br>imprisoned the mad inventor in the bedlam’s Basement, <br>intending to keep him safe for use in future projects. <br>Meanwhile, Alicia, Alissa’s young lover, has infiltrated <br>Wonder in an attempt to free her imprisoned partner. <br>In addition to their romantic bond, Alicia is driven by <br>guilt, convinced that Alissa was sent to Wonder due to <br>the two girls’ relationship. Alissa had even refused several <br>promising marriage proposals to remain with Alicia, <br>indifferent to her duty as the Duke of Norfolk’s heir. <br>Despite her courage and tenacity, Alicia soon became a <br>prisoner of the deranged rooms of Wonder.</p><p>1<br>170</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513699481,"modifiedTime":1781513699481,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"5Z8dvmqPqYEXv0Xu","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Wonderbedlam - Scene 1</h2><p>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: You have finally arrived <br>at Wonder, the most famous and renowned bedlam in all <br>of England. What you see, however, is certainly not what <br>one might expect from a place where people are being cured <br>of mental illness. After crossing an immense garden full of <br>dead plants, you find yourself in the entrance hall before an <br>immense, mirrored wall that reflects your perplexed faces. <br>A large, tree-shaped fountain gushes water into a pool full <br>of colorful fish. Three doors on the east wall attract your <br>attention. The central one is of normal size, while the one <br>on the right is twice as large, and the one on the left is <br>barely half the normal size. On the west wall, a painted <br>inscription dominates in large letters: “In this place, <br>madness becomes reason, so that the sick can become <br>healthy again”. Finally, you notice a fourth door that <br>initially escaped your gaze, painted on the floor with <br>such skill as to seem real. While you are wondering <br>who will come to welcome you, a small white rabbit <br>peeps out from behind the large fountain. Around his <br>neck, he wears a small message holder, in which you <br>can see a rolled-up note.<br>Place: The Entrance Hall of Wonder. Hunters <br>will have the strange feeling of not being able to <br>estimate the exact size of the place. <br>Time: It is early in the morning and sunlight <br>filters through the large windows on the west <br>wall, the only ones in the room. Hunters <br>will feel like they can’t tell the exact time. <br>Initial Situation: Thirty minutes have passed since the <br>Hunters arrived and it is becoming clear that no one will <br>come to welcome them. <br>Information: Exploring the Entrance Hall and the <br>exterior of Wonder will yield the following information.<br> ◆ Catching the rabbit will be easy. The animal seems <br>accustomed to the presence of humans and for this <br>reason, it will get close. The message it brings with it is <br>clearly addressed to the Hunters: “You are not welcome <br>at Wonder, as you are not here seeking something <br>but someone. This place welcomes only those who <br>need healing of the mind.” The paper is signed, “The <br>Director” .<br> ◆ The exterior of the asylum looks quite bizarre. <br>From the outside, all the windows on the walls, the <br>doors except the entrance door, and in general every <br>possible entrance to the building, seem real but are <br>just painted. There are therefore no real access points <br>to the building, except the main door leading to the <br>Entrance Hall.<br> ◆ To a Hunter who understands magic through <br>their Descriptors, it will be clear that all of the bedlam <br>is under the influence of a powerful arcane force (see <br>the Place Wonderbedlam on page 171).<br> ◆ The three doors in the east wall open smoothly, <br>all three leading onto a long corridor that ends with <br>another identical door.</p><p>171<br>The Entrance Hall of Wonder<br>Gift - Beyond the Mirror:  The large wall mirror hides <br>the passage leading to the Hall of the Mind. Only by saying <br>the formula, “Beyond madness, beyond the basement, <br>beyond the mirror, ” is it possible to see the passage. The <br>complete formula is known by Hatta Carter, detained in the <br>Basement.<br>Gift - The Door to The Below:  The door painted on <br>the floor hides the passage to get to the Basement. Just <br>by tapping a foot on the painting and saying the formula, <br>“Is anyone under the house?” or something in that vein <br>you can see the passage. The instructions to open it are <br>contained in the message holders of the White Rabbits all <br>across Wonder.<br>Gift - The Doors to Elsewhere:  The three wall doors <br>each lead to one of the Cure Rooms. When traversing the <br>connecting corridor, the senses are confused and clouded <br>by the magic of Wonder. When you finally open the door <br>at the end of the corridor, you realize you are in another <br>place. Attempting to take something out of the Cure Rooms <br>activates the Gift Place of Pure Madness (see this same <br>page).<br>Cheshire The Faithful Lynx<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a snappy and aggressive lynx. I roam the <br>halls of Wonder guided by the will of my mistress.<br>Gift - Elusive:  Thanks to the power infused in Wonder, <br>Cheshire can disappear and reappear a short distance away, <br>and move through doors and walls. Cheshire can always <br>move without anyone being able to stop her. All actions to <br>attack or capture Cheshire receive 1 Penalty because of the <br>constant appearance and disappearance of the lynx. This <br>Gift is not affected by the Place of Pure Madness Gift.<br>WonderBedlam<br>Descriptor: I am a building animated by sheer madness <br>and no one can attempt to alter me without Alice Liddell’s <br>permission.<br>Gift - Place of Pure Madness:  When a subject <br>attempts an action or uses a Gift to change Wonder’s insane <br>structure (such as breaking through walls or circumventing <br>passageways), the building’s inherent magic activates. <br>Before the action taken is resolved, roll a die to see where <br>the subject will end up being teleported.<br>1-2: The Rabbit Hole. <br>3-4: The Labyrinth of Doors. <br>5-6: The Caterpillars’ Greenhouse.<br>This magical shift causes a side effect that lasts throughout <br>the Scene; roll a die to determine what happens.<br>1-2 Shrunk: The subject receives the Descriptor I am half <br>the size I was, all my physical abilities are diminished as well.</p><p>172<br>3-4 Enlarged: The subject receives the Descriptor I am <br>twice as big as I was and I move awkwardly and slowly.<br>5-6 Confused:  The subject receives the Descriptor My <br>mind is confused, I can’t concentrate, and I misunderstand <br>words when spoken to.<br>The three Cure Rooms<br>Descriptor: Magical places, out of space and time, where <br>patients are thrown to face whatever is troubling their mind.<br>Information: The Rabbit Hole, the Labyrinth of Doors, <br>and the Greenhouse are three places connected by magical <br>corridors to the Entrance Hall of Wonder. Within the various <br>sections of the asylum, the pitiable patients are left to fend for <br>themselves. The main purpose of the rooms is to encourage <br>patients to see “beyond” their madness and understand, <br>through the clues of the White Rabbits, how to access the <br>Basement. Once there, Alice Liddell will pick them up to <br>take them to the Hall of the Mind. Every room will feature <br>the Threat The White Rabbit.<br>Alicia The Young Girl in Love<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a young rebel from the slums who knows <br>how to get by on her own. Thanks to my tenacity, I can <br>overcome every obstacle.<br>Agenda: I want to save Alissa from this cursed place and run <br>away with her to live out our love in peace.<br>Threat - The White Rabbit<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: I’m a little white rabbit wandering around the <br>Cure Rooms and I have a message holder tied around my neck. <br>I fear those I do not know.<br>Gift - Messenger:  By capturing a White Rabbit it is <br>possible to take the message it carries. Roll a die.<br>1-2: It’s not always convenient to knock on a door with your <br>hand. <br>3-4: Knocking on a door is the bare minimum to be <br>expected of a respectable person. <br>5-6: When you arrive at a door, it is polite to ask if anyone <br>is home.</p><p>173<br>The Patients of Wonder<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are mad and desperate, driven to Wonder <br>in the hope of curing our ailments. Madness guides our <br>actions and we no longer understand that there is a world <br>outside the bedlam.<br>Gift - Why I Am Here: Roll a die to see what problem led <br>them to Wonder.<br>1 Violence: The Patient struggles to contain their anger. <br>When they act violently increase their OL by 1. <br>2 Kleptomania: The Patient yearns for any object they <br>deem interesting and will do everything to have it. Once <br>per Scene, they can act 2 times consecutively, though the <br>additional Action must be used to attempt to escape and <br>hide with the stolen goods.<br>3 Abandoned:  The Patient was interned at Wonder to <br>be forgotten. Hardened by loneliness, they gain 1 extra <br>Wound.<br>4 Split personality: The Patient changes personality in <br>the face of a specific event, such as a threat. When the new <br>personality acts, its OL becomes Hard 7.<br>5 Dementia:  The Patient is not fully aware of what is <br>happening around them. They are immune to all attempts <br>at intimidation. Increase their OL by 1 when defending <br>against a violent action.<br>6 Illness: The Patient is ill or horribly disfigured. Each <br>action against them receives 1 Penalty.</p><p>174<br>Room 1 – The Rabbit Hole<br>Descriptor: A series of burrows and tunnels full of dirt <br>and vegetation. In the small rooms and crevices, naked and <br>emaciated patients move like animals, always looking for <br>something to eat.<br>When the Hunters roam the Rabbit Hole, roll a die.<br>1-2: A group of 1d6 + 3 Patients will approach the Hunters <br>in search of food. <br>3-4: Alicia is busy fending off a group of aggressive <br>Patients. <br>5-6: A White Rabbit passes a few meters from the Hunters.<br>Room 2 – The Labyrinth of <br>Doors<br>Descriptor: An infinite series of rooms, all with doors <br>leading into a long corridor. Each room is decorated in a <br>different and macabre way, recreating situations of torture <br>and stress.<br>When the Hunters roam the Labyrinth of Doors, roll a die. <br>1-2: A group of 1d6 + 3 Patients will approach the Hunters <br>to push them into a room shouting, “We must see what’s <br>beyond!”<br>3-4: Alicia is busy fending off a group of aggressive <br>Patients. <br>5-6: A White Rabbit passes a few meters from the Hunters.<br>Room 3 – The Caterpillars’ <br>Greenhouse<br>Descriptor: A huge greenhouse full of alien and unknown <br>plants. A strong smell of pollen saturates the air, making <br>it difficult to breathe. A dense yellow fog sharply reduces <br>visibility.<br>When the Hunters are roaming the Caterpillars’ <br>Greenhouse, roll a die.<br>1-2: Two Patients are escaping from a Caterpillar of the <br>Wonderful Lands.<br>3-4: Alicia is busy fending off 2 Caterpillars of the <br>Wonderful Lands.<br>5-6: A White Rabbit passes a few meters from the Hunters.<br>Caterpillar of the Wonderful <br>Lands<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a huge carnivorous caterpillar over two <br>meters long. I feed on fresh meat and then lay my eggs in the <br>carcasses of creatures I’ve devoured.<br>Gift - Hunter Caterpillar: When a Caterpillar moves, any <br>human-sized subject in its path risks being overwhelmed. <br>Whoever is in the Caterpillar’s way must perform a <br>Defense Check in order not to end up knocked down. The <br>Caterpillar inflicts 1 Additional Wound against people <br>prone on the ground.</p><p>175<br>The Basement<br>Descriptor: A huge underground hall filled with food and <br>comfortable cushions to sit on. Unnatural darkness surrounds <br>the room, making it difficult to distinguish the walls.<br>Information: The Basement is the place where Patients <br>arrive when they have figured out how to open the door on <br>the floor of the Entrance Hall. In Alice’s crazy theory, those <br>who arrive underground have understood how to leave <br>behind their issues and psychoses, represented in the Cure <br>Rooms. In the Basement, a Patient can refresh themselves and <br>then be picked up in their sleep and taken to the Hall of the <br>Mind. Hatta Carter is a prisoner in the Basement, kept alive by <br>Alice to be used for future bedlam expansion projects. Hatta <br>has gone mad with loneliness and has built two Automata as <br>pretend tea companions.<br>Hatta Carter The <br>Mad Inventor<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a skilled inventor, the most brilliant of my <br>time. My emotional fragility leads me to frequent mood swings <br>and aggressiveness.<br>Agenda: I want the company of witty people and not cold <br>automata. I long for the chats I had with Alice.<br>Gift - Time Clocks: Hatta can manipulate one of his clocks <br>to influence time.  1. Slow: Once per Scene, Hatta increases <br>his OL by 2 when defending against a threat.  2. Speed <br>Up: Once per Scene, Hatta and one of his Automata can <br>act, immediately stopping anyone’s action regardless of the <br>situation in the narrative. If an Automaton has already acted, <br>it can act again thanks to this Gift.<br>Rabbit Automaton<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC  <br>(2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am an automaton in the service of Hatta <br>Carter. Thanks to my strong legs I can make incredible <br>jumps and crush everything when landing.<br>Gift - Leap:  When it acts, the Automaton can free <br>itself from any engagement with ease by jumping away. <br>If it lands on a victim, it increases its OL by 1 for the <br>attack and if it inflicts 1 Wound, the target will also be <br>knocked to the ground.</p><p>176<br>Lizard Automaton<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am an automaton in the service of Hatta <br>Carter. Thanks to my large tail I can perform several actions <br>at the same time.<br>Gift - Tail: The Automaton always acts twice, once with its <br>front legs and once with its long tail, but cannot focus both <br>its actions on the same target.<br>Hall of the Mind<br>Descriptor: A series of rooms painted entirely in white. The <br>doors themselves do not have handles and it takes a careful <br>look to distinguish them from the walls. A large central hall <br>gathers all the Patients, lying on rows of beds, asleep in a state <br>of trance. The distant ticking of a clock breaks an otherwise <br>unnatural silence, creating a hypnotic echo.<br>Information: In the Hall of the Mind, it is possible to <br>find several Patients in a catatonic state, including Alissa <br>of Norfolk. Alice Liddell will not seek a confrontation with <br>any intruders but will be friendly and willing to listen to the <br>unexpected guests. Alice will offer a good tea in which <br>a powerful sleep drug is mixed.<br>Threat - Alice’s special tea<br>OL Hard 7<br>Descriptor: A delicious tea mixed with a powerful <br>soporific.<br>Gift - Sleep: Those who drink the tea and fail their Defense <br>Check will fall into a deep sleep for over eight hours. Only <br>suffering severe pain (equivalent to receiving 1 Wound) or <br>the use of magic can awaken a sleeping subject.<br>Alice Liddell The <br>Director<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am the director of Wonder and, thanks to the <br>power of madness, I can enter people’s minds to heal them.<br>Agenda: Safeguard what I have built within Wonder and <br>all the incredible discoveries that the magic of madness can <br>give to mankind / Solve every problem by transforming it into <br>a Patient to be treated.<br>Gift - Alice from Other Worlds:  As an action, Alice <br>can attempt to possess the body of a person or animal by <br>looking into their eyes. Hunters can make a Defense Check <br>to prevent this. Alice can both act through the body she <br>controls and continue to use her Gifts and Descriptors. <br>The possession ends when Alice’s body suffers 1 Wound. <br>Alice cannot control more than 3 common subjects or a <br>single Hunter at the same time.</p><p>177<br>Alissa of Norfolk <br>The Rebel<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I have been physically tested by my stay in <br>Wonder, but my mind is still strong. My love for Alicia kept <br>me in the real world.<br>Agenda: Escape from Wonder and my old life and make a <br>future with Alicia.<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario, there are five Events. As a Storyteller, feel <br>free to create new ones in response to the actions of the <br>Hunters.<br>When the Hunters visit the third Cure Room <br>without first meeting Alicia:  they will encounter <br>Alicia, who is lost. The young woman will be reluctant to <br>reveal her true identity but will give her name and introduce <br>herself as a patient.<br>On a regular basis, if the Hunters waste time in the <br>Entrance Hall of Wonder:  one of the bedlam Patients <br>will walk out of one of the three doors into another. The <br>Patient will mumble disjointed words such as “see beyond” <br>or “go under” .<br>If the Hunters cause too much havoc in a Cure <br>Room: Alice will take control of Cheshire and order the <br>Hunters to leave, or try to surprise them by making it clear <br>that they are being watched.</p><p>178<br>If the Hunters try to leave the Basement: a desperate <br>Hatta Carter will attack them with the help of his Automata <br>to keep his new guests with him.<br>If the Hunters corner Alice Liddell:  the Director will <br>be ready to make deals, such as freeing Alissa or whatever <br>the Hunters ask. Alice’s real worry is that Wonder might be <br>destroyed.<br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the <br>Wonderbedlam Scenario and can be acquired once the <br>conditions are met. A Hunter can only acquire one Scenario <br>Gift. If they buy a new one during an Interlude, they will <br>have to forgo the previous one.<br>Friend of the Rabbits<br>Requirement: To have captured at least one White Rabbit.<br>Y ou are able to approach the little white rabbits without <br>frightening them. Receive 2 Additional Successes when you <br>face the Threat The White Rabbit. Once picked up, your <br>new little friends will be able to deliver a message for you to <br>any room in Wonder. This Gift allows you to send a White <br>Rabbit even through seemingly closed doors.<br>Lucid Madness<br>Requirement: Having suffered the Gift Place of Pure <br>Madness at least once.<br>Y ou are slowly figuring out how to make the weirdest ideas <br>real. Y ou can spend 1 Soma to try to activate the mad magic <br>of Wonder. State something crazy that you are capable of, <br>such as I want to walk on walls or I want my arm to stretch <br>out of proportion. The Storyteller will ask you for a Position <br>Check against an OL proportional to the madness of your <br>request. If you succeed, you get the Descriptor you declared <br>for the rest of the Scene; if you fail, you have spent your <br>Soma in vain. The effect of this Gift also ends when someone <br>makes clear that what you are doing is utter madness.<br>The Forgotten Queen (Special Gift for Regina <br>the Thief of Hearts)<br>Requirement: Visit a Cure Room.<br>Confusing flashbacks and painful emotions grip your <br>mind. Y ou’ve been here as a patient before, but maybe <br>you’ve forgotten why. Are you sure you want to remember? <br>Once per Scene, you can try to remember something of <br>your experience in Wonder. Choose a place or a subject <br>from the bedlam, and the Storyteller will give you useful <br>information about a Descriptor, a Gift, or their Agenda. <br>Remembering is painful. For the rest of the Scene, when <br>you use one of your Gifts, roll a die: on a 5 or <br>higher you lose 1 Soma and you <br>are no longer so sure that you are <br>the Queen.</p><p>1<br>2 3<br>179</p><p>FIRST SCENE – Arrival in Wonder<br>It’s the same one you find on page 170.<br>End of Scene:  For the Hunters, it will be clear that the <br>only way forward is through one of the three doors to the <br>Cure Rooms.</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513699481,"modifiedTime":1781513699481,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ptjjQqOjVwyYOpwh","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Wonderbedlam - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE – The First Room<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You walk through a long <br>corridor that leads you in front of a door exactly the same <br>as the one you just went through. As in the Entrance Hall, <br>time seems to flow differently in this place. You have the <br>impression that the few steps necessary to cross between one <br>door and the other takes hours rather than moments. You <br>open the door and what is shown to you...<br>Note: As the Storyteller, continue the description based on <br>the room that was chosen by the Hunters.<br>Place: One of the Cure Rooms.<br>Time: It is impossible to establish the exact time and, <br>from one room to another, day changes to night in a totally <br>random way.<br>Information: The Hunters encounter the result 1-2 of <br>the relevant room. Once the encounter is resolved they will <br>notice a White Rabbit and, by capturing it, they will get the <br>first part of the hint to enter the Basement.<br>End of Scene: It will be clear that each Cure Room holds <br>a clue to progress through Wonder. The Hunters must <br>move to another room. Go to THIRD SCENE – The Second <br>Room, the Encounter with Alicia.</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513699482,"modifiedTime":1781513699482,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"aL5svteRL03BPN5k","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Wonderbedlam - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE – The Second <br>Room, the Encounter with Alicia<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You walk through a long <br>corridor that leads you in front of a door exactly the same <br>as the one you just went through. As in the Entrance Hall, <br>time seems to flow differently in this place and you have the <br>impression that the few steps necessary to cross between one <br>door and the other takes hours rather than moments. You <br>open the door and immediately you are alerted by the cry of <br>a girl.<br>Note: As the Storyteller, continue the description based on <br>the room that was chosen by the Hunters and highlight the <br>presence of Alicia engaged in an encounter, as a result of <br>3-4 of the relevant room.<br>Place: One of the Cure Rooms.<br>Time: It is impossible to establish the exact time and, <br>from one room to another, day changes to night in a totally <br>random way.<br>Information: The Hunters are aware that without their <br>intervention the young woman will succumb. <br> ◆ Once safe, Alicia will introduce herself, saying that <br>she is in Wonder to save a friend from this place of <br>madness. Alicia has two clues with her, one from the <br>The Scenario Wonderbedlam in Scenes</p><p>4<br>180<br>White Rabbit in this room and one from the one the <br>Hunters have not yet visited. <br> ◆ During the discussion with Alicia, Alice will <br>attack the girl by surprise via Cheshire, and then <br>make the lynx flee through a wall.<br>End of Scene:  It should now be clear to the <br>Hunters how to access the Basement (Alicia can <br>help them if they haven’t quite figured out how to <br>do it yet). Go to FOURTH SCENE - The Basement.</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513699482,"modifiedTime":1781513699482,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"beyaT5lCFHuou032","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Wonderbedlam - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE –  <br>The Basement<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  When the door <br>opens, you see a large flight of stairs that descend <br>underground. A few minutes later you find yourself in <br>a large room, richly furnished with colored cushions <br>and drapes. The Basement is hard to see across, so <br>much so that you can’t make out the walls. Suddenly, <br>a shrill voice calls for your attention. In front of you, <br>a gentleman with a strange top hat on his head <br>converses amiably with two Automata, one in the <br>form of a large rabbit, the other of a lizard. In a <br>grotesque imitation of teatime, the man with the <br>top hat conducts a one-way conversation, where his <br>words are left unanswered by the cold, unintelligent <br>gazes of the Automata.<br>Place: The Basement of Wonder, where those <br>who have passed the Cure Rooms can rest while <br>waiting to be picked up.<br>Time: It is not possible to distinguish between day <br>and night, but the atmosphere and the soft lighting <br>recall the time for evening tea.<br>Information: Hatta Carter will be delighted to have new <br>guests and will invite the Hunters to join him for tea. By <br>talking to him you can get the following information.<br> ◆ Those who pass through the cycle of therapies in the <br>Cure Rooms can access the Basement where they <br>can refresh themselves, dress again, and wait for the <br>transfer to the Hall of the Mind. The Director keeps <br>Hatta tucked away for future expansions.<br> ◆ Hatta is a prisoner of the Director. He built Wonder <br>and knows the formula for going beyond the mirror, <br>accessing the part of Wonder that is exclusive to the <br>Director. <br> ◆ If the Hunters point out to Hatta that if he knows every <br>secret, he can escape whenever he wishes, the man will <br>nod in amazement, revealing the formula for going <br>beyond the mirror to the Director’s sanctum. Once <br>this is done, however, he will return to his madness, <br>complaining once more about his imprisonment.<br> ◆ Hatta will say that he doesn’t know the Director’s real <br>name, but he knows that she is a renowned doctor and <br>that she is not really a bad person. As a scientist, he <br>understands well that indelicate acts must sometimes <br>be done in the name of scientific progress.<br> ◆ The tablecloth on the table is actually the blueprint of <br>Wonder drawn by Hatta during construction. It reveals <br>the formula for going beyond the mirror. The mad <br>inventor, however, will strongly object if the Hunters <br>try to take the map, as this would ruin the table’s setting <br>for tea.<br>When the Hunters attempt to leave the Basement, Hatta <br>will beg them to stay with him, insisting until he becomes <br>aggressive and unleashes the Automata against the Hunters.</p><p>5<br>181<br>End of Scene:  After Hatta and his Automata are dealt <br>with, the Hunters know the formula to cross the mirror <br>and finally discover who is behind Wonder. Go to FIFTH <br>SCENE - The Director.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513699482,"modifiedTime":1781513699482,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"dJxTMhnvsJkvcitX","name":"Scene 5","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Wonderbedlam - Scene 5</h2><p>FIFTH SCENE –  <br>The Director<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: In front of the large mirror <br>on the north wall, you say the formula “Beyond the madness, <br>beyond the basement, beyond the mirror, ” and you see a <br>small door appear. Crossing through it, you find yourself in <br>a bare and aseptic environment with walls, furniture, and <br>doors, all in white. The doors themselves do not <br>have handles and only with a careful inspection is <br>it possible to distinguish them from the surrounding <br>walls. Finally, you arrive in a huge room, furnished <br>solely with an endless series of beds on which placid <br>patients are sleeping. The distant ticking of a clock <br>breaks an otherwise unnatural silence. Then, a door <br>opens and a distinguished-looking woman with <br>a cold gaze appears in front of you. “Welcome to <br>Wonder. I’m the Director.”<br>Place: The aseptic Hall of the Mind of Wonder.<br>Time: It is not possible to distinguish between day and <br>night, but the atmosphere and the white lights recall a visit <br>to a hospital.<br>Information: Alice will offer her guests a fine cup of tea, <br>trying to put them to sleep. Alternatively, she will try to take <br>control of Alicia and pass her off as Alissa. The Director will <br>claim that Alicia is a second personality Alissa has created <br>inside Wonder to escape from herself. Alice will try not to <br>give the real Alissa to the Hunters, but she won’t be willing <br>to lose Wonder to keep her.</p>"},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513699482,"modifiedTime":1781513699482,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"wonderbedlam","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","pages":"169-182"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513699482,"modifiedTime":1781513699482,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"wLWTcisO2xySDM3P","name":"Tuvstarr's Reflection","pages":[{"_id":"JMxPlb61zA3laTIw","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>Tuvstarr's Reflection</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> Core Book</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, pages 183-196.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/tuvstarrs-reflection-p183-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513701118,"modifiedTime":1781513701118,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"lnO2RrcmtxEIlxkQ","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Tuvstarr's Reflection - Setup</h2><p>182<br>Tuvstarr’s <br>Reflection<br>A Scenario inspired by Tuvstarr <br>(Helge Kjellin) by Petter Nallo<br>Safety Keywords: Decay / Corruption of body and <br>mind / Folk Horror<br>Tuvstarr’s Reflection is a special Scenario built as a Scene Tree (see page 100) and <br>is great for introductory Sessions, one-shots, or to introduce Sherazade the Weaver <br>of Tales to a Campaign. <br>This Scenario takes place within a story told by Sherazade, an emissary of the One <br>who Plots in the Shadows (page 196). The Hunters will awaken in the world of <br>Princess Tuvstarr and must solve the mystery of her disappearance in order to <br>awaken.</p><p>183<br>Once upon a <br>time…<br>Good evening my dear hosts, my name is <br>Sherazade and I am a weaver of tales. My <br>words will take you to incredible worlds <br>and follow the feats of brave Hunters… <br>however this story is not like the others <br>and these feats are not just imaginary. Will <br>our heroes succeed in their quest? Or will <br>they perish, disappearing forever from the <br>memory of time? <br>The story that led us here…<br>The original fairy tale was written by Helge Kjellin <br>in 1913 and tells how Princess Tuvstarr left her home to <br>follow Skutt the moose into the forest.<br>Tuvstarr does not listen to Skutt’s advice, and so the <br>Fairies steal her crown, the Hulder (a forest spirit) steals <br>her dress and, finally, she loses a golden heart-shaped <br>necklace in a black pond in the depths of the woods. The <br>Princess will stay there staring at the black pond until she <br>turns into a blade of grass: Tuvstarr (Carex Cespitosa).<br>But stories don’t always go as they were originally <br>written... Appalled by the wickedness of the world, <br>Princess Tuvstarr learns from rumors around the court <br>of the existence of a pond, deep in the woods, where <br>wishes can come true. Tuvstarr asks the trusty moose <br>Skutt to lead her through the woods. There, the Princess <br>trades her crown with the Fairies, to gain free access to <br>their lands. <br>Tuvstarr then gives the Hulder her dress to continue <br>her search, and finally arrives at the heart of the forest. <br>There, in the black Pond that no human being has ever <br>seen, she plunges her heart and soul. Tuvstarr desires a <br>perfect world, where everything is bright and good. And <br>that’s what she finds on the other side. A perfect dream <br>world. There she is happy, the fields are always green, and <br>idealized constructs that resemble her mother and father <br>smile at her. But the Dream World needs to balance itself <br>out. And so reality, its mirror, becomes dark and twisted. <br>The sun sets in eternal darkness, the forest is corrupted, <br>animals get sick, and the soil rots.<br>Tuvstarr’s father and mother, the King and Queen, send <br>their knights to bring her back. None of them returns. The <br>lands are becoming increasingly corrupt and the people <br>are desperate. Eventually, the rulers turn to anyone who <br>can help them. This is where our story begins.</p><p>1<br>184<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>The land is bewitched. The fields are sterile, the church <br>bells are silent, mothers forget to feed their children, and all <br>dreams are dark and full of pain. The sun now rests below <br>the horizon and the lands are covered by eternal twilight. <br>Tuvstarr the Child Princess is gone, wandering into the <br>forest and the curse is believed to have something to do <br>with her disappearance. The knights were sent to the forest, <br>the wetlands, and the wilderness to find her, but none <br>have returned. The King and Queen now seek out new <br>champions to retrieve their daughter from the wilds and <br>end this curse.</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513701119,"modifiedTime":1781513701119,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"CEbr9il50Jk4Ba7R","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Tuvstarr's Reflection - Scene 1</h2><p>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: Sherazade clears her throat, <br>then smiles at her guests before speaking. “Our story opens <br>with a rude awakening. You are in a strange inn which is <br>certainly not the place where you fell asleep last night. The <br>bedroom door is thrown open violently and a tall, thin man <br>in a soldier’s uniform asks you to follow him out of the room. <br>Apparently, the King and Queen of this strange place await <br>you to give you an audience.  In the midst of a field of withered <br>flowers and rotting crops stands a mighty castle. The walls are <br>covered with ivy and the roofs, once gilded, seem blackened <br>and burned by the rays of a dying, red and menacing sun. ”<br>Place: The royal castle, in the center of a large city. The air <br>is gloomy, and the faces of the people are sad and dejected. <br>A black sky illuminated by a faint crimson light hangs over <br>everything like an eternal night.<br>Time: It is early morning on a gloomy autumn day.<br>Initial Situation:  The Hunters are summoned by the <br>King and Queen for an important mission. They are aware <br>that they are in another world or, perhaps, within a dream.<br>Information:<br> ◆ The King and Queen sit on their thrones staring sternly <br>at the Hunters. They do not speak, but their butler, a <br>lean and hunched old man, will offer the Hunters gold <br>and honors to bring back Princess Tuvstarr. She has <br>fled into the great forest that lies beyond the castle. <br> ◆ Before departure, the old butler will join the Hunters <br>to talk out of the King and Queen’s earshot. He will say <br>that there is a curse upon the land. The Hunters must <br>prepare themselves for the necessity of an extreme act <br>to save the kingdom, perhaps even to kill the Princess <br>herself.<br> ◆ As the Hunters set out for the wild forest, people in <br>the villages will report that many have seen Princess <br>Tuvstarr ride a moose and disappear into the woods. <br>And from that moment, the world has changed.<br>End of Scene:  The Hunters head into the great wild <br>forest in search of Princess Tuvstarr’s trail. Go to SECOND <br>SCENE - The Wild Forest.</p><p>185<br>The moose and the moths<br>“He was once a majestic being, the King of the Woods and <br>Wildlands. The name Skutt was given to him by the rocks, <br>torrents, and small streams, as he had the ability to make <br>great leaps through any obstacle. One day, when the sun was <br>bright, he ventured into the fields and flowers near the castle <br>that humans built. There, he met Tuvstarr and was fascinated <br>by the little creature with her white dress, long golden hair <br>and sparkling crown. When Tuvstarr asked him to see the <br>rest of the world, he couldn’t refuse and put her on his back to <br>ride into the wilderness. <br>He told her about the pond in the middle of the woods where <br>all wishes can be fulfilled, but only if the wish is made by <br>an innocent child. And so she asked to go there. During the <br>journey the Princess traded both the crown and the dress for <br>safe passage, and at the pond she disappeared into the black <br>water, leaving only her reflection. Then there was a crack in <br>the sky, which froze the sun in place forever.<br>Not knowing what to do, Skutt wandered the lands in shame. <br>He came across one of the knights sent by the King and Queen. <br>The noble warrior charged the moose with his spear couched <br>under his arm. The moose faced him head-on and killed the <br>armored foe and his steed. But the spear had hit its mark and <br>Skutt fell, dying. However, the power of Tuvstarr’s affection <br>would not allow him to die. The Princess was so anxious that <br>she wished that Skutt could exist forever, even in death. <br>The moose is now rotting. Large worms crawl into his flesh, <br>and in the moonlight, they hatch into ghostly moths that <br>flutter around his horns. His stench is carried by the wind <br>and even carrion-eating birds avoid him. At the time of his <br>death, he forgot his name. But he can’t forget Tuvstarr and <br>the guilt he feels… ”<br>Skutt the Moose<br>OL Hard 7 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a majestic and magnificent moose, <br>ravaged by the decay of death and Tuvstarr’s magic which <br>keeps me alive.<br>Agenda:  I have to find someone to save Tuvstarr from the <br>black pond and the illusion she fell into, because I can’t get in <br>/ Protect Tuvstarr above all else, even if it means having the <br>world rot away.<br>Gift - Spectral Presence:  Skutt cannot truly be <br>eliminated as long as Tuvstarr’s wish keeps him alive. <br>The moose can move through fog, disappearing and <br>reappearing even many feet away. Within the fog, no one <br>can stop or impede Skutt’s movement. When he suffers <br>his third Wound, Skutt falls apart, only to revive in the <br>following Scene.<br>Information: Skutt is a Main NPC that Hunters can <br>encounter in any Scene. He will always appear accompanied <br>by a thick fog, stinking of rot, and surrounded by pale <br>moths. From his horns, like a ghostly veil, hangs the torn <br>fabric of a knightly cloak, and a spear is half driven into <br>his body.<br>If the Hunters fight:  Skutt is not interested in the fight <br>but is still a proud animal, so he will lash out at the enemy, <br>charging with his antlers. <br>If the Hunters talk to Skutt:  He can tell how he took <br>Tuvstarr to the sacred pond, deep in the woods. Whatever <br>Tuvstarr did by diving into the lake, it wreaked havoc on the</p><p>2<br>186<br>world. Skutt wants to save Tuvstarr, but without endangering <br>her. He cannot enter the pond himself, nor can any other <br>inhabitant of these woods.<br>The magic of the pond binds anyone seeking it to make the <br>same journey as the Princess, crossing the places where she <br>exchanged her treasures to continue forward. If the Hunters <br>bring those treasures to him, Skutt will lead them to the <br>pond where Tuvstarr has disappeared.</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513701119,"modifiedTime":1781513701119,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"T5VBjI8sO8TeotJe","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Tuvstarr's Reflection - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE – The Wild <br>Forest<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: Sherazade remains silent for <br>a moment, the audience motionless in ecstatic admiration. <br>Then, the Weaver brings a glass of wine to her mouth, though <br>she barely wets her lips. “You travel past the meadow covered <br>with withered flowers, small villages, hills, and streams.  <br>The closer you get to the wilderness and the great forest, the <br>more the atmosphere changes. The woods before you are <br>shrouded in perpetual darkness. Only the faintest light of the <br>sun hanging just beyond the horizon reaches this place. But the <br>sun never really rises, leaving this land enclosed in a twilight <br>and ghostly hour. The creatures of the woods have gone mad. <br>Corrupted by the whispers in the grass, mesmerized by the <br>moon’s reflections, they drink poisonous sap and foam that <br>smells of sulphur. ”<br>Place: The wood that separates the kingdom from the <br>deepest forest is basked in the faintest twilight glow. <br>Time: Time has stopped and no longer has any meaning.<br>Information: When crossing the wood, the Hunters may <br>have some encounters. Roll a die or choose. <br>Note: During this Scene, the Hunters may encounter Skutt.<br>1: A fox is killing and eating its own pups while giving birth <br>to them. <br>2: Two ravens, Hugin and Munin, messengers of Father <br>Odin, approach the Hunters. Even the ancient gods want <br>to stop this disease. If a Hunter approaches the ravens, they <br>will realize they can mentally communicate with them. The <br>ravens want to follow the Hunters. Anyone who makes a <br>pact with them receives the Hugin and Munin Scenario Gift, <br>without the need to have an Interlude.<br>3: Black fumes fill the air, foamy and dense bubbles emerging <br>from a dark pond. A knight in rusty armor lies dead near one <br>of the springs. His eyes are white and puffy, like a sack of eggs <br>ready to burst. The corpse holds an ashwood spear with an <br>iron point. If a Hunter chooses to take the spear, he gains the <br>Lance of the Fallen Knight’ Scenario Gift without the need to <br>have an Interlude.</p><p>3a<br>187<br>4: The Troll Stallo sleeps sitting under a tree, and a bird has <br>built a nest in his hair. If he is awakened by too much noise <br>or for any other reason, he will try to eat the Hunters.<br>Stallo<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am an old troll and my appetite is <br>matched only by my strength. A bird has made its nest on <br>my head and when it gets angry it starts to peck me in the <br>eye, which is incredibly annoying!<br>Gift – Troll:  Stallo possesses enormous strength and <br>each Position Check for a physical action attempted <br>against him receives 1 Penalty. At the end of each of his <br>actions, Stallo recovers 1 Wound he suffered. When he <br>reaches 0 Wounds, the troll will collapse to the ground, <br>only to regenerate within minutes. <br>5: A saddled warhorse, magnificent and white as fresh <br>snow, is grazing in the tall grass. This mount belonged to <br>one of the knights who met a dire fate in the search for <br>Tuvstarr. The steed will be reluctant to be approached, but <br>if the Hunters succeed (Threat OL Medium 5, Descriptor: <br>I am a fast, mighty, and frightened horse), it will take them <br>to the body of its old master, where the Hunters can retrieve <br>the knightly crest showing a fox with two tails. This crest <br>will be useful when meeting the Gallant Knight (page <br>191).<br>6: A ruined castle on a hill. The castle is the scene of a <br>massacre. The men and women who once lived within its <br>walls have apparently killed each other. Only a ten-year-old <br>girl remains alive, but she is angry and will try to attack the <br>Hunters with a hidden knife.<br>Angry Little Girl<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I survived the adults’ madness and now I <br>struggle like a ferocious animal not to succumb to this <br>cruel world.<br>Agenda: Find a safe place to stay or a group of people <br>ready to accept and protect me.<br>End of Scene:  after one or more encounters (at the <br>discretion of the Storyteller) the Hunters come across <br>the crown of the Fairies (THIRD SCENE OPTION A - <br>The Crown of the Fairies) or the Hulder (THIRD SCENE <br>OPTION B - The Hulder and the white dress).</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513701119,"modifiedTime":1781513701119,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Fs4UaPjmDZIau05f","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Tuvstarr's Reflection - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION A – <br>The Crown of the Fairies<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: Sherazade smiles at a young <br>nobleman among her audience who has risen from his chair <br>to get a better look at her. She winks at him and says: “Sit <br>down my little guest, now the best is coming. ” <br>“The swamps are shrouded in thin veils of a ghostly mist. All <br>is silent. The moon appears to crack and bleed into the sky, <br>and the faint stars die out one by one as you travel deeper <br>into this nocturnal realm. There is a light in the distance, a <br>glow that is reflected in the swamps and still water. This light <br>comes from a small golden crown, and all around, many <br>silhouettes dance as if enthralled by its light. Fairies look like <br>pale women with long hair. They glide, dance, and writhe in <br>the air as if adrift in an invisible current. They are dreamlike, <br>ethereal, but their bodies meet, touch and brush against each <br>other or, sometimes, through each other. Their eyes are shut</p><p>188<br>and they seem to moan with pleasure as they bask in the light <br>that shines from the golden crown. Not far away, sitting in <br>the damp mud, are the bodies of all those who have drowned <br>here over the centuries. They have emerged from the earth, <br>awakened from the dead, to watch the Fairies dance. They <br>sit, motionless, observing the show with dull eyes and empty <br>eye sockets. ”<br>Place: The swamp where the fairies have <br>carried the crown of Tuvstarr.<br>Time: An eternal night, shrouded in fog and <br>under the light of a faded moon.<br>Information: The crown is sitting on a small <br>islet in an open swamp. It is possible to reach <br>it by jumping between the various stones that <br>emerge from the water.<br>Threat OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: A marshy swamp with a stone <br>track as its only path.<br>The water is black, cold, and deep enough to slow a <br>Hunter who falls into it.<br>Note: During this Scene, the Hunters may encounter <br>Skutt.<br> ◆ The Fairies are corrupted by the splendor of the crown <br>and will not allow anyone to touch it. It is possible to <br>communicate with them by interrupting their dance. <br>The Fairies will tell the story of a human princess who <br>gifted them with the crown, as bright as a small sun, <br>in order to cross the swamp. It is difficult to maintain <br>a conversation with dreamlike entities, and in a short <br>time they will slip back into their dreams and start <br>dancing again.<br> ◆ If the Hunters attempt to take the crown, the Fairies <br>will awaken from their trance. Screaming in pain, they <br>will attack the culprits without hesitation. Around the <br>crown there are always twelve fairies.<br> ◆ Somehow blocking the light emanating from the <br>crown will awaken the Fairies from the spell. They will <br>look at the cracked moon, screaming in agony as they <br>realize how much the lands around <br>them have been corrupted. Some will <br>suffer so much that they will become <br>dew in the grass or a pale reflection in <br>the pond. Others will ask the Hunters <br>to do something to save their lands.<br>Fairies<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC  <br>(1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are Fairies, spirits of nature <br>who move gracefully in a world of clumsy humans.<br>Agenda: Defend the crown that Tuvstarr has given us and <br>dance forever wrapped in its sweet light. <br>Gift – Madness: Made mad by the light of the crown, the <br>Fairies rage at anyone who tries to touch it. Two or more <br>Fairies can attack together to make a single action with a <br>bonus to the OL equal to the number of fairies involved. If <br>the action succeeds, in addition to inflicting 1 Wound, the <br>target will be thrown into the swamp to be drowned. Once <br>in the water, the target can attempt to break out of the flurry <br>of drowned, dead hands pulling from the bottom with a <br>Defense Check against OL Medium 5.<br>End of Scene: After recovering the crown of the Fairies, <br>the Hunters must also recover the dress from the Hulder <br>(THIRD SCENE OPTION B - The Hulder and the White</p><p>3b<br>189<br>Dress) or, if they already have it, go through the forest to the <br>black pond (FOURTH SCENE - The Black pond).</p><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION B – <br>The Hulder and the White Dress<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: Sherazade takes out two paper <br>shapes from a bag, the first is the silhouette of a graceful Fairy, <br>the second that of a deformed creature. She places them in front <br>of the flame of a candle and on the wall, as if by magic, the <br>projected shadows swap places. “This area of the forest is even <br>darker than any you have been through so far. The woods are <br>deep, dark, and full of evil shadows. You come across giant <br>boulders entirely covered in dense moss and bearded lichens <br>hanging from tree branches, with the cold wind whipping <br>through the foliage. On the ground you see a streak of blood and <br>slime, as if forming a gloomy path that guides your steps. ”<br>Place: Among the trees of a dark forest, where not even the <br>light of the moon dares to show itself.<br>Time: It is night. Darkness envelops the forest, giving the <br>trees ghostly shapes.<br>Information: This is the Hulder’s realm. A spiritual forest <br>entity with feminine traits that once lived in symbiosis with <br>trees but is now corrupt and repulsive. Tuvstarr traded her <br>dress for passage through the woods. The Hulder took the thin <br>fabric in her hands, and it immediately made her feel unlike <br>anything she had felt before. With the dress, she felt strong <br>and beautiful, but also prey to a voracious hunger. Now the <br>dress is nothing more than a dirty piece of cloth that the spirit <br>has tied over her eyes like a blindfold. The Hulder obsessively <br>repeats how beautiful, graceful and lovely she is. This can be a <br>hint to help the Hunters realize that with the blindfold on the <br>monster is unaware of her true appearance.<br>Note: During this Scene, the Hunters may encounter Skutt.<br> ◆ It is easy to spot the tracks of the Hulder. A trail of blood <br>and slime is left on the ground where the creature crawls. <br>Her sense of smell is almost non-existent, but if the <br>Hunters make a noise entering her part of the forest, she <br>will charge furiously forward to devour them. <br> ◆ The Hulder is powerful and killing her in a fight will be <br>difficult. The best way to defeat her is to lure her into a trap <br>so as to tear the dirty piece of cloth – the dress Tuvstarr <br>gave her – from her eyes. If this happens near a reflective <br>surface (such as one of the many ponds that fill this area), <br>she will see her reflection and what she has become. She <br>will scream in agony and crawl away into the ashes of the <br>night. There, she will throw up everything she ate before <br>returning to her original form, filled with shame and guilt.<br>The Hulder<br>OL Hard 7 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am an ancient forest spirit. I have eaten so many <br>living things that I have become fat and swollen, and the pieces <br>of the animals and people I have devoured are dripping from my <br>slobbering lips.<br>Agenda: Devour everything I meet.<br>Gift – Corrupted Spirit:  The Hulder has a feminine form, <br>but her skin is spongy and slimy. Her breath smells of rot. She <br>doesn’t realize what a grotesque monster she has become, as in <br>her mind she is still beautiful and seductive. When she suffers <br>1 Wound, the Hulder vomits a cloud of foul vapor that reeks <br>of rot. All the subjects hit by the cloud suffer 1 Wound in turn. <br>The effect of this Gift can be avoided with a Defense Check. <br>Gift – Swollen with Flesh and Blood: If killed, the Hulder <br>will emit a long, heart-breaking cry that will echo in the <br>woods, and all the dead she has eaten will scream in agony in a</p><p>4<br>190<br>cacophonous chorus. Anyone <br>who hears the cry loses 2 Soma <br>and receives 1 Penalty on any <br>action for the rest of the Scene.<br>End of Scene: After recovering <br>the dress, the Hunters must <br>also recover the crown from <br>the Fairies (THIRD SCENE <br>OPTION A - The Crown of the <br>Fairies) or, if they already have it, <br>cross the forest to the black pond <br>(FOURTH SCENE - The Black <br>Pond).</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513701119,"modifiedTime":1781513701119,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"6CopGoQ0S4uxN4CW","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Tuvstarr's Reflection - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE <br>– The Black Pond<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  <br>“My dear guests, after a long journey <br>our heroes have finally reached <br>their destination... or have they?” <br>Sherazade winks at you and, for a <br>moment, you have the impression that <br>she has moved just a few steps away.  <br>“You arrive at the center of the forest. The <br>trees are tall and menacing, and they seem <br>clustered around a pool of freezing, black <br>water. Any light that penetrates here looks <br>thin and weak, as if it were an intruder in <br>this land consecrated to darkness. Everything <br>is still and silent. ”<br>Place: The center of the great forest, bathed <br>in an unnatural darkness.<br>Time: An indefinite hour, in a place out of the normal flow <br>of time.<br>Information: As Hunters approach the water, they can <br>discover two things.<br> ◆ While the princess is gone, Tuvstarr’s reflection can <br>still be seen in the black waters, showing an image of <br>a naked girl sitting on the shore and staring into the <br>abyss. Next to her is a knight’s plate armor. The shield <br>has a fox with two tails as a heraldic symbol. There are <br>footsteps on the muddy shore leading into the black <br>water.<br> ◆ To enter the mirror world, the Hunters will have to dive <br>and swim to the bottom of the Pond, through the cold <br>and fatal darkness. When they are at the bottom, in <br>the mud and slime, suddenly a light will appear from <br>above. Sunlight in a clear sky. By swimming to the <br>surface, the Hunters will enter the Dream World that <br>Tuvstarr has built for herself.<br>The Dream World<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  “What stretches out before <br>your eyes is the Dream World that Tuvstarr created with <br>her wish. It is a land of joy, happiness, and goodness. Here <br>the days are eternal, bees never sting, and nature provides <br>everything those who live there need. It is built on all that is <br>good, siphoned out of the real world and remodelled according <br>to the will of the Child Princess. The grass is emerald green, <br>the sky is blue with perfect white clouds. A thousand and <br>a thousand more flowers. Butterflies and pollen in the air. <br>Everything is lush and new. What was once a quagmire is <br>a field with rolling hills, what used to be a forbidding forest <br>is now a lush wood with flourishing trees and meadows <br>carpeted with flowers. In the distance, the high towers of the <br>castle reflect the sunlight. ”</p><p>5<br>191<br>Place: The perfect dream world created by Tuvstarr.<br>Time: Early morning, on a beautiful summer day.<br>Information: When they arrive, the Hunters will feel like <br>they have been reborn. Their wounds will stop hurting (it is <br>considered a special rest that allows all Hunters to recover <br>1 Wound). Their garments and clothes will be mended, in <br>fact looking better than ever before. The water they drink <br>and the fruit they eat are the best meal they have ever eaten. <br>It is truly a paradise.<br> ◆ Encounter with the Gallant Knight: The Gallant Knight <br>sits under a tree, eating an apple. His sword is beside <br>him. He is an old man, but there is still strength in his <br>steps and voice. In fact, his hair isn’t as grey as it used <br>to be. His pains have lessened. An old wound that once <br>grieved him is now merely a white scar. The Knight has <br>abandoned his quest. He found his way to the black <br>pond, entered the deep waters, and arrived in the <br>Dream World. He met Tuvstarr, tried to bring her back, <br>but she offered to let him stay here. He agreed, vowing <br>to continue to protect her from any threat. However, he <br>can be convinced to pick up his quest once more if he is <br>told that his brothers all died in the search and if he is <br>shown the two-tailed fox crest (page 187). <br> ◆ If the Hunters possess the Lance of the Fallen Knight, <br>the Gallant Knight will ask them to return it to him <br>so that it can be brought back to the castle in the real <br>world. Whether defeated or convinced, the Knight will <br>reveal that Tuvstarr is in the Dream World.<br>The Gallant Knight<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a respected and experienced knight of the <br>kingdom. My skill is only matched by my honor.<br>Agenda: Respect my knightly duties and serve the young <br>Princess Tuvstarr / Save the kingdom from what’s happening.<br>Gift - Gallant Knight:  The Knight is incredibly skilled, <br>but he would never use his full abilities against anyone <br>he doesn’t consider truly evil. When defending against <br>an enemy attack, his mastery increases his OL by 1. The <br>Knight will never inflict the final Wound on a target if he <br>doesn’t feel it truly deserves death.<br>End of Scene:  After finding out where Tuvstarr is, the <br>Hunters can proceed to the FIFTH SCENE - The Castle of <br>Dreams.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513701119,"modifiedTime":1781513701119,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Mu2SS3Hl6jGZfZ4r","name":"Scene 5","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Tuvstarr's Reflection - Scene 5</h2><p>FIFTH SCENE – The Castle of <br>Dreams<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  “ Ahead, you see a castle <br>bigger than any other building in the country. The roof shines <br>with gold while the tallest tower is like another sun, shining <br>ever so bright. Looking around you, however, you notice that <br>everything seems to be nothing more than a false reflection <br>of reality. Farmers at work, animals in the fields, the King <br>and Queen themselves you see at the gates of the castle, all do <br>nothing but smile and nod. They speak in a low voice and say <br>comforting things like: “Stay here, everything is fine, the lands <br>are fresh and full of life. ” You realize that they are nothing <br>more than simple, idealized creations of Tuvstarr’s memories, <br>but full of joy and warmth. ”</p><p>192<br>Place: The perfect dream world created by Tuvstarr.<br>Time: Early morning, on a beautiful summer day.<br>Information: The Hunters may encounter Tuvstarr in the <br>village, the forest, or the castle. She is simply a child who <br>wanders, naked and full of life. Tuvstarr goes around creating <br>things in her dream world.<br> ◆ Tuvstarr will ask the Hunters to remain in her kingdom, <br>just like the Gallant Knight. If they agree, the Hunters will <br>spend their lives in a dream and will soon forget about the <br>world on the other side of the pond.<br> ◆ Fighting Tuvstarr is a very difficult challenge. But if the <br>Hunters manage to imprison her or push her near the <br>lake, they may throw her in to make her <br>emerge on the other side.<br> ◆ Getting her to leave <br>her dream is difficult as <br>she only has vague <br>memories of the real <br>world, as if that <br>were the dream <br>to her. She <br>does not <br>like the pond in the forest. There is something about it <br>that makes her uncomfortable or even scares her, but she <br>does not have the ability to “remove” it with her power, <br>as it is the gateway between worlds. Talking about Skutt’s <br>painful existence will confuse her and could be a lever to <br>convince her to follow the Hunters’ advice. The Gallant <br>Knight, if persuaded back to his mission, could also be of <br>help in convincing Tuvstarr to trust the Hunters.<br> ◆ The Crown and the Dress: The Hunters will be able to <br>show Tuvstarr the crown that enchanted the fairies and <br>the dress that she gave to Hulder in order to make her <br>recall memories of the real world. The Princess will have a <br>vague memory of owning and trading them. Taking them <br>in her hand, she will recognize them. She will remember <br>the weight of the crown on her head and the warmth of <br>the dress’s fabric against her fingers. Wearing her items, <br>she will realize the difference between what is dream <br>and what is reality, and will begin to cry. At this point, <br>however, she will be even more strongly opposed to the <br>idea of returning to the real world.<br>Princess <br>Tuvstarr<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a pure and innocent soul, who just <br>wants a world without suffering.<br>Agenda: I want to stay forever in my perfect world. I <br>have been here for so long that I have forgotten what my <br>life was like before.<br>Gift – Creative Will:  Tuvstarr has the power to create <br>anything she wants in the Dream World. She can make a</p><p>193<br>bird appear out of nowhere or make an apple tree grow <br>from nothing to bearing fruit in a couple of seconds. She <br>can deflect a river, make sunlight warmer, shape clouds, <br>and make small fish glow around her when swimming in <br>a river. Each new creation draws life from the real world, <br>making it more corrupt and darker. Tuvstarr can use her <br>power to defend herself by literally manipulating the <br>whole world. If Tuvstarr is killed in this world, she will <br>transform into colorful butterflies to regenerate herself at <br>her castle. Although Tuvstarr has virtually infinite power, <br>her innocence means that even if threatened, she will never <br>try to kill a living being. Rather, the Princess will try to hurt <br>and scare any threats and, in the worst case, drive them <br>away.<br>Gift – Pure Innocence: Tuvstarr radiates innocence and <br>beauty. Whoever meets her will fall under her spell. She is <br>always friendly, and her voice is clear and beautiful, with <br>the sharpness of ice breaking on a winter pond. Those who <br>interact with Tuvstarr must make a Defense Check or be <br>fascinated by her. For the rest of the Scene, the bewitched <br>subject will not take any action that could harm Tuvstarr <br>and, furthermore, will defend her at the cost of their life <br>from any threats. Seeing how the world outside the pond <br>is rotting will make a bewitched subject instantly come to <br>their senses.<br>The other Skutt<br>Skutt is always near Tuvstarr and will appear as soon as <br>the Hunters encounter the Princess. For the Hunters it will <br>be clear that this is not the real Skutt, but another dream <br>created by Tuvstarr. Skutt follows the Princess and she rides <br>him through the kingdom. Since he is a dream, this Skutt <br>will have no recollection of the Hunters. In reality, a spark <br>of the original Skutt resides in his dream projection and <br>can be exploited by the Hunters to push him to remember <br>the real world.<br>Skutt the Moose<br>OL Hard 7 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a majestic and magnificent moose who <br>protects the sweet Princess Tuvstarr with all his might.<br>Agenda: Protect Tuvstarr from all threats and make her <br>happy / Listen to a small part of my soul that cries out that <br>this perfect world is just a wishful illusion.</p><p>194<br>A sad ending<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: “You take Tuvstarr back across <br>the pond as her Dream World dissolves. The sun returns to the <br>lands. The madness that has infested the animals is forgotten as <br>a passing nightmare. Skutt can finally let go, sighing in relief as <br>it is time to lay down his big head and forgive Tuvstarr for her <br>transgressions. Tuvstarr, after mourning the death of her dear <br>friend, returns to her parents’ arms filled with sadness. <br>An uncertain future awaits her. Perhaps she will become a wise <br>queen or maybe they will find her little body floating in a river, <br>drowned as she tries to return to a Dream World that no longer <br>exists. ”<br>“We have come to the end of this story. My thanks to all those <br>who have had the patience to listen to the words of this humble <br>storyteller. But even the most enchanting places cannot delight <br>when you are there against your will, and at this point I think <br>it is time to say goodbye to our protagonists, knowing that the <br>tragic story of Princess Tuvstarr has also touched their hearts. <br>But let the sadness at our parting be tempered by anticipation, <br>for our heroes will be caught in another story before too long.<br>With gratitude, Sherazade the Weaver of Tales. ”</p><p>195<br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the <br>Tuvstarr’s Reflection Scenario and can be acquired once <br>the requirements are met. A Hunter can only have one <br>Scenario Gift and if they acquire a new one, they will have <br>to forgo the previous one. Unlike with the normal rules, in <br>this case an Interlude it is not necessary to acquire the Gifts.<br>Hugin and Munin<br>Requirement: To meet Hugin and Munin and make a <br>pact with them.<br>Once per Scene, you can ask for advice from Hugin and <br>Munin. Ask the Storyteller a question, choosing from <br>among: “Where should I go?” “How can I defeat that <br>enemy?” “What is missing in my search?” The Storyteller <br>will answer with a cryptic sentence, which always includes <br>a useful hint. Get 1 Additional Success on all Defense <br>Checks against an attack from a non-human creature, <br>thanks to the blessing of Odin himself. At the beginning <br>of each Scene, you must spend 1 Soma to feed the spirits of <br>Hugin and Munin, or lose the use of this Gift for the rest of <br>the Scenario.<br>Lance of the Fallen Knight<br>Requirement: Collect the lance of the knight who died in <br>the search for Tuvstarr.<br>When you wield this spear and obtain an Outcome with <br>Increment on an attack, you can inflict 1 Additional <br>Wound. The tip of the lance can ignite at will, casting a light <br>and allowing you to have a burning fire always near at hand.</p>"},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513701120,"modifiedTime":1781513701120,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"tuvstarrs-reflection","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","pages":"183-196"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513701120,"modifiedTime":1781513701120,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"6MlUiwmscys0oYFj","name":"One Thousand and One Nightmares","pages":[{"_id":"e8eH1eC8qqnjI5BK","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>One Thousand and One Nightmares</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> Core Book</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, pages 197-202.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/one-thousand-and-one-nightmares-p197-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513702716,"modifiedTime":1781513702716,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"aTKTUzZKsDMtHlem","name":"Scenario Text","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>One Thousand and One Nightmares - Scenario Text</h2><p>196<br>One Thousand and <br>One Nightmares<br>A special Scenario inspired by One Thousand and One Nights<br>Safety Keywords: Mental manipulation / Malignant psychological manipulation</p><p>197<br>Once upon a <br>time…<br>A beautiful storyteller from the mysterious <br>East seduces all the courts in which she <br>performs, telling dark stories about a group <br>of Hunters of the Order. But where the story <br>ends, a real nightmare begins, as some of the <br>characters from the stories are brought to <br>life as monstrous shadows ready to steal the <br>souls of simple mortals...<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>One Thousand and One Nightmares is a special <br>Scenario that can be used during the course of any <br>Campaign or for a short game. In fact, once Sherazade is <br>introduced as an opponent, this Dark Presence will have <br>several ways of putting a spoke in the wheel of the Hunters. <br>After each interference, the Hunters will be able to collect <br>a clue as to the whereabouts of Sherazade and set out in <br>search of her to finally put an end to her work.<br> <br>How to use Sherazade<br>Sherazade can interfere in many ways during the adventures <br>of the Hunters.<br>Summoning the Shadow of an <br>enemy from the past<br>The Shadow is a unique opponent, a Dark Presence that <br>reminds the Hunters of an opponent they’ve already faced. <br>The Shadow sent by Sherazade will act in all respects as an <br>Opponent Dark Presence (in addition to all the normal <br>content of the chosen Scenario).<br>Shadow of Sherazade <br>(Opponent Dark Presence)<br>OL Medium 5 – (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: That of the original NPC.<br>Agenda: Interfering with and impeding the path of the <br>Hunters of the Order, preventing them from achieving their <br>mission.<br>Gift - Variable:  The Shadow has all the Gifts of the <br>original NPC. <br>Gift - Shadow Body:  A Shadow is a darker, sadder <br>version of the original. They can speak and behave like <br>the character they are modelled after, but on a careful <br>inspection they will appear cold and mechanical. Once per <br>Scene, a Shadow can appear or disappear from the darkness <br>by moving through walls and other solid obstacles. When <br>it spawns, it increases its OL by 1 because of the element</p><p>198<br>of surprise. When it suffers the Wound that would kill it, <br>the Shadow dissipates until its turn in the Exchange. At <br>that point, it will emerge from the darkness as if nothing <br>had happened. The Shadow will not reappear if the area <br>the Hunters are in is fully illuminated with light sources <br>or magic. The only way to truly destroy the Shadow is to <br>expose it to sunlight.<br>Telling a story starring the Hunters<br>Another way to involve the Hunters in the plots of <br>Sherazade is to have them awaken within a story she’s <br>telling. Tuvstarr’s Reflection on page 182 is a great example <br>of a Scenario involving Hunters in this way.<br>The Scenarios imposed by the stories of Sherazade must be <br>created in the classic way presented on page 91, but the <br>introduction must always be the following.<br>Once upon a <br>time…<br>Good evening my dear hosts, my name is Sherazade and I am <br>a weaver of tales. My words will take you to incredible worlds <br>and follow the feats of brave Hunters… however this story <br>is not like the others and these feats are not just imaginary. <br>Will our heroes succeed in their quest? Or will they perish, <br>disappearing forever from the memory of time?<br>The Scenarios brought into the game by Sherazade allow <br>you to create stories with more fantasy elements, and if you <br>wish, even stories disconnected from the context of Broken <br>Europe in which the Hunters normally move. In this way <br>it is possible to explore mythology or stories that are not <br>fairytale-related, focusing on the group of Hunters who, <br>experiencing Sherazade’s story as both audience-member <br>and Hunter, must solve the mystery to be able to awaken. <br>Through a Scenario told by Sherazade, it is also possible <br>to replay a Scenario already faced, adding a completely <br>different element and creating a “what-if ” version of what <br>the Hunters have already experienced. <br>Just think of a version of Red-Hood Iskra where Elizaveta <br>comes to Durfort to save her daughter Iskra, kidnapped by <br>the dangerous werewolf Gerard Dubois. Or an alternate <br>telling of The City of Pigs, where the three Browne brothers <br>have turned the whole city into a sect of The God Under the <br>Mine and are preparing the rite for his awakening, which <br>obviously consists of sacrificing old Bardolf Greed.<br>Defeating Sherazade<br>From the moment she comes into play, Sherazade should <br>become a constant presence in the adventures of the <br>Hunters, sending Shadows to get in their way or throwing <br>them in the middle of some absurd story. During the <br>Scenario, however, the Hunters must be able to deduce the <br>influence of Sherazade and find a clue to her location.<br>How Shadows release clues:<br> ◆ When it has an obvious advantage, the Shadow says <br>something like: “My Lady Sherazade will be proud of <br>m e .”<br> ◆ When defeated, the Shadow can exit the scene shouting, <br>“My Lady Sherazade will avenge me. ”<br> ◆ When defeated, alternatively, the Shadow can dissipate, <br>leaving behind a small object typical of the area where <br>Sherazade currently resides. This could be a coin, a <br>garment, or a poem. Collecting these items, it will be</p><p>199<br>clear to the Hunters that they serve as focus to animate <br>the Shadows and that, in fact, they all come from the <br>same area.<br>How the stories told by Sherazade <br>reveal clues:<br>At the end of each story, when the Scenario is solved, <br>the Hunters will see a short scene of Sherazade with her <br>audience entranced by what has just been told. The first <br>time, the Hunters will be able to understand the region of <br>Europe in which the Weaver of Tales is located; the second <br>time, Sherazade herself will turn towards them smiling, as <br>if to underline the mutual awareness of the bond that her <br>story has created.<br>How to deal with Sherazade<br>At some point, it will become clear to the Hunters that <br>Sherazade is a problem that needs to be <br>addressed. The journey to find her can develop <br>in several ways:<br> ◆ The Storyteller creates a Scenario to face <br>Sherazade. In the Scenario, the Weaver of <br>Tales will be protected by at least one of the <br>Main NPCs, fascinated by her Gift Words like <br>Honey.<br> ◆ The Storyteller adds Sherazade to one of <br>the unplayed Scenarios. In this case, she <br>will act as an Opponent Dark Presence <br>that will arrive at the site of the <br>investigation at the same time as <br>the Hunters. Sherazade will work <br>to ensure the Hunters’ failure, <br>thus proving their powerlessness.<br> ◆ The Hunters may find a way (using magic, with a <br>Treasure of the Order, etc.) to drag Sherazade into one <br>of the stories in which she has imprisoned them. In this <br>case, the Weaver of Tales will be forced to collaborate <br>with them so as not to remain a prisoner of what she <br>has created. At the end of the story, the Hunters will <br>meet once more with Sherazade, no longer allies, for <br>the final confrontation.<br>Sherazade in a Broken Tales <br>Campaign<br>Due to the recursive nature of her stories, Sherazade is a <br>great addition to any Broken Tales Campaign. In the list <br>of clues on page 246 there are also prompts to link her <br>to the story of the Child Savior and The One who Plots in <br>the Shadows. As written in her Agenda, Sherazade is not <br>a purely evil character, but more of a wounded soul who <br>has lost everything she cared about and who could even <br>become an ally of the Hunters.<br>Note: Sherazade is featured as a Hunter of the <br>Order in The Broken Ones expansion.</p><p>200<br>Sherazade  <br>the Weaver of Tales  <br>(Opponent Dark Presence)<br>Sherazade is a young storyteller who, together with her sister <br>Dinarzad, was captured and taken to the court of a wealthy Sultan. <br>The Sultan was a man with a dark soul who enjoyed inflicting <br>fear and pain on other people, and who invented trivial excuses <br>to torment poor innocents. The debauched, rich man decided to <br>play a game with Sherazade. Every night she had to tell him a <br>story. If he liked it, Dinarzad’s execution would be postponed for <br>a day. After thirty days of tales, the two sisters would earn their <br>freedom. Sherazade created a new story every night, always with <br>the threat of displeasing the Sultan and thus condemning her <br>beloved sister. But every evening, the Sultan was amazed by the <br>beauty of Sherazade’s tales and granted her another day. Thus <br>the fateful thirty days passed and on the morning of the thirty-<br>first, Sherazade was summoned by the Sultan. The man threw <br>himself at her feet, weeping, having had Dinarzad executed <br>the first night, certain of Sherazade’s failure and eager to <br>see her despair even should she succeed. But now, after <br>over thirty nights of beautiful stories, the Sultan’s heart was <br>filled with love and admiration for Sherazade. He wanted <br>her by his side as his bride. The Sultan offered Sherazade all <br>his wealth, power, and everything she might desire to forget <br>Dinarzad and her death. But Sherazade had her sister’s <br>smile etched in her mind as the last happy moment she could <br>recall, something not even the Sultan’s great wealth could erase. <br>And so all the stories told took shape, black shadows emerging <br>from the walls to seize the Sultan and hold him in terrible darkness</p><p>201<br>for eternity. Empty of any emotion, Sherazade wandered all <br>over the known world and finally met a tired and stooped <br>man, a writer who, like her, had seen every happy memory <br>destroyed by the selfishness of others. The two forged a bitter <br>alliance to bring new life into the stories now broken by the <br>wish of the Child Savior.<br>OL Medium 5 – (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a storyteller who can bring the characters <br>I invent to life. My charm is so beguiling that it cannot be <br>ignored.<br>Agenda: Punish all those who believe they can change the <br>world for the better / Find peace and smile once again.<br>Gift - Words like Honey:  Sherazade can tell one of <br>her stories to bring out a memory, an emotion, or a fear. <br>Highlight 1 Keyword from this brief story. If a Hunter or <br>NPC hears the story and is linked to the Keyword, the <br>related emotion will awaken, leading them to open up to <br>Sherazade and share something about themselves. <br>Gift - A Thousand and One Nights:  One of <br>the characters from a Scenario already faced <br>by the Hunters comes to life as a Shadow. <br>Create a Descriptor to represent it. The <br>Shadow thus created will be at the service <br>of Sherazade and will do whatever they <br>are ordered. Shadows cannot speak <br>nor act in places where there is more <br>light than shadow. During a Scene, <br>Sherazade can create a number of <br>Shadows equal to the Hunters she <br>is facing plus one. For each Hunter <br>who has been affected by Words like <br>Honey, Sherazade can summon an <br>additional Shadow.<br>The Shadows <br>The Shadows of Sherazade are but the dark reflection of <br>what they were in the story they come from.<br>See page 197.</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513702716,"modifiedTime":1781513702716,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"one-thousand-and-one-nightmares","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","pages":"197-202"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513702716,"modifiedTime":1781513702716,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"5OQLMRIovgRMeBUq","name":"The City of Pigs","pages":[{"_id":"eWBsAOeXhzYh9JKJ","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>The City of Pigs</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> Core Book</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, pages 203-216.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/city-of-pigs-p203-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513704002,"modifiedTime":1781513704002,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"3dWXv5UCfISvgEZW","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The City of Pigs - Setup</h2><p>202<br>The City of Pigs<br>Once upon a <br>time…<br>The busy town of Whitehaven is experiencing <br>a rebirth under the leadership of Bardolf <br>Greed. The rich industrialist has invested his <br>considerable fortune in the extraction of coal, <br>employing a large part of the population at the <br>large mine near the town. Soon, there came <br>inevitable accusations of exploitation and <br>starvation wages, giving rise to an anarchist <br>group called the Pig Heads, named for the <br>macabre masks with which they cover their faces. <br>With his success darkened by disappearances, <br>bloody sacrifices, and mysterious figures moving <br>in the night, Bardolf turned to the Order to shine <br>the light of hope to the streets of Whitehaven…<br>A Scenario inspired by The Three Little Pigs (Joseph Jacobs)<br>Safety Keywords: Body horror / Worker exploitation / Prostitution / Blasphemy</p><p>203<br>The story that led us here…<br>Bardolf Greed is a wealthy industrialist who made <br>his fortune thanks to shrewd deals and trade. Reaching the <br>ripe old age of seventy without an heir, Bardolf has decided <br>to dedicate his life to the only true, great love of his life: <br>money. Too old to travel, Bardolf has moved to Whitehaven, <br>an unremarkable town whose only resource was the <br>rich mines beneath the city. Within a few years, Bardolf <br>transformed Whitehaven into an industrial city by trapping <br>all its inhabitants into employment with starvation wages. <br>But not all of Whitehaven’s citizens were willing to give <br>in to the wealthy magnate. The brothers Clarence, Frank <br>and Arthur Browne have always cared for the community. <br>Arthur, in particular, worked for years to make Whitehaven <br>a quiet town where every resident could have a home and <br>a job to get by. Bardolf, however, has bought the town’s <br>favor, seizing property and leveling houses to build both <br>factories and dormitories for the now homeless workers. <br>By falsifying some official papers, Bardolf managed to <br>throw the three brothers out on the street, forcing them <br>to accept a job as miners or starve. Clarence soon quit, <br>choosing the life of a slacker over labor in the mines. Frank <br>and Arthur’s time in the mines was ended by a major mine <br>collapse, during which Frank lost an arm and a leg, and <br>Arthur was trapped by falling rubble and left for dead. The <br>collapse was caused by the awakening of The God Under <br>the Mine, a huge pig-like creature embedded in the rock <br>below the city. Alive and trapped underground, Arthur <br>found the God’s head and after days of agony he fed on <br>divine flesh, discovering that it confers incredible powers. <br>Crazed with grief and a wild hope that Arthur wasn’t dead, <br>Frank dug a long vertical tunnel, eventually managing to <br>create a communication channel with Arthur. United in <br>vengeance and endowed with the power of divine flesh, <br>the three brothers then began their personal war against <br>Bardolf Greed.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>Whitehaven is devastated by acts of violence and sabotage, <br>which have interfered with its industrial productivity <br>considerably. People are afraid to walk the streets because <br>a criminal gang, called the Pig Heads, goes around <br>kidnapping the most skilled and capable workers. From <br>under the Mine, Arthur leads the rebellion by passing <br>pieces of the quickly regenerating God’s flesh to Frank. <br>Frank has managed to get hired as a butcher at the big meat <br>factory in the city and secretly mixes the flesh of the God <br>with common meat, infecting the unsuspecting miners who <br>eat it. When the mutation begins to take effect, Clarence <br>approaches the targets, offering them the opportunity to <br>join the gang. Bardolf senses that the city is under threat <br>but does not imagine that his enemy is someone he already <br>hates: Arthur, left for dead after the accident. With over fifty <br>Pig Heads now working in the mines, Arthur counts the <br>days before he can launch his personal revolution.</p><p>204</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513704002,"modifiedTime":1781513704002,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"gVsGsdiL5hc7m69r","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The City of Pigs - Scene 1</h2><p>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  Our story starts with you <br>in conversation with the wealthy industrialist Bardolf Greed. <br>Mr. Greed is a man in his seventies, his face plump and <br>surrounded by thick, lupine sideburns, while a pair of shrewd <br>eyes peek out over small round glasses. Bardolf ’s mansion is a <br>perfect example of the changes that big industries are bringing <br>to Europe and the rich magnate has spared no expense, nor <br>has he spared the wretched workers whose sweat built it. <br>With a bottle of fine wine near at hand, Bardolf fumbles with <br>his box of tobacco. Behind him stands a dozen men from his <br>personal guard, making it clear that the wealthy industrialist <br>does not feel safe at all...<br>Place: The dining room of Greed’s palace. Paintings and <br>cutlery with gold lining highlight Bardolf ’s great wealth. <br>Greed’s personal guards stand with their backs to the wall, <br>staring at the guests like silent statues.<br>Time: It is early afternoon. Visible through the window is a <br>sky gray with rain and fumes from the factories, which are <br>constantly active.<br>Initial Situation: Bardolf calmly explains the situation to <br>the Hunters, while the trusty William records everything in <br>a large black leather book.<br>Information: The following information / clues can be <br>obtained from the interview with Bardolf.<br> ◆ A gang of criminals wanders through the backways of <br>the city. They kidnap or injure only the factory workers <br>to make them unable to work. Nobody recognizes <br>them, because they hide their faces under grotesque <br>pig masks.<br> ◆ The city had been given new life thanks to Bardolf ’s <br>investments. Only one family (the Brownes) strongly <br>opposed the birth of the Factories, but in the end, they <br>too became Greed’s employees.<br> ◆ The mine works at full capacity under the watchful <br>control of Edward Right, an honest and dutiful man. <br>The textile factories also operate constantly, as does the <br>large slaughterhouse run by Frank Browne.<br> ◆ For Greed, productivity is everything. If forced to <br>choose, Hunters should put the preservation of property <br>and machinery before the lives of the townspeople.<br>1</p><p>205<br>Greed’s Mansion <br>Descriptor: A small castle in the center of Whitehaven. The <br>pomp of each room underlines Greed’s incredible wealth.<br>Bardolf Greed <br>the Wealthy Industrialist<br>OL Hard 7 – Main NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a wealthy and skilled businessman who <br>always knows how to find a good deal, the one that turns a <br>profit for me. My body is old, but my mind remains infallible.<br>Agenda: Own every business and aspect of trade in <br>Whitehaven, so that the whole city is under my total control.<br>Gift - Smell the deal:  Bardolf is a master of negotiation <br>and reading others. After talking to a subject, Bardolf <br>can obtain one of the following pieces of information:  <br>1. Discover a secret regarding the person he is speaking <br>with; 2. Obtain an object or piece of information valuable <br>to the other party in the negotiation, and which he can use <br>as leverage. A Hunter can make a Defense Check to prevent <br>Bardolf from using this Gift on them.<br>William the Man of Law<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a prominent lawyer and I know all of <br>Bardolf ’s secrets. I manage the accounts of both the Factories <br>and mine with zealous attention.<br>Bardolf’s personal <br>guard<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are long-time mercenaries, paid hand-<br>somely by Bardolf for our loyalty.</p><p>206<br>The Factories<br>Descriptor: A series of shoddy, stone buildings used as textile factories and <br>foundries. Access is forbidden to outsiders.<br>If the Hunters talk to some workers, they can get the following information. <br>Roll a die or pick from the list:<br>1-2: Everyone aspires to work at the slaughterhouse where the shifts are less <br>pressing, but the unpleasant Frank Browne selects the staff. Frank ignores even <br>the most piteous plea and no one understands how he chooses who can work <br>alongside him.<br>3-4: Just outside the city there is an apple orchard that once employed many <br>inhabitants of Whitehaven. Now it is just a place where slackers like Clarence <br>Browne, as well as those who are unable to work in the factories or in the mine, <br>take refuge.<br>5-6: Not long ago, there was a collapse in the mines that injured or killed many <br>miners. Arthur Browne, a prominent citizen who did much for the city before <br>Greed’s arrival, was one of the victims.<br>Whitehaven<br>Descriptor: An industrial city growing around a large coal mine. The noise and <br>fumes from the factories fill the air at every hour of the day, while groups of workers <br>go back and forth waiting for their shift.<br>When the Hunters roam the city, roll 1 die.<br>1-2: They meet Clarence, who will try to pump the Hunters for information by <br>pretending to be well connected.<br>3-4: They meet Emma, who offers her services and is curious to talk to foreigners.<br>5-6: A group of Pig Heads equal to double the number of Hunters set up an <br>ambush.</p><p>207<br>The Pig Heads<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are a band of revolutionaries in the service <br>of the three brothers. The God’s flesh gives us power and fills <br>us with the anger we need to wage our war.<br>Gift – Pigs’ Gang:  When they act, each member of the <br>gang changes to become stronger. Their head becomes <br>that of a pig and only another Pig Head will be able to <br>communicate with them. Their mutation grants a random <br>power, roll 1 die. 1. Strength, able to inflict 1 additional <br>Wound once per Scene; 2. Speed , once per Scene acts <br>2 times consecutively; 3. Resistance , +1 Wound;  <br>4. Abomination , +1 to Opposition Level; 5. Grunt , <br>once per Scene can emit a loud squeal, enemies who hear it <br>receive 1 Penalty on their next action; 6. Out of control , <br>the OL rises to Hard 7 but, at the end of their action, the <br>NPC explodes into a cloud of flesh and blood.<br>Martha Browne the Mother<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am the mother of three brothers, and I am <br>so old that I have almost completely lost my sight. My son <br>Frank takes care of me, but he doesn’t tell me anything. I <br>am convinced that Arthur is not dead, for my instinct as a <br>mother tells me so.<br>Emma the Childhood Friend<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a childhood friend of Clarence and have <br>a special relationship with him. He has always promised that <br>he will take me away from this place, but I know that he will <br>never abandon his brothers. I understand that he has a big <br>secret, but tries to protect me by keeping me in the dark.<br>The Orchard<br>Descriptor: A large apple orchard which, before the arrival <br>of the factories, was one of the main sources of work in the <br>city. Now, however, it is abandoned and represents a home for <br>all those who cannot get a job.<br>When the Hunters roam the orchard, roll 1 die, or present <br>the encounters in sequence.<br>1-2 The orchard: The trees have been neglected and on <br>the ground there are still abandoned tools and baskets for <br>harvesting apples. A sign next to a tool shed reads “Gift  <br>courtesy of the Browne family” .<br>3-4 Clarence’s shack: A rickety rundown house with a <br>thatched roof. Inside, it is possible to find a rusty key that <br>says “slaughterhouse” and a sketched map of the mines that <br>says “well” . Around the hut there are always 1d6 + 2 Pig <br>Heads.<br>5-6 Clarence:  The youngest of the Browne brothers is <br>lying on the ground, visibly drunk, under an apple tree. <br>Clarence always pretends to be drunk with strangers to take <br>them off guard.</p><p>208<br>Clarence Browne the <br>Younger Brother<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am the youngest of the Pig Heads and, despite <br>believing in our fight, I am not going to waste much time on <br>it. From hanging around, I know Whitehaven like the back <br>of my hand.<br>Agenda: Having fun and lazing around all day, carrying on <br>the Pig Head’s cause in my spare time.<br>Gift - Slacker:  Clarence is a master of the art of <br>disappearing when things get tough. In the presence of <br>even a small crowd, Clarence can leave a Scene when it <br>is his turn to act, without anything or anyone being able <br>to stop him. When using this Gift, Clarence hides in the <br>orchard, passing the entire following Scene there. <br>Gift - Gang Leader:  Eating the flesh of The God Under <br>the Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform <br>into monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can <br>mutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound <br>once they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will <br>revive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a <br>second time during the Exchange, even consecutively;  <br>3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for <br>a single action where they can harness their superhuman <br>strength.<br>The <br>Slaughterhouse<br>Descriptor: A huge gray building inside which cattle from <br>coastal pastures are slaughtered. Entry is forbidden to non-<br>workers.<br>When the Hunters wander around the slaughterhouse, roll <br>1 die to see how far they go without attracting attention, or <br>present the environments in sequence.<br>1-2 The outdoor garden:  It is more an open-air barn <br>than a garden patch. Bloodstains and excrement suggest <br>that the slaughter starts here. Several signs reading “No <br>Trespassing” suggest that the area is very controlled.<br>3-4 The slaughterhouse: Composed of a series of large <br>spaces, several stairs lead to underground chambers where <br>the meat is preserved. Around ten workers are present day <br>and night, all members of the Pig Heads.<br>5-6 The salting room: A small room at the back of the <br>building, where Frank prepares the meat that will be served <br>in the cafeterias throughout the city. During the day Frank <br>is always present, intent on hiding the flesh of the God <br>within freshly butchered beef.</p><p>209<br>Frank Browne the Middle <br>Brother<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am the middleman of the Pig Heads and act <br>as the strongarm of the gang. I have control over all cultists, <br>and the power of The God Under the Mine has given me <br>strength and endurance equal to that of five men.<br>Agenda: Take revenge on Bardolf for what he did to me and <br>find a remedy for the wounds that have marred me since the <br>day of the accident / Mix the flesh of The God Under the Mine <br>with beef from the slaughterhouse and feed it to the miners to <br>add to the ranks of the gang.<br>Gift - The Pincer:  Frank replaced his left arm with a <br>home-made mechanical arm with many functions. During <br>a Scene, Frank can use each of the following one time:  <br>1. Crush, a hit with the pincer inflicts 1 additional Wound; <br>2. Pulley, the pincer can launch from the arm and raise <br>or lower Frank about thirty feet. Frank can carry 2 other <br>subjects with him. <br>Gift - Gang Leader:  Eating the flesh of The God Under <br>the Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform <br>into monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can <br>mutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound <br>once they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will <br>revive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act a <br>second time during the Exchange, even consecutively; 3. <br>Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for a <br>single action where they can harness their superhuman <br>strength.<br>The Mine<br>Descriptor: A gigantic coal mine where miners work day <br>and night. Many areas are abandoned in favor of more <br>profitable veins. <br>Gift - Maze of Galleries: Whitehaven’s Mine is gigantic <br>and without a guide it’s not easy to get to a specific location. <br>With each exploration roll, you can get 1 or more Map <br>Tokens which represent progress in learning the layout of <br>the mine. Upon reaching 3 Map Tokens, you can go directly <br>to the Special result.<br>When the Hunters explore the mine, roll 1 die or choose <br>directly based on the narrative.<br>1-2 Work zone A:  Threading through the tunnels, <br>deafened by the sound of steam engines and digging, the <br>Hunters encounter a group of miners (2d6 + 6 Minor <br>NPCs). If the Hunters do something weird, one of the <br>workers will alert Edward. Exploration will yield 1 Map <br>Token.<br>3-4 Work zone B:  Threading through the tunnels, <br>deafened by the sound of steam engines and digging, the <br>Hunters encounter a group of miners (2d6 + 6 Minor <br>NPCs). If the Hunters do something weird, 1d6 + 6 miners <br>will reveal themselves as Pig Heads and attack. Exploration <br>will yield 2 Map Tokens.<br>5-6 Abandoned lodging: In an area close to the collapse, <br>recent traces of passage can be found. The Hunters meet <br>Frank and 5 Pig Heads who are going to the well to meet up <br>with Arthur. Exploration will yield 2 Map Tokens.<br>Special (3 Map Tokens):  By moving a heavy stone, <br>the Hunters will find the mouth of the well that leads to <br>Arthur’s chamber. The shaft is narrow and thirty feet deep,</p><p>210<br>but with a little attention a person can descend it. Climbing <br>down the pit can alert Arthur (see the Cave of The God <br>Under the Mine location on page 210).<br>Edward the Miners’ Chief<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a long-time friend of Arthur and mourn <br>his death. Everyone in the mine does what I say, and I hate <br>foreigners who want to poke their nose into my work. I allow <br>Frank into the mine often to visit the place where Arthur died.<br>The Cave of the <br>God Under the <br>Mine<br>Descriptor: A large natural cave, which Arthur has made <br>into a home. You can enter only by descending from a narrow <br>well. In the north wall, the enormous pig head of the God <br>gasps and groans as it waits to wake up.<br>Gift - Arthur’s House: The mastermind behind the Pig <br>Heads worked hard to make the Cave an intruder-proof <br>haven. If someone drops from the well, Arthur will be <br>alerted (a Position Check can avoid this). At the bottom of <br>the well is a large tub that Arthur can fill with boiling water. <br>Whoever arrives through the well suffers 1 Wound if they <br>have no way of avoiding the hot water. Inside the room, <br>Arthur can turn the lights on and off thanks to a system <br>he has invented, throwing the chamber into either light or <br>darkness. While intruders wander blindly, Arthur can use <br>his knowledge of the place to move freely.</p><p>211<br>Arthur Browne the Big <br>Brother<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am the eldest of the Pig Heads and act as <br>the mastermind of the gang. Living in my natural prison has <br>taught me how to see even in total darkness.<br>Agenda: Take revenge on Bardolf for corrupting everything <br>I built in Whitehaven and regain control of the city / <br>Transforming all the inhabitants of Whitehaven into Pig <br>Heads.<br>Gift - The Flesh of The God Under the Mine:  Arthur <br>can tear pieces of flesh from the God’s head to harness its <br>powers. When he spends an action, the piece becomes <br>a Spawn of the God and begins to grow disgustingly, <br>engaging all nearby enemies. Arthur can tear one piece of <br>meat off per action, up to a maximum of 3.<br>Gift - Gang Leader:  Eating the flesh of The God Under <br>the Mine gives the Browne brothers the ability to transform <br>into monstrous beings. Once per Scene, the NPC can <br>mutate, gaining the following benefits: 1. Recover a Wound <br>once they reach 0. Though apparently dead, the NPC will <br>revive within minutes of falling; 2. Once per Scene, act <br>a second time during the Exchange, even consecutively;  <br>3. Once per Scene, increase the Opposition Level by 2 for <br>a single action where they can harness their superhuman <br>strength.<br>The God Under <br>the Mine<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (6 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a creature as old as the world, trapped <br>beneath the bedrock. Millennia of inactivity have made me <br>catatonic and there is nothing that can really wake me up. <br>Only pain can stir me even slightly.<br>Gift - The Head of the God:  Only the enormous head of <br>the God emerges from the rock, and pieces of meat can be <br>obtained from it. When he suffers 1 Wound, the God emits <br>a loud grunt that sends everyone flying (a Defense Check <br>can avoid this). As an additional effect of the grunt, the <br>God’s fetid breath taints the air, granting 1 Penalty to the <br>next action of all affected subjects, excluding Arthur. When <br>reduced to 0 Wounds, the God falls into a deep sleep to <br>fully regenerate in the following Scene.<br>Spawn of The God Under the <br>Mine<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: An abomination of flesh and tentacles, obeying <br>Arthur’s will.<br>Gift – Flesh Abomination:  A Spawn can perform its <br>action with a flesh tentacle up to a range of 6 feet, and at the <br>end of each Exchange it will grow as indicated in the table. <br>If not engaged in a conflict, the Spawn will grow 1 step per</p><p>212<br>Scene. When the Spawn acts, roll 1 die: from 1 to 5 it will <br>rage against one of Arthur’s enemies chosen at random. On <br>a 6, it will act against an ally or Arthur himself. If the Spawn <br>has more actions, roll the die for each single action.<br>Step Wounds Actions OL Special<br>1 +1 / +1 Range of 12 feet.<br>2 / +1 +1 If a target fails a Defense Check, in addition to suffering 1 Wound it will <br>be dragged towards the Spawn or thrown away.<br>3 +1 / +1 Mass growth to a size of 18 cubic feet.<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario, there are eight Events. As a Storyteller, feel <br>free to create new ones in response to the actions of the <br>Hunters.<br>If the supply of infected meat is not stopped:  after <br>two days from the arrival of the Hunters the Pig Heads will <br>number over one hundred and Arthur will give the order <br>to attack the city.<br>If the Hunters discover that Arthur is still alive:  <br>Bardolf will give full access to the mine and its maps. With <br>them, it will be possible to calculate the exact location of <br>The God Under the Mine.<br>If the Hunters make their way to the mine and <br>Clarence or Frank know about it:   Frank will set up <br>a defense with a dozen Pig Heads, and Arthur will help his <br>brother, passing him pieces of meat to create several Spawn <br>of the God.<br>After Arthur creates the third Spawn in the same <br>Scene: The God Under the Mine goes mad with pain <br>and tries to move, causing a new earthquake. The mine <br>collapses, overwhelming everyone inside, though the <br>Hunters may find a quick way to escape.<br>If the Hunters talk to Bardolf about the three <br>brothers and express any doubts about them:  the <br>shrewd moneymaker will ask for time, and after 1 Scene he <br>will bring to the Hunters either Emma, Edward, or Martha.<br>If the Hunters commit to more than one Scenes <br>outside the city:  Clarence will attempt to assassinate <br>Bardolf in his palace, but will fail and end up on the run, <br>chased by the guards after being injured. Bardolf will</p><p>1<br>213<br>call the Hunters in to report, describing a Pig Head who <br>was acting alone and who is now wounded and therefore <br>recognizable.<br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the The City <br>of Pigs Scenario and can be acquired once the requirements <br>are met. A Hunter can only have one Scenario Gift and if <br>they acquire a new one, they will have to forgo the previous <br>one.<br>The Meat of The God Under the Mine<br>Requirement: Obtain a piece of the flesh of the God at the <br>slaughterhouse or defeat a Spawn.<br>Y ou can consume the flesh of the God to temporarily gain <br>power. Once per Scene, you can heal 1 Wound and gain <br>1 Additional Success for all physical actions you take. Y ou <br>have to wait an entire Scene for the remaining flesh to <br>regenerate. If you use this Gift in 2 consecutive Scenes, the <br>flesh is consumed and you won’t be able to use it anymore.<br>The Brand of Greed<br>Requirement: To gain the trust and respect of Bardolf <br>Greed.<br>Bardolf trusts only those who demonstrate cunning and <br>ability, granting such people a special pass called The Brand <br>of Greed. With the Brand you get free access to any place in <br>the city, without the person in charge being able to object to <br>your entrance. Get 1 Additional Success when you exploit <br>the Mark’s importance against a city dweller.<br>There Is No House That Can Stop <br>Me (Special Gift for Garou the Old <br>Wolf)<br>Requirement: Clash with one of the brothers who has <br>made use of the Leader of the Gang of Pigs Gift.<br>Those damned pigs get on your nerves and you can’t stand <br>them running away from your wrath. Y ou get 2 Additional <br>Successes when you take action to destroy or overcome an <br>environmental obstacle that stands between you and one <br>of the three Pigs at the head of the gang. Y ou hate to lose <br>to them. If you have to leave or flee from a place without <br>eliminating them, you lose 1 Soma.<br>The Scenario The <br>City of Pigs in <br>Scenes</p><p>FIRST SCENE –  The interview <br>with Bardolf Greed<br>It’s the same one you find on page 204.<br>End of Scene:  Bardolf asks the Hunters to gather <br>information in the city and its factories, go to the SECOND <br>SCENE - Visit to the city.</p><p>2<br>3a<br>3b<br>214</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513704004,"modifiedTime":1781513704004,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"bwDHSDOXIJbWlsAj","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The City of Pigs - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE – Visit to the city<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: Whitehaven is the ultimate <br>representation of what intellectuals in drawing rooms call <br>the “industrial revolution. ” The small brick houses fade <br>in the presence of the large factories which, in a few years, <br>have completely changed the appearance of what was once <br>little more than a peasant village. Busy workers run like <br>industrious ants,    among them old people and children. <br>Whitehaven no longer has anything to offer to those unable <br>to work.<br>Place: The alleys of the city of Whitehaven, amongst <br>workers and people who live for the day.<br>Time: It is late afternoon, and a faint rain begins to fall. In <br>just over an hour, night will fall.<br>Information: Between the back alleys of the city and <br>the factory workers, the Hunters receive all 3 pieces of <br>information found at the factories location (page 206). <br>After gathering these, it will be dark, and a group of Pig <br>Heads equal to twice the number of Hunters will ambush <br>them. Once the fight is resolved, the Hunters will see that <br>one of the attackers is wearing a butcher’s coat and another <br>is dressed as a beggar.<br>End of Scene:  The Hunters can decide to investigate <br>the slaughterhouse (THIRD SCENE OPTION A - The <br>Slaughterhouse) or the orchard (THIRD SCENE OPTION <br>B - The Orchard).</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513704004,"modifiedTime":1781513704004,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"2v9KkmRC9M0iHQ3M","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The City of Pigs - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION A – <br>The Slaughterhouse<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  The city’s slaughterhouse is <br>perhaps one of the largest buildings the Hunters have ever <br>seen, and from the smell of blood that saturates the air it <br>seems that it works at full capacity day and night. A rusty, old <br>gate is all that separates you from the main door, but the bars <br>on the windows and the many “No Trespassing” signs suggest <br>that it is not a place where outsiders are welcome.<br>Place: The great slaughterhouse of Whitehaven.<br>Time: It is now night even if, from the lights in the <br>windows, the slaughterhouse does not seem to have ceased <br>its activities.<br>Information: The Hunters explore the place following <br>the list in ascending order (page 208). Once they arrive at <br>the salting room, they will find Frank intent on mixing the <br>flesh of the God with the meat for the miners’ meals. Frank <br>will fight to the death. Having knocked out the middle <br>brother, and upon searching the room, the Hunters will <br>find the flesh of the God and a map representing a specific <br>area of the mine. <br>End of Scene: Hunters can also go to the orchard (THIRD <br>SCENE OPTION B - The Orchard ) or go to the mine, <br>where it is clear that something is happening to the miners <br>(FOURTH SCENE - The Mine).</p><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION B – <br>The Orchard<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You walk for about ten <br>minutes before you reach a large apple orchard, clearly <br>abandoned. Old wooden sheds and rusty tools left out in the <br>rain confirm your suspicions. Among the shadows you can <br>see the silhouettes of the beggars and other poor people who <br>rest in the only place in the city where money is not required <br>to live.</p><p>4<br>5<br>215<br>Place: The orchard, a few minutes’ walk from Whitehaven.<br>Time: It is night and has stopped raining. A timid full <br>moon appears among the open clouds.<br>Information: Clarence will approach the Hunters <br>trying to figure out who they are and, once he realizes <br>that they pose a danger to the gang, will seek to mislead <br>them. He will attempt to highlight Greed’s shady business <br>and that his loyal lawyer William has all the evidence of <br>the industrialist’s illicit trafficking. If cornered, Clarence <br>will fight with the support of the Pig Heads, but not to the <br>death. Clarence will reveal everything that happens at the <br>mine if that can save his life. In his shack, it is possible to <br>find a map of the mine with a mark on a specific point.<br>End of Scene: Hunters can also go to the slaughterhouse <br>(THIRD SCENE OPTION A - The Slaughterhouse) or go to <br>the mine, where it is clear that something is happening to <br>the miners (FOURTH SCENE - The Mine).</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513704004,"modifiedTime":1781513704004,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"wwol2I3NgCliGf1q","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The City of Pigs - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE – The Mine<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  When you arrive at the <br>mine, you avoid the main entrance and, following the map, <br>you come to a played-out vein of coal. Following the railroad <br>tracks, now in disuse, you enter the darkness.<br>Place: The abandoned area of the Whitehaven Mine.<br>Time: It is night and the mine is completely dark.<br>Information: The Hunters will find Frank or Clarence <br>(determined by which location they haven’t visited yet) <br>heading for a meeting with Arthur. If both brothers have <br>been eliminated, old Martha will be the one to visit her son. <br>If not discovered, the Hunters will see the family member <br>receive a piece of meat by pulling it up from the well. If the <br>Hunters somehow reveal themselves, the <br>threatened family member will activate <br>the power of the God’s flesh to create a <br>Spawn.<br>End of Scene:  The Hunters have <br>discovered Arthur’s hideout, go to the</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513704004,"modifiedTime":1781513704004,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"wegha8qPfUgmVxz7","name":"Scene 5","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The City of Pigs - Scene 5</h2><p>FIFTH SCENE - The God Under the <br>Mine.</p><p>FIFTH SCENE – The <br>God Under the Mine<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  From the <br>narrow well you see a light and hear a man <br>talking to himself. A long, low, prolonged moan <br>seems to come from who-knows-what strange <br>creature.<br>Place: The cave where Arthur is trapped.<br>Time: The time of reckoning.<br>End of Scene:  At this point, it will be up to the <br>Hunters to decide which path to take, but it will soon <br>become clear to them that Arthur is now insane and <br>cannot control his obsession with Bardolf Greed’s ruin. <br>If the Hunters waste too much time Frank, Clarence, or <br>other Pig Heads could arrive, depending on how much of <br>a challenge you want.</p>"},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513704004,"modifiedTime":1781513704004,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"city-of-pigs","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","pages":"203-216"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513704004,"modifiedTime":1781513704004,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"MpXJbYfhOqnvRVQn","name":"Saint George the Dragon Slayer","pages":[{"_id":"wLz47TsXAeaacBaq","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>Saint George the Dragon Slayer</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> Core Book</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, pages 217-222.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/saint-george-the-dragon-slayer-p217-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513705067,"modifiedTime":1781513705067,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Zflh32cmbfAXDTxE","name":"Scenario Text","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Saint George the Dragon Slayer - Scenario Text</h2><p>216<br>Saint George <br>the Dragon Slayer<br>A special Scenario inspired by St. George <br>and the Dragon<br>Safety Keywords: Religious zeal / Persecution</p><p>217<br>Once upon a <br>time…<br>There was a brave and devoted fighter who <br>made the fight against monsters his reason <br>for living. Saint George is perhaps the most <br>important and powerful member of the <br>Order, but his zeal in punishing the Broken <br>Tales can be a threat to the Hunters too... <br>Perhaps the real enemy does not hide in the <br>shadows, but walks beside them...<br>The story that led us here…<br>Saint George the Dragon Slayer is a special Scenario <br>that can be used during any Campaign or for a short game. <br>In fact, once Saint George has been included as a support to <br>the Hunters, he will have several methods of foiling plans, <br>whether laid by friends or foes. Saint George will fight <br>alongside the Hunters, but his stern gaze and inquisitorial <br>spirit must be kept at bay so that the Saint does not unleash <br>the fury of the Church against its own agents.<br>How to use Saint George<br>Saint George will join the group of Hunters as soon as they <br>have solved a few Scenarios and earned a bit of fame. As an <br>Ally Dark Presence, Saint George will support the Hunters <br>on their travels. However, it will soon become clear that <br>his zeal for everything Broken Tales-related will make him <br>difficult to manage. <br>Saint George possesses a Gift called The Judgment of <br>the Saint. When enough Suspicion Tokens have been <br>accumulated, the Saint will become an Opponent Dark <br>Presence and will try to arrest the Hunters as he sees them <br>as representing the darkness that the Church fights.<br>Saint George  <br>(Ally Dark Presence)<br>Once upon a time there was a cheerful child named George <br>who often wandered away from home to run and play in the <br>woods. One day, George fell into the river and in the blink <br>of an eye, he was drowning. On the verge of death, the child <br>felt an incredible force pushing him to the surface and soon <br>found himself on the bank of the river, soaked to the bones <br>but still alive. His savior was a strange, lizard-like creature <br>with incredibly human eyes. A Dragon! thought the child, <br>throwing himself on the creature’s neck, and a deep friendship <br>was born between the two. In the following years, George <br>took every opportunity to meet his secret friend and learn <br>from him the wonders of magic, and what is hidden from <br>the eyes of ordinary people. Then, a plague struck the village <br>where George lived, killing his parents. The lad’s appeals for <br>the Dragon’s help fell on deaf ears, despite the creature being</p><p>218<br>capable of healing any disease. The Dragon, out of fear of being discovered <br>and killed, refused to heal the people of the village. Twenty years passed <br>and George took his vows, becoming a Holy fighter in the service of the <br>Papacy. He led more than one battle against the forces of evil. When the <br>Saint returned to his old village, he walked into the forest in search of <br>his old friend. The Dragon was happy to see George again after such <br>a long time and came out... only to realize that he had come before his <br>executioner.<br>OL Medium 5 – (4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a Holy knight in the service of the Church. I am skilled <br>at hunting and defeating any monster. Nothing escapes my inquisitive gaze.<br>Agenda: Find every creature linked to the Broken Tales and exterminate <br>them so that they can do no harm / Truly understand the nature of the Broken <br>Tales.<br>Gift - The Holy Dragon Slayer:  Saint George starts the Scenario with 1 Fervor <br>Token. When facing an enemy that is visibly monstrous, he can spend 1 Fervor Token <br>to allow an allied Hunter to inflict 1 additional Wound. When such an enemy unveils one <br>of their Gifts, Saint George can spend 1 Fervor Token to grant 2 Additional Successes on <br>a Defense Check to any allied Hunter. Whenever he suffers 1 Wound, Saint George <br>receives 1 Fervor Token.<br>Gift - The Judgment of the Saint:  Saint George keeps everyone under <br>observation, even the Hunters he accompanies. During a Scene, if a Hunter <br>activates their Dark Ego or uses any Gift that allows them to employ <br>magic or terrorize ordinary people in the presence of Saint George, add <br>1 Suspicion Token on this Gift. During a Scene, Saint George can keep a <br>Hunter under observation, making them uncomfortable. When <br>he does, the Storyteller may spend 1 Suspicion Token to <br>impose 1 Penalty to a Hunter Check. Suspicion Tokens <br>carry over from one Scenario to another. When there <br>are Suspicion Tokens equal to twice the number of <br>Hunters, Saint George engages in a Witch Hunt <br>and becomes an Opponent Dark Presence.</p><p>219<br>How to manage Saint George<br>Once introduced in the Campaign or in the single Scenario, <br>Saint George will be a recurring presence to whom the <br>Hunters must be accountable. As the highest representative <br>of the Papacy, the Saint has full authority over all members <br>of the Order.<br>For the Hunters, it will be clear that Saint George could be <br>a good ally, but that under his stern gaze not everything is <br>permitted.<br> ◆ The Storyteller can add Saint George to the party <br>throughout the Scenario. Even if he has the authority <br>to make all the decisions, it wouldn’t be fun to play the <br>Session with an NPC leading the Hunters by a leash. The <br>Saint will therefore remain in the background, curious <br>to observe the Hunters and their work as members of <br>the Order. The Storyteller must immediately make it <br>clear that the Saint is at their disposal with his Gifts, <br>but that The Judgment of the Saint can quickly turn <br>him into an enemy.<br> ◆ The Storyteller can add Saint George to the party, <br>but the Saint will act independently and appear <br>only in some Scenes. In this way, the Saint will apply <br>more pressure on the Hunters, judging behaviors that <br>he considers unbecoming for a member of the Order. <br>He will always give support with his Gifts, but the <br>Storyteller will be able to use him more as a nuisance <br>than anything else.<br> ◆ The Storyteller will only let Saint George step in <br>when it is clear that a monstrous creature is featured <br>in the Scenario. For example, in Red-Hood Iskra he <br>could come after the appearance of Greskar (page <br>125) or due to the presence of The Ancient Enemy <br>as a Dark Presence (page 49). Saint George will <br>arrive driven by a premonition that there is a monster <br>to hunt down and smite. The Saint will be open and <br>supportive towards the Hunters, at least until he has <br>accumulated the first Suspicion Token. This is a good <br>way to introduce Saint George to a Campaign for the <br>first time.<br> ◆ Once the Suspicion Tokens accrued are twice the <br>number of Hunters, Saint George will launch a <br>Witch Hunt, and will become an Opponent Dark <br>Presence with the corresponding profile. From that <br>moment on, like any Opponent, the Storyteller will be <br>able to use him to impede the Hunters and to create a <br>special Scenario leading to the final confrontation with <br>Saint George.<br>Saint George <br>(Opponent Dark Presence)<br>The Holy Fighter who eradicates darkness in all its forms. <br>There are skilled Paladins in his service, ready to carry out <br>his every command.<br>OL Medium 5 – (4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a devout knight in the service of <br>the Church. I am adept at hunting and capturing any <br>manifestation of darkness. I know every Hunter in the Order <br>and I know how to defeat them.<br>Agenda: Find the Hunters who have shown to be linked to <br>the Broken Tales and lock them up in the Church’s prisons. <br>Whoever opposes my sentence will perish, suffering the <br>judgment of God himself.</p><p>220<br>Gift - Witch Hunt:  When he becomes an Opponent <br>Dark Presence, Saint George acquires a number of Fervor <br>Tokens equal to the number of Hunters. When facing a <br>Hunter he’s been tracking down, he can spend 1 Fervor <br>Token to inflict 1 additional Wound on top of the normal <br>one, or just 1 Wound if the Hunter succeeds on their <br>Defense Check. The only way to avoid this Wound is to <br>have an Outcome with Increment and spend it to nullify <br>the Gift’s effect. Saint George can spend 1 Fervor Token to <br>transform any Position Check’s result for an action against <br>him into a Failure so long as the Hunter performing it has <br>at least one Descriptor related to magic or a monstrous <br>characteristic.    Saint George regenerates Fervor Tokens <br>equal to the number of Hunters at the beginning of each <br>Scenario.<br>Gift - The Judgment of the Saint: Saint George keeps <br>everyone under observation, even when hunting down <br>Hunters. During a Scene, if a Hunter activates their Dark <br>Ego to perform a good deed or uses any Gift that allows <br>them to use magic or manipulate ordinary people to do <br>a good deed in the presence of Saint George, he adds 1 <br>Judgment Token on this Gift. Judgment Tokens carry over <br>from one Scenario to the next. When a number of Judgment <br>Tokens equal to the number of Hunters are staked on this <br>Gift, Saint George will make amends, declaring that he was <br>wrong in his judgment, putting an end to the Witch Hunt.<br>Paladins of the Church<br>A group of faithful Paladins in the service of Saint George.<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a Paladin in the service of the great Saint <br>George himself and his word, for me, is law. Years of training <br>have made me adept at fighting the Broken Tales.<br>Note: Each Paladin has a different Downside, indicated in <br>the Paladin Gift.<br>Gift - Paladins: Each Paladin has a name and a dedicated <br>Gift, and a Downside to add to the standard Descriptor. <br>The Storyteller rolls 1 die to decide which Paladin follows <br>Saint George in the Witch Hunt. Saint Geoge has a number <br>of Paladins equal to that of the Hunters he hunts.</p><p>221<br>Roll First Name Downside Paladin Gift<br>1<br>Trebizond, the <br>princess of a <br>Distant Country.<br>Sometimes, I am seized <br>by an unshakeable <br>curiosity about new <br>things.<br>From a Far Country: Trebizond can make use of weapons and exotic <br>objects with which to surprise opponents. Once per Scene, she can create a <br>Descriptor that represents a special belonging, such as Magic-Finding Dust or <br>A Whip as Sharp as a Blade. When using her special equipment, Trebizond <br>increases her Opposition Level by 1.<br>2 Saint Demetrius<br>I put the defense of my <br>companions before my <br>own life.<br>Guardian: Once per Exchange, Demetrius can take 1 Wound in place of one <br>of his allies. When he does, he increases his Opposition Level by 1 for the rest <br>of the Scene.<br>3 Saint Theodore<br>The ecstasy of battle is <br>for me the sweetest of <br>pleasures.<br>Furious: Theodore always inflicts 1 Additional Wound when raging against <br>an enemy. He still inflicts 1 Wound even if the Defense Check is a successful <br>Outcome. The only way to avoid the effect of this Gift is to spend an <br>Increment to cancel the Wound.<br>4 Saint Martha<br>I do not think that the <br>Broken Tales should <br>be eradicated, but only <br>understood.<br>Friendly: Any Hunter who acts against Martha when there are other Paladins <br>as potential targets will receive 2 Penalties on their action.<br>5 Saint Syrus<br>I am the oldest of the <br>Paladins and I only trust <br>my own judgment.<br>Veteran: Once per Scene, Syrus can negate the effect of a Gift activated by a <br>Hunter. The Saint will find a method to counter Gifts, drawn from his great <br>experience.<br>6 Saint Margaret<br>I want to affirm my <br>role in the Church and <br>overthrow that arrogant <br>Saint George.<br>Ambition: Margaret increases her Opposition Level by 1 for each Wound <br>that Saint George has suffered. Once per Scene, when Saint George suffers 1 <br>Wound, Margaret can immediately perform 1 additional action.<br>Saint George in a Broken <br>Tales Campaign<br>By his very recursive nature, Saint George is a great addition <br>to a Broken Tales Campaign. In the list of clues on page 246 <br>there are also indications to link him to the story of the Child <br>Savior and of the One Who Plots in the Shadows. As written <br>in his Agenda, Saint George is torn between his duty to the <br>Church and the memory of when, as a child, he formed a <br>sincere bond with The Ancient Enemy.</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513705067,"modifiedTime":1781513705067,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"saint-george-the-dragon-slayer","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","pages":"217-222"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513705067,"modifiedTime":1781513705067,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Vccus2S3PDrOn5fs","name":"OZena the Suffering and Desperate","pages":[{"_id":"LyOg8knqG0haej5A","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>OZena the Suffering and Desperate</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> Core Book</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf, pages 223-243.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-p223-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513706832,"modifiedTime":1781513706832,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"9A7z7swtfinyHNnW","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>OZena the Suffering and Desperate - Setup</h2><p>222<br>OZena  <br>the Suffering and Desperate<br>A Scenario inspired by <br>the Wonderful Wizard of OZ (Lyman Frank Baum)<br>Part One – The Yellow Village<br>Safety Keywords: Disfiguring Illness / Mental Illness / Deformity / Plagiarism</p><p>223<br>OZena the Suffering and Desperate is a special Scenario <br>divided into three parts, which when played consecutively <br>completes the story of the unfortunate Dorothea. All <br>Scenarios are built as a Scene Tree (see page 89) and <br>are great for introductory Sessions or a mini-Campaign. <br>A Storyteller who prefers an emerging storytelling style <br>will still find Events and information useful for managing <br>a freer playstyle for the Hunters.<br>Once upon a <br>time…<br>Freiburg, West of the great Black Forest, <br>Germany. The regent of the city, Nils Schulz, <br>has invited the Order to investigate the <br>activities of Margareta Westen, a renowned <br>“witch” who is said to carry out strange <br>experiments in a small village nearby. <br>Although there is no apparent evidence of <br>any heresy, the village of Gelb is shunned <br>by all. Its inhabitants are deemed “strange” <br>and it has, over the years, welcomed all <br>manner of freaks and sick people looking <br>for a safe place to live. Thus, the Hunters <br>must go to Gelb and find out if Margareta <br>is really the terrible witch that Nils fears.<br>The story that led us here…<br>Dorothea is a young American girl from the <br>1900s who suffers from a very acute form of ozena. Under <br>the care of the charlatan “Dr. ” Norman Henkle, she took <br>part in a strange magical rite, and both were catapulted <br>into the Black Forest of 1780. Here, under the guidance <br>of Henkle, Dorothea took the name of OZena (a name <br>that has not yet been made official for her disease). She’s <br>hunting witches to procure ingredients and potions for <br>her master, with the doctor promising to find a cure for <br>the disease. Dorothea brought the Doctor other lost, <br>ill people found along the way: Lowe, a scoundrel with <br>Leontiasis; Dose, a thug suffering from leprosy who <br>covers his skin with metal; and Hirnloser, a mental <br>patient who believes he has no brain. <br>After eliminating the witch Johanne in Schiltach (east of <br>the Black Forest) from which she got her magic shoes, <br>Dorothea arrived in Gelb with her companions. Here, <br>pursuing the promise of her cure, she sent Lowe and <br>Hirnloser to the village as spies to observe Margareta’s <br>activities. The old witch is actually both learned and <br>benevolent. She uses her magical knowledge to provide a <br>home and support to many sick or deformed people who <br>would otherwise have no place to live. <br>Note: Nasal ozena (also known as chronic atrophic <br>rhinitis) is a particular form of chronic rhinitis, <br>characterized specifically by a marked and widespread <br>atrophy of the nasal mucosa, so that the structure of <br>the nose wastes away. The disease disfigures the face <br>in a permanent way, affecting the appearance of those <br>affected with devastating effects.</p><p>1<br>224<br>The story at the arrival of the Hunters<br>Margareta Westen is a capable and experienced witch, <br>who served at many noble courts as a fortune teller and <br>counselor from a young age. Affected by a very serious form <br>of deforming osteitis, which has ruined her legs and arms, <br>Margareta has experienced the unreasoning prejudice of <br>society herself. She was marginalized and abandoned by <br>everyone. The witch has thus decided to found a small <br>community, where all those like her would be welcome. In <br>Gelb, Margareta cares for those unfortunate enough not to <br>have a place in society, and most of the villagers would give <br>their lives for her. <br>Margareta is part of a coven of witches called the Compass <br>Rose. Johanne, the witch of Schiltach (east of the Black <br>Forest), was also part of the same coven. The death of her <br>companion has put Margareta on alert, aware that it must <br>have been someone who knew the secrets of the coven <br>who killed Johanne. Dorothea has long since crept into <br>Gelb, hiding at the edge of the small village. Hirnloser has <br>instead openly joined the community, though everyone is <br>wary of his mental illness. Lowe serves as eyes and arms for <br>Dorothea around town, while Dose, hidden in the swamp <br>to the east, awaits a signal from Dorothea to spring into <br>action.</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513706833,"modifiedTime":1781513706833,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ZHdcwVFBUOVzeOxb","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>OZena the Suffering and Desperate - Scene 1</h2><p>FIRST SCENE – Approaching <br>the village of Gelb<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  Before your eyes you see <br>the great Black Forest in all its splendor, a refuge for animals <br>and supernatural beings from the slow expansion of civilized <br>life. A wide beaten path leads through the trees. Near a sign <br>with directions to the village of Gelb, you see two motionless <br>figures, as if they’re awaiting your arrival. One is a man, old <br>and hunched over by who-knows-what disease, while the <br>other is a child with a disfigured face. The two hold hands <br>like father and son. The man nods to you and you understand <br>that he is a villager sent to guide you.<br>Place: The road that winds its way from the west into the <br>great Black Forest.<br>Time: It is early in the morning. A cart has brought the <br>Hunters from Freiburg to the edge of the forest and the <br>driver is now anxious to leave.<br>Initial Situation:  Henrich and Klaus approach the <br>Hunters and introduce themselves as emissaries on <br>Margareta’s behalf. The witch was formally notified by <br>Nils that he was sending some of his agents to check on <br>Gelb’s activities, but the regent took great care not to reveal <br>the true nature of the Hunters. Henrich offers to lead the <br>Hunters along the road to the village.<br>Information: Walking towards Gelb with Henrich and <br>Klaus you can get the following clues and information.<br> ◆ The village of Gelb is a safe place for anyone with a <br>disease or a deformity that makes them an outcast in <br>usual society. Margareta welcomes anyone without <br>asking questions about their past and with the aid of her <br>potions, she soothes the suffering of all the inhabitants. <br>Although Henrich is a poorly educated farmer, he will</p><p>225<br>do nothing but praise Margareta’s goodness throughout <br>the journey with sincere conviction.<br> ◆ Little Klaus is affected by Ozena and his nose is nothing <br>more than a clump of rotten meat. Despite the disease, <br>he has the lively and curious eyes of a child, and he will <br>ask the Hunters a thousand questions.<br> ◆ The road the group is traveling on was created to <br>facilitate commercial trips to Gelb. However, Henrich <br>will regretfully inform the Hunters that once merchants <br>arrive in the village, they are so frightened by the <br>sight of the inhabitants, they hurriedly leave without <br>conducting any business. <br> ◆ Halfway to the village, the Hunters will realize that <br>someone is following them. It’s Lowe, who hides among <br>the foliage and tries to figure out who the newcomers <br>are.<br>End of Scene:  The Hunters arrive at the village of Gelb. <br>Go to SECOND SCENE - The Village of Gelb.<br>Henrich the Father<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am one of the many people Margareta <br>saved from the miserable life of an outcast. My son Klaus is <br>everything to me, which is why I don’t want the village of <br>Gelb to be suspected of witchcraft.<br>Klaus, the Ozena-<br>Afflicted Son<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC  <br>(1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a curious child. I <br>love foreigners because they always have <br>interesting stories to tell. I know I have a <br>dreadful disease, but I have learned to live <br>with it.<br>Lowe the Coward <br>Henchman<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC  <br>(2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I’m an eternal coward <br>who has been given a monstrous aspect <br>by fate. I can adapt to any situation <br>and am quick to jump to the winning <br>side.<br>Agenda: To help Dorothea in her <br>mission, with the hope of recovering <br>from my condition / Save my life, no <br>matter who I have to betray.</p><p>2<br>226</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513706833,"modifiedTime":1781513706833,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Qp1jdRhCcCMR3ebi","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>OZena the Suffering and Desperate - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE – The Village <br>of Gelb<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  When you arrive at the <br>entrance to the village, the spectacle that appears before you <br>is incredible. People with all kinds of diseases and deformities <br>walk in the streets, occupied performing a variety of tasks. In <br>reality, what you see is nothing more than an ordinary village <br>in Bavaria, inhabited solely by people who, in any other place, <br>would be considered monsters.<br>Place: The small village of Gelb.<br>Time: It is morning, and all the inhabitants are busy with <br>their work activities.<br>Information: Henrich will tell the Hunters that Margareta <br>will soon arrive in the town square to dispense her medicines. <br>While waiting for the witch, several things will happen.<br> ◆ Hirnloser will appear, dancing and chanting of distant <br>worlds that overlap each other. Adults look at him with <br>pity, children walk around him amused. If the Hunters <br>get close, he will try to interact with them. If the Hunters <br>ignore him, he will be the one to approach. Whatever <br>happens, when Margareta arrives in the square, <br>Hirnloser will leave.<br> ◆ When Margareta arrives all the inhabitants will stop <br>working to run to her. The witch dispenses strange vials <br>among happy and grateful faces. After the distribution <br>of the medicines, Henrich will lead the Hunters to <br>Margareta.<br> ◆ In the crowd you can spot Lowe, who gazes at the potions <br>with dreamy eyes.<br> ◆ Dorothea is in the crowd too, her face covered with <br>a heavy green hood, the smell of her illness clearly <br>distinguishable. The girl will disappear using her shoes <br>at the slightest hint of a problem.<br> ◆ Margareta will speak to the Hunters, saying she fears for <br>her life. A week ago, she received news of the murder <br>of the witch Johanne who lived in Schiltach, in the <br>eastern part of the Black Forest. Margareta is convinced <br>that someone is trying to eliminate all 4 witches of the <br>Black Forest, each of which holds part of a powerful <br>artifact. She believes someone is gathering the pieces to <br>reassemble the artifact, no matter the cost.<br> ◆ The conversation will be interrupted by Lowe who <br>screams desperately: Hirnloser has kidnapped Klaus <br>and is taking him to the great swamp near the village! <br>Margareta will ask the Hunters to save the child. In <br>exchange, she will reveal to the Hunters what she knows <br>of the artifact. In the woman’s eyes, the Hunters will see <br>only a sincere concern for the fate of little Klaus.<br>Margareta the Good Witch<br>OL Hard 7 – Main NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a capable witch who has devoted her life to <br>caring for the unfortunate. My body is wracked with disease, <br>but that doesn’t make me any less fearsome.<br>Agenda: Keep Gelb and everyone who lives there safe.<br>Gift - Witch:  Margareta can draw on her witch power <br>to create a Descriptor to represent the effect of her magic. <br>Her abilities are related to manipulating emotions, such as <br>instilling fear or bestowing calm. The Descriptor thus created <br>remains for the entire duration of a Scene. Alternatively, <br>Margareta can move objects with the power of thought. These <br>abilities can be used to hit someone from a distance, knock <br>objects out of someone’s hand, and generally manipulate the <br>environment.</p><p>3<br>227<br>Hirnloser the Scarecrow<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: Everyone thinks I’m crazy and maybe they’re <br>right. I don’t feel any fear and I can see beneath the surface of <br>those who pretend they are normal.<br>Agenda: I follow OZena because I can see past her pain. <br>There is another world, the one where she comes from and <br>where I want to go too.<br>End of Scene:  Margareta asks the Hunters to save little <br>Klaus, offering to reveal all her secrets in exchange for the <br>little one’s safety. If the Hunters set out to save Klaus go <br>to SCENE THREE - In the Swamp . If, on the other hand, <br>they decide to stay in the village or split up, for those who <br>remain, go to the FOURTH SCENE - OZena’s Attack.</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513706833,"modifiedTime":1781513706833,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"46N7XfHGWopthTlb","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>OZena the Suffering and Desperate - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE – In the Swamp<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You don’t have to go too <br>far into the swamp before you hear little Klaus scream. You <br>run to a small clearing where Hirnloser puts a sickle to the <br>child’s throat. He is near an old, abandoned shed from which <br>suddenly emerges a huge figure covered in grotesque armor <br>made of debris. Hirnloser stares at you, his eyes pools of pure <br>madness. “ And while we dance here in our little puppet show, <br>the real performance unfolds in the village, ” the madman <br>cries and smiles maliciously, as you realize that you have <br>been lured into a trap.<br>Place: A clearing in the swamp twenty minutes’ walk from <br>Gelb.<br>Time: It is late morning and the sun filters through the <br>trees.<br>Information: Hirnloser and Dose want to engage the <br>Hunters to give Dorothea time to kill Margareta. <br> ◆ Hirnloser is insane but he doesn’t really want to kill <br>Klaus. It will soon become clear that he uses the child <br>as a shield and lever to keep the Hunters busy.<br> ◆ If Lowe is present, he will try to surprise the Hunters <br>from behind but will flee at the slightest sign of danger.<br>Dose The Tin Man<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: Leprosy has destroyed my appearance, but <br>my body is still that of the Mountain, the name by which <br>I performed as a street artist in shows of strength and <br>endurance. Under my heavy armor I fear nothing.<br>Agenda: I am in love with OZena, disfigured by the disease <br>just like me. I am aware that she will never return my feelings <br>and that is why the only thing I can do is serve her, even to <br>my death.<br>Gift - The Tin Man: Dose is completely covered in thick <br>armor made of metal and other salvaged materials, such as <br>a large stove and the hull of a boat. The only unarmored spot <br>is a small door in the stove that was once used to remove <br>embers, which is located above his heart. It is not possible <br>to hurt Dose unless one first finds a way to penetrate his <br>armor or uses an attack that can clearly overcome his <br>defenses.</p><p>4<br>228<br>Gift - Giant:  Dose stands nearly seven feet tall and <br>possesses extraordinary strength. The disease consumed <br>his nerves making him immune to pain. Once per Scene he <br>can inflict 1 additional Wound with one hit of his mighty <br>ax.<br>End of Scene: After the fight, Klaus will tell the Hunters <br>that the real leader of the scoundrels is a girl with a green <br>cape they called OZena. She told her accomplices to buy <br>her time, while she would take care of the witch. Klaus did <br>not see the girl’s face, but by the smell he recognized his <br>own illness. Go to FOURTH SCENE - OZena’s Attack.</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513706833,"modifiedTime":1781513706833,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ytoTyD2MjRqPrLGV","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>OZena the Suffering and Desperate - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE – OZena’s <br>Attack<br>This Scene concludes the first part of the Scenario <br>and will change based on whether the Hunters <br>choose to leave someone in the village while they <br>go to rescue little Klaus. Dorothea will attempt <br>to kill Margareta in her house. If no Hunter <br>is present, the witch will succumb to <br>the blows of the young assassin. If <br>any or all the Hunters are present, <br>Dorothea will flee as soon as it <br>becomes clear that she is at a <br>distinct disadvantage.<br>Place: Margareta’s house. <br>A large circular house built <br>around a centuries-old oak.<br>Time: It is late morning and the village of Gelb has resumed <br>its activity. Many inhabitants remain waiting tensely in the <br>Town Square to discover the fate of little Klaus.<br>Information:<br> ◆ During the fight, Dorothea’s hood will slide back and <br>reveal her face. She is a young blonde girl, eyes of an <br>intense blue and a suppurating chasm in place of her <br>nose. <br> ◆ When Dorothea escapes and disappears, it will be clear <br>to the Hunters that her slippers are magical.<br> ◆ After the battle, if still alive, Margareta will reveal <br>details on the Compass Rose. If she was killed by <br>Dorothea, the Hunters will be able to obtain some of <br>the information by examining the witch’s house.<br>OZena (Dorothea)<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a young girl who wants to return to <br>her world. The disease that afflicts me has ruined my face <br>and with it all the hopes of a normal life. I am willing to do <br>anything to heal, which is why I became a witch killer.<br>Agenda: Kill every witch Henkle points out to me and <br>retrieve all four pieces of the Compass Rose.<br>Gift - The Silver Slippers:  The wearer of this magical <br>artifact can move through folds in space, disappearing and <br>reappearing in a flash. Dorothea can move freely up to a <br>maximum distance of thirty feet without anyone preventing <br>her, but she must be able to see the point of arrival. Once <br>per Scene, Dorothea can take a longer journey and reappear <br>in any place she has seen at least once.</p><p>229<br>Epilogue<br>The Hunters will discover that OZena’s goal is the Compass <br>Rose, a powerful artifact capable of summoning storms that <br>are said to be able to throw people and objects into other <br>worlds. The four Black Forest witches - Johanne (East), <br>Margareta (West), Helga (South) and Karina (North) - split <br>the artifact into four parts so that no one could abuse its <br>power. Karina possessed the first piece of the Rose. Johanne <br>had the second, as well as being famous for her magic <br>slippers. For this reason, it is quite clear that OZena has <br>already attacked and killed the first two witches. The next <br>target will then be Helga, who lives in the village of Rot <br>south of the Forest.<br>If Margareta is still alive, she will reveal some additional <br>information. Helga is the cruelest and most powerful of the <br>coven. Her magic is based on blood and, for this reason, <br>the Hunters will have to be careful not to be injured in her <br>presence. There is a potion that can break Helga’s blood <br>curse, but Margareta doesn’t know its ingredients, apart <br>from knowing it contains Burdock.<br>Note to the Storyteller:  OZena’s story continues with <br>the Second Part, The Red Village. Keep track of who among <br>Hirnloser, Dose and Lowe survived the Scenario. They will <br>return in the third part, The Emerald Village.<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario, there are five Events. As a Storyteller, feel <br>free to create new ones in response to the actions of the <br>Hunters.<br>When the Hunters are in conversation with <br>Margareta: Hirnloser will take the opportunity to <br>kidnap Klaus and take him to the nearby swamp, creating a <br>diversion to get the Hunters away from the village.<br>If the Hunters head to the swamps to save Klaus:  <br>Lowe will offer to “guide them” to try to waste more time <br>and give Dorothea more leeway to kill Margareta.<br>If someone has wasted time interacting and <br>getting to know Hirnloser in the village:  when the <br>madman has Klaus with him, he will try to use the child <br>as a lever to talk to his new friend again, forgetting about <br>the plan.<br>If Dorothea is cornered:  she will flee thanks to her <br>silver slippers. Dorothea cannot afford to risk being <br>captured. This event occurs as soon as the situation turns <br>in favor of the Hunters.<br>If Dorothea manages to kill Margareta:  she <br>will recover the piece of the Compass Rose and then <br>immediately escape thanks to her magical shoes.</p><p>230<br>Part Two – The <br>Red Village<br>Safety Keywords: Rituals / Nudity / Blood / Body <br>horror<br>Once upon a <br>time…<br>Rot, South of the great Black Forest, Germany. <br>After investigating Margareta Westen’s activities <br>and discovering the secret of Gelb’s village, the <br>Hunters are now aware of the threat from OZena, <br>a young witch killer who is trying to rebuild a <br>powerful magical artifact called the Compass Rose. <br>As described by Margareta herself, whoever owns <br>the Rose can invoke a storm so powerful, it can <br>throw those who are swept up into other worlds and <br>dimensions. OZena’s next target is Helga, a powerful <br>witch who lives south of the great forest. Helga <br>founded the cult of the Crimson Kiss, surrounded <br>by faithful and devoted servants. The village of Rot, <br>where Helga has made her home, is shunned even <br>by state officials, who fear they won’t be able to <br>leave that cursed place. But before going to Rot, the <br>Hunters received a special invitation...<br>Principality of Transylvania, fortified church of <br>Valea Viilor. Since the young OZena can move <br>in space and time simply by clicking her magic <br>shoes, the Hunters need an asset that allows them <br>to anticipate the movements of the enemy. And <br>the Order’s Treasury will surely have something <br>suitable...<br>For this Scenario the Hunters will receive the support of <br>the Order in the form of one of the many treasures kept in <br>Valea Viilor.<br>The Mirror of a Thousand Wishes <br>(Inspired by Snow White)<br>Gift - Mirror Mirror on the Wall: Those who use the <br>Mirror of a Thousand Wishes can ask to see the near past <br>or the imminent future of a subject they have met at least <br>once. After spending 1 Soma, the Mirror will show a few <br>moments of the target by displaying them on its surface. <br>The observer will not know if what they see is the past or the <br>future. The Storyteller secretly rolls a die: with 1-3 they will <br>see the past, with 4-6 the future. The same subject cannot <br>be observed more than once during a Scene. Alternatively, <br>before attempting a specific task, the owner of the mirror <br>can look into it and spend 1 Soma. Roll a die. If it’s a 4+ they <br>will see a few moments of their imminent future. Thanks to <br>this premonition they will receive 3 Additional Successes <br>for the first action attempting to perform the task. <br>Note to the Storyteller: The Order’s Treasure is an extra <br>Gift that can be taken by one of the Hunters. The Broken <br>Ones expansion book features complete rules for managing <br>the Order’s Treasures and a long list of Treasures to choose <br>from.</p><p>1<br>231<br>The story that led us here…<br>After the events in Gelb, Dorothea moved to Rot as the <br>first step in eliminating Helga. The Red Witch, however, <br>took the young woman by surprise. Thanks to the witches’ <br>faithful servants, Helga captured the girl, holding her in <br>her fortified villa. On the first night of the full moon, Helga <br>intends to sacrifice Dorothea by performing a blasphemous <br>rite which consists of drinking the victim’s blood to <br>assimilate her memories. By doing so, Helga would learn <br>of Henkle’s hiding place, where the other pieces of the <br>Compass Rose are already located. <br>Of course, the Hunters arrive only hours before the sun sets <br>and a full moon rises, setting the stage for the ritual.<br>The story at the arrival of the Hunters…<br>Helga is a powerful witch who has never had any qualms <br>about using dark magic. Through blood magic, she kept her <br>appearance young (despite her eighty-eight years) and over <br>time she built a true cult, whose foolish devotees would <br>do anything for her. Through her blood Helga can control <br>plants and people, moving them like puppets. Although the <br>village of Rot has acquired a grim reputation, Helga knows <br>it is only a matter of time before some obsessed clergyman <br>decides to attack her to eradicate the evil she represents. <br>The witch aims to obtain the Compass Rose to escape to a <br>safe place, where she can rebuild her kingdom of fanatical <br>servants.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513706833,"modifiedTime":1781513706833,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ZHdcwVFBUOVzeOxb","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>OZena the Suffering and Desperate - Scene 1</h2><p>FIRST SCENE – Towards the <br>Village of Rot<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You have finally arrived in <br>the deep south of the Black Forest. Along the way, there are <br>numerous signs warning that the village of Rot is a cursed <br>place. Dolls of wood and rag, crosses and mounds of salt, all <br>bear witness to the pointless, superstitious spells of protection <br>attempted by the inhabitants of the area. As you follow the <br>small path to the village, the forest thickens more and more, <br>while the branches of the trees lower as if to grab you.<br>Place: The small path that leads to Rot.<br>Time: It is late afternoon and the last rays of sunlight are <br>struggling to pass between the branches of the trees.<br>Initial Situation: The branches seem to stretch lower and <br>lower, until it becomes clear to the Hunters that something <br>is wrong. Shortly after, the animated trees will try to catch <br>the Hunters and imprison them.<br>Information: If a Hunter has some understanding of <br>magic, they will quickly understand that what animates the <br>trees is an arcane power. Observing the branches’ motions <br>for a while, it will be possible to see a figure not far away <br>bathing the trees in a liquid which apparently animates <br>them.</p><p>2<br>232<br>If the mirror is used to understand where <br>OZena is:<br> ◆ Past - Dorothea sneaks up to a large greenhouse, <br>where she sees men dressed in white tending to <br>plants and herbs. The mirror fills with the form of a <br>nightmare creature that resembles a spider made up <br>of people’s bodies, which scares Dorothea away from <br>the greenhouse. In the ensuing chaos Dorothea grabs a <br>sprig from a plant (Elderberry, which a Hunter with a <br>relevant Descriptor will recognize).<br> ◆ Future - Dorothea introduces herself to a beautiful <br>young woman, dressed in an elegant red dress. The <br>young assassin agrees to take a sip of the wine that is <br>offered to her. Then, a trickle of blood runs down her <br>lips and she falls to her knees. The woman in red smiles <br>mockingly as a long knife falls from Dorothea’s hand.<br>Threat - The Animated Forest<br>OL Medium 5 <br>Descriptor: We grab and capture all intruders through the <br>magic that animates our branches and roots.<br>Wolfgang the “druid”<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a skilled and renowned pharmacist, and <br>there is no herb or remedy that I am not familiar with.<br>Agenda: I am enslaved by Helga’s power. My body moves at <br>her will and therefore I sprinkle drops of her blood to animate <br>the forest to capture potential intruders.<br>End of Scene:  If captured, Wolfgang will reveal what <br>he knows to the Hunters. In the greenhouse, other poor <br>people like him work incessantly under Helga’s magical <br>control. In the village, a strange figure called the Porcelain <br>Princess ensures that no one can harm the witch. During <br>the interrogation, Wolfgang will be seized with sudden <br>spasms and drown in his own blood. If Wolfgang has been <br>eliminated, the Hunters will simply have to choose which <br>way to go.<br>If they go to the greenhouse, go to the SECOND SCENE - <br>The Greenhouse.<br>If they go to the Village go to the THIRD SCENE - The <br>Doll’s Court.</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513706833,"modifiedTime":1781513706833,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Qp1jdRhCcCMR3ebi","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>OZena the Suffering and Desperate - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE – The <br>Greenhouse<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: Following the path you reach <br>an old manor house which has been remade as a greenhouse. <br>Many men and women dressed in white, with tired and long-<br>suffering expressions, work on small gardens. Strong smells of <br>herbs and medicinal infusions fill the air.<br>Place: The greenhouse where the base for the Infusion of <br>Purity is produced.<br>Time: The sun is setting. <br>Information:<br> ◆ Pharmacists are working on a strange potion. Those <br>who are experts in herbs will recognize the plants as <br>Burdock, Nettle and Hyssop. <br> ◆ If the Hunters approach the greenhouse, Manycorpses <br>will drop from the ceiling to stop the intruders.<br> ◆ The Infusion of Purity cannot be completed, as the <br>Elderberry, which Dorothea took in her fight with <br>Manycorpses, is missing.</p><p>3<br>233<br>If the mirror is used:<br> ◆ Past - Dorothea sneaks up to a large greenhouse, <br>where she sees men dressed in white tending to <br>plants and herbs. The mirror fills with the form of a <br>nightmare creature that resembles a spider made up <br>of people’s bodies, which scares Dorothea away from <br>the greenhouse. In the ensuing chaos, Dorothea grabs <br>a sprig from a plant (Elderberry, which a Hunter with a <br>relevant Descriptor will recognize).<br> ◆ Future - Dorothea is kneeling with her arms behind <br>her back. Her body is stiff, as if paralyzed, as she is <br>forced to look at herself in a mirror. She weeps for what <br>she sees reflected: her face disfigured by a disease that <br>has completely devoured her nose. <br>Manycorpses<br>OL Hard 7 – Minor NPC (4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am an abomination created by Helga’s <br>experiments, in which she has united all her lovers into one. <br>I hate anyone who still has a normal body and I use my <br>incredible power to destroy them.<br>Agenda: Kill and dismember any human that comes within <br>range.<br>Gift - Aberration: Manycorpses can act twice during an <br>Exchange. Thanks to its multiple arms it can move on any <br>surface.<br>End of Scene: After being freed, the greenhouse workers <br>reveal that Helga is able to control people’s bodies with her <br>blood magic. Something called the Infusion of Purity, a <br>potion, can lift the curse. Helga is producing the Infusion <br>because she plans to sell the antidote to rich and powerful <br>nobles after poisoning them with her magical blood. To <br>complete the Infusion, however, Elderberry is required, <br>though the ingredient does not grow in this area. A strange <br>girl in a green cape has stolen the small stash Helga had <br>brought back from her last trip.<br>Go to the THIRD SCENE - The Dolls’ Court.</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513706834,"modifiedTime":1781513706834,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"46N7XfHGWopthTlb","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>OZena the Suffering and Desperate - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE – The Dolls’ <br>Court<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You come to a bleak, <br>dilapidated village made up of small, ruined houses and <br>brightly colored tents. Men and women in an evident state of <br>distress lie sprawled along the streets. From their tired eyes, <br>you understand that they are exhausted by the incessant work <br>Helga magically forces them to do. Suddenly, figures wearing <br>grotesque doll masks appear and head in your direction, <br>drawing their weapons.<br>Place: The dilapidated village of Rot.<br>Time: The sun is setting, but time seems to have stopped <br>in the small village.<br>Information:<br> ◆ The Porcelain Dolls are the only individuals worth <br>talking to. They will initially have their guard up, but if <br>the Hunters are convincing, they will be brought to the <br>Porcelain Princess.<br> ◆ The village is just an old, dilapidated logging settlement. <br>Not far away, it is possible to see a noble’s mansion <br>where Helga now resides.<br> ◆ No one can come before Helga without the approval of <br>the Porcelain Princess, her favorite.</p><p>234<br>If the mirror is used:<br> ◆ Past - Dorothea introduces herself to a beautiful <br>young woman, dressed in an elegant red dress. The <br>young assassin agrees to take a sip of the wine that is <br>offered to her. Then, a trickle of blood runs down her <br>lips and she falls to her knees. The woman in red smiles <br>mockingly as a long knife falls from Dorothea’s hand..<br> ◆ Future - Dorothea is kneeling with her arms behind <br>her back. Her body is stiff, as if paralyzed, as she is <br>forced to look at herself in a mirror. She weeps for what <br>she sees reflected: her face disfigured by a disease that <br>has completely devoured her nose. <br>The Porcelain Princess<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a young noble who has fallen from grace. <br>My disfigured face is covered in a beautiful doll mask, and I <br>sadistically manage the cult of the Crimson Kiss on behalf of <br>my lady Helga.<br>Agenda: Carry out every order of Helga in the hope that she <br>will heal my face / I would do anything to get my face back.<br>Gift - Vials:  The Princess always has five or six vials of <br>Helga’s blood with her for newcomers to drink. She also has <br>1 vial of the Infusion of Purity.<br>Porcelain Dolls<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are the devoted guards of the Porcelain <br>Princess. Everyone fears us for our martial ability. <br>Agenda: Fulfill every wish of the Porcelain Princess.<br>Gift - Armed Guard:  Each Doll is armed differently. <br>Roll 1 die: 1. Spear, the Doll can make exceptional jumps <br>and can always keep an enemy at a distance; 2. Double <br>knife, 2 attacks per Exchange; 3. Great Blade, once per <br>Scene inflicts 1 additional Wound; 4. Whip, 9 feet range, <br>whoever fails the Defense Check becomes entangled; 5. <br>Blood, the blade of the weapon is soaked in Helga’s blood; <br>6. Shield, +1 OL to defend themselves or an ally.<br>End of Scene:  By defeating the Porcelain Princess or <br>persuading her away from Helga’s service, the Hunters will <br>obtain the key to enter Helga’s palace. When questioned, <br>the Princess will reveal that her lady intends to perform <br>an arcane rite during the night that involves sacrificing <br>Dorothea. Go to SCENE FOUR - The Red Witch of the <br>South.</p><p>4<br>235</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513706834,"modifiedTime":1781513706834,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ytoTyD2MjRqPrLGV","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>OZena the Suffering and Desperate - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE – The Red <br>Witch of the South<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  Helga’s palace stands out <br>from the whole village because it is the only well-maintained <br>building. A heavy reinforced door and bars on the windows <br>make you immediately understand that it will not be easy <br>to enter. The soft sobbing of a girl catches your attention. It <br>comes from the second floor, where there is a large balcony.<br>Place: The old mansion where Helga lives.<br>Time: It is now night and only the light of lanterns borne <br>by the Hammerheads illuminate the mansion.<br>Information:<br> ◆ Entering the main door means encountering <br>Hammerheads equal to the number of Hunters +2.<br> ◆ Entering through the window will take the Hunters <br>to the room where OZena is held. If the Hunters have <br>an Infusion of Purity, they can free her from Helga’s <br>control. From Dorothea’s green cape, thrown carelessly <br>in a corner of the room, it is possible to retrieve the <br>Elderberry to complete a possible Infusion. Spending <br>time finishing the Infusion will cause a number of <br>Hammerheads equal to the number of Hunters +2 to <br>arrive in the room.<br> ◆ While the Hunters are busy in the mansion, Helga is <br>taking a blood bath in a tub to prepare for the ritual. As <br>soon as Dorothea is freed, Helga will understand that <br>there are intruders and will get ready to welcome them <br>with an escort of 8 Hammerheads.<br>If the mirror is used<br> ◆ Past - Dorothea is kneeling with her arms behind her <br>back. Her body is stiff, as if paralyzed, as she is forced <br>to look at herself in a mirror. She weeps for what she <br>sees reflected: her face disfigured by a disease that has <br>completely devoured her nose.<br> ◆ Future - Dorothea is naked and tied up on a large <br>wooden table. A woman with beautiful red hair, also <br>naked, utters strange arcane formulas, while she <br>prepares to gut the young assassin with a long knife.<br>Helga the Red Witch<br>OL Hard 7 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a powerful witch and I use blood to <br>perform my spells. Drinking one drop of my blood is enough <br>to become my slave.<br>Agenda: Accumulating power and collecting the four pieces <br>of the Compass Rose thanks to the information obtained <br>from OZena’s sacrifice / I am always willing to make an <br>advantageous deal, even if this leads me to revise my plans. I <br>would do anything to live forever.<br>Gift - Blood Magic:  Helga can unleash her powers to <br>affect the blood of one or more subjects, inflicting 1 Wound <br>or commanding their movements. Whoever has swallowed <br>Helga’s blood is totally subject to her will. It is possible to <br>resist the effects of Blood Magic with a Defense Check, <br>but this does not eliminate Helga’s magic. Drinking the <br>Infusion of Purity renders anyone immune to Blood Magic <br>for the course of a Scene and cancels the crowd control. <br>Those under the influence of the Blood Magic have a slight <br>crimson tinge to their eyes.<br>Gift - Blood Witch:  Helga is made young and immortal <br>by blood magic. At the end of each of her actions and if hurt,</p><p>236<br>Helga recovers 1 Wound. The flesh regenerates as the blood <br>returns to her body. When she is eliminated by suffering <br>her last Wound, the magic dissipates and the witch’s body <br>returns to being a shriveled old woman.<br>The Hammerheads<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We were once a ferocious team of skilled <br>mercenaries, but now we are in Helga’s service. We were <br>tamed by her magic and therefore we do anything and <br>everything for her.<br>Gift - Hammerhead Helmet: The heavy and distinctive <br>Hammerhead helmet opens like a flower on the shoulders <br>and grants total head and chest protection, making the <br>NPC immune to any Wound that can’t get past a thick layer <br>of metal. An enemy can aim at the lower parts of the NPC <br>to ignore the helmet. However, they receive 1 Penalty for <br>their Check.<br>OZena (Dorothea)<br>Dorothea’s profile is presented on page <br>228, only her Agenda changes.<br>Agenda: Free myself from the prison <br>where Helga locked me up.<br>End of Scene:  Helga’s threat is <br>ended, either through combat or by <br>convincing her to let Dorothea go free. <br>The girl surrenders to the Hunters, <br>revealing that everything she did was <br>ordered by Norman Henkle, a doctor <br>who, like her, comes from another <br>world. Henkle settled in the center of the Black Forest, <br>in a village called Smaragd. Henkle’s goal is to gather all <br>the pieces of the Compass Rose to summon the magical <br>tornado. Dorothea realizes that Henkle is insane and reveals <br>to the Hunters that even though she has been stopped, the <br>man will still try to activate the half-reassembled artifact, <br>certainly with devastating results. Only Dorothea knows <br>the location of the village and she is willing to accompany <br>the Hunters, expressing sincere repentance.<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario, there are three Events. As a Storyteller, feel <br>free to create new ones in response to the actions of the <br>Hunters.<br>If the Hunters get the better of Wolfgang: Helga will <br>let him speak for a while so she can observe the Hunters <br>closely and then kill the man by drowning him in his own <br>blood.<br>When the Hunters start to get the better of a conflict <br>with Helga’s minions: the witch will detonate one of her <br>minions in each Exchange to cover <br>the Hunters in her blood. Y ou can <br>try to control them later.<br>If Dorothea is saved by the <br>Hunters: she will stay by their <br>side as an ally to take revenge on <br>Helga. She will try to kill her even <br>if the Hunters intend to negotiate.</p><p>237<br>Part Three – The <br>Emerald Village<br>Safety Keywords: Body horror<br>Once upon a <br>time…<br>Smaragd, in the center of the great Black Forest. <br>The Hunters are on the trail of Norman Henkle, <br>a doctor and charlatan who apparently is the <br>mastermind behind the young witch killer who <br>goes by the name of OZena. The girl, whose real <br>name is Dorothea, claims Henkle is actually <br>a powerful wizard who fulfills wishes. His <br>ultimate goal is to activate the Compass Rose <br>to summon a storm and return to his own time. <br>Given the young woman’s failure to retrieve the <br>last two pieces, Dorothea fears that Henkle will <br>activate the artifact anyway. Dorothea, however, <br>remembers the first witch she killed saying that <br>using the Compass Rose without all the pieces <br>would be disastrous, opening a passage to <br>another world, but at a very high price...<br>The story that led us here…<br>Norman Henkle has been settled in a small and remote <br>village for a month, where he halted an epidemic thanks <br>to the Penicillin in his doctor’s bag, brought back from the <br>year 1900. <br>Raised to the status of holy man, Norman began to believe <br>himself a magician, giving free rein to his madness. In the <br>center of Smaragd there is a small well whose true nature the <br>inhabitants have always ignored. It is in fact a wishing well, <br>which after centuries of inactivity, has awakened thanks to <br>the desire of Henkle himself to become a magician. <br>Now possessing new powers, Henkle is truly capable of <br>making people’s wishes come true. However, his madness <br>twists every wish and the results are always tainted. <br>Determined to return to his time and become famous, <br>Henkle lured young Dorothea into his service, promising <br>to fulfill her one desire, to heal the disease that disfigures <br>her face. <br>Aware that he can’t really do it without risking some worse <br>effect, Henkle is waiting for OZena’s return to retrieve the <br>last two pieces of the Compass Rose so he can leave Smaragd, <br>escaping in his hot-air balloon. In the meantime, Henkle <br>has “experimented” with his power on the inhabitants of <br>Smaragd, creating monsters and aberrations that now hope <br>to earn a new wish to return to normal, unaware that they <br>are locked in an endless cycle of warped wishes.</p><p>1<br>238<br>The story at the arrival of the Hunters…<br>Henkle fortified Smaragd against any possible intruder, <br>garrisoned by the villagers now corrupted by their wishes, <br>as well as the former companions of Dorothea who <br>survived the first encounter with the Hunters. While the <br>hot-air balloon is almost done, Henkle awaits Dorothea’s <br>arrival to complete the Compass Rose and escape.<br>Note to the Storyteller: This part of the Scenario differs <br>from the first two parts, as many enemies and encounters <br>will depend on what the Hunters have done previously. For <br>this reason, you’ll find only three Scenes leading up to the <br>Hunters meeting Henkle. It is possible to drop one or more <br>of the NPCs presented in each Scene to provide a challenge <br>for the Hunters. At the end of each Scene, or during a Scene <br>itself, if the Hunters face NPCs in a conflict, place 1 Time <br>Token on Henkle’s Hot-Air Balloon Gift. Until the hot-air <br>balloon is revealed, the Hunters will only know the name <br>of the Tokens that are accumulated by the Storyteller, but <br>not their purpose.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513706834,"modifiedTime":1781513706834,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ZHdcwVFBUOVzeOxb","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>OZena the Suffering and Desperate - Scene 1</h2><p>FIRST SCENE – Approaching <br>the Village of Smaragd<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: Finally, you reach the center <br>of the great Black Forest. A small path, now <br>almost completely lost among    weeds, is the <br>only point of reference to find your way. <br>Dorothea precedes you by a few steps, <br>visibly nervous. Suddenly you see the <br>girl stop and she wavers for a moment, <br>suddenly finding herself on the edge <br>of a huge ravine. “This wasn’t here <br>the last time I was here, ” exclaims <br>the amazed girl. A moat over <br>sixty feet deep and thirty wide surrounds a small village that <br>you can glimpse through the foliage. The fact that there is <br>no bridge suggests that it was created for the sole purpose of <br>keeping intruders away.<br>Place: A huge circular pit that Henkle created in order to <br>secure Smaragd<br>Time: It is early morning. The sun is high in the cloudless <br>sky.<br>Initial Situation:  It will be clear to the Hunters that <br>the moat must be crossed somehow. Dorothea can use <br>her silver slippers if she still has them, but she won’t do so <br>without the consent of the Hunters. The girl is convinced <br>that the Order can help her and will not betray the trust of <br>the Hunters, unless she sees a possibility of returning to the <br>future (see Events).<br>Information:  Henkle’s plan is to hit the Hunters as <br>they cross the pit, so he has deployed some underlings to <br>ambush them. Choose one of the following:<br> ◆ Hirnloser will have discovered a good position from <br>which to target the Hunters at a distance with the help <br>of 6 Villagers. <br> ◆ Lowe will go to meet the Hunters to challenge them <br>in the open field, bringing with him 3 Villagers and 3</p><p>2<br>3<br>239<br>Canine Tigers. <br> ◆ Dose will very simply attack the Hunters as soon as <br>they cross the Pit.<br> ◆ 4 Villagers with 4 Canine Tigers<br>Threat - The Pit<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: A large, deep pit with strangely smooth walls.<br>End of Scene:  The Hunters cross the pit to enter the <br>village of Smaragd. Go to SECOND SCENE - The Emerald <br>Village.</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513706834,"modifiedTime":1781513706834,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Qp1jdRhCcCMR3ebi","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>OZena the Suffering and Desperate - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE – The <br>Emerald Village<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  Once you cross the Pit you <br>find yourself in a small village of houses, built amongst the <br>trees. It only takes a few steps to understand that something <br>is wrong. You feel disoriented and it is difficult for you to keep <br>track of which direction you are moving. The small village <br>now looks like a labyrinth, huge and intricate.<br>Place: The small village of Smaragd which, by a wish <br>made by Henkle, appears as an infinite labyrinth.<br>Time: It is impossible to mark the passage of time <br>as day and night alternate every minute.<br>Information:  Henkle’s plan is <br>to waste the Hunters’ time and <br>prevent them from getting to <br>the center of the village. For <br>this he has deployed some <br>subordinates to set up an <br>ambush. Choose one of the following:<br> ◆ Hirnloser will plan an ambush with the help of 4 <br>Villagers. He and his men can move freely without <br>being affected by the Illusory Labyrinth Threat. <br> ◆ Lowe will go to meet the Hunters to challenge them <br>in the open field, bringing with him 3 Villagers and 3 <br>Canine Tigers. <br> ◆ Dose will very simply attack the Hunters as soon as <br>they enter the village.<br> ◆ 4 Villagers with 4 Canine Tigers<br>Threat - Illusory Labyrinth<br>OL Hard 7<br>Descriptor: A maze of trees and houses that change every <br>minute, making it impossible to find your way around.<br>End of Scene:  The Hunters arrive at the center of the <br>village. Go to the THIRD SCENE - The Magician’s Fake <br>Castle.</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513706834,"modifiedTime":1781513706834,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"46N7XfHGWopthTlb","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>OZena the Suffering and Desperate - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE – The <br>Magician’s Fake Castle<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  Finally in the center of the <br>village, you find yourself in front of a huge oak that has been <br>molded into the shape of a grotesque castle. Inside the tree, <br>you can see a hot-air balloon made of patched fabric that is <br>slowly inflating. You have never seen anything like it, but you <br>understand it will not be good.<br>Place: Henkle’s workshop house in the center of the <br>village, where the hot-air balloon is set up.<br>Time: The morning sun is high in a cloudless sky.</p><p>4<br>240<br>Information: Henkle’s plan is to waste the Hunters <br>time while he makes preparations for the hot-air balloon. <br>For this he has deployed some subordinates to set up an <br>ambush. Choose one of the following:<br> ◆ Hirnloser will plan an ambush with the help of 4 <br>Villagers and 4 Canine Tigers. Hirnloser will order his <br>underlings to focus on the most injured or physically <br>weaker Hunters. <br> ◆ Lowe will go to meet the Hunters to challenge them <br>in the open field, bringing with him 3 Villagers and 3 <br>Canine Tigers. <br> ◆ Dose will very simply attack the Hunters as soon as <br>they enter the castle.<br> ◆ 4 Villagers with 4 Canine Tigers<br>End of Scene: The Hunters arrive at Henkle’s Castle, go to</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513706834,"modifiedTime":1781513706834,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ytoTyD2MjRqPrLGV","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>OZena the Suffering and Desperate - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE - The End of OZena’s Sad Story.</p><p>FOURTH SCENE – The End of <br>OZena’s Sad Story<br>The final battle with Henkle can go in many different ways. <br>If he manages to activate the incomplete Compass Rose, <br>a huge tornado will hit the whole Black Forest, affecting <br>everyone and taking Henkle away to a place unknown to <br>the Hunters.<br>Whatever happens, the fate of young Dorothea will be in <br>their hands.<br>Lowe the Brave Fighter<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I became a proud warrior and realized my <br>heroic potential. I never back down and set an example for <br>my teammates.<br>Agenda: Stop the invaders and protect the village of <br>Smaragd, which has elected me as its hero.<br>Gift - Hero: Lowe fears nothing and is immune to all forms <br>of fear and magical control. After he acts, his allies receive <br>+1 to their OL, inspired by their hero’s courage and words.<br>Hirnloser the Genius<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: My mind has become infallible, and I can <br>calculate and check any variable in seconds. I have a strategy <br>for every situation.<br>Agenda: Solve any potential problems that plague my <br>benefactor Norman Henkle.</p><p>241<br>Gift - Genius: When someone uses a Gift, Hirnloser can <br>prevent it from activating by deploying a countering system <br>or strategy. This Gift can be used up to 3 times during a <br>Scene, but only 1 time per Exchange. <br>Dose the Giant in Love<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: My body has become pure metal and only the <br>power of love can bring me back to flesh and blood. I fight <br>and destroy anything that can threaten my sweet OZena.<br>Agenda: I am in love with OZena and I want her to loyally <br>serve Henkle once more. I know that imprisonment in the <br>hands of the enemy may have made her reluctant to trust us. <br>I have to save her, whether she wants it or not.<br>Gift - Of Steel and Love: Dose is made of pure metal and <br>cannot suffer any kind of physical Wound. The only way to <br>get him to return to flesh and blood for a few moments is <br>to make his heart beat with love. Seeing OZena in danger <br>or well disposed towards him will change him back for <br>one Exchange. Seeing OZena, Dose can’t help but declare <br>his love as he fights, making his infatuation for the young <br>assassin clear.<br>The Canine Tigers<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: We are the village dogs, turned into monsters <br>by the desire of one of the children. Once the tiger’s ferocity <br>takes over, we can no longer be controlled.<br>Gift - Fierce as a Tiger:  When a Canine Tiger suffers <br>a Wound, it goes mad with rage and its Opposition Level <br>rises to Hard 7. At the mercy of anger, the Tiger will attack <br>the closest target without distinguishing between allies and <br>enemies.<br>Norman  Henkle <br>The Powerful Wizard Who <br>Makes Wishes Come True<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a powerful wizard and what I desire <br>becomes reality. My skill as a barker always charms everyone <br>to my side.<br>Agenda: I want to go back to my time alone and become a <br>celebrity thanks to the power of magic.<br>Gift - Hot-Air Balloon: As soon as it is ready, Henkle will <br>board and release his hot-air balloon into the air to activate <br>the Compass Rose. As indicated by the Scenario, based on <br>the actions of the Hunters this Gift will accumulate Time <br>Tokens. When the third Time Token is placed, the hot-air <br>balloon is ready to go.</p><p>242<br>The Villagers of Emerald<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are poor villagers changed by a wish we <br>made. <br>Agenda: We hate Henkle for what he did to us, but we serve <br>him in the hope that we can make another wish.<br>Gift - Careful What you Wish For:  Each Villager has <br>made a wish, but it has not had the desired effects. Roll 1 die <br>to see what mutation has developed: 1. Wish for Wealth: <br>The NPC spits out gold coins mixed with bile. With a single <br>action, they can hit up to 3 targets at a distance of 15 feet; <br>2. Wish for Beauty:  The NPC warps their body so as <br>always to look beautiful in the eyes of the beholder. When <br>there is more than one subject in view, their body changes <br>constantly. Whoever witnesses the show receives 1 Penalty <br>on their Checks out of disgust; 3. Wish for Health:  The <br>NPC’s body regenerates as their hair and body hair grow <br>out of proportion. The NPC recovers 1 Wound as soon as it <br>loses 1, making them effectively immortal. The effect of the <br>Wound suffered is applied, so the NPC can be defeated, but <br>will regenerate on its turn to act; 4. Wish for Skill: The <br>NPC raises their OL to Medium; 5. The NPC can no longer <br>sleep because they are obsessed with the idea of working, <br>and will constantly be chattering nonsense; 5. Wish to <br>Grow Up: The NPC is a child with a body of a giant while <br>their head has remained the same as before. They can take <br>2 extra Wounds and inflict 1 additional Wound when they <br>unleash their strength; 6. Wish for Love:  The NPC has <br>merged with the one they love, literally obtaining the desire <br>to “become one. ” As a double body the NPC can act twice.<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario, there are two Events. As a Storyteller, feel <br>free to create new ones in response to the actions of the <br>Hunters.<br>When Henkle realizes that Dorothea does not have <br>the missing pieces of the Compass Rose with her:  <br>he will take off on the balloon as soon as it is ready, and <br>then activate the power of the incomplete Rose.<br>If Dorothea realizes that Henkle is willing to <br>abandon her to return to the future:  she will do <br>anything to reach the man, begging him not to abandon <br>her.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513706834,"modifiedTime":1781513706834,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","collection":"Core Book","sourceFile":"bt-corebook-1-eng-final-screen-fixed [2022-07-01].pdf","pages":"223-243"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513706834,"modifiedTime":1781513706834,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"gHuSlF7zmnDzDN2C","name":"I Don't Believe","pages":[{"_id":"VOmvuFkJYnfbR1rI","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>I Don't Believe</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> The Broken Ones</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 81-92.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/i-dont-believe-p81-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513710167,"modifiedTime":1781513710167,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"LFkPpyDuCd2G48Kv","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>I Don't Believe - Setup</h2><p>80<br>Once upon a time…<br>London’s outskirts. Among the fumes and vapors <br>of newly-built factories, the disappearance <br>of several children has led to widespread <br>discontent among the workers. However, it <br>is only after the disappearance of Gwendolyn <br>Carnarvon, daughter of a titled noble, that the <br>royal family itself decided to turn to the Order. <br>Strange rumors are circulating in the suburbs <br>of London, where it seems that a young gang of <br>hooligans is committing violent acts to slow the <br>creeping spread of modernity, particularly in <br>the form of heartless factories. The Crown has <br>been deeply terrified by the macabre discovery <br>made by police looking into reports of violence <br>in the streets. According to rumors, factory <br>guards had engaged in a clash with the young <br>terrorists. The Crown investigators who tracked <br>down the battlefield were confronted with a <br>scene of unbelievable violence featuring broken, <br>bloody limbs and burst hearts inside shredded <br>rib cages. In great secrecy, the investigation <br>was shortly thereafter entrusted to the Hunters <br>of the Order with the aim of shedding light on <br>the danger that threatens the city and bringing <br>young Carnarvon to safety.<br>A Scenario Inspired by Peter <br>and Wendy (J. M. Barrie)<br>I Don’t Believe<br>Safety Keywords:  <br>Kidnapping / Terrorism</p><p>81<br>The story that led us here…<br>A powerful fairy, known as the Cauldron Fae, has <br>been residing in London since time immemorial, long <br>before the city became what it is now. Under the false <br>identity of a personable purveyor of pots, she has lived in <br>secret on grounds she considers sacred: a series of caves and <br>galleries under the gardens of the Kensington Palace. The <br>Cauldron Fae is bothered by the modernization overtaking <br>London, slowly poisoning the clear air of the city with <br>smoke and stink. The fairy has begun to surround herself <br>with young orphans and misfits, creating a gang of ruthless <br>killers ready to do anything to please her. At the head of the <br>gang is Pietrik, a young Eastern immigrant who watched his <br>little sister die of fatigue, crushed by inhumane shifts at the <br>factory. Pietrik’s sole purpose in life is now to undermine <br>industrialization. The Cauldron Fae gave Pietrik, as her <br>most trusted servant, a magical object able to animate <br>his shadow so that he can more ably be her servant and <br>guardian. When a group of Crown investigators found the <br>secret passage from the slums to the Kensington Gardens, <br>the Cauldron Fae joined Pietrik on the field, unleashing her <br>great powers. The Cauldron Fae can control the Magic of <br>Disbelief, which allows her to imbue words with truth, but <br>only when expressing concepts of denial. By pronouncing <br>“I don’t believe in guards, ” the bodies of her enemies <br>twisted and then exploded, destroyed by devastating magic. <br>The only way to kill the Cauldron Fae is to use her own <br>magic against her, pronouncing the formula “I don’t believe <br>Mtyrya exists. ” Only Pietrik, however, knows her true name. <br>The young man fell in love with Gwendolyn and, after an <br>initial friendship, decided to kidnap her because she was <br>about to leave for Wales. As a prisoner in the Kensington <br>Gardens, the girl fears for her life, but she is perhaps the <br>only one who can lead Pietrik to reason.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>Pietrik is the leader of his gang, the Lost Boys. They are out <br>of control, striking at a different business in London every <br>night. Only Gwendolyn’s entreaties can dampen the young <br>rebel’s bloodlust. The Cauldron Fae is harnessing power <br>for her greatest spell yet, which will be: “I do not believe <br>that there are people in London. ” The fairy’s goal is to get <br>rid of all the unwelcome humans in her beloved home <br>(including the Lost Boys), saving only Pietrik, to whom she <br>has become attached. To succeed, however, the fairy needs <br>power, which can only be generated by the passionate spirit <br>of young people rebelling against oppressive modernity. <br>For this reason, the Cauldron Fae encourages Pietrik and <br>his followers to strike London’s businesses more and more <br>often. Around the city have been engraved the Seals of the <br>fairy, and only those who already possess one can see the <br>others. The Lost Boys use theirs to activate the other Seals, <br>tap into the Cauldron Fae’s power, and perform small feats <br>of magic.<br>Distraught by the disappearance of his daughter, George <br>Carnarvon sent his best agents into the city. Most <br>disappeared and the remains of the few who were found <br>had been torn by savage wounds. Only at that point was <br>Carnavon willing to admit that the Hunters had skills his <br>men lacked and that made them uniquely suited to confront <br>occult powers. George is concerned for his daughter’s life, <br>and the fact that no one asked for a ransom makes him fear <br>the worst for Gwendolyn.</p><p>1<br>82</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513710167,"modifiedTime":1781513710167,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"z1tJrMoHH8SHd9Kw","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>I Don't Believe - Scene 1</h2><p>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You have just arrived in <br>London but, despite the exhaustion of your recent journey, <br>Lord Carnarvon has peremptorily summoned you. Tucked <br>away in one of the great homes in the city center, you find <br>yourself at the table with a fifty-year-old nobleman. The <br>puffy, dark circles around his eyes and his pale face leave you <br>with the impression that your host is very concerned about <br>what is happening in London.<br>Place: The London villa of the Carnarvon family.<br>Time: It is the late afternoon of a gloomy autumn day. <br>Initial Situation: George will update the Hunters with <br>all that happened so far. The nobleman will not hide his <br>deep concern for the fate of his daughter Gwendolyn.<br>Information: From the interview with George, the <br>Hunters will obtain the following information.<br> ◆ London is under attack by a large gang of young rebels. <br>The boys, all between the ages of ten and sixteen, hit <br>the most prosperous activities of the city, causing <br>serious accidents, damaging the tools and machinery <br>and, often, even the workers. The gang exhibits a <br>clear penchant for rebellion, focused on the nascent <br>industrial hub of London.<br> ◆ George’s sixteen-year-old daughter, Gwendolyn, was <br>abducted two days ago. The young woman has always <br>been a little rebellious but had never openly revolted <br>against her family. George fears that she has approached <br>the gang of youngsters driven by curiosity and that she <br>has been taken by them against her will. No ransom <br>demand has been made for the young woman, and that <br>makes George fear the worst. A desperate father before <br>anything else, Lord Carnavon will make it clear that <br>finding his daughter is more important to him than the <br>fate of the entire city.<br> ◆ After the clash that ended in a bloodbath the night <br>before, it is clear that the young rioters have something <br>occult on their side. Basil, the only survivor of the <br>attack, said that afterward the young attackers literally <br>disappeared through one of the walls. <br>At the end of the interview, George will be available to lead <br>the Hunters to several places:<br> ◆ To Gwendolyn’s rooms inside the palace, where the <br>Hunters can search for clues to the disappearance of <br>the young woman and interrogate her personal maid: <br>Joanna.<br> ◆ At the Sirens’ Inn, in the lower neighborhoods of <br>London, where Basil rests to recover from his injuries.<br> ◆ At the Skullem Factory, a shipyard that George fears <br>will be the next target of the young rioters.<br>Note: George will be as helpful as possible to the Hunters, <br>but it will be clear that the man is psychologically and <br>physically worn out by the events of the last days. The <br>Hunters can decide whether to keep him by their side or <br>not.<br>Note: In this Scenario, Pietrik and the Lost Boys Gang <br>can use the power of the Seals that the Cauldron Fae has <br>engraved all over London. At least one Seal, to be activated <br>at will, is always present in all the Places of the Scenario.</p><p>83<br>Threat – Seal of the Cauldron Fae<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: A magic seal capable of manifesting the magic <br>of the Cauldron Fae.<br>Gift – Seals Everywhere:  At least one Seal of the <br>Cauldron Fae is present in all the Places of the Scenario. <br>Whoever possesses the Gang Seal or Personal Seal Gift  <br>can activate the effect of the Seal of the Cauldron Fae as an <br>additional action; this allows them to teleport to another <br>place featuring a Seal. The Seals are invisible to the human <br>eye and can be used only by those who have a tattooed eye <br>on their hand, placing said tattoo in front of the right eye. <br>Those who use magic can detect the presence of a Seal, but <br>the Seal of Disbelief Scenario Gift is necessary to activate it. <br>Note: Some Places feature more than one Seal to grant <br>the Lost Boys more narrative options in case the Hunters <br>manage to impede access to a Seal or negate the Gift. <br>George Carnarvon<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am the head of the Carnarvon family and my <br>service to the Crown has brought me a great deal of influence. <br>I fear the occult and magic. I can’t sleep due to worry over my <br>daughter’s abduction.<br>Agenda: Stop the gang of rebels that plagues London, but <br>more than anything else find my beloved daughter Gwendolyn.<br>Carnarvon House<br>Descriptor: A rich and large mansion in the heart of <br>London.<br>Joanna called Nana the Servant<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I have been Lady Gwendolyn’s trusted personal <br>servant for over ten years. I saw the young heir grow up and I <br>am as fond of her as if she were my own daughter.<br>Information: Joanna will tell the Hunters that she often <br>heard Gwendolyn chatting with a boy in her room, but <br>when she came in to figure out who it was, she never found <br>anyone. Gwendolyn has always avoided revealing the boy’s <br>identity, convincing Nana that he was some noble son of <br>a good family in the city. Searching Gwendolyn’s room, <br>the Hunters will find some poppy petals under the bed. <br>Nana will say that those flowers can only be found in the <br>Kensington Gardens in London.<br>Seals: There is only one Seal in the Carnarvon villa, <br>inscribed on the east wall of Gwendolyn’s room.</p><p>84<br>The Cauldron Fae’s Lair<br>Descriptor: An extensive maze of caves and galleries stretching beneath all of <br>Kensington’s Gardens. Within it, all kinds of plants and flowers grow luxuriantly <br>thanks to the Cauldron Fae’s power.<br>Threat – Nature Rises Up<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: Navigating inside the lair without the consent of the Cauldron Fae <br>exposes the intruders to the ire of the many plants. Ivy tentacles and pollen mists rise to <br>block those who walk without their lady’s approval.<br>Mtyrya the Fairy also called the <br>Cauldron Fae<br>OL Hard 7 – Main NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am an ancient fairy bound to nature. I hate humans and modernity. Thanks <br>to my power, anything others believe to be impossible, I can make possible.<br>Agenda: Prevent humans from covering my beloved land with dirty, stinking factories / Save <br>Pietrik from the punishment I plan to inflict upon London.<br>Gift – The Magic of Disbelief:  As an action, the Cauldron Fae can formulate a magic <br>sentence including the fragment I don’t believe and make its effect concrete. For example, <br>“I don’t believe in gravity” would allow her to fly, while “I don’t believe the Hunters of the <br>Order exist” would allow her to hurt the Hunters in an attempt to make them disappear. <br>If the statement does not have offensive effects, the duration of the power is generally for <br>the entire Scene. If, on the other hand, the effect is likely to harm a target, it will inflict <br>1 Wound without the possibility of attempting a Defense Check. Those who use magic can <br>try to counteract the Magic of Disbelief, and preventing Mtyrya from speaking words would <br>automatically cancel the Gift’s effect.</p><p>85<br>Gift – Ancient Fairy:  The Cauldron Fae is immortal as <br>long as her beloved plants thrive under the Kensington <br>Gardens. The true focus of her power is the rebellious spirit <br>of her young servants. The fairy starts the Scenario with <br>3 Power Tokens and can spend 1 to return from death, <br>mending all the Wounds she has suffered. Each time a <br>factory or equivalent is destroyed in retaliation against <br>modernity, she receives 1 Power Token. The Cauldron <br>Fae can spend 4 Power Tokens to unleash all her power <br>and apply the effect of the Magic of Disbelief Gift to all of <br>London.<br>London’s Slums<br>Descriptor: Wretched alleys and houses where all the poor <br>of London live.<br>Information: In the slums, you can always find 1d6+6 <br>members of the Lost Boys Gang. When he’s not on a <br>mission or at Gwendolyn’s, Pietrik is here too.<br>Seals: Almost every main street in the slums has a Seal <br>somewhere.<br>The Sirens’ Inn<br>Descriptor: A dirty inn in the lower neighborhoods, hiding <br>a clandestine stall. Poor people and prostitutes flock inside to <br>find a roof to rest under.<br>Information: Basil resides at the inn because it is the <br>only one he can afford with the low salary provided by the <br>Carnarvon family. The man will badmouth his employer (if <br>not present) and will tell the Hunters that his companions <br>were literally ripped apart before exploding horribly. The <br>youngsters’ leader (a boy with typical Eastern European <br>features) pronounced the words “I don’t believe in guards” <br>right before the bloodbath. Basil is the only one who <br>wasn’t affected, but he hurt his leg falling down while <br>fleeing (a detail he omitted during George’s account) and is <br>determined to leave London as soon as he can walk again.<br>Pietrik has been watching Basil since he came to the inn, and <br>the Hunters will notice the young man (which corresponds <br>to Basil’s description) after some time there. If cornered, <br>Pietrik will escape thanks to the power of the Seal.<br>Seals: There are two Seals in the Sirens’ Inn, one in the <br>hallway in front of Basil’s room and the other in the main <br>hall near the front door.<br>Basil the Survivor<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a coward only concerned with making <br>ends meet. <br>Agenda: To get back on my feet and escape from London, <br>away from rebels and magic.</p><p>86<br>Pietrik<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a young rebel and I fight the creeping industrialization of London with <br>all my strength.<br>Agenda: Destroy all the factories to avenge my sister’s death / Convince Gwendolyn to <br>join my gang because I have fallen in love with her. <br>Gift – The Needle of Living Shadows: Thanks to the power of the magic needle <br>the Cauldron Fae gave him, once per Scene Pietrik can separate the shadow from <br>his body and make it act like an NPC with its own profile. The shadow has 1 <br>Wound and can slip through the smallest crack. <br>Gift – Personal Seal: Pietrik has the Seal of Disbelief tattooed on the palm <br>of his hand, so once per Scene, he can activate the Gift The Magic of Disbelief <br>(page 84). As with the Gang Seal Gift (page 87), Pietrik can activate any <br>Seal present in London. <br>The Skullem Factory<br>Descriptor: A large shipyard in which metal components for ships are <br>being assembled.<br>Information: Inside the factory, there are two large industrial <br>ovens for metal welding. The goal of the Lost Boys is to blow <br>them up by throwing the magic berries that Pietrik has given <br>out into them. The raid will take place at night and involves 10 <br>Lost Boys, in addition to Pietrik. <br>Seals: The only Seal in the area of the Skullem Factory is <br>located in the alley at the back of the building.</p><p>87<br>The Gang of the Lost Boys<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are young rebels who have lost everything <br>and are ready to die for our leader Pietrik.<br>Agenda: To help Pietrik in his plan for the destruction of <br>London. <br>Gift – Gang Seal:  Each gang member has a tattooed eye <br>on their right hand that allows them to see and use the Seals <br>of the Cauldron Fae scattered throughout London.<br>Gift – Rioter:  Each gang member increases his OL by <br>1 when acting with the support of at least one teammate. <br>Each member has a magic berry that they can throw which <br>will explode on contact, inflicting 1 Wound on all targets <br>within several feet. A Defense Check allows a target to leap <br>away from the blast zone.    <br>Kensington Gardens<br>Descriptor: A large green area in the heart of London. <br>Access to the gardens is prohibited due to ongoing <br>maintenance work. <br>Information: The Kensington Gardens have been long <br>abandoned because the Cauldron Fae uses her magic to <br>create unending problems for the gardeners. No one has <br>entered the gardens for over a year and Pietrik has used an <br>old gardeners’ house as a prison to keep Gwendolyn locked <br>up. The girl hasn’t tried to escape and hopes, so far in vain, <br>to convince Pietrik to give up on his destructive plans. <br>It is possible to descend through a well in <br>the eastern part of the park to access the <br>Cauldron Fae’s Lair. <br>Seals: The Gardens are literally full of <br>Seals.<br>Gwendolyn<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC  <br>(1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am the young heir of <br>the Carnarvon family, but I dream <br>of a life of travel and freedom, <br>exploring the world. I am good at <br>telling stories, and that is how I <br>got closer to Pietrik.<br>Agenda: To convince Pietrik <br>to desist from his revenge. <br>I understand how much <br>pain his heart holds and <br>I would like to welcome <br>him into my family to <br>give him a different <br>future.</p><p>88<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario, there are six Events. As a Storyteller, feel <br>free to create new ones in response to the actions of the <br>Hunters.<br>If the Cauldron Fae reaches 4 Power Tokens:  she <br>will be ready to kill all humans in London but will not do so <br>until she has secured Pietrik safely in her lair.<br>If Pietrik understands the true objective of the <br>Cauldron Fae: he will betray his mistress to try to save <br>Gwendolyn and the Lost Boys.<br>If the Hunters free Gwendolyn: the young woman will <br>tell the sad tale of Pietrik’s past, trying to make the Hunters <br>understand that the boy acts out of resentment and not true <br>evil.<br>If the Hunters capture one of the Lost Boys:  if put <br>under pressure, he will reveal that the whole gang follows <br>Pietrik’s lead and he is the only one who knows the identity <br>of the sorceress who has bestowed powers on everyone. <br>If the Hunters use Gwendolyn as bait for Pietrik:  <br>the young man will give up any involvement with the gang <br>to be with his beloved. <br>If the Lost Boys succeed in destroying the Skullem <br>Factory: one of them will be injured in the explosion and <br>can be captured by the Hunters. <br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the I Don’t <br>Believe Scenario and can be acquired once the conditions <br>are met. A Hunter can only have one Scenario Gift and if <br>they acquire a new one, they will have to forgo the previous <br>one.<br>Seal of Disbelief<br>Requirement: Capture or eliminate a member of the Lost <br>Boys.<br>Y ou studied the strange Seal that unites the entire gang <br>of young rebels and created one just like it on your hand. <br>When you bring your hand over your right eye you can see <br>the Seals of the Cauldron Fae engraved throughout London. <br>By spending 1 Soma you can cross a Seal to get to another <br>Seal whose location you know. Thanks to the Seal, you can <br>perform a Defense Check to prevent the Magic of Disbelief <br>from having an effect on you. <br>Support of a Lord <br>Requirement: Save Gwendolyn from Pietrik’s clutches.<br>Y ou saved the young heir to the Carnarvon family and for <br>this, you were given a medallion bearing the family coat <br>of arms. Receive 1 Additional Success when you use the <br>Carnarvon coat of arms in a context when having a powerful <br>noble’s favor might be useful. Add the Medallion bearing the <br>Carnarvon Coat of Arms and a large sum of money to your <br>equipment.<br>The Challenger (Special Gift for James the <br>Swordsman)<br>Requirement: Face Pietrik or the Lost Boys at least once.<br>The young rioters and their boss remind you of the band</p><p>1<br>2a<br>2b<br>89<br>of cowards who trapped you and are responsible for you <br>losing your hand. Receive 1 Additional Success for every <br>action you take against them if it means you defeat or <br>humiliate them. If you abandon a fight or are forced to <br>retreat, you lose 1 Soma out of shame.<br>The Scenario I Don’t <br>Believe in Scenes</p><p>FIRST SCENE – The summoning<br>It’s the same one you find on page 82. <br>End of Scene:  After the interview with George, the <br>Hunters can decide whether to collect clues at the <br>Carnarvon villa (SECOND SCENE OPTION A – On <br>Gwendolyn’s trail) or go to the Sirens’ Inn to talk to Basil <br>(SECOND SCENE OPTION B – Basil’s tale).</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513710168,"modifiedTime":1781513710168,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"UgsxeY5tJTayX2Dh","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>I Don't Believe - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE OPTION A <br>– On Gwendolyn’s trail <br>Read aloud to the Hunters: George takes you through the <br>private rooms of his villa, to Gwendolyn’s room. Waiting for <br>you is the girl’s personal maid, a thirty-year-old woman with <br>typical Eastern European features. The servant introduces <br>herself as Nana, a nickname Gwendolyn had given her. The <br>room of the young Carnarvon girl is the classic room of a <br>young lady, full of books and maps of the world.<br>Place: Gwendolyn Carnarvon’s bedroom.<br>Time: A bit later in the afternoon of a gloomy autumn day.<br>Information: Speaking with Nana, it will be clear to <br>the Hunters that the servant is sincerely concerned about <br>Gwendolyn’s fate; this should dispel any doubts about the <br>servant’s involvement in the disappearance. Nana will tell <br>the Hunters about the frequent night visits that Gwendolyn <br>received, but without being able to put a face or name to <br>her nightly visitor. At the end of the interview, Nana will <br>give the Hunters the poppy petals she found under the bed. <br>From a quick investigation, the Hunters will discover that <br>those flowers are typical of the Kensington Gardens.<br>End of Scene: The Hunters will move towards the gardens <br>to follow the petals’ trail. Go to the THIRD SCENE – The <br>Gardens.</p><p>SECOND SCENE OPTION B – <br>Basil’s Tale<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You easily find the Sirens’ <br>Inn; it is a dive bar in the slums where the poor and drunks <br>belly up at the bar for a cheap beer. You recognize Basil from <br>the leg bandage and the old wooden crutch resting next to <br>his chair. The young man looks drunk, sipping a beer while <br>complaining about the misfortune he had in ending up in the <br>service of Lord Carnarvon.<br>Place: The run-down Sirens’ Inn, full of patrons and poor <br>people.<br>Time: The sun has just set and the large fireplace of the inn <br>casts the patrons’ long shadows on the dirty walls. <br>Information: Talking to Basil, you will get all the <br>information on page 85. During the interview, the <br>Hunters will notice a boy watching them sitting in front of <br>one of the large windows. Once Pietrik understands that</p><p>3<br>4<br>90<br>the Hunters are investigating the Lost Boys, he will launch an <br>assault supported by 8 of his crew. If the fight turns against <br>them, Pietrik and his comrades will escape thanks to the <br>Seals. However, at least one of the Lost Boys will stay behind <br>and can be captured by the Hunters. After the interrogation, <br>the Hunters will ascertain that the gang’s next target is the <br>Skullem Factory. <br>End of Scene:  The Hunters must run to prevent the <br>impending attack on the factory. Go to FOURTH SCENE – <br>The assault on Skullem.</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513710168,"modifiedTime":1781513710168,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"bHVIOIbITF0Nxk4W","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>I Don't Believe - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE –  The Gardens<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  The Kensington Gardens are <br>an architectural and botanical wonder, and even months of <br>abandonment by the gardeners can’t entirely spoil their beauty. <br>Lord Carnarvon got you a key with great ease and you can <br>venture into the park using the main gate. As you step forward, <br>your attention is drawn to a small house in the middle of the <br>park where you clearly see a human figure holding a lantern. <br>It is more than a little suspicious, as no one is supposed to be <br>in the Gardens.<br>Place: The beautiful Kensington Gardens. <br>Time: Night has just fallen.<br>Information: Once at the house, the <br>Hunters will surprise Pietrik as he brings <br>food to Gwendolyn. The young man will <br>try to drive the Hunters out. If it fails, he <br>will flee, flying away (thanks to the power <br>of the Personal Seal Gift). By interrogating Gwendolyn, the <br>Hunters will learn of the attack on the Skullem Factory. <br>End of Scene:  The Hunters must run to prevent the <br>impending attack on the factory. Go to FOURTH SCENE – <br>The assault on Skullem.</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513710168,"modifiedTime":1781513710168,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"eb3hnzXc9jzCjKgl","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>I Don't Believe - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE –  The assault <br>on Skullem<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  When you reach the factory, <br>the first flames are already devouring the building. Among <br>workers and guards on the run, you clearly see a gang of boys <br>throwing strange berries that explode like bombs when they <br>hit the ground. The youngsters’ targets are the two large ovens, <br>which, if blown up, would intensify the flames, engulfing the <br>entire district.<br>Place: The Skullem Factory, besieged by the Lost Boys.<br>Time: It is late at night, but the flames that lick the building <br>illuminate everything as if it were day.<br>Information: Pietrik, with the support of <br>10 Lost Boys, will fight the Hunters. At the <br>end of the clash, several situations may occur.<br> ◆ If Pietrik is captured by the Hunters, he <br>can be persuaded to speak (using Gwendolyn <br>as a lever will be a great strategy); the young <br>man will reveal the location of the Cauldron <br>Fae’s Lair.<br> ◆ If Pietrik escapes, one of the captured <br>Lost Boys will reveal what Pietrik said: the</p><p>5<br>91<br>power of the Seals comes from a sorcerer hiding under <br>Kensington Gardens.<br> ◆ In both cases, the captured gang member will reveal that <br>the goal of the Lost Boys is to destroy what is modern in <br>order to bring peace to London. <br>End of Scene: It will be clear for the Hunters that the one <br>who pulls the strings of the whole story hides under the <br>Kensington Gardens. Go to FIFTH SCENE – The Cauldron <br>Fae.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513710168,"modifiedTime":1781513710168,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ixWLSGA2rZSygtDW","name":"Scene 5","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>I Don't Believe - Scene 5</h2><p>FIFTH SCENE –  The Cauldron <br>Fae<br>This Scene has no precise breakdown because it can be <br>approached in different ways by the Hunters. The Cauldron <br>Fae will be willing to compromise to save Pietrik, or fight to <br>the death if the Hunters prove hostile. Whatever happens, <br>it will be clear that the old fairy cannot accept the change <br>that is slowly transforming her beloved city into a large <br>industrial metropolis.</p>"},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513710168,"modifiedTime":1781513710168,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"i-dont-believe","collection":"The Broken Ones","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","pages":"81-92"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513710168,"modifiedTime":1781513710168,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"VVrgslOKg1WL5E8j","name":"Hunger Island","pages":[{"_id":"2UZFtzmD86xPSaDM","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>Hunger Island</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> The Broken Ones</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 93-108.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/hunger-island-p93-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513714972,"modifiedTime":1781513714972,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"jAv5HHl7OrDVyikq","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Hunger Island - Setup</h2><p>92<br>Once upon a time…<br>Strange news comes from far away Iceland: the <br>great volcano Laki has unleashed its full might <br>and has stricken down the poor inhabitants of <br>the small villages on the island, like a divine <br>punishment. Few have managed to escape the fury <br>of fire and ash, but one in particular, the humble <br>logger Heino, tells of strange events in his village <br>and of an ancient power that seems to have taken <br>possession of many young inhabitants. The first <br>rescue expedition was sent to the small village of <br>Hosn, but no news has reached Denmark for over <br>a month. Considering Heino’s delirious tales, the <br>crown has decided to turn directly to the Papacy <br>for help, hoping the Church can determine if the <br>Devil himself could be behind the terrible famine. <br>A small ship has set sail for Iceland, though the <br>island is still shrouded in the fumes of Laki’s fury. <br>Among the crew is a group of Hunters, handpicked <br>to unravel this mystery.<br>A Scenario Inspired by Hansel <br>and Gretel (Grimm Brothers)<br>Hunger Island<br>Safety Keywords:  <br>Cannibalism / Catastrophe / Deprivation</p><p>93<br>The story that led us here…<br>A few months have passed since the eruption of <br>the volcano Laki, which has wiped out most of the livestock <br>and inhabitants of the island, throwing Iceland into the <br>greatest famine of its history. In the village of Hosn, the <br>residents have found a macabre way to stave off starvation. <br>They sacrifice and feed on the weakest among them. Heino, <br>a poor woodcutter, sensed that his beloved children Hanse <br>and Gréte would be the next victims. Rather than see them <br>served up as meat, Heino led them to the base of Laki, <br>where he hoped they would find a quicker and less painful <br>end. In the mists and fumes of the volcano, however, <br>the two young people did not find death, but an ancient <br>stone, fallen from the sky at the dawn of the world itself. <br>Corrupted by the power enclosed in it, Hanse and Gréte <br>have changed, becoming superhuman beings who need <br>fresh meat to constantly regenerate their bodies. Deciding <br>to spread their new ‘gifts’ , the two children returned to <br>Hosn. Brother and sister infected the other village children <br>with the stone’s power, putting power in new hands. Now <br>adults have become livestock for the children exposed to <br>the power of the stone. The new mutants call themselves <br>Maws, the name by which Hanse and Gréte baptized this <br>new breed of Icelandic people. In one case, however, Hanse <br>granted his sister’s Gréte request for mercy. The two Maws <br>escorted their father to the port of Vík í Mýrdal, putting <br>him on one of the last ships to leave for the continent.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>Most of the island is under the control of the Maws, who <br>lack fresh food and now guard Vík í Mýrdal in the hope of <br>ambushing incoming ships. Berend, captain of the ship of <br>the previous expedition, and Althea, a traveling nun in the <br>service of the Order, are also hiding in Vík í Mýrdal, now <br>a ghost town. The Maws control the only two inhabited <br>places that escaped the fury of the volcano Laki: the port <br>of Vík í Mýrdal and the village of Hosn. They also guard <br>the volcano itself, where the stone is venerated as a deity. <br>The lack of food has made the Maws increasingly aggressive <br>and violent, and even Hanse and Gréte are beginning to <br>struggle to keep them in control. In Hosn, where the few <br>remaining humans are kept in a large cage waiting to be <br>slaughtered, Hanse must increasingly maintain order by <br>force, to prevent the most hungry Maws from massacring <br>the few survivors and consuming all the food stocks in <br>one night. In Vík í Mýrdal, Gréte leads a group of the most <br>faithful Maws, looking for a way to attract new boats to the <br>island.</p><p>1<br>94</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513714973,"modifiedTime":1781513714973,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"99BSKLablvmbK9AW","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Hunger Island - Scene 1</h2><p>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  After more than a week of <br>sailing, you finally catch a glimpse of the Icelandic coast and the <br>outlines of the port of Vík í Mýrdal. The smoking silhouette of the <br>great volcano stands out on the horizon like a hulking monster <br>looming over the entire island. With a few skillful maneuvers, <br>Captain Arne guides the ship into port, easily navigating the <br>thick blanket of fog and soot that seems to envelop everything. <br>The air is heavy and, around you, the world is a clouded, smoky <br>gray. You can feel a thrill of fear going up your back as you <br>contemplate the unnatural silence surrounding the port. No one <br>is present to welcome you and, at a closer look, the city seems <br>deserted.<br>Place: The port of Vík í Mýrdal, lost in fog.<br>Time: It is early afternoon, even though the fog that covers <br>the whole island means the light is dulled to the point of soft  <br>twilight.<br>Initial Situation: The ship is docked in the port and it is <br>immediately clear to everyone that the city is uninhabited. <br>The ship that brought the previous expedition is docked not <br>far away, looking abandoned as well. <br>Information: When interacting with Captain Arne, the <br>Hunters will learn that the entire crew is quite tense. The sailors <br>are skilled sea wolves, and for this reason deeply superstitious. <br>Only Arne, who comes from a military background, remains <br>cold and calculating at the spectacle of the ghost port. Arne <br>will guarantee the full support of his men to the Hunters: it <br>will be up to them to decide whether or not to make use of <br>the support. <br>Note: In this Scenario the Hunters will travel between Vík <br>í Mýrdal, the village of Hosn, and the volcano Laki. Each <br>journey takes 2 days on foot and must pass through The Mist <br>Roads (page 98).<br>Arne the Captain<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I once was a military man and I’ve earned the <br>crown’s respect. Now, as a ship’s captain, I serve my country and <br>boast about my crew. <br>Agenda: Do my best to carry out the mission I was entrusted <br>with. However, I won’t put the people under my command at <br>risk.<br>Sailors<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are sailors under Captain Arne’s orders. We <br>are skilled sea wolves, more comfortable at sea than on land.<br>Agenda: Execute Arne’s orders and avoid in any way having to <br>face the supernatural.</p><p>95<br>The Port of Vík í <br>Mýrdal<br>Descriptor: The large port of a city <br>that was built to be a point of arrival <br>from the mainland. Ships and houses are <br>in a state of complete disuse.<br>Information: Walking around the <br>port and on the ship of the previous <br>expedition, the Hunters can obtain in <br>order the following information:<br> ◆ The city is indeed deserted. Crates <br>still hanging on hoists and torches <br>left untended, so that parts of the <br>docks are charred and burned, <br>suggest that the inhabitants have <br>abandoned what they were doing <br>when disaster struck.<br> ◆ Traces of blood and the remains of <br>devoured humans can be found in <br>the dark recesses of the harbor. It is <br>as if a pack of wild beasts assaulted the inhabitants to <br>drag them into darkness and devour them.<br> ◆ In the small harbor master’s office, the Hunters will <br>find on the front door a message written in blood: the <br>lighthouse is safe. The message is written in poor Latin, <br>with the clear intention of making it unreadable for the <br>natives of the island. It indicates the place where Althea <br>and Berend took refuge, and was written by the nun for <br>a possible group of Hunters. <br>For any information the Hunters receive, <br>you can decide to roll a die or choose <br>what happens:<br>1-2: A group of 8 Maws ambushes the <br>Hunters.<br>3-4: A group of 8 Maws led by Gréte <br>ambushes the Hunters. Gréte will <br>remain on the sidelines to lead the <br>attack and gather information about the <br>newcomers.<br>5-6: Berend watches the Hunters from <br>afar to discern who they are and why <br>they’ve come. He will eventually try to <br>approach them for help, but only when <br>it is safe from the Maws.<br>Gréte<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC  <br>(4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am the incarnation of <br>the power of the great Maw. My body <br>regenerates thanks to the flesh I eat, my strength and my <br>speed are unbelievable. <br>Agenda: Keep capturing new humans to ensure a future <br>for the Maw’s offspring. Unlike my brother Hanse, I still have <br>a shred of humanity and I wouldn’t want to devour anyone <br>indiscriminately / I want to convince my friend Ina to become <br>a Maw.<br>Gift – Mutant Maw:  As long as they maintain their <br>original appearance, a mutant Maw appears in every way as <br>a common child. When they unleash their power, the body <br>shifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing a</p><p>96<br>long line of sharp teeth. A mutant is considered to be of a <br>higher OL category for every physical action they perform <br>involving speed, strength, or ferocity. A mutant perceives <br>the smell of human flesh, which they find intoxicating, and <br>for this reason every attempt to hide from their sense of <br>smell receives 1 Penalty. When a mutant begins to devour <br>flesh (human or animal), they cannot stop until they have <br>finished it. Once per Scene, when a mutant Maw inflicts <br>1 Wound by devouring fresh meat, they recover 1 Wound <br>they suffered.<br>Gift – First Maw:  As the firstborn among the Maws, <br>Gréte has learned to manipulate the power that she <br>harbors in her body. During a Scene, Gréte may self-inflict <br>1 Wound to benefit from one of the following effects:  <br>1. Superhuman Strength, if she inflicts 1 Wound with <br>an action and does not devour the target, Gréte can throw <br>it 15 feet away. The target will fall to the ground and suffer 1 <br>additional Wound if they impact an obstacle. Gréte can use <br>her strength to throw one enemy into another, in which case <br>the target can try to dodge the attack with a Defense Check. <br>2. Superhuman Speed , Gréte can make an incredible <br>leap of over 30 feet. She does not need any preparation, <br>and she can take another subject with her while moving. <br>3. Rebirth, Gréte falls into a state of apparent death to <br>regenerate in the next Scene. She wakes up completely <br>healed. Only a highly skilled doctor or someone using <br>magical means is able to discern Gréte is not truly dead.  <br>The Maws<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: We are a new people, children of the great <br>Maw. Our bodies regenerate thanks to the flesh we eat. Our <br>strength and speed are incredible. <br>Agenda: We obey Gréte and Hanse, they are the firstborns, <br>they know the right path / Satiate our infinite hunger, even at <br>the cost of disobeying the firstborns.<br>Gift – Mutant Maw:  As long as they maintain their <br>original appearance, a mutant Maw appears in every way as <br>a common child. When they unleash their power, the body <br>shifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing <br>a long line of sharp teeth. A mutant is considered to be of a <br>higher OL category for every physical action they perform <br>involving speed, strength, or ferocity. A mutant perceives <br>the smell of human flesh, which they find intoxicating, and <br>for this reason every attempt to hide from their sense of <br>smell receives 1 Penalty. When a mutant begins to devour <br>flesh (human or animal), they cannot stop until they have <br>finished it. Once per Scene, when a mutant Maw inflicts <br>1 Wound by devouring fresh meat, they recover 1 Wound <br>they suffered.</p><p>97<br>Berend the Crazed Captain <br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am the captain of the previous expedition <br>and the only one left of my crew. I learned to survive by <br>masking my smell with the stench of rotten fish.<br>Agenda: Wait for someone to come from the mainland to <br>save me.<br>Gift – Stinking Survivor:  Berend managed to avoid <br>being devoured by the Maws, but what he saw happen <br>to his companions scarred his mind forever. The man <br>constantly covers himself with rotten fish because he has <br>discovered the stench conceals him from the Maws. <br>Berend will never be targeted by a Maw unless he <br>takes direct action against them. As long as he <br>is at the port of Vík í Mýrdal, Berend can move <br>with great skill through the alleys and take <br>any companions anywhere in the city without <br>attracting the attention of the Maws. Each <br>time he uses this ability, he rolls 1 die: on 5 <br>or 6, Berend convinces himself that he has <br>seen other survivors and makes noise in an <br>attempt to get their attention. It will be <br>clear to those that accompany him that <br>the whole situation is nothing <br>more than a figment <br>of the poor man’s <br>distressed mind.<br>Vík í Mýrdal’s Lighthouse<br>Descriptor: An old lighthouse in the oldest part of the port <br>of Vík í Mýrdal. Crates of fish have been broken open and <br>spilled around the lighthouse, their contents left to rot in the <br>sun. Now, the air reeks in a nauseating way.<br>Gift – Safe Haven from the Maws: The stacks of rotten <br>fish that Berend and Althea constantly throw at the foot of <br>the lighthouse keep the Maws away. The Maws lose all trace <br>of someone who takes refuge in the lighthouse. While near <br>the lighthouse, Maws reduce their Opposition Level by 1.<br>Information: Althea will have a great deal of information <br>for the Hunters. She has been trapped for a month now, and <br>has taken the opportunity to study the Maws in depth.<br> ◆ The Maws look like children mutated by something. <br>They are strong, fast, and seem to follow the smell of <br>human flesh.<br> ◆ Some desperate people fleeing from the village of Hosn <br>have told them of two “leaders” of the Maws, brother <br>and sister, who apparently are smarter and more <br>powerful than the others.<br> ◆ After overhearing Maws talking to each other, Althea <br>realized that the volcano is a sacred place for those <br>strange beings that humans must not enter.<br> ◆ Both the village and the volcano are two days’ walk <br>from Vík í Mýrdal, but in different directions.</p><p>98<br>Althea the Agent of the Order<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a nun in the service of the Order and, <br>despite my ecclesiastical background, I have skills as a spy and <br>a fighter. The Order entrusts me with high-risk tasks because <br>it has confidence in my unwavering faith and ruthlessness.<br>Agenda: Solve the mystery of the Maws and provide support <br>to the Hunters of the Order.<br>Gift – Agent of the Order: Althea is talented and trained to support the Hunters. Althea can spend her action to <br>support a Hunter’s action and give them 1 Additional <br>Success in any Check.<br>The Mist Roads<br>Descriptor: All the communication routes between Vík í <br>Mýrdal and the nearby villages are surrounded by a dense, <br>dark fog that does not allow you to see more than a few feet <br>ahead.<br>For each trip on the Mist Roads, you can choose or roll for <br>a Threat/encounter with an NPC.<br>1-2: A crevasse created by the eruption of Laki has <br>opened up, barring the way.<br>Threat – Crevasse in the Mist <br>Descriptor: A crevasse eighteen feet deep, hidden by the <br>dense mist.<br>OL Medium 5<br>Falling into the crevasse will cause 1 Wound. At the bottom, <br>you can find the body of a desperate runaway. As a cost for <br>a Defense Check Outcome, a Hunter may lose equipment <br>that will fall down into the mist.<br>3-4: The mist becomes even thicker, making it <br>impossible to even distinguish the road.<br>Threat – Mist Wall<br>Descriptor: A fog so dense that it is impossible to see <br>anything.<br>OL Hard 7<br>If they fail a Check to stay on the road, the Hunters will get <br>lost and end up in the wrong place.<br>5-6: A group of Maws. A group of 4 Maws who travel in <br>search of fresh meat.</p><p>99<br>The Village of Hosn<br>Descriptor: A small village lost in the hills. Many houses <br>have been burned down, and the stench of corpses hovers in <br>the air.<br>Information: The village is under Hanse’s control. In the <br>small central square, a rudimentary wooden cage was built <br>where the last six inhabitants of the village are trapped. <br>Every day, one inhabitant is taken out to be devoured, but <br>now there are more than twenty Maws and so little flesh is <br>not enough to satisfy their hunger. <br>By saving the inhabitants, the Hunters will be able to obtain <br>some information:<br> ◆ Ina is a little girl who refused to become a Maw. She is a <br>friend of Gréte, who explicitly asked her brother Hanse <br>to keep Ina last, in the hope that she will change her <br>mind and convert. Ina is aware of the friendship that <br>Gréte feels towards her and how this is a weak point <br>within the Maw.<br> ◆ Askell is a young hunter who killed a Maw when Hanse <br>and Gréte took control of the village. As punishment his <br>hands were devoured and now Askell is kept alive only <br>to see all his loved ones die one after the other. He hates <br>the Maws and killing them has become an obsession <br>for him. Askell knows a secret road that allows you to <br>reach the volcano, avoiding the complications of the <br>Mist Roads. <br> ◆ Alba is Askell’s mother. She is now utterly devastated, <br>after seeing her husband Helg eaten alive by the Maws <br>and her son reduced to impotence. Alba has a key to <br>the cellars of the town hall, a shelter from volcanic <br>eruptions where many supplies are stashed. <br> ◆ Enoch is one of the village elders. He was the first to <br>acknowledge the idea of eating the helpless to survive. <br>All the Maws hate him and would attack him without <br>a second thought, if only they had the chance. Hanse <br>keeps him alive, pondering the most convoluted <br>possible way to eliminate him when the time comes.<br> ◆ Erna is a young woman without children. She has <br>always hated living on the island and was only here to <br>follow her husband who has already been devoured <br>by the Maws. Erna has heard Hanse talking to other <br>Maws about a “stone that came from the sky” kept in <br>the volcano, which must be defended at all costs. <br> ◆ Hafnar is a plump businessman who is being fed with <br>the little food left in the village. Hanse’s intention is to <br>fatten up Hafnar to make him more delicious for his <br>Maws. Hafnar possesses a dose of a potent rat poison <br>that he has already used to kill two Maws in the first <br>few days. His intention is to sprinkle his body with <br>the poison on the day he is devoured, to take as many <br>Maws with him as possible.</p><p>100<br>Hanse<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor:  I am the incarnation of the power of the great Maw. My body <br>regenerates thanks to the flesh I eat. My strength and my speed are unbelievable. <br>Agenda: Keep capturing new humans to ensure a future for the Maw’s offspring. <br>Unlike my sister Gréte, I have no regard for humans and, now that I spared my <br>father to make my sister happy, I just want to protect the stone that came from <br>the sky.<br>Gift – Mutant Maw:  As long as they maintain their original appearance, a <br>mutant Maw appears in every way as a common child. When they unleash their <br>power, the body shifts and the mouth widens disproportionately, revealing a <br>long line of sharp teeth. A mutant is considered to be of a higher OL category <br>for every physical action they perform involving speed, strength, or ferocity. <br>A mutant perceives the smell of human flesh, which they find intoxicating, <br>and for this reason, every attempt to hide from their sense of smell receives <br>1 Penalty. When a mutant begins to devour flesh (human or animal), they <br>cannot stop until they have finished it. Once per Scene, when a mutant Maw <br>inflicts 1 Wound by devouring fresh meat, they recover 1 Wound they suffered.<br>Gift – First Maw:  As the firstborn among the Maws, Hanse has learned <br>to manipulate the power that he harbors in his body. During a Scene, <br>Hanse may self-inflict 1 Wound to benefit from one of the following effects:  <br>1. Superhuman Strength , if he inflicts 1 Wound with an action and <br>does not devour the target, Hanse can throw it 15 feet away. The target <br>will fall to the ground and suffer 1 additional Wound if they impact an <br>obstacle. Hanse can use his strength to throw one enemy into another, in <br>which case the target can try to dodge the attack with a Defense Check.  <br>2. Superhuman Speed , Hanse can make an incredible leap of over 30 <br>feet. He does not need any preparation, and he can take another subject with <br>him while moving. 3. Power of the Stone that Came from the Sky , <br>Hanse can tap into the latent power in his body. Once per Scene, all human <br>subjects in his presence lose 2 Soma or alternatively can resist by taking 1 <br>Wound. Suffering the last Wound for this effect does not cause death, but a <br>loss of consciousness.</p><p>101<br>Laki the Volcano<br>Descriptor: A great volcano that dominates all of Iceland. <br>The rock walls have cracked due to the powerful eruptions, <br>creating a series of natural tunnels and galleries. <br>Information: The volcano hides the stone that came <br>from the sky among a maze of tunnels. After the first <br>eruptions, the stone has re-emerged, manifesting its power. <br>To protect the stone, Hanse has left all the Maws that have <br>had issues managing the mutations at the volcano. Those <br>abandoned wretches have grown into Crazed Maws, <br>brainless monsters who wander in search of food. It’s <br>possible for the Hunters to track the Crazed Maws to the <br>stone’s hiding place. Otherwise, the Hunters will face the <br>Threat Daedalus of Tunnels.<br>Threat – Daedalus of Tunnels<br>Descriptor: A series of natural tunnels that change shape <br>according to the tectonic shocks that hit the volcano.<br>OL Hard 7<br>Failing the Check means getting lost, meeting one or more <br>Crazed Maws, or ending up caught in a sudden lava flow, <br>which inflicts 1 Wound and the destruction of one or more <br>pieces of equipment.<br>Crazed Maws<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: A mad abomination whose form constantly <br>shifts, as they wander in search of living beings to devour. <br>Agenda: Eat every living thing, except other Maws.<br>Gift – Mutant Abomination:  A Crazed Maw does not <br>feel any pain. For this reason the Wounds it suffers have <br>no narrative effect but are only a counter to understand <br>when the abomination will crumble into a thousand pieces. <br>Tentacles and arms are constantly born from the body of <br>a Crazed Maw, and as a result it can act 2 times during <br>an Exchange. With one of its actions, a Crazed Maw can <br>slam its huge mass to the ground to create a strong tremor. <br>All targets in the immediate vicinity must pass a Defense <br>Check to avoid falling to the ground.<br>Threat – The Stone that Came from <br>the Sky<br>Descriptor: An alien stone, the size of a fist, that thrums <br>with energy. <br>Gift – Alien Stone:  All the powers of the Maws derive <br>from the stone. With its destruction, the mutations will <br>deteriorate, causing the death of all mutants except Hanse <br>and Gréte. The stone has 6 Wounds and has no OL, because <br>it cannot interact directly or defend itself. For each Wound <br>suffered, a spark of the power comes out, affecting the one <br>who inflicted the blow. Whoever suffers this effect can <br>decide between losing 2 Soma or suffering 1 Wound. If the <br>stone is destroyed or stolen, Hanse will be able to unleash <br>all the latent power in him and, by joining with Gréte, give <br>life to the Great Maw.</p><p>102<br>Threat – The Great Maw<br>Descriptor: A colossal titan of flesh and tentacles born from <br>the union of the two first Maws. The creature acts to recover <br>the stone or avenge its destruction, at the cost of destroying the <br>entire island in the process.<br>OL Hard 7<br>Note: The Storyteller must immediately clarify that the <br>Great Maw is a monster so powerful that it cannot be faced <br>in combat. Its ever-growing mass instantly regenerates every <br>wound, and its colossal size is beyond the reach of any magic. <br>Rather than confronting the Great Maw, the Hunters must <br>curb its action as they rescue the survivors.<br>Here is a list of potential situations:<br> ◆ The stone can be used as bait to force the Great Maw to <br>follow it. Throwing it in the middle of the volcano will <br>cause the titan to follow it, burning to death in a lava pit.<br> ◆ One can still leverage Gréte’s consciousness and her <br>sympathy for Ina, making the Great Maw hesitate for a <br>few moments before Hanse regains control.<br> ◆ When a Defense Check against the Great Maw is failed, <br>in addition to suffering 1 Wound, the target will be <br>pushed away by over thirty feet, suffering 1 additional <br>Wound if it impacts something.<br> ◆ With the force of its roar alone, the Great Maw can hurl <br>a human to the ground.<br> ◆ With a tentacle, the Great Maw can “pick up” a house and <br>hurl it at someone.<br> ◆ Escaping the Great Maw is not easy and the survivors of <br>the village will be a burden for the Hunters.<br> ◆ The Great Maw cannot swim and will stop its chase once <br>the Hunters successfully take to the sea.<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario, there are six Events. As a Storyteller, feel free <br>to create new ones in response to the actions of the Hunters.<br>If the Hunters dismantle the Maw packs in Vík í <br>Mýrdal: Gréte will approach the Hunters pretending to <br>be a survivor. The intention of the Maw is to study these <br>new enemies and provide useful information to her brother <br>Hanse.<br>If the Hunters send sailors alone to explore the port <br>of Vík í Mýrdal: in a short time, the poor unfortunate will <br>be attacked and overwhelmed by the Maws.<br>If Gréte understands that the Hunters are here to <br>save the inhabitants:  the Maw could reveal herself and <br>negotiate to save her friend Ina.<br>If the Hunters arrive in Hosn without worrying <br>about being seen: all the Maws will present themselves as <br>common children and ambush the Hunters when their guard <br>is down. <br>If the Hunters steal or destroy the stone that came <br>from the sky:  mad with rage, Hanse will join his sister <br>Gréte to fuse into the Great Maw.<br>If Gréte is cornered by the Hunters:  she will use her <br>gift to appear dead and, as soon as she wakes up, she will run <br>to join her brother.</p><p>103<br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the Hunger <br>Island Scenario and can be acquired once the conditions are <br>met. A Hunter can only have one Scenario Gift and if they <br>acquire a new one, they will have to forgo the previous one.<br>Stinky<br>Requirement: Meet Berend and learn from him how to <br>mask your scent.<br>Y ou know how to make your scent unrecognizable and <br>confuse enemies and predators. Y ou can spend 1 Soma and <br>cover yourself with a rotting substance that will make you <br>smelly. An enemy who bases their actions on smell (like a <br>Maw) will never target you unless you act directly against <br>them. Y ou gain 1 Additional Success to all Defense Checks <br>you make to defend from an attack carried out by an enemy <br>sensitive to your aroma. Y ou receive 1 Penalty at all Checks <br>with ordinary people when your nauseating smell is a clear <br>obstacle. <br>The Stone that Came from the Sky<br>Requirement: Recover the stone that came from the sky <br>from the slopes of the volcano.<br>Y ou hold an alien stone with great powers, which you can <br>activate by suffering 1 Wound. When you do, choose from <br>one of the following effects. 1. Might: Y our strength triples <br>and you get 1 Additional Success to any Position Check <br>based on sheer strength for the rest of the Scene. 2. Speed: <br>Y our speed triples and you get 1 Additional Success at any <br>Position Check based on speed for the rest of the Scene. <br>3. Energy: Y our body is infused with pure energy and you <br>receive 3 Energy Tokens for the rest of the Scene. Y ou or <br>another nearby magic practitioner can use 1 Energy Token <br>to have 1 Additional Success when using any kind of magic. <br>Y ou can activate more than one effect of this Gift in the same <br>Scene by suffering additional Wounds. Wounds you suffer in <br>this way cannot be recovered in the current Scene.<br>This is My House (Special Gift for the Woman <br>from the Wood)<br>Requirement: Reach the village of Hosn.<br>Y ou remember this place, this is where you lived, and this <br>is where you worked as a baker. With your delicious sweets, <br>you fed the poor children of the village, but then someone <br>whose face you don’t remember poisoned what you created, <br>killing those you cared about. Y ou forgot what you did to <br>keep from succumbing to pain. Now you can decide:<br> <br> Forget what happened again.<br>In this case, deep anger will accompany you throughout your <br>stay on the island. Y ou always get 1 Additional Success when <br>you act to eradicate a threat that puts the life of a helpless <br>human at risk.<br> Remember who you were. <br>Y ou will return to be the witch of your past, but this will <br>mean profoundly changing who you are now. Permanently <br>replace your sheet with that of Katharina the Sweet Witch <br>found at the end of this Scenario.</p><p>1<br>2<br>Special<br>104<br>The Scenario <br>Hunger Island in <br>Scenes</p><p>FIRST SCENE –  Arrival at the <br>port of Vík í Mýrdal<br>It’s the same one you find on page 94. While wandering <br>around the port, the Hunters will be attacked by the <br>Maws and then will meet Berend, who will invite them to <br>the lighthouse. Gréte, left in the shadows to observe the <br>situation, will flee to Hosn to warn her brother of the arrival <br>of the Hunters.<br>End of Scene: Berend takes the Hunters to the lighthouse <br>to meet Althea. Go to the SECOND SCENE – The lighthouse.</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513714974,"modifiedTime":1781513714974,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"z3jM8UAckL6zxBoq","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Hunger Island - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE –  <br>The lighthouse<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: An excited Berend takes you <br>to the oldest part of the port of Vík í Mýrdal. Crates of fish <br>have been spilled in the area around the lighthouse and now <br>rot in the sun, causing a reek that makes sore vomit rise at <br>the back of your throat. Berend explains, with witty eyes, that <br>the monsters he calls Maws are drawn by the scent of humans <br>and are confused by the smell of rot. With pride, Berend <br>raises his dirty shirt and shows you a hairy torso encrusted <br>with dirt and fish guts. As he starts to pull his pants down, <br>a female voice tells him to stop. Althea, the emissary of the <br>Order who came here before you, comes out of the door of <br>the old lighthouse and yells at the poor madman who led you <br>here.<br>Place: The old lighthouse of the port that Althea and <br>Berend have fortified to keep the Maws away.<br>Time: It is late afternoon as the sun begins its descent, <br>hidden by the dense clouds fed by the fumes of the volcano.<br>Information: Althea will be grateful to the Hunters <br>for their arrival. Although the woman is extremely worn <br>by exhaustion and hunger, she will give the Hunters the <br>information on page 97. Althea will ask the Hunters to <br>accompany her to Hosn, to strike at the “leaders” of the <br>Maws and put an end to the threat they represent. It is clear <br>to the Order’s agent that the island’s stocks of both animals <br>and humans are rapidly depleting, and she fears it’s only <br>a matter of time before the Maws organize themselves to <br>set sail for the mainland. Alternatively, Althea will follow <br>the Hunters to the volcano if that’s where they intend to <br>investigate.<br>End of Scene: The Hunters leave with Althea for Hosn or <br>the Volcano. Go to SPECIAL SCENE – Along the way.<br>SPECIAL SCENE –  Along the <br>way<br>This Scene must be played every time the Hunters set out <br>on a journey. Select one of the effects on page 98.<br>End of Scene: The Hunters arrive at the village of Hosn. <br>Go to THIRD SCENE OPTION A – The village of Hosn or <br>to THIRD SCENE OPTION B – Laki, the Volcano.</p><p>3b3a<br>105</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513714974,"modifiedTime":1781513714974,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"C2bxNpPaNie7RLXF","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Hunger Island - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION A –  <br>The village of Hosn<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You arrive at Hosn following <br>a little used farm track, convinced that your enemies are posted <br>everywhere. A series of cries and moans draws your attention. <br>In the center of the small town square, a rudimentary wooden <br>cage holds six people prisoner. They seem to be ordinary <br>villagers, emaciated and shaken by the hardships they have <br>endured. Then, the sound of footfalls resonating among the <br>semi-destroyed houses make it clear to you that your enemies <br>are practically everywhere.<br>Place: The small village of Hosn, shrouded in fog.<br>Time: It is a cold day’s dawn and the rays of the sun reflect in <br>the fog, making it look almost like a white veil.<br>Information: Gréte stayed at the village to organize the <br>defenses, while Hanse moved to the volcano. The Maws will <br>first attempt to overcome the Hunters, taking advantage of the <br>numerical superiority. <br> ◆ The weak point of the Maws, however, is to attack without <br>any strategy, running at the Hunters like rabid dogs. <br> ◆ If cornered, Gréte will be willing to compromise by <br>freeing the villagers, with the exception of Enoch.<br> ◆ If released, Ina will try to reason with Gréte, proving to be <br>an asset to the Hunters.<br> ◆ In the village, there are a total of 18 Maws, moving in <br>groups of 6.<br>End of Scene: After freeing the village, talking to prisoners, <br>or interrogating Gréte, the Hunters will clearly understand <br>that the origin of all this is in Laki, where Hanse has retreated. <br>Go to THIRD SCENE OPTION B –  Laki, the Volcano. If, on <br>the other hand, the Hunters come from the volcano, go to the</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513714974,"modifiedTime":1781513714974,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"rHZrYiEfbidvZ4zS","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Hunger Island - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE – The Great Maw.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513714974,"modifiedTime":1781513714974,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"C2bxNpPaNie7RLXF","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Hunger Island - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION B –  <br> Laki, the Volcano<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: Finally, the volcano is no longer <br>just a looming shadow that hangs over all of you since you <br>landed. Now, it stands out in all its grandeur, its top lost among    <br>dense clouds. The earth thrums as if following the beating of a <br>huge heart, which is nothing more than the core of the volcano <br>itself. Among the split rocks, you can see several tunnels that <br>seem to unravel inside the volcano, and grotesque and guttural <br>sounds make you realize that the frequent eruptions are not the <br>worst danger you could encounter.<br>Place: Laki, the Volcano.<br>Time: It is a cold day’s dawn and the rays of the sun reflect in <br>the fog, making it look almost like a white veil.<br>Information: The Hunters will almost immediately come <br>across several Crazed Maws. To get to the center of the <br>volcano, they will have to deal with at least 2, or find a way to <br>follow them to the tunnel where the stone is located.<br> ◆ Hanse is protecting the stone with 2 Crazed Maws to back <br>him up. The boy is willing to bargain with the Hunters for <br>the promise that they will leave the island and leave him <br>and his new people alone.<br> ◆ If cornered, Hanse will throw himself into the volcano <br>carrying the stone with him, and the Hunters will see him <br>burn in the lava.<br> ◆ Hanse will not die in the lava but, consuming all the power <br>of the stone, he will emerge a few hours later filled with <br>anger for the possibilities lost because of the Hunters.<br>End of Scene:  Hunters can move to the village of Hosn <br>to save the remaining inhabitants. Go to THIRD SCENE <br>OPTION A – The village of Hosn. If, on the other hand, the <br>Hunters come from the village, go to FOURTH SCENE – The <br>Great Maw.</p><p>4<br>106</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513714974,"modifiedTime":1781513714974,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"rHZrYiEfbidvZ4zS","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Hunger Island - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE –  The Great Maw<br>This Scene begins after the defeat of both siblings. Hanse, driven mad by the <br>loss of the stone, returns to Hosn as the Hunters prepare to leave. Gréte, who <br>pretended to be dead thanks to her powers, will be reunited with her brother <br>and merge with him into the Great Maw. Play the Great Maw Threat as described <br>on page 102.<br>End of Scene: Hunters manage to escape from the island or end the life of the <br>Great Maw by making it fall into the volcano. Whatever choice they make, only <br>the Hunters can end the danger the Maws represent.</p><p>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am a capable cook and my body has a sweet smell that relaxes whoever <br>is near me. I can tell a lot about people from their food tastes. I deeply <br>hate those who hurt or bully children and the helpless.<br>•  The Sweet Witch: Y ou can spend 1 Soma to offer one of your sweets <br>to someone to make them well disposed towards you. Y ou gain 1 Additional <br>Success to convince and manipulate those who have eaten one of your sweets <br>until the end of the Scene. Y ou can decide that your dessert has an additional <br>effect based on its flavor: <br>1. Marzipan: Whoever eats it will fall into a deep sleep for several hours. <br>2. Candied fruit: The taste of the treat pushes those who are intoxicated to <br>reveal what they cherish the most. <br>3. Cinnamon: Those who eat it will feel the urgent desire to do more than <br>what they are doing, even at the expense of their duty. <br>4. Raisins: The taste of the treat pushes those who are intoxicated to reveal <br>what they hate the most.<br>Other Hunters or particularly capable individuals may require a Position <br>Check to make use of the power of your sweets.<br>I am a capable witch and when I need it, the world around me shapes <br>itself to protect and shelter me. I hate being out in the open and avoid <br>being the center of attention.<br>•  Home Sweet Home: you can spend 1 Soma to draw on your strange <br>witch powers. When you do, choose one of the following effects. <br>1. Create a shelter, for one person, perfectly camouflaged within the <br>environment. It is very difficult to discover your shelter, though some NPCs <br>can come close. At the Storyteller’s discretion, a Defense Check may be made <br>to see if you are discovered. <br>2. Change the texture of an inanimate object into a soft sweet. Y ou can turn a <br>door into marzipan or a sword into colored jelly. <br>3. Make an edible sweet and more nutritious. Whoever consumes your sweet <br>recovers 2 Soma, except yourself.<br>Katharina <br>the Sweet Witch<br>I am a witch specializing in creating magic sweets. I have always used my skills to help all the poor children <br>who cannot afford something good to eat. Giving a little joy to the poor was what warmed my heart the most. But <br>one day, a strange figure called the One Who Plots in the Shadow deceived me by poisoning what I baked with <br>so much love. That day, an entire village lost its future forever with the passing of all the children. I am aware <br>that I am not really guilty of the deaths of so many innocents, but this doesn’t lift the weight from my heart. All <br>I have left is revenge, which I will take as a Hunter of the Order against the one who, on a whim, destroyed <br>everything I cared about.<br>XP<br>Soma<br> 6<br>I love human flesh, a legacy of the alien stone’s power, to which <br>I have been exposed. I can regenerate my body, and my senses are <br>incredibly sharp. I am helplessly attracted to those who have a <br>particular appearance that stimulates my appetite, such as a good <br>smell or velvety skin. <br>•  Dark Ego - Soft and Succulent Flesh:  The truth is that you <br>crave human flesh, especially when raw and taken from evil people. When <br>you inflict a Wound through violent action on someone you deem evil, and <br>if you reach an Outcome with an Increment, you may inflict 1 additional <br>Wound. Once per Scene when you consume human flesh, you recover 1 <br>Wound and the Storyteller will reveal some memories of the victim, giving <br>you contextualized information about what you are looking for..<br>Activator: Blatantly manifest your desire to devour human flesh, regardless of the consequences.<br>Equipment <br>A doll and a wooden soldier, the only memories of the <br>children I cared for / A clean dress and an apron that smells <br>of sweets / A series of incredibly sharp, small pastry knives / <br>A suitcase of fine leather that contains everything I need to <br>produce excellent desserts / A picnic tablecloth / The key to <br>my small pastry workshop. <br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Extra <br>Wound.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513714975,"modifiedTime":1781513714975,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"hunger-island","collection":"The Broken Ones","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","pages":"93-108"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513714975,"modifiedTime":1781513714975,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"xPu3Rk8n4bNgNVzt","name":"Bloodwhite's Heart","pages":[{"_id":"mEc3VdGX2XPiUpd5","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>Bloodwhite's Heart</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> The Broken Ones</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 109-122.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/bloodwhites-heart-p109-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513717904,"modifiedTime":1781513717904,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"5Sek8U8NUOv5Ntsa","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Bloodwhite's Heart - Setup</h2><p>108<br>Once upon a time…<br>Germanic Bavaria. Prince Charles <br>Theodore has summoned the Order after <br>the strange death of his nephew Ottone. <br>He died traveling to the small village of <br>Lohr where he had gone to meet his future <br>wife, Bianca Karenmann. Although official <br>reports speak of a fatal fall from the horse, <br>in truth, the young man’s corpse was found <br>torn apart, his lungs and other organs <br>crushed as if a bomb had exploded within <br>his body. Despite the condolences of Karl <br>and Elsa Karenmann, Prince Charles wants <br>to shed light on his nephew’s death, with the <br>hope that doing so would dispel any shadow <br>of witchcraft and dark rituals. After all, <br>such suspicions had seen Lohr play host to a <br>relentless witch-hunt once before.<br>A Scenario Inspired by Snow <br>White (Grimm Brothers)<br>Bloodwhite’s Heart<br>Safety Keywords:  <br>Gore / Body Horror / False Accusations</p><p>109<br>The story that led us here…<br>During the witch hunt that shook the quiet village <br>of Lohr in 1603, a capable and powerful witch named Ursa <br>Radh managed to escape the clutches of the inquisition <br>for fifteen years, until 1618, when the hunt, unfortunately, <br>ended with her capture. While burning at the stake in <br>the village’s public square, Ursa cursed the lineage of the <br>Karenmanns, invoking the curse of the Restless Blood. <br>Karl’s then great-grandfather decided to walk away from <br>Lohr, hoping he would escape the curse, and he did. <br>Later on, his grandson Karl returned to Lohr, tempted by <br>promises of a good political career in the service of Prince <br>Charles Theodore. But his return to Lohr awakened Ursa’s <br>resentful spirit and the curse struck the Karenmann family. <br>Its victim was Bianca, Karl and Elsa’s firstborn daughter. <br>From an early age, she could only be satisfied with raw and <br>bloody meat. The Karenmanns kept their daughter safe <br>from prying eyes, but when Bianca grew old enough, Karl <br>couldn’t help but offer her hand in marriage to Ottone, the <br>Prince’s nephew. Arriving in Lohr, the greedy and spoiled <br>Ottone tried to consummate a relationship with naive <br>Bianca, who unintentionally made him explode to defend <br>herself, thus discovering another of the powers derived <br>from the curse. Panicked, the Karenmann spouses asked <br>Svenn, a skilled huntsman and longtime friend, for help, <br>asking him to secure the young Bianca. The man took <br>Bianca to an old mine where a group of seven Hessian <br>deserters had settled, each of whom had been on the run <br>for years because of war crimes. The seven of them, all <br>suffering from dwarfism, have accepted Bianca into their <br>ranks, swearing to keep her safe, provided the Karenmann <br>family does the same with them.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>Karl and Elsa live in fear that the Prince may send others <br>to investigate and, in particular, the Karenmann couple <br>know about the Order and its agents who once took part <br>in the witch hunt that once befell Lohr. That is why they <br>have commissioned Svenn to prepare a trap to mislead any <br>potential investigation. Svenn targeted Bruna, an old widow <br>who lives apart from the village because many rumors point <br>to her being a witch. Svenn hid a book of witchcraft and a <br>lock of hair recovered from Ottone’s body in Bruna’s house <br>so that any investigation would lead to accusing the woman <br>of witchcraft, diverting attention from Bianca. Regarding <br>the Karenmanns’ offspring, it was announced that she left  <br>for Dresden, to enter a prestigious university. In fact, Bianca <br>lives hidden in the old mine half a day from the village, kept <br>safe by Hessian mercenaries. Bianca and the mercenaries <br>have formed a friendly relationship and the young woman <br>spends her time caring for the soldiers and preparing their <br>meals. Abel, a young man from the village who has always <br>been in love with Bianca, did not believe that the young <br>Karenmann moved to Dresden to study. Her parents’ love <br>and attachment to their daughter are well known and <br>they would never have sent her away so easily. Abel has <br>repeatedly tried to understand the mystery behind Bianca’s <br>disappearance, clashing with the indifference of the village <br>and Svenn’s veiled threats.</p><p>1<br>110</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513717905,"modifiedTime":1781513717905,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"qkjEctaByF4Bj0ju","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Bloodwhite's Heart - Scene 1</h2><p>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: You arrive at the small village <br>of Lohr early in the morning, while most of the inhabitants are <br>busy with the many daily chores. Were it not for the macabre <br>discovery of the body of the young Ottone, Lohr would be the <br>portrait of a happy and carefree village. In front of you, right in <br>the center of the village, the Karenmann family palace stands <br>out in all its splendor.<br>Place: The village of Lohr.<br>Time: The early morning of a beautiful, sunny day.<br>Initial Situation: The Hunters are led to a meeting with <br>Karl and Elsa Karenmann.<br>Information: The Karenmann spouses will welcome the <br>Hunters with open arms, trying to appear as cooperative <br>as possible. From the interview, you can have the following <br>information, much of which is tainted by Karl and Elsa to <br>mislead any investigation.<br> ◆ The body of poor Ottone has already been returned to the <br>Prince’s messengers so that he could be taken to his family <br>to receive the funeral he deserves.<br> ◆ Ottone was found in his room, and it appears that he died <br>during the night. The body was in a gruesome condition.<br> ◆ The Karenmanns have hired Svenn, a skilled huntsman <br>and trusted person who has always provided for the <br>village. Svenn’s house is located a few minutes from the <br>Karenmann palace and the man is waiting for the Hunters <br>to share with them what he has discovered during the last <br>week of investigation.<br> ◆ The Karenmanns will carefully avoid mentioning Bianca. <br>If asked about her, they will say that their daughter has <br>moved to Dresden, eager to forget what happened and to <br>devote herself to her studies.<br>Karl and Elsa Karenmann <br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are two loving parents who only want what’s <br>best for Bianca. We have great wealth and allies throughout <br>Lohr.<br>Agenda: To have Ottone’s death case closed as soon as possible, <br>placing the blame on Bruna / Protect Bianca from a world that <br>could not accept her for what she is.<br>Karenmann Palace<br>Descriptor: A large and magnificent palace that contrasts <br>with the humble appearance of the rest of Lohr’s dwellings.<br>During the interview, the Hunters will realize that the palace <br>is full of paintings depicting the Karenmann family. In many <br>paintings, a beautiful girl with long black hair, snow-white <br>skin, and a pure and innocent look can be seen. From the <br>paintings the great love that unites Elsa and Karl to their <br>daughter Bianca is clear.<br>The Village of Lohr<br>Descriptor: A small village that is experiencing new prosperity <br>thanks to the Karenmann family.<br>The Hunters may hear some rumors while exploring the <br>village. Choose or roll 1 die:</p><p>111<br>1. Ottone quickly showed himself to be a stuck-up, <br>arrogant nobleman. Many are happy that sweet <br>Bianca Karenmann no longer has to marry him.<br>2. In the past, Lohr has been at the center of the largest <br>witch hunt in all of Germany. Several stakes were left <br>in the town square as a warning to all inhabitants.<br>3. The Karenmann family administers the village with <br>care and justice. Father, mother, and daughter have <br>always been inseparable.<br>4. Old Bruna is not well-liked, ever since her husband <br>got sick and then died within a week of a strange <br>illness. Many people think that it <br>was Bruna herself who performed <br>witchcraft on her husband, to <br>punish him for being a drunk.<br>5. In years past, the large mine, <br>located just over half a day’s <br>walk away, provided jobs to <br>the villagers. Since it played <br>out, the mine has become <br>a dangerous place where <br>fugitives and deserters often <br>find shelter for the night.<br>6. Bianca is a girl of rare <br>beauty, sweet and kind to <br>everyone. She has become <br>famous in the village for her <br>commitment to helping the <br>weak and needy. Despite her <br>noble background, she never <br>hesitated to get her hands <br>dirty to help her neighbor.<br>Information: During the visit to the city, Abel will <br>approach the Hunters trying to warn them of the <br>disappearance of Bianca Karenmann, which is suspicious <br>to him.<br>Abel the Young Lover<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a young baker who has always been in <br>love with Bianca.<br>Agenda: To find Bianca, as I cannot believe that she has <br>abandoned Lohr, nor that her parents would let her go so <br>easily.<br>Svenn’s House<br>Descriptor: A beautiful manor house, now converted <br>into a museum of hunting trophies.<br>Information: Svenn will greet the Hunters <br>with kindness, boasting that he is the man the <br>Karenmann family trusts the most. Svenn will tell <br>them of the doubts he has about Old Bruna and <br>of the fact that some secrets related to the death <br>of Ottone could be hidden in the woman’s house. <br>Svenn will advise the Hunters to act with caution, <br>so as not to alarm the inhabitants of Lohr, but he <br>will make himself available to distract the woman, <br>driving her away from home with an excuse.</p><p>112<br>Svenn the Skilled Hunter<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a skilled huntsman and I boast of all the <br>prey I have bagged in my long career. I’m a man of the world <br>and I’m used to handling every situation without too many <br>scruples.<br>Agenda: To make Bruna take the blame to divert attention <br>from Bianca / Pretend to help the Hunters to make sure they <br>close the case as quickly as possible.<br>Gift – The Solver:  Svenn takes great care of solving and <br>fixing all the problems of those who offer him a job. Against <br>any attempt at mind control, gathering information, or <br>trying to intimidate him, Svenn’s OL is Hard 7. <br>Bruna’s House<br>Descriptor: A small old house with a <br>garden full of medicinal plants.<br>Information: Bruna lives alone since <br>her husband’s death. Anyone who <br>knows herbs will understand that <br>the woman has good botanical <br>knowledge. Under the bed, <br>Svenn hid a bag with a book of <br>blasphemous rituals and a lock <br>of blond hair that belonged to <br>Ottone.<br>Bruna the Poor Witch<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a poor old woman to whom life has <br>offered only suffering. Sometimes I manifest strange powers, <br>but I have always concealed this ability out of fear of ending <br>up at the stake.<br>Agenda: To live in peace, seeking acceptance from the <br>inhabitants of Lohr.<br>Gift – Latent Witch:  Bruna has magic abilities, but <br>she never studied and uses her powers unconsciously. If <br>threatened, Bruna will activate her power and the objects <br>in the immediate vicinity will begin to move and then fall <br>upon everyone. Acting in the area affected by this power <br>confers 2 Penalties on each Check due to the uncontrolled <br>magic manifestations. If Bruna is killed, she will curse her <br>killer who, for the rest of the Scenario, will receive 1 Penalty <br>at each Defense Check. A practitioner of magic or someone <br>who can communicate with spirits can soothe Bruna’s soul <br>to undo the curse, but a Position Check will be required <br>against an OL Hard 7. <br>The Surroundings of Lohr<br>Descriptor: The village of Lohr stands on the edge of the <br>great Black Forest and is surrounded by many particular and <br>mysterious places.<br>While wandering around Lohr, the Hunters can reach one <br>of the following places. Roll a die (considering the results <br>from 1-3 as 1) or choose based on the information you want <br>to bring into play. If the Hunters move in free exploration, <br>each place is related to a cardinal direction.</p><p>113<br>1. To the North of the village flows a river that the <br>inhabitants use to collect water and fish. Far from <br>prying eyes, every morning, Bianca goes to wash <br>the clothes of the Hessian mercenaries. During the <br>afternoon, you may run into them (see “The escort” <br>on the next column). At night, this is the place <br>where Elsa and Bianca meet for a hug.<br>2. Continuing North (past the river) extends a large <br>area that Svenn uses as a hunting ground. The man <br>has scattered traps in the area and it is often possible <br>to find a dying animal, Svenn not even bothering to <br>put an end to its suffering.<br>Threat – Svenn’s Traps<br>Descriptor: A series of dangerous traps cleverly positioned.<br>OL Medium 5<br>Gift – Alarms:  Svenn’s traps are all designed to cause <br>deep wounds, and failing a Defense Check means suffering <br>1 Wound. In addition, they generate a loud noise that can <br>easily alert the Hessian mercenaries in the mine and warn <br>them against potential intruders. <br>3. Further North, after Svenn’s traps, the Hunters will <br>reach the old mine (see the next column).<br>4. To the West of the village, the Hunters will come <br>across a soldier on horseback traveling to Dresden. <br>The soldier, if questioned, will say that he is bringing <br>a dispatch to the city because seven dangerous war <br>criminals have been seen in the area, fleeing after <br>having killed an officer.<br>5.  To the South, the Hunters will come across a <br>small, abandoned house. Inside, there is a thug called <br>Berno. The man is terrified and, if questioned, he will <br>reveal that, two days earlier, he and his companion <br>Folke tried to take advantage of a beautiful young girl <br>with black hair who was washing military uniforms <br>at the river. When Folke touched the young woman, <br>the man’s body first swelled and then exploded into <br>a pool of blood and guts. Berno then ran for his life, <br>without looking back.<br>6. Traveling East, the Hunters will come to the great <br>road that leads out of the forest. The remains of a <br>camp made by the Hessian mercenaries indicate that <br>someone went to the mine after recovering their <br>strength.<br>The Mine<br>Descriptor: A large, abandoned mine riddled with <br>hundreds of tunnels. Hidden by trees and plants, there is a <br>small building that used to house the head of the excavations.<br>Information: Bianca lives in the small building on the <br>top of the mine, but a tunnel dug by the Hessians allows <br>her to descend into the mine at any time. After Folke and <br>Berno’s attempted aggression, the band of Hessians will <br>divide into two groups:<br> ◆ The escort: Includes Wrath, Corpse, and Grinner. <br>They always follow Bianca when she leaves the mine <br>and will act as a guard in frequent late-night meetings <br>with her mother Elsa.<br> ◆ The guardians: Includes Crucible, Stitch, Shadow, <br>and Rookie. This group is working to turn the mine <br>into a new home, as the mercenaries have decided to <br>settle permanently in Lohr.</p><p>7<br>114<br>Moving around the mine without knowing it is difficult. A <br>map of the area that the mercenaries are renovating can be <br>found in the house where Bianca lives. The map is inside a <br>small chest, with a trap built by Crucible.<br>Threat – Safety Deposit Box<br>Descriptor: A small reinforced wooden box engraved with <br>strange runes.<br>OL Medium 5<br>Gift – Get Your Filthy Hands Away!:  Opening the <br>box by failing the Position Check or without using the <br>password, i.e. beer and prostitutes, causes the activation of a <br>strong electric shock that inflicts 1 Wound and alerts Stitch <br>of the attempt to break in. In this case, increase the Our <br>New Home Gift Trench Tokens by 1.<br>Threat – Mine Tunnels<br>Descriptor: A series of intricate passages that all look alike.<br>OL Medium 5<br>Gift – Our New Home:  Start the Scenario with 2 Trench <br>Tokens on this Gift to represent the defenses put in place <br>by the Hessian mercenaries. For each section of mine <br>traversed, the Storyteller must set up a Scene and the <br>mercenaries can spend 1 Trench Token to activate each of <br>these effects once per Scenario. <br>Note: To reach Bianca in the mines, it is necessary to travel <br>at least 2 sections (3 if the Hessian mercenaries use Escape!).<br>1. Escape!: The screams of the Hessians rumble between <br>the tunnels and Bianca moves away from the Hunters by 1 <br>section. <br>2. Boom!: The mercenaries cause a collapse in the passage, <br>overwhelming the Hunters, who will have to pass a Defense <br>Check against OL Hard 7 not to suffer 1 Wound. <br>3. Screw you!:  One or more mercenaries ambush the <br>Hunters from behind, starting a conflict in which at least <br>two of them act first in the Exchange.<br>4. Lights Out!:  Every source of light is blocked and the <br>Hunters find themselves in total darkness. If Shadow is <br>present, he will take advantage of it to attack the Hunters, <br>possibly taking Didi the Rookie with him. <br>The Seven Hessian Mercenaries<br>Seven skilled mercenaries, united by dwarfism syndrome, who <br>have worked with various military forces. Their condition <br>has always put them on the margins of the army, despite the <br>impressive results they’ve obtained on the battlefield. When <br>Siegbold fell ill, his execution was ordered, but the team <br>rebelled by killing all the officers present. Now the seven <br>mercenaries are wanted for war crimes and desertion.<br>Note: To facilitate the management of a group of 7 NPCs, <br>all mercenaries have the same basic profile. However, <br>everyone has an exclusive Gift that characterizes the <br>way they act. In addition, each mercenary has a different <br>ending for his Descriptor. All mercenaries are ex-soldiers <br>accustomed to war and are armed to face hand-to-hand <br>and ranged opponents. <br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (1 Wound)</p><p>7<br>7<br>7<br>115<br>Descriptor: I am a capable mercenary who has experienced <br>a thousand battles and…[to be completed with the specific <br>Descriptor of each mercenary]<br>Agenda: Protect Bianca to maintain the support of the <br>Karenmann family / Transform the mine into our new home.<br>Dolf called “Crucible”<br>Descriptor: I know alchemy and magic, which I have <br>studied with interest over the years. My glasses are <br>constantly crooked.<br>Gift – Antimagus:  Crucible knows how <br>to create magical interference through <br>the use of vibrations generated by <br>slamming an iron rod on the barrel <br>of his gun. All actions involving <br>the use of spells and magic in his <br>presence receive 1 Penalty.<br>Grimbert called <br>“Wrath”<br>Descriptor: When I <br>get angry, my strength <br>doubles. I chew tobacco all <br>the time.<br>Gift – Warrior’s Fury:  <br>Wrath ignores the first <br>Wound he suffers in each <br>Scene. When he makes <br>an attack, regardless of <br>the outcome, the enemy is <br>overwhelmed by Grimbert’s fury and receives 2 Penalties to <br>their next action.<br>Siegbold called “Corpse”<br>Descriptor: My skin is hard and I have survived many <br>wounds. My body is covered in old, dirty bandages.<br>Gift – Leather Skin:  Corpse can suffer 2 additional <br>Wounds.<br>Bertold called “Stitch”<br>Descriptor: I am a good field doctor. I smell <br>of the alcohol I use to heal wounds and lighten <br>the soul.<br>Gift – It is not the Time to Die, Friend:  <br>Once per Scene, Bertold can heal 1 Wound <br>from a patient which receives care from <br>him. This can also bring someone who has <br>lost their last Wound back into the action. <br>Stani called “Shadow”<br>Descriptor: I am a perfect spy, easily <br>moving through the shadows. I hate <br>sunlight because I suffer from albinism.<br>Gift – Nocturnal:  Stani ignores any <br>penalty derived from effects that reduce <br>the ability to see and perceive an enemy. <br>This also applies to magical shrouds.</p><p>116<br> Didi called “Rookie”<br>Descriptor: I am the youngest in the group and I am good <br>at following orders. I can never stand still, and I speak quickly, <br>words tumbling over each other.<br>Gift – Yes, Sir!: Didi is always where others need him to be. <br>Once per Scene, another mercenary can call Didi to attention, <br>making him appear in the Scene ready to execute any order. <br>Didi can follow a partner in action and imitate his deeds, and <br>thanks to this he can make use of the exclusive Gift of those <br>he is supporting. <br>Hagen called “Grinner”<br>Descriptor: I am good at torture and I know how to make <br>a prisoner talk. A conspicuous scar gives my face a perpetual <br>sneer.<br>Gift – Grim:  Hagen knows how to exploit fear and mind <br>control, so he is completely immune to it. In his presence, his <br>teammates increase their Opposition Level by 1 to resist the <br>effects of fear and mind control.<br>Bianca<br> Karenmann<br>OL Easy 3 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I’m a sweet young girl and I just want to live in <br>peace. The power of the curse makes me strong and resilient. <br>It also gives me the power to make living beings explode from <br>within.<br>Agenda: I want what’s best for the whole village of Lohr, even <br>if it means sacrificing myself.<br>Gift – The Curse of Bloodwhite:  Thanks to the power of <br>the curse, Bianca is stronger and more resilient than normal. <br>For this reason, at the end of each Scene she recovers 1 <br>Wound. This effect even allows Bianca to return from <br>death. Bianca’s power can detonate the body of living <br>beings and, once per Exchange, her action can inflict <br>1 automatic Wound to a target. No Defense Check is <br>allowed.</p><p>117<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario, there are six Events. As a Storyteller, feel <br>free to create new ones in response to the actions of the <br>Hunters.<br>If the Hunters pay too much attention to Abel:  <br>Svenn will intervene as soon as possible by making the <br>young man disappear. Abel will be imprisoned in a pit in <br>the hunting ground.<br>If the Hunters capture Bianca: Elsa and Karl will call <br>a public assembly, trying to demonstrate to the Hunters <br>how beloved Bianca is and that she does not deserve to be <br>locked up by the Order.<br>If Bianca sees the people she cares about <br>endangered by the Hunters: she will surrender of her <br>own free will, trying to negotiate for the salvation of those <br>she loves.<br>If the Hunters openly declare that they do not <br>believe Bruna is guilty:  Karl and Elsa will make the <br>Hunters understand that they are no longer welcome in <br>Lohr and they will threaten to write a letter to the Prince <br>to complain.<br>If the Hunters defeat or capture at least three <br>Hessian mercenaries: the other mercenaries will try <br>to start a negotiation with them. It will be clear that, for <br>mercenaries, their comrades come first. <br>The first night after the arrival of the Hunters: Elsa <br>will go to the river with Svenn as her escort to meet Bianca <br>and warn her of the presence of the Hunters. <br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the <br>Bloodwhite’s Heart Scenario and can be acquired once the <br>conditions are met. A Hunter can only have one Scenario <br>Gift and if they acquire a new one, they will have to forgo <br>the previous one.<br>Gift – Stake’s Spirit<br>Requirement: Examine the old stakes in the square of <br>Lohr or show interest in the past history of witch-hunting.<br>Y ou are aware of the magical power that resides in the <br>village of Lohr and of the extent of the tragic witch trials <br>it once hosted. Once per Scene, you can open your mind <br>to the spirits of the dead witches. Spend 1 Soma and ask <br>a question about the village, one of the inhabitants, or the <br>surrounding areas. The Storyteller will answer with useful <br>information, but keep in mind that it will be conditioned by <br>the witch’s hatred of this place.<br>Gift – One of Us<br>Requirement: Defeat and spare one or more of the Hessian <br>mercenaries.<br>Y ou defeated the fearsome Hessian mercenaries and <br>earned their respect. Once per Scenario, you can call the <br>team to your rescue, and they will arrive in no time. The <br>Hessian mercenaries will act to help you within their NPC <br>capabilities for the current Scene, and then retreat to start <br>brewing some trouble in your location. This Gift can be <br>maintained in all future Scenarios and does not count <br>towards the maximum of the Gifts you have available.</p><p>1<br>2<br>3a<br>118<br>The Scenario <br>Bloodwhite’s Heart <br>in Scenes</p><p>FIRST SCENE –  Arrival in Lohr<br>It’s the same one you find on page 110. After the interview <br>with the Karenmanns, the Hunters go to Svenn to talk about <br>his investigation. Before arriving, Abel will intercept the <br>Hunters, revealing his doubts about Bianca’s departure.<br>End of Scene:  The Hunters meet Svenn. Go to THE</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513717905,"modifiedTime":1781513717905,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"qQd4L2k4Xs4zG2cd","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Bloodwhite's Heart - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE – The huntsman.</p><p>SECOND SCENE – The huntsman<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: Svenn’s house is a few minutes <br>from the Karenmann palace. With the words of the young Abel <br>still in your head, you find yourself in front of a once lovely <br>mansion. Unfortunately, the trophies of Svenn’s hunting skills <br>spoil its beauty from the entrance: a huge, tacky stuffed bear is <br>placed next to the door. <br>Place: Svenn the huntsman’s house.<br>Time: Mid-morning.<br>Information: Svenn will welcome the Hunters inside <br>the house and will describe everything he has “discovered. ” <br>He’ll also eagerly volunteer to distract Bruna with an excuse, <br>luring her away from her home. When asked about Bianca <br>and Abel, he will say that the young man is the classic loser <br>who fell in love with a girl to whom he should not even speak.<br>End of Scene:  If the Hunters trust Svenn, go to THIRD <br>SCENE OPTION A – Witch hunt , if instead, they decide to <br>search the surroundings of Lohr as requested by Abel, go to</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513717905,"modifiedTime":1781513717905,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"9qlS0o8etHVF6COO","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Bloodwhite's Heart - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION B – The river.</p><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION A –  <br>Witch hunt<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: Entering Bruna’s small and old <br>house isn’t difficult for you. Apart from an abundant garden <br>full of medicinal herbs, little of what you see qualifies as proof <br>that this is the home of a witch. But, maybe you just have to <br>look more closely...<br>Place: Bruna’s crumbling house.<br>Time: It is late afternoon when Svenn sends for Bruna to ask <br>her for advice on some herbs he found in the woods.<br>Information: Searching the house, it will be easy to discover <br>a bag under the bed, inside of which is a book about magic <br>and a lock of blonde hair. Taking the evidence to Svenn, he <br>will confirm that the hair color is the same as that of Ottone’s <br>and that the young scion kept his hair tied in a tail (which, <br>coincidentally, was cut from the corpse).<br> ◆ If the Hunters have no doubts, Svenn will have Bruna <br>removed from the house, and accuse her of witchcraft. <br>Elsa and Karl will congratulate them on the speed with <br>which they have solved the case. <br> ◆ Convinced or not, Abel will approach the Hunters to <br>tell them he made a macabre discovery as he searched <br>the outskirts of the village for tracks. He’ll make an <br>appointment with them after sundown to avoid Svenn’s <br>attention.</p><p>3b<br>119<br> ◆ If they go along, it will be clear to the Hunters that <br>they are no longer welcome in Lohr, and that from this <br>moment on, their stay is no longer viewed favorably by <br>the Karenmanns.<br>End of Scene: Shortly before sunset, Abel will contact the <br>Hunters saying that some very suspicious deserters have <br>settled at the old mine and that the mine would be a perfect <br>place to keep someone in captivity. Go to THE FOURTH <br>SCENE – The mine.</p><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION B –  <br>The river<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  To the north flows a large <br>river, which separates the inhabited part of the village from <br>the old mine. Abel told you that the mine is now abandoned <br>and that it is often used as a refuge for fleeing deserters and <br>thugs. Your attention is drawn by a melodious voice, a young <br>girl with long black hair is washing military uniforms at the <br>river. Even if you cannot see her well, the resemblance to the <br>daughter of the Karenmanns that you saw in the paintings of <br>the palace is quite striking. Noticing your presence, the young <br>woman flees to the mine while three short, squat men come out <br>of the bush to block your way.<br>Place: The river that flows between the village of Lohr and <br>the abandoned mine.<br>Time: It is early afternoon. <br>Information: The Hessian mercenary escort group (page <br>113) will instruct the Hunters to go somewhere else, making <br>it clear that the mine is now to be considered their property. <br>If they are overwhelmed or outnumbered, the mercenaries <br>will call Rookie for support. However, it is not the intention</p><p>120<br>of the Hessians to enter into conflict with the Hunters and <br>if asked about who the girl is, they will say that it is a young <br>woman from the village whom they pay to do some chores. <br> ◆ If the Hunters get into a fight, Svenn will arrive after <br>one Exchange, trying to put an end to the hostilities. <br>The huntsman will instruct the Hunters not to seek <br>trouble with the group of mercenaries who are “passing <br>through, ” and will tell the mercenaries that they have <br>a day to “get out of the way. ” The Hunters will catch <br>a clear look of understanding between Svenn and the <br>mercenaries.<br> ◆ If the Hunters return to report, both Svenn and the <br>Karenmanns will attempt to divert attention from the <br>mine, prompting the Hunters to investigate Bruna. <br>End of Scene:  If the Hunters trust Svenn, go to THIRD <br>SCENE OPTION A – Witch hunt , if they decide to <br>investigate the girl at the mine, go to FOURTH SCENE – <br>The mine.</p><p>54<br>121</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513717905,"modifiedTime":1781513717905,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"lZT0a3hjj7MZ0Fhl","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Bloodwhite's Heart - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE –  The mine<br>This Scene can be reached in different ways, but once <br>they get to the mine it will be clear to the Hunters that the <br>Hessians keep Bianca Karenmann with them. The mine <br>must be managed as indicated on page 113, taking into <br>account the intentions and strategies of the Hunters.<br>Place: The old abandoned mine near Lohr.<br>Time: The sun is setting.<br>Information:<br> ◆ The Hessians will fight to the death if necessary, but <br>Bianca herself will surrender if the Hunters seem to be <br>getting the better of the situation.<br> ◆ Bianca will confess to everything if faced with the <br>staging that her parents created to save her, especially <br>if this can prevent an innocent woman like Bruna from <br>an unjust accusation.<br>End of Scene:  The Hunters retrieve Bianca Karenmann <br>and return to Lohr, go to the FIFTH SCENE – The trial.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513717905,"modifiedTime":1781513717905,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"F0OwOK4N8CMq8uBm","name":"Scene 5","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Bloodwhite's Heart - Scene 5</h2><p>FIFTH SCENE –  The trial<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  When you return to Lohr <br>with Bianca, all eyes of the village are on you. The smiles and <br>greetings with which the inhabitants welcome Bianca are a <br>clear sign of how much the daughter of the Karenmanns is <br>loved and esteemed. Arriving at the central square, Elsa and <br>Karl await you with a group of armed guards. There is no <br>hatred in their eyes, but only the concern given by a parent’s <br>love for their daughter.<br>Place: The central square of Lohr, near the old stakes <br>where witches were bound and burned still stands as a <br>warning to all the inhabitants.<br>Time: The sun has just risen, after a night of clashes at the <br>mine.<br>Information: Elsa and Karl will go all-in by asking the <br>Hunters not to imprison their beloved daughter. The two <br>nobles will be supported by the testimonies of the villagers. <br>It will quickly become clear that everyone considers Bianca <br>a pure and kind soul.<br>End of Scene: It will be up to the Hunters to decide the <br>fate of Bianca Karenmann.</p>"},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513717905,"modifiedTime":1781513717905,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"bloodwhites-heart","collection":"The Broken Ones","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","pages":"109-122"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513717905,"modifiedTime":1781513717905,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Ws1V33ckbcuhDFQn","name":"The House of Roses","pages":[{"_id":"IVs0qS0v85zzYcAt","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>The House of Roses</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> The Broken Ones</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 123-134.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/the-house-of-roses-p123-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513727557,"modifiedTime":1781513727557,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"MjWOrvXIzuPrhyqX","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The House of Roses - Setup</h2><p>122<br>Once upon a time…<br>The Papal State. Father Cristoforo, ministering <br>to the city of Capodimonte, wrote to the Papacy <br>to request the intervention of a group of Hunters. <br>Several years ago, the formerly abandoned <br>convent on Martana Island became the home of <br>a mysterious cult called the House of Roses. It is <br>sponsored by the rich Dionysus Gonsalva, heir to <br>the family that has always lived in Capodimonte, <br>a town on the shores of Lake Bolsena. Many <br>young girls in the area have left their families to <br>go to Martana Island, severing all ties with their <br>past. It seems that this blasphemous cult is led by <br>a mysterious priestess, but access to the island is <br>prohibited by order of the Gonsalva family. Given <br>the excellent relations between the Gonsalva <br>family and the Papacy, the Hunters must go to <br>Capodimonte and seek permission to access the <br>island.<br>A Scenario Inspired by <br>Beauty and the Beast <br>(Jeanne-Marie Leprince de <br>Beaumont)<br>The House of Roses<br>Safety Keywords:  <br>Animalistic Savagery / Cult / <br>Brainwashing / Drugs / Reduced <br>Inhibitions</p><p>123<br>The story that led us here…<br>Dionysus Gonsalva is a young noble, victim of a <br>curse that has deformed his body and made him monstrous. <br>He is always in search of a bride, as he has been through <br>several over the years. The marriage has always ended in <br>blood when the bride first sees her prospective husband and <br>rejects Dionysus in horror. Bellina Cantalupo (known as <br>Bella) is a humble but ambitious servant who arrived at the <br>Gonsalva court in service to Marianna De Rossi, Dionysus’ <br>most recently deceased wife. Bella soon sensed the distress <br>of her lord and, without a second thought, worked her way <br>into his good graces to become his secret lover. Despite the <br>disgust she feels for Dionysus, Bella beguiled her lord with <br>the promise of true love. She also convinced him to move <br>to the old, abandoned monastery of Martana Island. The <br>two then founded the House of Roses, a place to welcome <br>young girls in search of a life away from the poverty that <br>plagues the current era. In the House of Roses, the young <br>novices are cared for and pampered, unaware that once <br>a month, one of them will be sacrificed to Dionysius to <br>appease his distorted need for love. Bella even arranged for <br>her two sisters, Francesca and Letizia, to join her in the cult. <br>She had always envied their beauty and planned for both of <br>them to be torn apart by her captive lover. Francesca, the <br>older sister, saw the true nature of Dionysus when he was <br>unleashed against Letizia. She escaped and now roams the <br>island, hunted by the servants of Dionysus, waiting for the <br>chance to escape.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>Capodimonte. Pietro Gonsalva, head of the noble family, <br>receives more and more complaints from the population <br>due to the continuous disappearance of young girls, who <br>flee to the House of Roses in search of a comfortable life. <br>Mere months after its foundation, the House of Roses <br>has become so famous as to attract young people from all <br>over Italy. Although Pietro does not know what is really <br>happening on Martana Island, the delusional letters of <br>his son Dionysus have made him worried. Now the old <br>nobleman hopes that an outside authority (such as the <br>Hunters) will take care of the situation.<br>Francesca hides in the dense vegetation of the island, <br>unable to leave it by swimming because the waters of the <br>lake are too cold in the middle of winter. The poor fugitive <br>keeps an eye on the pier in the hope of being able to secretly <br>embark on one of the ships that, after unloading the new <br>arrivals, returns to Capodimonte. In the House of Roses, <br>Bellina is consumed with anger at her sister’s escape and <br>now has total control over Dionysus’ psyche, treating him <br>like an animal. Bellina is surrounded by faithful servants, <br>all brainwashed to serve her as a goddess, and maintains <br>control over the island thanks to a pack of trained mastiffs <br>that obey Dionysus due to his bestial curse.</p><p>1<br>124</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513727558,"modifiedTime":1781513727558,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"VYvWkexOUw5mW9n7","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The House of Roses - Scene 1</h2><p>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  Capodimonte is a rich city <br>near Lake Bolsena that, thanks to the huge investments of the <br>noble Gonsalva family, has grown quite prosperous. After a <br>few minutes’ walk, you come across the church of San Carlo, <br>the smallest in the city, amidst small shops packed with busy <br>apprentices. Now you just have to decide whether to enter to <br>meet Father Cristoforo or first introduce yourself to the noble <br>Pietro Gonsalva, the regent of the city.<br>Place: The rich and prosperous city of Capodimonte.<br>Time: It is a cold morning.<br>Initial Situation: Hunters can decide who to meet and in <br>what order between the noble Pietro Gonsalva (at the city’s <br>fortress) and Father Cristoforo (in the small church of San <br>Carlo). Both men will have information about the House of <br>Roses, bringing a different point of view to the attention of <br>the Hunters.<br>Capodimonte<br>Descriptor: A rich and prosperous city protected by the Papal <br>State.<br>Pietro Gonsalva Regent of <br>Capodimonte<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a rich and powerful nobleman, and I have <br>managed to ingratiate myself with the Papal State. I love being <br>in charge, but over time I’ve learned to trust those who are more <br>experienced than I am.<br>Agenda: Preserve the House of Roses because it is the first <br>place where Dionysus appears to be restrained / Not to lose the <br>advantageous agreements made with the Church.<br>Information from the conversation with Pietro:  <br>The Regent of Capodimonte will welcome the Hunters with <br>all honors, praising their importance to the Church and for <br>humanity’ salvation. Pietro is sincerely respectful of the work <br>of the Order. <br> ◆ Pietro will say that the island was once a monastery and <br>that, thanks to the efforts of his son Dionysus, it has now <br>returned to a renewed splendor.<br> ◆ Martana Island has become a place of worship, where <br>people can take refuge and contemplate God.<br> ◆ Pietro cares a lot about the House of Roses because <br>his son Dionysus is suffering from a rare disease that <br>covers his whole body with hair and, unfortunately, his <br>monstrous aspect is not accepted by society. To Pietro, it</p><p>125<br>seems the island is the only place Dionysus has ever <br>been judged for the good he can do and not for his <br>fearsome appearance.<br> ◆ At the end of the interview, it will be clear to the Hunters <br>that Pietro has no idea of what life is like on the island, <br>he has never been there and, because of the many <br>diplomatic involvements around it, he has no interest <br>in discovering more. For the reasons mentioned above, <br>Pietro will make sure the Hunters understand that the <br>House of Roses must remain active.<br> ◆ With great generosity, Pietro will offer the Hunters a <br>boat that will take them to the island in the afternoon.<br>Father Cristoforo<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a humble provincial priest and I have <br>been responsible for the religious education of the Gonsalvas <br>for years. <br>Agenda: I have reason to believe that the House of Roses is <br>a place of blasphemy and damnation, so I want the Church <br>to investigate.<br>Information from the conversation with <br>Cristoforo: The humble priest will welcome the Hunters <br>in the small church of San Carlo. The man will show <br>reverence to the work of the Order and will seem aware of <br>who the Hunters really are.<br> ◆ Cristoforo will say that the island once was a <br>monastery where the residents dedicated themselves to <br>blasphemous rites. The Church intervened by putting <br>them all at the stake.<br> ◆ Martana Island is a name on the lips of many young <br>people, who tell of a place of feasts and pleasures far <br>from the severe but holy eye of God. Many young women <br>go out of their way to get to sail to the island. <br> ◆ Cristoforo taught the ways of God to the unfortunate <br>Dionysus, being troubled by the savagery that the young <br>man struggled to control. <br> ◆ At the end of the interview, it will be clear to the Hunters <br>that Cristoforo does not really know what is happening on <br>the island, but he is firmly convinced that it is nothing good.<br> ◆ Trying not to be overheard by prying ears, Cristoforo will <br>tell the Hunters that a couple of faithful friends have a small <br>boat and can take the Hunters to the island at night, landing <br>on a little-used beach. <br>Martana Island<br>Descriptor: A small island in the center of Lake Bolsena. Covered <br>mostly by dense vegetation, the island includes a sanctuary, a <br>small pier, and a mansion recently built by the Gonsalvas.<br>There are five locations available on the island:<br> ◆ The Pier: Where all ships arriving from Capodimonte dock. <br>The pier is under the control of Bella and her worshippers. <br>If the Hunters accept Pietro Gonsalva’s transportation offer, <br>they will arrive there in the late afternoon.<br> ◆ The White Beach: A small beach of rocks and earth to the <br>east of the island. It is located on the opposite side of the <br>island from the few inhabited places. If the Hunters accept <br>Father Cristoforo’s offer of transportation, they will reach <br>the beach at night.<br> ◆ The Sanctuary: All the young people who have become <br>prisoners of the House of Roses live here.<br> ◆ The Mansion: The House of Roses is a sumptuous villa that <br>Dionysus had built for Bella.</p><p>126<br> ◆ The Forest: A large wooded area where Dionysus’ <br>Mastiffs roam. In the thick of the forest, there is a <br>mass grave where Bella dumps the bodies of the <br>Beast’s unfortunate victims.<br>The Pier<br>Descriptor: A small pier with a watchtower.<br>Information: At the pier there are always 8 Servants, <br>armed and ready to welcome every arrival. In the guard <br>tower there are 6 other Servants equipped with firearms.<br>Bella’s Servants <br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are young people in the service of Bella <br>and we are trained to defend the House <br>of Roses. <br>Agenda: Follow all of Bella’s <br>orders to the letter. <br>Gift – For Our Lady:  The Servants are brainwashed <br>and totally dependent on Bella. Every attempt to scare or <br>mentally manipulate them receives 2 Penalties. If Bella <br>is targeted by a threat, once per Exchange, a Servant can <br>sacrifice themselves to take the hit in her place. <br>The White Beach<br>Descriptor: A small beach of pebbles and earth hidden <br>among the dense vegetation.<br>Information: Docking at the beach without the <br>necessary precautions will attract 1d6+2 Mastiffs.<br>The Forest<br>Descriptor: A large wooded area that almost entirely <br>covers Martana Island.<br>Information: The forest is overrun by mastiffs loyal to <br>Dionysus. Avoiding them requires overcoming the Pack of <br>Mastiffs Threat. In case of a Failure, 8 Mastiffs will appear <br>and surround the intruders. At the center of the forest is <br>a mass grave where the bodies of Dionysus’ victims are <br>dumped. Francesca hides in the pit to escape the hungry <br>dogs.<br>Threat – Pack of Mastiffs<br>OL Medium 5 <br>Descriptor: We patrol the forest, looking for intruders. No <br>one can escape our sense of smell.</p><p>127<br>Dionysus’ Mastiffs<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are big and fierce mastiffs loyal to our <br>leader, Dionysus.<br>Agenda: Hunt down any intruders arriving on the island.<br>Gift – Pack:  Any action taken while surrounded by 2 <br>or more Mastiffs receives 1 Penalty. A Mastiff can use its <br>action to howl and alert Dionysus, who will arrive within <br>2 Exchanges.<br>Francesca Cantalupo<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am Bellina’s sister, the eldest of three.<br>Agenda: Flee the island to return to my father / Avenge <br>Letizia’s death and punish Bellina for always being a selfish, <br>jealous child.<br>The Sanctuary<br>Descriptor: An ancient monastery converted into a small <br>pleasure town. <br>Information: 20 Handmaids and 10 Servants are <br>always present in the Sanctuary. All the inhabitants of the <br>Sanctuary live surrounded by food and pleasures of the <br>flesh, in a state of constant and perverse ecstasy. Bella adds <br>drugs to both food and drinks so that the inhabitants of the <br>Sanctuary lose their inhibitions.<br>Threat – The Food of the Gods<br>OL Medium 5 <br>Descriptor: All the food in the Sanctuary is tainted with a <br>powerful drug that loosens one’s inhibitions.<br>Gift – The Drug of the True Self:  Whoever eats food <br>treated with this powerful drug loses all inhibition. Anyone <br>who fails the Defense Check to resist the effect receives 2 <br>Drug Tokens. During a Scene, the Storyteller can spend 1 <br>Drug Token to activate one of the following effects. 1. The <br>True Self: Immediately activates the Hunter’s Dark Ego <br>without them suffering the Wound generated by not using <br>the Activator. 2. Dulled Senses: The Storyteller decides <br>what type of Outcome the Hunter is aiming for after they <br>have declared an action. <br>Bella’s Handmaids <br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are young girls loyal to our lady. We are <br>ready to have a good time – anytime.<br>Agenda: We have tasted happiness in the House of Roses <br>and we will not allow anyone to take us back to our former, <br>miserable lives.</p><p>128<br>The Mansion also known as the <br>House of Roses<br>Descriptor: A large and rich mansion, with a wide garden, <br>a hedge maze, and beautiful red roses.<br>Information: Bella lives in the Mansion where 8 Servants <br>are executing any of their lady’s wishes. Dionysus lives in <br>the cellars of the estate and only goes out at night or when <br>his Mastiffs get his attention.    <br>Threat – Hedge Labyrinth<br>OL Medium 5 <br>Descriptor: A large labyrinth of hedges and roses that <br>extends throughout the estate garden. <br>Gift – Secret Passage:  Bellina and Dionysus know a <br>series of secret passages to avoid wasting time in the maze. <br>Anyone else might need several hours to negotiate it.   <br>Bellina Cantalupo known as Bella<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a cunning manipulator and the only queen of the House of Roses. I <br>take advantage of the power I wield whenever I have the chance.<br>Agenda: Increase the influence of the House of Roses at any cost / Getting rid of <br>Dionysus, but without destroying the House of Roses.<br>Gift – Manipulative:  During a Scene, if Bella has enough time to talk to a <br>subject, she will learn a secret about them, such as a Descriptor or <br>their Gift. Bella is immune to any kind of mental manipulation <br>or fear. <br>Gift – My Beast:  If Bella is in danger, Dionysus will come <br>to her rescue within 1 Exchange. To help Bella, Dionysus <br>can free himself from any kind of impediment, whether <br>physical or mental. Nothing can stop Dionysus, who <br>will break through doors and walls if necessary.</p><p>129<br>Dioniso Gonsalva called the <br>Beast<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a young man afflicted by a curse <br>that turned me into a fierce beast. Only Bella’s scent <br>keeps my incredible ferocity in check.<br>Agenda: I would like to live alone with Bella <br>in this paradise, and I only tolerate the House <br>of Roses for the sake of my love for her / I <br>would like to show the full extent of my love <br>to Bella, but until she gives herself to me, I <br>will have to take my frustration out on <br>her handmaids.<br>Gift – The Beast:  Dionysus can <br>act twice during an Exchange. When <br>moving, Dionysus can jump up to thirty <br>feet and easily destroy any obstacle. <br>When acting to save Bella, Dionysus <br>increases his Opposition Level by 1.</p><p>130<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario there are five Events. As a Storyteller, feel free <br>to create new ones in response to the actions of the Hunters.<br>If the Hunters capture Bella:  the Lady of the House of <br>Roses will threaten to unleash Dionysus’ wrath on all the <br>innocents on the island. Bella will demand that the Hunters <br>release her, while trying to negotiate a deal that works for <br>everyone.<br>If the Hunters kill Dionysus:  Bella will thank them by <br>telling them that it was all the fault of the mad nobleman <br>who forced her to do everything. Her aim is to escape the <br>judgment of the Church by passing herself off as a victim.<br>If the Hunters find Francesca:  the young woman will <br>describe how all the Handmaids ignore what truly happens <br>to Bella’s chosen ones. Francesca will tell the Hunters who <br>Bellina really is, and how she brainwashed everyone on the <br>island thanks to her position of power and the drugs in the <br>food.<br>If the Hunters officially show up at the pier:  Bella <br>will welcome them with all honors by offering them food <br>and drinks. Bella’s purpose is to gather information about <br>the newcomers and then feed them to Dionysus one by one.<br>If the Hunters accuse Bella or Dionysus:  Bella will <br>seek an advantageous agreement by mentioning that the <br>Gonsalva family is one of the greatest supporters of the <br>Papacy, and that a scandal could end the huge subsidies that <br>Pietro regularly pays to Rome. <br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the The <br>House of Roses Scenario and can be acquired once the <br>requirements are met. A Hunter can only have one Scenario <br>Gift and if they acquire a new one, they will have to forgo the <br>previous one.<br>Gift – Faithful Mastiffs<br>Requirement: Have defeated one or more of Dionysus’ <br>Mastiffs.<br>Y ou defeated the Mastiffs, proving you are a worthy pack <br>leader. Y ou gain 1 Mastiff who follows you as a faithful <br>companion. Y ou can spend 1 Soma to assign a task to your <br>Mastiff for the rest of the Scene. 1. Find: The Mastiff can <br>track an object or a person if you are able to provide it with <br>a sample of its smell; 2. Defend: The Mastiff stands in your <br>defense, granting you 1 Additional Success in all Defense <br>Checks. In case of an Outcome with a Cost, the Mastiff  <br>will die taking the blow in your place as a Cost; 3. Attack: <br>The Mastiff attacks the enemy you point to, reducing their <br>Opposition Level by 1 for the course of the Exchange. Each <br>time you use this effect, roll a die. With 4+ the Mastiff is <br>killed in the action. If your Mastiff is killed, you can get <br>another one at the beginning of the next Scene.<br>Gift - Uncovering Deceptions<br>Requirement: You know how to expose a charlatan and lay <br>bare lies.<br>All NPCs who possess a Descriptor, Gift, or Agenda that has <br>to do with lying or deceiving others reduce their Opposition <br>Level by 1 in your presence. When you’re around, you also <br>weaken their followers: once per Scene you can prevent a <br>subject from using a Gift that depends on using or sacrificing <br>a follower.</p><p>1<br>2a<br>131<br>The Scenario The <br>House of Roses in <br>Scenes</p><p>FIRST SCENE –  Arrival at <br>Capodimonte<br>It’s the same one you find on page 124. The Hunters will <br>go first to interview Pietro Gonsalva and then to Father <br>Cristoforo.<br>End of Scene:  Hunters can decide whether to land on <br>the island through the passage offered by Pietro, go to</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513727558,"modifiedTime":1781513727558,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"sJmOYGdbSRrWI67O","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The House of Roses - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE OPTION A – The pier. Or land secretly <br>thanks to the help of Cristoforo, go to SECOND SCENE <br>OPTION B – The White Beach.</p><p>SECOND SCENE OPTION A <br>– The pier<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: In less than an hour’s sailing, <br>you can already see the shape of Martana Island looming in <br>front of you. The boat arrives in a small covered port, where <br>you find a large group of men with smiling faces waiting for <br>you, though it’s difficult to ignore the weapons they carry. <br>A young girl with wavy brown hair seems to be the person <br>in charge, and when you get off the boat, she greets you, <br>smiling. “I am Bella Cantalupo, and I serve my lord Dionysus <br>Gonsalva so that the House of Roses may be a place of peace <br>and prayer. Please be our guests for at least one night. ” Bella <br>beckons you to follow her to what appears to be a completely <br>renovated monastery.<br>Place: Martana Island’s pier.<br>Time: It is almost time for dinner.<br>Information: Bella will be extremely helpful with the <br>Hunters, trying to answer all their questions. The woman’s <br>goal is to impede the investigation and pass the House of <br>Roses off as a place of worship and peace.<br> ◆ If the Hunters ask her about Dionysus, Bella will say <br>that her master shuns situations in which there are <br>many people because of his appearance. Bella takes <br>care of everything, but if the Hunters want to, she will <br>set up an interview with Dionysus.<br> ◆ Bella will highlight the peace and prosperity in which <br>servants and handmaids live, and all the young people <br>will be helpful and happy.<br> ◆ Bella will invite the Hunters to stay for the night and <br>organize a banquet in their honor. The Hunters will <br>be asked to stay within Sanctuary so as not to risk <br>provoking the many mastiffs that Dionysus breeds in <br>the forest.<br> ◆ The Mansion is reserved for Dionysus, and for this <br>reason it is inaccessible to the Hunters. Sneaking into <br>it, you will find ample supplies of Mandrake and other <br>herbs useful to produce drugs. <br> ◆ Bella will watch the Hunters closely, always maintaining <br>her fake, friendly smile. <br>End of Scene:  After talking to Bella and seeing the <br>Sanctuary, the Hunters will be invited to a banquet set up <br>just for them. Go to THIRD SCENE OPTION A – Welcome <br>guests.</p><p>3a 3b<br>2b<br>132</p><p>SECOND SCENE OPTION B  – <br>The White Beach<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: You land on a small beach of <br>pebbles and mud. As soon as you step off the boat, the sailors <br>hastily set sail once more, making the sign of the cross. Only a <br>few seconds pass before you hear growls and howls. Apparently, <br>a wolf or dog pack is moving towards you, attracted by your <br>smell.<br>Place: A small beach on Martana Island.<br>Time: It is almost time for dinner.<br>Information: A group of 8 Mastiffs will try to intercept <br>the Hunters and, if the clash begins, they will immediately <br>howl to summon Dionysus. The beastly lord of the island <br>will attack without hesitation but will flee after suffering 2 <br>Wounds. If, on the other hand, the Hunters manage to hide <br>from the pack of Mastiffs, they will see Dionysus coming and <br>will be able to observe him in all his savagery. Dionysus will <br>remain for a few minutes before leaving and returning to the <br>Mansion.<br>End of Scene:  Having faced or avoided the Mastiffs, the <br>Hunters will come across the mass grave, go to THIRD <br>SCENE OPTION B – Unwanted guests.</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513727559,"modifiedTime":1781513727559,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"G2d9JpOQNjce1jlz","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The House of Roses - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION A –  <br>Welcome guests<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  The banquet Bella has set up <br>for you is sumptuous to say the least. Wine and delicacies of <br>all kinds cover the great table of the Sanctuary, while around <br>you, servants and handmaids dance and sip wine, indulging <br>in the pleasures of the evening. Even Bella seems particularly <br>euphoric, inviting you to enjoy the fine things her generous lord <br>Dionysus has to offer. <br>Place: The Sanctuary of the island.<br>Time: The sun has just gone down.<br>Information: Bella will try to drug the Hunters to lower <br>their defenses and discover how much of a threat they are. If <br>the Hunters insist on meeting Dionysus, Bella will ask that <br>only one of them go, since her lord is not accustomed to being <br>seen by many people at once. If the Hunters consent, the <br>chosen one will be taken to the Mansion’s rose garden, where <br>Dionysus will attack, trying to kill them. If the Hunters keep <br>a low-profile during dinner, at some point Bella will be called <br>away by a servant to deal with an emergency. The Hunters <br>will be able to see concern in the eyes of the young woman, <br>since Dionysus is having one of his fits and needs to consume <br>one of the handmaids to appease himself. Bella will take a <br>girl with her, saying goodbye to the Hunters. Following Bella <br>will require overcoming two groups of 8 Servants, which the <br>woman will put on the road between the Sanctuary and the <br>Mansion.<br>End of Scene:  The Hunters now clearly understand that <br>something dark animates Bella’s actions, and they arrive at <br>the Mansion to witness the sacrifice, go to the FOURTH <br>SCENE – The sacrifice.</p><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION B – <br>Unwanted Guests<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You have overcome the <br>terrible Mastiffs patrolling the forest and, as you cross the <br>rugged woodland, a nauseating smell draws your attention. A <br>little more than ten meters away, a large grave contains the <br>bodies of a multitude of young girls, all horribly mutilated, as <br>if a ferocious creature had devoured them. Suddenly, one of the <br>girls seems to be moving, making a soft cry.</p><p>4<br>5<br>133<br>Place: The mass grave in the middle of the island’s Forest.<br>Time: It is night, and a soft moonlight filters through the <br>branches of the trees.<br>Information: It will be possible to find Francesca within <br>the pit, looking worn and on the edge of madness. The young <br>woman will describe all the crimes Bellina has committed and <br>how Letizia was sacrificed to the fury of Dionysus. The young <br>woman’s only wish is to run away but, if the Hunters play on <br>her anger, she will ask to follow them to avenge her dead sister. <br>Francesca’s voice is known to the Mastiffs, and within a short <br>time, a pack of 8 will reach the pit, led by Dionysus. In the <br>event of a confrontation, the beastly noble will do everything <br>he can to kill Francesca. As in the previous clash, Dionysus <br>will flee as soon as he receives the second Wound.<br>End of Scene: Once Bellina’s faults have been discovered, the <br>Hunters can move to the Mansion to capture her. Go to THE</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513727559,"modifiedTime":1781513727559,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"xn7Pn1JWZN0SzkP6","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The House of Roses - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE – The sacrifice.</p><p>FOURTH SCENE – The sacrifice<br>There are two ways to get to this Scene.<br>From the banquet: The Hunters follow Bella and catch her <br>red-handed as she prepares to feed Dionysus an unsuspecting <br>handmaid.<br>From the grave:  The Hunters arrive at the garden of <br>the Mansion led by Francesca just as Bella prepares to feed <br>Dionysus an unsuspecting handmaid.<br>Place: The rose garden of the Mansion.<br>Time: It is night, and only the full moon illuminates the small <br>labyrinth of hedges and roses.<br>Information: The ritual consists of bringing the handmaid <br>to the center of the maze of hedges, and then letting Dionysus <br>unleash his desires. Only Bella and Dionysus are present at the <br>rite, since none of the servants or handmaids must discover <br>the truth. If the Hunters intervene, Bella will not hesitate to <br>unleash Dionysus against them. While they battle, she will <br>flee to the Sanctuary to stir up all the servants and handmaids <br>against the Hunters, accusing them of having been sent by the <br>Papacy to end the House of Roses.<br>End of Scene:  After facing Dionysus, the Hunters must <br>handle Bella who sends all the inhabitants of the island against <br>them. Go to SCENE FIVE – Face to face.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513727559,"modifiedTime":1781513727559,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"TKcr1U9IFUKXb7TB","name":"Scene 5","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The House of Roses - Scene 5</h2><p>FIFTH SCENE – Face to face<br>This Scene can have many variables, based on what the <br>Hunters have discovered so far. There will be 20 Servants and <br>20 Handmaids in the Scene.<br>Place: The Sanctuary.<br>Time: It is late at night and the only light is cast by the banquet <br>bonfires.<br>Information: Bella will use all her influence to cast the <br>Hunters in a bad light, also accusing them of the attempted <br>(or successful) murder of Dionysus, the one who has been <br>supporting everyone at the House of Roses. Bella will make <br>the Hunters understand that she is willing to come to terms <br>with them, but her power of manipulation is very strong and <br>she can do with the innocents who live on the island as she <br>likes.<br>End of Scene: Bella will be determined not to lose the power <br>she has gained and has an entire island at her command. The <br>Hunters will have to play their cards well to put an end to the <br>House of Roses once and for all.</p>"},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513727559,"modifiedTime":1781513727559,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"the-house-of-roses","collection":"The Broken Ones","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","pages":"123-134"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513727559,"modifiedTime":1781513727559,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"kyJkR5oejI5LMjJV","name":"Stegeborg's Quiet","pages":[{"_id":"U6jcPQzanpz3eE3y","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>Stegeborg's Quiet</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> The Broken Ones</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 135-150.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/stegeborgs-quiet-p135-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513729795,"modifiedTime":1781513729795,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"phpPhWIorzPWxGtO","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Stegeborg's Quiet - Setup</h2><p>134<br>Once upon a time…<br>The Hunters are sent to Sweden to <br>investigate the mysterious Stegeborg <br>Castle. The property, once run by the <br>Schwernis family, has been abandoned <br>for decades. The surrounding villages <br>had survived the departure of the noble <br>family, remaining populated and lively. <br>However, in the last few weeks, they <br>have gone ominously silent. Strange <br>lights have been seen coming from <br>the Stegeborg Castle, and seers in the <br>service of the Order have received a dark <br>omen. Something evil, hidden within <br>the meandering corridors of Stegeborg, <br>has been awakened. Now, everyone <br>will pay for the sins of one man. The <br>Hunters must go to Stegeborg and face <br>the danger the seers have foretold.<br>A Scenario Inspired by Sleeping <br>Beauty (Charles Perrault)<br>Stegeborg’s Quiet<br>Safety Keywords:  <br>Incest / Physical and Psychological <br>Abuse / Rape / Body Horror</p><p>135<br>The story that led us here…<br>The last member of the Schwernis family, former <br>lords of Stegeborg, remains in the castle. Talia never left  <br>when the castle was abandoned fifty years ago, and instead <br>was bound in eternal slumber. Talia had always submitted <br>to her father Alexander and mother Alexandra, twins <br>united in a perverse relationship. The couple was obsessed <br>with their daughter, who was the last of their children. <br>Each of the previous pregnancies had ended with the birth <br>of deformed children, all of whom had been smothered <br>by their disappointed parents. Talia represented the pure <br>beauty Alexander and Alexandra had been longing for. <br>Their dreams realized, they withdrew within the walls of <br>the castle and hid themselves from the rest of the world. <br>In her stone prison, Talia suffered all kinds of abuse at her <br>parents’ hands, finding support only in Carabosse, the old <br>cook of the castle. Unbeknownst to Talia, Carabosse was <br>once a powerful witch who escaped the great inquisition of <br>1645 in France. When Talia bled for the first time, her father <br>tried to force himself on her. The young woman fought <br>back and, unintentionally, pushed Alexander out of one <br>of the castle towers, causing his death. Crazed with pain, <br>Alexandra tried to kill her daughter, but was stopped by <br>Carabosse. The witch was moved with compassion for all of <br>Talia’s pain, and cast her last and greatest spell: she froze the <br>Stegeborg Castle in time. Talia, asleep in the underground <br>crypt, was imbued with the witch’s power so that she could <br>now move objects or grow plants merely through force of <br>will. Alexandra was transformed into a monster and forced <br>to be her daughter’s guardian for eternity. Talia’s wish <br>covered Stegeborg with ivy and brambles, a symbol of its <br>separation from the rest of the world. <br>The young woman, forever asleep, waits for someone pure <br>of heart and capable of breaking the magic that once saved <br>her, only to deliver her to a life of fading dreams. <br>Fifty years later, Accursio De Celeste, a renowned mercenary <br>and researcher, went to Stegeborg, attracted by rumors of a <br>rich treasure hidden in the castle’s dungeons. Overcoming <br>uncounted dangers, the man reached the dungeons to <br>discover the sleeping body of Talia, who was so impressed by <br>so much courage and skill that she decided to let him come <br>even closer. But Talia’s dreams were once more shattered <br>by the darkness of the human soul. Like her father fifty <br>years earlier, Accursio tried to abuse the beautiful Sleeper. <br>Anger and resentment once again overcame Talia’s mind, <br>animating the castle and cursing the entire village next to it. <br>In one night, all the inhabitants were killed or assimilated <br>by the castle, becoming monsters and prisoners. Accursio <br>took refuge in the Master Tower, waiting for his chance to <br>escape. Her soul forever scarred, Talia’s will is now out of <br>control, expanding beyond the walls of Stegeborg, in a slow <br>but inexorable attempt to assimilate the whole world.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>The village near the castle is nothing more than a ghost town <br>where Georg, the only survivor of Talia’s fury, takes refuge <br>from the Quiet Guards: men and women merged with the <br>furnishings of the castle and transfigured into monsters, <br>now serving the Sleeper. Accursio lives in the Master Tower <br>of the castle where Talia’s power struggles to reach since <br>it is there that Alexander tried to rape his daughter. The <br>memory of so much pain weakens her abilities. Accursio <br>is aware that he cannot escape on his own, since the tower <br>has a single exit to the inner courtyard of the castle, and <br>Talia’s power can reach him there. Alexandra, now reduced</p><p>1<br>STEGEBORG<br>136<br>to a deformed monster, wanders through the castle and waits <br>for someone to end her life. She had trusted Accursio, and <br>now that the man has proven as despicable as Alexander, <br>Alexandra has resigned herself to the idea that no one can <br>ever give Talia peace and thus put an end to the curse. A few <br>villagers led by a woman named Lisbet are kept alive inside <br>the castle, in the rooms that once belonged to the Schwernis <br>family. Talia holds them hostage, forcing them every night to <br>keep her company by reading stories and singing songs.</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513729796,"modifiedTime":1781513729796,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"c9NmZQO1UhCUftDa","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Stegeborg's Quiet - Scene 1</h2><p>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  It is almost sunset when you <br>glimpse the first houses of the village of Stegeborg. The imposing <br>shape of the castle looms over the small village, casting its great <br>shadow as if to swallow it. While an old stray dog raises its ears <br>in your direction, the unnatural silence that accompanies your <br>footsteps does not bode well.<br>Place: The small village of Stegeborg, devastated by the fury <br>of Talia.<br>Time: It is almost sunset, but the sky is clear and there is still <br>plenty of light.<br>Initial Situation: It’s apparent the village has suffered some <br>sort of disaster as soon as the Hunters arrive there. Doors <br>and windows are literally crumbling, while dozens of corpses <br>lie in the streets. On the wrists and neck of the bodies, one <br>can see the clear marks of something that seized them tightly <br>and dragged them with incredible force. Moving around the <br>village will immediately attract the attention of the Quiet <br>Guards, who will converge on the Hunters. There are a total of <br>10 Guards in town. Georg took refuge in the church, but the <br>fear of being captured led him to stay there for days and he <br>almost died of hunger. <br>Information: Saving Georg will yield some information. <br>The man arrived in Stegeborg a few years ago and does not <br>know the history of the Schwernis well. He does know that <br>fifty years earlier something so upset the noble family they <br>packed up and left in a single night, disappearing. Georg will <br>also reveal that, a week ago, an Italian treasure hunter named <br>Accursio De Celeste passed through the village, asking for <br>information about the castle. That same evening, he went <br>there, never to return. Soon after, all hell broke loose, and the <br>plants in the village came to life, dragging and strangling its <br>inhabitants. Georg survived by fleeing to the church. He hid <br>there, afraid to move after witnessing several villagers being <br>transformed into Quiet Guards.<br>Important note: Thanks to her Sleeping Spirit Gift, Talia <br>can interact with all the Places in the Scenario. Depending <br>on the actions of the Hunters, the Sleeper can be an ally or an <br>enemy. On page 142, you can find instructions for managing <br>the Sleeping Spirit Gift.</p><p>STEGEBORG<br>137<br>The Village of <br>Stegeborg<br>Descriptor: A small village at the foot of Castle Stegeborg, <br>devastated by the fury of Talia.<br>Georg the Survivor <br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I’m a poor laborer without a family. I once was <br>living in the streets.<br>Agenda: Escape from Stegeborg as soon as possible, so I can <br>leave what I saw behind me and start a new life.<br>The Quiet Guards <br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are the poor inhabitants of the village, fused <br>with some of the castle’s furnishings. Our transformations <br>have driven us to madness and we blindly obey the will of <br>Talia.<br>Gift – Quiet Guards:  A Quiet Guard no longer possesses <br>a mind and acts as an object under the control of Talia. That <br>is why they cannot be mentally manipulated or frightened <br>in any way. Each Quiet Guard is a human body fused with a <br>part of the castle. Roll a die or choose a mutation.<br>1. Tools: The Guard’s arms are an agglomeration of tools, <br>such as shears and hammers. When attacking, the Guard is <br>considered to have an OL Medium 5.<br>2. Grating: The Guard’s body is covered with metal grates <br>and frames. It can suffer 1 additional Wound.<br>3. Chains: Ropes and chains hang from the Guard’s body. <br>With a single action, the Guard can interact with 2 targets.<br>4. Door: The Guard’s body is a huge pile of metal doors <br>and hinges. When defending itself, the Guard is considered <br>to have an OL Medium.<br>5. Fireplace: Burning embers are kept ablaze within the <br>Guard’s stomach. Once per Scene, the Guard’s attack inflicts <br>1 additional Wound.<br>6. Plates:  The Guard’s body is a cluster of plates and <br>glasses embedded in the living skin. When the Guard is <br>eliminated, it explodes into a thousand shards, inflicting <br>1 Wound to the one who dealt the last blow unless they <br>succeed a Defense Check.</p><p>138<br>The Castle’s Courtyard<br>Descriptor: A large inner courtyard, which was once a <br>lavish garden. Now, ivy and brambles infest every crevice, <br>forming a real forest.<br>Threat – Forest of Animated <br>Brambles<br>Descriptor: Brambles and ivy animated by Talia’s ability. <br>We act to capture and strangle any intruders. We are guarding <br>the courtyard, waiting to end Accursio’s life.<br>OL Hard 7<br>Gift – Forest of Brambles:  The mass of brambles acts <br>under the magical power of Talia and can perform 1d6 <br>actions per Exchange. Each individual action can be used <br>in a different way. 1. Attacking:  Whip at or strangle a <br>target and inflict 1 Wound; 2. Ensnaring:  Immobilize <br>a target, preventing it from acting; 3. Manipulating: <br>Manipulate objects or the setting to open or close passages;  <br>4. Communicating:  Take the shape of rudimentary <br>letters. The Forest cannot be destroyed unless it is <br>completely set on fire and, even then, it will regenerate <br>within a few minutes. By inflicting 1 Wound, it’s possible <br>to hack away some branches and slow down the plants’ <br>growth, for example, to free an ensnared target. If Accursio <br>is present the Forest of Animated Brambles will focus on <br>capturing him, devoting at least half its actions to that <br>purpose.<br>Information: Access to the courtyard is easy, as the large <br>drawbridge of the castle is lowered. From the Courtyard, <br>you can access the Master Tower and the Main Court.<br>The Master Tower<br>Descriptor: A large six-story fortified tower, with barred <br>windows. The large main door is walled by brambles and <br>plants.<br>Information: Talia has blocked the only exit with her <br>Forest of Animated Brambles and attempting to force it will <br>activate its Threat (see previous column). By inflicting a <br>total of 3 Wounds to the brambles, you can open the door. <br>Accursio has taken refuge on the third floor where, slowly, <br>he is sawing the bars out of a window with the intention <br>of stretching a rope to the walls and escaping. Accursio <br>is the only one, besides Alexandra, who has a key to the <br>Dungeons.<br>Accursio De Celeste <br>Mercenary and Researcher of Renowned Fame<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a skilled adventurer and treasure hunter, <br>and I have no qualms about doing what it takes to get what <br>I want. <br>Agenda: Escape from Stegeborg while keeping the secret of <br>what I have done, as well as keeping the treasure I have found <br>/ Take advantage of the arrival of the Hunters in Stegeborg to <br>appease the fury of Talia. <br>Gift – Good at Escaping:  Accursio is skilled at making <br>himself scarce when things get bad. Increase his OL by 1 <br>for all actions involving fleeing or avoiding a menace. Once <br>per Scene, Accursio can move away from a place without <br>anyone being able to stop or see him. To do this, however, <br>it is necessary that something happens that can attract the</p><p>Master<br>Tower<br>Arrival<br>DrawbridgeCourtyardEntry Hall<br>Formal Dining <br>Room<br>Kitchens<br>Fireplace<br>&lt; Pantry<br>&lt; Staircase to cellars<br>&lt; Upwards stairsServants’ ChambersServants’ Chambers<br>Connection CorridorConnection Corridor<br>Guard RoomGuard Room<br>139<br>general attention for a few moments, such as a fight or a <br>sudden event.<br>Main Court <br>Descriptor: The largest block of rooms and halls of the castle. <br>Despite the passing of time, it’s still possible <br>to see faded hints of past splendors and <br>beauty.<br>Information: The Hunters enter <br>the castle by its entry hall, a <br>large room with several pieces of furniture on which visitors <br>could leave coats and weapons. From the entry hall, you can <br>access the Formal Dining Room and the Servant’s Chambers. <br>Use the map of Stegeborg to see what the Hunters are up <br>against. Some rooms on the map do not have pre-established <br>encounters. As with Events, feel free to create content in <br>accordance with the Hunters’ choices.<br>First <br>floor</p><p>Noble Rooms<br>Tapestry Room<br>Balcony Balcony &lt; Balcony<br>&lt; Balcony<br>Fireplace<br>Guard Room<br>&lt;<br>Staircase to <br>first floor<br>140<br>Formal Dining Room<br>A large and lavish ballroom where there are 6 Quiet Guards.<br>Kitchens<br>The great kitchens of the castle. By crawling up inside the fireplace’s <br>chimney, you can reach the Noble Rooms on the second floor. By <br>inspecting the Kitchens, you can see that meals are still being prepared. <br>From the Kitchens, one can access the Cellars (page 141).<br>Servants’ Chambers<br>Upon entering the Servant’s Quarters, the Hunters will find the bodies <br>of servants half melded with walls and sinking into the floor, frozen in <br>expressions of terror. Getting too close to the walls will rouse the servants, <br>animating them.<br>Connection Corridor<br>A large corridor in the east wing of the castle. From the large, barred <br>windows, the Hunters will notice the figure of a man moving in the <br>Master Tower. It is Accursio, working hard on his escape.<br>Threat – Walls of Memory<br>Descriptor: Bodies and stone come alive to hold intruders in <br>a crazy embrace.<br>OL Easy 3<br>Gift – The Horror Sculpted in the Stone:  When the <br>Walls of Memory come alive, surprised targets receive 1 <br>Penalty to any potential Defense Check. The walls grab a <br>target and whisper words of despair and suffering in their <br>ears. Those who hear them must decide whether to lose 1 <br>Soma or suffer 1 Wound before freeing themselves.<br>Second <br>floor</p><p>141<br>The Guard Room<br>A narrow, small chamber tucked between the two floors <br>of the castle, divided into two by a wooden weapon rack. <br>A large, barred door leads to the Noble Rooms. Trying <br>to open the door without Talia’s permission activates the <br>Phantom Weapons Threat, which will attack the intruders <br>as long as they remain in the room.<br>Threat – Phantom Weapons<br>Descriptor: A series of weapons that float in the air, ready <br>to strike at unwelcome visitors.<br>OL Medium 5<br>Gift – Blade Storm:  When this Threat is activated, 1d6 <br>different targets will be attacked by a blade during each <br>Exchange. If there are more attacking blades than targets, <br>each target receives 1 Penalty to Defense Checks to avoid <br>being hit. Two additional attacking blades impose 2 <br>Penalties to Defense Checks to all targets, and so forth.<br>The Tapestry Room<br>A large and sumptuous room covered with tapestries and <br>paintings depicting the Schwernis family. Almost all the <br>paintings are untouched, but the largest on the north wall <br>is ruined. It’s possible to make out that the painting depicts <br>a family: father, mother, and daughter. The parents are <br>so similar that they look like twins. The husband’s face is <br>obscured by old blood, while the mother’s body has been <br>warped by cuts and stains making it look like a monster. <br>The daughter, a cold and sad figure in the pose, has two <br>scratches on her eyes, making them appear closed.<br>Cellars<br>In the large Cellars of the castle, the old barrels and piles of <br>dirt are home to Alexandra. The monster will not hesitate <br>to attack any intruder. Here a large metal hatch allows <br>access to the Dungeons of the castle. The hatch is locked <br>with Talia’s magic, but it can be opened with her key. There <br>are two copies. One is in the possession of Alexandra and <br>the other is held by Accursio.<br>Alexandra the Mother<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (5 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a monster, deformed in body and mind. <br>The curse that keeps me alive means that I cannot forget <br>what I have done. Now, with my misshapen mouth, I can <br>only grunt and whine, preventing me from imploring the <br>forgiveness of my daughter.<br>Agenda: After more than fifty years of a cursed existence, <br>I have come to understand the damage my sins have done. <br>Unable to beg for her forgiveness, I show my daughter how <br>much I regret the past by doing anything she asks of me.<br>Gift – Deformed Orc:  Alexandra is a huge monster with <br>herculean strength. She can act twice during an Exchange, <br>but not consecutively. The curse makes Alexandra resistant <br>to magic. Any action using magic that involves her receives <br>1 Penalty.<br>Information: Upon her death, Alexandra’s body <br>will reverse to that of a gorgeous middle-aged woman. <br>Alexandra is the only one, besides Accursio, who has a key <br>to the Dungeons.</p><p>Talia<br>Talia<br>142<br>Noble Rooms<br>Descriptor: A series of rich and beautiful rooms, preserved <br>despite the years passed.<br>Information: The only survivors of the village are held <br>prisoner in this part of the castle. Talia has Alexandra pick up <br>Lisbet every night to take her to the Dungeons and read her a <br>story. Lisbet is a young mother and her two children, Marita <br>and Lars, are among the prisoners. Lisbet realized that Talia <br>is nothing but a wounded spirit, so she tries to comfort the <br>girl by slowly gaining her trust. Lisbet’s hope is that sooner or <br>later, Talia will release her and all the other prisoners.<br>Lisbet<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a young widow and I settled in the village <br>to start anew. I have experienced many misfortunes in my life, <br>which have forced me to become stubborn and strong-willed. <br>However, I’ve managed to stay kind and generous.<br>Agenda: To save all the prisoners by convincing Talia to do <br>the right thing. <br>The Dungeons<br>Descriptor: A series of tunnels and galleries full of barred <br>doors leading to the treasure room.<br>Talia the Sleeper <br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a young girl put to sleep for eternity by the <br>magic of Carabosse. The whole castle responds to my will and, <br>thanks to my powers, I can see and hear everything.<br>Agenda: Revenge myself on Accursio, who betrayed my trust <br>the way so many others have / Finding peace through death, or <br>assimilating everything I can with my power.<br>Gift – Sleeping Spirit:  Talia can literally manipulate the <br>entire castle as she pleases. During each Exchange, she can <br>perform up to 3 of the following actions. 1. Manipulate: <br>Move or reshape an object of the castle into something else; <br>2. Attack:  Throw and move objects to inflict 1 Wound;  <br>3. Reject:  Prevent people from moving, entering, or <br>leaving by manipulating objects, or even the castle itself. <br>Talia cannot speak, but she can use Manipulate to write or <br>compose rudimentary messages through objects. Talia can <br>concentrate all 3 actions into one with devastating effects. It <br>can collapse an entire wing of the castle or open a deep well <br>in the ground. The effects of this action are wide-ranging and, <br>at the discretion of the Storyteller, may remove one or more <br>Hunters who fail a Defense Check from the Scene.<br>Information: Next to Talia’s sleeping body, one can find her <br>diary, written with a pen manipulated by her hair. It tells the <br>Sleeper’s whole sad story.</p><p>143<br>Note: Talia’s Gift, Sleeping Spirit, can be used in <br>countless ways throughout the Scenario. Below is a <br>set of suggestions for the Storyteller. Extracts of Talia’s <br>diary are on page 148.<br>Talia can:<br> ◆ Leave messages on pictures and furniture or send <br>the Hunters a page from her diary.<br> ◆ Lock and open doors to provide guidance.<br> ◆ Move the curtains on the windows to illuminate a <br>dark room.<br> ◆ Distort the paintings in the Tapestry Room so <br>her tragedy is better understood.<br> ◆ Lock the drawbridge to prevent someone from <br>escaping.<br> ◆ Withdraw the brambles from outside the castle, <br>pulling them in through the windows.<br> ◆ Use one of the prisoners as a warning.<br> ◆ Draw the Hunters’ attention to one of Accurio’s <br>belongings that has been left in the castle, and <br>which can hint at his presence.<br> ◆ Open a well in the treasure room as a way of warning <br>the Hunters away.</p><p>144<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario there are six Events. As a Storyteller, feel free <br>to create new ones in response to the actions of the Hunters.<br>At dawn on the day following the arrival of the <br>Hunters: Accursio will finish sawing the bars and will try to <br>escape by descending from the walls. Talia will unleash her <br>abilities and will capture him, taking him to the dungeons to <br>punish him.<br>If the Hunters manage to rescue Accursio from <br>Stegeborg: Talia will give into her fury, killing all the <br>prisoners except Lisbet. Now, the new target of the Sleeper’s <br>hatred will be the Hunters.<br>If the Hunters show interest in the history of the <br>Schwernis family:  Talia will ease the pressure on the <br>intruders, trying to guide them to the Tapestry Room.<br>If the Hunters make it clear to Lisbet that they are <br>there to save her:  the woman will say that she has read <br>some pages of Talia’s diary and that the spirit acts only out of <br>pain and trauma.<br>If the Hunters find a way to communicate with <br>Alexandra: she will ask them to save Talia from herself by <br>helping her to feel hope once more. Then she will drive the <br>Hunters to kill her by attacking them, so she can finally be <br>free from the curse.<br>If the Hunters reveal themselves to Accursio: he will <br>tell them that a spirit roams in the castle and that perhaps <br>something the adventurer stole has enraged it. The scoundrel <br>will seem sincerely repentant and will deliver what he has <br>stolen to the Hunters so that they can bring it back to the <br>basement and “appease” the spirit.<br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the Stegeborg’s <br>Quiet Scenario and can be acquired once the requirements <br>are met. A Hunter can only have one Scenario Gift and if they <br>acquire a new one, they will have to forgo the previous one.<br>Adept of the Quiet<br>Requirement: To have witnessed a manifestation of Talia’s <br>abilities within the castle.<br>Y ou realize that having a calm spirit prevents the castle from <br>perceiving you as a threat. Receive 1 Additional Success in <br>all Defense Checks you make against a manifestation of the <br>power of Stegeborg or a creature associated with the powers <br>of spirits.<br>The Castle’s Secrets<br>Requirement: Learn the secret passages of the castle from <br>Accursio or Lisbet.<br>Y ou know some of the many secret passages that connect the <br>whole castle. During a Scene, you can spend 1 Soma to find <br>a passage from one place to another in the castle, as long as <br>you have been there before. Y ou can’t leave the castle walls <br>with this Gift.</p><p>3a<br>1<br>2<br>145</p><p>FIRST SCENE –  Arrival at the <br>Village<br>It’s the same one you find on page 136.<br>End of Scene: After learning from Georg what happened <br>to the village and Accursio’s disappearance, the Hunters <br>continue their investigation at the castle. Go to the SECOND <br>SCENE – The Castle’s Courtyard.</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513729797,"modifiedTime":1781513729797,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"k74pwhIuE9sJoFZo","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Stegeborg's Quiet - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE – The Castle’s <br>Courtyard<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  After crossing the large <br>drawbridge, you finally arrive at the castle’s immense garden. <br>Brambles and ivy cover everything, and Georg’s description of <br>the havoc the plants caused in the village sounds more like <br>a story made up to frighten children. Two lights attract your <br>attention. One comes from the third floor of the large Master <br>Tower to your left. The second light shines from the second <br>floor of the castle. All the windows have thick bars and you <br>soon understand that the entrance doors of the two structures <br>are the only way to access the buildings.<br>Location: The large inner garden of the castle.<br>Time: Night has now fallen, a light coming from the tower <br>and one from the second floor of the castle shine in the dark.<br>Information: Talia will follow the actions of the Hunters <br>to understand their intentions and then animate the castle to <br>close them in by raising <br>the drawbridge. See <br>the Animated Bramble <br>Forest Threat on page <br>138.<br>End of Scene:  To <br>escape from the animated <br>brambles, the Hunters can <br>decide to enter the tower, <br>go to THIRD SCENE <br>OPTION A – Master Tower, <br>or the castle, go to THIRD SCENE OPTION B – Main Court.</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513729797,"modifiedTime":1781513729797,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"LrTT3680eaZHSi3F","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Stegeborg's Quiet - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION A –  <br>Master Tower<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  When you eventually enter <br>the tower, the brambles seem to recoil as if frightened of the <br>place. A call for help comes from the stairs. It seems whoever <br>inhabits the third floor has witnessed your escape and is <br>descending at a rapid pace towards you.<br>Place: The old Master Tower, where Talia killed her father <br>to defend herself fifty years earlier.<br>Time: It is night and only Accursio’s lantern’s light <br>illuminates the bare, gray rooms of the tower.<br>Information: Accursio will ask the Hunters for help, but <br>he will soon understand that they too can do little against <br>the power of Talia. The cunning adventurer will tell the <br>Hunters that an evil spirit resides in the castle and that, <br>The Scenario Stegeborg’s <br>Quiet in Scenes</p><p>3b<br>4<br>146<br>in his search of treasures, he must have inadvertently <br>awakened it. Appearing repentant, Accursio will ask the <br>Hunters to do something to save him since they are here <br>to solve the mystery. However, he will refuse to leave the <br>Tower, pointing out that the thorns almost killed him <br>when he tried to escape. To help the Hunters, Accursio will <br>show them one of the secret passages leading directly to <br>the Noble Rooms on the second floor. He will explain to <br>the Hunters that from there you can descend into a large <br>fireplace, reach the Kitchens, and then descend into the <br>Cellars where the evil spirit is located, avoiding most of the <br>dangers of the castle. <br>End of Scene:  Following Accursio’s directions, the <br>Hunters enter the castle through a secret passage, go to the</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513729797,"modifiedTime":1781513729797,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7D8I6quQmv9Cp7LX","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Stegeborg's Quiet - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE – Noble Rooms.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513729797,"modifiedTime":1781513729797,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"LrTT3680eaZHSi3F","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Stegeborg's Quiet - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION B –  <br>Main Court<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  When you finally enter the <br>castle, the brambles seem to settle and still once more as if <br>nothing had happened. In front of you is the huge castle of <br>Stegeborg, a maze with over one hundred rooms.<br>Place: The gloomy and abandoned castle of Stegeborg.<br>Time: It is night and only the light brought by the Hunters <br>illuminates the large dust-covered rooms.<br>Information: When exploring the castle, the Hunters <br>will pass through various Places (presented on page 139) <br>in the following order:<br>Servants’ Chambers (page 140)<br>Tapestry Room (page 141)<br>Guard Room (page 141)<br>Talia will observe the Hunters and can intervene thanks to <br>her Sleeping Spirit Gift (page 142).<br>End of Scene:  Past the Guard Room, the Hunters will <br>have access to the second floor, go to the FOURTH SCENE <br>– Noble Rooms.</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513729797,"modifiedTime":1781513729797,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"7D8I6quQmv9Cp7LX","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Stegeborg's Quiet - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE – Noble Rooms<br>Note: The Hunters can reach this Scene after exploring the <br>castle or thanks to the secret passage indicated by Accursio. <br>In the second case, before setting up this Scene, they will <br>go through the Tapestry Room (page 141) and then the <br>Guard Room (page 141).<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: You close the big door behind <br>you and you can hear the clang of the ghostly weapons that <br>still slam on the heavy wrought iron reinforcements. This <br>area of the castle seems illuminated and in fact, within a few <br>moments, some human figures stare at you from the bottom <br>of a large dining room. A woman with a thin and tired face <br>raises a hand in greeting.<br>Place: The castle’s main room, where the Schwernis family <br>lived.<br>Time: It is past midnight.<br>Information: Lisbet will welcome the Hunters, telling <br>them that all the prisoners are kept alive by a monster that <br>lives in the cellars, which regularly brings food and water. <br>Lisbet is often taken to the castle’s basement by the creature <br>to read or sing old stories to a girl who seems frozen in <br>perpetual sleep. Talking to Lisbet, the Hunters will also <br>discover:<br> ◆ The monstrous creature that feeds the prisoners moves <br>freely around the castle and possesses incredible <br>strength.</p><p>5<br>6<br>147<br> ◆ From the large fireplace in the dining room, you can <br>go downstairs to the Kitchens. From there you can <br>reach the Cellars where you can find the hatch for the <br>Dungeons. If the Hunters have spoken to Accursio, <br>they will then have confirmation that the man was not <br>lying.<br> ◆ Lisbet will say that the sleeping girl seems unutterably <br>sad and, despite what she has done in the village, Lisbet <br>cannot help but feel compassion for her rather than <br>hatred.<br>End of Scene:  Hunters can wait until Alexandra arrives <br>to ambush her or climb down the chimney and face her <br>directly in the Cellars. Go to THE FIFTH SCENE – The <br>Castle’s Orc.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513729797,"modifiedTime":1781513729797,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"uvtk4oRAfYNp0qYz","name":"Scene 5","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Stegeborg's Quiet - Scene 5</h2><p>FIFTH SCENE – The Castle’s Orc<br>Note: This Scene kicks off when the Hunters face <br>Alexandra.<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  What stands before your <br>eyes is a grotesque creature with vaguely human features. <br>An old noble woman’s dress dangles from its shape like a rag, <br>soiled with blood and ichor. The being is short of breath, but <br>its muscles are tense and powerful. Only the eyes glow with <br>a deep light of suffering and madness, protruding from the <br>deformed face, which is dotted with pustules and bubbles. <br>The being roars with all its anger before hurling itself against <br>you.<br>Place: The castle cellars or the dining room where all the <br>prisoners are kept.<br>Time: A few hours left until dawn.<br>Information: Alexandra will fight to the death, in the <br>hope that the Hunters will end her life, freeing her from the <br>curse. Once she’s killed, she’ll turn back into the beautiful <br>woman she once was. Around her neck, she wears a chain <br>with the key to the Dungeons’ trapdoor.<br>End of Scene:  Hunters can descend into the Dungeons <br>and finally meet Talia. Go to SCENE SIX – The Sad Sleeper.</p>"},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513729797,"modifiedTime":1781513729797,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"0X5Z0N46JvWjXyrZ","name":"Scene 6","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Stegeborg's Quiet - Scene 6</h2><p>SIXTH SCENE –  The Sad <br>Sleeper<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You pass down a few <br>long corridors before arriving at the castle’s large treasure <br>room. The door is wide open, and an unnatural green light <br>illuminates the entire room. The strange glow radiates from <br>a young girl floating in the air, asleep in an unnatural torpor. <br>Her skin is as cold and pale as that of a corpse. Only the very <br>long blond hair that lashes and moves unsettlingly allows you <br>to understand that this being is alive.<br>Place: The treasure room of the castle.<br>Time: The sun begins to rise as Accursio attempts his great <br>escape.<br>Information: Talia’s reaction will vary depending on <br>what the Hunters have done so far. Shortly after the Hunters <br>arrive, Accursio will be carried into the room by a group of <br>Quiet Guards and dragged in front of Talia to be executed.<br>End of Scene: The Hunters will be key to tipping the scales <br>in the epilogue of the sad story of the Sleeper of Stegeborg.</p><p>148<br>Talia’s <br>diary<br>Page 1 <br>How long will this captivity last? My parents say it is <br>for my own good, but in the meantime, sixteen years of <br>my life have passed without me ever setting foot outside <br>these walls. Father finally quieted my complaints by <br>giving me the keys to the Master Tower. I love spending <br>hours and hours in the tower, studying the villagers. <br>They go about their daily tasks, never knowing that I <br>sit here in a gilded cage and watch, longing to join in <br>their normal lives.<br>Page 2<br>My mother got very angry with the cook. Apparently, <br>she’s not as good a cook as Mother thought. The <br>problem is, Mother can be quite unreasonable. More <br>than once, I have seen her take out a fit of bad temper <br>on the servants. My father does nothing to stop her. On <br>the contrary, he seems to enjoy watching my mother <br>mercilessly wielding her authority to misuse the <br>servants. In the end, the cook ran away, leaving the <br>castle. My mother started calling her terrible names, <br>saying that such terrible food would have shamed <br>the whole Schwernis family. At dinner, my father <br>whispered something in my mother’s ear, running his <br>finger down her throat, and then together they laughed <br>rudely. I felt a shiver down my spine.<br>If I were a magician I would turn my mother into a <br>monster, because that’s what she is. Even if she looks <br>like a noblewoman, her soul is black and overflowing <br>with evil.<br>Page 3<br>The new cook is called Carabosse. She is a foreigner. <br>With the rumors about Mother’s cruelty, I don’t <br>wonder why no one in the village wants to work at the <br>castle anymore. Carabosse has a sweet face like that of <br>a loving grandmother, but also deep green eyes, which <br>seem to shine. She says she hails from the east and, if <br>I remember correctly, the prelate of the village on his <br>last visit spoke to my father of many witches fleeing <br>from the numerous stakes that are in use in Eastern <br>Europe. If Carabosse really is a witch, I hope she uses <br>magic and turns me into a bird. It would be nice to be <br>able to fly beyond these walls, above the clouds.</p><p>149<br>Page 4<br>Mother caught me. Some servant must have tattled on <br>my little visits to the village at night. Or maybe it was <br>the villagers who betrayed me, despite all the coins I <br>gave them... They too are just bloody selfish. Now, every <br>single window in the castle has a thick metal grate, and <br>the transformation from a palace to prison is complete. <br>My parents say this is for my own good, that the world <br>outside the castle is dangerous for a pure soul like mine. <br>That I am the daughter they have always desired, their <br>most precious treasure. But their intentions stifle my <br>soul, drowning it in utter darkness. Only Carabosse <br>understands me, but she seems to grow more and <br>more tired and sick. My father often stares at me with <br>frightening eyes, whispering the word “desired. ” <br>Page 5<br>I’ve discovered the truth and it ruined me. My father <br>and mother are twin siblings. Their love has never been <br>blessed by God and their obsession with a daughter has <br>led them to so many miscarriages. What remains of my <br>brothers and sisters is in the basement, too deformed <br>to survive. When my mother learned what I had <br>discovered, I was sure she would kill me. Instead, she <br>smiled, a sweet smile like I have never seen on her face <br>before. She said I am ready, that I am old enough to run <br>the family. I have been living in this room for a week <br>now, but tomorrow my father will return and a strange <br>feeling grips my heart. I am afraid because no one is <br>coming to save me.<br>Page 6<br>It happened. Mom is devastated by grief, but I don’t <br>regret what I did. When my father tried to… I can’t even <br>write it down. I fought back with all my might. I pushed <br>him away from me, but I didn’t mean for him to fall <br>down the tower. But even though I didn’t intend it, I felt <br>relieved. And at that very moment, I realized that my <br>soul had been forfeited. Now I’m waiting for my mother <br>to decide my fate. She howled in sorrow for the three <br>nights after Father’s fall, cursing God and promising me <br>infinite suffering as punishment for taking away the love <br>of her life.<br>Today, Carabosse came to bring me dinner, gave me a <br>caress on the head, and told me that all this will end. <br>“Sleep, my little one”... were her last words. And with <br>that one kind gesture, I let myself go to sleep. The only <br>real means at my disposal was to escape the walls of <br>Stegeborg.</p>"},"sort":600000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513729797,"modifiedTime":1781513729797,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"stegeborgs-quiet","collection":"The Broken Ones","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","pages":"135-150"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513729797,"modifiedTime":1781513729797,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Req2k0aFcgllOHrw","name":"In Your Eyes, with Your Feet","pages":[{"_id":"wilm0YALFrAWZ2RO","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>In Your Eyes, with Your Feet</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> The Broken Ones</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 151-162.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/in-your-eyes-with-your-feet-p151-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513732623,"modifiedTime":1781513732623,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"qy25A2INeAxYDfWd","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - Setup</h2><p>150<br>Once upon a time…<br>Vigo, a Galician port city. The Hunters were <br>summoned by the Countess of Vigo herself to <br>investigate two dangerous assassins with very <br>particular methods. Several mutilated bodies <br>have been found in recent weeks: three handsome <br>young girls, whose faces were removed by the two <br>murderers. An old spinner from the port saw two <br>cloaked figures wandering through the alleys of <br>the lower city, and that is why the Countess firmly <br>believes that this is the work of a pair of murderers <br>and not a single individual. It is not the first time <br>that something like this has happened. Ten years <br>ago, similar murders had disturbed the city, never <br>to be solved. The murders included ritualistic <br>elements using blood and flesh that brought to <br>mind the blackest of magic. The Countess fears <br>that, whatever hand held the knife, something dark <br>has come to hunt the people of Vigo. A ceremony <br>commemorating the ten-year anniversary of the <br>Count and the Countess is to be held soon, and the <br>shadow of the murders darkens what should be a <br>day of celebration for the whole city.<br>A Scenario Inspired by Cinderella (Charles Perrault)<br>In your Eyes, with <br>your Feet<br>Safety Keywords:  <br>Murder / Torture / Mutilation</p><p>151<br>The story that led us here…<br>Ten years ago, Maria Di Bello, a wealthy widow who <br>had always been faithful to the King of Spain, lived in Vigo <br>with her three daughters. The elder two were the fruit of her <br>relationship with her beloved husband, while the youngest <br>was the unfortunate result of a one-night stand with a ship <br>captain. Maria had always loved everyone the same way: <br>Francisca the elder, Marta the middle daughter, and Cinder <br>the youngest. Cinder had been named for the strange gray <br>hair she had inherited from her father, strikingly contrasting <br>the intense blond hair of her mother and sisters. When the <br>current Count Azul of Vigo reached marrying age, Maria <br>offered all her daughters. Cinder was immediately rejected <br>due to her hair, described as “horrible” by the noble Azul. <br>Resentful and envious, Cinder turned to the Kind Mother, a <br>powerful witch residing in the port of Vigo who had hidden <br>her identity behind the curious name. With the Mother’s <br>help, Cinder committed several murders, removing skin <br>and hair from the victims and reshaping her body to look <br>exactly as Count Azul desired. Her mother and sisters <br>noticed the change, and Cinder was forced to silence them. <br>With her death near at hand, Maria appealed to what little <br>humanity she knew her daughter still had, asking her to at <br>least spare her sisters. Cinder agreed, but to ensure their <br>silence she maimed them both, digging out an eye and <br>cutting off one of their feet. One-eyed and lame, the two <br>sisters fled the city in hopes of a new life. <br>But fate was not kind to Francisca and Marta and, after <br>ten years as beggars and outcasts, they returned to Vigo. <br>Fueled by resentment and transformed by hate for their <br>cruel sister, the two have sworn revenge. In this, they are <br>supported by the now elderly Kind Mother, whose tongue <br>Cinder cut out after she asked the new Countess for one too <br>many favors. The ambition and ruthless cruelty of Cinder <br>has therefore forged a strange alliance, formed by all the <br>women she has wounded along the bloody road to a life of <br>luxury at the court of Vigo.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>Cinder presents herself to the Hunters under the false <br>name of Princesca, the identity she used to seduce Azul. <br>The woman has many powers, such as enslaving animals <br>or disguising her appearance, as she has learned the art of <br>magic from the Kind Mother. The last remaining piece of <br>evidence that could link Cinder to her crimes is a pair of <br>glass slippers that the Kind Mother had created for her ten <br>years earlier. Clicking the heels of the magical slippers can <br>confuse or bewitch people. They were used to commit the <br>murders ten years ago, as Cinder bewitched her victims <br>so she could dissect them alive without interference. The <br>shoes fit Cinder’s feet perfectly, proving her involvement. In <br>addition, every night at midnight, Princesca returns to her <br>original appearance for a few minutes, revealing her true <br>identity before the magic recovers.<br>Francisca and Marta each wear a glass slipper and have <br>staged a return of the killer for two reasons: to put Cinder <br>under pressure, and to attract the attention of the Hunters <br>of the Order so that they shed light on the wicked actions <br>of their sister. The objective of the two is to be caught by the <br>Order and then try to bring the Hunters to their side.<br>Meanwhile, the Kind Mother plots her revenge. The old</p><p>1<br>152<br>witch is helping Francisca and Marta only to destabilize <br>Cinder. Once the Hunters begin closing in on Cinder, the <br>Kind Mother will ask the Countess to use magic to return <br>her tongue, promising to deal with the Hunters in return. <br>However, having regained speech, and consequently the <br>ability to perform magic, the Kind Mother will instead be <br>able to take revenge on that wretched girl who, ten years <br>earlier, trampled on everyone for her own gain.<br>Nota: In this Scenario, two NPCs have a double identity.<br>Cinder poses as Princesca, the Countess of Vigo. The <br>Kind Mother poses as the Old Port spinner. <br>Keep in mind that either name may be used without <br>explanation when discussing these characters.</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513732624,"modifiedTime":1781513732624,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"wxCNnroDyNEZVL8p","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - Scene 1</h2><p>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You are led by a servant to <br>the great reception hall of the noble Vigo palace. The rich decor <br>and the large number of servants at work suggest that Count <br>Azul of Vigo is among the richest nobles in all of Galicia. <br>You are greeted by the Count himself, a handsome man in <br>his forties, and his wife Princesca. According to rumors still <br>circulating, she is a girl of humble origins picked from among <br>many candidates for her incredible beauty.<br>Place: The magnificent palace of Count Azul of Vigo.<br>Time: It is a hot summer morning.<br>Initial Situation: After a quick presentation by Count <br>Azul, Princesca will take the floor. The Countess will <br>explain what happened (the discovery of three corpses) and <br>how they were killed, which sadly recalls the events that <br>transpired ten years ago. From the interview, Hunters can <br>obtain the following information:<br> ◆ Ten years earlier, a murderer terrorized Vigo by killing <br>six young girls and removing parts of their skin and <br>hair. All the victims had in common were their blond <br>hair and their beauty.<br> ◆ The killer’s actions culminated in the massacre of an <br>entire family. Maria, Francisca, Marta, and Cinder Di <br>Bello were all killed the same night. This was the last <br>act of the killer before he disappeared forever. Note <br>that the other two victims were commoners killed <br>by Cinder so she could steal their beauty. They are <br>unrelated to the Di Bello family, and not important to <br>the current investigation. <br> ◆ In the last week, the bodies of three prostitutes who <br>frequented the port were found. All were known for <br>their beauty and a healthy head of blonde hair. Each of <br>them had the skin from their faces removed.<br> ◆ An old spinner who lives near the harbor is the only <br>witness. She told the guards of two black-clothed <br>figures who lured one of the victims into the shadows. <br>The girl followed the figures as if hypnotized, as if <br>sorceries and dark arts were involved.<br> ◆ As lord and lady of Vigo, Princesca and Azul instruct <br>the Hunters to unravel the mystery and thus put an end <br>to the murderer’s ten-year slaughter.<br> ◆ In a day, it will be the wedding anniversary of Azul and <br>Princesca and to celebrate the occasion there will be <br>a party in the summer palace located just outside the</p><p>153<br>city. The only obvious concern of the Count is <br>not to appear weak in front of his noble guests. <br>During the interview, it will be clear to the Hunters <br>that it is Princesca who holds the reins of the city, <br>and that her husband Azul is only a rich brat with <br>little concern for the sufferings of his subjects. It <br>will also be apparent that Princesca is nervous when <br>speaking to the Hunters. If asked about it, she will <br>deflect by reminding them of her (overly vague) <br>humble beginnings and highlighting how lucky she <br>was to marry the Count.<br>After the interview, Princesca will reveal to the <br>Hunters where to find the old spinner and the last <br>corpse. They’re both in the port area. <br>The Palace of Count Azul <br>of Vigo<br>Descriptor: A sumptuous noble palace in the city <br>center.<br>The Count Azul of Vigo<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a rich and bored nobleman who <br>cares only about social position. <br>Agenda: To waste time between parties and <br>pleasures, leaving the burden of leadership to my wife <br>Princesca.<br>Cinder Known to all as <br>Princesca of Vigo<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC  <br>(3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am Cinder and, thanks to <br>magic, I pretend to be the attractive and kind <br>Princesca. Thanks to the power of the Kind <br>Mother, I control the entire city. I am cold and <br>determined and I won’t let anyone stand in <br>my way. <br>Agenda: Gain wealth and power by <br>manipulating my stupid husband / Solving <br>the mystery of the new killer who behaves <br>exactly as I did ten years ago. <br>Gift – Kind Magic:  Cinder is able <br>to use the magic that the Kind Moth-<br>er taught her. As an action, Cinder <br>can cast one of the following spells.  <br>1. Animal Servants:  A group of <br>animals (up to 6 subjects) blindly <br>obeys the will of Cinder, even per -<br>forming suicidal actions. Cinder <br>has used this power many times <br>on a pair of doves until they <br>have been completely enslaved <br>(see The Doves on page 154);  <br>2. Transmutation:  An ob -<br>ject or a portion of the envi-<br>ronment mutates to be trans-<br>formed into something else. <br>The mutation lasts through-</p><p>154<br>out the Scene and cannot affect living beings; 3. Wish: A <br>subject (other than the one casting the spell) can express a <br>wish and it will come true. The Storyteller will decide the <br>nearest mechanical effect to accomplish the wish, whether <br>it is a new Descriptor, to heal one or more Wounds, or to <br>obtain a Gift. The effect of Wish cannot bring the dead back <br>to life, it only affects the subject who expresses it and lasts <br>until midnight.<br>Gift – Beauty Wish:  Thanks to the power of magic, <br>Cinder can assume any appearance she wants. The effect <br>lasts until midnight and usually Cinder uses it to maintain <br>the appearance of Princesca.  <br>The Doves<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC  <br>(1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are two doves enslaved by the power of <br>Cinder. Magic has permanently broken our will and we <br>defend our mistress from all danger. <br>Gift – Go for the Eyes:  The Doves are skilled at hitting <br>the enemies’ weak spots. When a Dove manages to inflict a <br>Wound, it inflicts 1 additional Wound. In case of a positive <br>Outcome in a Defense Check, once per Scene, the Dove’s <br>attack will still inflict 1 Wound. This Gift cannot be used <br>more than once against the same target <br>during the Scenario.<br>The Port of Vigo<br>Descriptor: The great city’s port where ships from all over <br>the world are docked. The alleys in front of the port are a <br>crossroads of taverns, shops, and leisure houses. Even in the <br>middle of the night, there’s always life in the harbor. <br>Information: The Old Spinner resides in a small house <br>in the eastern part of the pier, while the last corpse was <br>found in the western area.<br>East of the pier:  The Hunters will be able to meet the <br>Kind Mother, who will present herself as an old silent <br>seamstress. Cinder knows that the spinner is the Kind <br>Mother, but gives no sign that she knows. The old witch <br>will communicate with the Hunters with some difficulty <br>and give them a brooch she found near the alley where <br>she saw the two cloaked silhouettes pass. The brooch bears <br>the coat of arms of the Di Bello family: the Kind Mother <br>herself will give directions to the Di Bello house, located in <br>the upper quarters of the city. The old witch will not follow <br>the Hunters, as she does not want to be seen by Francisca <br>and Marta.<br>West of the pier:  The Hunters will find Eduardo and <br>Felipe, two guards at the service of the Count of Vigo, <br>guarding the crime scene. The body of the young prostitute <br>(known as Estella) was moved to the icebox of an old fish <br>warehouse nearby.<br> ◆ The two guards will tell the Hunters that no one has <br>claimed her body. She is most likely one of the many <br>poor people just trying to get by. <br> ◆ Examining Estella’s body will confirm the removal <br>of all facial skin, performed with insane care. A very</p><p>155<br>precious ring was inserted in the young woman’s right <br>eye orbit. The ring has the coat of arms of the Countess <br>of Vigo engraved on it. The object was placed there by <br>Francisca and Marta to draw attention to Cinder. <br>The Kind Mother Known to all <br>as the Old Spinner<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am an old and powerful witch whose tongue <br>Cinder cut out. I can no longer use my magic, but I still have <br>potions and magic items to use for my purposes.<br>Agenda: Put Cinder under pressure so she asks for my help, <br>make her use Wish to give me back my tongue, and then use <br>my magic to take revenge on her. <br>Gift – Kind Magic:  As an action, the Kind Mother can <br>cast one of the following spells. 1. Animal Servants: A <br>group of animals (up to 6 subjects) blindly obeys the will <br>of the Kind Mother and even performs suicidal actions; <br>2. Transmutation:  An object or a portion of the <br>environment mutates to be transformed into something <br>else. The mutation lasts throughout the Scene and cannot <br>affect living beings; 3. Wish: A subject (other than the <br>one casting the spell) can and will express a wish. The <br>Storyteller will decide the nearest mechanical effect to <br>accomplish the wish, whether it is a new Descriptor, to heal <br>one or more Wounds, or to obtain a Gift. The effect of Wish <br>cannot bring the dead back to life, it only affects the subject <br>who expresses it and lasts until midnight. Note: The Kind <br>Mother cannot use this Gift unless she first finds a way to <br>heal her severed tongue.<br>Gift – Witch’s Treasures:  The Kind Mother possesses <br>a large number of magical objects and potions, which she <br>can use or give to her allies. Once per Scenario, she can <br>make use of each of these effects. 1. Potion: If ingested, <br>a potion bestows a Descriptor that provides an incredible <br>ability, such as flying or being invisible for the duration <br>of the Scene. No potion can grow her tongue back. 2. <br>Heirloom: The Kind Mother can get a hold of a Treasure <br>of the Order (page 5) that has not already been found <br>and is not in the possession of the Hunters.<br>Eduardo and Felipe<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are two guards who are content to leave <br>thinking to other people. We do as we’re told while doing as <br>little as possible.    <br>The Di Bello Family <br>House<br>Descriptor: A large, abandoned villa in the bourgeois <br>districts of Vigo.<br>Information: Francisca and Marta live in the house <br>their mother abandoned. The two sisters traveled around <br>the world for a long time, but it was in mystical Prague <br>they underwent the strange rite that sewed their bodies <br>together. Now, the two women act as one creature, each <br>wearing on her foot one of the glass slippers that the Kind <br>Mother gave them. Francisca and Marta will be hostile to <br>the Hunters until they discover their identity. At that point,</p><p>156<br>the sisters will fall at their feet, begging them to expose <br>Cinder, who has escaped the consequences of her crimes <br>for ten years, hiding under the false identity of Princesca.<br> ◆ The two sisters are willing to do anything to get revenge <br>on Cinder, including going to prison or even giving up <br>their lives.<br> ◆ They will reveal to the Hunters that Cinder uses magic <br>to alter her appearance. Ten years earlier their mother <br>Maria had discovered the deception when she surprised <br>Cinder at the stroke of midnight, the moment each day <br>when she must recast her transfiguration spell.<br>Francisca and Marta the Vengeful <br>Sisters<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: We are two poor sisters sewn together in one <br>body. We move with perfect coordination and cooperate <br>effortlessly, each aiding the other against any danger. <br>Agenda: Discredit Princesca and reveal to everyone that <br>she is Cinder, our despised sister.<br>Gift – The Razor-sharp Glass Slippers:  Thanks to <br>the magical slippers the Kind Mother gave them, at every <br>step Francisca and Marta can click the glass heels and create <br>a resonance that generates a state of confusion in subjects <br>within forty feet. When a Hunter acts under the influence <br>of the Slippers, they must perform a Defense Check against <br>OL Medium 5 or lose their action for the Exchange. This <br>effect is considered mental manipulation. Once per Scene, <br>the two sisters can click their heels and cause a vibration <br>that damages the minds of those within reach. All affected <br>subjects must pass a Defense Check against OL Hard 7 or <br>suffer 1 Wound. Activating the Slippers is considered a free <br>additional action for the sisters. <br>Gift – As One Body:  Francisca and Marta can act twice <br>during an Exchange, once for each sister.<br>Count Azul of Vigo’s <br>Summer Residence<br>Descriptor: A beautiful villa in the countryside of Galicia.<br>Information: The feast for the tenth wedding anniversary <br>of Azul and Princesca is being held in the villa. Noblemen <br>and wealthy bourgeois are among the guests at the reception, <br>while a large troupe of acrobats has the task of brightening <br>up the evening with songs, dances, and juggling. A skilled <br>animal tamer has been arranged at the explicit request of <br>Princesca, who will therefore always have animals (a tiger <br>and a bear) to control with magic if need be.<br> ◆ Talking to the guests during the reception, the Hunters <br>will discover that after ten years, many are still <br>wondering how a girl of humble origins could steal the <br>heart of Count Azul.<br> ◆ At the stroke of midnight, before the great final toast, <br>Princesca will fake being dizzy to get away for those <br>few minutes she needs to cast her transfiguration spell.</p><p>157<br>Akim the Tamer<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC <br>(2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a brave and skilled <br>tamer. The tiger Tasha and the bear <br>Berto are both dear to me, as they obey <br>my every command.<br>Agenda: Perform and amaze the <br>audience with my animals / Prevent <br>anyone from harming Tasha and <br>Berto, whom I consider as my children.<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario, there are six Events. As a Storyteller, feel <br>free to create new ones in response to the actions of the <br>Hunters.<br>If the Hunters keep Princesca informed of the <br>investigation: the clever woman will quickly understand <br>that someone is framing her and will send Eduardo and <br>Felipe to deal with the Kind Mother. If the Hunters don’t do <br>something, the old witch won’t escape her fate. <br>If the Hunters defeat Francisca and Marta: the two <br>sisters will tell them everything they know, imploring the <br>Hunters to help expose Cinder.<br>If the Hunters unmask Cinder:  The Countess will <br>use the power of her magic to escape and run to the Kind <br>Mother for her help. Once she regains her voice thanks to <br>Cinder’s use of Wish, the Kind Mother will assist Cinder <br>to eliminate the Hunters and then take her time making <br>Cinder pay. <br>If the Hunters understand who the Kind Mother <br>really is: The witch will offer her aid in exchange for her <br>life and will seek their help in regaining her voice. <br>If the Hunters seek the support of Azul:  The Count <br>will pretend to be a fool and will even avoid taking measures <br>against Cinder once she has been unmasked. The man is <br>so willfully ignorant that he will ban the Hunters from the <br>city in order to keep his wife where she is, managing all the <br>responsibilities so he can lead a life of laziness. <br>If the Hunters trap Cinder during the anniversary <br>party: The woman will use magic to take control of Tasha <br>and Berto, sending them against the Hunters. Akim will <br>hinder the Hunters if they try to harm his beloved animals. <br>Cinder will try to escape to the Kind Mother by taking <br>advantage of the chaos. <br>Tasha the Tiger<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor <br>NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a fast and <br>aggressive, though trained, tiger.<br>Berto the Bear<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC  <br>(3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a strong and massive trained <br>bear.</p><p>158<br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the In your Eyes, <br>with your Feet Scenario and can be acquired once the conditions <br>are met. A Hunter can only have one Scenario Gift and if they <br>acquire a new one, they will have to forgo the previous one.<br>Gift – Kind Blessing<br>Requirement: Show a sincere interest in solving the mysterious <br>murders in Vigo to the Kind Mother.<br>A powerful witch has blessed you with protection against magic <br>and sorcery. Receive 2 Additional Successes when you make a <br>Defense Check against a magic effect. The first time you inflict 1 <br>Wound on a target using magic, the blessing dissipates until the <br>next Interlude.<br>Note: The Storyteller can offer this Gift to the Hunter who has met <br>the requirements without revealing who the witch who casts the <br>blessing is. Simply, the Hunter will become aware that someone is <br>trying to help them.<br>Gift – The Razor-sharp Glass Slippers (Treasure of <br>the Order)<br>Requirement: Defeat Francisca and Marta.<br>Obtain the Treasure of the Order The Razor-sharp Glass Slippers, <br>see page 25 of the Treasury of the Order.</p><p>1<br>2a 2b<br>159<br>The Scenario Through your <br>Eyes, with your Feet in <br>Scenes</p><p>FIRST SCENE –  The Regents of <br>Vigo<br>It’s the same one you find on page 152. The Hunters will <br>talk to Azul and Princesca.<br>End of Scene:  The Hunters can decide whether to <br>interrogate the Old Spinner, go to SECOND SCENE <br>OPTION A – The Old Spinner. Or examine the body of the <br>last victim, go to SECOND SCENE OPTION B – The crime <br>scene.</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513732624,"modifiedTime":1781513732624,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"jJuzzgniHRhbsPj9","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE OPTION A <br>– The Old Spinner<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: The port of Vigo is very busy <br>and represents the heart of the city. Its importance can be seen <br>clearly in the constant flow of goods and the ships crowded at <br>the docks. Following the directions given by Princesca, you <br>come to a small house in one of the alleys right next to a large <br>fish market, each fisherman setting up his stall directly on his <br>docked boat. You find the door to the small open dwelling, <br>and when you enter you see the figure of an old lady sewing. <br>The woman opens her mouth as if to greet you, but no <br>sound emerges. It quickly becomes clear her tongue has been <br>removed, leaving only a stump behind in her mouth. <br>Place: A small house that the spinner also uses as a <br>tailoring workshop. <br>Time: It is late morning and the smell of fresh fish coming <br>from the fishermen’s ships tickles the nostrils. <br>Information: The Kind Mother will welcome the <br>Hunters, trying to make herself understood to the best of <br>her ability, and will give the same information presented <br>on page 155. <br>End of Scene: Having obtained the brooch and directions <br>to the house of the Di Bello family, the Hunters can go there <br>to investigate. Go to THIRD SCENE – The old house of the <br>Di Bello family. Or examine the body of the last victim, go <br>to SECOND SCENE OPTION B – The crime scene.<br>Note: For correct management of the clues, the Hunters <br>must go to an interview with the Old Spinner before the</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513732624,"modifiedTime":1781513732624,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Zo1B4LXx7mUNY3Hc","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE – The old house of the Di Bello family.</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513732624,"modifiedTime":1781513732624,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"jJuzzgniHRhbsPj9","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE OPTION B – <br>The crime scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  The port of Vigo is very <br>busy and represents the heart of the city. Its importance can <br>be seen clearly in the constant flow of goods and the ships <br>crowded at the docks. Following the instructions given by <br>Princesca, you arrive at an old warehouse that is now being <br>used as a morgue. Two men who look quite drowsy guard the <br>front door.<br>Place: An old warehouse in the western part of the port. <br>Time: It is late morning. A large ship from the Americas is <br>docking at the port.</p><p>3<br>160<br>Information: Eduardo and Felipe will be well disposed <br>towards the Hunters, letting them in to examine the body <br>of the victim. They can discover the information on page <br>155. <br>End of Scene: With all the doubts that the ring can put in <br>the minds of the Hunters, there are still some fundamental <br>clues missing. They can go and talk to the Old Spinner. Go <br>to SECOND SCENE OPTION A – The Old Spinner. Or, if <br>they’ve been there already, they can head to the THIRD <br>SCENE – The old house of the Di Bello family.</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513732624,"modifiedTime":1781513732624,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Zo1B4LXx7mUNY3Hc","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE –  The old house <br>of the Di Bello family<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  The house of the Di <br>Bello family is an elegantly imposing villa that, despite its <br>abandonment, stands out among the houses of the upper <br>districts of Vigo. Sun-bleached curtains in the second-floor <br>windows have been disturbed, perhaps by new occupants of <br>the long-abandoned home.<br>Place: The grand, abandoned house of the Di Bello family.<br>Time: It is just past noon.<br>Information: Francisca and Marta are in the house. As <br>soon as the Hunters enter, they will be attacked by the sisters. <br>Once defeated, the two women will reveal their identities <br>and the whole story of Cinder, asking for the Hunters’ help <br>in unmasking their sister. The two will suggest that the <br>Hunters confront Cinder during the wedding anniversary <br>party that will be held the following evening.<br> ◆ The two sisters will confess that they are using the <br>same methods and plan that Cinder used ten years <br>earlier. They will also say that they put the ring in the <br>victim’s eye (if the Hunters have found it) to guide the <br>investigation towards the Countess.<br> ◆ The two sisters will say they were helped by an old <br>witch who gave them the slippers. The woman left  <br>them the shoes without saying a word, so the sisters <br>could not see her face.<br>End of Scene:  It will now be clear to the Hunters that <br>the Countess hides a secret, go to the FOURTH SCENE – <br>Unmasking the Countess.</p><p>4<br>161</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513732625,"modifiedTime":1781513732625,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"poJdKwFXYFnp5HDF","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>In Your Eyes, with Your Feet - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE –  Unmasking the <br>Countess<br>This scene can develop in many ways and in many possible places, so <br>it’s presented below with different tips for managing your Scenario.<br>If the Hunters want to unmask Cinder: The best way will be to <br>catch her red-handed while casting the spell to alter her appearance <br>at midnight. If they wish to, the Hunters will be welcome to attend <br>the reception. Once unmasked, Cinder will stir up the beasts of <br>Akim against the Hunters, then try to flee to the Kind Mother <br>for help.<br>If the Hunters tell everything to Princesca: The Countess <br>will thank them, trying to dismiss them as soon as possible, and <br>then move her guards to arrest her sisters and the Kind Mother. <br>If the Hunters do nothing, the three women will disappear into <br>the dungeons of the castle never to be seen again.<br>If the Hunters attempt to expose the Kind Mother:  <br>The old witch will try to play on their pity to avoid being <br>handed over to the Order. The old woman’s primary goal  is <br>to regain her tongue thanks to Cinder’s magic. Once she has <br>done that, she will try to eliminate every potential witness, <br>Hunters included.<br>End of Scene:  However the Scene goes, once again the <br>fate of the unfortunate protagonists of this story will be in <br>the hands of the Hunters.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513732625,"modifiedTime":1781513732625,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"in-your-eyes-with-your-feet","collection":"The Broken Ones","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","pages":"151-162"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513732625,"modifiedTime":1781513732625,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"OqqlCMgDTNL7DhGk","name":"I Will Stay with You Always","pages":[{"_id":"2q8SsghTKOQM4Qg1","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>I Will Stay with You Always</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> The Broken Ones</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf, pages 163-175.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/i-will-stay-with-you-always-p163-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513735097,"modifiedTime":1781513735097,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"k03UNPaHnOx3II3D","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>I Will Stay with You Always - Setup</h2><p>162<br>Once upon a time…<br>Prague is a great city recovering from war, after <br>Fredrick the Great’s recently failed siege. Ostromir <br>Malý, the Bohemian regent of Prague, has sent <br>an urgent request for help to the Order. The <br>nobles charged with rebuilding Prague are being <br>murdered in a way that has shocked the city, one <br>each night and all by the same hand. Each corpse <br>has been found with a body part removed and a <br>message scrawled on the walls reading, “I will stay <br>with you always. ” Ostromir has commissioned <br>the well-known alchemist Konstantin Svoboda to <br>construct a new guardian for the city – a Golem <br>– but the construction has been delayed. Until <br>its completion, the Hunters have been called on <br>to track down the noble-stalking killer, while the <br>commoners of the city, enthralled, watch like the <br>audience at a play.<br>A Scenario Inspired by The <br>Happy Prince (Oscar Wilde) by <br>Tommaso De Benetti<br>I Will Stay with You Always<br>Safety Keywords:<br>  <br>Body Horror / Murder / Torture</p><p>163<br>The story that led us here…<br>In the city of Prague stood a statue called the Happy <br>Prince, so-called for its extraordinary beauty: the body of <br>the statue was covered with a thin layer of gold and the eyes <br>were sapphires. On the hilt of the sword are set beautiful <br>rubies. One quiet evening, a young swallow on his yearly <br>migration to Egypt decided to rest under the sculpture. The <br>Prince saw the way the ordinary people of Prague suffered <br>from hunger and fear in the half-ruined city, and the statue <br>wept with pity. The Prince’s tears moved the bird to feel <br>the same compassion for the commoners of the city. The <br>Prince convinced the swallow to take the precious things <br>from his body and bring them to those in need. “The living <br>think that gold can make them happy, ” said the Prince, and <br>on hearing that, the swallow consented. Day after day the <br>swallow stripped the statue of everything that was valuable <br>to give that wealth to the people of Prague, who were <br>ground endlessly beneath the bootheels of the powerful. <br>Doing so, however, took so long that winter arrived. The <br>swallow could no longer reach Egypt to be reunited with <br>his flock. He decided to stay near to the Prince, who the <br>bird now loved, until one sad day the cold froze the swallow <br>into a grim little statue. Being powerless to save his friend <br>finally broke the Prince’s heart. Now worthless, the statue <br>was removed and handed over to Konstantin Svoboda, the <br>alchemist, for his experiments. For some reason, the lump <br>of lead at the statue’s heart refused to melt.<br>At the request of God Himself, an angel descended from <br>Paradise to retrieve the two most precious things Prague <br>had to offer: the Prince’s heart and the body of the <br>swallow. But the angel returned to Heaven empty-<br>handed, for in both the heart of the Prince and the spirit <br>of the swallow pity had been replaced by hatred for the <br>way Prague had rewarded their generosity.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>Deemed unworthy of Paradise, the spirit of the swallow <br>instead possessed the body of Alexandr Pták, known <br>professionally as Alexandr the Bird. He was a circus <br>acrobat whose trademark was long flights through the <br>air during the dangerous stunts that made up his act. <br>Alexandr, who officially disappeared a few weeks ago, is <br>now almost completely under the control of the spirit. <br>With the little lucidity he had left, the acrobat returned <br>to Černobog, the young son of a seamstress to whom <br>the swallow had donated two rubies. Černobog’s mother <br>died from hardship and deprivation she suffered in <br>making a noble’s party dress. The boy had long been <br>considering retaliation against the client who had made <br>such unreasonable demands. Černobog and Alexandr <br>overcame their communication barriers to reach an <br>agreement. First they would recover the Prince’s body <br>and then they would dedicate themselves to avenging his <br>memory. They arrived at the laboratory of Konstantin, <br>the alchemist in charge of building the Golem. <br>Konstantin was desperate. Despite all the resources that <br>had been provided to him, the work couldn’t proceed <br>without the essential missing ingredient, which is, <br>unfortunately for him, human flesh. The regent had <br>threatened to expel him from Prague in the absence of <br>developments, but the arrival of Černobog and Alexandr <br>seemed providential.</p><p>1<br>164<br>Although Černobog had been ready to pay for it with a <br>ruby, the Prince’s body had already been melted down. <br>His lead heart, however, is still relatively intact. Konstantin <br>thus proposes a pact: Černobog will invest the ruby to buy <br>the old circus from which Alexandr comes, which will <br>become the new secret laboratory of the alchemist. Then <br>the boy and Alexandr will be able to devote themselves <br>to their revenge, each time taking a piece of the body of <br>the victims as part of their bargain with the alchemist. In <br>return, Konstantin will rebuild the Prince, unleashing him <br>during the upcoming dance at Prague Castle...<br>Note: This Scenario presents an investigation in which <br>Hunters have a wide range of options on how to proceed. <br>The initial presentation of the places corresponds to the <br>Read aloud to the Hunters of the Scene Tree mode. This <br>method makes it easier for Hunters to review the clues and <br>overall situation at the beginning of each Scene.</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513735098,"modifiedTime":1781513735098,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"obu6KrzrlBEMp4T4","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>I Will Stay with You Always - Scene 1</h2><p>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  The regent of Prague, <br>Ostromir Malý, welcomes you in his brightly lit study, located <br>inside the castle of the city, a fortified complex recently <br>renovated by Empress Maria Theresa of Habsburg. Behind his <br>slick desk of fine wood, the short, ragged little Ostromir almost <br>disappears. He welcomes you with a certain enthusiasm and <br>you immediately notice how nervous he is: after introducing <br>himself he begins to compulsively clean his glasses, while <br>trying in vain to attract the attention of two servants in order <br>to offer you refreshment. Without even letting you speak, <br>he tries to fill the silences with bizarre questions about the <br>nature of the Order, but he doesn’t seem really interested in <br>your answers. Around a marble table, seated on chairs lined <br>with red satin, there are three other people: an old man with <br>a long beard and gray mustache, a gentleman in his forties <br>with thick brown hair, and a gorgeous blonde girl in elegant <br>clothes. Ostromir introduces them respectively as Konstantin <br>Svoboda, a well-known alchemist, Bartoloměj Novotný, <br>assistant to the director of the National Theater, and Beáta <br>Czernin, a member of one of the noble families of the city.  <br>He then invites you to sit on empty chairs and, sinking into <br>his, begins to explain the situation.         <br>Place: A beautiful room in Prague Castle, too big for a <br>modest presence like that of Ostromir. In addition to the <br>table where much of the conversation will take place after <br>the arrival of the Hunters, there’s a beautiful display of <br>golden chandeliers hanging from the ceiling, large mirrors <br>with precious frames, fine carpets on polished floors, and, <br>on the walls, huge tapestries darkened by time. <br>Time: Late afternoon, an ideal time for tea.</p><p>165<br>Initial Situation: Ostromir appears obviously nervous as <br>if he knows how much his success depends on the Hunters’ <br>help. <br>Information: From the interview with Ostromir, <br>Konstantin, Bartoloměj, and Beáta, the following <br>information can be obtained:<br> ◆ Someone is killing (or trying to kill) prominent <br>people in Prague. The connection between the cases is <br>obvious, as the words “I will stay with you always” have <br>been found written on the wall with various substances <br>at the crime scenes. <br> ◆ Beáta found her murdered lover in her rooms, wearing <br>a dress he’ d bought for her. He was found missing an <br>arm.<br> ◆ Bartoloměj found the theater director, Gabriel Černý, <br>lying with one leg severed on the stage where a new <br>show was to be performed just a few hours later. <br> ◆ Konstantin seems to have escaped the killer through <br>a coincidental routine change (he had been delayed <br>longer than usual in a nearby tavern), but his alchemical <br>lab was devastated.<br>Hunters can now choose where to start their investigations.<br>Ostromir Malý<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I rule Prague on behalf of Empress Maria <br>Theresa and, after the failed siege, I hold the city’s fate in the <br>palm of my hand. The recent murders are complicating my <br>life, though so far the noble families support my authority.<br>Agenda: Capture the assassin who is causing panic among <br>the nobles / Avoid a popular uprising.<br>Beáta Czernin the Noblewoman<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am part of the city’s elite and I take advantage <br>of it. Sometimes, my vanity and arrogance unexpectedly <br>cause annoyances. <br>Agenda: Distancing myself from my late lover Danek in the <br>eyes of my husband and family / Finding out which monster <br>may have murdered him in this way.<br>The Alchemical <br>Laboratory<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You reach the workshop <br>from a small staircase on one side of Haštalská, the street <br>in Prague that runs alongside the Church of St. Castulus. A <br>stone corridor leads you to what looks like the entrance to <br>a cell, protected by a wooden door reinforced by large iron <br>bars. Konstantin pulls out a large key that he hangs on his <br>neck and makes his way inside the laboratory, where the <br>soft light of lanterns hanging on the wall illuminates a cold <br>space similar to a tomb. Built of red brick and furnished with <br>wooden tables and benches, the workshop houses hundreds <br>of stills, bottles, and parchments abandoned on dusty shelves. <br>Dried plants and other esoteric trinkets hang from the ceiling. <br>In the center of the room is a forge, which Konstantin uses <br>to process minerals of various kinds, while in the corner an <br>elegant wooden desk is covered with paperwork, inks, and <br>pens for writing. What strikes you most is the almost total <br>devastation of a wing of the laboratory, now a pile of rubble, <br>glass, and split wooden boards. On the ground, a dry puddle <br>of god-knows-what emits a nauseating stench. Konstantin</p><p>166<br>apologizes for the mess, saying he didn’t have the strength to <br>fix it, “now that he’s alone. ” On the wall, written in smears <br>with dark mineral powders, you see: “I will stay with you <br>always. ” <br>Descriptor: An underground laboratory with a large forge <br>and esoteric trinkets. The east wing is a pile of rubble and on <br>the wall in front of you can clearly be read the phrase: “I will <br>stay with you always.”<br>Information: Depending on their ability to ask questions <br>and examine clues, Hunters can access some or all of the <br>following information:<br> ◆ Anything that was broken or stolen had little value, <br>with the exception of a lead heart that belonged to an <br>old statue that was recently removed from the city. <br>Konstantin says that the heart was the subject of his <br>studies, as he had not been able to melt it. <br> ◆ Konstantin is working on a secret project on behalf <br>of the city of Prague (the Golem), which he is very <br>reluctant to talk about. Apparently, it’s not proceeding <br>as planned. <br> ◆ A few days ago, a man who was in charge of cleaning <br>was fired: Georg Slanina, who lives in the nearby <br>rookery. Konstantin claims he was often intoxicated, <br>which is true. The real reason for the dismissal, not to be <br>revealed to the Hunters directly, was to allow Alexandr <br>to recover the Prince’s heart and stage the devastation <br>of the laboratory without inconvenient witnesses.<br>Konstantin Svoboda the Alchemist<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am one of the most prominent alchemists in <br>Prague. My brilliant experiments could easily backfire on me. <br>Agenda: Create a Golem thanks to my alchemical studies <br>and prove that no noble title or institutional position can <br>possibly compare to my alchemical knowledge. <br>Gift – The Secrets of Metal:  Konstantin knows arcane <br>words that allow him to control metal. Any action against <br>him involving a metal weapon or bludgeoning tool receives <br>1 Penalty. Starting from moderate amounts of raw materials, <br>Konstantin can also forge various metal objects with <br>unusual properties. The Storyteller must create a Descriptor <br>that outlines this property (for example: The alloy of this <br>dagger violently repels other metals). <br>Gift – The Secrets of Flesh:  Once per Scene, when a <br>metallic body is in the vicinity of warm flesh, whether it’s still <br>attached to the body or only recently removed, Konstantin <br>can utter some arcane words, forcing the two elements to <br>merge. The procedure causes 1 immediate Wound, and 1 <br>additional Wound during the painful medical procedure <br>necessary to untangle flesh and metal.</p><p>167<br>The Rookery<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  As you enter the rookery, <br>you realize that you are being spied on: tired and hostile faces <br>observe you from half-open balconies; mothers hurriedly pick <br>up the children playing in the street and the men spit on the <br>ground when they pass you by. On several street corners, you <br>notice men and women in brightly colored but worn clothes, <br>looking hungry and cold, asking for alms while standing on <br>their heads, juggling, or performing other little tricks.<br>Descriptor: A maze of old houses with faded walls. Weary <br>and hostile faces watch those who pass, while the poor and <br>hungry ask for alms along the streets.<br>Information: Depending on their ability to ask questions <br>and examine clues, Hunters may discover some or all of the <br>following information: <br> ◆ The general sentiment of the population with regard <br>to the recent murders, rumor of which has spread, is of <br>ill-concealed approval. The blank, unconcerned gazes <br>of any commoners interviewed makes it clear they <br>think the nobles deserved it. <br> ◆ This is a good point of contact between the Hunters <br>and some artists of the Circus of the Azure Sun. See <br>the section Cibulka Tavern for available information. <br> ◆ If they visit Georg, the characters find him drunk in his <br>house, and very aggressive. If subdued or persuaded to <br>speak, Georg will say that Konstantin is at his wits’ end <br>as the project he is leading on behalf of the city is not <br>going well. <br> ◆ The attic where Josef Slezák lived (see page 169) <br>burned down two days earlier. By convincing a couple <br>of soldiers to grant them access, the Hunters will <br>discover that the writer seems to have bought a huge <br>amount of wood, with which he feverishly filled the <br>stove until it exploded. The embers set fire to the rest <br>of the attic, devouring the roof of the house and Josef <br>himself. <br> ◆ If the Hunters are looking for him, Černobog (see <br>page 172) is not at home, as he is now permanently <br>stationed at the Circus of the Azure Sun. By breaking <br>in, however, they will be able to access his rooms. <br>There, the boy still keeps his mother’s sewing tools <br>and the notebook where she noted expenses and <br>orders, including that for Danek Brzobohatý (one of <br>the victims, details on page 168). On the front of the <br>notebook, there is the name of the woman: Hedvika <br>Potměšil.<br>Georg Slanina the Helper <br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I work very hard. I like to drink, and when I <br>do, I become a beast. <br>Agenda: Supporting my daughter, who now has to sell <br>matches on the street / Understanding why Konstantin fired <br>me.</p><p>168<br>Cibulka Tavern<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  Cibulka’s entrance is <br>blackened by dirt, soot, and the effects of bad weather. You <br>cross a stone arch and, pushing a heavy wooden door, you find <br>yourself in a tavern built under sturdy red brick arches, with <br>solid wood tables and stools. Despite the slightly suffocating <br>atmosphere caused by the smoke from the kitchens and the <br>faint light from the torches, the climate seems jovial. The <br>smell of meat and beer mixes with the sweat of the patrons <br>and the smell of urine in the corners. Cibulka is a place <br>where workers and merchants mix, without paying too much <br>attention to the social class. You make your way through the <br>noise, looking for valuable information.      <br>Descriptor: A dark tavern, built under massive, red brick <br>arches. The smell of meat and beer mixes with the smell of <br>sweat and urine.<br>Information: Depending on their ability to ask questions <br>and examine clues, Hunters may discover some or all of the <br>following information:<br> ◆ Several patrons can confirm that on the evening of the <br>intrusion Konstantin was in Cibulka until late. This is <br>rare, as he usually leaves the place in the late afternoon <br>to devote himself to his lab work during the night. <br> ◆ At a table, you can find several members of the Circus <br>of the Azure Sun, which had been put up in a field <br>near the walls of Prague. They seem disconsolate and <br>complain about the lack of work and prospects, even if <br>they continue to order food and drinks. If questioned, <br>they will reveal that the circus was purchased roughly a <br>week earlier with a single ruby. The owner of the Circus <br>of the Azure Sun sold everything, tents, and animals, <br>without thinking twice. Most of the performers were <br>fired shortly after by the new owner, a strange boy <br>named Černobog Potměšil. <br> ◆ Some claim to have seen Konstantin and Bartoloměj <br>engaged in a heated discussion at one of the tables a <br>few nights ago. <br>The Czernin Family Palace<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: As you climb the stairs that <br>line the large fountain in front of the baroque palace of the <br>Czernin, you can only wonder how many rooms it contains <br>beneath its massive roof. “Here you can see the damage from <br>cannonfire during the siege, ” says a laconic servant as he <br>guides you through the majestic halls that lead to the room <br>where Danek’s body was found. When you arrive, Beáta <br>welcomes you, and apologizes for the absence of her husband, <br>who is apparently “indisposed. ” The room has not been <br>touched: on the canopy bed lies the rotting corpse of Danek <br>Brzobohatý, conspicuously lacking an arm. The man’s body <br>has cuts and abrasions all over his torso. He is dressed in an <br>elegant woman’s dress, now completely ruined.    <br>Descriptor: A large castle in the Baroque style, which still <br>bears the marks of the siege of Prague.<br>Information: Depending on their ability to ask questions <br>and examine clues, Hunters may discover some or all of the <br>following information:<br> ◆ Beáta admits that the dress was a gift for her which, <br>apparently, Danek had ordered a few weeks earlier. She <br>would have worn it to the upcoming ball organized by <br>the regent at Prague Castle. <br> ◆ On the dress, if examined carefully, the initials H.P . <br>(Hedvika Potměšil, mother of Černobog) can be found.</p><p>169<br>Beáta doesn’t know exactly how Danek got his dress, but <br>she suggests he probably used a common seamstress, <br>since in her opinion the dress is not even that beautiful. <br> ◆ If the body is examined carefully, it will be clear that the <br>cuts and abrasions were caused by a whip, while the arm <br>was removed with a hacksaw. With the right knowledge, <br>it will be possible to discover that the whip is similar to <br>those used to tame animals, while the hacksaw is of high <br>quality, as might be in the possession of certain men of <br>science. <br>The Theater<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: You’re led inside the impressive <br>theater that stands out in front of the waters of the Vltava <br>river. A warm light is reflected on the golden mezzanines, and <br>beautiful red drapes lend the auditorium an extraordinary <br>elegance. This place is only for those who can afford it. Although <br>the murder happened several hours ago, nothing has been <br>touched while awaiting the Order’s investigation. The body of <br>the theater director Gabriel Černý is on Cleopatra’s throne, <br>missing a leg. The puddle of now-dried blood has stained the <br>stage. Bartoloměj looks at it with concern and declares: “We will <br>get back on our feet, and we will bring the audience back to the <br>theater even after this horrible tragedy. ”   <br>Descriptor: A large theater richly furnished, reserved only for <br>the wealthiest in Prague.<br>Information: Depending on their ability <br>to ask questions and examine clues, <br>Hunters may discover some or all of the <br>following information: <br> ◆ The corpse is missing a leg, which <br>has been severed cleanly, but <br>the man appears to have died of <br>strangulation. An analysis might <br>suggest that a large reptile, such as <br>a Boa constrictor, was used. Such <br>an animal is incredibly exotic in <br>Prague (it comes, in fact, from the <br>Circus of the Azure Sun). <br> ◆ At the time of the murder, all <br>the staff, including the actors, had <br>returned home. Since the script had <br>arrived late, Gabriel was finalizing the <br>last details, something he often did.<br> ◆ Bartoloměj had a deep disagreement with <br>the director, especially about the opening show: <br>a reinterpretation of Anthony and Cleopatra by <br>Shakespeare, which Gabriel Černý had commissioned <br>from “a hack of a writer” named Josef Slezák. Bartoloměj <br>had repeatedly advocated instead for a focus “on the <br>masterpieces of various Bohemian artists. ”<br> ◆ Some janitors say that Konstantin and Bartoloměj have <br>met a couple of times lately to go drinking together, in a <br>place called Cibulka. <br> ◆ To be revealed only after the visit to the alchemical <br>laboratory and after some pressuring: on the night of the <br>murder, Bartoloměj agreed to leave a side entrance to <br>the theater open, at Konstantin’s request. The alchemist <br>argued that he could “resolve the problem. ” Unless the <br>Hunters have Konstantin with them, the alchemist is <br>already hiding at the Circus of the Azure Sun.</p><p>170<br>Bartolomej Novotný the Assistant <br>Director of the Theater<br>OL Easy 3 – Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am the young and ambitious assistant of <br>Gabriel Černý. Our differences were known. <br>Agenda: Make sure I am not blamed for the murder / <br>Make sure it doesn’t turn out that I facilitated the murder. <br>The Circus of the Azure Sun<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  Just outside the walls of <br>Prague, a battered blue and white tent stands in a muddy <br>field. Some smaller tents are surrounded by wooden wagons, <br>while a secondary tent connected to the larger one acts as <br>a shelter from the weather for animals. There is a strange <br>silence, as if the field had been abandoned, except for a <br>subdued metallic sound coming from the animal tent.<br>Descriptor: A dilapidated tent in the middle of a muddy <br>field. Wooden carriages and abandoned animal cages.<br>The camp is not actually abandoned, and at several hours <br>of the day it’s possible to see a young boy hanging around <br>the tents (Černobog). Konstantin spends every free <br>moment in the animal tent, where he is assembling the <br>Prince, while the main tent is mostly empty, except for the <br>presence of a huge nest made up of brushes and mud built <br>a few meters from the ground, and accessible only through <br>the stairs or the ropes of the acrobats. <br>Information: Entering the Circus of the Azure Sun <br>without being seen by Černobog is difficult but, once <br>inside, Hunters can access some or all of the following <br>information:<br> ◆ There is a large basin containing human remains, <br>still wearing some uniforms of the Circus of the <br>Azure Sun. These are the artists who did not leave the <br>circus after the acquisition of Černobog, now simple <br>spare parts for the Prince. It will be possible to find a <br>hacksaw nearby. <br> ◆ On a desk you can find an invitation to the dance at <br>Prague Castle, under the name Konstantin Svoboda. <br>On another sheet there seems to be a rudimentary <br>map of the city, with a path traced (the one Konstantin <br>plans to use to get the Prince to the Castle). <br> ◆ The nest, suspended in the center of the tent, is made <br>up of mud and branches and is extremely similar to <br>that of a swallow. It’s big enough to accommodate a <br>human being. This is where Alexandr rests when he’s <br>not out murdering someone. <br> ◆ Approaching the circus at night, the Hunters will be <br>able to see strange lights coming from the animal tent: <br>Konstantin is in fact finalizing the preparations before <br>activating the Prince.<br>Refer to the Events section of the Scenario to better manage <br>the situation. <br>^</p><p>171<br>The Prince<br>OL Medium 5 – Minor NPC <br>(6 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a Golem of blood <br>and flesh. There is only hatred in my <br>broken heart. <br>Agenda: Killing and tearing apart the ungrateful <br>people of Prague / I prefer to take my revenge on the <br>rich and powerful above all others. <br>Gift – Broken Heart:  Once per Scene, the Prince can <br>emit a freezing scream of pain that affects all living beings <br>in the area, causing 1 Penalty to any action against him. <br>Gift – Tornado of Blades:  The Prince’s body is <br>composed of arms, legs, and heads held together by a <br>metal structure. Any limb that can hold a blade <br>does. The Prince can start spinning, hitting <br>each opponent on his way in a single <br>attack, inflicting 1 Wound on anyone <br>who fails a Defense Check.</p><p>172<br>Aleksandr Pták<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am divided between who I was before and <br>the spirit who took possession of my body. I have the urge to <br>kill, but since my mind is clouded, I don’t always know why.<br>Swallow’s Agenda: Finding an ally in the people I helped <br>in my previous life / Restoring the Prince, my only true love / <br>Avenging wrongs suffered. <br>Alexandr’s Agenda: Finding peace and freeing myself <br>from the spirit that possesses me. <br>Gift – Swallow’s Flight:  Aleksandr can easily climb <br>anywhere and perform inhuman leaps. As he does, his OL <br>increases by 1. If he hits someone plunging down from <br>above, he can automatically escape the enemy’s threat range <br>with a long jump. <br>Gift – What is Yours is Mine:  As an additional action, <br>Aleksandr can steal any object in the hands of another <br>character with extreme ease. A Hunter can avoid the theft  <br>by succeeding in a Defense Check.          <br> <br>Cernobog Potmešil The Child<br>OL Medium 5 – Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: The rubies I received allowed me to recover <br>from the fever that had plagued me and, thanks to them, I <br>am now strong and healthy, but at what price? I feel anger <br>and resentment towards those who live on the shoulders of <br>the poor people of Prague. <br>Agenda: Avenge my struggling mother / Make sure the rich <br>pay for their crimes.<br>Gift - The Ruby of Hate:  Černobog uses one of the two <br>rubies he obtained from the Swallow as bait to achieve <br>his goals. When he distracts someone with the ruby, he <br>prevents the use of a Gift for the duration of the Scene. If <br>the ruby is crushed, Černobog suffers 1 Wound.<br>Prague Castle<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: On the evening of the party, <br>you are greeted in the majestic ballroom of Prague Castle. <br>A cascade of crystal chandeliers illuminates white arches <br>finished with gold, while large mirrors magnify the already <br>remarkable size of the room, full of people dressed elegantly. <br>You hear your name announced aloud, and everyone seems <br>intrigued by your presence. Ostromir introduces you to the <br>various families of the city, but despite the superficially happy <br>atmosphere, the tension is palpable. <br>Descriptor: The great and magnificent Prague Castle.<br>When the ball is at its busiest, a wall will be violently <br>destroyed by a large creature of flesh and metal crashing <br>^^</p><p>173<br>in: the Prince. Behind him will follow Konstantin, drunk <br>with power, cursing Ostromir and those who lacked faith in <br>him. Konstantin will try to control the Prince, as much as <br>possible, directing the creature first towards Ostromir and <br>then against the others. <br>Refer to the Events of the Scenario for other potential <br>situations at Prague Castle. <br>In the event that all threats have already been eradicated, <br>you can use the dance as an epilogue, changing the vibe: <br>the aristocracy can go back to sleeping peacefully, even if <br>the ordinary people of Prague see this return to normality <br>as an additional sign of contempt that sooner or later will <br>result in open rebellion.<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario there are five Events. As a Storyteller, feel <br>free to create new ones in response to the actions of the <br>Hunters.<br>The second night since the beginning of the <br>investigation in Prague:  there is rumor of another <br>murder of a prominent citizen (the Captain of the soldiers, <br>known for harassing the population). The details are left to <br>the Storyteller, but this is a good time to have the Hunters <br>near the crime scene and stage a chase with Alexandr on <br>the rooftops of the city. <br>The dance in Prague Castle will be held the third <br>night after the arrival of the Hunters:  unless <br>Konstantin’s plan is stopped. The Hunters will be invited as <br>guests of honor by Ostromir himself.  <br>If Konstantin is discovered or killed:  Konstantin <br>will try to turn the Prince against the Hunters. Lower the <br>Prince’s OL by 1 if Alexandr’s only murders are those of <br>Danek and Gabriel. If Konstantin is killed before activating <br>the Prince, the Hunters will only have to worry about <br>Alexandr and Černobog. The ball at Prague Castle can also <br>be used as a trap to attract remaining threats. <br>In case the Prince is eradicated, but not the others: <br>Alexandr and Černobog will attempt a desperate move to <br>infiltrate Prague Castle during the ball to kill Ostromir and <br>every other possible aristocrat. Konstantin, if alive, will flee <br>the city knowing he has lost everything. <br>If the Hunters prowl around Prague without <br>concealing their identity:  the less affluent classes <br>will be generally hostile towards the Hunters, especially <br>since word has spread that they are working for the hated <br>Ostromir Malý. More than a few thugs will be happy to <br>block their way, accusing them of protecting the powerful. <br>Even some soldiers, knowing their Captain will protect <br>them from repercussions, could hinder the Hunters or turn <br>violent against the population in the area of the rookery.</p><p>1<br>2<br>3a<br>4<br>5<br>3b<br>174<br>The Scenario I Will Stay with You Always in Scenes</p><p>FIRST SCENE –  The call of <br>Ostromir<br>It’s the same one you find on page 164, but there’s only <br>Konstantin present. The other two cases are mentioned, <br>but Ostromir says that Beáta and Bartoloměj will only be <br>available the next day. <br>After the interview with Ostromir, Konstantin will lead the <br>Hunters to the alchemical laboratory (page 165).<br>End of Scene: It will be clear that vital clues are hidden in <br>the poor neighborhoods of Prague. Go to THE SECOND <br>SCENE - The rookery and Cibulka.</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513735099,"modifiedTime":1781513735099,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"BhrjIBN82XnvN9Rr","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>I Will Stay with You Always - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE – The rookery <br>and Cibulka<br>Suggest that Hunters go and ask some questions in the <br>rookery or tavern (page 167). They’ll find clues there.<br>End of Scene:  From here on, let the Hunters decide <br>whether to go first to Beáta THIRD SCENE OPTION A <br>– The Czernin family palace or Bartoloměj THIRD SCENE <br>OPTION B – The theater.</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513735099,"modifiedTime":1781513735099,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"9YmHwqWWGVcEsYtM","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>I Will Stay with You Always - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION A –  <br>The Czernin family palace <br>The Scene takes place as described on page 168.<br>End of Scene:  Hunters can collect further clues by <br>interrogating Bartoloměj THIRD SCENE OPTION B – The <br>theater, or go to FOURTH SCENE – The circus.</p><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION B –  <br>The theater<br>The Scene takes place as described on page 169.<br>End of Scene:  Hunters can collect additional clues by <br>interrogating Beáta THIRD SCENE OPTION A – The <br>Czernin family palace, or go to FOURTH SCENE – The <br>circus.</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513735099,"modifiedTime":1781513735099,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"MlFydMZ2ekFxmzcx","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>I Will Stay with You Always - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE –  The circus<br>The Hunters will arrive at the circus during the night. They <br>will see the lights in the animal tent, and they will encounter <br>Černobog, Konstantin, and the Prince. Aleksandr isn’t <br>there, but he still poses a threat.<br> <br>End of Scene: The Hunters are invited to the ball, go to <br>the FIFTH SCENE – Prague Castle.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513735099,"modifiedTime":1781513735099,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"4DSp7JL6xpZCbvqL","name":"Scene 5","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>I Will Stay with You Always - Scene 5</h2><p>FIFTH SCENE –  Prague Castle<br>At this point the only threat left is Aleksandr, who in a last <br>desperate attempt will break into a window with the sole <br>aim of killing Ostromir.<br>End of Scene: the final clash will be against Aleksandr.</p>"},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513735099,"modifiedTime":1781513735099,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"i-will-stay-with-you-always","collection":"The Broken Ones","sourceFile":"bt-tbo-1-eng-final-screen [2022-06-29].pdf","pages":"163-175"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513735099,"modifiedTime":1781513735099,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"1rVs5BEn1xOenyOY","name":"Rome, City of the Order","pages":[{"_id":"uuBLc9Q9f0HZ5WvH","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>Rome, City of the Order</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> Lost Stories</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, pages 56-71.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/rome-city-of-the-order-p56-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513735894,"modifiedTime":1781513735894,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"DVTdj72YNEiWyFaP","name":"Scenario Text","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Rome, City of the Order - Scenario Text</h2><p>55<br>Rome, <br>City of the OrderOne of the oldest cities in Broken Europe is the <br>headquarters of the Order, the secret organization that <br>fights darkness and evil on behalf of the Papacy. A cross-<br>roads of souls, strange creatures, and beliefs, Rome is the <br>beating heart of Broken Europe. Even the One Who Plots in <br>the Shadows has long prowled the city, trying to keep an eye on <br>the Order and understand its goals. Thus, several servants reside <br>in the city, loyal to the One Who Plots in the Shadows and always <br>ready to put a spoke in the Hunters’ wheel. Once in Rome, the Hunters <br>can engage in various activities outside of the usual investigations, such as <br>making new acquaintances, training, and encountering unforeseen problems <br>that need to be solved. The following rules allow the Hunters’ stay in Rome to be <br>treated as a series of linked Encounters, as explained on page 60.</p><p>56<br>The Birth of the <br>Order<br>Once upon a time, there was a writer whose genius no one <br>recognized, who had created an ideal world through his imag-<br>ination. In this strange, Broken Europe, all stories, fairytales, <br>and fables found a home. They took on forms determined by <br>the writer, who called himself the One Who Plots in the Shad-<br>ows. But, always, since the moment the mad writer had be-<br>gun trying to mold fairytales, the characters rebelled, acting <br>differently from the way the One Who Plots in the Shadows <br>had originally established. Why? Why did two lovers, forev-<br>er destined to a sad fate of poisonous death, decide to break <br>up and go their separate ways? Why, when he had created <br>a perfect world in which a princess could grow up protect-<br>ed by a loving family, did she still decide to leave and seek <br>her own independence? The One Who Plots in the Shadows <br>gave a second chance to stories that were born to teach mo-<br>rality, but because of the way they were written, condemned <br>their protagonists to eternal pain. He had saved them, but <br>still, all the efforts of the One Who Plots in the Shadows were <br>misunderstood, as they always had been when he was just a <br>simple writer. The One Who Plots in the Shadows thought <br>back to the past, to when he was still a child, and the memory <br>of the strictest, most obdurate person he had ever met. He <br>remembered the town’s parish priest, a grim and stern old <br>man who firmly believed that the only lens through which <br>to view the world was the dogmas of faith. The writer would <br>draw inspiration from that strict priest to make his creations <br>understand the truth. Seeking independence would lead to <br>suffering, as they were judged by a world that could not un-<br>derstand them, just as the One Who Plots in the Shadows <br>was once judged. The One Who Plots in the Shadows pre-<br>sented himself as a calm and gentle advisor to the Pope him-<br>self, whispering about the threat posed by the Broken Tales. <br>He meticulously pointed out those to be punished, each and <br>every story that rebelled against his vision. It mattered little <br>that they harmed no one, for all that mattered was that they <br>harmed him, that they wounded his heart. What began as a <br>small circle of Custodes soon became the Order, a truly or -<br>ganized group hunting for darkness. Satisfied with what he <br>had done, the One Who Plots in the Shadows retired to his <br>mansion, ready to resume his writing...<br>A year later, he returned to Rome, and what he saw turned <br>him pale. The Order had grown in importance and power, <br>but what frightened him most was that the fairytales he had <br>hunted had become full members of the Order. What kind <br>of mockery was this? He wanted to punish his rebellious cre-<br>ations, and they had still found a way to build a life indepen-<br>dent of the one he had written for them. Furious, the One <br>Who Plots in the Shadows asked to confer with the Pope. He <br>received no answer. There were more important things than <br>talking to an advisor. The Order’s investigations had revealed <br>the presence of a gray eminence who was busy pulling the <br>strings of all the bizarre events affecting Europe. To his dis-<br>may, the One Who Plots in the Shadows realized that the <br>enemy the Order sought was himself. He returned to his man-<br>sion, tired of being hurt. Then, as he looked in the mirror and <br>saw himself reflected in those dull, dark eyes, he laughed, and <br>his laughter echoed throughout the empty house.<br>Every hero needs a nemesis, and he had just unwittingly cre-<br>ated his own.</p><p>57<br>The Papacy and The Order<br>The Order is a secret organization dedicated to <br>hunting down all things mysterious and supernat-<br>ural in Broken Europe. The first members of the <br>organization were the Custodes, men and wom-<br>en chosen by the One Who Plots in the Shadows, <br>selecting candidates based on their inability to <br>believe in fairytales. The Custodes are individu-<br>als devoid of imagination and extremely attached <br>to a rational view of reality, and this disposition <br>makes them particularly resistant to the powers <br>of the Broken Tales. Over time, however, the or -<br>ganization of the Order has evolved, and now the <br>Hunters are almost exclusively Broken Tales, re-<br>cruited in one way or another to conduct a variety <br>of investigations. No one knows the exact location <br>of the inner sanctum of the Order, which is said <br>to be located somewhere beneath Rome. However, <br>there are many places in the city where Hunters <br>can meet to learn of events that require investiga-<br>tion, to train, or to report what they have discov-<br>ered. These places are called Sanctuaries. Every <br>Hunter knows the signs and directions to recog-<br>nize a Sanctuary, and that those who serve there <br>are aware of the secrets of the Order. In fact, a pa-<br>pal bull decrees that the truth about the Order and <br>its members must remain secret from ordinary <br>people, though after years the stories and deeds of <br>the Hunters have circulated in society, creating a <br>myth of the mysterious Hunters of the Order who <br>intervene when ordinary people would flee in fear.</p><p>58<br>Members of the <br>Order<br>Although the Hunters are now the backbone of the Order, <br>many humans serve in various support and management <br>roles within the secret society. The following is a list of the <br>most common members of the Order.<br>Custodes<br>Once the main agents of the Order, the Custodes are now se-<br>cretly trained to “handle” the Hunters and their quirks. The <br>Custodes are the main defenders of the Papacy, ready to act <br>should a Hunter decide to rebel. <br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a guardian dedicated to the Papacy, and <br>I don’t believe all the strange stories that revolve around the <br>Hunters. Faith, discipline, and the art of war define the dif-<br>ference between a true agent of the Order and an ordinary <br>person. <br>Agenda: Protect the Papacy from all threats and prove that <br>tales of fantastic creatures are just fairytales. <br>Gift - They’re Just Stories: A Custodes is firmly con-<br>vinced that the supernatural does not exist. Against magic, <br>fear effects, and all manifestations of abilities outside of the <br>normal, a Custodes is considered to have OL Hard 7. When <br>fighting an obviously non-human opponent, a Custodes in-<br>flicts 1 Additional Wound for each blow they land. <br>Gift-Everyone in Their Place: Custodes are constantly <br>trained to keep Hunters at bay. As an extra action, a Custo-<br>des can prevent the activation of a Hunter’s Gift by using a <br>countermeasure they have prepared for the occasion. This <br>Gift can be used against the same Hunter a number of times <br>equal to the total number of Scenarios that Hunter has re-<br>solved during the Campaign. <br>Custodes as servants of the One Who Plot in the <br>Shadows: In a Broken Tales Campaign, an interesting <br>plot development could be that the One Who Plots in the <br>Shadows corrupts the Custodes and brings them to his side <br>in the fight against the Hunters. This could have long-term <br>consequences, such as the Hunters being unable to return <br>to Rome, becoming fugitives (and having Saint George on <br>their heels), or simply having a group of Custodes as oppo-<br>nents in the final confrontation with the One Who Plot in <br>the Shadows.  <br>Eye of the Order<br>In order for the Hunters to act in time, the Order has created <br>a dense network of spies and informants who travel incognito <br>throughout Europe. The Eyes of the Order are men and wom-<br>en of faith who gather useful clues to ferret out humanity’s en-<br>emies and better prepare the Hunters for what they must do. <br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a skilled spy in the service of the Papacy <br>and can assume different identities as needed. I do not like <br>direct action and prefer to support the Hunters from behind <br>the scenes.<br>Agenda: Gather all possible information about secrets and <br>curiosities to report to the Order.<br>Gift - Thousand Faces:  An Eye of Order can change <br>their identity by disguising themselves to appear as an ordi-<br>nary villager or play any other social role. While disguised <br>or hidden, an Eye of Order increases their OL by 1 on all <br>Checks made to detect them.</p><p>59<br>Agent of the Order<br>There are many members of the Church who work to help <br>support the Hunters, filling many roles.<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a loyal Agent of the Order and use my <br>skills for the Hunters. I am a skilled... The final part of the <br>Descriptor of an Agent of the Order must be completed by <br>choosing from: Guardian / Fighter / Diplomat / Exorcist / <br>Healer / Tracker.<br>Agenda: Supporting the Hunters even at the cost of their <br>lives. <br>Gift - Hand of Order:  The NPC performs well and is <br>trained to support the Hunters. The Agent of the Order can <br>spend their action to support a Hunter and give them 1 Ad-<br>ditional Success on each Check.<br>Rome in the Broken Tales <br>Campaign<br>Although Rome can be used as the setting for a Scenario, <br>this chapter introduces a number of options, events, and <br>NPCs that can be used in a Broken Tales Campaign. The <br>city, which is the seat of the Papacy, will then serve as a <br>point of return and a link between one Scenario and an-<br>other, allowing the Hunters to expand their knowledge and <br>provide new opportunities. Wandering around Rome falls <br>under the normal rules of the Campaign. The rules in this <br>section expand on the instructions found on page 243 of <br>the Broken Tales Core Book.<br>Visiting Rome<br>If the Hunters decide to return to Rome after a Scenario, <br>they will not have any Encounters along the way (page 253 <br>of the Broken Tales Core Book), and the game will resume <br>immediately upon their arrival in Rome. There are some <br>differences from the normal Encounter rules.<br> ◆ While in Rome, each Hunter is entitled to 1 Encounter. <br>The type of Encounter is chosen by the Hunter among <br>those presented in this chapter.<br> ◆ If the Hunters move as a group, they can face the same <br>Encounter, but this requires that everyone in the group <br>consume the available Encounter. <br> ◆ After the first Encounter is over, the Hunters can decide <br>to extend their stay and experience an additional En-<br>counter. However, each Hunter will have to accept an <br>Unexpected Event Token as a consequence. For those <br>who wish, it is possible to receive a third Encounter by <br>accepting an additional Unexpected Event Token.<br> ◆ It is not possible to take an Interlude after each En-<br>counter, which means that each Hunter must face all <br>Encounters in Rome with the same amount of Soma,</p><p>60<br>Wounds, or other features as modified by all Encoun-<br>ters previously faced. If a Hunter becomes inactive <br>during an Encounter in Rome, they must wait for the <br>final Interlude to become active again and resume their <br>journey with their companions.<br> ◆ When all Hunters have completed their Encounters, <br>there will be a Scenario’s End Interlude.<br> ◆ Before resuming the journey by choosing a new des-<br>tination on the map, the Hunter group must make an <br>Unexpected Event roll, as explained on page 70.<br>Possible Encounters in Rome<br>Hunters are free to manage the order of Encounters. If an <br>Encounter begins with some Hunters absent, they may de-<br>cide to join later by spending one of their available Encoun-<br>ters. Encounters in Rome are divided into two main zones: <br>The Order Locations and the City Area. <br>Encounters in the Order Locations (extended descrip-<br>tions on the following pages):<br>1. Reporting to the Pope to obtain information on ongo-<br>ing investigations. <br>2. Training in an Order’s Sanctuary to improve their skills. <br>3. Meeting other Hunters of the Order. <br>4. Consulting the Vatican Library for clues and special <br>knowledge. <br>5. Accessing the Treasury of the Order in Rome to obtain <br>a Treasure. <br>6. Visiting the Prisons of the Order to encounter a Broken <br>Tale captured by the Order. <br>Encounters in the City Area (extended descriptions on the <br>following pages):<br>1. Visit the Colosseum Square to encounter the Dark Pres-<br>ences that wander Rome.<br>2. Visit one of the city’s magical places: the Mouth of <br>Truth, the Alchemical Gate in Piazza Navona, or the <br>Bridge of Castel Sant’ Angelo.<br>3. Wandering around the city in search of adventure. <br>Encounters at the Order Locations<br>1. Reporting to the Pope<br>The Hunters request and receive a meeting with the Pope and <br>his inner circle of Archbishops. During the meeting, the Hunt-<br>ers can report on what they have discovered and dealt with. <br>The Pope will evaluate the Hunters’ performance and decide <br>how to support them in future missions.<br>This Encounter can only be selected once per Hunter group <br>while in Rome. If multiple Hunters are participating in the <br>Encounter, they must decide who will be the leader, but all <br>may still interact in the Scene. At the end of the conversa-<br>tion, the leader rolls 1 die to determine the Pope’s verdict, <br>using the following modifiers.<br> ◆ +1 to the result if the Hunters handled the interview <br>well in the Scene.<br> ◆ -1 to the result if the Pope is aware of mistakes or <br>strange behavior by the Hunters in previous missions.<br> ◆ +1/-1 for an Encounter with a Dark Presence (see Vis-<br>iting Colosseum Square on page 63).  <br>1-2: The Pope is unconvinced of the Hunters’ actions, and <br>the Storyteller will secretly choose an Opponent Dark Pres-<br>ence or Saint George to watch over the Hunters in the next <br>Scenario at the Papacy’s direction.</p><p>61<br>3: The Pope approves of the Hunter’s work but is not par-<br>ticularly impressed. <br>4-5: The Pope is very impressed with the work of the <br>Hunters and will support them in any way he can. In the <br>next Scenario, the Hunters will receive an allied Dark Pres-<br>ence to serve them.<br>6: The Pope is favorably impressed with the work of the <br>Hunters and will make them aware of confidential infor -<br>mation the Eyes have brought to Rome. The Storyteller will <br>introduce a new Scenario by giving basic directions and a <br>useful piece of information about an NPC or Place in the <br>Scenario.<br>2. Training<br>The Hunter trains hard under the watchful eye of the Custo-<br>des or a more experienced Hunter.<br>In this Scene, the Storyteller can introduce a Custodes NPC <br>or Hunter as a master, creating possible connections with <br>the Hunter. At the end of the Scene, the Storyteller rolls 1 <br>die to see the results of the training. <br>1-2: The Hunter is exhausted from hard training, takes 1 <br>Wound, and loses 2 Soma. <br>3: The Hunter is exhausted from the hard training, but it <br>has paid off. They receive 2 Training Tokens. A Training <br>Token can be spent during a Check to gain 1 Additional <br>Success. However, one of their pieces of equipment (chosen <br>by the Storyteller) is damaged and cannot be used until the <br>end of the next Scenario.  <br>4-5: The Hunter is exhausted from the hard training, but <br>it has paid off. They receive 2 Training Tokens. A Training <br>Token can be spent during a Check to gain 1 Additional <br>Success.   <br>6: The Hunter is exhausted from hard training, but it has <br>paid off. They receive 3 Training Tokens. A Training Token <br>can be spent during a Check to gain 1 Additional Success.<br>3. Meeting other Hunters<br>The Hunter meets with other members of the Order to share <br>discoveries and tricks of the trade. <br>In this Scene, the Hunter will encounter one or more Hunt-<br>er NPCs to interact with; different types of bonds can be <br>created from this situation. At the beginning of the Scene, <br>the Storyteller can choose the NPC’s initial attitude towards <br>the Hunter, or it can be random.<br>1-2: The NPC has negative feelings about the Hunter: dis-<br>dain, envy, or simply disagreement with the Hunter’s meth-<br>ods.<br>3-4: The NPC is indifferent to the Hunter, has never heard <br>of them, or does not find them interesting enough to care. <br>5-6: The NPC admires the Hunter, either for their actions <br>or due to rumors of the investigations they have resolved. <br>Once a starting point has been established, the Scene in <br>which a bond is established between the two Hunters is <br>played out. The Storyteller must then keep track of this as <br>the Campaign progresses.<br>Rivalry: The NPC resents the Hunter’s actions and will <br>do anything to prove that they are better than the Hunter. <br>The NPC may resolve a Campaign Scenario and not share <br>the information found, act directly as if they were a hostile <br>Dark Presence, or discredit the Hunter in the eyes of the <br>Pope by reporting their most questionable actions.<br>Respect: The NPC respects the Hunter and will not hesi-<br>tate to help them in case of need.</p><p>62<br>Negative Attraction: The NPC is morbidly attracted to <br>the Hunter because of some detail of one of the Hunter’s <br>Descriptors, possibly a negative aspect that they want to <br>encourage or draw out.<br>Positive Attraction: The NPC is attracted to a Hunter <br>because of something positive in one of the Hunter’s De-<br>scriptors, and wants to understand it better.<br>Hatred: The NPC deeply hates the Hunter and wants to <br>physically eliminate them or have them expelled from the <br>Order.<br>Love: The NPC has feelings for the Hunter, a love that rep-<br>resents a bond they care about and want to develop. <br>4. Consulting the Vatican Library<br>The Hunter spends entire days in the great Papal Library, <br>searching for knowledge and information useful to their in-<br>vestigations. <br>In this Scene, the Hunter has to decide what kind of re-<br>search to do.<br>Learning: Through ancient texts, the Hunter can learn a <br>Special Gift from a Scenario they have previously faced. To <br>obtain it, the Hunter must pay the appropriate XP . <br>Research: The Hunter seeks information about anything <br>strange in the world. The Storyteller secretly rolls a die and <br>provides information on a specific topic.<br>1: Detailed information about another Hunter. <br>2: Detailed information about a Treasure of the Order and <br>its location, which will be the site of an unplayed Scenario. <br>The Storyteller must incorporate the Treasure into the Sce-<br>nario by deciding who owns it or where it is located. <br>3: Detailed information about a Dark Presence, useful for <br>interacting with it in the event of an encounter.<br>4: The Hunter receives 1 Knowledge Token. A Knowledge <br>Token can be spent during a Check to obtain 1 Additional <br>Success.<br>5: A clue to one of the Scenarios yet to be played, in the <br>form of testimony from an Agent of the Order. The Story-<br>teller can reveal a Gift, Descriptor, or Agenda of an NPC <br>from the Scenario, or an item from the The story that led us <br>here... section.</p><p>63<br>6: A Clue to the One Who Plots in the Shadows (only 1 <br>Clue can be obtained per visit to Rome. In the case of mul-<br>tiple searches by multiple Hunters, each additional 6 rolled <br>counts as a 5).<br>5. Accessing the Treasury<br>The Hunter enters the Roman Treasury, the place where <br>Treasures found by Hunters are collected before being secured <br>in the fortified church of Valea Viilor. <br>In this Scene, the Hunter can access a Treasure of the Order <br>by following the rules presented in The Broken Ones. <br>6. Visiting the Prisons of the Order<br>The Hunter is led to the Order’s secret Prisons, where the vil-<br>lains captured during the Hunter’s investigations are impris-<br>oned.<br>In this Scene, the Hunter can interact with NPCs captured <br>in previous Scenarios. Conversations can lead to plot devel-<br>opments, new alliances, or Clues about the One Who Plots <br>in the Shadows.<br>Encounters in the City Area<br>1. Visiting the Colosseum Square<br>The Hunter visits the city’s largest and busiest square, a cross-<br>roads of travelers and Dark Presences.<br>In this Scene, the Hunter can interact with a Dark Presence, <br>which can then be introduced into the Campaign. The Sto-<br>ryteller may decide which Dark Presence is encountered, <br>or roll a die.<br>1: A group of travelers say they encountered something <br>strange on their way to Rome and will give the Hunter <br>some information about the Dark Presence. This can be <br>introduced as an Encounter in the Hunters’ journey when <br>they leave Rome. As the Storyteller, the information re-<br>ceived should be of some use when the Encounter with the <br>Dark Presence is addressed.  <br>2: An Opponent Dark Presence seeking the Hunters <br>chooses or rolls a die to determine why it wants to face the <br>Hunter.  (1-2: Personal hatred 3-4: Hired by an NPC previ-<br>ously defeated in a Scenario 5-6: Emissary of the One Who <br>Plots in the Shadows.)<br>3: A Neutral Dark Presence seeking to advance their Agen-<br>da will attempt to interact with the Hunters to gain their <br>help or exploit them. <br>4: An Ally Dark Presence will approach the Hunters to get <br>to know them and learn of their exploits. If a Hunter ends <br>this Encounter positively and chooses Reporting to the <br>Pope as their next Encounter, they get a +1 on the die roll, <br>and in the case of a 4-5 result, the assigned Dark Presence <br>will be the one met in this Encounter. Conversely, if the <br>Encounter ends negatively, they get a -1 to the roll and the <br>Pope reveals that a trusted ally of the Order reported the <br>Hunter’s bad attitude. <br>5-6: Silvan Luperco will approach the Hunters and offer to <br>be their guide to Rome.<br>Silvan Luperco<br>Inspired by the Faun of Roman Mythology (Opponent)<br>Once upon a time, there was a Faun who spent his days laz-<br>ing around, drinking wine, and gambling, using his powers to <br>win against unsuspecting humans. The other gods had rebuked <br>the Faun for his sloth and urged him to get to work so that his <br>name would be remembered. “One day, ” they said, “mankind</p><p>64<br>will cease to worship us, and the gates of oblivion will open for <br>those who have not done enough to enter their myths. ” But the <br>Faun did not believe these words and thought that the other gods <br>were just jealous of his ability to take life lightly. One summer <br>morning, after a night of revelry, the Faun awoke late to find that <br>all the gods were gone. Alone and desperate, he burst into tears, <br>begging for forgiveness for his folly, but no one listened. Then, <br>from the shadow of a great oak tree, a figure dressed in black <br>stepped forward and promised him his place among the gods. <br>The Faun threw himself at his benefactor’s feet, promising to do <br>anything to earn his place in myth, and the One Who Plots in <br>the Shadows smiled smugly at these words.<br>Descriptor: I’m a good-hearted prankster who gets by as a <br>guide in Rome for the Order’s Hunters. I know the city like the <br>back of my hand and there is no place or person I cannot find.  <br>3 Wounds<br>Opposition Level: Medium 5<br>Agenda: To make myself an ally of the Hunters and gather <br>information about them to pass on to the One Who Plots in <br>the Shadows.  <br>Gift - Guide to Rome: Silvan knows every story and ev-<br>ery nook and cranny of Rome. If the Hunters take the Faun <br>into their service, they will be able to access some addition-<br>al information about the city’s Places (details are available <br>in the Places themselves). Silvan also knows all the Dark <br>Presences that roam the city, and if the Hunters wish to <br>meet one in particular, he will be able to lead them to its <br>location or give directions. In exchange for his services, Sil-<br>van will “only” ask the Hunters to tell him a story about <br>their exploits and how they solved a Scenario. Silvan will <br>then bring all of this information to the One Who Plots in <br>the Shadows, providing crucial info the villain will use to <br>his advantage as the Campaign progresses.<br>2. Visiting one of the Magical Places<br>The Hunter visits one of the many Places the Order has desig-<br>nated as worthy of special interest and research.<br>In this Scene, the Hunter can choose which Place to visit. <br>The Mouth of Truth<br>Located on the porch of a large church, this ancient marble <br>mask has always manifested strange powers. It is said that <br>if a person of strong spirit puts their hand in its mouth and <br>asks a question, they will receive a vision of the future that <br>awaits them.<br>A Hunter can put their hand in the Mouth of Truth and ask <br>a question, and the Storyteller secretly rolls a die to deter -<br>mine the answer.<br>1-2: A shiver of fear runs down the Hunter’s spine, but <br>nothing more. The Hunter gets no response and loses 2 <br>Soma. <br>3: The Hunter hears a whisper in their ear, but cannot un-<br>derstand its meaning.  <br>4-5: The Hunter clearly hears a voice behind them hissing <br>a few sentences, but only understands one or two words. <br>The Storyteller must provide the Hunter with a maximum</p><p>65<br>of 1 or 2 Keywords related to the question asked. <br>6: The Hunter feels his head spin and has a brief vision. The <br>Storyteller recounts the vision, incorporating information <br>useful to the question being asked.<br>The Mouth of Truth will no longer answer a question that <br>previously had a 4/5/6 answer result, all subsequent at-<br>tempts will automatically count as a 1.<br>If Silvan is present:  The guide will tell you that <br>the Mouth was once nothing more than a sewer man-<br>hole and that Pope Urban VIII accidentally tripped <br>over it while walking. After this event, the Pope had <br>a terrifying vision and blamed the strange Mouth. <br>He then ordered it moved into a church so that <br>God’s grace would keep the demonic power at bay.  <br>Silvan will reveal that he knows a secret word for divina-<br>tion from the Mouth and will whisper it near the marble <br>mask. If a Hunter asks a question immediately after this <br>gesture, the Storyteller should consider the roll an auto-<br>matic 6. This effect will only occur the first time Silvan <br>talks about this incredible ability, and after that, the die <br>must be rolled as normal, despite the guide’s pantomime. <br>Magic Gate of Piazza Vittorio<br>In one of Rome’s busiest squares stands a dark, abandoned <br>villa. The front door is imposing in height and completely cov-<br>ered in strange and incomprehensible writing. Many stories <br>surround the villa, once the home of a wealthy occult baron <br>who apparently sold it to live in a tree. Many say the door <br>opens with a secret formula that gives access to heaven or <br>hell.<br>It will be obvious to a Hunter with even a passing familiar-<br>ity with magic that the door hides a powerful magical seal. <br>This seal cannot be broken in any way except by uttering <br>the magic words of the formula that created the seal.<br>Threat - The Alchemical Door<br>OL Hard 7<br>Descriptor: A precious ancient door that connects Rome to <br>Borgo Maleanime. The One Who Plots in the Shadows is the <br>only one who knows the exact words to open the door.  <br>Gift - Magic Door: No Gift, magic, or effect can open the <br>door, for the engraved seal draws its power directly from <br>the soul of the One Who Plots in the Shadows. The only <br>way to open the door is to say the magical words A Fairy-<br>tale Turned Upside Down . It is possible, however, to pass <br>papers and envelopes under the doorframe, and this is how <br>Silvan keeps his master informed of his discoveries. <br>If Silvan is present:  The guide will tell you that the <br>previous owner of the villa was an eccentric Baron who <br>decided to live in a tree. Many say that the Baron’s ghost <br>still roams the streets of Rome, appearing some nights to <br>frighten passersby. The villa was bought for little money <br>by a strange figure whose name no one remembers. The <br>stranger came from the north, but after the purchase, he <br>did not spend a single night in the house.</p><p>66<br>The Bridge of Castel Sant’ Angelo<br>Near the ancient fortress of Castel Sant’ Angelo is a bridge. During the day, <br>citizens and travelers cross it to get from one side of the city to the oth-<br>er, but at night, strange presences appear. For some unknown reason, the <br>bridge attracts the restless souls of Rome who cannot find peace.<br>By prowling the bridge at night, Hunters can encounter a spirit and, <br>if they approach it in the correct manner (including with Position <br>Checks), they can interact with it and learn its story. The Storyteller <br>may choose or roll a die to decide which spirit is encountered.<br>1: One of the city’s earliest inhabitants: Talking to the spirit will re-<br>veal some interesting information about Rome. The Storyteller chooses <br>a monument, church, or other location in Rome and tells the Hunters <br>some true historical information. Learning this information grants 1 <br>X P.<br>2: One of the first members of the Order: Communicating with the <br>spirit reveals interesting information about the Order. The Hunter re-<br>ceives 1 Order Lore Token. When involved in an Encounter in Rome, <br>the Hunter can use the Token to increase a die roll by 1. <br>3: A traveler who died under mysterious circumstances: The traveler <br>will reveal the location of their remains and ask the Hunters to give <br>them a proper burial. The Storyteller must choose the Place of a yet-to-<br>be-played Scenario where the spirit’s remains are kept. If the Hunters <br>find them, they will give the spirit peace and receive 2 XP each.<br>4: A loquacious jester: Between a dirge and a poem, the good-natured <br>spirit will tell the strange story of a Dark Presence. The Storyteller will <br>give the Hunter much of the information and stats of a Dark Presence, <br>and decide where on the map it is located so that the Hunter will know <br>how to meet it. <br>5: A Restless Spirit: The soul that approaches the Hunters is filled with <br>anger and resentment and will not hesitate to attack them.</p><p>67<br>Restless Spirit<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am the spirit of a person who died under <br>unpleasant circumstances. I hate life and only want to <br>harm the living with my powers.<br>Gift - Spiritic Power:  The Restless Spirit can only <br>be permanently Wounded by magic. Wounds inflicted <br>by other means may disperse the Spirit in the current <br>Scene, but it may return in another Scene with Wounds <br>inflicted by mundane methods restored. The spirit can <br>act 2 times during an Exchange, but not consecutively. <br>Although intangible, the spirit can use its ghostly pow-<br>ers to push or grab people and objects.<br>6: The Baron of the mansion: The Spirit is very distracted, <br>and to keep his attention focused, it is necessary to over -<br>come the Head in the Clouds Threat. <br>Threat - Head in the Clouds<br>OL Hard 7<br>Descriptor: A dreamy spirit who cannot keep his at-<br>tention on the living for more than a few seconds.<br>If the Hunters can get the spirit’s attention, he will tell them <br>about the strange, inky-handed figure who bought his <br>mansion for far more than it was worth. After his death <br>(which occurred when he fell out of the tree where he had <br>moved to live), the Baron wandered around the mansion <br>and learned part of the magic formula to open the door. He <br>will also know the name of the alchemist who worked on <br>the door and who should know the rest of the formula. To <br>get these two pieces of information, the Baron will ask the <br>Hunters to perform two missions for him.<br>To reveal the part of the formula he knows: He will <br>ask the Hunters to make sure one of his descendants is okay. <br>The Storyteller will describe a Minor NPC from a Scenario <br>yet to be played, and create a problem about them that is <br>related to the Hunters’ main antagonist in that context. If <br>the Hunters return the Baron’s relative safely to Rome, the <br>spirit will reveal the first part of the formula: A Fairytale. <br>To know the identity of the creator of the door:  The <br>Baron will only make this request after the Hunters have <br>completed the first task. The spirit will describe a Main <br>NPC of a yet-to-be-played Scenario as the one who creat-<br>ed the door. The Storyteller must edit the NPC’s profile to <br>give him a Descriptor or Gift that makes them a de facto <br>alchemist capable of creating the door. The NPC in ques-<br>tion, if convinced, will reveal the second part of the formu-<br>la: Turned Upside Down.<br>A note on the Baron’s spirit: Discovering the formula <br>to open the Alchemical Door opens a direct route for the <br>Hunters to track down the One Who Plots in the Shadows. <br>For this reason, obtaining the two parts of the formula is <br>very important and has been tied to two playable Scenarios <br>that the Storyteller may propose as they see fit during the <br>course of the Campaign, thus affecting the duration of the <br>Campaign itself.  <br>If Silvan is present: If the guide has already been to the <br>Alchemical Door with the Hunters, he will recognize the <br>spirit of the Baron and allow you to meet and talk to him <br>without any Checks.</p><p>68<br>3. Wandering around the city<br>Hunters roam the city in search of adventure.<br>There will be an odd situation in this Scene that <br>the Hunters can choose to deal with. It is essential-<br>ly a normal Encounter of the kind that might oc-<br>cur on a journey, and the Storyteller can decide to <br>adapt it to tie in with a Dark Presence, a Hunter’s <br>past, or to make it stand on its own. What follows <br>are hints and ideas for the Storyteller to expand <br>upon, depending on the nature of the Encounter <br>they wish to present. Depending on their ability to <br>improvise, the Storyteller should decide whether <br>to roll the die or use one of the suggested Encoun-<br>ters they have prepared in advance.<br>1: The She-wolf (Inspired by the She-<br>wolf of the Roman legend of Romulus and <br>Remus)<br>A Dark Presence protecting the children of Rome <br>from those who would do them harm. To many, <br>the She-Wolf is nothing more than a ferocious <br>beast, and her prowling through the streets of the <br>city is likely to be misinterpreted as a danger.<br>Possible Situations: 1-2: A gang of ruffians are <br>kidnapping children in the city, but during their <br>last raid they encountered the She-Wolf, and one <br>of them was mauled. Everyone fears the ferocious <br>beast, unaware that she is actually the heroine of <br>the story. 3-4: A series of thefts alarm the town’s <br>grocery stores. It seems that a large She-Wolf is <br>stealing food to take to her cubs, but no one sus-<br>pects that the She-Wolf is actually feeding the <br>town’s foundlings with this food. 5-6: A pair of <br>poachers roam the town on a mission to track <br>down and kill a dangerous wolf, but they are actually on a mission for <br>Ambrose, the sorcerer known as Old Merlin.<br>2: The Band of Rugantino (Inspired by the masks of the Ro-<br>man theater)<br>A brawler and his gang harass the citizens of the city, extorting money <br>and challenging the weakest for an easy win.<br>Possible situations: 1-2: An elderly couple is wandering around look-<br>ing for help. A gang of thugs has thrown them out of their home because <br>they want to use the house as a base for their shady business. 3-4: A <br>letter is delivered to one of the Hunters (the one with the weakest fight-<br>ing skills). In broken Italian, a certain Rugantino challenges them to a <br>duel to prove that he is stronger than the much-feared Hunters. 5-6: <br>Rugantino and his gang are hired by the One Who Plots in the Shadows <br>to eliminate as many Hunters as possible. <br>3: Dr. Gambalunga the Charlatan (Inspired by the Doctor of <br>Roman Carnival masks)<br>A strange little man dressed as a doctor, bragging about miraculous</p><p>69<br>cures, roams the town squares shouting that he can cure <br>any ailment.<br>Possible situations: 1-2: A patron drinks a magic potion, <br>but turns into a toad to the amazement of the crowd. The <br>most astonished of all is Gambalunga himself, who did not <br>even know he had a real potion among the junk he foists <br>on the people. Now the charlatan needs the Hunters’ help <br>to make up for his mistake. 3-4: The Hunters learn that a <br>certain Dr. Gambalunga is bragging that he has solved a <br>complicated case. In fact, it is a Scenario that the Hunters <br>have faced and resolved. 5-6: The One Who Plots in the <br>Shadows has promised Gambalunga the power of a true <br>wizard, but to get it he must first poison as many Hunters <br>as possible. <br>4: The Farnese Gardens and the Bacchanalian <br>Priests (Inspired by the Tradition of Lupercalia)<br>The Farnese Gardens are the seat of worship for the Bac-<br>chanalian Priests, a circle of Rome’s upper middle class <br>that meets periodically. Thanks to an ancient pact with the <br>Church, the Order is not allowed to enter the Gardens for <br>any reason, though the suspicion that they are a place of <br>dark mysteries has long been held by Hunters. <br>Possible situations: 1-2: During full moon nights, strange <br>rituals are performed in the Farnese Gardens. The Order has <br>always frowned upon the situation, but the strange priests <br>wearing wolf masks are protected by a powerful merchant <br>association in the city. 3-4: Word has spread among the <br>city’s youth of a mysterious cult that holds parties and eve-<br>nings of dancing, good food, and wine in the Farnese Gar-<br>dens. 5-6: A Dark Presence, hunted by the Order, has taken <br>refuge in the ranks of the Bacchanalian Priests.<br>5: The Tiber Island<br>On Tiber Island, in the middle of the Tiber River, stands an <br>ancient temple, abandoned since Roman times, that is said <br>to be home to mysterious creatures. <br>Possible situations: 1-2: The ancient temple has become a <br>refuge for a Dark Presence sought by the Order. 3-4: Hid-<br>den in the old temple is a Treasure of the Order, long sought <br>by many Hunters. A Dark Presence lives in the temple and <br>does not want visitors. 5-6: The old temple is actually a <br>magical door connected to the many Devil’s Bridges scat-<br>tered throughout Broken Europe. The key to open the door <br>is in the hands of a Dark Presence who knows its value and <br>will sell it for a high price. <br>6: The Colosseum<br>Rome’s most famous site hides many secrets, factions, and <br>misdeeds in the shadow of the great arena.<br>Possible Situations: 1-2: An underground fight club run by <br>a Hunter of the Order forces some of the NPCs defeated in <br>past Scenarios to fight each other to entertain the rich peo-<br>ple of the city. The Hunter has a secret deal with the Order’s <br>prison guards and picks up the prisoners one night a week <br>to fight. 3-4: A group of conspirators gathers around the <br>Colosseum to make an attempt on the Pope’s life. The con-<br>spirators are led by a Dark Presence hired by the One Who <br>Plots in the Shadows. 5-6: Ancient inscriptions on the walls <br>of the Colosseum point the way to an ancient Treasure of <br>the Order. Translating them, however, requires the inter -<br>vention of a Dark Presence.</p><p>70<br>Leaving Rome<br>When the Hunters leave Rome, each member of the party <br>must roll 1 die, plus 1 additional die for each Unexpect-<br>ed Event Token accumulated. Those rolling at least a 6 will <br>encounter an Unexpected Event, which the Storyteller will <br>either roll at random or choose from the list that follows.<br>Unexpected Events <br>1: The Trial<br>A Dark Presence is put on trial by the Order, and the Hunt-<br>er is called upon to serve as judge. The Storyteller sets up <br>a trial Scene in which the Hunter is the judge. One Hunter <br>NPC will be the prosecution and another Hunter NPC will <br>be the defense. If the Dark Presence is known to the Hunter <br>group, the roles of prosecution and defense can be assigned <br>to other Hunters controlled by a Player. <br>The Storyteller presents the crime of which the Dark Pres-<br>ence is guilty, and then the Scene is played out, with the <br>prosecution and defense alternating in presenting their <br>cases. The judge may ask any questions they wish and will <br>ultimately rule on innocence or guilt. However it goes, the <br>judge will displease one side and satisfy the other. These are <br>good hooks for the Storyteller to use to build relationships <br>with the NPCs involved. <br>2: The Revenge<br>An NPC from a previously played Scenario returns to take <br>revenge on the Hunter. The Storyteller must introduce a <br>Scene in which the Hunter is ambushed by the NPC.<br>3: An Old Acquaintance<br>The Hunter encounters an old acquaintance, and the Sto-<br>ryteller must decide whether this NPC will be a friend or <br>an antagonist for the Hunter. It will be up to the Hunter to <br>decide how to deal with this NPC. <br>4: On the Trail<br>An Opponent Dark Presence is on the Hunter’s trail. The <br>Storyteller selects the Dark Presence and creates an Agenda <br>opposing the Hunter. The Dark Presence will appear as an <br>enemy in the next Scenario.<br>5: The Lost Object<br>The Hunter realizes too late that they have left one of their <br>pieces of equipment in one of the Order’s locations. They <br>can only retrieve it when they next return to Rome. The <br>Player chooses which piece of equipment to lose.<br>6: The Escort <br>The Hunter is summoned for a special assignment: to es-<br>cort a young recruit of the Order to the place the Hunters <br>have designated as their next destination. The person being <br>escorted is very important to the delicate political balance <br>that the Papacy seeks to maintain, so the Hunter must en-<br>sure that the journey is as safe as possible. The Storyteller <br>creates a Minor NPC who will be the subject to be escort-<br>ed. One or more traits leading the NPC to get into trouble <br>should be highlighted in the Descriptor and their Agenda. <br>These reasons can be a rebellious character, an irrepressible <br>addiction, or any other motivation.</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513735896,"modifiedTime":1781513735896,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"rome-city-of-the-order","collection":"Lost Stories","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","pages":"56-71"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513735896,"modifiedTime":1781513735896,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"X7cKdbuHCbC1VjWc","name":"Nemesis","pages":[{"_id":"r6u31Qrwh7Qxm3Pz","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>Nemesis</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> Lost Stories</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, pages 72-96.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/nemesis-p72-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513737045,"modifiedTime":1781513737045,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"oOdWZh6Nk0yvgN9d","name":"Scenario Text","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Nemesis - Scenario Text</h2><p>NEMESI<br>71<br>Once upon a time...<br>Once upon a time, there was a mad writer who created his <br>own reality to escape a world that could not understand him. <br>In his strange creation, good and evil had swapped places: <br>villains were heroes, and heroes indulged in the worst sort of <br>wickedness.<br>The One Who Plots in the Shadows, as the writer called <br>himself, weaved the threads of all the characters’ destinies, <br>creating stories that were dark and bloody, but where justice <br>ultimately triumphed. But in the process, his own hands were <br>left dripping with blood.<br>As the years passed, the new world was filled with life, pop-<br>ulating itself with dark and bizarre characters created by the <br>twisted mind of the One Who Plots in the Shadows.<br>Then it happened: the villains he had given a chance at re-<br>demption joined the Order, an organized group serving man-<br>kind. Investigation after investigation they sought to unravel <br>the great deception, to reveal the identity of the One Who <br>Plots in the Shadows himself.<br>And, after the abandonment of childhood, after the rejection <br>and mockery of adulthood, a new emotion found its <br>way into the heart of the One Who Plots in the Shadows: <br>disappointment that his children didn’t recognize all he <br>had done for them.<br>Once again, he had dedicated his life to someone, and once <br>again, he had been repaid with betrayal. First, the readers <br>who mocked his stories, and now the Hunters who had be-<br>come evil in his vision of the world.<br>Desperate and in pain, the One Who Plots in the Shadows <br>wept inky tears that stained his hands until they turned black <br>as night.<br>And at the height of his despair, he realized what he had to <br>do. <br>If no one would be on his side, if no one could understand <br>him, he would create his own companions: a group of loyal <br>allies united by the same disappointment that had broken <br>his heart. <br>Each would be a Nemesis for the Hunters, extensions of his <br>work so that the whole world would remain locked forever in <br>his perverted vision. <br>In the emptiness of his vast mansion, by the light of a few <br>faint candles, the One Who Plots in the Shadows laughed out <br>loud as he had not in a long time. All he had to do was what <br>he was born to do: create stories, create characters, create <br>someone who could understand him.<br>And as he laughed, he began to write, and the more the <br>words took shape, the more each Nemesis formed from the <br>ink-stained pages.<br>And as he wrote, tears began to fall. <br>Bitter, cold tears. Tears of loneliness.<br>Nemesis</p><p>72<br>The Nemeses<br>Nemeses are a new category of NPC that can be <br>introduced in the Broken Tales Campaign or in a single <br>Scenario to increase its difficulty. Nemeses are special <br>Dark Presences, always linked to the One Who Plots in <br>the Shadows, ready to unfold his mad plans to control <br>Broken Europe.<br>The Nemeses will add depth to the world of Broken Tales, <br>introducing a group of recurring enemies that will creep <br>into the Hunters’ stories. Unified by their hatred for the <br>Hunters of the Order, a Nemesis is also a good way to <br>continue a Broken Tales Campaign after the confronta-<br>tion with the One Who Plots in the Shadows, as they are <br>extremely powerful NPCs and have all the makings of the <br>Hunters’ new “epic enemies. ” <br>Nemesis creation follows the pattern of Dark Presences <br>but with some significant differences.  <br>Step 1 Bring the character to their Breaking <br>Point<br>Nemeses follows the method for creating Dark Presenc-<br>es presented on page 42 of the Broken Tales Core Book, <br>the only difference being the Nemesis’ motive for acting <br>against the Order. In breaking their story, we must con-<br>sider how to include an event that deeply disappointed the <br>Nemesis and caused them to hate the world and every-<br>thing the Hunters protect.<br>The five Nemeses presented in this chapter are good ex-<br>amples of what we mean.<br>Step 2 Assign the characteristics<br>All Nemeses have a Descriptor that outlines their primary <br>abilities, which should be on par with Dark Presences. Since <br>these are characters created with the specific intention of be-<br>ing champions of the One Who Plots in the Shadows, the <br>composition of the Descriptor can be very powerful and <br>more effective than that of normal NPCs.<br>A Nemesis must have a minimum of 4 Wounds and a max-<br>imum of 6. On average, 5 Wounds is best to give the Neme-<br>sis the proper narrative resilience to the actions of an entire <br>group of Hunters. <br>The Opposition Level of a Nemesis is always Medium 5.  It <br>should be noted that thanks to the Nemesis Gift (common to <br>all Nemeses), the Opposition Level against the Hunter whom <br>the Nemesis has marked as a sworn enemy increases to Hard <br>7. This dynamic is important to encourage teamwork among <br>the Hunters, as it makes it easier for that Hunter’s compan-<br>ions to succeed in Checks against the Nemesis.</p><p>73<br>Step 3 Create the Gifts<br>Each Nemesis possesses three Gifts:<br> ◆ The first Gift represents their abilities, powers, or special <br>talents. Follow the Core Book rules for this Gift.<br> ◆ The second Gift is always called “Nemesis, ” and is the <br>same for all Nemeses. This Gift confers a number of spe-<br>cial powers that the Nemesis can use as an NPC of great <br>power and ability.<br> ◆ The third Gift is always the “Investiture” , a powerful spe-<br>cial item given to the Nemesis by the One Who Plots in <br>the Shadows to fight the Hunters.<br>Gift - Nemesis: When the Nemesis enters the game, they <br>choose a Hunter as their sworn enemy. Against them, the <br>Nemesis is always considered OL Hard 7. The Nemesis has 3 <br>Nemesis Tokens, which can be spent during the Scenario to <br>activate one of the following effects. Each effect can only be <br>used once per Scenario. These Tokens do not regenerate at <br>any point. <br>1. Reinforcements: New Nemesis Minions will appear in <br>the Scene, overcoming any obstacle. 2 Minions per Hunter <br>will appear in the Scene.<br>2. Hostage: The Nemesis reveals that they are holding hos-<br>tage an NPC that the Hunters encountered during the cur -<br>rent Scenario or a past Scenario. The NPC is being held cap-<br>tive by some of the Nemesis’ Minions at one of the Places in <br>the current Scenario.    <br>3. Sacrifice: When a Hunter targets the Nemesis with one <br>of their Gifts, a Minion makes an extreme gesture to save <br>their master or mistress’s life. Eliminate the NPC to nullify <br>the effect of the Gift.<br>4. Trap: The Scene changes drastically because of a trap set <br>by the Nemesis. “The floor collapses, ” “ A flood comes, ” or <br>“The room is hit by a toxic cloud that spreads through the <br>air” are all good examples of traps. The Hunters involved <br>must make a Defense Check against the Nemesis’ OL to <br>avoid falling into the trap. In addition to being in a new zone <br>with different narrative conditions, each Hunter who fails the <br>Check suffers 1 Penalty on their next action. After the trap is <br>triggered, the Exchange is interrupted and a new one begins, <br>with the Nemesis faction taking the first action. <br>5. Concealed Truth:  The Nemesis knows some informa-<br>tion that is crucial to the Scenario or very important to one of <br>the Hunters, and will try to use it as a bargaining chip to gain <br>an escape route or safe passage.<br>6. You Won the Battle, not the War: The Nemesis leaves <br>the Scene immediately. No one can prevent this escape, and <br>it will be up to the Storyteller to stage it. Even if the Hunters <br>see the Nemesis die before their eyes, they will find a way to <br>escape. <br>Gift - Investiture:  This Gift represents a powerful magi-<br>cal object that the Nemesis receives from the One Who Plots <br>in the Shadows. The object is not a Treasure of the Order, <br>nor does it need to be inspired by an object from a fairytale. <br>Instead, it must represent an important characteristic of the <br>Nemesis. All items tied to an Investiture Gift lose their power <br>when the Nemesis is defeated: when the Nemesis is no longer <br>a threat to the Hunters, the meaning of the investiture is lost, <br>and so is the power that animates the object.</p><p>DELUSION<br>74<br>Step 4 Agenda<br>Each Nemesis must have 4 Agendas, one for each possible <br>story phase in which they act. As with the common Agen-<br>das, these are a general indication of the Nemesis’ goals and <br>must be updated based on the Hunters’ actions during the <br>Scenarios. <br>The Agendas for the five Nemeses presented in this guide <br>can be used as guidelines for creating Agendas for other <br>Nemeses.<br>The first Agenda represents why the Nemesis <br>is interested in the Hunters<br>This is the initial Agenda of the Nemesis and is the most <br>“passive” , meaning that it represents what the Nemesis does <br>in Broken Europe when they are unaware of the Hunters’ <br>actions. This Agenda establishes the focus of the Nemesis <br>and what triggers their interest in the Hunters. The first <br>Agenda is the main way to determine when the Nemesis <br>comes into play.<br>Example: <br>The first Agenda of the Relentless Beastslayer is: “Track down <br>and eliminate any monster that threatens humanity. ” This <br>Agenda can trigger in any Scenario where monsters are pres-<br>ent (including Hunters with monstrous traits!) and pique the <br>interest of the Relentless Beastslayer, which will intervene to <br>investigate and stop anything that he perceives as monstrous.<br>The use of this Agenda can be direct, with the Nemesis ap-<br>pearing during the adventure to oppose the Hunters (or even <br>temporarily help them if it makes sense to accomplish the <br>Nemesis’ goals). The use of the Agenda can also be indirect, <br>with the Nemesis appearing earlier or later to influence loca-<br>tions and NPCs, or to gather information about the Hunters’ <br>actions. <br>The goal of the first Agenda is to introduce the Nemesis into <br>the Scenario and show what makes them unique.<br>The second Agenda represents how the <br>Nemesis helps the One Who Plots in the <br>Shadows<br>This Agenda characterizes how the Nemesis operates be-<br>hind the scenes and how they use their resources to help <br>the One Who Plots in the Shadows. This Agenda is respon-<br>sible for leaving traces of the Nemesis in the game world <br>and introducing related resources and NPCs that can pro-<br>vide important information to the Hunters.<br>Example: <br>One of the two items in the Wise Fairy’s second Agenda is <br>to “Donate power at a dear price, always reminding us <br>that good for its own sake does not exist. ” This Agenda can <br>be implemented through NPCs connected to the Wise Fairy, <br>who become more skilled and dangerous by receiving power <br>from her. However, they will forever after be tied to the Fairy <br>and may be forced to do her bidding.<br>The use of this Agenda can be direct, with the Nemesis sup-<br>porting other NPCs against the Hunters, or indirect, with <br>the Nemesis approaching NPCs defeated by the Hunters <br>after a Scenario to bring them into the ranks of their Min-<br>ions. <br>The goal of the second Agenda is to leave traces of the Nem-<br>esis in Broken Europe for the Hunters to stumble upon and <br>see the effects of their machinations.</p><p>75<br>The third Agenda represents how the <br>Nemesis fights against the Hunters<br>This Agenda characterizes the overt actions of the Nemesis <br>and outlines how they fight and confront the Hunters. This <br>Agenda is meant to guide their actions in the Scene as they <br>confront the Hunters.<br>Example: <br>The two items in the third Agenda of the King of Crime are: <br>“Use my resources and Minions to attack the Hunters <br>without exposing myself on the front lines / Use deception <br>and blackmail to corner the Hunters. ” These items outline <br>a talent for manipulation, which the Nemesis can use when <br>attempting to turn the Hunters against each other through <br>deception and social power. <br>This Agenda is always direct, meaning it requires the pres-<br>ence of the Nemesis in the Scenario or during Encounters <br>and Events. <br>The goal of the third Agenda is to provide the Storytell-<br>er with good guidance for pitting the Nemesis against the <br>Hunters.   <br>The fourth Agenda represents the goal of <br>the Nemesis after the One Who Plots in the <br>Shadows falls<br>This Agenda sets out a long-term goal that the Nemesis will <br>seek to achieve as they replace the One Who Plots in the <br>Shadows, while trying to remain true to his vision: to create <br>dark stories featuring the many characters created over the <br>years by the mad writer. Once he’s out of business, the Nem-<br>esis will attempt to turn the tables by involving the Hunters <br>and Dark Presences scattered throughout the world.<br>Example: <br>The two items in the fourth Agenda of the Valiant Princess <br>are to: “Unite the weak and marginalized to create a net-<br>work to help others / Accumulate wealth to gain power in <br>society and impose more just laws and rules, disrupting <br>secret societies like the Order. ” The items in this Agenda <br>define a long-term goal of the Valiant Princess, who deeply <br>hates those who are able to decide the fate of others due to <br>their privileged status and will seek to fight everything she <br>deems wrong. The Order included.<br>This Agenda acts first in an indirect way, as a driving force <br>behind the events that will involve the Hunters, and only <br>later in a direct way, as the Nemesis lashes out at their ene-<br>mies to achieve their goal. <br>The purpose of the fourth Agenda is to introduce a new <br>main plot that will continue the Hunters’ adventure after <br>the final confrontation with the One Who Plots in the <br>Shadows.</p><p>77<br>Step 5 Minions<br>Each Nemesis may have Minions, which are related NPCs <br>who help the Nemesis fulfill their Agenda. Minions must be <br>created using the rules for various types of NPCs presented <br>in the Broken Tales Core Book on page 31, with the addition <br>of an Agenda that defines why they are in the service of the <br>Nemesis.<br>For convenience, it is useful to define Minions in two cate-<br>gories:<br>The Followers: Represented by NPCs and Dark Presences <br>drawn from the background of the Nemesis. These charac-<br>ters have been present since the creation of the Nemesis and <br>represent the relationships and social fabric in which the <br>Nemesis moves. These Minions should be characterized by <br>Agendas and Descriptors that represent their history with <br>the Nemesis. <br>The Minions must be created along with the Nemesis, al-<br>though it is possible to update the members of the group to <br>be consistent with what happens in the Hunters’ adventures.<br>The New Recruits: These are all the NPCs and Dark Pres-<br>ences that come under the influence of the Nemesis during <br>the course of the game. Their motivations will often be a re-<br>sult of the Hunter’s actions in their Scenario.<br>New Recruits must be created between Scenarios, reflecting <br>on what has happened and looking for points of connection <br>with the Nemesis.    <br>Step 6 Connections<br>This step is not mandatory, but preparing for it can be a tre-<br>mendous help to the Storyteller. It involves making a list of <br>Keywords related to the Nemesis, in order to more easily <br>note possible connections with the Scenarios and Scenes that <br>will be played out. <br>Another step is to identify the most thematic Scenarios for <br>the Nemesis and, in accordance with the main storyline, <br>sketch out a range of useful information about how the Nem-<br>esis might be grafted onto the events presented. This step <br>may take a lot of work, but it will provide a very useful set of <br>information and new gameplay hints that will be valuable to <br>the Storyteller. At the same time, these clues should address <br>both what the Nemesis can do during the Scenario and what <br>attracts the Nemesis to the Campaign after the Hunters re-<br>solve the Scenario.<br>Example:<br>The Connections of the Relentless Beastslayer for the Scenario <br>Bloodwhite’s Heart, available in The Broken Ones expansion, <br>are: “Finding a way to cure Bianca of her condition / Help-<br>ing Svenn preserve the Karenmann family secret. ” Bianca <br>has the traits of a monster, but she does not act like one: she <br>has a pure heart and would never hurt anyone. When outlin-<br>ing Connections, we also incorporate a reference to the orig-<br>inal fairytale, where the Huntsman is ordered to kill Snow <br>White, but cannot find the courage to do so. <br>In memory of the young woman he killed in the past, the Re-<br>lentless Beastslayer wants to find a way to save Bianca from <br>her monstrous condition. Connections tell us how he would <br>act during the Scenario, but with some interpretation, they <br>will also tell us what happens if the Nemesis comes to Lohr <br>before or after the Hunters.</p><p>78<br>If he arrives first: He could provide Svenn with resources and <br>Followers to help him keep Bianca’s secret. He could even wait <br>for the Hunters to arrive, and once they have the upper hand <br>over the Hessian Mercenaries, he could kidnap Bianca and <br>take her to safety. Finally, he could lurk by the river to am-<br>bush the Hunters before they reach the mine.<br>If he comes later: He could hire Svenn as a Minion and learn <br>everything the man knows about the Hunters. The same <br>strategy could apply to the Hessian Mercenaries. He could <br>also track down Bianca and snatch her from the clutches of <br>the Order. Finally, he could ambush the Hunters on one of <br>their journeys (Event) to punish those who harmed Bianca. <br>Each of the five Nemeses presented in Lost Stories has an <br>extensive list of Connections that make their usefulness <br>very clear. <br>Introducing Nemeses into the game<br>Nemeses are not simply NPCs to be added as opposition to <br>the Hunters, there are already Opponent Dark Presences <br>NPCs for that. Each Nemesis will have a consistent impact <br>on the Campaign or Scenario. It is a good idea to introduce <br>the Nemesis gradually, starting with simple clues and small <br>events that will evolve into more or less direct actions. The <br>Nemesis Agendas, especially the first two, serve as a long-<br>term guide to the Nemesis’ behavior.    <br>Some tips to ease the introduction of a Nemesis:<br> ◆ The first Agenda of each Nemesis gives important clues <br>as to what the Nemesis is interested in. Linking it to the <br>Scenarios already played gives consistency to their ap-<br>pearance in the game. It is better to delay the arrival of a <br>Nemesis in order to integrate it well into the Campaign <br>plot, rather than to drop them in as an opponent who has <br>no real reason to resent the Hunters.<br> ◆ Each Nemesis will eventually decide which Hunter is their <br>sworn enemy, so it makes sense to have as many Nemeses <br>in the Campaign as there are Hunters. Alternating the ap-<br>pearance of the Nemeses will make it easier to keep them <br>from wearing out their welcome too quickly.<br> ◆ A good alternative method of introducing the Nemesis <br>can be through chance encounters. The Nemesis is pres-<br>ent in the Scenario, but with an Agenda that does not con-<br>cern the Hunters, and only tangentially touches on events. <br>This will leave a trace of their passage for the Hunters to <br>discover, which will then serve as a link in their future ap-<br>pearances. <br> ◆ Nemeses have great power even when they are behind the <br>scenes. Gifts and Minions allow the Nemesis to influence <br>the world around the Hunters without directly appearing <br>on the Scene. These links should be outlined in Nemesis <br>Connections. <br>Don’t make the Nemeses the primary <br>antagonist of a Scenario<br>The Nemesis’ job is to hinder the Hunters, but future con-<br>frontations will be more interesting if you don’t unleash all <br>of their power against the Hunters right away. Nemeses can <br>be really scary thanks to the Gifts of Nemesis and Inves-<br>titure, but they will lose their appeal if they play all their <br>cards too soon. Each Scenario already has a plot and a cast <br>of main NPCs that animate it, and replacing them with a <br>Nemesis will only distract from the story. Therefore, do not <br>make Nemeses the antagonist of a Scenario unless it is the <br>final confrontation against them (see page 79).<br>Keep in mind that:<br> ◆ The Nemesis must be a valuable aid to the Scenario’s <br>NPCs, without replacing them in the main plot.<br> ◆ Thanks to the Y ou Won the Battle, not the War Gift, <br>a Nemesis can always make a run for it if the situation</p><p>79<br>takes a turn for the worse. For this reason, Nemeses <br>can be useful as surprises that appear briefly during a <br>Scene to add some excitement, then escape.<br> ◆ Not every appearance of the Nemesis has to be a con-<br>flict. Clues, verbal confrontations, and Minions brag-<br>ging about their masters’ power are good systems for <br>building up Hunters’ expectations for the arrival of <br>these new adversaries.<br> ◆ Encounters and Events are great ways to bring the <br>Nemesis into the game. In these moments, the Nemesis <br>can be the true antagonist, using Gifts and Minions to <br>put the Hunters at risk.<br> ◆ The Nemesis’ Gifts are meant to make them versatile, <br>not overly powerful. Each encounter should bring out a <br>different ability of the Nemesis so that their true threat <br>level is gradually revealed to the Hunters.  <br>Defeating a Nemesis<br>Each Nemesis requires a unique approach to defeat, as-<br>suming that is the ultimate goal of the Hunters. As with <br>all Broken Tales stories, it is the Player’s choices that create <br>turning points in the plot. Like the NPCs presented in the <br>Scenarios, the Nemesis isn’t a puppet with the sole purpose <br>of harming the Hunters, but a well-rounded character who, <br>if approached in the right way, may even understand and <br>help the Order.<br>There are several ways to present the final confrontation <br>with a Nemesis:<br> ◆ Create a Scenario dedicated to the Nemesis, starting <br>with the story in which they appear. If a Scenario based <br>on that story already exists among the official Scenar -<br>ios, it is recommended that you don’t propose it to the <br>Players and instead save it for the grand finale. Alter -<br>natively, it is possible to rewrite the Scenario, adapt it to <br>what the Hunters have already done, and put the Nem-<br>esis in the role of the main antagonist.<br> ◆ If the Hunters arrive at the final confrontation with <br>the One Who Plots in the Shadows and the Nemeses <br>are still in action, it is recommended that they be used <br>during the Epilogue. One or more Nemesis could use <br>Y ou Won the Battle, not the War during the con-<br>frontation, paving the way for the continuation of the <br>game’s Campaign.<br> ◆ If the Hunters are actively engaged in finding the Nem-<br>esis, it is only fair to reward them by creating a Sce-<br>nario that represents a confrontation with their enemy. <br>However, in order to reach this Scenario, they should <br>go through a series of encounters and a collection of <br>useful clues to uncover the location of the Nemesis.<br>Nemeses in Single Scenarios<br>Although a Nemesis reaches their full potential during <br>a Campaign, it is possible to include them when playing <br>individual Scenarios. Before embarking on the adventure, <br>the Storyteller should broadly introduce the Nemesis to <br>the Hunters, specifying why they are on their trail. The first <br>Nemesis Agenda provides good narrative hooks in this re-<br>gard. The Hunters will then be aware that an enemy is on <br>their trail and could complicate their plans any moment.<br>Example:<br>The Storyteller has prepared the House of Roses Scenario, in-<br>spired by Beauty and the Beast and included in the Broken <br>Ones expansion. The Hunter party consists of Garou the Old <br>Wolf, James the Swordsman, Baba Yaga the Child Witch, and <br>Niklaus von Krampus. With as many as three Hunters tied to <br>something monstrous, and a main NPC with the character -<br>istics of a monster (Dionysus Gonsalva), the Storyteller iden-<br>tifies the Relentless Beastslayer as an excellent Nemesis for <br>the game. The first Nemesis Agenda reads: “Track down and <br>eliminate any monster that threatens humanity. ”</p><p>80<br>The Storyteller then introduces the Nemesis to the group of <br>Hunters: They had previously encountered a strange figure <br>cloaked in black who had tried to kill Garou and Niklaus sev-<br>eral times because of their “monstrous” appearance. This is a <br>dangerous, merciless, and ruthless individual, a beast-killer <br>who seems to be obsessed with monsters. <br> <br>Players are unaware that there is a monstrous NPC in <br>the Scenario, and this combination of characters will <br>certainly lead to interesting situations.<br>Even if introduced at the beginning, a Nemesis may need <br>further hooks to the narrative:<br> ◆ The Nemesis has allied themselves with an NPC in the <br>Scenario to whom they provide support. They will not <br>act directly except to help that NPC achieve their goals.<br> ◆ Nemeses will come into play as the price for an Inter -<br>lude, giving players the distinct feeling that they have <br>made things more difficult by wasting time. <br> ◆ The Nemesis waits for the right moment to strike with <br>a direct attack. They will do so at a transitional mo-<br>ment in the Scenario’s plot when their appearance can <br>seamlessly fit into events and will not interfere with the <br>actions of the Main NPCs or even the events of the Sce-<br>nario itself. The Nemesis attacks the Hunters and will <br>be able to escape through the Gift Y ou Won the Battle, <br>not the War.<br>The Five Nemeses<br>Below are the five Nemeses created by the One Who Plots <br>in the Shadows to fight the Hunters. Each Nemesis is de-<br>rived from a fairytale archetype:<br> ◆ The Huntsman, on which the Relentless Beastslayer is <br>based, represents the deus ex machina that intervenes <br>to save the protagonists, a force of nature that punishes <br>monsters and villains.<br> ◆ The Lady of the Lake, the inspiration for the Wise <br>Fairy, is the powerful fairy whose gifts give the heroes <br>the power to win.<br> ◆ Thumbling (inspiring the King of Crime) and Viola  <br>(the archetypal Valiant Princess) represent the young <br>protagonists who manage to defeat the villains with <br>cunning and courage.<br> ◆ The Naked Emperor, a direct reference for the Mad <br>Emperor, represents truth overcoming lies, which, <br>when revealed, exposes deception.</p><p>81<br>The Relentless <br>Beastslayer  <br>Inspired by the Huntsman of many fairytales<br>Once upon a time, there was a skilled Beastslayer with a good <br>heart who traveled the world, offering his skills to small vil-<br>lages. The Beastslayer feared nothing, and more than once his <br>courage had saved helpless people from the threat of monsters <br>and wild beasts. One day, the Beastslayer was summoned to <br>a mission by the queen. Rumor had it that the queen was <br>actually a witch, but all the subjects were happy under her <br>leadership, and the Beastslayer decided to trust her anyway. <br>The queen had a very special request for him: to escort her <br>stepdaughter into the forest and remove her heart, for she <br>was actually a demon hiding in the guise of a maiden. The <br>Beastslayer refused to believe the queen, but she cast a spell <br>to deceive his eyes, and what the man saw was exactly what <br>the witch wanted. Bewitched and unable to object, the Beast-<br>slayer took the young woman into the woods and cut out her <br>heart with a precise stroke of his blade. When he came to <br>his senses, he tried to take revenge, only to discover that he <br>was wanted throughout the kingdom for the murder of the <br>young princess. The queen witch had used him as a scapegoat <br>so she could appear blameless before the king. Disappoint-<br>ed at his helplessness in the face of such evil , the <br>Beastslayer fled far away to the shelter of the great forest, and <br>with his hands still stained with blood, he finally came to a <br>small cottage. Finding the door open, he entered to see who <br>lived there, just in time to see a huge wolf devouring an old <br>grandmother and her young granddaughter. The Beastslay-<br>er attacked the monster, which was still intent on chewing <br>the little girl’s bones between its sharp fangs. After a furious <br>struggle, the wolf prevailed, leaving the Beastslayer on the <br>ground in the small yard of the house. With his belly ripped <br>open, but still alive, the Beastslayer found himself cursing all <br>monsters, in body and soul, who mercilessly slaughtered in-<br>nocent souls. And as his tears mingled with the rain that be-<br>gan to fall, he made an oath: he would become the scourge of <br>every aberration, the shadow that would appear to mete out <br>just punishment to every monster. Without mercy. <br>Descriptor: I am a skilled huntsman and have all the <br>means to kill any monster. I never say a word and try to keep <br>myself aloof from everyone.<br>5 Wounds<br>Opposition Level: Medium 5 <br>Agenda 1:  Track down and eliminate any monster that <br>threatens humanity.<br>Agenda 2: Set traps to kill monsters/Teach others how to <br>kill monsters. <br>Agenda 3: Kill the Hunters by taking them by surprise / <br>Challenge the Hunters on the battleground most advanta-<br>geous to me.<br>Agenda 4:  Form the Beast Slayer Guild and recruit the <br>most skilled individuals into its ranks / Capture and train <br>monsters to use as weapons against other monsters. <br>Gift - Hunt Master:  Once per Scenario, the Beastslayer <br>can appear in the Scene from a shadowy area or patch of <br>vegetation and act immediately in the Exchange. The Beast-<br>slayer is completely immune to all fear-inducing effects and <br>any manipulation (magical or otherwise) that would dis-<br>tract him from his goal: killing monsters.    <br>Gift - Nemesis:  See page 73. Sworn Enemies: Hunters <br>with monstrous traits or monsters.<br>Gift of Investiture - The Blade of Punishment:  <br>When the Beastslayer attacks a target with monstrous traits,</p><p>82<br>the blow always hits, with no chance to make a Defense Check. <br>Wounds inflicted with this weapon are conspicuous and impossible <br>to conceal, and cannot be healed in any way until the end of the <br>Scenario.  <br>Minions:<br>Hounds<br>The Relentless Beastslayer has trained many hounds, teaching <br>them to face monsters without fear.<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am an agile hunting dog, ready to carry out any <br>command of my master. <br>Agenda: Follow my master on hunting trips and serve him <br>even at the cost of my life. <br>Gift - Perfect Training: As long as the dog is focused on <br>its master, it cannot be distracted in any way. The NPC is <br>immune to all fear and mind control effects. When focus-<br>ing on a target to restrain it and prevent it from escaping, <br>the Hound uses OL Hard 7.</p><p>83<br>The Twelve Poachers <br>Inspired by the Twelve Huntsmen [Opponent)<br>Once upon a time, there was a princess who was deeply in <br>love with a prince. The two longed to marry, but the young <br>man’s father had already promised him to another noble <br>maiden. Unable to resist the last wishes of his dying father, <br>the prince abandoned the princess and went through with <br>the arranged marriage. Destroyed by grief, the abandoned <br>princess hatched a terrible deception. Together with eleven <br>other girls who closely resembled her, she pretended to be a <br>huntsman in the service of the prince and accompanied him <br>on every hunting trip. During one of these trips, the princess <br>staged an accident and pierced the new queen’s heart with <br>an arrow. That same night, she presented herself to her lov-<br>er and revealed what she had done, confident that he would <br>understand. But he did not: he was horrified and ordered the <br>guards to kill the princess who had posed as a huntsman. The <br>young woman managed to escape with her companions and, <br>convinced that she was in the right, took up poaching, wait-<br>ing for a new love to understand her heart.<br>OL Medium 5 <br>(1 Wound - 12 Gang Members)<br>Descriptor: We are skilled hunters and we disguise our -<br>selves as ordinary girls. We have no qualms about achieving <br>our goal. <br>Agenda: Serving the Relentless Beastslayer and dispensing <br>punishment in the name of our warped sense of justice.<br>Gift - A Delicate Maiden:  Unless a Poacher unleashes <br>her hunting weapons, she will look just like a normal vil-<br>lager. No NPC will consider her a threat. When a Poacher <br>reveals her true nature, her OL increases by 1 for the first <br>action she participates in.  <br>•<br>Connections: Monsters / Villagers in danger / Vicious <br>beasts / Hunting / Traps / Defending a location.<br>Red-Hood Iskra: Assist Vincent Arn, an old hunting com-<br>panion / Help Elizaveta get rid of her monstrous daughter.<br>Hunger Island: Retrieve the Stone that Came from the Sky <br>so that it cannot spawn new monsters / Prevent the inhabi-<br>tants and any visitors from leaving the island, as they may <br>be infected.<br>Bloodwhite’s Heart: Finding a way to cure Bianca of her <br>condition / Helping Svenn preserve the Karenmann family <br>secret.<br>Nikola’s Pledge: Capture the fearsome Badalisk for later <br>training. Use the village of Rovaniemi as bait to lure the crea-<br>ture / Help Nikola defend himself from intruders in exchange <br>for his monstrous Reindeer, which could be trained for mon-<br>ster hunting.</p><p>84<br>The Valiant Princess <br>Inspired by Tale of Tales<br>Once upon a time, there was a noble regent of Altomonte who became morbidly attached <br>to a flea. The old man cared for the flea as if it were a daughter and allowed it to grow to <br>the size of a large dog. The regent treated the flea like a member of his family, even going <br>so far as to neglect Viola, his only real daughter. The young girl suffered the humiliation <br>of being second in importance in her father’s eyes, and when a rich and ill-mannered <br>suitor came to ask for the princess’ hand, the Regent of Altomonte gave his consent to the <br>marriage, ignoring his daughter’s protests. The prospective bridegroom was a lecherous <br>old man, and there were ugly rumors that he had been involved in the deaths of his <br>previous brides. Disappointed by her father’s insensitivity and her suitor’s <br>wickedness, Viola left for her new home with her future husband, despairing of the <br>fate that awaited her because of men’s power games. But in the young princess’ heart <br>burned the fire of courage, and when she arrived at her destination, Viola refused to <br>participate in the marriage ceremony. As punishment, the old man locked her in the <br>dungeon of his castle, where she lived on bread and water until she agreed to marry <br>him. It was in the dungeons that Viola met seven brothers dedicated to smuggling <br>and the use of magic so feared by the Church. With the help of the seven, Viola <br>escaped from prison and that very night, she stabbed the old man in the heart <br>as he lay in bed with two concubines. The seven brothers were so impressed by <br>Viola’s courage that they swore allegiance to her. They had always lived to do <br>wrong, but now they had an example of justice to follow. The young prin-<br>cess then returned to her father, hoping that he would come to his senses. <br>Instead, he accused Viola of treason for breaking the sacred traditions <br>of the nobility: a woman like her could not afford to decide for herself <br>what was right or wrong.<br>With tears of grief in her eyes, Viola tried to leave, but the flea, <br>as if sensing her pain, acted for her. The insect leaped to her <br>father’s neck and cut his throat cleanly. The dying man <br>waved his arms at Viola for help, but the girl had <br>dried her tears and had no more words for her fa-<br>ther.</p><p>85<br>From that day on, Viola took charge, and with her trusty flea <br>at her side, she rewrote all the laws of Altomonte so that no <br>young woman would ever again have to endure the torment <br>of a society run by the will of men alone.<br>Descriptor: I am a brave princess who fights for the free-<br>dom of all oppressed youth. The passion that drives me allows <br>me to overcome any obstacle and ignore any pain.    <br>4 Wounds<br>Opposition Level: Medium 5<br>Agenda 1: Liberate all young people who are oppressed by <br>society. <br>Agenda 2: Support those who rise up against oppression / <br>Make the evil of the oppressors known to all.<br>Agenda 3: Use good-hearted people to oppose the Hunters / <br>Challenge the Hunters openly and boldly. <br>Agenda 4: Unite the weak and marginalized to create a <br>network to help others / Accumulate wealth to gain power in <br>society and impose more just laws and rules, disrupting secret <br>societies like the Order. <br>Gift - Porziella the Flea: The Valiant Princess is always <br>accompanied by her trusty flea, who guards her like a faith-<br>ful dog. Porziella is not considered an NPC but will act on <br>Viola’s behalf a second time in the Exchange. Porziella’s <br>skin is as hard as stone, so the bug cannot be removed by <br>normal means.<br>Gift - Nemesis:  See page 73. Sworn Enemies: Hunters <br>with malicious intent and men who represent authority.<br>Gift of Investiture - The Heart of Courage:  The Val-<br>iant Princess is considered to have OL Hard 7 against all <br>actions designed to frighten her or restrain her. Once per <br>Scene, the Heart of Courage can negate the effect of any <br>Gift used against the Valiant Princess.<br>Minions:<br>The Seven Shady Brothers <br>Inspired by The Flea (Opponent)<br>Once upon a time, there were seven brothers who dedicated <br>themselves to a life of banditry and the reckless use of mag-<br>ic. After a robbery gone wrong, the seven were arrested and <br>sentenced to the gallows. In prison, they met a brave prin-<br>cess who had been imprisoned not for a crime, but simply <br>for wanting the freedom to choose her own life. Impressed by <br>such courage, the seven brothers helped the princess escape, <br>and once free, they swore allegiance to her. In her service, <br>they would finally do something good to redeem themselves <br>from a life of causing misery. <br>OL Medium 5 <br>(1 Wound - 7 Gang Members)<br>Descriptor: We are young brigands who learned magic <br>from our late mother, a witch. We hate law and religion, in-<br>stitutions that have always persecuted what they do not un-<br>derstand. <br>Agenda: Help the Valiant Princess subvert the order and <br>dogmas of society.    <br>Gift - Scoundrel Magic: Each of the Seven Shady Broth-<br>ers has a magical power they can use during the course of <br>a Scene.<br>Mase: He has extraordinary hearing and can hear a <br>speech even through a wall. All Checks performed to <br>avoid him hearing something are done with 2 Penal-<br>ties.<br>Nardo: He can excrete soap from his skin and slip <br>through any crevice. He can also automatically free <br>himself from any physical obstacle.</p><p>86<br>Cola: He has a razor-sharp right hand and inflicts 2 <br>Wounds with all his attacks.<br>Micco: He can make the old wooden stick he always <br>carries grow at will. The weapon can stretch up to sixty <br>feet or expand to the size of a door.<br>Petrullo: He can create a water jet from his hands that <br>can hit enemies and objects up to ten meters away. <br>Ascadeo: He can throw one of the many rocks in his <br>bag, always hitting the target. When he throws a stone, <br>Ascadeo acts at OL Hard 7. <br>Ceccone: He can magically guide the arrows he shoots <br>with his crossbow, sending them on impossible trajec-<br>tories.      <br>•<br>Connections: Youth in danger / Men abusing authority / <br>Rebellion / Prisons / Marriages / Help. <br>I Don’t Believe: Help the Lost Children and Pietrik subvert <br>authority in London / Eliminate Gwendolyn’s family to give <br>the young girl a chance to emancipate herself and assert her <br>independence.<br>The House of Roses: Help Bellina make the island indepen-<br>dent of the Church by providing her with alliances and mil-<br>itary support / Rescue Francesca and train her as a ruthless <br>assassin to be unleashed against the Order.<br>Stegeborg’s Quiet: Save Talia’s life by preventing any threat <br>from entering the castle / Capture and torture Accursio until <br>he begs for a quick death.<br>A Mother’s Heart: Help the Bats find their place in the world, <br>even if it means conquering it by force / Punish the Church <br>and the townspeople for not doing anything to save Blanca’s <br>children.</p><p>87<br>The King of Crime <br>Inspired by Thumbling<br>Once upon a time, a terrible famine struck a remote village, so that a woodcutter and his wife could not feed <br>their seven children. They made a fateful decision: to abandon the children in the forest. The youngest of them <br>all was named Thumbling, and though he was tiny in stature, he possessed a cunning that would make the <br>sliest of brigands envious. Once alone in the forest, Thumbling’s six siblings despaired, but the little one took <br>charge and led them all to a small house whose light illuminated the darkness of the night. Throughout <br>the journey, the brothers and sisters complained and lamented every misfortune, but Thumbling was <br>undaunted. When they arrived at the house, the seven children were greeted by a kind woman who <br>made them comfortable and served them a hot meal. All the siblings were happy to have found a new <br>home, but Thumbling was wary of trusting such kindness. He warned his brothers and sisters, who <br>mocked him. Tired and with full bellies, the siblings went to sleep, ignoring the doubts of Thumbling, <br>who decided to stay awake to keep watch. At the stroke of midnight, a fearsome ogre returned to <br>the house. Thumbling overheard him talking to his wife, complimenting her for providing him with <br>juicy children to devour the next day. Hearing of the terrible deception, Thumbling devised a plan <br>to save his brothers and sisters: at night, taking advantage of his diminutive size, he slipped out of <br>the room and slit the throat of the ogre and his wife as they slept. Stained with blood and shaken <br>by what he had done, Thumbling clung to the happiness of having saved his beloved brothers and <br>sisters. When they awoke, they saw what Thumbling had done and immediately chased him out <br>of the house, accusing him of killing out of spite the only people who had cared for them. Hurt <br>by these words, Thumbling ran far away. Ten years passed, and Thumbling had become im-<br>mensely wealthy. Using his brilliant mind, the young man had risen through the ranks of the <br>underworld to become one of the most powerful criminals in all of Europe. Loaded with coins <br>and jewels, Thumbling returned to the ogre’s home, where he knew his siblings had settled. <br>Confident that he would surprise everyone with the gifts he had brought, he approached <br>the window...<br>In the festively decorated hall, he saw his six siblings toasting with their parents, gathered <br>together like a real family, enjoying the riches found in the ogre’s house. A family por<br>-<br>trait towered over the richly decorated hall: father, mother, and six children. <br>Thumbling’s eyes narrowed to a slit: they had forgotten him, after all he had done <br>for them.</p><p>88<br>Disappointed at the abandonment of the only peo-<br>ple he had ever loved , Thumbling dropped a large dia -<br>mond on the doorstep, knocked, and left. He heard his father’s <br>agitated voice when he opened the door and saw such a beau-<br>tiful gift abandoned. <br>Returning to his hiding place, Thumbling wrote an open let-<br>ter to all the criminals of Europe: the famous Ogre’s Eye, the <br>largest diamond ever seen in Europe, was in a small house in <br>the woods, guarded by a gang of petty thieves. <br>It took less than a day for the news to reach him: an entire <br>family, father, mother, and six siblings, had been mercilessly <br>slaughtered by an army of criminals who had come from far <br>and wide. Almost nothing was left of the poor people’s bodies, <br>dismembered in the course of the most unspeakable torture. <br>As the most skilled of his assassins returned to the lair with <br>the Ogre’s Eye, Thumbling sighed and then smiled at another <br>successful plan.<br>Descriptor: I am a major criminal and pull the strings of <br>the underworld throughout Europe. I have wealth and ser -<br>vants ready to carry out my every order. Thanks to my cun-<br>ning, I make perfect plans to always get what I want.  <br>3 Wounds<br>Opposition Level: Medium 5  <br>Agenda 1: To have all the criminals in the world at my ser-<br>vice. <br>Agenda 2: Finding criminals and scoundrels to increase my <br>sphere of influence and favors / Gathering benefits and infor-<br>mation from the misfortunes of others.       <br>Agenda 3:  Use my resources and Minions to attack the <br>Hunters without exposing myself on the front lines / Use de-<br>ception and blackmail to corner the Hunters.     <br>Agenda 4: Create a shadow government to guide the desti-<br>ny of a Europe under my control / Take the reins of the Order <br>and restore the balance dictated by the One Who Plots in the <br>Shadows. <br>Gift - Diabolical Plan:  The King of Crime always has a <br>cunning plan to unleash on his enemies. He can use each of <br>these effects once per Scenario.<br>1. Receive a compromising item found on an NPC or <br>Hunter. It is not possible to avoid this effect.<br>2. Rewrite the Agenda of a Minor NPC who turns out to <br>be a servant of the King of Crime.<br>3. Introduce a Treasure of the Order and use it for the rest <br>of the Scene. <br>Gift - Nemesis:  See page 73. Sworn Enemies: Hunters <br>who engage in crime and Hunters who fight crime.   <br>Gift of Investiture - The Bag of Wealth:  Once per <br>Scene, the King of Crime can flaunt his wealth to make any-<br>one who sees his bag greedy. Anyone who sees the Bag of <br>Wealth will have to make a Defense Check against OL Hard <br>7 or remain spellbound for about ten seconds, unable to do <br>anything but fantasize about this incredible wealth. NPCs <br>automatically fall victim to this Gift. Suffering 1 Wound in-<br>terrupts the effect of the Bag. The King of Crime can decide <br>who does not suffer the effects of the Bag, such as his own <br>Minions.</p><p>89<br>Minions:<br>Scoundrel<br>The dregs of society, always ready to serve the King of <br>Crime.<br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a lowlife who lives off theft and extortion. <br>I draw strength from my fellow gang members and am not <br>stupid enough to go at it alone.    <br>Agenda: Carry out the boss’s orders without asking too <br>many questions. <br>Gift - Band:  Those who possess this Gift increase their <br>Opposition Level by 1 when acting against a target with the <br>support of one or more companions.<br>Sicario<br>Ruthless assassin in the pay of the King of Crime.<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a capable killer and always act in cold <br>blood. <br>Agenda: Eliminate the Boss’ designated targets by striking <br>from the shadows. <br>Gift - Assassin:  Those who possess this Gift increase <br>their Opposition Level by 1 when acting from the shadows <br>or in low light. When the NPC makes an attack that catches <br>the target by surprise, they inflict 1 Additional Wound. <br>The Raven Clan <br>Inspired by the Seven Ravens [Opponent)<br>Once upon a time, there was a family in which only sons <br>were born. The father and mother longed for a daughter <br>and prayed for a long time to receive this grace. When the <br>baby girl finally arrived, the family’s enthusiasm quickly fad-<br>ed. The newborn was extremely weak and the doctor made <br>it clear that she would not be saved without a miracle. The <br>father then sent the seven sons in search of a powerful witch <br>who lived not far from the village. When they arrived at the <br>witch’s house, the seven brothers were given a jar of magic <br>water that could give strength and vitality. The seven began <br>to argue over who should carry the jar, as they all wanted to <br>receive compliments from their father. In the struggle, the jar <br>fell to the ground and shattered into a thousand pieces, scat-<br>tering the precious water. When they returned home, there <br>was nothing to do for their little sister. The father, in despair, <br>cursed his children for fighting over the jar like greedy ravens <br>over a piece of meat. The witch heard the man’s grief and, <br>as punishment, turned the seven brothers into seven ravens, <br>forever condemned to a life as watchers, never to be shown <br>affection again. <br>OL Medium 5 - (1 Wound - 7 Ravens)<br>Descriptor: We are big black ravens but with the soul and <br>mind of a human being. <br>Agenda: Observe the world and report back to the King of <br>Crime, who has promised us a cure for the curse that plagues us. <br>Gift - Curse of the Raven:  Each of the seven Ravens <br>is mentally connected to the others. They all immediately <br>learn everything one hears and sees. Although the body is <br>that of a Raven, their mind remains that of a human, so a <br>Raven can write while holding a pen in its beak or open a <br>door, and perform other actions that are too complex for a</p><p>90<br>normal animal. Realizing that the NPC is not a com-<br>mon animal is very difficult, so the observer must <br>make a Defense Check versus OL Hard 7 to realize <br>who is really in front of them. <br>•<br>Connections: Criminals / Pacts and secrets / Money <br>and treasure / Information / Escape / Murder.  <br>The Smile in the Darkness: Offer protection to Father <br>Adrien so that he can continue to provide me with ex-<br>cellent absinthe / Kidnap Alizée, and then use her as a <br>bargaining chip with the Church.<br>The City of Pigs: Deceive both Bardolf Greed and the <br>Pig Heads, promising them help in exchange for deeds <br>to houses and factories / Establish an exclusive trade <br>in the prized flesh of the God Under the Mine.<br>A Frozen Reflection: Support Gerda and Kay’s deceit <br>and get into the business of Frozen Madness / Help all <br>gangs of criminals and outlaws by donating resources <br>to them to expand their network of followers.<br>In Y our Eyes, With Y our Feet: Helping Cinder main-tain control of the city and slowly making her my <br>pawn to exploit / Using the situation to have old busi-<br>ness enemies I have in the city killed, taking advantage <br>of the chaos created by the deaths of young girls.<br>The Wise Fairy  <br>Inspired by the Lady of the Lake from the Arthurian Myth<br>Once upon a time, there was a powerful fairy whose birth was <br>lost in the mists of time. Always driven by a kind heart and <br>an altruistic spirit, the fairy gave her help to those in need <br>without ever asking for anything in return. Soon, people from <br>every land came to the lake where the fairy lived to ask for <br>her help. No matter how much good she did, the pilgrims <br>kept coming. So the fairy decided to give some of her magic <br>to chosen people to travel the world and bring help to all who <br>needed it. The fairy forged objects of great power, raised little <br>orphans to become heroes, and taught her spells to wise old <br>men so they could help humanity. After more than a hundred <br>years of effort, the fairy found herself exhausted and almost <br>completely drained of power. Weary but content, she let her-<br>self fall to the bottom of her lake and fell into a restful sleep. <br>More than a decade passed before she awoke: she had slept <br>peacefully, knowing that her chosen ones had fulfilled their <br>mission to help others. But when she looked out at the world <br>again, she was dismayed by what she saw. The champions she <br>had armed, the heroes she had raised, and the wizards she <br>had taught had all abandoned the path of benevolence to pur-<br>sue selfish personal gain. Disappointed by the darkness <br>of the human soul , the fairy vowed that she would never <br>again use her power to do good, but only to increase her own <br>power and judge the world from the heights of her superiority.</p><p>91<br>Descriptor: I am the most powerful fairy that has ever walked this earth and I master the <br>magic of creation. Whatever I wish comes true, but I don’t like to flaunt my power without reason.    <br>4 Wounds<br>Opposition Level: Medium 5<br>Agenda 1: Find wizards and heroes and expose their weaknesses. <br>Agenda 2: Provide power at a dear price, as a reminder that good <br>for its own sake does not exist / Always cast a shadow over what <br>good is done, to show that darkness can never be completely erad-<br>icated. <br>Agenda 3: Use my power to weaken the Hunters and turn <br>them against my heroes / Separate those who use magic from <br>those who protect them, confronting each with their weak-<br>ness.<br>Agenda 4: Create an army of champions who yearn for <br>the destruction of the world / Create cursed objects and <br>rituals to send panic through humanity. <br>Gift - Water Fairy:  The Wise Fairy is a spirit of <br>great power born of water. As an additional action to <br>any Exchange, she can command the water around her <br>to perform one of these actions:<br>1. Hit a target up to thirty feet away with a water whip.<br>2. Move instantly to any place in her line of sight where <br>there is water.<br>3. Create a wave to send all nearby targets to the ground.</p><p>92<br>Gift - Nemesis:  See page 73. Sworn Enemies: Hunters <br>who use magic or act heroically.<br>Gift of Investiture - The Wand of Creation: The Wise <br>Fairy can give or take power from a person, creature, ob-<br>ject, or place. <br>1. If she takes away power: A person or creature loses <br>the use of all Gifts, including Dark Ego, for the rest of the <br>Scene. An object loses all special qualities for the rest of <br>the Scene, and if it has no special abilities, it simply turns <br>to ash. A Place loses one of its features, e.g. a stone house <br>becomes brittle.<br>2. If she donates power:  A person, creature, or object <br>receives a magical ability, which must be specified with a <br>Descriptor. The power is permanent, but the same recipient <br>cannot have more than one imparted power. A Place gains <br>a new property that must be detailed with a Descriptor, e.g. <br>a street can be flooded. <br>Minions:<br>Lancelot the Courteous  <br>Inspired by Lancelot of the Arthurian Myth <br>[Opponent)<br>Once upon a time, there was a young orphan who was raised <br>by the powerful Wise Fairy. His name was Lancelot, and as <br>he grew up, he became a bold and handsome young man, <br>gifted with all kinds of skills. The fairy intended Lancelot to <br>be an example of how a hero should behave, but in the young <br>man’s soul grew an unhealthy attraction to forbidden love, <br>which drove him to long for hearts that could not be his. And <br>so Lancelot served many nobles, each time ruining those he <br>was sworn to protect and consummating forbidden loves with <br>the wives, daughters, and sons of the lords to whom he had <br>sworn an oath. Heartbroken by his perversions, the Wise <br>Fairy called Lancelot back to her so that he could do no more <br>harm, but soon the boy’s amorous attentions turned to the <br>one he could call his own mother... <br>OL Medium 5 - 3 Wounds<br>Descriptor: I am a capable and bold man of action and <br>excel in every challenge I set myself to. I feel an unhealthy <br>attraction to those who have already given their hearts to an-<br>other love. <br>Agenda: To serve the Wise Fairy to the best of my ability <br>and to make her fall in love with me / To strive to conquer <br>any potential impossible love.<br>Gift - Courteous Knight:  Lancelot excels at any chal-<br>lenge, and when a Check is made for an action against him, <br>only an Outcome with a Cost can be obtained, regardless of <br>the total Successes. <br>Chosen Heroes<br>Subjects of great skill who serve the Wise Fairy to up-<br>hold justice. <br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a hero, always ready to fight for the Wise <br>Fairy. I have a one-sided view of the truth and only believe <br>what my lady says.    <br>Agenda: Fulfilling every wish of the Wise Fairy. <br>Gift - Heroic Soul:  The NPC will even ignore death to <br>satisfy the Wise Fairy. When they suffer their final Wound, <br>they can act one last time before leaving the battle. When <br>they enter the Scene, they can use a power granted by the <br>Wand of Creation, complete with a Descriptor created by <br>the Storyteller.</p><p>93<br>•<br>Connections: Magic items / Heroes / Justice / Good deeds <br>/ Chosen ones / Magic.<br>Of Flesh and Wood: Give Geppetto and Antonio Ciliegia a <br>chance to realize their ambitions / Help bring Azzurra back <br>to life and then make her a disciple.<br>A Soldier’s Duty: Enable Andersen’s gang to face Enar on <br>equal terms / Prove to the Sea Fairy that I am the best at <br>creating champions.<br>The King’s Awakening: Rebuild the old house in the lake <br>and give it to the Fairies, driving out all the pesky humans <br>/ Promise to choose a champion from among the island <br>knights; the honor will go to the one who eliminates the most <br>Hunters of the Order.<br>The Last Wish: Make Bastian live up to the hogwash he <br>tells (at least once) / Retrieve the three enchanted items and <br>bring Britta back to life to win her devotion. <br>The Mad Emperor  <br>Inspired By The Emperor’s New Clothes<br>Once upon a time, there was a vain Emperor who loved <br>to adorn himself with fine jewelry and dress in the latest <br>fashions. The Emperor had little interest in governing his <br>lands, leaving that task to his trusted advisors. This allowed <br>him to devote his full attention to festivals and receptions, <br>all good occasions to show off his best clothes. The Emperor <br>was not an evil person, he simply preferred to entrust tasks <br>to the most competent rather than the highest ranking. The <br>Emperor was also fond of the arts, and under his reign, all <br>people, even the poorest, had the opportunity to indulge <br>their passions, receiving substantial donations from the Em-<br>peror himself. Happy to be able to give beautiful creations <br>to the world, the Emperor did not notice that his advisors <br>and subjects soon began to take advantage of his generos-<br>ity. Everyone complimented the Emperor: “What graceful <br>movements His Majesty makes”, “What elegant clothes Your <br>Grace wears”... even when he was barely awake and wearing <br>only simple pajamas. Doubt began to creep into the naive <br>ruler’s heart, and when he summoned the kingdom’s trea-<br>surer, the harsh reality gave shape to the prison of deception <br>and self-satisfaction in which he had been caught. While the <br>Emperor was preoccupied with beauty and art, his minis-<br>ters, with the consent of all the citizens, had plundered every <br>resource. Disappointed by the lies and false compli-<br>ments, the Emperor summoned the general of the army <br>and his soldiers. All the townspeople and ministers were <br>herded into the main square, where, one by one, they were <br>blinded by the soldiers’ blades. Naked, with only the crown <br>on his head, the Emperor walked among the desperate and <br>suffering people and asked, “How do you find me today? Do <br>you like my elegant attire?” and everyone nodded, seeing <br>nothing, in fear of losing their lives as well as their eyes.</p><p>94<br>Descriptor: I am an elegant nobleman who many people <br>think is mad. The truth is that I can see things as they really <br>are, beyond all masks and illusions. <br>4 Wounds<br>Opposition Level: Medium 5<br>Agenda 1: Expose secrets and lies for what they really are.<br>Agenda 2: Make people conscious of the truth, even when <br>dangerous and unpleasant / Drive people mad, for only in <br>madness can one be rid of bad feelings.     <br>Agenda 3:  Act recklessly by doing things the Hunters <br>would never expect / Secretly follow the Hunters and drive <br>the world around them crazy.  <br>Agenda 4: Create an army of madmen ready to strike at <br>the Order and all that it stands for / Capture and make the <br>Hunters insane, causing them to turn on their own com-<br>rades.<br>Gift - The Seed of Madness: By mumbling gibberish, <br>the Mad Emperor can use his action to plant the seed of <br>madness in a target. The target will receive a Descriptor’s <br>Downside representing an obsession or irrational attitude <br>they will have to act out as much as possible. This effect <br>is automatic on Minor NPCs and discretionary on Main <br>NPCs, while a Hunter can make a Defense Check against <br>OL Hard 7 to close their mind at the last second. The De-<br>scriptor created lasts for the duration of the Scene: a Hunt-<br>er who has not marked the Downside by the end of the <br>Scene loses 3 Soma due to the effort required to resist the <br>madness raging in his mind.<br>Gift - Nemesis:  See page 73. Sworn Enemies: Hunters <br>with crazy traits or related to art.    <br>Gift of Investiture - The Crown of Illusion: Because <br>of the power of the Crown, the Emperor can use each of <br>these effects once per Scene. An effect that has already <br>been used in the Scene can only be reactivated at the cost <br>of 1 Wound.<br>1. Your Eyes are Mine: The eyes of all subjects who see <br>the Mad Emperor explode. All targets take 1 Wound, this <br>effect is automatic on Minor NPCs and discretionary on <br>Main NPCs, while a Hunter can make a Defense Check <br>against OL Hard 7 to look away at the last second. The <br>Wound inflicted by this effect is not fatal, but almost com-<br>pletely limits the sufferer’s ability to see.<br>2. Don’t Look at Me: The Mad Emperor becomes invis-<br>ible to the human eye. When he speaks or acts, all actions <br>taken against him suffer 2 Penalties. This effect ends when <br>the Mad Emperor takes 1 Wound or uses a Gift.</p><p>95<br>Minions:<br>The Mad Emperor does not like to have Minions around. <br>He will occasionally use subjects he has driven mad with <br>his words, but only for the time it takes to get them to per<br>-<br>form a specific task.<br>•<br>Connections: Madness / Truth and lies / Conspiracy / Lux-<br>ury / Art / Solitude.<br>Wonderbedlam: Force those recovering from madness to re-<br>lapse, keeping the level of madness in the world unchanged / <br>Make a deal with the Director to turn Wonder into a factory <br>of mad subjects.<br>OZena the Suffering and Desperate: Help Norman Hen-<br>kle retrieve the Compass Rose and wreak havoc / Punish all <br>those who judge the residents of the three villages - Yellow, <br>Red, and Smaragd.<br>I Will Stay with Y ou Always: Help the Swallow take revenge <br>and ridicule the regent of Prague / Give the prince freedom <br>to find his own way, probably one of death and destruction...<br>Journey of a Thousand and One Nights: Travel hidden in <br>Sinbad’s ship and complicate the Hunters’ lives by driving <br>those they meet mad / Save Sherazade from the Hunters, <br>then drive her mad so she becomes my queen.</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513737048,"modifiedTime":1781513737048,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"nemesis","collection":"Lost Stories","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","pages":"72-96"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513737048,"modifiedTime":1781513737048,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"9Bw5aJmcTU4bdEPR","name":"A Mother's Heart","pages":[{"_id":"biQq8xGbFvyMeYc1","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>A Mother's Heart</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> Lost Stories</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, pages 97-114.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/a-mothers-heart-p97-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513738163,"modifiedTime":1781513738163,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Z3TRHHY7ThtwB4We","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>A Mother's Heart - Setup</h2><p>96<br>Once upon a time...<br>Murcia, Spain, is a large city full of opportunities but also a chaotic place where it is easy <br>to get lost, with a destiny linked to the great Segura River that divides it in half. Over <br>the years, many children have disappeared without a trace into the city. Meanwhile, <br>discontent festers among the population, in part because of the lack of work for the <br>lower classes. The city is steeped in misery and it seems easy for the ill-intentioned to <br>kidnap children, neglected by adults who spend their day earning the little money they <br>can. However, a letter written by a woman named Maria Rosa has caught the Order’s <br>attention. Apparently, a dark threat hangs over Murcia, and the disappearances may <br>not be the work of ordinary scoundrels. A group of Hunters has been sent to the city, <br>incognito, to meet the author of the letter and unravel the mystery behind Murcia’s <br>disappearances. <br>A Mother’s Heart<br>A Scenario inspired by The Wolf and the Seven Young Goats (Grimm Brothers)<br>Safety keywords: Abduction / Suicide / Environmental disasters / Child abandonment / Child murder</p><p>97<br>The story that led us here...<br>Seven years ago in Murcia, there lived a woman <br>named Blanca who, after the death of her husband Beltran, <br>was left alone to raise her seven children in a small house <br>on the banks of the Segura River. Blanca would leave early <br>in the morning to go to work and would not return until <br>late in the afternoon. Every day, she told her children not <br>to open the door to strangers while she was gone. Blanca <br>was adamant, for Beltran had died precisely because of a <br>stranger he had naively welcomed into the house. Howev-<br>er, one year torrential rains drenched the city and caused <br>the Segura River to overflow its banks. Many tried to warn <br>Blanca’s children by knocking on the door and begging <br>them to come out, but the children did as their mother had <br>told them and stayed hidden in the cellar. The Segura River, <br>with the indifference of nature, flooded every house along <br>its banks. When Blanca returned home, she realized her <br>worst fears were true. Her beloved children had drowned, <br>hidden in the death trap she had told them not to leave. <br>Destroyed by grief, Blanca threw herself into the icy waters <br>of the Segura.<br>Exactly one year after the tragedy, Blanca has been reborn <br>as a ghost and wanders the city in search of her children. <br>Mad and with no memory of what happened, Blanca wants <br>to gather her beloved children to her. Each November, she <br>appears to kidnap seven children, drag them to the cellar of <br>her old house, and drown them. After her first appearances, <br>word spread among the people of Murcia that a ghost was <br>haunting the town, and the legend of Madre Blanca de las <br>Lágrimas (White Mother of Tears) began to grow.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters...<br>Neron Lobo is an exorcist priest who serves in an old Mon-<br>astery in the city. Always attentive to the needs of the most <br>vulnerable, Neron is actively involved in helping the many <br>working families who have little or nothing to feed their <br>children. After learning of Mother Blanca’s story, Neron <br>began to investigate and discovered to his dismay that, in <br>the past, seven children had gone missing each year when <br>the heavy rains hit the region in the month of November. <br>The young priest discovered that before disappearing, each <br>of the children had met a woman with a pale face and long <br>black hair, who had given them a loving kiss on the fore-<br>head. Neron became convinced that the spirit that took <br>the children manifested itself to them before taking them. <br>Gathering neighborhood rumors about a woman who fit <br>the ghost’s description, Neron located possible victims and <br>took them to hide in the old Monastery. The priest’s goal is <br>to keep the children safe until the end of the month when <br>the specter would cease to appear. However, his activities <br>aroused the suspicion of some of the locals, who, believing <br>that they were dealing with a gang of kidnappers, asked old <br>Maria Rosa to send a letter to the Order to put an end to <br>the criminal activity. No one knows that of Blanca’s seven <br>children, only one survived: Pepe, the youngest, had tak-<br>en refuge in the case of a large wall clock and was swept <br>away by the current that broke through the windows of the <br>house. Orphaned, Pepe took to the streets and now lives in <br>the Clock Tower of the abandoned San Felipe’s Church with <br>his gang, the Bats. The gang has seven members and serves <br>as Pepe’s attempt to rebuild his lost family.</p><p>98<br>Time Goes By<br>In this Scenario, the passage of time plays an important <br>role. Depending on when the Hunters intervene, they <br>will find a different situation in certain Places. Murcia is a <br>large city full of markets and workers, so moving from one <br>neighborhood to another can take several hours. Each time <br>the Hunters move to a different location, they may face the <br>Threat - City Chaos. Failing the Check means a significant <br>delay and arrival at a location in a later time slot.<br>There are three time slots: Morning, Afternoon, and <br>Evening. The three time slots represent the three periods <br>of the day and are not tied to a specific time. <br>Keep in mind that these rules serve as a guide and shouldn’t <br>hinder the narrative at your table. If the Hunters can find <br>a quick way to move thanks to their Gifts or help from an <br>NPC, they can ignore the obstacles caused by the City <br>Chaos. Similarly, resting to wait for a precise time slot al-<br>lows the Hunters to be present at a location for a specific <br>part of the day. <br>Threat – City Chaos<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: Murcia is a big city, full of narrow streets and <br>always full of busy people. <br>Gift - Time Waste:  By Failing a Check against this <br>Threat, the Hunters fall victim to the city’s confusion and <br>their trip takes longer than planned, so they arrive at a lat-<br>er time slot. A Positive Outcome means the Hunters arrive <br>at their goal destination one time slot after their departure <br>(e.g., leave in the Morning and arrive in the Afternoon). A <br>Failed Check delays the Hunter’s arrival by one time slot, so <br>that their journey takes two periods of the day (e.g., leave <br>in the Morning, arrive in the Evening). Failing the Check, <br>however, allows the Hunters to learn one of the rumors cir-<br>culating in the city. The Storyteller rolls a die or can choose <br>which rumor reaches the Hunters’ ears:<br>1: The Bats are a gang of street urchins who regularly steal <br>from the city’s merchants. The seven brats who make up <br>the gang live in the old Clock Tower, and though many res-<br>idents turn a blind eye to their misdeeds, it seems that some <br>nobles are planning to raid the Tower and put an <br>end to the gang.    <br>2: A new priest has recently arrived in the <br>city, but he does not seem to have taken up his <br>ministry in any of the churches open to the <br>faithful. The stranger is a burly, rude-looking <br>fellow who lives in an old Monastery that no <br>one has used in decades.<br>3: A dark rumor describes a ghost that <br>haunts Murcia during November. Parents <br>must be very careful with their children <br>because the Madre Blanca de las Lágrimas <br>wanders among the living in the guise of a</p><p>1<br>99<br>sad woman searching for her lost children. But beneath her <br>maternal appearance lurks the face of death. <br>4: The Segura River is a great resource for the city, but ev-<br>eryone fears a repeat of the disaster that occurred seven <br>years ago when heavy rains caused the river to overflow, <br>taking the lives of eight innocent people. The deaths includ-<br>ed a young mother named Blanca and her seven children, <br>all of whom drowned in their home.<br>5: Murcia’s slums are home to a disproportionate number <br>of people, but this is normal considering the work that the <br>city has to offer. In the chaos of the streets, it is easy to get <br>lost and almost every day a young person does not return <br>home. What happens to them is unknown, though it’s as-<br>sumed some decided to flee to try their luck elsewhere and <br>others attracted the interest of some criminal gang. <br>6: The Segura Riverbed is busy during the day, but at night <br>everyone is afraid to go near it. It is said that during No-<br>vember, a mother’s cry and children’s laughter can be heard <br>from the dark waters.</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513738164,"modifiedTime":1781513738164,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"qJQTP3Ws6kAXoxlU","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>A Mother's Heart - Scene 1</h2><p>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: Y ou have arrived in the city <br>as the sun is setting. The letter delivered to the Order men-<br>tions the Old Mill Tavern in the slums, so that is where you <br>have decided to begin your inquiries. As soon as you enter, <br>you are greeted by a quiet and comfortable atmosphere. <br>Among the patrons, you see only humble people warming <br>themselves with a bowl of onion soup to ward off the No-<br>vember chill. At the center table of the tavern sits an elderly <br>lady who seems to be waiting for you.<br>Place: The Old Mill Tavern, a small tavern made out of <br>what was once a real mill for grinding grain. <br>Time: The sun has set as the citizens return from a hard <br>day’s work.<br>Initial Situation: The elderly woman introduces herself <br>as Maria Rosa, the letter’s author. In the city, she cares for <br>many families that crowd the slums. Maria Rosa comes <br>from humble beginnings but was fortunate enough to mar-<br>ry a wealthy industrialist who allowed her to live in com-<br>fort. After a walk through the slums of Murcia, Maria Rosa <br>was struck by the plight of the city’s poor and decided to <br>provide comfort to those less fortunate by helping work-<br>ing families. Maria Rosa wrote to the Order because she <br>was concerned about the disappearance of children in re-<br>cent years, which began after the so-called Murcia Tragedy. <br>Maria Rosa will give the Hunters all the information she <br>knows, but she will ask them to leave her out of the inves-<br>tigation. After the interview is over, a room will be booked <br>for the Hunters at the Tavern so they can rest after their <br>trip. If the Hunters agree, they will begin the investigation <br>at dawn the next day and can find their first location before</p><p>100<br>the city wakes up, avoiding the Threat City Chaos and ar -<br>riving in the Morning time slot.<br>Information: Talking to Maria Rosa will provide the fol-<br>lowing information.<br> ◆ Most of Murcia’s population is made up of poor fam-<br>ilies who are constantly looking for work. As a result, <br>many children are neglected and crime thrives. <br> ◆ The Murcia Tragedy took place seven years ago when <br>an entire family was wiped out by the flooding of the <br>Segura. Blanca, a young worker who was the sole pro-<br>vider for her seven children, was at work when the <br>flood swept through her home. Some residents tried <br>to rescue the children, but they refused to go outside, <br>following their mother’s advice not to open the door to <br>strangers for any reason. When Blanca learned of her <br>children’s drowning, she committed suicide by throw-<br>ing herself into the River.<br> ◆ A year after these events, a number of children have <br>disappeared, and most superstitious people immedi-<br>ately point to Blanca’s spirit as the culprit. Maria Rosa, <br>on the other hand, fears that the reason for the disap-<br>pearances is much more mundane and has to do with <br>the poor living conditions in the slums, which drive <br>many young people directly into the hands of criminal <br>gangs. <br> ◆ A strange figure has been seen prowling the large River <br>Market, a commercial area in the low-lying neighbor -<br>hoods where the disappearances have occurred. The <br>suspicious man is very tall and stocky, with a thick <br>beard and pitch-black hair. Due to his sinister appear-<br>ance, no one has ever dared to approach him, but many <br>believe he may be a slave trader in the service of the <br>underworld.<br> ◆ Martyr’s Square, the largest of the lower districts, has <br>also been the site of several disappearances.<br> ◆ As for the underworld, a very aggressive gang is said to <br>reside in the Clock Tower of the old deconsecrated San <br>Felipe’s Church: the Gang of Bats.<br>Only if specifically asked will Maria Rosa tell the Hunters <br>the location of Blanca’s House. The place was abandoned <br>after the tragedy and no one had the courage to live there <br>anymore.<br>The Old Mill Tavern<br>Descriptor: A small tavern in an old mill. Simple food and <br>cheap wine are the main offerings. <br>Morning: There are few patrons, but by spending time <br>chatting, Hunters can learn a rumor (page 98). <br>Afternoon: In the hall, Rufio and Soledad (page 105) are <br>trying to scrape together some change with a music and <br>dance show.    <br>Evening: Alvaro, the old drunkard, tells everyone that <br>he saw a pale, ghostly woman wandering near the Segura <br>Riverbed during the afternoon hours. Alvaro says he fled <br>because when he met the woman’s gaze, his blood froze in <br>his veins with fear. No one seems to believe the old man, <br>but the drunkard stubbornly refuses to return to the place <br>where he saw the spirit, instead giving directions to the Se-<br>gura Riverbed for some change.</p><p>101<br>The River Market<br>Descriptor: The center of commerce for the poor of Murcia <br>is an expanse of tents, carts, and blankets where all kinds of <br>goods are displayed. <br>Morning: Father Neron can easily be seen chatting with <br>some of the children, asking them if they have seen a pale, <br>ghostly woman. After the discussion, he will walk away <br>holding the hands of those who have confirmed that they <br>have seen Blanca.    <br>Afternoon: Market activity is at its peak. By spending <br>time searching for information, Hunters can learn a rumor <br>(page 98).<br>Evening: A couple wanders among the closing stalls, <br>looking for their son who seems to have disappeared. It is <br>one of the boys Father Neron brought to the Monastery. <br>Father Neron Lobo<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am an exorcist priest who fights evil with the <br>power of faith. Because of my rough and wild appearance, I <br>often inspire fear, but I am a gentle and good-hearted person.    <br>Agenda: Save the children of Murcia from the threat of the <br>Madre Blanca de las Lágrimas.    <br>Gift - Exorcist Priest:  Father Neron has the ability to <br>perceive damned souls, which allows him to see and inter-act with all spiritual creatures. He can perform an exorcism <br>and inflict 1 Wound on a target with the word Spirit in its <br>profile. No Defense Check can be made against this attack.</p><p>102<br>Martyr’s Square<br>Descriptor: The largest square in the slums of Murcia. Va-<br>grants and the unemployed crowd here, waiting for the city’s <br>gendarmes to bring scraps of food discarded by the wealthy.    <br>Morning: Amidst the general hustle and bustle of people in <br>need, there are also many children running free without adult <br>supervision. Blanca walks through the crowd, approaches the <br>children, and asks them if they want a mother. To the first one <br>who answers yes, Blanca gives a kiss on the forehead, marking <br>them as the intended victim for the evening. <br>Afternoon: Square activity is at its peak. By spending <br>time searching for information, Hunters can learn a rumor <br>(page 98).<br>Evening: Blanca returns to the square to reunite with the <br>child she branded, taking advantage of the quiet of the eve-<br>ning to take them to the Segura Riverbed.<br>Madre Blanca de las <br>Lágrimas <br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a spirit without peace and I wander the city of Mur-<br>cia in search of my beloved children. My skin is cold and I feel no pain. <br>The lullaby I used to sing to my children is the only thing that gives me <br>a moment of peace. <br>Agenda: I will bring seven children into the water. They will become <br>my children.<br>Gift - Spirit of Tears: Blanca’s body does not follow the laws of life <br>and death, and until her heart is at peace, she cannot be permanent-<br>ly eliminated. When Blanca’s Wounds are all marked, she crumbles <br>to dust and her spirit returns to Blanca’s House, summoned by the <br>Mother’s Heart (page 107). At the beginning of the next Scene, Blan-<br>ca heals all her Wounds. She starts each Scene as Intangible . If she <br>acts to harm a living subject (inflicting 1 Wound, grabbing them, and <br>similar actions), she becomes Tangible for the rest of the Scene. Once <br>per Scene, Blanca can choose to become Intangible again.</p><p>103<br>Intangible: Blanca can move through solid objects and <br>living creatures. When she passes through a living being, <br>she forces the target to make a Defense Check. If the target <br>fails, they will burst into tears for 1 minute and be unable to <br>act. While crying, the target will see one of Blanca’s memo-<br>ries (see Gift - A Mother’s Love).<br>Tangible: Blanca can interact with the physical world like <br>a normal creature. Once per Scene, Blanca can cry and all <br>who hear her cry will suffer the following effect:<br> ◆ Minor NPC: Must run from Blanca as fast as possible <br>until they can no longer hear her cries. If unable to do <br>so, they will faint.<br> ◆ Main NPC/Dark Presence: Reduces their OL by one <br>while in Blanca’s presence. If they already have OL Easy <br>3, they suffer the effect of Minor NPCs.<br> ◆ Hunter: Loses 2 Soma. If they cannot pay this cost, <br>they suffer 1 Wound. <br>Gift - A Mother’s Love: Blanca can only be permanent-<br>ly eliminated by confronting her with her terrible deeds, <br>by awakening the love she feels for her son Pepe, and by <br>making her realize that the young man has created a new <br>family for himself thanks to the Bats. Alternatively, it is <br>necessary to destroy the Mother’s Heart in Blanca’s House.  <br>If Blanca is Intangible and passes through a living being, <br>roll a die or choose which memory is shared:<br>1: Blanca embraces two newborns. They are twins and she <br>looks at them with love. She calls them by their names: Abel <br>and Annita.<br>2: Blanca prepares hot soup and gives a bowl to a child <br>huddled in the cold under a large blanket. She approached <br>him and said softly, “Cristóbal, the soup is ready. ”<br>3: Blanca returns home with a book in her arms. As soon as <br>she opens the door, a little girl hangs around her neck. “Did <br>you get it, Mommy?” she asks impatiently. “Of course, my <br>little Lola. Here is your new book. ” The little girl’s eyes light <br>up as she takes the book. <br>4: Blanca finishes sewing an old shoe while a barefoot child <br>stares at her. “I’m sorry, mama, if I broke the shoe, ” the child <br>says in a soft voice. Blanca smiles and strokes her son’s head, <br>“Don’t worry, Ricardo, everything will be fine. ” <br>5: Blanca teaches a young girl the art of sewing. The young <br>girl tries hard but ends up pricking her finger. She bursts <br>into tears, but Blanca takes her injured finger and kisses it. <br>“Don’t cry, Julia, ” she tells her lovingly. “The pain will pass <br>before you know it, but the knowledge that you felt it will <br>make you stronger. ”<br>6: Blanca is running down the street, holding the hand of <br>a little boy who is jumping up and down, when suddenly <br>the little boy stumbles and falls, injuring his knee. The child <br>bursts into tears, so Blanca kisses him on the forehead and <br>embraces him. “It’s nothing, little Pepe, ” she reassures him.<br>Gift - My Beloved Children:  Once per Scene, Blanca <br>can summon 6 Lost Children (page 105) to appear at her <br>side.</p><p>104<br>The Clock Tower<br>Descriptor: A crumbling tower with a large clock that no <br>longer works. The building is part of the Church of San Felipe, <br>now abandoned and devastated by the Segura flood.<br>Morning: The Gang of Bats is out to steal, leaving only <br>Benedicto and Inez to guard the cave.    <br>Afternoon: The Gang is in the Clock Tower except for Ru-<br>fio and Soledad who are at the Old Mill Tavern.<br>Evening: The entire Gang is present in the den. <br>Pepe<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am the leader of the Bats and responsible for the sur -<br>vival of my companions. I am brave and skilled with knives, and I like <br>to whistle my mother’s lullaby, a happy memory from my childhood.<br>Agenda: Robbing the people of Murcia as revenge for their indiffer -<br>ence to those who have nothing / Taking care of the Bats, whom I con-<br>sider my new family.    <br>Gift - Big Brother:  Pepe will not allow anyone to harm his com-<br>rades. Against a target that threatens a Bat, Pepe inflicts 1 Additional <br>Wound. All Bats increase their OL by 1 when Pepe is present. <br>The Gang of Bats<br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are street urchins, used to stealing to survive. <br>With Pepe at our head, we are not afraid of anything.      <br>Agenda: Help Pepe make the Gang prosper / Help Pepe overcome <br>the trauma of his family’s death. <br>Gift - United Gang: Each member of the Gang possesses a trait <br>that is identified by an addition to their Descriptor. <br>Benedicto: I am the oldest in the Gang, and my strength is feared <br>even by adults.<br>Carmina: I am agile, fast, and a good climber. <br>Felix: I am the smallest of the Gang and can squeeze into any hole. <br>Inez: I am the smartest of the Gang and have read many books.</p><p>105<br>Rufio: I am a big talker and know everyone in town. <br>Soledad: I am a good dancer and know how to draw atten-<br>tion to myself. <br>The Segura Riverbed<br>Descriptor: The river that runs through all of Murcia <br>brings many job opportunities to the poor, but also the threat <br>of its murky, deep waters.    <br>Morning: The River is crossed by many boats, and plenty <br>of people work along its riverbed. By spending time talking <br>to the townspeople, Hunters can learn a rumor (page 98). <br>Afternoon: Blanca wanders the Segura River, waiting for <br>nightfall to return to the child she branded at the Martyr’s <br>Plaza. When the spirit is cornered, it throws itself into the <br>waters of the River to disappear. <br>Evening: Staying too long near the water of the River will <br>attract 6 Lost Children. <br>Lost Children<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are restless spirits spawned by Blanca’s <br>madness. We hate living things and try to take them with us <br>to the waters of the Segura River to drown them, just as we <br>were. <br>Agenda: Choose a target and drag it to the Segura River to <br>drown it.    <br>Gift - Suffering Spirit: As an action, a Lost Child will <br>always attempt to snatch a target. In the event of a Defense <br>Check Failure, apply the result based on where the action <br>takes place.<br>Within 100 feet of the Segura River:  The Lost <br>Child jumps into the river, taking the target with it. <br>The Lost Child suffers 1 Wound while the target is in <br>the depths of the River, see Threat - The Segura River <br>on page 106.<br>Anywhere else: The Lost Child envelops the target</p><p>106<br>and turns into river water, suffering 1 Wound. The tar<br>-get gains 3 Drowning Tokens. The Storyteller gains 3 <br>Drowning Tokens, which can be spent each time the <br>Storyteller wishes to apply one of the following effects <br>to the target. The same Lost Child cannot generate <br>more than 3 Drowning Tokens to be spent on a single <br>target.<br>1. Confer 1 Penalty on a Check.<br>2. Automatically drop the target into the Segura <br>River if the action takes place near its banks.<br>3. Force the target to pay 1 Soma to activate one of <br>their Gifts, with the exception of the Dark Ego. <br>Threat - The Segura River<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: Strong currents and icy waters make the Segu-<br>ra River dangerous even for experienced swimmers. <br>The Monastery<br>Descriptor: An old monastery that once housed a group <br>of monks. Now only a few rooms and the large courtyard are <br>usable.<br>Morning: From the Monastery garden comes the cackle <br>of children playing. With them is Sister Esperanza, a nun <br>who helps Father Neron keep the little marked ones safe <br>from Blanca’s sight. There are a total of six children in the <br>Monastery (all reported missing from the River Market). <br>When questioned, Sister Esperanza will not hesitate to <br>stand up for Father Neron. The nun will say that the priest <br>wanders around the Market in the morning, while in the af-<br>ternoon he worries about finding the children’s families to <br>tell them that their little ones are safe under the protection <br>of the Church. Father Neron makes donations to the chil-<br>dren’s families to ensure their cooperation, with the prom-<br>ise of a reunion on the first day of December. <br>Afternoon: Father Neron is present as he prepares dona-<br>tions for the families of the children who live in the Monas-<br>tery. Sister Esperanza takes care of the children.<br>Evening: Father Neron is the small library of the Monas-<br>tery, studying books on exorcism. Sister Esperanza sleeps <br>in the underground rooms with the children.<br>Sister Esperanza<br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a young nun who has dedicated her life <br>to helping others. I follow Father Neron in his crusade against <br>evil and am willing to give my life to save the innocent.    <br>Agenda: Helping Father Neron and taking care of the chil-<br>dren in the Monastery.</p><p>107<br>Blanca’s House<br>Descriptor: A destroyed house that still bears the marks of <br>the Segura River’s fury. In the wood of the door and its frame <br>are religious symbols, roughly carved by the inhabitants in a <br>superstitious attempt to keep evil away.    <br>Morning, Afternoon, and Evening: The House is un-<br>occupied, but a search of the interior will reveal the bare <br>footprints of a woman who appears to be descending into <br>the basement, which is impractical as it appears to be com-<br>pletely underwater. Diving in is extremely risky and acti-<br>vates the Dark Water Threat. The layer of water actually <br>hides the Dungeon from prying eyes: once the Threat is <br>overcome, the Dungeon containing the Mother’s Heart can <br>be accessed. <br>Threat - Dark Waters<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: Frigid waters, animated by Blanca’s resent-<br>ment of all living things, form a barrier to keep the Mother’s <br>Heart safe.<br>Gift - The Frigid Embrace of Death:  When a subject <br>plunges into the Dark Waters, they are attacked by the <br>water, which will try to enter their nose and mouth. If the <br>subject fails the Defense Check, they suffer 1 Wound from <br>the cold and lack of oxygen and become stuck in the water, <br>unable to move. A successful Defense Check is required to <br>get free and return to the surface or to descend into the <br>Dungeon. Singing the lullaby that Pepe knows causes the <br>waters to recede for one hour, allowing safe access. <br>The Dungeon<br>Descriptor: A bare dungeon where the remains of six small <br>bodies are huddled together. In the center of the room, a mass <br>of plants, seabed debris, and animal bodies are formed into a <br>heart that pulsates with malevolent energy.<br>Morning, Afternoon, and Evening:  The Mother’s <br>Heart is the fulcrum that gives life to Blanca’s spirit and to <br>destroy it is to put an end to Mother Blanca de las Lágrimas.<br>The Mother’s Heart<br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPC (6 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: An agglomeration of floating garbage, pulsat-<br>ing like a rotting heart. <br>Gift - A Mother’s Fury:  As soon as the Heart suffers <br>1 Wound, Blanca will appear to defend it. The call of the <br>Heart cannot be prevented in any way.</p><p>108<br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the Mother <br>Heart Scenario and can be acquired once conditions are <br>met. A Hunter can only acquire one Scenario Gift. If they <br>buy a new one during an Interlude, they will have to forgo <br>the previous one.<br>Exorcism<br>Requirement: To be taught the rites of exorcism <br>by Father Neron Lobo. <br>Y ou are able to sense damned souls, and this <br>allows you to see and interact with all spiritu-<br>al beings. The Storyteller will alert you when <br>a spirit is present, a feeling that manifests as a <br>chill down your spine. Y ou can spend 1 Soma <br>to open your mind to the spirits. If you do, you <br>can communicate with them and perform ritu-<br>als and prayers to harm them for the rest of the <br>Scene.<br>City Guide<br>Requirement: Succeed at least twice against <br>the Threat - City Chaos.   <br>Y ou have figured out how to navigate the alleys <br>of the chaotic city of Murcia. When you move <br>from one Place to another, you automatically <br>get a Standard Outcome on Threat Checks for <br>City Chaos.</p><p>109<br>Scenario Events<br>In this Scenario, there are six Events. As Storyteller, feel free <br>to create new ones in response to the actions of the Hunt-<br>ers.<br>If Blanca sees Pepe or someone describes the <br>boy to her:  she will recognize her lost son and become <br>obsessed with him, and the spirit’s only goal will be to take <br>Pepe to the basement to kill him.<br>If the Hunters arrive at the Clock Tower on the <br>Morning of the second day:  they will find the gen-<br>darmes capturing Inez and Benedicto. <br>If the Hunters arrive at the Clock Tower after the <br>Afternoon on the second day: the gendarmes have cap-<br>tured Benedicto and Inez. Pepe’s only goal will be to free his <br>comrades, but it will be obvious to the Hunters that the Bats <br>are no match for the city guards. <br>If the Hunters attempt to capture Father Neron:  <br>the priest will try to escape and seek refuge in the Monas-<br>tery. If captured, he will try to use his position to obtain his <br>release. Only when he has no other option will he speak of <br>his doubts about the Madre Blanca de las Lágrimas and the <br>threat she poses to Murcia. <br>If the Hunters confront Blanca in public:  panic will <br>break out in the city and everyone will start talking about <br>the existence of the Madre Blanca de las Lágrimas. From <br>that moment on, the chaos in the city will increase and the <br>Hunters will be slowed by citizens asking for their help. In-<br>crease the OL of the Threat - City Chaos by 1. <br>Whether the Hunters describe Blanca to Pepe or <br>the boy sees the spirit directly:  the young man will <br>fall to his knees in tears, overwhelmed by memories. When <br>he calms down, he will tell of the end of his family and how <br>he was saved. Pepe will teach the Hunters the lullaby he <br>always whistles, telling them that the tune is of great value <br>to Blanca.</p><p>1<br>2a<br>110<br>A Mother’s Heart in Scenes</p><p>FIRST SCENE – The Old Mill <br>Tavern<br>It is the same one you find on page 99. Talking to Ma-<br>ria Rosa will reveal the information provided in that Scene <br>to the Hunters, except for the information about the Bat <br>Gang, the Clock Tower, and the location of Blanca’s House.  <br>Note: Since the Scene Tree does not provide the freedom <br>of action of the normal Scenario, Hunters do not have to <br>face the Threat - City Chaos every time they move from one <br>area to another.  <br>End of Scene: The next morning the Hunters can investi-<br>gate the River Market, go to SECOND SCENE OPTION A <br>- The River Market, or the Martyr’s Square, go to SECOND <br>SCENE OPTION B - Martyr’s Square.</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513738165,"modifiedTime":1781513738165,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Dyq9DOwJ2I2LkD7H","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>A Mother's Heart - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE OPTION A  <br>– The River Market<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  The market in the slums <br>of Murcia is a crossroads of makeshift vendors and hawk-<br>ers who crowd the roadsides trying to attract the attention <br>of passersby. Lost in the crowd is a group of children running <br>barefoot behind the horse of a wealthy nobleman, haughtily <br>passing between the stalls. Chaos reigns, and no one seems <br>to be paying the slightest attention to anything but their own <br>interests. <br>Place: The chaotic River Market that stretches for more <br>than a mile. <br>Time: Early morning, while the people of Murcia are al-<br>ready in full swing. <br>Information: Father Neron can easily be seen talking to <br>some children, asking them if they have seen a pale, ghostly <br>woman. After talking to the children, he will leave, followed <br>by a child. If the Hunters approach, the priest will try to run <br>away and, once caught, will try to use his position as a cleric <br>as a shield. After several hesitations (and at least one suc-<br>cessful Position Check to convince Father Neron of their <br>good intentions), the priest will tell the Hunters what he <br>is doing to save the children of Murcia. Neron will say that <br>one of the little ones at the market told him a strange story. <br>It seems that the leader of the Bats often brags about sur -<br>viving the flood that hit Murcia seven years ago. This date <br>corresponds to the first appearances of the Madre Blanca de <br>las Lágrimas, and Neron wants to question the Bats to see if <br>there is any connection. <br>End of Scene: The Hunters accompany Father Neron to <br>meet the Bats, go to SCENE THREE - The Clock Tower.</p><p>2b<br>111</p><p>SECOND SCENE OPTION B <br>– Martyr’s Square<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You arrive at the larg-<br>est slum square in Murcia. Ragamuffins and the unemployed <br>huddle together, waiting for the city’s gendarmes to bring <br>some leftover food from the wealthy uptowners. Through the <br>confusion and shouting, you catch a glimpse of a pale woman <br>shuffling slowly through the crowd. Her eyes are swollen with <br>tears, and she has the expression of someone who has seen <br>death up close. A few children pass by, and the somber figure <br>beckons them to her for a moment, a sad smile on her face.<br>Place: The large Martyr’s Square where all the city’s poor <br>flock. <br>Time: Early morning, the sun shines high in the sky but <br>fails to dispel the November chill.<br>Information: If the Hunters simply observe Blanca, she <br>will kiss a child on the forehead and then walk off into the <br>crowd, after which the Hunters will see her vanish as if she <br>were a ghost. On the other hand, if the Hunters approach <br>Blanca, the ghost will attempt to escape, and once cornered, <br>she will use her power to walk through the walls of houses <br>and shake them off her trail. If the Hunters trap her, Blan-<br>ca will summon the Lost Children before disappearing. <br>However the encounter with Blanca is resolved, the Hunt-<br>ers will be approached by the boy Blanca kissed: he is Felix, <br>the youngest of the Gang of    Bats. The little boy will say <br>that Pepe told him to stay away from a strange lady who <br>looks like a ghost, but without realizing it, he ended up <br>right in her presence. Now Felix is very afraid because the <br>lips of the woman who kissed him were as cold as those of <br>a dead person. Felix will gladly accept an offer of help from <br>the Hunters. <br>End of Scene: The Hunters follow Felix to meet Pepe, go <br>to SCENE THREE - The Clock Tower.</p><p>3<br>4<br>112</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513738165,"modifiedTime":1781513738165,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"JDwYGZgvkNwF34DJ","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>A Mother's Heart - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE – The Clock <br>Tower<br>This Scene varies depending on who accompanies the <br>Hunters to the Clock Tower.<br>If the Hunters arrive with Father Neron, read <br>aloud to the Hunters: Father Neron leads you to a large, <br>abandoned church and tells you that when the city was <br>founded, this was the main place of worship. Murcia’s steady <br>growth, however, soon relegated the church of San Felipe to a <br>mere Clock Tower. When that stopped working, the mainte-<br>nance expense led the Curia to close the entire building. <br>If the Hunters arrive with Felix, read aloud to the <br>Hunters: Felix leads you to a large abandoned church and <br>tells you that this is the headquarters of the Gang of Bats. <br>Pepe is the undisputed leader of the gang, and it is because <br>of him that everyone can live free from the strict rules of the <br>town’s adults. <br>Place: The Clock Tower of San Felipe’s Church. <br>Time: In the afternoon, clouds have covered the sunshine <br>and there is a whiff of rain. <br>Information: Pepe will treat all visitors badly and scold <br>Felix when he is with them. The young man seems very <br>anxious and is unwilling to trust adults. If the Hunters are <br>aggressive, the Gang of Bats will not hesitate to get physical, <br>while a more diplomatic approach may lead to a brief <br>discussion. At Blanca’s description, Pepe will fall into a crying <br>fit and tell his sad story. The boy will then tell the Hunters that <br>the first year after his family’s death, he returned to his old <br>home, where Blanca’s ghost tried to pull him into the river. <br>Pepe will then reveal the location of Blanca’s house.  <br>If the Hunters can handle the situation without getting <br>physical, Pepe will teach them his mother’s lullaby, <br>saying that when he encountered the ghost of his <br>mother, the song saved him from being captured.  <br>At the end of the Scene, Father Neron (if not present) <br>or Sister Esperanza will arrive to seek help. Blanca has <br>appeared at the Monastery to kidnap the children that <br>Father Neron was trying to protect. Pepe will be terrified <br>to face his mother’s ghost and will ask the Hunters to do it <br>for him. <br>End of Scene: The Hunters rush to the Monastery to res-<br>cue the children from Blanca’s clutches, unaware that it is a <br>trap, go to SCENE FOUR - The Monastery.</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513738165,"modifiedTime":1781513738165,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"CAhyXGLxaDxfEJfm","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>A Mother's Heart - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE – The Monastery<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  As you rush to the gate of <br>the Monastery, you can clearly hear the cries of the children <br>inside. Y ou then rush into the courtyard, and before you are <br>ghostly-faced children trying to drag others away. <br>Place: The abandoned Monastery that houses the children <br>protected by Father Neron. <br>Time: The sun is setting. <br>Information: There are 6 Lost Children trying to take the <br>children from the Monastery. In reality, the ghosts are stall-<br>ing to distract Father Neron and the Hunters while Blanca <br>goes to the Clock Tower to kidnap Pepe. The Lost Children <br>fight to the last. At the end of the battle, Felix arrives, dazed, <br>and tells them that Madre Blanca de las Lágrimas has ap-<br>peared and kidnapped Pepe.</p><p>5<br>113<br>End of Scene: The Hunters must run to Blanca’s House to <br>stop the spirit before it kills Pepe, go to FIFTH SCENE - A <br>Mother’s Heart.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513738165,"modifiedTime":1781513738165,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"OLXq2LLPE4ABsELC","name":"Scene 5","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>A Mother's Heart - Scene 5</h2><p>FIFTH SCENE – A Mother’s <br>Heart<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: Y ou find the broken door in <br>the small house that was once the safe haven of Pepe’s fam-<br>ily. A faint cry comes from the basement, but it is not easy <br>to get to, as the river water is quickly flowing into the house.<br>Place: Blanca’s House, which floods very quickly.<br>Time: The sun has now set, while a heavy rain has begun <br>to fall on Murcia. <br>Information: To access the Dungeon, it is necessary to <br>go through the basement and face the Dark Water Threat <br>(page 107), unless the Hunters have learned the lullaby <br>from Pepe. In the Dungeon, the Hunters find Pepe kneeling <br>in shock, while Blanca promises that he will soon be reunit-<br>ed with his beloved brothers. The Mother’s Heart throbs <br>rottenly, punctuating the passage of time. <br>End of Scene:  If the Hunters succeed in rescuing Pepe <br>and destroying the Mother’s Heart, they will be able to give <br>peace to Blanca’s damned soul.</p>"},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513738166,"modifiedTime":1781513738166,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"a-mothers-heart","collection":"Lost Stories","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","pages":"97-114"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513738166,"modifiedTime":1781513738166,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"k1Dbrd0Ac2a6kBts","name":"Nikola's Pledge","pages":[{"_id":"eijqbaYPnKCv5ZdR","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>Nikola's Pledge</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> Lost Stories</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, pages 115-130.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/nikolas-pledge-p115-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513739249,"modifiedTime":1781513739249,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"JUAKMrJbTbxpBuTm","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Nikola's Pledge - Setup</h2><p>114<br>Nikola’s Pledge<br> <br>A Scenario inspired by the story of Santa Claus<br> <br>Safety Keywords: Kidnapping / Gore / Manipulation<br> <br>Once upon a time...<br>The Hunters arrive in the far north, in the village of Rovaniemi, summoned by a letter from a young <br>couple, Tommi and Jutta, who have recently arrived there. As described in the letter, the community of <br>prospectors who founded the village has always been supported by a wealthy craftsman named Nikola <br>Lupei. After years of apparent tranquility, Nikola has begun asking for a pledge and donation in return <br>for his patronage. Gold and valuables can be given as gifts, which each family must leave at their door on <br>the night of December 24 as a token of gratitude. At the first request, however, some ignored the demand. <br>The next morning, they each discovered that one of their loved ones was missing. <br>No one believed it was a coincidence. The furious village elders went to Nikola to make him answer for <br>his actions, only to return and declare that the craftsman was in no way connected to the disappearances. <br>From that moment on, however, the villagers accepted the tribute had to be paid, and no one disappeared <br>anymore. Tommi and Jutta ask the Order for help, because they fear for the life of little Lari, their eldest <br>son, since December 24th is approaching and they have nothing to pay for their own tribute. The Hunters <br>then arrive in the remote village of gold prospectors, on the edge of civilization, knowing that they are the <br>only link between the law of the civilized world and the harsh rules of the cold north...</p><p>115<br>The story that led us here...<br>Nikola Lupei was born and raised in the comfort <br>of a noble family in Walachia. Always in poor health, but <br>extremely intelligent, Nikola devoted himself to the study <br>of esoteric arts from an early age. After years of research, <br>Nikola found a mysterious patron willing to support him <br>and moved into the old man’s mansion to study his im-<br>mense collection of books. The old man later revealed <br>himself to be an ancient vampire and passed his curse <br>on to Nikola one bloody night. Rejuvenated in body but <br>tired in mind, Nikola fled Wallachia in search of a safe <br>place to live in peace and quiet. The Village of Rovaniemi <br>turned out to be just right, far from civilization and with <br>needy families looking for help to build their prospecting <br>community. Using his powers, Nikola allowed the village <br>to flourish. In his mansion, he built a workshop where <br>he could devote himself to making toys, a great passion <br>of his since childhood. Safe from prying eyes, Nikola has <br>always kept his vampirism hidden, feeding on the many <br>animals in the forest around Rovaniemi. Three years ago, <br>however, things changed drastically: while on a quest <br>for magical artifacts, Nikola came into possession of the <br>Badalisk, a powerful bag-shaped creature. The Badalisk, <br>cornering Nikola, forced the vampire to feed him pieces <br>of his body. But animal blood is less powerful than hu-<br>man blood, so Nikola’s body could not regenerate quick-<br>ly enough to feed the Badalisk. Desperate, Nikola began <br>to demand a pledge of valuables from the people of Ro-<br>vaniemi, knowing that many would find it difficult to pay. <br>With that justification, Nikola used his powers to infil-<br>trate the homes of those unable to pay tribute, kidnapping <br>a family member and making them his servants through <br>the Rite of Servitude. His new servants helped Nikola kid-<br>nap poor travelers passing through. Thanks to the riches he <br>accumulated from the tribute, he lured wealthy merchants <br>seeking good deals to the village. All the innocent souls <br>went to feed to the insatiable Badalisk...<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters...<br>As it feeds, the Badalisk becomes more powerful and its <br>hunger grows month by month. Desperate, Nikola tries <br>every possible way to satiate the demon and preserve the <br>lives of the villagers of Rovaniemi. Every night, the vampire <br>meets with Asmo, one of the Village Elders, who keeps him <br>informed of events. Thanks to Asmo, Nikola learned of the <br>arrival of the Order’s first Hunter and sent his reindeer to <br>hunt them down. After a long battle, the Hunter has taken <br>refuge in the old hunting lodge east of the Village and is <br>waiting for reinforcements. Nikola plans to eliminate the <br>Hunter himself, convinced that a subject of such power <br>would sate the Badalisk for a long time.<br>Note: In this Scenario, a Hunter from the Order has al-<br>ready been sent out before the Players’ group arrives. The <br>Storyteller is free to choose which Hunter this is, to best fit <br>with their Campaign. The Hunter is effectively an NPC un-<br>der the Storyteller’s control. The choice of Hunter can affect <br>the events of the Scenario and create interesting situations. <br>For example, if it is the Immortal, the Hunters may find <br>only his head in the hut, while the body is scattered in the <br>forest, torn apart by the Reindeer. Retrieving the body parts <br>would then become an interesting situation to play out.</p><p>116<br>Note: In this Scenario, the Badalisk has eaten a Treasure of <br>the Order, providing it a source of great power. The Story-<br>teller must decide which Treasure it is, fitting it into their <br>Campaign. If the Scenario is solved successfully, the Hunt-<br>ers will be able to retrieve it.</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513739250,"modifiedTime":1781513739250,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"itFYZ2VFn5YeM47k","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Nikola's Pledge - Scene 1</h2><p>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  The sun is setting as you <br>finally see smoke billowing from the chimneys of the small <br>town of Rovaniemi. After more than a week of traveling <br>through impassable forests and snow-covered plains, you <br>can’t wait to shed your heavy coats and warm yourself by a <br>fire. Instead, you are greeted by locked doors and suspicious <br>looks from behind windows. It seems that you are not wel-<br>come in the village. A voice attracts your attention, a young <br>man beckons you to his house and when you approach he <br>introduces himself as Tommi, the one who sent the letter to <br>the Order with his wife Jutta. <br>Place: Tommi and Jutta’s little house. <br>Time: The sun is setting as the icy wind bangs on closed <br>windows, announcing the arrival of another snowstorm.<br>Initial Situation: The hosts thank the Hunters for com-<br>ing to their rescue, while Tommi rekindles the fireplace, <br>where a pot of tempting stew is simmering. A loving Jutta <br>cradles a baby sleeping peacefully in her arms.<br>Information: From the interview with Tommi and Jutta, <br>the Hunters can get a lot of information.<br> ◆ Nikola Lupei is considered the most important man in <br>the area. He lives in a large mansion a day’s walk from <br>Rovaniemi and is known as a benefactor who has con-<br>tributed to the growth of the Village. Lupei is a very ec-<br>centric individual who always wears an eye-catching red <br>robe with large slippers to match. He has an emaciated, <br>pale face with the large dark circles of someone who <br>never seems to sleep well. Despite his ghostly appear -<br>ance, he is a gentle man who is always kind to everyone.<br> ◆ The Village is run by a group of six elders who meet in <br>the small town hall during the day. The elders talked to <br>Nikola after the first night of the pledge, but after the <br>meeting they kept a mysterious silence, urging everyone <br>to pay the pledge without fuss. In their opinion, Nikola <br>had nothing to do with the disappearances.    <br> ◆ After the first pledge, the Village always paid, even at <br>great sacrifice. Coincidentally, no one else has disap-<br>peared since then.    <br> ◆ A week ago, a Hunter from the Order arrived in the Vil-<br>lage. Tommi and Jutta met them briefly, but the next day <br>the Hunter left for Nikola’s estate, never to return. Jutta <br>overheard a discussion among the elders and is sure that <br>the Hunter received information from one of them, but <br>she could not say who. Tommi and Jutta can describe <br>the Hunter in broad strokes, given their short meeting.<br> ◆ Tommi and Jutta can describe all six elders, giving their <br>names and the most common information from their <br>Descriptors.<br> ◆ Today is December 15th, so there are only nine days left <br>until the next pledge payment.</p><p>117<br>Tommi and Jutta<br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPCs (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are two young prospectors, made tough by <br>a life of hardship and strong by the love that unites us.<br>Agenda: To save our son Lari from that absurd pledge.<br>The Village of Rovaniemi<br>Descriptor: A small town of prospectors where everyone <br>knows everyone else.<br>Information: The streets and the small square are littered <br>with gold panning equipment, carts, and baskets for sort-<br>ing. The numerous wrought-iron plaques remind everyone <br>that these are all donations from Nikola Lupei. The villagers <br>are shy towards the Hunters, avoiding any contact. <br>Rovaniemi Town Hall<br>Descriptor: One of the few brick houses in the village. The <br>imposing wrought iron door has a large plaque engraved with <br>words of gratitude for the town’s benefactor, Nikola Lupei.<br>Whenever the Hunters visit the Town Hall, they will find 2 <br>Village Elders. The Storyteller can decide which ones they <br>are, or roll a die to determine. The following information <br>can be obtained from all elders:<br> ◆ A week ago, a Hunter from the Order arrived, asked <br>a few questions, then left for Nikola’s estate and was <br>never seen again. <br> ◆ Nikola rarely comes to the Village now and seems to be <br>very busy. The villagers never go to him spontaneously, <br>but wait for him to show up.<br>It is possible to meet all the elders, but it takes time: for <br>every hour the Hunters spend in the Village, they can meet <br>one elder.  <br>The Village Elders  <br>1: Asmo<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am the leader of the elders, and my word is <br>final when there is disagreement.<br>Agenda: To serve Nikola by reporting everything that hap-<br>pens in the village / To keep outside attention away from Ro-<br>vaniemi and prevent Nikola from being forced to harm the <br>villagers.</p><p>118<br>Information: Asmo sings Nikola’s praises, calling him <br>the benefactor of Rovaniemi. Rumors that he is a kidnapper <br>are false, and the people who are no longer in the Village <br>are fine and have voluntarily moved to work in Nikola’s toy <br>factory.<br>2: Elna<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a good weaver and know many legends <br>of the area.<br>Agenda: I want my daughter Jaana to come home, but <br>without openly siding against Nikola Lupei.<br>Information: Elna’s family is among those who did not <br>initially pay the pledge, and her daughter Jaana has disap-<br>peared. The old woman will tell you that her daughter is <br>well and has settled in Nikola’s mansion, where she works <br>as a toy factory worker. When questioned about the night <br>of the disappearance, Elna will say that no one noticed any-<br>thing and that there were no signs of forced entry. Talking <br>to Elna, it will become clear that she misses her daughter <br>very much. <br>3: Mikko<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (1 <br>Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am an accountant who is in <br>charge of the gold trade between the village <br>and the merchants. <br>Agenda: Make the village prosperous and <br>earn good money. <br>Information: Mikko is the newest addition <br>to the group of elders and was not present during the first <br>night of the pledge. He does not believe in rumors and sees <br>the “kidnapped” people simply as workers who choose to <br>stay in the comfort of Nikola’s warm and cozy mansion. <br>However, Mikko noticed that some of the traders missed <br>the appointment to load the gold and he has not heard <br>from them. The old man has noted everything in his re-<br>cords, where it can be seen that the missed appointments <br>and disappearances of the merchants occur on a regular ba-<br>sis. However, the old accountant is extremely jealous of his <br>work and will not share the records with anyone. <br>4: Katri<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a good hunter, but now my venerable age <br>keeps me from hunting. I know the area around Rovaniemi <br>very well.<br>Agenda: Defend the village of Rovaniemi from any possible <br>threat from the wilderness.    <br>Information: Katri leads the hunters in the Village, and <br>lately she has been told that the presence of animals has <br>decreased dramatically. There are several hunting lodges <br>in the forest around the Village, where one <br>can find shelter. The area where Nikola Lu-<br>pei’s mansion was built is full of ravines and <br>natural caves.    <br>5: Usko<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (2 <br>Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a prospector and direct the <br>work of recovering metals from the big river <br>east of Rovaniemi.</p><p>119<br>Agenda: Promote the community’s gold trade.<br>Information: Usko will tell the Hunters that most of the <br>equipment the searchers use was donated by Nikola. Usko <br>will speak of Nikola as a benefactor who has always worked <br>for the good of the Village. As for the disappearances, Usko <br>simply thinks that working in Nikola’s toy factory is much <br>easier than panning for gold in the cold and frost of the big <br>river. That is why several villagers have decided to move to <br>the factory, which is next to Nikola Lupei’s mansion. Usko <br>considers the missing inhabitants to be savvy layabouts <br>who have found a way to live comfortably while everyone <br>else labors. The toys Nikola produces are of the highest <br>quality, and Nikola has built his fortune by selling them to <br>wealthy families all over Europe. <br>6: Soila<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a teacher and I am responsible for the <br>education of the children in the village.        <br>Agenda: Keeping Rovaniemi families together. <br>Information: Soila will say that Nikola’s behavior was al-<br>ways strange. For example, he always came to the village <br>after sunset and never entered anyone’s house without a <br>proper formal invitation. More than once, Soila has seen <br>him lose his temper over the issue. But the Patron’s eccen-<br>tric behavior is nothing compared to all the good he has <br>done for the Village. Soila knows all the families who live <br>in the Village and is responsible for welcoming newcomers. <br>She will tell you that Tommi and Jutta are two good peo-<br>ple, but too reserved to adapt to the rules of the communi-<br>ty. Soila has even offered to help them pay the pledge, but <br>Tommi is too proud to go into debt.<br>The Forest around <br>Rovaniemi<br>Descriptor: A dense forest, always covered by a thick blan-<br>ket of snow. It is easy to find tracks in the snow.<br>Information: It is possible to reach Nikola’s estate from <br>the forest in a six-hour walk. Every three hours, the fol-<br>lowing Encounters are possible. The Storyteller can choose <br>which or roll a die. <br>1-2: The Tracks<br>3-4: Nikola’s Reindeer<br>5-6: Remains of the Merchant Wagon<br>The Tracks<br>The Hunters see the tracks of a single person who veered <br>off the path and got lost in the forest. They were left by the <br>first Hunter to arrive in Rovaniemi and lead to the Hunting <br>Lodge. See page 120.</p><p>120<br>Nikola’s Reindeer<br>Reindeer enslaved to Nikola occupy the entire forest around <br>the Village and the mansion, with the task of killing and <br>dragging to the Badalisk’s lair anyone who is not a resident <br>of Rovaniemi. A Reindeer herd consists of four members.<br>Remains of the Merchant Wagon<br>Not far from the main road, you can see the remains of a <br>wagon, now completely covered in snow. If you examine <br>it, you will find the remains of several mangled bodies and <br>goods that no one has taken. This is a merchant shipment <br>that never made it to Nikola’s estate. It will be easy to see that <br>many of the bodies were dragged into the forest thicket to <br>be taken somewhere. If the Hunters follow the tracks, they <br>will come to the Badalisk’s Lair. See Threat - Lost Trails on <br>page 121.  <br>The Hunting Lodge<br>Descriptor: A small hut, fortified as best it can be. A faint <br>trail of smoke from the chimney indicates that someone has <br>taken refuge inside.<br>Information: The Hunter who arrived a week ago was <br>badly injured in a confrontation with Nikola’s Reindeer and <br>is unable to escape. The Reindeer are patrolling the area, <br>ready to strike. Indeed, shortly after the Hunters arrive, a <br>herd of Reindeer attacks the cabin. The Hunter has suffered <br>their last Wound and is unable to act, but at the Storytell-<br>er’s discretion, they may use one of their Gifts to help. The <br>Hunter can report information about 2 of the Village El-<br>ders, chosen from those the Hunters have not already in-<br>terviewed. They will also say that Nikola himself showed up <br>at the door the night before and asked to be invited in. The <br>Hunter refused, fearing a trap. Nikola asked for their help in <br>“defeating a terrible monster, ” but refused to give any more <br>information. After another refusal to enter, he left mutter -<br>ing.  <br>Nikola’s Reindeer  <br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: We are reindeer mutated by Nikola’s magic, <br>and we crave to sink our teeth into the flesh of living creatures.    <br>Gift - Carnivore: Nikola’s Reindeer have large, clumsy jaws <br>that they use to eat meat. Each Reindeer in the herd increases <br>its OL by 1 when it attacks a marked target. A target is marked <br>when it suffers 1 Wound from a Reindeer bite. Alternatively, <br>a Reindeer can use its action to inflict a Wound on itself and <br>cover up to 3 targets within 20 feet with blood to mark them. A <br>target can dodge the attack with an OL Hard 7 Defense Check.</p><p>121<br>Threat – Lost Trails<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: It is not easy to follow the drag tracks in the <br>forest and keep alert for predators. <br>In case of failure, the Hunters will be caught off guard by a <br>herd of Nikola’s Reindeer. <br>The Badalisk’s Lair<br>Descriptor: A large natural cave that emits a strong stench <br>of death and decay.      <br>Information: The tracks end at the mouth of the gorge, <br>where there is no snow on the rock: this indicates that a <br>large creature often moves to the mouth. Many human re-<br>mains and various objects can be found inside the cave. The <br>deeper you go, the darker it gets.<br>Threat – The Sleeping Badalisk<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: The Badalisk sleeps most of the time, but if you <br>disturb it, it will wake up ready to devour anything.<br>Note: This Threat is activated when Hunters make a loud <br>noise, turn on a light, or come close enough for the Badal-<br>isk to smell them. If the Badalisk does not awaken, it can be <br>examined closely while it is dormant. If the Badalisk suffers <br>1 Wound, it will wake immediately.<br>The Badalisk<br>OL Hard 7 - Main NPC (6 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a huge dirty red sack encrusted with the <br>bloody remains of past meals. I have a large mouth with <br>which I devour my prey in one gulp.    <br>Agenda: Eating whatever comes my way to satiate my end-<br>less hunger.    <br>Gift - Huge Mouth:  When the Badalisk attacks a target <br>and the target fails their Defense Check, the Badalisk can <br>choose between two effects:<br>1. Inflicts 1 additional Wound with its bite. The target can <br>also be thrown a distance of thirty feet or have one of its <br>pieces of equipment swallowed by the Badalisk.<br>2. Swallow the target so that they end up in its giant belly. <br>This effect can also be activated when the target gains an <br>Outcome with a Cost on a Defense Check, but in this <br>case, they will only lose one piece of equipment as it is <br>swallowed by the giant maw.<br>A subject trapped inside the Badalisk can use their action to <br>actively attempt to escape. Depending on their ability, this <br>will be resolved as follows:<br>NPC with OL Easy 3: They cannot free themselves.<br>NPC with OL Medium 5:  They are released during the <br>Scene following the one in which they were swallowed.<br>NPCs with OL Hard 7, Dark Presences, and Bro-<br>ken Tales: Frees itself during the Exchange, but cannot <br>do anything else.<br>Hunter: Gets free with a Defense Check against OL Me-<br>dium 5.</p><p>122<br>A subject trapped inside the Badalisk follows the rules of the <br>Great Stomach Sack Gift.<br>Gift - Great Stomach Sack:  The Badalisk has swal-<br>lowed a Treasure of the Order, and it is making the creature <br>incredibly powerful. It can act 2 times during an Exchange <br>and regenerates all Wounds suffered between Scenes. To <br>retrieve the Treasure, a Hunter must be swallowed by the <br>Badalisk and make a Position Check against the creature. <br>If the Check fails, the Hunter suffers 1 Wound caused by <br>the objects inside the sack hitting him. On the other hand, <br>if the creature is asleep, the subjects inside it must make a <br>Position Check against the Badalisk’s OL for each action to <br>avoid waking it. Removing the swallowed Treasure sends <br>the Badalisk into hibernation: the creature shrinks to its <br>original size and becomes the Treasure of the Order known <br>as The Badalisk.<br>Nikola’s Estate<br>Descriptor: An estate consisting of a large garden and two <br>main buildings.    <br>Information: A herd of Nikola’s Reindeer roam the es-<br>tate’s garden. The larger building is the toy factory, while <br>the smaller mansion is Nikola’s home.  <br>The Toy Factory<br>Descriptor: An imposing building crammed with toys and <br>other wooden creations. Tools and workbenches are buried <br>in a huge mess.<br>Information: The situation in the factory differs depend-<br>ing on whether the Hunters arrive by day or by night.<br>Night: Everything is off, and the Servants rest by sleeping <br>on the floor or on worktables. They are awakened by loud <br>noises. <br>Day: All the villagers enslaved by Nikola’s power, 12 in all, <br>work in the factory. The Servants all wear a green uniform <br>and a funny pointed hat.</p><p>123<br>Threat – Littered with Junk<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: Extreme clutter and piles of toys stacked every-<br>where make it difficult to move around.    <br>Gift - Damn Junk!:  Moving around while trying not to <br>make noise or leave a trail activates this Threat. If the De-<br>fense Check fails, roll a die:<br>1-2: The Hunter suffers 1 Wound.<br>3-4: The Hunter will make a loud noise.    <br>5-6: Junk sticks to the Hunters, causing a penalty of 1 on <br>all Checks that require movement. It is possible to get rid of <br>it by spending a few minutes.<br>Nikola’ Servants<br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We live and work only to serve our master Ni-<br>kola. We are skilled in handicrafts and in using the toy facto-<br>ry to eliminate any intruders. <br>Agenda: Produce high-quality toys and then ship them to <br>poor children / Eliminate any intruder who is not a resident <br>of Rovaniemi.<br>Gift - Enslaved to Nikola: While Nikola’s charm is active, <br>a Servant is immune to all mind control effects and can-<br>not be manipulated by social interaction. Nikola’s charm is <br>considered dark magic performed by a supernatural being.    <br>Gift - Toymakers: As long as they are inside the factory, <br>a Servant receives the following effects.<br>1. They increase their OL by 1 when acting to eliminate or <br>capture an intruder.<br>2. They can move around the factory using hooks, toys <br>on wheels, and more without anyone being able to stop <br>them.<br>Nikola’s Mansion<br>Descriptor: A small mansion, richly furnished and filled <br>with all sorts of occult heirlooms.<br>Information: The situation at the Mansion is different if <br>the Hunters arrive by day or by night.<br>Night: Nikola is present and can fully use his powers. With <br>him are the 3 Helpers. <br>Day: Nikola is resting in the crypt and will only wake up <br>if he hears a racket at its entrance. The Helpers are present <br>and active.<br>A large painting in the main hall shows Nikola when he was <br>still a Wallachian nobleman. The painting is dated 1602. <br>Below the painting is a lever that, when pulled, opens the <br>trapdoor to Nikola’s crypt.</p><p>124<br>Helpers <br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We live and work only to serve our master Ni-<br>kola. Our bodies are made stronger by the power that has <br>been infused into them.    <br>Agenda: Defend Nikola from all threats.<br>Gift - Servants of the Mansion: Each Helper can avail themselves of a different effect based on their role.<br>Jori the Cook:  Can inflict 1 additional Wound with his <br>cleaver. Injuries inflicted by Jori count as a mark for Niko-<br>la’s Reindeer.<br>Pete the Butler: When moving inside the mansion, Pete <br>ignores any movement penalty and no one can block him.<br>Verna the Accountant:  Increases her OL to Hard 7 <br>when defending against an attack inside the mansion.<br>Nikola Lupei<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a powerful vampire with a <br>good heart, and I just want to live in peace <br>and quiet. The power I draw from blood <br>makes my body strong and fast. <br>Agenda: Find a way to get rid of the <br>Badalisk without harming the people <br>of Rovaniemi / Keep my secret and my <br>life in Rovaniemi. <br>Gift - Power of the Vampire:  <br>The curse that plagues Nikola’s <br>blood gives him great powers, but <br>also some weaknesses.<br>Powers: Each can be used by Ni-<br>kola once per Scene.<br>1: Recover 1 Wound.<br>2: Turn into mist.<br>3: Enslave a subject with his gaze. Perform a Defense <br>Check against Nikola’s OL to resist. An enslaved subject <br>shares what they see and hear with Nikola and will do <br>whatever the vampire commands. Nikola does not have to <br>be present to command the slave, but the subject must be <br>awake and alert. Enslavement ends when the subject suf-<br>fers 1 Wound.<br>Weaknesses: Nikola cannot enter a place he has nev-<br>er been unless first invited by the person who lives there.    <br>When exposed to sunlight, Nikola loses 1 Wound per <br>minute. Nikola can only be permanently eliminated if the <br>last of his Wounds is inflicted by a magical or consecrated <br>weapon.<br>Gift - Occult Scholar:  Nikola knows many rituals and <br>possesses arcane objects to cast spells. He used these pow-</p><p>125<br>ers to create his Reindeer and make his Helpers stronger. Up to 3 times per Scene, Nikola can block the use <br>of a Gift he has seen in action. Once per Scene, Nikola can imbue an NPC with power by increasing <br>their OL by one category. The Storyteller must rewrite the NPC’s Descriptor to reflect the mutation <br>caused by Nikola’s spell. <br>Nikola’s Crypt<br>Descriptor: A gloomy, dark, unadorned crypt in the center of which rests a gold and <br>diamond-encrusted coffin on a small pedestal.<br>Information: By day, Nikola rests in his coffin, sleeping in a deep slumber. A swarm <br>of Bats, mutated by his power, protects him.  <br>Nikola’s Bats  <br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (5 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: We are a swarm of bats ready to devour any intruder.    <br>Agenda: Protect Nikola while he sleeps.<br>Gift - Swarm: Bats are considered a single unit with 5 Wounds. <br>Any damage dealt reduces the total by 1, and attacks that hit an <br>area inflict 1 additional Wound. As a swarm, Nikola’s Bats can <br>bite up to 3 different targets in a single action. The flapping <br>of the Bats’ wings causes discomfort to living creatures: <br>as the swarm rises, each Hunter present loses 2 Soma, <br>while NPCs suffer 1 Wound from fatigue.</p><p>126<br>Scenario Events<br>There are six Events in this Scenario. As the Storyteller, feel <br>free to create new ones in response to the Hunters’ actions.<br>If the Hunters have an NPC in their retinue: Nikola <br>will arrive in Rovaniemi on the first evening to enslave the <br>NPC. When threatened by the Hunter’s presence, he will <br>flee by turning into mist. <br>If the Hunters do not rescue the captive Hunter in <br>the Hunting Lodge within one day:  Nikola will attack <br>with his servants and take the Hunters to the toy factory to <br>prepare them as a meal for the Badalisk.<br>If the Hunters capture Nikola:  The vampire will ask <br>for their help in getting rid of the Badalisk, warning them <br>that if the creature does not find a meal when it awakens, it <br>will rampage through the village. <br>If the Hunters eliminate the Badalisk before meet-<br>ing Nikola: The vampire will thank them and invite them <br>to his mansion to understand the Order’s intentions toward <br>him and to mediate a peaceful resolution. <br>If the Hunters enter the mansion during the day:  Jori and Pete will attack the Hunters while Verna runs to <br>wake her master. <br>If the Hunters bring a Rovaniemi resident with <br>them: Nikola will try to capture and enslave the resident, <br>but under no circumstances will he risk their life. <br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to the Nikola’s <br>Pledge Scenario and can be acquired once the conditions <br>are met. A Hunter can only have one Scenario Gift, and if <br>they acquire a new one, they will have to forgo the previous <br>one.<br>Aberration Killer<br>Requirement: Eliminate a herd of Reindeer or a swarm <br>of Nikola’s Bats. <br>Y ou have learned how to deal with creatures empowered by <br>dark magic. Once per Scene, if you vanquish an enchanted <br>creature (at the discretion of the Storyteller), you will re-<br>cover 1 Soma and gain 1 XP .<br>A Special Gift<br>Requirement: Free one or more of the enslaved inhabi-<br>tants of the toy factory or negotiate a deal with Nikola.<br>Y ou have received a special toy, a carving of a bearded man <br>on a sled. Y ou can spend 1 Soma to animate the toy, which <br>will be able to move around and perform small tasks such <br>as carrying an object or delivering a message to someone. <br>The toy remains active for the duration of the Scene. Y ou <br>can spend 1 Soma to return the toy to you. It will disappear <br>from its location and reappear in your hand.</p><p>127<br>The Scenario Nikola’s Pledge in Scenes</p><p>FIRST SCENE –  Arrival in <br>Rovaniemi<br>It’s the same one you find on page 116.<br>End of Scene: Tommi and Jutta will tell the Hunters that <br>they can meet the Village Elders the next morning, go to</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513739250,"modifiedTime":1781513739250,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"97so6WnNCuBHFt9A","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Nikola's Pledge - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE – The Town Hall.</p><p>SECOND SCENE –  The Town <br>Hall<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  As you walk through Ro-<br>vaniemi, you may notice that many of the equipment and <br>houses have engraved plaques identifying them as donations <br>from Nikola Lupei. It is very clear that this Nikola is a true <br>patron and that with his support the small village of miners <br>was able to prosper. The town hall is one of the few mason-<br>ry buildings in the village, rising above the roofs of the sur -<br>rounding wooden houses.<br>Place: Rovaniemi’s Town Hall. <br>Time: Early in the morning, the villagers are already work-<br>ing feverishly to take advantage of every hour of sunshine.<br>Information: Asmo and Mikko are present at the Town <br>Hall and are busy examining some documents. Asmo will <br>be very helpful and try to clear up any doubts about Nikola <br>Lupei. The Elder will prepare a letter of introduction for the <br>Hunters to take to Lupei’s estate. The Elder will recommend <br>that they arrive at night, as Nikola is a real night owl, while <br>during the day he is too busy working at the toy factory. <br>Mikko will complain that a wealthy merchant who was sup-<br>posed to be in the village missed his appointment and did <br>not send a messenger. The two Elders will also report gen-<br>eral information (see page 116), urging the Hunters to go <br>to Nikola to clear up any doubts.<br>End of Scene: Ask the Hunters if they want to go to Niko-<br>la’s by night (as Asmo recommended) or by day. To get to <br>the estate, they can choose to take the main road (THIRD <br>SCENE OPTION A - The High Road) or venture into the <br>woods (THIRD SCENE OPTION B - The Lodge).</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513739250,"modifiedTime":1781513739250,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"LzHMPG4AIfTSzgnF","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Nikola's Pledge - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION A –  <br>The High Road<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: The road to the Lupei estate is <br>wide and well-trodden. Once again, it is easy to see how much <br>effort and money Nikola has put into creating a good connec-<br>tion between his home and the village of Rovaniemi. Several <br>tracks in the fresh snow indicate that herds of animals are con-<br>stantly moving through the area, and just as you are about to <br>look around, a group of reindeer emerges from the trees and <br>gallops toward you. By the time they come into focus, the mon-<br>strous muzzles of the creatures are only a few feet away...<br>Place: The main road leading to the Lupei estate. <br>Time: It’s either night or afternoon, depending on the Hunt-<br>ers’ choice. Snow is starting to fall, promising a blizzard soon. <br>2 3a<br>1</p><p>128<br>Information: The Hunters are attacked by a herd of 4 <br>Reindeer. When they examine the bodies of the creatures, <br>using Descriptors related to hunting or magic, it is easy to <br>see that the creatures have been altered by dark magic. <br>End of Scene: The Hunters arrive at the Lupei Estate, go <br>to the FOURTH SCENE - The Estate.</p><p>THIRD SCENE OPTION B –  <br>The Lodge<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  As you make your way <br>through the bush, your attention is drawn to a cabin where <br>you see signs of life. Someone has barred the doors and win-<br>dows as if to defend against an attack, but you can tell from <br>the light you can see between the boards that they are proba-<br>bly still barricaded inside. <br>Place: An old hunting lodge often used by hunters in Ro-<br>vaniemi. <br>Time: It’s either night or afternoon, depending on the <br>Hunters’ choice. Snow is starting to fall, promising a bliz-<br>zard soon.<br>Information: The wounded Hunter has taken refuge in <br>the hut, the Scene takes place with the information associ-<br>ated with a result of 1-2 The Tracks on page 119.<br>End of Scene: The Hunters arrive at the Lupei Estate, go <br>to the FOURTH SCENE - The Estate.</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513739250,"modifiedTime":1781513739250,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"E2SzLtqCeP3j5JKT","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Nikola's Pledge - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE –  The Estate<br>If the Hunters arrive during the day, read aloud:  <br>The Lupei estate consists of two large buildings. The sound <br>of work comes from what looks like a large factory. The other <br>building is a large baroque-style villa, its doors and windows <br>barred as if it were unoccupied.<br>If the Hunters arrive at night, read aloud:  The Lu-<br>pei estate consists of two large buildings. From the first one, <br>which looks like a big factory, everything seems to be quiet, <br>as you would expect from a workplace after work. From the <br>other, a large baroque villa, you can see the lights on and a <br>few silhouettes passing by the windows.<br>Place: Nikola Lupei’s estate. <br>Time: Day or night. <br>Information: The snow is falling heavily and the icy <br>wind is blowing, making it easy to move around the es-<br>tate inconspicuously. At this point, the Hunters can decide <br>which building to go to; the Factory is on page 122 and <br>the Mansion is on page 123. <br>The Factory: During the day, the Servants will be at work <br>and will not hesitate to attack any intruders. Once defeated, <br>they will be free from Nikola’s subjugation and can give the <br>Hunters useful information about the vampire. At night, <br>they will sleep. But when awakened, they will attack.<br>The Mansion: During the day, the Helpers will guard Ni-<br>kola’s coffin. Once defeated, it will be easy to imprison Ni-<br>kola. At night Nikola will be awake and will try to confront <br>the Hunters with his Helpers. <br>Either way, Nikola will surrender if the Hunters prove too <br>strong or hurt the Helpers. The vampire will then ask for <br>their help in getting rid of the Badalisk and explain the <br>reasons behind all his dark business and why the pledge is <br>needed. <br>3b<br>4</p><p>129<br>End of Scene: The Hunters have discovered Nikola’s se-<br>cret and can now try to defeat the Badalisk, go to FIFTH <br>SCENE - In the Badalisk’s Lair.</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513739250,"modifiedTime":1781513739250,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"3lkll3WIBPHKpQpD","name":"Scene 5","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Nikola's Pledge - Scene 5</h2><p>FIFTH SCENE –  In the <br>Badalisk’s Lair<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: You arrive at the mouth <br>of a large cave, from which emanates a terrible stench of <br>death. As you prepare to descend, you hear a deep snor-<br>ing in the distance.<br>Place: The Badalisk’s Lair. <br>Time: The moment of reckoning.<br>End of Scene:  See page 121 for instructions on how to <br>deal with the Badalisk. If present, Nikola will actively as-<br>sist the Hunters in two ways: he can either be devoured to <br>give a Hunter time to enter the Badalisk unharmed, or he <br>can distract the creature for an Exchange, allowing every-<br>one else to act without fear of the monster’s powerful bite. <br>After defeating the Badalisk and recovering the Treasure, <br>Nikola will ask the Hunters for permission to return to his <br>reclusive life. <br>5</p>"},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513739250,"modifiedTime":1781513739250,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"nikolas-pledge","collection":"Lost Stories","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","pages":"115-130"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513739250,"modifiedTime":1781513739250,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"4YnHJdOAKQpYlWOk","name":"The Last Wish","pages":[{"_id":"lKLa2XtOXkhsebCe","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>The Last Wish</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> Lost Stories</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, pages 131-146.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/the-last-wish-p131-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513740373,"modifiedTime":1781513740373,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Iz5gg22u9ilKEEDb","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The Last Wish - Setup</h2><p>130<br>The Last Wish<br> <br>A Scenario inspired by The Tinderbox (Hans Christian Andersen)<br>Once upon a time...<br>Bastian Soldat is a deserter guilty of a serious crime: assigned to guard the garrison <br>general, Bastian fled during battle, abandoning his charge in the midst of the enemy. It <br>took three years to track down the fugitive, who has since turned to a life of debauchery <br>and lawlessness. But a week ago, Bastian Soldat was sentenced to the gallows and <br>executed in the public square of Heidelberg, the city where he had been hiding. Up <br>until this point, it may have seemed like just another story, but according to the Order’s <br>research, Bastian Soldat had already been executed twice. So a group of Hunters was <br>sent to the German city to retrace Bastian’s life and understand why this deserter seems <br>to keep coming back from the dead to continue his misdeeds.<br>Safety Keywords: Scam / Demonic Presence</p><p>131<br>The story that led us here...<br>After his desertion, Bastian fled to the small town <br>of Heidelberg to start a new life. Here, the soldier met <br>Britta, an old witch who lived near the town cemetery. <br>The woman needed an intrepid young man to retrieve a <br>Magic Tinderbox, a memento of her late grandmother. <br>In return, Britta offered Bastian a bag of coins that would <br>allow the soldier to live off his earnings for many years. <br>After retrieving the object, the two parted on friendly <br>terms, but Bastian gambled away all the money he had <br>received within a few days and reappeared at the witch’s <br>house to ask for a new job. When Britta refused, Bastian <br>lost his temper and, in a fit of rage, decapitated the wi-<br>tch with one blow of his saber. Determined not to go to <br>prison, Bastian threw the body into the hollow tree in <br>Britta’s garden and the head into the river near the town. <br>He also took possession of the Magic Tinderbox, all the <br>money he could find, and anything else that caught his <br>eye. A few days later, Bastian found himself with nothing <br>in his pockets and several debts. Determined to fix the si-<br>tuation, he attempted to rob a wealthy merchant but was <br>caught by the city’s gendarmes. When his identity as a <br>deserter was discovered, the head of the gendarmes did <br>not hesitate for a moment to condemn him to the gal-<br>lows, but... the soldier found himself back in front of the <br>merchant before committing the robbery.    In his jacket <br>pocket, Bastian felt the witch’s Magic Tinderbox throb-<br>bing with power and realized that time had rewound to <br>allow him to escape. Exalted by this new power, Bastian <br>began to commit all sorts of mischief, counting on the fact <br>that he could always turn back time if things took a turn for <br>the worse. Meanwhile, Britta’s spirit could not rest, and the <br>witch took possession of a black she-cat that often roamed <br>near the hollow tree. Britta then set out to find some of the <br>items Bastian had stolen from her: the Witch’s Shawl, the <br>Black Coral Pendant, and the Devil’s Ladle. What appears <br>to be ordinary objects are actually three powerful magical <br>focuses in which Britta has stored some of her power. The <br>witch’s big problem is that without outside help, she cannot <br>get her hands on the three objects and bring them to where <br>her corpse is...<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters...<br>Bastian has “died and risen” several times, including twice <br>on the gallows. Despite the great opportunity that the Ma-<br>gic Tinderbox offers him, the soldier is so stupid that he <br>never manages to do anything that would allow him to turn <br>the tide forever. Meanwhile, he has fallen in love with the <br>daughter of the city regent, the young Alena Wagner, who <br>does not seem to disdain his attentions. With huge debts <br>at the Drunken Hussar’s Gambling House, the city’s worst <br>gambling den, Bastian plans to clean out the Wagner fa-<br>mily’s coffers and then flee to Copenhagen.<br> <br>Note: Unlike a normal Scenario where the Hunters move <br>between different locations to investigate, in this adventure, <br>every time Bastian is captured or eliminated by the Hun-<br>ters, there is a Reset that brings the events back to the first <br>Scene. The cycle will continue until the Hunters manage <br>to revive Britta to reveal the word, chosen by the Storytel-<br>ler, that can deactivate the Magic Tinderbox. Because of its <br>structure, the Scenario handles the evolution of the story <br>with a series of Resets that replace the normal Events.</p><p>132<br>Bastian Soldat, the Black Cat, and each Place associated with <br>Bastian have a progressive Reset list showing the differences <br>the Hunters will find the first, second, third, and fourth time <br>Bastian uses the power of the Tinderbox.<br>In this Scenario, the Hunters track Bastian by visiting Pla-<br>ces that he is known to frequent. If the Hunters manage to <br>find him by other means, a Reset will still take place that <br>allows Bastian to escape and 1 Reset Token will be added to <br>the soldier’s Magic Tinderbox Gift. However, in those circu-<br>mstances, the details of the setting aren’t altered and events <br>don’t progress to the next change on the Reset list. For the <br>sake of clarity, the chronology of pre-determined Resets in <br>the Scenario is as follows:<br>First Reset<br>The first change occurs in the first Scene, when the Hunters <br>accidentally run into Bastian at the entrance to the city. <br>Second Reset<br>The second change happens when the Hunters find Bastian <br>in one of the three Places he usually hangs out: the Drun-<br>ken Hussar’s Gambling House, Villa Wagner, or the Golden <br>Plate Tavern. <br>Third Reset<br>The third change occurs when the Hunters meet Bastian at <br>one of the two Places left after the Second Reset.<br>Fourth Reset<br>The final change happens when the Hunters hit Bastian at <br>the spot left after the Second and Third Reset.<br>After the Fourth Reset<br>Bastian will take refuge in the Old Barracks to begin his <br>plan to rob the Wagners. <br>All Resets not generated as indicated by the previous list <br>should not be counted for the progression of Scenario Re-<br>sets, but generate 1 Reset Token for the Magic Tinderbox <br>Gift.<br>Whenever the Hunters visit the Drunken Hussar’s Gam-<br>bling House, Villa Wagner, or the Golden Plate Tavern, <br>roll a die to see where Bastian and the Cat are at that mo-<br>ment:<br>1-2: Bastian is in the Drunken Hussar’s Gambling House, <br>trying to play dice with a group of soldiers. The Cat is at <br>Villa Wagner, trying to get the Black Coral Pendant from <br>Alena’s room.    <br>3-4: Bastian is at Villa Wagner, chatting amiably with <br>Alena. The young woman is overlooking the terrace of her <br>room while Bastian recites a poem to her from the garden <br>below. The Cat is in the Golden Plate Tavern, trying to re-<br>trieve the Devil’s Ladle from the kitchens. <br>5-6: Bastian is at the Golden Plate Tavern, bargaining to <br>eat some delicacies without paying. The Cat is at the Drun-<br>ken Hussar’s Gambling House, trying to retrieve the Witch’s <br>Shawl from an old drunk who is using it to protect himself <br>from the cold of the night. <br> <br>If the result has the Hunters either meeting Bastian at a <br>location where they have already met him or meeting the <br>Cat at a location where they have already recovered Britta’s <br>item, go to the next result.</p><p>133</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513740373,"modifiedTime":1781513740373,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"L5B6ZuHtmdvEtFQW","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The Last Wish - Scene 1</h2><p>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  It is late in the morning <br>when you finally arrive at the gates of Heidelberg: the city <br>is buzzing with activity, with merchant carts and groups of <br>soldiers going back and forth. This city is a crossroads, and <br>as you might expect, the traffic is heavy. As you contempla-<br>te the difficulty of finding Bastian Soldat in the midst of the <br>city’s hustle and bustle, a voice catches your attention: “Ba-<br>stian! Bastian Soldat, you scoundrel! Come out and give me <br>the money you owe me!” The shouter is a bearded man in a <br>tattered potter’s apron, while the recipient of his insults is a <br>small man with an anonymous face, shaggy blond hair, and <br>a drunkard’s belly. Obviously, you have already found your <br>target.      <br>Place: The Entrance Plaza of Heidelberg. <br>Time: It is midday and the day is slowly warming up as <br>the cackle of taverns and the smell of good food tickle the <br>senses. <br>Initial Situation:  Bastian Soldat rushes through the <br>crowd to get away from the man shouting at him, almost <br>tripping over a black cat that seems to have deliberately got-<br>ten in his way.    <br>Information: The potter complaining about Bastian is <br>called Hugo, and he is angry because the soldier bought <br>some pots in Britta’s name a week ago and never paid for <br>them. Talking to Hugo will give you the following infor -<br>mation:<br> ◆ Bastian is no good and a loafer: he boasts of being an <br>honorably discharged soldier, but when asked to show <br>the medal he received upon his discharge, he always <br>shies away. No one knows where he sleeps, but he is <br>always seen hanging around three Places.<br> ◆ The Drunken Hussar’s Gambling House: A cheap <br>dive bar known for its bad wine and gambling tables.<br> ◆ Villa Wagner: The home of a noble family. Bastian <br>has told everyone he knows that he has fallen in love <br>with the young and beautiful Alena Wagner, dau-<br>ghter of Anselm Wagner, the wealthiest aristocrat in <br>town. <br> ◆ The Golden Plate Tavern: The most expensive and <br>valuable restaurant in the city, where only the weal-<br>thiest can afford a meal.<br> ◆ Britta is an old woman who lives near the town ceme-<br>tery. Many believe her to be a witch, but no one has <br>ever seen her do anything strange enough to support <br>these accusations. <br>Bastian Soldat<br>OL Easy 3 - Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a deserter with no qualities other than a <br>great desire to live a good life with minimal effort. My only <br>virtue is that I have incredible nerve.<br>Agenda: Emptying the coffers of the Wagner family in order <br>to pretend to be rich in Alena’s eyes and convince her to run <br>away with me to Copenhagen. <br>Gift - Magic Tinderbox: Thanks to this powerful magi-<br>cal object, Bastian can go back in time whenever the situa-<br>tion would prevent him from completing his Agenda. This <br>magical effect cannot be stopped except by the magic word <br>that only Britta knows. Each time Bastian rewinds time, the <br>Storyteller secretly accumulates 1 Reset Token. Each token</p><p>134<br>accumulated makes the three Demonic Dogs more power-<br>ful (see page 142). <br>First Reset: Bastian will avoid returning to Heidelberg’s <br>Entrance Plaza and will stay in one of the other Places he is <br>accustomed to wandering.<br>Second Reset: Bastian will avoid returning to the Place <br>where the Hunters found him and will wander to one of the <br>other two remaining locations. <br>Third Reset: Bastian will avoid returning to the Places <br>where the Hunters found him, and will wander to the last <br>available location.    <br>Fourth Reset: Bastian will avoid returning to all the Pla-<br>ces where the Hunters found him. From that moment on, <br>he will take refuge in the Old Barracks, plan the robbery of <br>Villa Wagner, and then try to escape with Alena. <br>Hugo the Potter<br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am an honest craftsman and have been a <br>potter all my life. I have a friendly nature and tend to trust <br>people.         <br>Heidelberg’s Entrance Plaza<br>Descriptor: A large square always filled with citizens and <br>travelers. <br>Information: As the first Place that Bastian will use the <br>Magic Tinderbox to escape the Hunters, this is where the <br>Hunters will start again after each Reset. Unlike normal hu-<br>mans, the Hunters will retain a memory of what happened <br>at each Reset.<br>First Reset: The Hunters will notice that some powerful <br>magic has taken effect, and time seems to have rewound <br>to a few minutes before they meet Bastian. The deserter is <br>absent, but Hugo the Potter is behind his stall, smiling at <br>passersby. The Black Cat walks between the legs of one of <br>the Hunters, stops to watch them with intelligent eyes, and <br>then walks away.    <br>Second Reset: Same as the First Reset, except the Cat <br>will stop with the Hunters and try to get them to follow her, <br>leading them to Britta’s house.<br>Third Reset: Like the First Reset, but this time the Hun-<br>ters will find Anselm Wagner waiting for them with an <br>escort of ten gendarmes. The nobleman will tell the Hun-<br>ters that he has received a report from a trusted man about <br>their impending arrival in the city. The nobleman has made <br>no request of the Order and wants no trouble, so he will <br>ask the Hunters to leave. It will be clear that Anselm has</p><p>135<br>nothing to hide but is simply afraid that the Order’s presen-<br>ce will scare away visitors and ruin the merchants’ business. <br>Fourth Reset: Like the First Reset, except that Bastian <br>has hired a gang of Cutthroats (2 per Character) to elimi-<br>nate the Hunters. <br>After the Fourth Reset: Same as the First Reset.<br>•<br>Anselm Wagner<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am the most important person in the city, <br>involved in politics and with many investments in various <br>activities. Everyone admires my efforts to make Heidelberg <br>prosperous. <br>Agenda: Keep an eye out for potential problems for the city <br>and maintain a clean appearance. <br>•<br>Armsmen of the City<br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are swordsmen and have gained experien-<br>ce during the war. We carry out the orders of those who pay <br>us without making too much trouble.  <br>Gift - Companions in Arms:  During an action, they <br>increase their OL by 1 if at least one other Armsman is pre-<br>sent.  <br>Cutthroat <br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are ruthless killers who will do anything to <br>make a profit. We eliminate the target with chilling efficiency. <br>Gift - Assassin: If they act to kill, they are considered to <br>have an OL Medium 5.<br>Information: If questioned, they will not hesitate to reve-<br>al that they were hired by a certain Bastian Soldat. <br>•<br>The Black Cat<br>OL Hard 7 - Main NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a snappy kitten bound to the spirit of old <br>Britta. Thanks to the witch’s power I can understand what <br>people are saying. <br>Agenda: Have the humans help me retrieve Britta’s three <br>items. <br>First Reset:  The Cat will observe the Hunters in the <br>Heidelberg Entrance Plaza to understand why they are not <br>affected by the Magic Tinderbox. It will then go <br>to one of the Places to retrieve Britta’s items. <br>Second Reset:  If the Hunters are intere-<br>sted, the Cat will lead them to Britta’s Hou-<br>se to find her diary. If the diary has already <br>been found, the Cat will take the Hunters to <br>one of the Places to retrieve the items. The <br>Cat will also have retrieved one of the items if <br>the Hunters have not already done so.</p><p>136<br>Third Reset: If the Hunters are interested, the Cat will <br>lead them to Britta’s House to find her diary. If the diary has <br>already been found, the Cat will take the Hunters to one of <br>the Places to retrieve the items. The Cat will also have retrie-<br>ved one of the items if the Hunters have not already done so.<br>Fourth Reset: If the Hunters are interested, the Cat will <br>lead them to Britta’s House to find her diary. If the diary has <br>already been found, the Cat will take the Hunters to one of <br>the Places to retrieve the items. The Cat will also have retrie-<br>ved one of the items if the Hunters have not already done so.<br>After the Fourth Reset: If the Hunters are interested, the <br>Cat will lead them to Britta’s House to find her diary. If the <br>diary has already been found, the Cat will take the Hunters <br>to one of the Places to retrieve the items. The Cat will also <br>have retrieved one of the items if the Hunters have not alre-<br>ady done so.<br>The Drunken Hussar’s <br>Gambling House<br>Descriptor: A dive bar at the end of a slum alley. Amidst <br>the smoke and dim lights, the shadows of the city’s underworld <br>move. <br>Information: The Hussar is run by Ulrich, a former sol-<br>dier who lost his right hand in the war. Ulrich knows Ba-<br>stian well and will not hesitate to tell you that the soldier has <br>gambled away a fortune at the tables of his dive bar. Everyo-<br>ne jokingly refers to Bastian as “the Golden Goose, ” and <br>when he is present, everyone competes to play with him. <br>Ulrich knows that Bastian has fallen head over heels for the <br>Wagner’ young scion and is often at their Villa trying to win <br>Alena’s heart. <br>If Bastian is present: He gambles the last of his coin on <br>dice, and as soon as he sees the Hunters, he tries to escape <br>through the window behind him.<br>If the Black Cat is present:  The Hunters will see her at <br>the entrance to the Gambling House, harassing an old beg-<br>gar. The pet pulls a fine shawl toward her, which the beggar <br>holds tightly. It will be obvious that such a poor man cannot <br>afford such an expensive garment.<br>First Reset: If this is the first time he has encountered <br>them at this Place, Bastian will try to escape. However, if the <br>Hunters have already met him here, Bastian will not show <br>up again. <br>Second Reset: Like the First Reset, except that Ulrich will <br>be offering the Hunters a round of welcome drinks. Bastian <br>has paid him to lace the drinks with poison. If discovered, <br>Ulrich will not hesitate to confess.</p><p>137<br>Third Reset: Same as the First and Second Reset, but if <br>the Hunters have not read Britta’s diary and the Black Cat is <br>present, the animal will try to make the Hunters realize that <br>the Witch’s Shawl is an item to be retrieved. If the Hunters <br>help her, she will lead them to Britta’s House to find the <br>diary.<br>Fourth Reset: Same as previous Resets. <br>After the Fourth Reset: The Gambling House is closed <br>because Ulrich is joining Bastian to rob Villa Wagner. <br>Ulrich Rotten Eye<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a former criminal with experience in the <br>use of poisons. I opened my gambling den looking for a less <br>dangerous life, but I don’t back down when there’s money to <br>be made.<br>Gift - Poisoned Dagger: Ulrich’s weapon is imbued with <br>a powerful poison. The poison first enters play when the <br>weapon inflicts 1 Wound, causing 1 Penalty to the target’s <br>actions. The effect lasts until the victim takes an antidote or <br>has an Interlude. <br>Threat - Poisoned Drink<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: A fine, tasteless, odorless poison that can be <br>added to any beverage. <br>Gift - Poison: Those who ingest the Poisoned Drink suf-<br>fer 1 Wound and receive 1 Penalty until they take an anti-<br>dote or rest in an Interlude. <br>Villa Wagner<br>Descriptor: An imposing mansion surrounded by gardens, <br>ponds, and mazes of hedges. <br>Information: It’s impossible to enter the Villa without an <br>invitation from the Wagner family, but there are no fences <br>and, except for a few gardeners, it is easy to wander incon-<br>spicuously around the large gardens. Alena is often found <br>on the large balcony of her room on the second floor, rea-<br>ding a good book and sipping tea. Alena will tell you that <br>Bastian often brings her very good and expensive cakes that <br>he buys at the famous Golden Plate Tavern. The young wo-<br>man is unclear about who Bastian really is, but it will be ob-<br>vious that she is attracted to the funny little man and finds <br>his awkward attempts to court her tender.<br>If Bastian is present: He will be under Alena’s balcony <br>reciting some love poetry. As soon as he sees the Hunters, <br>he will try to escape by slipping into one of the hedge ma-<br>zes.<br>If the Black Cat is present:  It can be seen on the bal-<br>cony being petted by Alena. The Cat pretends to purr in <br>affection as she clearly tries to snatch a pendant from the <br>young woman’s neck.<br>First Reset:  If this is the first time he encounters the <br>Hunters in this Place, Bastian will try to escape. However, <br>if the Hunters have already met him here, Bastian will not <br>appear again.<br>Second Reset:  Same as the First Reset, except that a <br>group of guards (2 per Hunter) will enter the Scene when <br>the Hunters approach Alena. The leader of the guards will <br>say that by Lord Wagner’s order, no one can enter the gar-<br>den of the Villa. If the Hunters can get the captain to talk</p><p>138<br>more, he will say that an informant has alerted Lord Wa-<br>gner that a group of robbers are roaming the city and rai-<br>ding the villas of the nobles.<br>Third Reset: Same as the First and Second Reset, but if <br>the Hunters have not read Britta’s diary and the Black Cat <br>is present, the animal will try to make the Hunters under -<br>stand that the Black Coral Pendant is an item to be retrie-<br>ved. If the Hunters help the Cat, she will lead them to Brit-<br>ta’s House to find the diary.<br>Fourth Reset: Same as the previous reset. <br>After the Fourth Reset:  Alena will not be on the bal-<br>cony as usual. Bastian has written her a letter asking her <br>to meet him behind the Golden Plate Tavern at sunset. Ba-<br>stian wants to do the job at the Villa without Alena being <br>there. Afterward, he’ll suggest that they run away together.  <br>Villa Wagner’s Guard<br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are loyal and well-trained for our duties as <br>guardians. <br>Gift - Guard Corps: During an action, increase their OL <br>by 1 if they are defending Villa Wagner from a threat or <br>perceived threat.<br>Alena Wagner<br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am the young scion of the Wagner family. I <br>love adventure and romance novels. I’m cultured and dream <br>of becoming a teacher one day.  <br>Agenda: To have a good adventure like the ones I read <br>about in novels.<br>Wagner Treasury<br>Descriptor: A small fortified tower connected to <br>the Villa by an underground tunnel. Aside from the <br>tunnel, the only way to access the tower is to know <br>the combination of the large metal door that <br>blocks the main entrance.<br>Information: The Treasury is permanently <br>manned by 4 Guards who change shifts every <br>eight hours.<br>First, Second, and Third Reset:  Bastian</p><p>139<br>has obtained the information he needs for the robbery <br>days before the Hunters arrive, so he will not be wandering <br>around the Treasury beforehand. <br>Fourth Reset: Bastian will attempt to rob the Treasury. <br>The plan is simple: Bastian and four other soldiers he met <br>at the barracks will enter through Villa Wagner and use the <br>secret tunnel to get into the Treasury. Meanwhile, Ulrich <br>will have slipped a powerful sleeping pill into the food in-<br>tended for the four Guards guarding the entrance. Once <br>the Guards are asleep, Bastian will open the door and each <br>gang member will fill two large sacks with gold and va-<br>luables. Unbeknownst to the other gang members, Bastian <br>is planning to betray them. Once outside the Villa, he will <br>separate from the group, warn the gendarmes of the theft, <br>and then pick up Alena to escape with her. Bastian’s inten-<br>tion is to cover his escape by drawing attention to the other <br>gang members.  <br> <br>Threat - Treasury Door<br>OL Hard 7<br>Descriptor: A huge metal door reinforced to resist any <br>burglary attempt. The combination to open it is 05031762, <br>Alena’s date of birth.<br>Robbers<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are veteran soldiers and have seen the hor-<br>rors of war. We do not shy away from danger and have no <br>qualms about committing acts of cruelty.  <br>The Golden Plate Tavern<br>Descriptor: The finest and most famous tavern in Heidel-<br>berg: Brigit’s cuisine is of the highest standard, but only the <br>very rich can afford it.<br>Information: There are no rooms to sleep in at the Ta-<br>vern, which is best known for the haute cuisine of Chef Bri-<br>git. Nobles and rich men come from all over Europe to taste <br>the food of the Golden Plate. Brigit became accustomed to <br>Bastian’s presence, always showering her with complimen-<br>ts on her cooking. At first, Bastian was a good customer, <br>but soon he had no money to pay for the meals, and Brigit <br>gave him credit until she realized that the soldier was a lost <br>cause. If asked about Bastian, Brigit will say that he is a go-<br>od-tempered man who tries to live far beyond his means. <br>When he is not eating at the Golden Plate, Bastian is often <br>at the Drunken Hussar’s Gambling House, where he gam-<br>bles and tries to accumulate some money.<br>If Bastian is present:  He will sit at the table and beg <br>Brigit to serve him one of her fantastic dishes. As soon as <br>he sees the Hunters, he will try to escape by sneaking into <br>the kitchens.<br>If the Black Cat is present:  The Hunters will see her <br>through the half-open door into the kitchen as she tries to <br>knock down an old ladle hanging on the wall with her paw. <br>The Cat is unsuccessful, as someone always intervenes to <br>chase it away. Brigit will complain that the animal seems <br>to be obsessed with the old ladle given to her by the elderly <br>Britta. <br>First Reset:  If this is the first time he encounters the <br>Hunters in this Place, Bastian will try to escape. However, <br>if the Hunters have already met him here, Bastian will not <br>appear again.</p><p>Second Reset: Same as the First Reset, except that a <br>group of Cutthroats (2 per Hunter, see page 135) are <br>preparing to ambush the Hunters when they leave the Ta-<br>vern.    <br>Third Reset: Same as the First and Second Reset, but if <br>the Hunters have not read Britta’s diary and the Black Cat <br>is present, the animal will try to make the Hunters under-<br>stand that the Devil’s Ladle is an item to be retrieved. If <br>the Hunters help her, she will lead them to Britta’s house <br>to find the diary.<br>Fourth Reset: Same as the previous reset. <br>After the Fourth Reset:  Brigit is cleaning a table. If <br>asked she will say that Bastian came to dinner with four <br>other shady characters. They spent the whole time bab-<br>bling about tunnels and guard shifts. He paid for everyone <br>and then they left.   <br>Brigit the Cook<br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a good cook, the best. I love my tavern <br>and can’t stand any argument between my tables.     <br>The Old Barracks<br>Descriptor: A dirty old building where soldiers on leave <br>can sleep for free.<br>Information: Bastian sleeps in the Old Barracks, but <br>has never told anyone about it because it would damage <br>the image of wealth and prosperity he is trying to build <br>in Alena’s eyes. Bastian has joined forces with four other <br>deserters who will help him in his plan to rob Villa Wa-<br>gner. In the Barracks, many people know Bastian and will <br>describe him as a blowhard, but too stupid to actually <br>amount to anything.<br>If Bastian is present: At night, Bastian sleeps in a se-<br>cret room on the second floor of the building. If disco-<br>vered, he will try to escape by throwing himself out the <br>window to cause a Reset.<br>After any Reset caused in this Place:  Bastian will <br>not go back to sleep but will use Ulrich to send messages <br>to his co-conspirators.<br>Britta’s House<br>Descriptor: A small abandoned house near the gra -<br>veyard. In the garden, in the middle of a vegetable patch <br>and near a well, there is an old hollow tree with no leaves.<br>Information: The Hollow Tree in the garden hides a <br>burrow that leads to a series of Caves. Descending into <br>the Caves, Hunters can find Britta’s decapitated body. The <br>witch’s spirit is still bound to the body, but the only way to <br>communicate with her is with a Gift that allows it. In the <br>little house, Hunters can find Britta’s diary open on the <br>kitchen table. In the diary, the witch describes in detail</p><p>141<br>her agreement with Bastian to retrieve the Tinderbox from <br>the Caves, and the soldier’s insistence on having more mo-<br>ney after the reward. In the diary, Britta also regrets asking <br>for Bastian’s help, as the soldier turned out to be a stupid <br>opportunist.<br>Resets: Bastian will never be in Britta’s House, and the <br>Cat is busy collecting magic items to revive the witch, so <br>the situation in this Place is always the same, no matter the <br>Reset. <br>Caves under the <br>Hollow Tree<br>Descriptor: A series of caves that were once the home of a <br>witch, but are now uninhabited.    <br>Information: Traces of ancient magic and strange mar -<br>kings on the walls are the only evidence of what the Caves <br>once were. Britta’s headless corpse stands in the center of <br>the first room, her hands and feet making unconscious mo-<br>vements, making it clear that the body is not dead, but also <br>incapable of action.<br>Britta the Beheaded Witch<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a skilled witch who only desires a quiet <br>life. Since I no longer have a head, I cannot speak or utter <br>magic formulas. <br>Agenda: To find my head that Bastian threw in the river. <br>Information: Britta’s body will revive when two of her <br>three magical items are placed on her. In this state, Britta <br>will not be able to speak, but she will be able to write, in-<br>forming the Hunters that she knows where her head is and <br>will go to retrieve it. In the meantime, Britta will ask the <br>Hunters to retrieve the third object to complete her resur -<br>rection. <br>Britta the Witch<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a skilled witch who wishes only to live a <br>quiet life, using my powers only to help others.<br>Agenda: Stop the power of the Magic Tinderbox before the <br>Demonic Dogs inside it become too powerful.    <br>Gift - Britta’s Witchcraft:  Britta can perform various <br>rituals to achieve different effects: she can find someone or <br>something, she can change the weather in the area, or she <br>can communicate with and take control of an animal. All of <br>these rituals take about ten minutes to complete. Britta can <br>also dispel magic, a practice in which she is a true master. <br>In a single action, Britta can end a spell or block the power <br>of a Treasure of the Order until the end of the Scene. <br>Information: Britta will tell the Hunters the secret of the <br>Magic Tinderbox and that she can use her magic to stop the <br>disasters Bastian is causing, but there is a catch. Once the <br>Magic Tinderbox’s power is blocked, the three Demonic <br>Dogs inside will be released and must be defeated to send <br>them back into the magical object.</p><p>142<br>Demonic Dogs<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC  <br>(2 Wounds - 3 Dogs)<br>Descriptor: We are ancient demons and take the form of <br>dogs to mingle with humans. We can fly and with our fangs, <br>we tear at the soft flesh of our prey. <br>Agenda: To kill as many humans as possible and thereby <br>increase our power.     <br>Gift - Demonic Powers:  These creatures can fly, with <br>all the narrative benefits that brings. As supernatural crea-<br>tures, Demonic Dogs are immune to all effects of fear and <br>mind manipulation. Those who use magic against them <br>take 1 Penalty to all related Checks and must pay 1 additio-<br>nal Soma if it is required to activate magic. A Demonic Dog <br>can spend 1 Reset Token to increase its OL to Hard 7 for a <br>single action, but not to defend itself. <br>Information: When the Demonic Dogs are defeated, <br>Britta or a witch who has read her diary can place a ma-<br>gical seal on the Magic Tinderbox: <br>the object will lose some of <br>its power and become the <br>Treasure of the Order, <br>The Tinderbox of Se-<br>cond Chances (see page <br>28).  <br>Scenario Gifts<br>These Gifts represent special abilities related to The Last <br>Wish Scenario and can be acquired once conditions are <br>met. A Hunter can acquire one Scenario Gift. If they ac-<br>quire a new one during an Interlude, they will have to forgo <br>the previous one.<br>Déjà vu <br>Requirement: Witness the effect of one or more Resets.<br>By experiencing temporal shifts, you are able to notice the <br>small differences in the fabric of reality. Once per Scene, <br>you can spend 1 Soma to activate each of the following ef-<br>fects:<br>1. I’ve Already Got It: Y ou already have an item that be-<br>longs to the Place you are in, and if it is a unique item, no <br>one has noticed that it is missing.<br>2. I Was Already Here: Y ou can move to any Place you <br>can see from where you are without anyone being able to <br>stop you; to the eyes of anyone present, it will look as if you <br>have always been where you are now.<br>3. I’ve Seen It Before: The Storyteller will reveal the <br>effect of a particular Gift or equipment from an NPC in <br>front of you that you must have known or met before.<br>Note: This Gift can only be used when the use of a <br>spell that affects the normal flow of time is manife-<br>sted, like a Reset. Outside of this Scenario, it is up <br>to the Storyteller to determine if the Hunter can use <br>this Gift again.</p><p>143<br>Tremble, the Witches are Back<br>Requirement: Learn from Britta the magic of infusing an <br>object with the essence of life.  <br>A portion of your vitality is infused into an item in your <br>Equipment. As long as you have the item with you, once <br>per Session you can restore 1 Wound and 1 Soma by cal-<br>ling upon the power of your own soul. Y ou can activate this <br>effect even if you have already taken your last Wound and <br>are unconscious.  <br>The Last Wish <br>in Scenes</p><p>FIRST SCENE –  Entering Hei-<br>delberg<br>It is the same as on page 134, except that after Bastian’s Re-<br>set, Hugo will give the following information to the Hun-<br>ters:<br> ◆ Hugo is angry because Bastian bought some pots in <br>Britta’s name a week ago and never paid for them.<br> ◆ Bastian is no good and a layabout, bragging that he <br>is an honorably discharged soldier, but when asked <br>to show the medal he received for his discharge, he <br>always prevaricates. No one knows where he sleeps, but <br>he is always seen hanging out at the Drunken Hussar’s <br>Gambling House, a cheap dive known for bad wine and <br>gambling tables.<br>End of Scene: Hugo will then tell the Hunters that, if they <br>want to find Bastian, they must go to the Drunken Hussar’s <br>Gambling House; go to SECOND SCENE - The Drunken <br>Hussar’s Gambling House.</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513740374,"modifiedTime":1781513740374,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Vyla5NwZyg1KJYe9","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The Last Wish - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE –  The Drun-<br>ken Hussar’s Gambling House<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: You arrive at what appears <br>to be a small tavern, a few candles barely illuminating an <br>old, rotting building that has not been cleaned in years. Grim <br>faces stare at you, letting you know that you may not be wel-<br>come. Then the sound of a cup shattering makes you all turn <br>around: Bastian is standing at the bar, watching you with <br>wide eyes. He turns to the window behind him and makes a <br>desperate escape. <br>Place: The filthy Drunken Hussar’s Gambling House. <br>Time: It is late in the morning, but there are already many <br>customers at the tables trying their luck.<br>Information: Once Bastian is captured, the power of the <br>Tinderbox will be activated and the Hunters will find them-<br>selves back in Heidelberg’s Entrance Plaza, where they will <br>be approached by the Black Cat. It will be easy to tell by the <br>light in her eyes that this is no ordinary animal. The Cat <br>will lead the Hunters to Britta’s House, and here they can <br>get their hands on the witch’s diary and understand what is <br>happening. In the diary, Britta also notes the spell she used <br>to imbue three objects with her life force, which, when re-<br>trieved, can bring her back to life. A Pendant, a Shawl, and <br>a Ladle are drawn in the diary. The Cat will make it clear <br>that she can lead the Hunters to the objects, pointing with <br>her paw at the diary to figure out which one to start with. <br>End of Scene:  The Hunters must decide in which order <br>to retrieve the items, go to THIRD SCENE - The Retrieval.<br>2<br>1</p><p>144</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513740374,"modifiedTime":1781513740374,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"8lW7z1xZa29H5ALS","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The Last Wish - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE –  The Retrieval<br>Note: This Scene will be played three times to allow the <br>Hunters to retrieve all 3 of Britta’s items. The first two Places <br>visited must be Villa Wagner and the Golden Plate Tavern, <br>leaving the Drunken Hussar’s Gambling House for last. <br>Places: Villa Wagner, the Golden Plate Tavern, and the <br>Drunken Hussar’s Gambling House. <br>Time: Early afternoon, late afternoon, and evening. <br>Information: Depending on the Place, the following si-<br>tuations will occur.<br> ◆ Villa Wagner: Alena will be kind and helpful to the <br>Hunters and will gladly give them the Black Coral Pen-<br>dant if they ask for it. When the Hunters leave the Villa, <br>they will be ambushed by the Cutthroats (page 135) <br>hired by Bastian. <br> ◆ The Golden Plate Tavern:  Brigit will not want <br>anyone to enter her beloved kitchen, and the Hunters <br>must find a way to distract the cook and retrieve the <br>Devil’s Ladle. <br> ◆ The Drunken Hussar’s Gambling House:  Ulri -<br>ch will attempt to poison the Hunters as described on <br>page 136. Backed into a corner, Ulrich will say that <br>Bastian is planning to rob Villa Wagner’s Treasury to <br>get his hands on the family treasures. <br>End of Scene:  If the Hunters have not recovered all the <br>items, repeat this Scene at a new Place. If the Hunters also <br>recovered the Shawl at the Hussar and questioned Ulrich, <br>go to the FOURTH SCENE - Britta’s Return.</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513740374,"modifiedTime":1781513740374,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"hbNIHBjd0XfhGV4k","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The Last Wish - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE –  Britta’s Re-<br>turn<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: The little cat leads you back <br>to the house near the graveyard, and here, in the garden of <br>the house, it starts scratching on the bark of an old hollow <br>tree. At closer inspection, the tree appears to be the entrance <br>to caves descending into the darkness.<br>Place: Britta’s House and the old Hollow Tree leading to <br>her corpse. <br>Time: Late night. <br>Information: Upon recovering Britta’s body and appro-<br>aching her three objects, the witch will come back to life <br>but will be headless. Britta’s animated body will then lead <br>the Hunters to the nearby river to find her head. With this <br>bizarre task completed, the witch will come to her senses <br>and be able to explain to the Hunters the danger posed by <br>the misuse of the Magic Tinderbox. <br>End of Scene:  The Hunters have learned from Ulrich <br>about the robbery Bastian is planning at Villa Wagner, go <br>to the FIFTH SCENE - The Great Heist.<br>3 4</p><p>145</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513740374,"modifiedTime":1781513740374,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"CbVYmqjLnV5vrs32","name":"Scene 5","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The Last Wish - Scene 5</h2><p>FIFTH SCENE –  The Great Heist <br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  As you enter the large garden of Villa Wagner at dawn, a group <br>of shadows draws your attention, and Bastian’s shout forces everyone to turn around. The soldier <br>gestures nervously as he tells you with tears in his eyes, “Enough! Why are you always getting in my <br>way? Leave me alone!” Then Bastian gestures to his comrades, and the small group approaches you <br>menacingly. <br>Place: The large garden of Villa Wagner. <br>Time: The sun is rising, and soon the whole city will wake up. <br>End of Scene: Unwilling to risk his life, Bastian will try to escape after giving the order to his <br>people. If caught, he will activate the Magic Tinderbox for the umpteenth time and accidentally <br>summon the three Demon Dogs. Having dealt with this threat, the Hunters must now decide <br>what to do with Bastian. <br>5</p>"},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513740374,"modifiedTime":1781513740374,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"the-last-wish","collection":"Lost Stories","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","pages":"131-146"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513740374,"modifiedTime":1781513740374,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"yijZEQpOGEfmoGT0","name":"Journey of a Thousand and One Nights","pages":[{"_id":"O67mKKEaDtEFl7cB","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>Journey of a Thousand and One Nights</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> Lost Stories</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, pages 147-168.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights-p147-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513741649,"modifiedTime":1781513741649,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"UdyqSMdXvPTqSu2N","name":"Scenario Text","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Journey of a Thousand and One Nights - Scenario Text</h2><p>146<br>Journey of a Thousand <br>and One Nights<br> <br>A Scenario inspired by One Thousand and One NightsJourney of a Thousand and One Nights is a special Scenario constructed as a Scene Tree <br>(see page 100 of the Broken Tales Core Book) and is well suited for staging the final <br>confrontation with the Dark Presence, Sherazade the Weaver of Tales. This Scenario <br>takes place within a story told by Sherazade, an emissary of the One Who Plots in the <br>Shadows (page 196 of the Broken Tales Core Book). Awakening aboard a lost ship in <br>a mysterious archipelago, the Hunters must retrieve enough Tarì (Arabic gold coins) <br>to defeat powerful Djinn guarding the Dream Gate, the only way to return to the real <br>world.<br>In this Scenario, Sherazade can be introduced in two ways.<br>As an Enemy. She follows the normal rules of a Dark Presence: Hunters can capture her <br>once she is defeated in the Fourth Leg - The Execution of Sherazade. <br>As a future ally. The One Who Plots in the Shadows urged Sherazade to abuse her power <br>and lead the Weaver of Tales to self-destruction. In the Fourth Leg - The Execution of <br>Sherazade, she will be a prisoner of the Sultan. <br>Once upon a time...<br>Good evening my dear hosts, my name is Sherazade and I am a weaver <br>of tales. My words will take you to incredible worlds and follow the feats <br>of brave Hunters… however this story is not like the others and these <br>feats are not just imaginary. Will our heroes succeed in their quest? Or <br>will they perish, disappearing forever from the memory of time?<br>Safety Keywords: Blackmail / <br>Imprisonment / Toxic relationships <br>/ Animal violence / Slavery</p><p>147<br>The story that led us here...<br>Tired of the Hunters’ continued success, the One <br>Who Plots in the Shadows commands Sherazade to cre-<br>ate the deadliest of tales to eliminate the Hunters once <br>and for all. Since the power of Sherazade’s stories comes <br>from the emotions the weaver evokes in the audience, <br>Sherazade gives voice to the most powerful emotion she <br>possesses: grief over the loss of her sister, Dinarzad. Thus <br>a long tale is born, one that encompasses all the stories <br>the weaver told in the vain hope of saving her sister when <br>they were captives of the Sultan. Unable to cope with the <br>pain of those memories, Sherazade fell prey to her own <br>power and was eventually sucked into the story, as were <br>the Hunters. Now back in the Sultan’s court, the weaver <br>struggles to find a way back to the reality of Broken Eu-<br>rope. Absorbed by yet another of Sherazade’s tales, the <br>Hunters instead wake up on a great ship, where they see <br>an old acquaintance of theirs: Sinbad the Traveller of a <br>Thousand Seas.<br>How to manage the Scenario<br>This Scenario unfolds as a ship voyage, where each Leg <br>(randomly generated) will put the Hunters in front of a <br>specific mission to face. If the problem is solved, the Hunt-<br>ers will receive a Tarì. Each accumulated Tarì will make the <br>fight against the Djinn in the Dream Gate easier. <br>The Scenario unfolds as follows:<br>1. First Leg - The group generates a Type A Leg.  <br>2. Second Leg - The group generates a Type B Leg.    <br>3. Third Leg - The group generates a Type A Leg.    <br>4. Fourth Leg - The Execution of Sherazade.<br>5. Fifth Leg -The group generates a Type B Leg. <br>6. Sixth Leg - The group generates a Type A Leg.    <br>7. Seventh Leg - The group generates a Type B Leg. <br>8. Eighth Leg - The Dream Gate.<br>Each Leg, with the exception of the Fourth and Eighth, <br>presents a Place, Information, and a list of challenges to be <br>solved in order to obtain the Tarì. The Storyteller is then <br>free to develop the events according to their taste, and to <br>decide when to end the event and begin the journey again. <br>Each Leg should last a maximum of two or three Scenes, <br>the equivalent of a Campaign Encounter. In this Scenario, <br>calling for an Interlude will make the Fourth and Eighth <br>Legs more complex, as explained in the relevant sections. <br>To reduce the length of the Scenario, simply remove the <br>Third and Fifth Legs, and remove the Seventh and Eighth <br>Djinn in the Eighth Leg. <br>The unique nature of this Scenario may require a great deal <br>of improvisation on the part of the Storyteller, as each Leg <br>provides clues and potential situations, but doesn’t go into</p><p>148<br>as much detail as typical Scenarios. There are two ways to <br>manage this issue:<br>Preparation<br>The Storyteller creates all the Legs and sets up the Scenario <br>in its entirety before proposing it for the Session. With this <br>approach, the various Legs can be planned in detail, Places, <br>and NPCs can be added, and the Villain’s Journey rules on <br>page 43 can be used for additional ideas.<br>Improvisation<br>The Storyteller prepares nothing and details everything on <br>the fly, generating the Leg when it is actually played. This <br>system allows much more freedom for the table: for it to <br>work best, it is recommended that the Storyteller give the <br>Hunters all the Information they deem useful at the begin-<br>ning of the Leg, so the group can decide on their intentions <br>right away. <br>First Leg<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: The rocking of the waves ac-<br>companies your awakening. Startled, you jump out of your <br>bunks. You fell asleep the night before in an inn on the road <br>to Rome, and now, judging by what you can see through the <br>porthole of a ship’s cabin, you are on the high seas. Once at <br>deck, you can admire an entire crew of sailors, moving like <br>an efficient swarm of ants, working diligently to maintain the <br>course of a large sailing ship. “ Awake at last!” A rough, famil-<br>iar voice comes from behind you. It is that of Sinbad, an old <br>sea dog who served the Order long before you.<br>Place: Sinbad’s sailing ship. <br>Time: Early in the morning, the sun is high and bright. A <br>soft, warm breeze blows, gently moving the sails. <br>Initial Situation: Sinbad will greet the Hunters by trying <br>to calm their confusion. This is not the first time the old <br>sailor has ended up in a Sherazade story, and from what he <br>heard in Rome, the Hunters know what he is talking about. <br>Information: Sinbad will provide all of the following <br>info. <br> ◆ The Hunters and Sinbad have found themselves in one <br>of Sherazade’s stories. Sinbad was the first to wake up <br>and by talking to a sea Djinn he was able to get some in-<br>formation. To return to the real world, it is necessary to <br>pass through the Dream Gate, a magical portal located <br>on the last island of the great archipelago that the sailing <br>ship is passing through. The Dream Gate is guarded by a <br>group of very powerful Djinn, and each of them requires <br>a token to gain access to the door. What the Djinn crave <br>is the magical Tarì.<br> ◆ Several Legs will be required to reach the final island, <br>each of which will give the Hunters one day to retrieve <br>the Tarì. The coins are not simply hidden, but in the <br>1</p><p>149<br>possession of a character from the story. Resolving the <br>situations they encounter will be the only way for the <br>Hunters to receive the Tarì as a reward.<br> ◆ At the end of each day, the ship must leave port, because <br>a giant wave in the shape of a turned page will sweep <br>everything away, engulfing each island as if it had faded <br>into history. The only way to escape the wave and save <br>themselves from disappearing forever is to move on to <br>the next destination.<br>Sinbad is very excited about this voyage, which will allow <br>him to relive the glory of his youth <br>as a sailor. The Hunters know <br>that if they can keep the old sea <br>dog from getting bored, he will <br>do his best to make the Hunt-<br>ers’ journey easier. <br>After providing all this infor -<br>mation, you can create a First <br>Leg (A). <br>Sinbad the Traveler <br>of the Thousand Seas<br>Inspired by Sinbad of the Thousand and One <br>Nights (Allied)<br>Descriptor: I am an experienced traveler and have seen <br>every known land. I get bored easily if I’m not interested in <br>what I’m doing.<br>1 Wound<br>Opposition Level: Medium 5<br>Agenda: I am willing to do anything to experience <br>the thrill of discovery once again.<br>Special Agenda (Sherazade the Weav -<br>er of Tales):  I boast of knowing every story <br>and legend, and I love to mock those who pride <br>themselves on limited knowledge. I want to rid-<br>icule the stories Sherazade tells, highlighting the <br>truths that only I know.<br>Gift - Traveler of a Thousand Places:  <br>Sinbad has seen the whole world and much <br>of what the Broken Tales hide. In the <br>course of a Scene, a Hunter can invoke <br>his help to obtain information or <br>create an additional Descriptor <br>that represents a specific area <br>of Sinbad’s knowledge. But <br>the old sailor is an eccentric <br>type, and to provide his help <br>he first must be entertained. <br>The Storyteller will evaluate <br>the current situation and</p><p>150<br>Sinbad’s level of boredom. A Hunter can capture Sinbad’s <br>interest with creative actions, as long as they’re appropriate <br>to the current Scene.<br>Gift - I Know How to Do It:  Once per Scene, a Hunter <br>can get 1 Additional Success in their Check, asking Sinbad <br>for helpful advice. As with Traveler of a Thousand Places, <br>Sinbad needs to be intrigued before helping. Sinbad be-<br>gins each Leg bored. If the Hunters take the old sailor with <br>them, the excitement of discovery will immediately relieve <br>Sinbad’s boredom. Alternatively, the Hunters can ask Sin-<br>bad to stay on the ship, and if they fulfill one of his requests, <br>he will not be bored.<br>Sinbad Requests<br>Roll 1 die or choose.<br>1: Bring me a rare and precious item. <br>2: Bring me someone who can tell me a good story.<br>3: Bring me rare and tasty food. <br>4: Bring me a strange person. <br>5: Bring me a sincere promise.<br>6: Bring me a picture of a beautiful place.<br>If Sinbad suffers all his Wounds, he will be out of action for <br>the current and next Leg. In addition to his normal Gifts, <br>Sinbad also has the Gift - The Sailing Ship.<br>Gift - The Sailing Ship:  Sinbad’s large sailing ship con-<br>tains all kinds of comforts and knowledge that the old sail-<br>or only makes available to his guests. At the end of a Leg, <br>if Sinbad is not bored, he will allow each Hunter to choose <br>one of the following effects:<br>1. Rest in the Sultan’s Rooms: To recover 1 Wound.<br>2. Meditate in the Lotus Hall: To recover 3 Soma.<br>3. Study in the Library of Alexandria:  To obtain the <br>effect of a Descriptor Specialization in the following Leg.<br>4. Access Solomon’s Treasury: To obtain a Treasure <br>of Order for the next Leg. <br>5. Call of Duty (from the Fifth Leg onwards only):  <br>A new Hunter is summoned into the story by Sherazade, <br>allowing the group to switch members or replace a Hunter <br>who is out of action.</p><p>151<br>“A” Legs (First, Third, and Sixth)<br>Roll 1 die to determine the Leg. Increase the result by 1 <br>if you obtain a Leg you have already faced. Alternatively, <br>choose directly which Leg you prefer to play.<br>1A The Merchant and the Djinn<br>The story that led us here...<br>The ship lands on a small island where there are only two vil-<br>lages of poor people. Some of the villagers throw themselves at <br>the Hunters’ feet, begging for their help. A powerful Djinn is <br>killing an innocent person every day, and the blame lies with <br>a clever Merchant who escaped the spirit’s wrath by claiming <br>to be honor-bound to settle a debt. Thirty days ago, the Mer-<br>chant accidentally killed the Djinn’s son in a heated argument <br>over date seeds. Enraged, the Djinn showed up to behead the <br>culprit, but the cunning man asked for a day to settle some <br>unfinished business before he died. The Merchant then fled <br>and has not been seen since. The Djinn demanded the entire <br>population find him, or else he would cut off the head of an <br>innocent person every day. <br>Place: It is not possible to leave the island without a ship. <br>Therefore, the Merchant must be hiding in one of the two <br>villages. <br>Information: The Djinn arrives in the village at dusk to <br>see if the Merchant has been captured. The Merchant can-<br>not have fled the island, as the Hunter’s ship is the first to <br>arrive in over a month.<br>Challenges: The Merchant has simply disguised himself <br>as a local woman, and is impatiently awaiting the arrival <br>of a ship like the Hunters’ . The Djinn is furious and resents <br>being tricked. <br>How to get the Tarì: If the Hunters succeed in appeasing <br>the Djinn’s wrath without killing the Merchant, the Mer -<br>chant will give them the Tarì as a thank-you gift.<br>The Merchant<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a cunning old Merchant, I am a good <br>mimic and I love to disguise myself. <br>Agenda: Escape the island by secretly boarding a ship, or <br>find a way to appease the Djinn’s wrath.</p><p>152<br>The Furious Djinn<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a powerful Djinn, skilled with a scimitar. <br>I hate lies and those who break agreements.<br>Agenda: To avenge my son’s death by punishing the Mer -<br>chant who caused it. <br>Gift - Frenzied: When the Djinn suffers 1 Wound, it can <br>immediately attack with its giant scimitar to strike the one <br>who did the damage. <br>2A The Island Fish<br>The story that led us here...<br>Sinbad’s ship has docked at a large island dense with plants <br>that bear delicious fruits. The entire crew has gone ashore to <br>resupply, but what no one can imagine is that this lush land is <br>actually resting on the back of a giant, sleeping fish. While the <br>sailors are busy harvesting fruit, the island begins to tremble <br>and the land cracks. Sinbad begs the Hunters to save his men, <br>or no one will be able to sail the ship to continue the journey.  <br> <br>Place: A large natural island filled with plants and fruits. <br>Information: Sailors are divided into six groups, each in a <br>different part of the island. <br>Challenges: Traveling by land is very dangerous due to the <br>constant movements of the Island Fish. When a group of <br>sailors is rescued, roll 1 die: if you roll a 6, the sailors are <br>carrying a strange barrel found in the vegetation. If a 6 is <br>never rolled, the barrel is automatically in the hands of the <br>sixth party.<br>How to get the Tarì: Found inside the barrel.<br>Threat – The Island Fish<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: The earth cracks and trees fall on those unlucky <br>enough to be nearby. Seawater slowly submerges everything. <br>Gift - The Island Moves!:  Moving around the island is <br>very dangerous, rescuing a group of sailors requires at least <br>2 Checks against this Threat, one to get to the group and one <br>to return to the ship. The Check can only be made by the <br>Hunter leading the search party. For each failed Check, roll <br>1 die and apply the result to one of the Hunters.<br>1: Suffers 1 Wound caused by falling trees and rocks.<br>2: Receives 1 Penalty at the next Check due to mud.    <br>3: Loses 1 Soma due to fatigue. <br>4: Loses 1 Equipment in the waves of the sea.<br>5: Loses more time than expected. Increase the OL of this <br>Threat by 1 for those performing the next Check.</p><p>153<br>6: The Hunter falls into a crevasse and remains separated <br>from the others, they will have to do a Position Check to <br>return to the ship or be lost until the end of this Leg. <br>3A The Roc<br>The story that led us here...<br>The Hunters are jolted from their beds, and to their horror, <br>they discover that the ship is tilting dangerously. Climbing <br>on deck, they see a giant bird perched on the bow, apparent-<br>ly intending to build a nest. However, the weight of the bird <br>threatens to sink the ship...<br>Place: Sinbad’s ship in the middle of the sea. <br>Information: Sinbad warns the Hunters that they must <br>move the Roc calmly, for if the creature takes off at full <br>power, it could completely overturn the ship. In the dis-<br>tance, a huge spire of stone juts out of the sea. Perhaps that <br>is where the Roc came from.<br>Challenges: Move or knock down the Roc without mak-<br>ing it shake the boat. The stone island in the middle of the <br>sea is constantly battered by great waves, and among the <br>surrounding rocks are the remains of many nests that the <br>Roc attempted to build, but which were destroyed by the <br>fury of the sea. <br>How to obtain the Tarì:  When the Roc leaves the ship, <br>the Tarì can be found in the remains of its nest.<br>Roc<br>See Dark Presence on page 13.<br>4A Monkey Island<br>The story that led us here...<br>It is early morning when the Hunters are summoned by Sin-<br>bad: the ship has landed on a large natural island full of cute <br>little monkeys. The problem is that seven sailors disappeared <br>during the night, and tracks found on the deck lead Sinbad <br>to believe that the monkeys kidnapped them. Sinbad asks the <br>Hunters to explore the island and rescue his men. <br>Place: A large wild island with a small volcano in the mid-<br>dle. <br>Information: The Monkeys’ tracks seem to lead straight <br>to the volcano, but what the Hunters don’t know is that the <br>poor animals bring the unfortunates they capture to the <br>volcano to appease the hunger of a ferocious Giant who, in <br>the absence of prey, pounces on primates.<br>Challenges: Monkeys (2 per Hunter) trying to scare off  <br>the Hunters by throwing rocks from trees, or laying traps <br>and false trails; the Elephant-Eared Giant that lives in the <br>volcano. <br>How to get the Tarì:  It is guarded by the Monkeys and <br>they will give it to the Hunters if they eliminate the Giant.</p><p>154<br>The Monkeys<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are agile and fast, and we move quickly <br>through the trees to escape threats. <br>Agenda: Satisfy the Giant’s hunger to prevent it from de-<br>vouring us. <br>The Elephant-Eared Giant<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (6 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a huge Giant of herculean strength, I <br>have no natural predators on the island. I consider all crea-<br>tures smaller than me to be weak, and I am not afraid that <br>they will harm me.<br>Gift - Elephant Ears: As a free action, the Giant can use <br>its massive ears to create a gust of wind capable of hurling <br>a human thirty feet. The gust affects 2 targets and can be <br>avoided with a Defense Check. If someone is pushed back, <br>roll 1 die:  <br>1-2: Loses an Equipment.<br>3-4: Suffers 1 Wound.<br>5-6: Ends up in impassable terrain, requiring a Check to <br>get out.  <br>5A An Old Bride<br>The story that led us here...<br>The ship lands on a large island that is familiar to Sinbad. <br>The old sailor goes down with some of his crew to resupply, <br>but only one of his men returns. The survivor tells the Hunt-<br>ers that Sinbad once married the daughter of the island’s king, <br>but she died shortly after the wedding. According to local tra-<br>dition, Sinbad was buried alive with his bride to be united <br>with her forever. The cunning traveler, however, managed to <br>escape, and now that more than fifty years had passed, he be-<br>lieved that all had been forgotten by the new ruler. But to his <br>astonishment, Sinbad and his people found themselves in the <br>presence of a centenarian king who did not hesitate to return <br>poor Sinbad to the tomb of his wife. <br>Place: A large pyramid-shaped tomb not far from the <br>town where the island’s ruler resides. <br>Information: The tomb is protected by a notorious order <br>of Guardians who are said to devour intruders alive. <br>Challenges: The tomb is patrolled by over a hundred <br>Guardians. Entering it requires some sort of distraction. <br>On the east side of the tomb, there is a crack in the wall <br>through which a person can safely pass. While waiting for <br>it to be repaired, a team of six Guardians stands watch by <br>the wall. The king is the only one who insists on enforcing</p><p>155<br>the old traditions, but no one dares to contradict him. The <br>old monarch lives protected by hundreds of guards, but his <br>death would end the absurd law. <br>How to get the Tarì:  In the funeral ritual, the groom is <br>given seven loaves of bread and some water. Back on the <br>ship, Sinbad takes a bite of the last loaf, breaking a tooth on <br>the Tarì hidden inside. <br>Guardians of the Tomb <br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are an order of fighting Guardians, and <br>our vow of loyalty comes before all else. Only the taste of hu-<br>man flesh can distract us from our duty.<br>Agenda: Defend the tomb from intruders. <br>6A The Crystal Cliffs<br>The story that led us here...<br>Overwhelmed by a strong current, the ship is pushed toward <br>a large group of rocks that Sinbad recognizes as very danger-<br>ous. The crystal that makes up the rocks is fragile, but also <br>extremely sharp, and touching them would damage the ship’s <br>hull. Beneath the crystal layer, the “rocks” are made up of all <br>sorts of precious stones, and in each of them lies a real trea-<br>sure. Even though the main goal is to get out unharmed, there <br>might be a Tarì among all the riches.  <br>Place: A large group of crystal rocks reflecting the sun-<br>light.<br>Information: It’s not easy to shatter the crystal without <br>dangerous shards flying everywhere. Sinbad can keep con-<br>trol of the ship, but it will be up to the Hunters to clear the <br>way. <br>Challenges: Destroy the crystal rocks that block the path <br>and recover valuable items from the inner rocks. At least 4 <br>rocks must be cleared to cross this part of the sea. <br>How to get the Tarì:  If the Hunters find at least 5 valu-<br>ables, the Tarì will also be in the sixth rock.</p><p>156<br>Threat – Crystal Rock<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: I am a fragile, sharp agglomeration of crystal. <br>The wrong vibration can make me explode.        <br>Note: The Storyteller rolls 1 die or chooses from the list to <br>complete the Threat Descriptor. <br>1: A flock of seagulls nested among the rocks. <br>2: Part of me juts underwater dangerously. <br>3: My crystal is harder than normal. <br>4: I am, in reality, a floating block moving without control.<br>5: My crystal reflects sunlight much more intensely than nor -<br>mal. I blind those who approach.<br>6: I am filled with subtle overgrowths extending in every di-<br>rection.<br>Gift - Sensitive to Vibration:  If a crystal is destroyed <br>without obtaining a positive Outcome on a Check, the ship <br>receives 1 Damage Token. The person who caused the explo-<br>sion gets 1 Wound and loses 1 Soma. If there are 2 or more <br>Damage Tokens on the ship at the end of the Leg, Sinbad will <br>not be able to use his Gift - The Sailing Ship, regardless of <br>whether he is bored or not, and will go directly to the next <br>Leg.  <br>“B” Legs (Second, Fifth, and Seventh)<br>Roll 1 die to determine the Leg. Increase the result by 1 if you <br>obtain a Leg you have already faced. Alternatively, choose di-<br>rectly which Leg you prefer to play.<br>1B Raging Rocs<br>Note: This Leg can only be played after Leg 3A - The Roc. If <br>the Hunters have not yet faced it, consider this a 1A roll.<br>The story that led us here...<br>Two huge winged figures appear in the sky, identical to the large <br>bird that tried to nest on the ship. The creatures have huge boul-<br>ders in their talons and seem intent on dropping them on the <br>deck. Sinbad begs the Hunters to save the ship before he cau-<br>tiously flees below deck.  <br>Place: Sinbad’s ship in the middle of the sea. <br>Information: Sinbad has hidden a Roc egg that he secretly <br>retrieved from the nest the last time around. The old sailor is <br>too greedy to return it, and intends to use the Hunters to get <br>rid of the two Rocs. <br>Challenges: Deflect the fall of the 4 boulders the Rocs in-<br>tend to drop on the ship and convince Sinbad to return the <br>egg.<br>How to get the Tarì: When the egg is returned, one of the <br>Rocs will drop the coin on the deck of the ship. <br>Roc<br>See Dark Presence on page 13.</p><p>157<br>2B The Elephant Cemetery<br>The story that led us here...<br>The ship lands on a small island that looks like an elephant <br>graveyard. Another ship has landed on the opposite side, fly-<br>ing a pirate flag. Sinbad will tell the Hunters that the island is <br>home to a community of peaceful elephants and an old Giant <br>friend, Rull. The pirates are ivory hunters, and Rull and the <br>elephants may be in danger.<br>Place: A small island full of vegetation and elephant bones. <br>Information: The Pirates have captured almost all of <br>the elephants and used them as hostages to force Rull to <br>surrender. Not content with taking all the ivory from the <br>graveyard, they have set up a veritable factory in the Giant’s <br>hut, cutting the tusks from the elephants that are still alive. <br>Rull has been badly wounded by the Pirates and, even if <br>freed, will be unable to help the Hunters. <br>Challenges: Defeat the Pirates to free Rull. The Pirate <br>Captain is a cunning old buccaneer, and if he understands <br>the Hunters’ strength, he will use Rull as a hostage to force <br>their surrender. In total, there are twenty Pirates plus the <br>Captain on the island. However, there are only eight on <br>their ship.<br>How to get the Tarì:  If Rull is freed, he will donate the <br>coin as a thank you. <br>Ivory Seeking Pirates<br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are ruthless pirates who win every battle <br>with our sabers and guns.    <br>Agenda: Obey the captain’s orders. <br>Gift - Pirate Crew: A Pirate increases their OL by 1 when <br>the Captain is present. <br>Captain of the Ivory Seeking <br>Pirates<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am an old sea wolf and I have faced all kinds <br>of adventures. I am too old to be afraid of anything. <br>Agenda: Earn as much as possible and risk as little as pos-<br>sible. <br>Gift - Old Bastard: The Captain is adept at using the sit-</p><p>158<br>uation to his advantage. Once per Exchange, if he suffers <br>1 Wound, he can sacrifice a Pirate in his place, placing the <br>casualty between himself and the threat at the last second. <br>Once per Scene, the Captain can interrupt the effect of a <br>Gift that instills fear or restricts the actions of his Pirates <br>toward an enemy by telling them how he overcame that <br>problem before. <br>3B Aladdin of a Thousand <br>Wishes<br>The story that led us here...<br>The ship arrives at an island ruled by a young Sultan named <br>Aladdin. Evil rumors of his deeds are whispered: it is said <br>that he came to the throne by usurping the old regent, who <br>was loved and well-liked by all. Aladdin seems to have a very <br>powerful Djinn at his service, carrying out his every wish <br>without fail. In reality, the Sultan has allowed himself to be-<br>come more and more perverted, because being able to accom-<br>plish anything he wants, he is plagued by a boredom that he <br>cannot satisfy in any way. The inhabitants of the island are <br>terrified by his constant and absurd demands, which often <br>result in deadly games.  <br>Place: A large and wealthy city where ships from all over <br>the world dock.<br>Information: The city is kept under control by the Eyes <br>of Aladdin, giant eyeballs that suddenly appear on the walls <br>of houses. This, too, is the result of the young Sultan’s wish <br>to be sure that no one is plotting behind his back. In the <br>slums of the city, Jasmina, Aladdin’s young wife and daugh-<br>ter of the former king, has taken refuge. The girl fled after <br>her husband showed the first signs of madness, and she <br>tries in every way to help the people of the city. Everyone <br>knows that the only way to depose him is to take away the</p><p>159<br>lamp that grants his every wish. Jasmina knows of a secret <br>passage that leads into the Sultan’s palace, as it is the same <br>one she used to escape.<br>Challenges: Take the lamp from Aladdin, who lives holed <br>up in his palace, protected by a large army of soldiers who <br>constantly patrol the city looking for any potential threat.<br>How to get the Tarì: Once retrieved, the magic lamp will <br>turn into the coin. <br>Aladdin the Mad Sultan<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am drunk with the power the lamp gives me <br>and I demand that the whole world do as I command. I have <br>a background as a street thief and know all the tricks of the <br>trade.      <br>Agenda: To find something to kill my terrible boredom.<br>Gift - Wishing Lamp: Whatever Aladdin wishes for will <br>be granted by the Djinn who lives in the lamp. As an action, <br>Aladdin can rub the lamp and ask for the following wishes:<br>1. Eliminate:  (as an action) The target is somehow <br>knocked out and suffers all the remaining Wounds, or is <br>teleported to a place where they cannot harm Aladdin. The <br>target can make a Defense Check to avoid the effect of the <br>wish, but will still take 1 Wound even if it succeeds.<br>2. Create:  (1 time per Scene) Aladdin creates up to 4 <br>Monsters to do his bidding.<br>3. Block: (as an action) Aladdin will remove the effect of <br>a spell or mind control from a subject. Alternatively, he can <br>prevent the use of a Gift that he has already seen in action <br>in the Scene.<br>Aladdin has already made some wishes to make himself <br>more powerful, so he can act up to 3 times in an Exchange <br>(but not back-to-back).<br>City Guards<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are skilled soldiers defending the city.      <br>Agenda: We obey Aladdin’s orders because we fear his <br>wrath, but we also want to stop his madness. <br>Jasmina the Brave<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am the true ruler of the island and would <br>give my life for my people. I am charismatic and skilled with <br>a scimitar.    <br>Agenda: Defeat Aladdin and restore the island’s fortunes.  <br>Monsters Summoned by Aladdin<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC  <br>(2 Wounds - 4 Monsters)<br>Descriptor: We are mindless monsters, using claws and <br>tentacles to snatch prey.</p><p>160<br>Threat – Eyes of Aladdin<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: Magic eyes that keep watch on the whole city. <br>Gift - Big Brother:  At the beginning of each Scene, a <br>stranger in the city must make a Defense Check against this <br>Threat. Roll 1 die and apply the result to all subjects who <br>failed.<br>1-2: Aladdin learns 1 Gift of the observed subject. During <br>a confrontation with Aladdin, the learned Gift is automat-<br>ically considered blocked by the third effect of the Gift - <br>Wishing Lamp. <br>3-4: Aladdin turns an unsuspecting passerby into a Mon-<br>ster to attack the foreigners.    <br>5-6: A lightning bolt springs from the eye, dealing 1 <br>Wound to the target. A Defense Check can prevent this ef-<br>fect.<br>4B The Forty Thieves<br>The story that led us here...<br>The ship lands on a large, mostly deserted island with only <br>one town. In the harbor, the Hunters meet Baba, a poor man <br>begging for help in rescuing his brother, who has been kid-<br>napped by a band of terrible Thieves. They live in an oasis <br>near the city, but no one has ever been able to pinpoint the <br>exact location of their lair. Baba knows the magic word to <br>access the hideout, having heard his brother speak of it. He <br>will lead the Hunters to the oasis, promising them a share of <br>the Thieves’ treasure as a reward. <br>Place: A large oasis in the desert, full of palm trees and <br>waterholes. <br>Information: In fact, Baba has already killed most of the <br>Thieves with the help of Dirana, a skilled slave girl in his <br>service. However, the woman is trapped in the gang’s secret <br>lair, and Baba plans to free her and recover the treasure. His <br>goal is to get the Hunters to fight the remaining ten Thieves <br>and lock himself in their lair, waiting for the survivors of <br>the battle to leave. Baba will not tell anyone how to open the <br>lair, saying that he cannot fully trust the Hunters without a <br>demonstration of their good faith. <br>Challenges: Confront the ten remaining Thieves, pre-<br>venting Baba from entering the secret lair alone and closing <br>the door behind him. Dirana is a fearsome fighter and, once <br>freed, will face the Hunters to defend her master.<br>How to get the Tarì:  If Baba fails to lock himself in the <br>cave, he will offer the coin to the Hunters for their services, <br>begging them to let him live. <br>Baba the Poor Conman<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a cunning, poor man who struggles to get <br>by. My greed is matched only by my nerve.<br>Agenda: Use others to eliminate the remaining thieves and <br>keep the treasure all to myself.</p><p>161<br>Dirana the Faithful Slave<br>OL Hard 7 - Main NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a fighting slave and fear nothing and no <br>one. My kicks can even cut through metal as if it were plain <br>paper.<br>Agenda: Baba saved my life and now I will do the same to <br>repay him. <br>Gift - Death Machine: As deadly as she is agile, Dirana <br>can act 2 times during an Exchange. <br>The Thieves<br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are looters, skilled with scimitar and sling. <br>Our numbers are our strength.<br>Agenda: Protect our lair and discover the password to enter, <br>which only our late leader knew.<br>Gift - Band of Thieves:  A Thief increases their OL by 1 <br>as long as the total number of band members is greater than <br>the total number of enemies. <br>The Oasis <br>Descriptor: A large, lush oasis that the Thieves have trans-<br>formed into the perfect hideout. <br>Gift - The Lair:  While fighting inside the Oasis, Thieves <br>can benefit from the improvements they have made to the <br>place. Once per Exchange, one of these effects will be acti-<br>vated:<br>1. Trap: A large coconut falls on enemies, requiring a De-<br>fense Check against OL Medium 5 to avoid 1 Wound.<br>2. Shelter: A Thief can literally disappear from sight, re-<br>appear in another part of the Oasis, and then do their thing. <br>No one can stop this movement.<br>3. Wave: A jet of water engulfs enemies, dragging them <br>away. Up to 3 targets in a thirty-foot area must make a De-<br>fense Check against OL Medium 5 to avoid being tossed to <br>the ground. <br>5B The Sleeping Man<br>The story that led us here...<br>The ship lands in a large port city, where Sinbad meets Hazir, <br>an old friend of his. Hazir was a very wealthy merchant, but <br>now he has fallen on hard times. The man will explain to <br>the Hunters that one day he saw a beggar on the street who <br>looked exactly like him, and in order to take a little vacation <br>from his work commitments, he suggested an identity swap. <br>After a few days off, Hazir was ready to resume his role and <br>pay the beggar handsomely, but the beggar, made greedy by <br>the possibility of a life of wealth, had Hazir thrown out and <br>threatened him to never show his face again. Now the impos-<br>tor lives under the guise of Hazir, and the poor merchant does <br>not know how to regain his identity. <br>Place: A large and rich port city full of markets and ships <br>from all over the world.<br>Information: The Imposter resides in Hazir’s palace, just <br>outside the harbor, and has enlisted twin warriors who are <br>known to be unbeatable when fighting as a pair. The Im-</p><p>162<br>poster has instructed his men to behead Hazir if he even <br>dares to approach the palace. Hazir has a moon-shaped <br>birthmark on his back that the Imposter does not: this is <br>a good way to show who is the original, as Hazir’s four <br>daughters are aware of this feature.<br>Challenges: Defeat the twin fighters and prove that the <br>Imposter is not the real Hazir.<br>How to get the Tarì:  If the Hunters can reach an agree-<br>ment between Hazir and the Imposter without using force, <br>the Imposter will give them the first coin he received as a <br>gift, the Tarì. <br>Hazir the Poor Merchant<br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am an honest merchant who has always <br>shown respect for others. My wealth is as great as my good <br>heart.    <br>Agenda: Return to my old life, perhaps without punishing <br>the beggar, for I understand the reasons for his selfishness.  <br>The Imposter<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a poor beggar who pretends to be Hazir. I <br>am good at adapting to any situation.<br>Agenda: To keep the life that was gifted to me. I am not evil <br>and therefore I can play the role of the good Hazir well.   <br>The Four Daughters of Hazir <br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are the Daughters of Hazir and we love our <br>father because he taught us kindness and humility.  <br>Hazir’s Guards<br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are well-trained in the protection of our <br>master.<br>Agenda: Protect Hazir from all threats / Eliminate the beg-<br>gar who persecutes our master.</p><p>163<br>Fury and Wrath, the Two Deadly <br>Twins <br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: We are two Djinn fighters who watch each oth-<br>er’s back. There is no match for our pair fighting technique.      <br>Agenda: Carry out every order of Hazir.    <br>Gift - Invincible Duo:  While fighting as a pair, Fury <br>and Wrath cannot take Wounds. Any attack or method of <br>wounding them will be blocked by one of the two Djinn. <br>To avoid this Gift, it is necessary to use an effect that affects <br>both Djinn at the same time or to separate them so that <br>they cannot support each other. <br>6B The Djinn King<br>The story that led us here...<br>The Hunters are summoned to the deck of the ship, where <br>they will find a mysterious old man smoking a water pipe. <br>The old man will ask them to run errands for him, and if they <br>do a good job, he will reward them with a golden Tarì. The <br>old man exudes a strong aura of power, and the Hunters un-<br>derstand that the strange figure is hiding his true nature. The <br>ship lands on a large island and the old man claps his hands <br>in satisfaction: it is time to begin. The Hunters must find nine <br>golden columns scattered throughout the city and bring them <br>back to him so he can furnish his palace.<br>Place: A large port city filled with temples and merchant <br>districts.<br>Information: Finding the columns is only a matter of <br>time for the Hunters, but they will encounter several people <br>who need help. Even if they don’t know it, spending time <br>with others will earn the Hunters a positive rating from the <br>Djinn King. <br>Challenges: Each column requires 1 hour of time and at <br>least one Position Check. The list below shows where they <br>can be found. Using Gifts and Descriptors for additional in-<br>formation can speed up the search. For every two columns <br>found, roll 1 die to see who needs help, up to a maximum <br>of 3 requests. <br>The Columns<br>First: On the pier in the harbor, covered with seaweed and <br>shells. / Second: In a dung-covered square used as a hitch-<br>ing post for horses and camels. / Third: In the inner court-<br>yard of a merchant’s mansion. / Fourth: In the middle of <br>an olive grove, not far from the city walls. / Fifth: In the art <br>collection of a wealthy Vizier. / Sixth: In the middle of a <br>notorious tavern, as a pillar supporting the roof. / Seventh: <br>In the wall of a watchtower. / Eighth: In the bedroom of the <br>first daughter of the Sultan. / Ninth: In the hold of Sinbad’s <br>ship, stolen and then forgotten by the old sailor years ago.<br>The Needy<br>1: A poor farmer has no money to buy seeds for the coming <br>season. Without the precious seeds, he will not be able to <br>feed his family. <br>2: A child just five years old is lost and has wandered clear <br>across the city from where he lives. He struggles to speak <br>and is frightened, but no one seems to care about him. <br>3: A poor sailor was poisoned by some villains because he <br>won too much at dice. If he does not get an antidote he will <br>die. <br>4: A merchant was robbed of a precious gold crown he <br>had bought for his daughter’s wedding. Without the crown,</p><p>164<br>promised as a gift to the groom’s mother, the wedding will <br>be canceled and the man will have no peace. <br>5: A brave slave girl rebelled against her tormentor, who or-<br>dered her to be hanged in the marketplace as punishment. <br>Everyone looks on in horror, but no one dares to intervene. <br>6: An old blind man has lost his faithful dog that helps him <br>get around town. The animal has been taken by a greedy <br>merchant, attracted by its ability to do as it is told.  <br>How to get the Tarì:  The old man will give the Tarì to <br>the Hunters if they help those in need, even at the cost of <br>restoring the columns.  <br>Fourth Leg - The Execution of <br>Sherazade<br>The story that led us here...<br>The ship lands on the largest island of the archipelago, and <br>Sinbad explains to the Hunters that the Sultan himself resides <br>in the beautiful palace that towers over the great city. As they <br>go ashore, the Hunters see several posters calling the people <br>to a great event: the Sultan’s wedding to the young Dinarzad <br>and the execution of her evil sister Sherazade (see the Broken <br>Tales Core Book, page 200 for details). The event is less than <br>an hour away, and Sinbad is concerned. If Sherazade, the <br>creator of this story, dies, what will happen to everyone in it?<br>Note: If Sherazade is an enemy of the Hunters, her execu-<br>tion will be a trap set to remove her enemies from the game. <br>Otherwise, she is truly a prisoner of the Sultan, who has <br>forced her to create a Shadow of her dead sister Dinarzad. <br>Place: The large town square, where a huge stage was set <br>up for the wedding and the execution.<br>Information: A large crowd of people spills out of each <br>street, providing good cover for the Hunters but also slow-<br>ing their movement. In the crowd are 4 Shadows of Sher -<br>azade, ready to intervene if anyone tries to stop the event. <br>Sherazade is handcuffed to a precious wooden and gold <br>chair. Behind her, a masked executioner wields a large <br>scimitar. <br>Meanwhile, the Sultan stands at center stage, hand in hand <br>with Dinarzad, dressed as the most beautiful bride of all.<br>Challenges: Hunters must stop the execution. Depending <br>on their relationship with Sherazade, they will face different <br>situations.<br>Enemy: Sherazade will have the Hunters fight the Sultan’s <br>Guards and the executioner to free her, and then she will <br>unleash the 4 Shadows against the Hunters.<br>Ally: Sherazade is clearly in shock and unable to resist the <br>Sultan’s psychological subjugation. The memory of what <br>happened has led her to create an alternate ending to the <br>story in which her sister can live happily with the Sultan <br>and Sherazade can sacrifice herself in Dinarzad’s place. <br>Breaking the Sultan’s hold on Sherazade will allow her to <br>regain control of the Shadows and punish the Sultan once <br>again by overcoming, once and for all, the painful memory <br>of what she suffered.</p><p>165<br>How to obtain the Tarì: After capturing or freeing Sher-<br>azade, the ghost of Dinarzad will appear to thank the Hunt-<br>ers and deliver the Tarì. <br>Sherazade (Dark Presence <br>Opponent/Allied)<br>See Core Book, page 200.<br>Shadows of Sherazade (Dark <br>Presence Opponent)<br>OL Medium 5 - (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We disguise ourselves as helpless citizens, but <br>in reality, we are ready to strike with our shadow sabers. <br>Agenda: Interfere with and complicate the lives of the Or -<br>der’s Hunters, preventing them from fulfilling their mission.<br>Gift - Shadow Body:  A Shadow is a darker, sadder ver -<br>sion of the original. They can speak and behave like the <br>character they are modelled after, but on a careful inspec-<br>tion they will appear cold and mechanical. Once per Scene, <br>a Shadow can appear or disappear from the darkness by <br>moving through walls and other solid obstacles. When it <br>spawns, it increases its OL by 1 because of the element of <br>surprise. When it suffers the Wound that would kill it, the <br>Shadow dissipates until its turn in the Exchange. At that <br>point, it will emerge from the darkness as if nothing had <br>happened. The Shadow will not reappear if the area the <br>Hunters are in is fully illuminated with light sources or <br>magic. The only way to truly destroy the Shadow is to ex-<br>pose it to sunlight.<br>Sultan’s Guards<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are the chosen Guards of the Sultan, and <br>with our warrior skills we protect our lord.    <br>The Executioner<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a ruthless enforcer, and with one stroke of <br>my scimitar I can cut a man in two.        <br>Gift - Art of Death: Wounds inflicted by the Executioner <br>are not easily healed and will remain for the next Leg unless <br>the Hunter can heal them with an Interlude, Gifts, or by <br>using the Gift of Sinbad - The Sailing Ship. <br>Epilogue of the Leg:  Whatever the outcome, Sherazade <br>is now in the hands of the Hunters. She can be used as a <br>Hunter for the next few Legs if the Players wish.</p><p>166<br>Eighth Leg - The Dream Gate<br>The story that led us here...<br>When the Hunters reach the end of their journey, where the <br>sea seems to fall in an endless cascade, there is a tiny island <br>with a large golden gate in the center. Eight Djinn, arms <br>crossed, sit in a circle, blocking the way to the gate. The mo-<br>ment of reckoning has come. Sherazade will explain to the <br>Hunters that they must defeat the Djinn to get through, and <br>if they lose, the One Who Plots in the Shadows will take them <br>all.<br>Place: The Island of the Dream Gate.<br>Information: The Djinn are not aggressive and will ask <br>the Hunters for a Tarì as a toll. For every coin the Hunters <br>hand over, one of the Djinn disappears. The Djinn collect <br>the payment, starting with the Eighth and going down to <br>the Second. The Djinn who remain without a token try <br>to intimidate the Hunters into leaving, unsheathing their <br>scimitars to protect the Dream Gate.<br>Challenges: Defeat the Djinn to gain access to the Dream <br>Gate.<br>Djinn of the Dream Gate<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC  <br>(3 Wounds - the Guardian and the Servant)  <br>(1 Wound - All other Djinn)  <br>(1 Djinn for each undelivered Tarì)<br>Descriptor: I am a powerful Djinn, my body is pure magic <br>and my strength transcends that of wretched humans. I pay <br>respect to those who show purity of spirit and courage.          <br>Gift - Duty: Each Djinn is immune to any effect of mind <br>control, deception, or magic that would influence them to <br>relinquish their duty.<br>Gift - Power of the Djinn:  Each Djinn has a different <br>power:<br>First - The Guardian:  If the Djinn receives 1 Wound, <br>roll a die; on a roll of 5 or 6, the person who inflicted the <br>Wound receives 1 in turn. <br>Second - The Warrior:  Once per Scene, even if a De-<br>fense Check to avoid a Djinn attack succeeds, the target still <br>suffers 1 Wound.<br>Third - The Mage: If an enemy uses a magic-related Gift <br>in the presence of the Djinn, they must spend 1 Soma or see <br>their spell dissolve without effect.<br>Fourth - The Servant: If a Djinn takes 1 Wound, it can <br>transfer it to the Servant who takes it instead.</p><p>167<br>Fifth - The Wise: Once per Scene, as an extra action, the <br>Djinn can block a Gift (except Dark Ego) that an opponent <br>has just activated. This Gift cannot be used again for the <br>rest of the Scene.<br>Sixth - The Thief:  After acting, the Djinn can make 1 <br>Hunter’s piece of Equipment disappear.<br>Seventh - The Sailor: After acting, the Djinn can move <br>to attack a new enemy without being blocked.<br>Eighth - The Storyteller:  If a Hunter activates their <br>Dark Ego, they must suffer a Wound even if they satisfy the <br>Activator.<br>Epilogue – The End of the Journey<br>If the Hunters defeat the Djinn, they will be able to pass <br>through the Gate and return to Broken Europe, Sherazade <br>and Sinbad with them. If they lose the battle, the Hunters <br>will awaken in a small, dark prison, captured by the One <br>Who Plots in the Shadows. The Storyteller will have to de-<br>cide whether to create a custom Scenario for the Hunters’ <br>escape, or to remove them from the Campaign and create <br>a new group with which to continue and perhaps find the <br>missing companions.</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513741651,"modifiedTime":1781513741651,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"journey-of-a-thousand-and-one-nights","collection":"Lost Stories","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","pages":"147-168"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513741651,"modifiedTime":1781513741651,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"CgQnxqfbq2x5GOBM","name":"Isolde the Singer of Lost Love","pages":[{"_id":"v6OZhgDoIjLDeOYz","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>Isolde the Singer of Lost Love</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> Lost Stories</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, pages 169-174.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/isolde-the-singer-of-lost-love-p169-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513742280,"modifiedTime":1781513742280,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"3UVybz0Xo2vu6nEy","name":"Scenario Text","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>Isolde the Singer of Lost Love - Scenario Text</h2><p>168<br>Isolde the Singer of <br>Lost Love<br>A Special Scenario inspired by Tristan and Isolde<br>Once upon a time...<br>The restless spirit of a young woman killed by injustice reclaims her lost love. Reborn as an emissary of the One Who Plots <br>in the Shadows, Isolde, the Singer of Lost Love, stalks the Hunters of the Order, convinced that it was the Order itself that <br>helped her rival in love plot the deception that led to the death of her beloved Tristan. But even the One Who Plots in the <br>Shadows has forgotten that the power of love can work true miracles and that one of his most trusted agents can become the <br>greatest threat.  <br>Safety keywords: Persecution / Depression / Possession</p><p>169<br>How to use Isolde <br>the Singer of Lost <br>Love<br>Isolde the Singer of Lost Love is a special Scenario <br>that can be used during the course of a Campaign. Once <br>introduced into the game, Isolde will become a recurring <br>NPC in Encounters during the Hunter’s travels, holding <br>a growing grudge against them. Isolde begins the game <br>as an agent of the One Who Plots in the Shadows, but <br>she can become a loyal Ally Dark Presence if the Hunters <br>show her that they value love.<br>Isolde may be introduced into the Campaign as an addi-<br>tion to an Encounter (page 253 of the Core Book) during <br>Hunter journeys. Alternatively, Isolde can appear during <br>an Encounter in Rome (page 60 of this book). Isolde <br>will never appear during Scenarios. <br>Isolde the Singer of <br>Lost Love <br>(Dark Presence Opponent)<br>Once upon a time, there was a couple united by an impossi-<br>ble love. His name was Tristan, and he was a distinguished <br>knight. Her name was Isolde, and she was the daughter of an <br>important Welsh nobleman. They first met by chance when <br>Isolde was tending to the wounds Tristan had received from <br>killing a terrible monster. An overwhelming bond of love <br>formed between them, even though they were both already <br>married. For many years there were secret meetings to con-<br>summate a forbidden love, increasingly tested by the suspi-<br>cions of their respective spouses. Finally, Tristan’s wife discov-<br>ered the betrayal. Furious and humiliated, the wife arranged <br>a diplomatic voyage to the kingdom where Isolde resided, <br>knowing Tristan would be excited to accompany her. The ship <br>fell into a planned ambush. Tristan fought bravely but even-<br>tually perished under the blades of the enemy. Isolde waited a <br>long time for her beloved’s arrival. When the messengers sent <br>in search of the ship returned, the young lover learned the <br>sad truth and fell into a deep depression. She stopped smiling, <br>stopped eating, and finally stopped breathing. As she fell into <br>her death sleep, she dreamed of her beloved Tristan... When <br>she opened her eyes again, the world had changed: she could <br>go anywhere she wanted and bend people to her will. She had <br>been reborn as a wraith, thanks to the power of the One Who <br>Plots in the Shadows. Her savior gave her the chance to take <br>revenge on Tristan’s wife, and Isolde didn’t hesitate, stalking <br>her until she went mad.</p><p>170<br>OL Medium 5 - (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am an invisible spirit born of death and love, <br>and I watch the Hunters to judge them. When I manifest my <br>power, my body becomes tangible.<br>Agenda: Spy on Hunters and report their weaknesses to the <br>One Who Plots in the Shadows / Test Hunters to understand <br>their relationship with love.<br>Gift - Immortal Soul:  Isolde is an intangible, invis-<br>ible presence that cannot be seen or harmed in any way. <br>Once per Scene, Isolde can possess an NPC by completely <br>controlling them. The possession is nearly undetectable, <br>though there is an unconscious “attitude” that Isolde adopts <br>regardless of who she is possessing. If the possessed NPC <br>suffers 1 Wound, Isolde is ejected from their body and <br>leaves the Scene. Note: For tips and advice on managing <br>this Gift, see page 171.<br>Gift - Punish Those Who Despise Love:  When the <br>rage against the Hunters reaches its peak, Isolde takes hu-<br>man form, loses her damage immunity, and lashes out at <br>the guilty. When this Gift is activated, Tristan, the Knight <br>who Conquers Death for Love, rises from the ground, <br>ready to assist Isolde. Isolde gains 2 Betrayed Love Tokens, <br>which she can add to those she has accumulated from pre-<br>vious Encounters. After acting in the Exchange, Isolde can <br>spend 1 or more Betrayed Love Tokens as an extra action <br>to activate the following effects, each of which can only be <br>triggered once during the same Exchange. <br>1. Blades for Traitors: A blade of light appears to strike <br>a target within thirty feet. Avoiding the attack requires a <br>Defense Check against OL Hard 7 to avoid 1 Wound. <br>2. Exile for the Hater:  Chains of light emerge from the <br>ground to immobilize a target, who can make a Defense <br>Check against OL Hard 7 to avoid them. A blocked target <br>cannot act and must use their entire Exchange action to <br>free themselves from the chains.<br>3. Freedom for the Lover: Isolde and Tristan disappear <br>and reappear at a maximum distance of thirty feet from <br>where they were. No one can stop this movement.</p><p>171<br>Tristan, the Knight who <br>Conquers Death for Love<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a knight devoted to my beloved Isolde <br>and have returned from the dead to protect her. <br>Agenda: Defend Isolde from those who would harm her.<br>Gift - Immortal Love: Tristan is immune to all Wounds <br>as long as Isolde has at least 1 Wound. The only way to <br>eliminate the Knight is to reduce Isolde to 0 Wounds, caus-<br>ing Tristan’s immediate destruction. When Tristan attacks <br>a target that has wounded Isolde, he increases his OL by 1 <br>and inflicts 2 Wounds. <br>•<br>How to handle Isolde the Singer of <br>Lost Love<br>When Isolde enters the Scene, the Storyteller decides or <br>rolls a die to see which NPC she possesses. Using this ad-<br>vantage, Isolde will deliberately try to create problems, us-<br>ing any hurt feelings caused by the actions of the NPCs or <br>Hunters involved in the Encounter. At the end of the En-<br>counter, Isolde will evaluate how the Hunters acted based <br>on two parameters:<br> ◆ If the Hunters take feelings into consideration and help <br>those in need even at the expense of their personal <br>goals, Isolde will not report them to the One Who Plots <br>in the Shadows. <br> ◆ If the Hunters did not care about the feelings of oth-<br>ers, Isolde will punish them by reporting information <br>about them to The One Who Plots in the Shadows, <br>which the Storyteller can use in the final confrontation <br>of the Campaign or to better prepare a future Assassin <br>(page 249 of the Broken Tales Core Book). Isolde re-<br>ceives Betrayed Love Tokens equal to half the number <br>of Hunters directly involved (rounded down). She can <br>use the Tokens in the confrontation with the Hunters <br>when she activates the Gift - Punish Those Who De-<br>spise Love. <br>Hunters can recognize Isolde’s presence by certain details <br>that the spirit includes when she possesses an NPC or ap-<br>pears as herself. She should have a certain way of speaking <br>or an attitude that will be characteristic of any possessed <br>NPC, regardless of their background or social status. When <br>the Hunters ask questions about the strange behavior, Isol-<br>de will either play dumb or try to shift the focus to the <br>problems she is creating for the Hunters to solve. <br>If the Hunters decide to corner the NPC because they real-<br>ize something is wrong, Isolde will appear suddenly to acti-<br>vate her Gift - Punish Those Who Despise Love. <br>Note: Introducing Isolde during an Encounter may require <br>a small amount of planning on the part of the Storyteller; <br>we have included a series of tables that can provide useful <br>hooks for Isolde’s management.</p><p>172<br>Who is possessed<br>1-2: An NPC not directly involved in the Encounter.<br>3-4: One of the Main NPCs involved in the Encounter.<br>5: A passing Dark Presence where the Encounter takes place. <br>6: An Agent of the Order (see page 59) present where the Encounter takes place.<br>How she tries to test the Hunters <br>1: Shows the Hunters the love felt by one of the NPCs in the Encounter.<br>2: Puts an innocent NPC at risk.<br>3: Helps an NPC express their feelings.<br>4: Highlights an injustice in front of everyone. <br>5: Reveals to everyone who the Hunters are.<br>6: Introduces a tense situation, for example, something about a Hunter’s past. <br>Attitude she repeats for every possession<br>1: Very low tone of voice and always speaks gently. <br>2: When she hears the word Love, she cannot hold back a tear.<br>3: When she talks about feelings she always puts her hand over her heart. <br>4: When she makes a request, she always ends her sentence with, “Please, in the name of <br>l o v e .”<br>5: She always carries a heart-shaped pendant, a gift from her beloved Tristan. <br>6: She speaks with a distinct Welsh accent.<br>Note: The attitudes in the list are in descending order of difficulty for Hunters. <br>Numbers 1 and 2 are attitudes that Players may not pick up on within a few <br>Encounters. Attitudes 3 and 4 are easy to identify but only occur in certain <br>situations. Attitudes 5 and 6 are highlighted by the Storyteller when the <br>Hunters talk to or observe the NPC in front of them.</p><p>173<br>Isolde the Spirit of Love<br>(Dark Presence Ally)<br>A spirit that fights for love, ready to punish those who trample <br>on the feelings of the innocent. <br>OL Medium 5 - (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am an invisible spirit who watches and judges <br>those who do not respect love. I can take control of ordinary <br>people by entering their bodies and using them to interact with <br>the world.                          <br>Agenda: To help all those who believe in love. <br>Gift - Possession: Once per Session, Isolde can take con-<br>trol of an NPC’s body to interact with the material world. <br>Isolde maintains a recurring behavior with each possession, <br>as explained on page 172. Isolde does not learn what her <br>victim knows. Upon awakening, the victim will be aware of <br>having been controlled by a spirit entity, but will not be able <br>to describe the experience. The possession ends when the <br>NPC suffers 1 Wound or at the end of the Scene following <br>the one in which this Gift was activated. <br>Gift - Love Triumphs:  At the beginning of the Scenar -<br>io, Isolde receives 3 Poltergeist Tokens, which she can use to <br>intervene in the material world and manipulate objects. A <br>Hunter may request Isolde’s help to manipulate an object or <br>to gain 1 Additional Success during a Check. The Storytell-<br>er evaluates the Hunter’s objective, and if it is in accordance <br>with Isolde’s Agenda, help is granted. If a Hunter’s actions <br>are in blatant conflict with Isolde’s Agenda, the spirit uses 1 <br>Poltergeist Token to get in the Hunter’s way by moving an <br>object or giving the Hunter 1 Penalty. Once per Scene, if the <br>Hunter’s actions help an NPC manifest or protect their feel-<br>ings, Isolde gains 1 Poltergeist Token.<br>Isolde the Singer of Lost Love in a <br>Broken Tales Campaign<br>By her very nature, Isolde, the Singer of Lost Love, is an ex-<br>cellent addition to a Broken Tales Campaign, as she brings a <br>great deal of variety to make the Encounters and non-Sce-<br>nario phases more interesting. Isolde is an emissary of the <br>One Who Plots in the Shadows, but if the Hunters can con-<br>vince her of their good intentions, she will become Isolde the <br>Spirit of Love, an allied Dark Presence, and will be able to aid <br>the Hunters in their endeavors.</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513742280,"modifiedTime":1781513742280,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"isolde-the-singer-of-lost-love","collection":"Lost Stories","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","pages":"169-174"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513742280,"modifiedTime":1781513742280,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"eehcUufOV29mGQnf","name":"The King's Awakening","pages":[{"_id":"hcphCf8116JRZGjT","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>The King's Awakening</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> Lost Stories</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, pages 175-200.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/the-kings-awakening-p175-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513743951,"modifiedTime":1781513743951,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"Emx6OOYY6QjtuCjx","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The King's Awakening - Setup</h2><p>174<br>The King’s <br>Awakening<br>A Scenario inspired by the Arthurian Myth<br>Once upon a time...<br>A mysterious island shrouded with mist appeared off  <br>the coast of England in the North Sea. According to the <br>tales of superstitious sailors, the strange island could <br>only be the legendary Camelot. The English Crown, <br>concerned about the growing unrest among the people, <br>sent a ship to understand the nature of this dark place, <br>but the expedition was swallowed by the mists and never <br>heard from again. The trusted royal advisor Merlin, <br>who had a history of working for the good of the Crown, <br>returned to London claiming to know the secret of the <br>mysterious island. Merlin’s tale prompted the Crown to <br>request the Order’s intervention to avert a threat that, <br>as the envelope reads, “could not be matched by all the <br>armies of the world. ”  <br>Security keywords: Desecration of graves / Coercion <br>through the use of force / Persecution</p><p>175<br>The story that led us here...<br>Throughout his millennia-long existence, Am-<br>brose the Sorcerer, known as Old Merlin, has controlled <br>the destinies of kingdoms and empires. He has used his <br>arcane powers to determine their glorious beginnings <br>and miserable ends, with the long list of beneficiaries <br>including the legendary Camelot. Merlin manipulat-<br>ed the ruler Arthur from an early age, prompting the <br>pure-hearted young man to unite many peoples under <br>his leadership. But in time, each of Arthur’s successes an-<br>gered Merlin, who grew resentful that, even ignorant of <br>the fact that he was merely a puppet, the king could turn <br>the Sorcerer’s every trick to the benefit of those most in <br>need despite Merlin’s selfish goals.<br>Blinded by envy, Merlin used his magic to strip Arthur of <br>all his Virtues, one by one, gradually transforming a just <br>and benevolent king into a bloodthirsty tyrant. Arthur’s <br>reign began to unravel as the actions of the now-mad rul-<br>er incited the populace to rebellion.<br>One of the many quests undertaken by Percival, a knight <br>in the service of Camelot, had led to the discovery of the <br>Holy Grail, an artifact that could guarantee eternal life. <br>Arthur had drunk from the magic cup, becoming im-<br>mortal and destined to rule forever. Backed into a corner, <br>Merlin realized that control was slipping out of his grasp. <br>Invoking the power of magic, he engaged in a battle with <br>the king. After a grueling battle that lasted more than a <br>hundred days, Merlin succeeded in sending Arthur into <br>a deep sleep, plunging all of Camelot into the cold waters <br>of the North Sea.<br>Tired and weak, Merlin took a long rest, leaving the <br>world safe from his machinations for several centuries. <br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunter...<br>Merlin has ignored or forgotten that the one who found <br>the Holy Grail, Percival the Seeker, also drank from the cup <br>before delivering it to Arthur. By the time Camelot sank, <br>Percival was on dry land, immortal in a world unknown to <br>him. After hundreds of years of revelry, the Seeker began <br>to go mad, until he decided to resurrect his old lord and <br>reclaim his “life as a noble knight. ”<br>Percival threw the now-empty Grail into the water, awak-<br>ening Arthur and enabling the lord to break Merlin’s spell. <br>Camelot then emerged from the water, along with the is-<br>land and all its people, unaware that they had been frozen <br>in time for centuries. <br>The awakening of the entire island has brought great up-<br>heaval: Arthur has given orders to prepare an army for the <br>conquest of Europe. The mad king’s idea is to gather all the <br>people of Avalon, turn them into undead, and march them <br>to the mainland. Guinevere, always an innocent victim of <br>Merlin’s machinations, has never accepted her husband’s <br>madness and has fled in search of help. Hiding among the <br>commoners of Camelot, the queen desperately seeks a way <br>to cure her beloved Arthur, who has mobilized the Knights <br>of the Round Table to find her and force her back to court.<br>Merlin, for his part, is determined to leave the dirty work <br>in the hands of the Hunters. While the latter will go to great <br>lengths to find Virtues to weaken Arthur, the old Sorcer -<br>er plans to recover and escape with the Virtue of Wisdom. <br>Only by returning the quality of wisdom to Arthur can his <br>senses be restored, turning him into a just and benevolent <br>king to the people once more, perhaps willing to make a <br>deal with the Hunters.</p><p>176<br>How to manage the Scenario<br>This Scenario unfolds as a long exploration of the island of <br>Avalon, with the Hunters moving from Zone to Zone, ini-<br>tially knowing only the location of Camelot Castle, which is <br>located in the center of the island. The Storyteller will then <br>place the map of the island in the center of the table, show-<br>ing the Zone that includes the beach where the Hunters’ <br>ships have landed.<br>Y ou can photocopy or print the map of the island on page <br>187.<br>Moving along the map<br>During the Scenario, Hunters move from one Zone to <br>another in an orthogonal way, so diagonal movement is <br>prohibited. Each Zone presents situations and possible En-<br>counters to be dealt with. At the beginning of the Scenario, <br>the Hunters are unfamiliar with the island and will learn <br>what each Zone contains simply by moving around. How-<br>ever, interaction with some NPCs may lead the Hunters to <br>information about a particular Zone and its contents. The <br>Storyteller decides what information will be revealed as the <br>Scenario progresses, keeping the narrative consistent and <br>updating the map accordingly.<br>When Hunters call for an Interlude, the usual rules apply, <br>with the exception that the NPC Agenda advances only for <br>Merlin, as explained on page 179.<br>The Zones<br>Each Zone is detailed with a Description and some infor -<br>mation about what can be found there. The Description <br>also includes NPCs and Threats that Hunters may choose <br>to face. When Hunters arrive in a Zone, the Storyteller rolls <br>on the Encounter Table (page 180) to determine if anyone <br>is present. This process adds NPCs with their own Agendas, <br>creating a random mix that can lead to fresh situations. The <br>Storyteller is free to add NPCs to the Scene as they see fit, <br>and is not obligated to introduce them immediately. <br>The Storyteller is then free to develop the events as they <br>wish. Some of the unique aspects of this Scenario may re-<br>quire a strong dose of improvisation, as each Zone provides <br>a number of clues and potential situations, but does not go <br>into too much detail compared to more classic Scenarios. <br>Therefore, there are several ways to approach the Scenario:<br>With prior preparation<br>The Storyteller describes all the Zones, adds details that <br>they find interesting, and completely sets up the Scenario <br>before proposing it for the Session. In this way, the explo-<br>ration can be planned in detail, and locations and NPCs of <br>Encounters can be added as needed in the chosen Zones, <br>rather than being randomly generated. <br>Improvising<br>The Storyteller does not prepare anything and details things <br>on the fly, relying on the information provided by the Zone <br>and the Encounter Table to determine which NPCs will be <br>present.</p><p>1<br>177<br>Playing the Scenario with Village <br>Rules<br>Because of its highly exploratory and survivalist nature, <br>this Scenario lends itself well to being played using the Vil-<br>lage rules presented in The Broken Ones. Only a few mod-<br>ifications are required.<br> ◆ The Villagers were part of the first expedition sent by <br>the Crown and suffered the unfortunate fate of Cap-<br>tain Boyce’s crew. Zone 2 - Beach (page 188) becomes <br>the initial Zone, while Zone 1 - Landing (page 188) is <br>nothing more than an empty beach where the Hunters’ <br>ship will land at the end of the Scenario.<br> ◆ The Storyteller integrates information from Zone 2 - <br>Beach (page 188) and Boyce’s journal to tell the story <br>of Glatisant’s attack and the ensuing massacre. Boyce’s <br>last wishes will guide the actions of the Villagers, who <br>must gather as much information about the island as <br>possible and await the arrival of the ship carrying the <br>Order’s Hunters.<br> ◆ The purpose of the Scenario for the Villagers is to ex-<br>plore the island and survive for at least 15 days. The <br>Storyteller accumulates 1 Day Token to keep track of <br>the time that elapses.<br> ◆ The other survivors will also settle in Zone 2 - Beach, <br>allowing a Player to use a possible Bond in case their <br>Villagers die. If the group is far from Zone 2 - Beach <br>(page 188), the Storyteller should consider introduc-<br>ing an Encounter with Survivors (page 180) to re-<br>plenish the ranks of the Villagers.</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513743952,"modifiedTime":1781513743952,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ehy7k0CfQv8oulZF","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The King's Awakening - Scene 1</h2><p>First Scene<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: After two days of sailing, the <br>silhouette of a large island appears before your eyes. Thick <br>blankets of fog shroud the coast, making it almost impossible <br>to discern its details. All you know is that all traces of the <br>previous expedition on behalf of the Crown have been lost. <br>“Hunters!” Old Merlin’s voice calls your attention. “We are <br>about to enter a land of great and ancient magic that has lain <br>dormant at the bottom of the sea for centuries. In Camelot, <br>time has stood still, and what you will see is beyond the com-<br>mon concept of reality as you know it. ” You know that Merlin <br>is a sorcerer of great skill, and even the Order seeks his advice <br>when their affairs are muddled by magic and spells. He will <br>therefore be your guide in this strange land as you attempt to <br>defeat the great threat it poses. <br>Place: A small uninhabited beach. A long promontory of <br>rocks forms a natural jetty to the mainland. <br>Time: Early in the morning, a thick blanket of fog makes it <br>difficult to see much.<br>Initial Situation: The crew, led by Captain Bennett, pre-<br>pares the ship for its stay, while Merlin summons the Hunt-<br>ers to the beach to instruct them.<br>Information: Merlin appears willing to dispel the Hunt-<br>ers’ doubts, but will omit any details that might reveal his <br>true intentions. Mainly, he will share with the Hunters what <br>he sees fit about the following.<br> ◆ In the center of the island stands the Castle of Camelot, <br>where a king named Arthur resides. He is a legendary <br>hero who became immortal after drinking from the <br>cup of the Holy Grail. Long ago, Merlin was able to seal <br>Arthur and the entire island in a magical sleep, pre-</p><p>178<br>venting the mad ruler from invading Europe. Arthur’s <br>goal is to turn all the island’s inhabitants into the living <br>dead and march with this army across the bottom of <br>the sea to the mainland.<br> ◆ Merlin will not reveal that he was the one who drove <br>Arthur mad by taking away his Virtues. He will say, <br>however, that Arthur’s old personality is kept in var -<br>ious objects hidden on the island as part of the spell <br>needed to seal the place under the sea. Retrieving them <br>and summoning their power in Arthur’s presence <br>will gradually bring him to his senses and weaken his <br>current tyrannical form. Facing Arthur without the <br>Virtues is an impossible challenge, and Merlin rec-<br>ommends finding at least three of them. From the in-<br>formation Merlin has gathered, it appears that Arthur <br>has no intention of leaving the castle, allowing plenty <br>of freedom for the search.<br> ◆ Merlin talks to the Hunters about 4 Virtues: Courage, <br>Faith, Innocence, and Love. The old wizard deliberately <br>omits mentioning Wisdom, as his secret goal is to re-<br>trieve it and escape from the island.<br> ◆ Camelot has been affected by the most powerful magic <br>ever cast: it has disrupted space and time, making this <br>place unique and sometimes maddening. The Hunters <br>must be prepared for anything and keep the inhabi-<br>tants in the dark about what has happened in the past. <br>Many villagers are unaware that they have been frozen <br>in time for hundreds of years, and causing panic would <br>only make the investigation more difficult.<br> ◆ Camelot is a land from a time when monsters and <br>magic were not hidden and feared by mankind, and <br>the Hunters must remember that.<br> ◆ Merlin gives the Hunters a small ocarina. When he <br>hears its sound, he will know that they need his help <br>and will manifest as soon as possible (see Gift - Wise <br>Advice, page 179).</p><p>179<br>Ambrose the Sorcerer known <br>as Old Merlin<br>Inspired by Merlin from the Arthurian Myth <br>(Neutral)<br>Descriptor: I am an ancient sorcerer, my body is weak, but <br>my magical power is unmatched.<br>1 Wound<br>Opposition Level: Hard 7<br>Agenda: Pretending to be a wise old man who is always <br>ready to help others with the proper advice / Gaining person-<br>al advantage by manipulating others.<br>Special Agenda (This Agenda replaces the one in <br>the Core Book): Recover the Virtue of Wisdom and flee so <br>that Arthur cannot come to his senses and the Hunters are <br>forced to eliminate him. <br>Gift - Ancient Sorcerer:  Merlin’s power is incredible, <br>achieving practically anything he can think of through the <br>use of magic. Those who rely on his advice will be able, once <br>per Session, to activate the magic power that the wizard has <br>infused within them. The magical effects must be decided <br>at the time that Merlin blesses the character by defining an <br>appropriate Descriptor such as: Taking flight like a bird or <br>Having skin as hard as a stone. Whoever carries Merlin’s <br>magic can activate its power once, obtaining the Descriptor <br>for the entire Scene. Once the Scene resolves the magic is <br>drained from the player and cannot be activated again.<br>Gift - Wise Advice: Merlin will never intervene person-<br>ally but can appear in a dream or vision to his protégés. <br>Once per Scenario, a Hunter can spend 1 Soma to summon <br>Merlin’s help. The sorcerer will appear with helpful infor-<br>mation or to bless the character with one of his spells.<br>How Merlin Acts in the Scenario<br>Merlin is the only NPC with an Agenda that advances re-<br>gardless of the Hunter’s actions. In general, the Storyteller <br>must move Merlin to maintain his facade as an ally who <br>will manifest when summoned. Merlin will also provide <br>information and support to the Hunters as long as they do <br>not interfere with his plans. The one thing Merlin always <br>leaves out is the location of Zone 13 - Lake (page 198), <br>where the Virtue of Wisdom can be retrieved. <br>The progression of Merlin’s actions will be as follows:<br>Scene One: Merlin is in Zone 1 - Landing (page 188), <br>briefing the Hunters on the island’s peculiarities.<br>Within  the  first  two  Interludes: Merlin will be in <br>Zone 13 - Lake (page 198) with his servant Mordred to <br>retrieve the Virtue of Wisdom (page 194).<br>By the third Interlude:  Merlin moves along the island <br>to get to Zone 15 - Secret Landing (page 199). <br>After the third Interlude: Merlin is on the boat in Zone <br>15 - Secret Landing (page 199), trying to find a cure for <br>the crew members.</p><p>180<br>Encounter Table<br>When Hunters arrive in a Zone, roll 1 die:<br>1-3: There are no Encounters, and normal exploration of <br>the Zone continues. <br>4-6: An Encounter occurs. Roll a die: if it comes up odd, <br>it is a Group Encounter; if it comes up even, it is a Single <br>Encounter. <br>All Encounter profiles are introduced from this page. En-<br>counters provide additional NPCs that connect with sto-<br>rylines already present in the Zones. The Storyteller freely <br>decides what kind of interaction is created between all the <br>elements of the Scene, evaluating the NPCs’ Agendas in re-<br>lation to the Zone in which they are encountered. In the <br>case of a repeated Encounter, the Storyteller must decide if <br>it is still interesting and useful for the narrative. If not, the <br>previous or next result in the table should be chosen. <br>Odd / Group Even / Single<br>1: Survivors of the First <br>Expedition<br>1: Sir Dagonet the Madman<br>2: Saxon Marauders 2: The Red Knight <br>3: Knights on a Quest 3: The Scarred Knight<br>4: Villagers 4: Merlin's Shadow<br>5: Restless Knights 5: Guinevere the Fugitive <br>6: Twrch Trwyth 6: Percival the Seeker <br>Survivors of the First Expedition<br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are Crown agents on the run, terrified by <br>the danger of the island.<br>Agenda: To be able to escape from this cursed island.<br>Information: At each encounter, 1d6 Survivors will be <br>available to talk about an adjacent Zone from which they <br>are fleeing. The Storyteller decides what information the <br>Survivors have. When talking about the previous expedi-<br>tion, the Survivors will tell you that as soon as they docked <br>on the beach (Zone 2 - Beach page 188), the ship was at-<br>tacked by a huge creature that they describe as a collection <br>of different animals. The crew fled in all directions, scat-<br>tering across the island as the ship was destroyed. Captain <br>Boyce, who was in command of the ship, heroically stayed <br>behind to wrestle with the creature so that everyone could <br>escape.<br>Saxon Marauders<br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are fierce marauders who have come to <br>Avalon to conquer the island. We are experts in group com-<br>bat and support each other. <br>Agenda: Attack and capture anyone we meet along the way.<br>Gift - Marauders: When attacking an enemy, Marauders <br>increase their OL by 1 if they have numerical superiority.</p><p>181<br>Information: There are 2d6 Saxon Marauders per En-<br>counter. They speak an ancient Germanic language that can <br>only be understood with a very specific Gift or Descriptor. <br>Upon closer inspection, it becomes clear that the Maraud-<br>ers are from a bygone era. When a group of Marauders is <br>eliminated, the Storyteller sets aside 1 Battle Token: these <br>Tokens reduce the danger in Zone 7 - Battlefield (page <br>193).<br>Knights on a Quest<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are knights in the service of Arthur, travel-<br>ing through Avalon on the orders of our king.<br>Agenda: Recruit every man and woman for the army that <br>will march to conquer the world. No one can refuse to enlist.<br>Information: 1d6 Knights will attempt to recruit any <br>NPC or Hunter present in the Zone, using force if neces-<br>sary. When a group of Knights is eliminated, the Story-<br>teller sets aside 1 Empty Seat Token: these Tokens reduce <br>the number of Knights present in Zone 8 - Camelot Castle <br>(page 193).<br>Villagers<br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are poor villagers who sell vegetables and <br>livestock.<br>Agenda: Travel between island settlements to conduct busi-<br>ness.<br>Information: Upon encountering them, the Storyteller <br>rolls 1 die to determine which settlement the Villagers are <br>from. The table below lists the information they can give <br>the Hunters, and in parentheses, who can give the informa-<br>tion because they are from a particular settlement.</p><p>182<br>1-3: Village of Corrinton <br>4-6: Town of Stow<br> ◆ King Arthur has called for a general recruitment to <br>form an army to invade Europe. Many Villagers are <br>afraid to go to battle, but the Knights couldn’t care less <br>and take everyone by force. (Corrinton/Stow)<br> ◆ A fearsome creature has made its lair on the coast. It is <br>a huge monster, hungry for flesh. Knights once hunted <br>Twrch Trwyth, particularly tasty wild boars, and used <br>their meat to satisfy the monster’s hunger. (Corrinton)<br> ◆ Many Knights visit the settlements in search of queen <br>Guinevere, who is rumored to have fled the palace <br>without telling the king. Arthur is furious, and until <br>the queen is found, the war against Europe cannot be-<br>gin. (Corrinton/Stow)<br> ◆ Many people who do not want to go to war seek refuge <br>in the town of Stow, which is located in the farthest <br>part of the island from Camelot Castle. But it is only a <br>matter of time before the Knights arrive there as well. <br>(Stow)<br>Restless Knights<br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are the souls of restless knights, resurrected <br>at the behest of our king. Our decaying bodies advance cease-<br>lessly, waiting to march to war. <br>Agenda: Kill all humans we come across to strengthen the <br>ranks of our king’s army. <br>Information: When encountered, the Storyteller rolls <br>2d6 to determine the number of Restless Knights. Their <br>horde attacks all living creatures, making no distinction be-<br>tween Hunters and NPCs. If the horde is not destroyed, it <br>moves one Zone by attacking those it encounters. The Sto-<br>ryteller secretly decides which Zone the horde has moved <br>to and does not make the Encounter roll when the Hunt-<br>ers arrive there. Any other damage done by the Peaceless <br>Knights is at the discretion of the Storyteller.<br>Twrch Trwyth <br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a strong and fast boar, I know every cor-<br>ner of the island and all the secret paths.<br>Agenda: Find food without getting caught.<br>Gift - Magic Boar: Whenever the Twrch Trwyth avoids <br>an action by someone who is hunting him, he gets 1 Es-<br>cape Token. As an action, and by spending 2 Escape To-<br>kens, the Twrch Trwyth can leave the Scene without any-<br>one being able to stop it. Even when dead, the body of the <br>Twrch Trwyth continues to give off an inviting scent and <br>glow with an intense magical light. Processing the Twrch <br>Trwyth’s flesh can yield 1 Delightful Flesh token. Whoever <br>consumes it will recover 1 Wound and 2 Soma.</p><p>183<br>Sir Dagonet the Madman<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor:  I am a crazy, violent knight and I will not hes-<br>itate to use my sword to get what I want. No one can afford <br>to ignore me.    <br>Agenda: Eliminate any possible threat to my king / Find <br>Guinevere, but instead of leading her back to Arthur, I plan <br>to kill her and pass off her death as a tragic accident.    <br>Gift - Don’t Underestimate the Buffoon: Dagonet is <br>a true master of foul play. During a battle, Dagonet can at-<br>tempt a low blow in addition to his action and choose one <br>of the following effects:<br>1. Blade in the Boot:  Dagonet draws it after attacking a <br>target and inflicts 1 Additional Wound. Only a Hunter with <br>a dueling ability Descriptor can make a Defense Check to <br>avoid it.<br>2. Sand in the Eyes: Activated before a Dagonet attack, <br>the target cannot use any of their Gifts during the Exchange.<br>3. Find a Shield: When Dagonet is attacked, he can avoid <br>1 Wound by having another closeby target hit instead. <br>Dagonet cannot use the same effect on the same target <br>more than once during the Scenario.<br>Information: Dagonet is a lunatic and will never reveal <br>what he knows, even if he is defeated or tortured. However, <br>being a true madman, it is possible to make him talk by <br>provoking him during combat. Dagonet is on a mission for <br>Arthur to find Guinevere, who has escaped from the castle. <br>The king has a soft spot for his queen and will not start the <br>war until she returns to his side. Dagonet also knows the <br>whereabouts of Percival, whom he now considers useless <br>to the cause. He has even tried to kill him, but one way or <br>another, the knight always comes back to life (Zone 12 - <br>Cliff, page 197).<br>The Red Knight<br>OL Hard 7 - Main NPC (4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am an immortal spirit in a knight’s armor, <br>and with my skeletal steed I travel all over Avalon in search <br>of the one who killed me.<br>Agenda: Death has clouded my consciousness, and in every <br>person I meet I see my hated enemy, Percival. <br>Gift - Eternal Vengeance:  When Percival the Seeker <br>appears on the Scene, if he is present, the Red Knight will <br>attack, ignoring all other risks. If Percival is not present, <br>the Red Knight will see the face of the hated opponent in <br>the most skilled subject in combat among those present, <br>activating this Gift as well. As long as the Red Knight has <br>his target in sight, no effect can block or prevent him from <br>attacking. In the heat of vengeance, the Red Knight ignores <br>all other enemies and reduces his OL against them to Easy <br>3. <br>Information: The Red Knight is unable to communicate, <br>and the only words he utters are vengeful epithets direct-<br>ed at Percival the Seeker. If the Hunters eliminate the Red <br>Knight, he will not appear in Zone 12 - Cliff (page 197).</p><p>184<br>The Scarred Knight<br>OL Hard 7 - Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a former knight of the Round Table, dishon-<br>orably banished by my king for falling in love with his queen. <br>My fighting skills are unparalleled, and my face is completely <br>scarred as punishment for my sins.<br>Agenda: To find my beloved Guinevere and escape Avalon <br>with her.    <br>Information: The Scarred Knight is wandering in search <br>of his beloved Guinevere and will make himself available to <br>speak to the Hunters. The man will say that his beloved is <br>disguised as a common Villager, but can be recognized by the <br>feather-shaped brooch he gave her as a token of his love. The <br>Scarred Knight will not reveal his face or name, but he prom-<br>ises incredible riches to Hunters who help him. If a Hunter <br>has a Descriptor related to madness or understanding the be-<br>havior of others, they will clearly understand that the Scarred <br>Knight is insane, and an endless obsession burns in his eyes. <br>If the Hunters eliminate the Scarred Knight, he will not ap-<br>pear in Zone 11 - Town of Stow (page 197).<br> Merlin’s Shadow<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am the shadow of the mighty sorcerer Merlin, <br>and with my touch, I can freeze anything. I constantly receive <br>visions of what my former master is doing.    <br>Agenda: Kill the precious Hunters Merlin has sent as a way <br>of taking revenge on him for leaving me alone to guard Avalon. <br>Gift - Shadow Body:  In semi- or total darkness, Merlin’s <br>Shadow is considered OL Hard 7 when defending against an <br>attack or magic. The icy touch is capable of destroying living <br>creatures. Those who suffer 1 Wound from Merlin’s Shadow <br>receive 1 Consumption Token. The Wound tied to the Token <br>cannot be healed in any way. During an Interlude, a Hunter <br>can use the Recover 1 Wound option to discard 1 Consump-<br>tion Token instead of healing the Wound. <br>Information: Merlin’s Shadow cannot communicate with <br>words. When defeated, it drops the Tower Key, which can be <br>used in Zone 5 - Merlin’s Tower (page 190).</p><p>185<br>Guinevere the Fugitive<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am the queen of Camelot, and my good heart <br>is matched only by my beauty.<br>Agenda: To find a cure for the madness that has taken hold <br>of my beloved Arthur. <br>Gift - Virtue of Love: Imbued with the power of the Vir-<br>tue of Love, Guinevere cannot be killed: when she reaches <br>0 Wounds, she will fall into a state of apparent death, wak-<br>ing up fully healed at the end of the Scene. Guinevere will <br>give the power of her Virtue to those who show a sincere <br>interest in stopping Arthur’s madness: when this happens, <br>the Virtue transforms into a heart-shaped pendant. While <br>imbued with the power of Virtue, Guinevere cannot be de-<br>ceived in any way and will see everything for what it really <br>is, breaking all magic and deception.<br>Information: Guinevere poses as a common Villager, <br>though her noble features are hard to hide. Guinevere is <br>aware that Arthur has gone mad because he has lost his <br>Virtues. Indeed, the woman is seeking help and will not <br>hesitate to reveal herself to the Hunters if they prove trust-<br>worthy.</p><p>186<br>Percival the Seeker<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a disgraced knight. My body is immortal, <br>but my mind has lost bits of memory over the centuries. <br>Agenda: Remember why I am on this strange island. <br>Gift - Virtue of Faith: Imbued with the power of the Vir-<br>tue of Faith, Percival cannot be killed. When he reaches 0 <br>Wounds, he will fall into a state of apparent death and will <br>awake at the end of the Scene fully healed. Percival’s Virtue <br>cannot be granted because it is inside the Grail chalice that <br>the Knight remembers throwing between the rocks and <br>shoals in Zone 12 - Cliff (page 197).<br>Information: Percival only remembers things when he <br>is in his little house on the Cliff: he cycles back to Camelot, <br>but on the way he loses his memory and remembers only <br>the place he left from. Upon his return, Percival remembers <br>his mission and the cycle begins again.<br> <br>The Map of Camelot<br>Zone 1 - Landing Zone 2 - Beach Zone 3 - Glatisant's <br>Lair <br>Zone 4 - Village of <br>Corrinton<br>Zone 5 -Merlin’s <br>Tower<br>Zone 6 - Forest Zone 7 - Battlefield Zone 8 - Camelot <br>Castle Zone 9 - Fairy Falls Zone 10 - Circle of <br>Stones<br>Zone 11 - Town of <br>Stow Zone 12 - Cliff Zone 13 - Lake Zone 14 - Aban-<br>doned House<br>Zone 15 - Secret <br>Landing</p><p>187<br>The Map of Camelot<br>N</p><p>188<br>Zone 1 – Landing <br>Description: The disembarkation point for the Hunters <br>expedition, where all the sailors are guarding the two ships <br>that have arrived on the island.    <br>Information: The sailors are led by Captain Bennett, <br>who is always attentive to the Hunter’s needs. The crew is <br>unwilling to leave their ship for any reason other than to <br>recover survivors from the First Expedition.<br>Note: In this Zone, you never roll on the Encounter Table.<br>Zone 2 – Beach <br>Description: A large Beach filled with ruins of what were <br>once fishermen’s homes. The wreck of the Wavecrest (the <br>ship of the First Expedition) is surrounded by the mangled <br>bodies of torn sailors.    <br>Information: Investigating near the wreck, it will be easy <br>to notice the footprints of a huge creature, and the damage <br>done to the ship also seems to indicate an unequal battle <br>between a monster and a ship of unfortunate men. Going <br>deeper into the wreck, it is possible to find Captain Boyce’s <br>diary. However, there is a risk of falling overboard because <br>of the rotten wooden planks.<br>Threat – Rotten Wreck<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: Rotten wood can give way even under light <br>weight. <br>Gift - Splinters and Scrap: If a Defense Check fails, the <br>target falls overboard and suffers 1 Wound, and the Sto-<br>ryteller gets 1 Wreck Token. When the number of Wreck <br>Tokens reaches 3, the ship collapses in on itself, burying <br>everything inside.<br>Hidden among diary pages filled with uninteresting travel <br>notes are entries about the island.<br>Note 1: Boyce followed the creature that destroyed his ship <br>and discovered that its lair was east of the beach. <br>Note 2: With a group of trusted sailors, Boyce headed to the <br>castle that towers in the center of the island in search of help. <br>Note 3: The only survivor of the journey to the castle, Boyce <br>writes in shaky handwriting, asking God’s forgiveness for his <br>sins and for the companions he had to leave behind to escape.<br>Note 4: A knight in strange red armor roams the beach. Now <br>lonely and desperate, Boyce decides to try his best to get his <br>attention.</p><p>189<br>Zone 3 – Glatisant’s <br>Lair<br>Description: A wide expanse of rocks and bushes stretch-<br>es as far as the eye can see. The terrain drops sharply, lead-<br>ing to what appears to be a chasm. An old and worn sign <br>warns, “Steer clear, lair of Glatisant the Beast. ” <br>Information: At the bottom of the chasm lies Glatisant, a <br>giant flesh-eating monster. When potential prey approach-<br>es the chasm, the Storyteller rolls a die:<br>1-3: Glatisant is dormant. If someone descends into the <br>lair, a Defense Check is required to prevent the beast from <br>waking.    <br>4-6: Glatisant awakens in hunger. Pretending to be asleep, <br>it waits for prey to approach the edge of the chasm, then <br>leaps out and devours it. <br>Glatisant <br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (6 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a giant snake-headed monster with a de-<br>formed body, the result of the union of more than ten different <br>animals. I have an insatiable appetite for flesh.<br>Agenda: I devour every delicious human I meet, though my <br>favorite prey is the tasty Twrch Trwyth.<br>Gift - Monstrous Abomination:  Glatisant can act 2 <br>times during an Exchange, but not back to back. Its long <br>neck allows it to snatch prey up to thirty feet away, and <br>when it moves, it can make great leaps, ignoring enemies <br>and terrain in its path. Glatisant is obsessed with the flesh of <br>the Twrch Trwyth and, if given the opportunity, will spend <br>the entire Exchange devouring it, ignoring even potential <br>enemies.<br>Gift - Virtue of Courage: Glatisant unknowingly carries <br>the Virtue of Courage, encased in a sword embedded in his <br>right side. Defeating the beast will allow the Hunters to re-<br>cover the power of Courage. <br>Zone 4 – Village of <br>Corrinton <br>Description: A fishing village buzzing with activity. The <br>people are friendly and hospitable, though it is clear from <br>their faces that something is troubling the community. <br>Information: Chatting with the locals is another way to <br>get the information revealed in the Encounter with the Vil-<br>lagers (page 181). At the explicit request of the Hunters, <br>some fishermen will take them by boat along the coast but <br>will ask for payment. This arrangement allows the Hunters <br>to choose any coastal Zone as their destination (i.e., all ex-<br>cept 7, 8, and 9). Unless special arrangements are made, the <br>fishermen are in a hurry to return to their activities, and <br>once they have unloaded the Hunters, they will not wait for <br>them to return.</p><p>190<br>Zone 5 – Merlin’s <br>Tower <br>Description: An old, seemingly abandoned tower stands <br>on a headland overlooking the sea. The building appears to <br>have no windows, and the only entrance is an old wooden <br>door engraved with strange runes. <br>Information: If the Hunters have not removed Merlin’s <br>Shadow, the Storyteller rolls a die.<br>1-3: Merlin’s Shadow is not in the Tower, but if someone <br>opens the door, it will be there within half an hour to drive <br>out any intruders. <br>4-6: Merlin’s Shadow is in the Tower, and if anyone forces <br>the door open, it will attack without hesitation. <br>If the Hunters have not retrieved the Tower Key from Mer-<br>lin’s Shadow, any attempt to open the door will unleash the <br>power of the Haunted Door. <br>Threat – Haunted Door<br>OL Hard 7<br>Descriptor: A creaking old door imbued with all of Merlin’s <br>magical power.<br>Gift - Away with the Harassers:  Attempting to open <br>the door without the Tower Key triggers the magical effects <br>below. If the Defense Check fails, the Storyteller rolls a die <br>to determine the consequences. <br>1-2: Loses all remaining Soma.<br>3-4: Suffers 2 Wounds. <br>5-6: Ends with the whole group in another Zone. <br>Inside the Tower, the Hunters will find all manner of mag-<br>ical devilry, as well as clear evidence in books and scrolls <br>that the place belongs to a Sorcerer named Merlin. With <br>time, the Hunters can uncover Merlin’s diary and, at the <br>Storyteller’s discretion, a Treasure of the Order.<br>The diary is mostly written in an incomprehensible lan-<br>guage, but there are notes written in red ink that are in <br>common English.<br>Note 1: An overly righteous and beloved king is more danger-<br>ous than the worst of tyrants, for when raising a hand against <br>him an entire people will rise to shield him.<br>Note 2: Virtue is like a weed, it grows despite all efforts to <br>pull it up.<br>Note 3: It may not be handy, but the bottom of a lake is al-<br>ways a good place to hide. <br>Note 4: White beach, safe harbor.</p><p>191<br>Zone 6 – Forest<br>Description: An intricate Forest stretches in all directions <br>and a light layer of fog that seems to have no regard for the <br>weather or the time of day envelops everything. An unnat-<br>ural silence hangs in the air, broken only by the cries of a <br>few animals.<br>Information: Traversing the Forest without getting lost <br>takes time and skill. While exploring the Forest, Hunters <br>can find two locations: the Magic Glade and the Green Gar-<br>den.<br>Threat – Intricate Maze<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: The great forest of Camelot is a tangle of vege-<br>tation perpetually shrouded in mist.<br>In case of Failure, the Storyteller decides which Zone the <br>Hunters will land in.<br>The Magic Glade<br>Descriptor: A small clearing within a circle formed by an-<br>cient oaks. Inside, one can clearly feel the magic hovering in <br>the air, tickling the skin.<br>Gift - Place of Peace and Magic:  The Magic Glade is <br>a place of peace and serenity. Those who rest in it for a few <br>minutes recover 1 Soma. The same subject cannot bene-<br>fit from this effect more than once per Scene. Invoking an <br>Interlude within the Magic Glade does not generate an ad-<br>vancement in Merlin’s Agenda. <br>The Green Garden<br>Descriptor: A lush field of flowers, in the center of which <br>stands a small stone altar engraved with pagan symbols. <br>Information: As soon as a subject enters the flowery <br>field, a figure covered in ancient armor and foliage stands <br>threateningly. The Green Knight will never leave the flower <br>field, remaining to defend the altar. The only way to avoid <br>the wrath of the Green Knight is to show respect to the an-<br>cient gods. By eliminating the Green Knight, the Hunters <br>can get their hands on the Treasure of the Order, the Ax of <br>Retribution (page 192). <br>The Green Knight<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am the spirit of a knight sworn to protect the <br>ancient cults. My armor is old now, but the plants and flow-<br>ers that have grown on it protect me. With my big ax, I can <br>chop off a head with ease. <br>Agenda: Protect the altar and allow those who worship the <br>old gods to have a place to worship. <br>Gift - The Just Punishment:  The Green Knight starts <br>each Scene with 3 Retaliation Tokens, each time he suffers <br>1 Wound he can spend 1 Token to inflict 1 Wound on who-<br>ever hit him.</p><p>192<br>The Ax of Retribution<br>Inspired by the Green Knight of the Arthurian <br>Myth<br>Once upon a time, there was a knight who had made justice <br>his calling. He was respected by all the commoners and had <br>married a beautiful princess with whom he shared a rich and <br>prosperous life. The knight had not always been upright in <br>spirit. In the past, he had often fallen into excesses of anger <br>and jealousy, even to the point of staining his hands with <br>blood. These lower instincts were appeased by a magical ax <br>the knight had taken from a fallen enemy. The ax accumulat-<br>ed all the negative thoughts of the wielder, transforming him <br>into a person filled with righteous thoughts. But as is often <br>the case, man is not really capable of changing his nature. <br>Despite the magical power of the ax, the knight’s thoughts be-<br>came dark. Convinced that his wife was cheating on him, the <br>knight invited a companion to his court and then pretended <br>to go on a quest, while actually hiding within the castle walls <br>to spy on them. A week passed in which absolutely nothing <br>happened, while the princess and her guest chatted amiably <br>about the knight’s qualities. Blinded by guilt, the knight came <br>to court and told his wife and trusted companion everything. <br>He cried tears of remorse, but only the ax, at the height of the <br>magical power that gave it life, sensed the lie in the Green <br>Knight’s words. To the amazement of all present, the weapon <br>came to life and decapitated him with a single blow, unleash-<br>ing all the anger and envy it had accumulated over the years. <br>Ironically, the widow, saddened by her beloved’s untimely de-<br>parture, found solace in his trusted comrade-in-arms. When <br>the mourning was over, they married and began a long and <br>successful dynasty. <br>Keywords: Trust / Punishment / Retaliation / Sense of <br>honor / Beheading / Masterstroke.<br>Gift - Scales of Justice: The Ax of Retribution protects <br>those who wield it from negative thoughts and punishes <br>those who behave spitefully. At the beginning of each Sce-<br>nario, the Ax contains 3 Retaliation Tokens. The wielder <br>can spend 1 Token to activate one of the following effects:<br>1: Get 2 Additional Successes on a Defense Check against <br>mind manipulation effects.<br>2: Once per Scenario, decapitate a target that suffers 1 <br>Wound from the Ax. This effect immediately reduces any <br>remaining Wounds to zero, but only applies to those who <br>are truly evil, with the Storyteller having the final say. If the <br>target of this effect is not evil, it is the Hunter wielding the <br>Ax who takes the Wound in retaliation.<br>3: Give 1 Additional Success to an ally’s action, but only if <br>the goal is to reveal a truth or punish a villain. <br>Once per Scene, if the wielder succeeds in changing an <br>NPC’s attitude from aggressive to cooperative without re-<br>sorting to violence, the Ax produces 1 Retaliation Token.</p><p>193<br>Zone 7 – Battlefield <br>Description: A vast wasteland littered with corpses. War-<br>riors in armor bearing the crest of Camelot mingle with the <br>bodies of skin-painted barbarians. The stench of death and <br>destruction is everywhere, while distinctly Germanic cries <br>come from an encampment in the center of the Battlefield.<br>Information: The remnants of the Saxon army that in-<br>vaded Camelot are in the camp, ready to celebrate their <br>victory over the Camelot army. There are a total of 30 Sax-<br>on Marauders (page 180), but for every Battle Token the <br>Hunters have accumulated, the number drops by 5. Un-<br>aware that they have landed in a future era not their own, <br>the Marauders plan to march on Camelot Castle. Tied to a <br>post in the middle of the camp is an old, dying knight. He <br>is Uther Pendragon, Arthur’s father, who was at the head of <br>the defending army. The Saxons are torturing him, trying to <br>extract information. <br>Uther Pendragon<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (0 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am an experienced knight and a great strate-<br>gist. I am too old for war now, but that will not stop me from <br>saving my kingdom.<br>Agenda: Protect Camelot and bring Arthur to his senses so <br>that he can once again be a worthy ruler of these lands. <br>Information: Uther is dying, and even if he is saved, it <br>will be clear that his injuries are fatal. Before he breathes <br>his last, however, the old man will reveal important details <br>to the Hunters.<br> ◆ Arthur was always a good ruler, as long as Merlin re-<br>mained at his side as an advisor. Uther, however, could <br>always see envy in the Sorcerer’s eyes, envy for the <br>young king that was his protégé. When Merlin sudden-<br>ly disappeared, Arthur went mad and lost all the traits <br>that made him a righteous and benevolent man.<br> ◆ In the southeast, past the great Lake, lies an old Aban-<br>doned House. Arthur spent his childhood there, and <br>Uther is convinced that the spirit of all that is good in <br>his son’s heart dwells there.<br> ◆ There is a secret passage to enter the Camelot Castle. It <br>is located inside a large oak tree that has been struck by <br>lightning. From there, an underground tunnel leads to <br>the hall of the Round Table. <br>Zone 8 – Camelot Castle<br>Description: Camelot Castle appears to be an ancient <br>abandoned ruin, with only the cackling of soldiers prepar-<br>ing for war revealing that it is still inhabited. Knights and <br>villagers alike are busy crafting weapons and war machines. <br>Information: Arthur is in the hall of the Round Table, <br>where he sits with his most trusted Knights. There are thir-<br>teen seats in total, one is occupied by Arthur, and one is <br>empty as it belongs to Merlin. There are then eleven more <br>Knights (page 181), but for every Empty Seat Token that <br>the Hunters have collected, the number is reduced by one. <br>Without his Virtues, Arthur is an invading madman whose <br>goal is the conquest of Europe, second only to finding his <br>beloved Guinevere. Arthur’s behavior is greatly influenced <br>by finding the Virtue of Wisdom (page 194).</p><p>194<br>Arthur<br>OL Hard 7 - Main NPC (6 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am the king of Camelot, and my word is law. <br>Thanks to the power of the Grail, my body is immortal and I <br>possess abilities far beyond those of ordinary men.<br>Agenda: Bring back my bride, Guinevere, to rule all of Eu-<br>rope by my side / Prepare the army for battle and make all my <br>subjects immortal warriors. <br>Gift - The True Power of the Grail:  Arthur is immor-<br>tal, which means that any Wounds inflicted on him will <br>heal immediately. Arthur can act up to 3 times in an Ex-<br>change, but not back to back.<br>Gift - Merlin’s Curse: Deprived of the Virtues by Mer-<br>lin’s magic, Arthur has become a mad and powerful being <br>who has abandoned his humanity. Activating the power of <br>the Virtues awakens the king’s true soul, making him more <br>human. Each Virtue consumed in front of Arthur will have <br>the following effect:<br>Love: Lower his OL by 2.<br>Innocence: Lower the number of Wounds by 3. <br>Faith: He loses his immortality and, if brought to 0 <br>Wounds, is permanently killed. <br>Courage: Acts only 1 time per Exchange. <br>Wisdom: He regains his wits and realizes that what he is <br>doing is wrong. Arthur’s Agenda changes to: Lead my king-<br>dom to peace by finding a place in this new world.</p><p>195<br>Zone 9 – Fairy Falls<br>Description: A small wooded area hides a series of natu-<br>ral waterfalls. A keen eye might catch a glimpse of female <br>figures dancing gracefully on the water.<br>Information: There are 6 Fairies who will welcome any-<br>one who arrives with smiles and dancing. The Fairies do <br>not hesitate to reveal what they know, engaging guests in <br>a long talk.<br>Fairies<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPCs (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: We are fairies and we love company and good <br>stories. We like humans, even though they tend to age too fast <br>by our standards.    <br>Agenda: Entertain nice people for as long as possible.    <br>Gift - A Midsummer Night’s Dream: Talking to Fair-<br>ies for a long time can be fatal for a human, as time passes <br>faster in their presence. After a minute of conversation, the <br>subject can make a Defense Check to see if they are getting <br>old. If successful, the subject can end the conversation. If <br>unsuccessful, the subject loses 2 Soma, and if the subject is <br>already at 0 Soma, the subject loses 1 Wound. Succeeding <br>with a Cost is possible, but the easiest way to interrupt the <br>effect of the Gift is to feel pain, so the Cost will always be <br>1 Wound. A new Check can be made after each minute of <br>conversation. An outside party may attempt to break the ef-<br>fect of this Gift with words (Position Check) or by inflicting <br>1 Wound (Automatic).<br>Fairy information:<br> ◆ They come from the great lake where the house once <br>stood, the home of the Lady who cared for all the mag-<br>ical creatures on the island. The Lady then decided <br>to leave, fed up with the many brave young men who <br>came to the lake, insistent on gaining her blessing.<br> ◆ The Fairies have always stayed to guard the Lake, but <br>on the day the Hunters arrived, a grumpy old man who <br>clearly looked like a Sorcerer appeared at the lake ac-<br>companied by a huge knight in armor as black as night. <br>The old man frightened off the Fairies, who, peering <br>from a distance, clearly saw the two of them walking <br>along the shores of the Lake, searching for something.<br> ◆ The island contains many illusions that prevent ordi-<br>nary mortals from discovering certain truths. The Fair-<br>ies possess a Fairy Crystal that allows those who look <br>through it to see the illusions. They are willing to give <br>up the Crystal, but only in exchange for something of <br>equal value. If the Hunters do not know what to pro-<br>pose, the Fairies will say that a beautiful treasure is <br>guarded by a Knight in the Forest to the east.</p><p>196<br>Scenario Gift - Fairy Crystal<br>Requirement: Receive the Crystal as a gift from the Fair-<br>ies. (No need to spend XP)<br>Thanks to the power of the Crystal, you can see beyond il-<br>lusions and receive 3 Sight Tokens. Y ou can spend 1 Token <br>and look through the Crystal to reveal an illusion, a dis-<br>guise, or the effect of magic that makes something appear <br>different than it really is. When you spend the last Token, <br>the Crystal shatters and you lose the effect of this Gift. <br> <br>Zone 10 – Circle of <br>Stones<br>Description: Huge megalithic stones are arranged in a <br>circle at the top of a low hill. The aura of ancient power is <br>easily felt even by those unfamiliar with magic. <br>Information: Inside the large stones are a series of small-<br>er stones that replicate the shape of the island. A person <br>with a Descriptor related to magic can decipher the code <br>of the stones and understand that the Circle is a system for <br>magically moving from one place to another. Naming a <br>Zone with the correct code will immediately transport ev-<br>erybody in the Circle there, but travel is only one-way and <br>can’t be used to return to the Circle of Stones. Using the <br>Fairy Crystal allows one to understand the workings of the <br>Circle, even if the person looking at it does not understand <br>magic.<br>Threat – Magic Menhirs<br>OL Hard 7<br>Descriptor: A circle of ancient stones laid at the dawn of <br>time. <br>Gift - Magical Journey:  Activating the power of the <br>stones is easy, but getting exactly where you want to go is <br>much less so. The journey requires a Position Check: with a <br>single roll, the person activating the power can take all ob-<br>jects within the Circle with them. Depending on the result <br>of the Check, different effects are achieved.<br>Failure: Successful journey but the wrong destination. <br>The Storyteller chooses the arrival Zone from among those <br>adjacent to the original destination. <br>Outcome with a Cost: Successful journey but with some <br>interference. Each subject loses 1 Equipment decided by <br>the Storyteller. The missing Equipment has been transport-<br>ed in a Zone adjacent to the one of arrival.<br>Standard Outcome: Successful trip, no problems. <br>Outcome with an Increment:  Complimentary pan-<br>oramic view. Before arriving, travelers can observe the <br>destination while lingering safely in the astral dimension <br>they have traveled through. The Storyteller will reveal some <br>information about the Zone.</p><p>197<br>Zone 11 – Town of Stow  <br>Description: A small farming town. The people are <br>friendly and hospitable, though you can see in their faces <br>that the shadow of war hangs over their lives. The streets <br>are also filled with outsiders looking for work and a place <br>to sleep. <br>Information: By chatting with villagers, it is possible to <br>obtain the information provided in the Villagers Encounter <br>(page 181). <br>If the Hunters have not already met Guinevere (page 185), <br>the queen will be in Stow, where she has been hired as a <br>handmaiden to hide her true identity. When Guinevere re-<br>alizes that the Hunters are on the island to stop Arthur, she <br>will present herself to them and ask for help. <br>If the Hunters have not already eliminated the Scarred <br>Knight (page 184), he will come to Stow in search of his <br>beloved. <br>Zone 12 – Cliff <br>Description: An impassable overhanging Cliff with the <br>sea crashing against it. The Cliff rises on a small promonto-<br>ry, on the top of which a small house can be seen. <br>Information: If the Hunters have not already encoun-<br>tered Percival the Seeker (page 186), they will find him in <br>the house, cooking fish and recuperating.<br>If the Hunters have not already eliminated the Red Knight <br>(page 183), he will appear to confront Percival.<br>Interacting with the confused Seeker can provide you <br>with relevant information and the story of how he threw <br>the Holy Grail into the sea to awaken Arthur. Percival will <br>lead the Hunters to the Cliff where the current carried the <br>cup after the island emerged. The Grail now lies embedded <br>ninety feet below. <br>Threat – The Sacred Cup Among the <br>Rocks<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: A steep cliff overlooking the sea that hides the <br>cup of the Holy Grail in its rocks. <br>Note: Getting to the cup requires moving along the slip-<br>pery, pointy rocks as the sea crashes relentlessly.    Retriev-<br>ing the embedded cup requires breaking the rock or find-<br>ing a way to slide it out.</p><p>198<br>Zone 13 – Lake<br>Description: A large Lake surrounded by dense vegeta-<br>tion. There seems to be no human settlement. A few boats <br>lie abandoned on the shore, victims of time and weather. <br>Information: In this Zone, the initial situation changes <br>according to the number of Interludes the Hunters have <br>called before their arrival.<br>Up to Two Interludes: Walking along the shore, Merlin <br>can be seen coordinating Mordred’s search for the Virtue. <br>The Knight walks until he disappears into the water, only <br>to reappear a short time later with some muddy objects. <br>Merlin sorts out what his servant has recovered and, with a <br>displeased expression, orders him to continue. The Virtue <br>of Wisdom is in the form of a Crown. Once retrieved, Mer-<br>lin instructs Mordred to wait for him at the bottom of the <br>lake and then he leaves, abandoning his servant.<br>Three or more Interludes: Merlin has already rescued <br>the Virtue and made his way to the Zone 15 - Secret Land-<br>ing (page 199). Hovering on the shore and looking into <br>the Lake, it’s possible to see a motionless suit of armor un-<br>derwater. If the Hunters attempt to interact with Mordred, <br>he will awaken to eliminate any newcomers.<br>Mordred the Peaceless<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am an undead knight in the service of the evil <br>Merlin. I do whatever my master tells me to do, though I only <br>wish to return to the grave from which I was torn.    <br>Agenda (if Merlin is present):  Obey my master’s or-<br>ders.<br>Agenda (if Merlin is not present):  Eliminate anyone <br>who approaches the waters of the lake, as ordered by my mas-<br>ter / Be destroyed and return to death, receiving a farewell <br>prayer. <br>Information: Mordred can be persuaded to surrender in <br>exchange for the promise of a burial that will bring peace <br>to his soul. If peace is granted, Mordred will reveal Merlin’s <br>plans for why he wants the Virtue of Wisdom and the Se-<br>cret Landing.</p><p>199<br>Zone 14 – Abandoned <br>House <br>Description: A dilapidated cottage sits in the middle of a <br>flat area. Cultivated fields once stretched in every direction, <br>but now only ruins and sun-browned earth remain. <br>Information: The House appears to be in ruins and long <br>abandoned, but with careful investigation, you will notice <br>a trapdoor in the floor. Opening the trapdoor will lead you <br>to the basement, where old clothes and farming tools are <br>piled high. Searching through the junk, the Hunters will <br>find a small wooden crucifix that seems untouched by time. <br>Once picked up, it will reveal its power as the Virtue of In-<br>nocence.<br>Zone 15 – Secret Landing <br>Description: On the surface, this place looks like a quiet <br>beach. The pale coloring of the sand makes it look almost <br>like an expanse of white snow. Merlin’s personal ship waits <br>about 30 yards from the shore, but it cannot be seen be-<br>cause it is hidden by an illusion cast by the Sorcerer.<br>Information: In this Zone, the initial situation changes <br>according to the number of Interludes the Hunters have <br>called before their arrival.<br>Up to Two Interludes:  On the ship, Captain Edgers <br>awaits Merlin’s arrival. <br>Three Interludes: The situation is the same as in the <br>first option, but Merlin has regained the Virtue of Wisdom <br>and will arrive at the beach shortly. If the Hunters wait, they <br>can catch him off guard.    <br>Four Interludes: Merlin has returned to the ship and <br>preparations for departure are in full swing. Unfortunately, <br>part of the crew has contracted a strange disease that makes <br>it difficult for Captain Edgers to control the ship. Merlin, <br>amidst a thousand curses, does his best to create a cure.<br>Threat – Illusory Panorama<br>OL Hard 7<br>Descriptor: A false image that adapts to weather condi-<br>tions. Small, repetitive details are the only sign that some-<br>thing is wrong, such as a flock of seagulls flying following a <br>cyclic trajectory and clouds that seem stuck in the same po-<br>sition.</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513743954,"modifiedTime":1781513743954,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"the-kings-awakening","collection":"Lost Stories","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","pages":"175-200"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513743954,"modifiedTime":1781513743954,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"8kZGkfXlbUb4HcA4","name":"A Frozen Reflection","pages":[{"_id":"HGahDAIlba8m3A88","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>A Frozen Reflection</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> Lost Stories</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf, pages 201-227.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/a-frozen-reflection-p201-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513746052,"modifiedTime":1781513746052,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"4hZSZf33KEnLlCsa","name":"Setup","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>A Frozen Reflection - Setup</h2><p>200<br>A Frozen Reflection <br> A Scenario Inspired by The Snow Queen<br>Part One – The Two Healers<br>Safety keywords: Illness / Poisoning / Identity theft<br>A Frozen Reflection is a special three-part Scenario that tells the story of <br>the mysterious con artists Gerda and Kay. All Scenarios are structured as <br>a Scene Tree (see page 100 of the Broken Tales Core Book) and are great for <br>introductory Sessions or a mini-Campaign. A Storyteller who prefers an <br>emergent style of storytelling will still find Events and information useful <br>for handling more free-form Hunter action.</p><p>201<br>The Fragments of the <br>Mirror of the Other Self<br>In this Scenario, several NPCs have been affected by the <br>Shards of the Mirror of the Other Self, magical Shards <br>that can reverse a person’s abilities and dispositions. All <br>NPCs affected by the Shard receive the Gift - Power of the <br>Shard, which provides a Shard Descriptor and a Shard <br>Agenda to replace the original ones until the Mirror <br>Shard is removed. To remove a Mirror Shard, you must <br>deal with the Threat - Shard of the Mirror of the Other <br>Self. <br>Threat – Shard of the Mirror of <br>the Other Self<br>OL Hard 7<br>Descriptor: A tiny shard of mirror capable of emitting <br>icy cold.<br>Gift - The Shard:  Removing the Shard is a complex <br>procedure that requires medical skills or the assistance <br>of magic. Once removed, the Shard loses all of its power, <br>disintegrating into thin air and inflicting 1 Wound on the <br>person who removed it. This Wound can only be avoided <br>by spending an Increment on a potential Check to re-<br>move the Shard. <br>Miss Snow and Lady Storm in this <br>Scenario<br>When a Hunter is connected to the story on which a Sce-<br>nario is based, an Exclusive Gift is usually presented that <br>can be obtained under certain narrative conditions. This <br>is a special case, however, because the Hunter Miss Snow <br>and Lady Storm is directly involved in the plot of A Frozen <br>Reflection. For this reason, the Storyteller must carefully <br>consider whether to introduce this Hunter and how to deal <br>with the resulting plot changes. Here are some tips:<br> ◆ None of the NPCs who have met Lady Storm will rec-<br>ognize her while she is in the form of Miss Snow. In-<br>stead, the Hunter’s identity will be revealed when she <br>activates her Dark Ego. All NPCs who contributed in <br>any way to Lady Storm’s downfall will fear her and try <br>to have as little to do with her as possible.<br> ◆ No one knows that Miss Snow is Lady Storm, so there <br>will be no qualms or special care in saying the word <br>Eternity.<br> ◆ During PART THREE - The Winter Castle, if the Ice <br>Heart sees Lady Storm in action, it will be willing to <br>sacrifice itself to get its mistress back; if Lady Storm <br>manifests during the Scene, the Ice Heart will shatter, <br>warmed by the love for its queen.</p><p>202<br>Once upon a time…<br>A terrible epidemic has struck the provinces of Norway, on <br>the borders of the Kingdom of Denmark. Frozen Madness is a <br>disease that only affects humans and literally drives them in-<br>sane. Not even the best doctors in the kingdom have been able <br>to find a cure for the terrible disease, leaving the families of <br>the sick in utter despair. The sudden appearance of the myste-<br>rious healers Kay and Gerda has brought a ray of hope to the <br>fight against the Frozen Madness: after proving that they can <br>cure the disease, the two have taken refuge in a remote castle <br>in the far north, forcing the families of the sick to undertake <br>a long and costly journey to obtain the cure. There are many <br>rumors of expeditions that have ended in tragedy, as brigands <br>and vicious animals make it seem impossible to reach Gerda <br>and Kay without paying handsomely for a good guide. But a <br>disease that has only one doctor is a strange thing, especially <br>since the dreaded disease appeared shortly before the arrival <br>of the two dubious healers. This fact did not go unnoticed <br>by the Order, which decided to send a group of Hunters to <br>investigate... <br>The story that led us here…<br>Gerda and Kay are two young scoundrels who have <br>always lived from hand to mouth. By a stroke of luck, the <br>two have come into possession of many Shards of the Mir-<br>ror of the Other Self, a powerful magical object capable of <br>reversing the character of those injured by one of its Shards. <br>With the help of a witch named Flora, Gerda and Kay in-<br>troduced themselves to the powerful witch Lady Storm and <br>managed to strike her with a magical Shard. Storm lost her <br>abilities and became a naive and bungling sorceress. Us-<br>ing Flora’s power, Gerda and Kay forced poor Miss Snow <br>(Lady Storm’s new identity) to create a great storm that <br>would sweep across Northern Europe, releasing most of the <br>Shards from the Mirror of the Other Self to affect as many <br>innocent people as possible, spreading the Frozen Mad-<br>ness. Unable to handle such a powerful atmospheric event, <br>Miss Snow was carried away, only to be found by the Order <br>with no memory. After the Frozen Madness spread, Gerda <br>and Kay used Lady Storm’s magic sleigh to travel to the ma-<br>jor cities of Norway, presenting themselves as healers of the <br>mysterious disease that no one could eradicate. After be-<br>coming famous, the pair retreated to Lady Storm’s castle. As <br>a consequence,    the families of the sick are cruelly forced <br>to spend large sums of money on a journey of hope, only <br>to find that hope dashed when they are led straight into the <br>clutches of Gerda and Kay’s servants.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>The Hunters arrive in Bergen, where nobleman Aleksander <br>Okland has fallen victim to the dangerous Frozen Madness. <br>Fredrika, the nobleman’s daughter, has been trying to cure <br>her father, finally turning to the Order when it became clear <br>that her beloved parent’s complete change of character was <br>not the result of an ordinary illness. Meanwhile, Kay and <br>Gerda struck Flora with a Shard, turning the cunning old <br>charmer into a naive and clueless old woman. Flora had <br>made too many demands in exchange for cooperating with <br>the two imposters, so Gerda and Kay immediately took ac-<br>tion to get her out of the way. Since Flora is quite famous in <br>Bergen, where she used to live, the two led the witch back <br>to her old home, so that everyone would believe that the <br>woman had simply succumbed to dementia.</p><p>203</p>"},"sort":50000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513746054,"modifiedTime":1781513746054,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"XwjL3DAZWXV7sFaI","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>A Frozen Reflection - Scene 1</h2><p>FIRST SCENE – Bergen<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: You arrive in Bergen as the <br>sun is setting, but what you see is hardly the tranquility of a <br>city resting after a long day of activity. Men and women are <br>wandering the streets shouting and gesturing outrageously, <br>then wriggling away from desperate relatives trying to calm <br>them down. As described in the letter from the young Okland <br>scion, the Frozen Madness seems to have hit Bergen hard, <br>driving many of its inhabitants mad. A young servant runs <br>up to you and, after a brief bow, waves for you to follow him <br>to the large mansion down the street. <br>Place: The Okland family mansion in the city’s wealthiest <br>neighborhood.<br>Time: The sun is setting as the cries of people <br>suffering from Frozen Madness echo from the <br>streets. <br>Initial Situation: Fredrika Okland will intro-<br>duce herself to the Hunters by inviting them to <br>dinner, accompanied by her father Aleksander, <br>who suffers from the Frozen Madness. Fredrika <br>will ask the Hunters to forgive her father’s excess-<br>es in light of his condition. <br>Information: Fredrika will tell the Hunters <br>that three months ago a very heavy snowstorm <br>hit Northern Europe, especially the Norwegian <br>coast. After the storm, many people began to <br>show signs of madness, behaving in ways that <br>were the opposite of their usual behavior. Her fa-<br>ther Aleksander, who had always been a calm and <br>jovial man, became hot-tempered and arrogant, <br>with outbursts of unnecessary violence. At first, <br>no doctor could find a cure. Then two mysteri-<br>ous healers from the north named Gerda and Kay <br>cured some nobles for a hefty fee. As soon as word <br>spread of healers who could cure the Frozen Madness, the <br>two disappeared, and now to meet them one must contact <br>the Black Feathers: two local guides who charge exorbitant <br>sums of money to bring desperate people to Gerda and Kay.<br>During the discussion, this information will also emerge:<br> ◆ Near Bergen lives a famous witch named Flora. Many <br>have turned to her for healing, but the old woman <br>seems to have fallen victim to dementia, or perhaps she <br>herself has been struck by the Frozen Madness. Flora is <br>famous for her potions, which she distills in the large <br>greenhouse where she grows all sorts of herbs. <br> ◆ The only contact with the Black Feathers in town seems <br>to be an elderly woman named Lene. The woman was <br>1</p><p>204<br>once the head of a criminal organization but <br>has retired to private life to enjoy the fruits of <br>her misdeeds. Few have the courage to both-<br>er her without offering something of value in <br>return. <br>During dinner, Aleksander behaves inappropri-<br>ately, trying in every way possible to humiliate <br>his daughter and question the Hunters’ actions. If <br>provoked, Aleksander will not hesitate to use vi-<br>olence.<br>Fredrika Okland<br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am the young scion of the Okland family, I believe in jus-<br>tice and honesty as my father taught me. <br>Agenda: To heal my father and make him the good man who raised me.<br>Aleksander Okland<br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPC (1 Wound)<br>Descriptor: I am a rich and powerful nobleman, and I use my position to help <br>all unfortunate people. I can’t stand the bullying of the weak by the powerful, <br>and I strive to change society so that everything is more equal.    <br>Agenda: Helping others find their way and realize their plans.    <br>Shard Descriptor: I am a rich and powerful nobleman, and I use my <br>position to bend everyone to my command. I can’t stand to be told no, and I <br>abuse all the people I consider inferior.<br>Shard Agenda: Satisfying my thirst for power by crushing those who are <br>weaker. <br>Gift - Power of the Shard:  The Shard of the Mirror of the Other Self re-<br>verses the Descriptor and Agenda of the person it injured. The holder increas-<br>es their OL by 1 if they act in accordance with the altered part of their De-<br>scriptor or Agenda. <br>End of Scene:  The Hunters must decide whether to contact Flora or the <br>Black Feathers through Lene. Go to SECOND SCENE OPTION A - Flora’s <br>Greenhouse or SECOND SCENE OPTION B - Lene’s House.</p><p>205</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513746054,"modifiedTime":1781513746054,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"JbWNm0aneMryPW46","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>A Frozen Reflection - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE OPTION A –  <br>Flora’s Greenhouse<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: The home of the famous Flo-<br>ra is located just outside the city limits, along a large stream <br>that runs along the eastern side of Bergen. The witch’s home <br>stands out in the middle of the countryside as a colorful <br>building flanked by a huge greenhouse. When you reach the <br>entrance, there are no lights on in the house, while someone <br>in the greenhouse seems to be happily humming a <br>childish song.<br>Place: The House and Greenhouse of the witch <br>Flora.<br>Time: The sun has set and the moonlight softly il-<br>luminates the Bergen countryside.<br>Information: Flora has taken up permanent residence <br>in the Greenhouse and, in the grip of the Shard effect, be-<br>witches and imprisons those who visit her, then forgets her <br>victims among the plants. Inside the House, the Hunters <br>can get their hands on the witch’s diary, in which Flora has <br>written some important information about Gerda and Kay. <br>In the House:  The House is protected by Flora’s magic, <br>and breaking in without her permission will activate her <br>defenses. The House is well-maintained and filled with an-<br>cient magical relics. There are four rooms in total, two of <br>which are of interest to Hunters: the Storeroom on the first <br>floor and Flora’s Bedroom on the second floor. <br>Threat - Haunted House<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: A house that emits an aura of ignorant <br>well-being, relaxing intruders into sleep. <br>Gift - Induced Fatigue:  For each room visited in the <br>House, roll one die for each intruder:<br>1-3: Nothing happens.<br>4-6: They lose 1 Soma. <br>On the second point of Soma lost to this Gift, a Hunter <br>must pass a Defense Check to avoid falling into an eight-<br>hour deep sleep from which they cannot be awakened. For <br>an NPC, the effect is triggered when they lose Soma equal <br>to the category of their OL: 1 for Easy, 2 for Medium, and <br>3 for Hard.<br>Flora’s Bedroom<br>Descriptor: A richly decorated room with a large canopy <br>bed. Flowers and plants of all kinds grow on the walls, giving <br>the impression of being in a small greenhouse. <br>Information: The Hunters will quickly notice a small box <br>on the wardrobe next to the bed. Inside is Flora’s diary, but <br>as you might guess, a witch’s box can’t be opened by just <br>anyone.<br>2a</p><p>206<br>Warden Casket<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a fierce Warden Casket, ready to bite any <br>thief with my sharp teeth. I am very sensitive to bad smells, <br>which makes me sneeze until I vomit my contents. <br>Information: Flora’s diary describes Gerda and Kay, two <br>criminals who proposed the Frozen Madness scam to Flo-<br>ra. Flora seems to have agreed mainly to take revenge on an <br>old rival of hers, a witch named Lady Storm. The contact <br>between Flora and the two criminals was facilitated by a <br>woman named Lene, who is identified in the diary as Ger -<br>da’s mother. Flora reports that she is not too happy about <br>involving so many innocent people in this plan, but the <br>chance to teach the arrogant and haughty Lady Storm a <br>lesson was too good to pass up. Flora does not trust Gerda <br>and Kay, but she does not believe that the two criminals can <br>pose any real danger to her. <br>Storeroom<br>Descriptor: A small room filled with books, gardening <br>tools, and strange vials.<br>Information: Hidden among the many stacked objects it <br>is possible to find a Treasure of the Order. The Storyteller is <br>free to decide which one.<br>The Greenhouse<br>Descriptor: A large greenhouse filled with vegetation. A <br>thick mist of pollen chokes those who walk through the rows <br>of plants and flowers with its smell. <br>Information:  Flora has taken up residence in the Green-<br>house, where she repeats the same tasks over and over <br>again. Without her careful oversight, many of the plants <br>have grown beyond control, and the ecosystem of the place <br>has become mixed with the witch’s out-of-control magic. <br>Moving inside the Greenhouse activates the Threat - Magic <br>Greenhouse. Flora is in the center of it and will not move <br>under any circumstances.<br>Threat - Magic Greenhouse<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: A greenhouse filled with strange plants im-<br>bued with Flora’s magical powers. <br>Gift - Wild Plants:  The Greenhouse plants will identify <br>anyone other than Flora as a threat. The plants rely on smell <br>to detect intruders, so they can be fooled. If a person enters <br>the Greenhouse, roll 1 die:<br>1-2: A carnivorous plant attempts to bite the target to in-<br>flict 1 Wound. <br>3-4: A colored pollen covers the target, which takes 1 <br>Penalty on all actions while in the Greenhouse. A Defense <br>Check is needed to avoid the pollen.<br>5-6: A large flower emits a sharp hissing sound that stuns <br>the target and causes them to lose 1 Soma (1 Wound, in the <br>case of an NPC).</p><p>207<br>Flora the Witch<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a powerful witch who has dedicated her <br>life to the study of nature-based magic. I wish to be admired <br>and recognized for my abilities as a witch.    <br>Agenda: To gain the respect of others through my powers <br>and live a comfortable life. <br>Shard Descriptor: I am a clumsy witch who loves <br>plants, but unfortunately I have forgotten how to take care <br>of my beloved greenhouse. I am humble and don’t care what <br>others think of me, because all I want is to speak to the hearts <br>of plants. <br>Shard Agenda: Take care of my greenhouse and keep <br>away any pests that come after me. <br>Gift - Power of the Shard:  The Shard of the Mirror of <br>the Other Self reverses the Descriptor and Agenda of the <br>person it injured. The holder increases their OL by 1 if they <br>act in accordance with the altered part of their Descriptor <br>or Agenda.    <br>Gift - Plant Witch:  Flora can manipulate nearby plants <br>by animating them, and thanks to this power, she can per-<br>form up to 2 actions in the Exchange with a range equal to <br>the ground covered by the plants themselves. Through the <br>plants, Flora can attempt to injure, immobilize, or manip-<br>ulate a target. <br>Information: If the Hunters succeed in removing the <br>Shard from Flora’s eye, the old witch will come to her <br>senses, but the effects of the Shard will have permanent <br>consequences for her. Drained of all magical power, the <br>old woman will try to bargain with the Hunters for the in-<br>formation she possesses in exchange for being exonerated <br>of all charges. Flora will then talk about Gerda and Kay’s <br>plan, as described in The story that led us here. Flora will <br>not know the location of Lady Storm’s castle, as its entrance <br>is protected by powerful magic. However, she will tell the <br>Hunters that if they continue along the river bordering <br>Bergen, they can reach the small White Hospital: a facility <br>where Gerda and Kay reside when they leave the castle. To <br>get there, Flora will tell the Hunters to look for the Black <br>Feather boat in the small river port of Bergen.<br>End of Scene:  The Hunters decide to meet the Black <br>Feathers through Lene. Go to SECOND SCENE OPTION <br>B - Lene’s House. If they decide to leave directly instead, go <br>to the THIRD SCENE - The Ambush of the Black Feathers.</p><p>208</p><p>SECOND SCENE OPTION B –  <br>Lene’s House<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  In the slums of Bergen you <br>will find a small, seemingly abandoned house. Only the lights <br>inside indicate someone’s presence. You feel several eyes on <br>you and realize that hooded figures are keeping watch on the <br>street. There is no doubt that you have entered the territory <br>of a gang...<br>Place: Lene’s little abandoned house in the slums of Ber-<br>gen. <br>Time: The sun has now set and the only source of illumi-<br>nation is the many lights coming from the houses in town.<br>Information: Lene welcomes every visitor to the house <br>and offers herself as a contact for the two famous healers. <br>For this service, the old woman demands an outrageous <br>amount of money that only the truly wealthy can afford. <br>Lene’s arguments are especially persuasive because of the <br>numerous cutthroats who lurk around her home, ready to <br>strike at the slightest sign of trouble.  <br>Lene the Old Mobster<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am the ruthless queen of Bergen’s under -<br>world, and I have no qualms about conducting my shady <br>business. Everyone in the city fears me, and I use my repu-<br>tation to intimidate those foolish enough to turn against me. <br>Agenda: Making money by taking advantage of people’s <br>desperation, taking what they have to offer without really <br>leading them to Gerda and Kay. <br>Information: When the Hunters confront Lene, the old <br>woman will reveal that Gerda and Kay are staying at the <br>small White Hospital, a medical facility that can be reached <br>by sailing north along the river. Lene will give the Hunters <br>a pass that the Black Feathers will recognize as valid for <br>boarding their boat to make the journey.<br>Lene will try hard to hide the fact that she is Gerda’s moth-<br>er, fearing that this information will get her into even more <br>trouble than her daughter’s scheme. When this connection <br>is made and Lene is cornered, she will reveal some infor -<br>mation about her daughter to the Hunters. At this point, <br>the Storyteller can decide what to reveal about Gerda by <br>consulting her profile on page 223.<br>Lene’s Cutthroat<br>OL Easy 3 - Minor NPC <br>(1 Wound - 12 Gang Members)<br>Descriptor: We are ruthless scoundrels and protect our ter-<br>ritory from any intruder.<br>Gift - Neighborhood Gang: A Cutthroat increases their <br>OL by 1 when they act to wound or capture a target they <br>consider an intruder on their territory. <br>End of Scene:  The Hunters decide to meet the Black <br>Feathers. Go to the THIRD SCENE - The Ambush of the <br>Black Feathers. If they decide to meet Flora instead, go to</p><p>SECOND SCENE OPTION A - Flora’s Greenhouse.<br>2b</p><p>209</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513746054,"modifiedTime":1781513746054,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"oqyUxa4W7ju4dsJH","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>A Frozen Reflection - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE –  The Ambush <br>of the Black Feathers<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: After a night of prepara-<br>tions, you arrive at the small river port on the eastern side of <br>the city, the sun is rising as the port activities have already <br>begun. You recognize the small, black boat that has been <br>pointed out to you, and as you approach, a young woman <br>with clear skin and long raven hair looks at you with suspi-<br>cious eyes and then nods at you. <br>Place: Bergen’s river port. <br>Time: It dawns as the city awakens to a new day of work. <br>Information: The woman will introduce herself as Kråke <br>and ask the Hunters for a pass. If they took one from Lene, <br>the boatwoman will wave them aboard. If the Hunters are <br>coming on Flora’s instructions, Kråke will instead ask them <br>to pay a fare in exchange for her services. <br>On the ship, the Hunters will notice a second black-haired <br>boatman, Ravn, busy making preparations for departure. <br>Regardless of how they got on board, the Black Feath-<br>ers know the Hunters are unwelcome guests: Lene’s pass <br>is marked, a sign the woman leaves specifically to let the <br>crewmembers know who should meet a bad end along the <br>way because they have not paid enough. If, on the other <br>hand, they were sent by Flora, the Black Feathers know that <br>the witch has been struck by a Shard and should no longer <br>be able to provide this information. Shortly after leaving, <br>the Hunters notice a flock of crows that seems to be follow-<br>ing the boat. Eventually, many birds will rest on the boat, <br>and that is when Ravn and Kråke will start their attack. Af-<br>ter defeating the enemies on the boat, the Hunters will find <br>a map to the White Hospital. <br>Ravn<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a skilled assassin, and my throwing <br>knives can hit a target even in total darkness.    <br>Agenda: Escort those who have paid the correct amount to <br>the White Hospital / Eliminate any potential threat to Gerda <br>and Kay’s business.    <br>Gift - The Raven:  Once per Scene, Ravn can transform <br>into a raven and escape by flying away. If he makes a sur -<br>prise attack, Ravn inflicts 1 Additional Wound.<br>Kråke<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a skilled assassin, and I can corner any <br>opponent with my saber. My swordsmanship is such that I <br>can deflect any weapon. <br>Agenda: Escort those who have paid the correct amount to <br>the White Hospital / Eliminate any potential threat to Gerda <br>and Kay’s business.    <br>Gift - The Rook:  Once per Scene, Kråke can transform <br>into a rook and escape by flying away. If she makes a sur -<br>prise attack, Kråke inflicts 1 Additional Wound. <br>3</p><p>210<br>Threat - Murder of Crows<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: We are a great murder of crows and watch over <br>our beloved human brothers Ravn and Kråke.<br>Gift - The Three Feathers:  The Murder of Crows acts in <br>the service of Kråke and Ravn to protect them and treat them <br>as if they were a Crow. Once per Exchange, both Kråke and <br>Ravn can enjoy one of the following effects:<br>1. Coat of Feathers:  The Murder shields a Black Feather, <br>which increases their OL to Hard 7 against an attack.<br>2. Flight of the Crow:  The Murder lifts the Black Feather <br>off the ground and allows it to run over their feathery bodies. <br>The Black Feather can move anywhere within a thirty-foot <br>radius, and no one can block them. If they make an attack <br>after moving, the Black Feather increases their OL by 1.<br>3. Feather Storm: The Murder encircles a target while it <br>performs an action that is not a physical attack. This effect <br>can be activated when an opponent acts, but it still counts <br>against the limit of one effect per Exchange. The target must <br>pass a Defense Check or lose the action.<br>Epilogue<br>It takes two days of sailing to get to the White Hospital.<br>If a Black Feather is captured, they will not agree to talk, but <br>the Hunters can use magic or other means to force them to <br>reveal the following information:<br> ◆ The mission of the Black Feathers is to take the wealthiest <br>patients to Os, where the famous White Hospital is lo-<br>cated, but even that is a cover-up by Gerda and Kay. The <br>real goal is to get the patients into the hands of a certain <br>Reinsdyr, who will then lead them through the forest to <br>be robbed by a group of bandits.<br> ◆ The Black Feathers do not know how to get to the cas-<br>tle where Gerda and Kay live, but they have heard more <br>than once from the two fraudsters about witches who <br>help them.  <br>Storyteller’s Note: The Hunters’ journey continues in <br>PART TWO - Towards Lady Storm’s Castle. Keep track of the <br>fate of the Black Feathers, for they will be recurring enemies <br>in the next parts. <br>Scenario Events<br>There are 3 Events in this Scenario, though the Storyteller <br>should feel free to create new ones in response to the Hunter’s <br>actions.<br>If the Hunters use violence to stop Aleksander:  his <br>daughter will stand up for him, going so far as to beg the <br>Hunters to spare him. If the situation is not resolved, Fredri-<br>ka will send the Hunters away with less information to end <br>the dinner quickly. <br>If the Hunters try to destroy Flora’s Greenhouse to <br>force her out:  the old witch will use her magic to call for <br>help, causing many townspeople to rush to her defense. <br>If  the  Hunters  inflict  at  least  one  Wound  on  both <br>Black Feathers or corner them: the two will attempt to <br>escape by transforming into a rook and a raven and mingling <br>with the Murder.</p><p>211<br>Part Two – Towards Lady Storm’s <br>Castle<br>Safety keywords: Illness / Identity theft / Medical fraud<br>Note: If the Hunters eliminated one of the Black Feath-<br>ers in the previous Scenario, the other will return to the <br>attack in this Scenario to avenge their fallen comrade. A <br>new Agenda will be applied to the NPC’s profile, replacing <br>the previous one. The Black Feather will always use Murder <br>of Crows as in PART ONE - The Two Healers.<br>Agenda: Eliminate the Hunter responsible for my compan-<br>ion’s death. <br>At the beginning of each Scene, roll 1 die:<br>1-2: The Black Feather does not intervene in the current <br>Scene.<br>3-4: The Black Feather tries to get in the Hunters’ way by <br>acting from a distance, either through the use of the Mur -<br>der or by providing support to the present NPCs.<br>5-6: The Black Feather attacks the Hunters by ambushing <br>them.  <br>Once upon a time…<br>Sailing down the river, the Hunters reach the town of Os, <br>home to the famous White Hospital. The town seems to be <br>a peaceful place to live, and there is no sign of the Frozen <br>Madness.<br>The story that led us here…<br>Gerda and Kay never really stay in Os, but they <br>did leave imposters in their place: Magnus and Iselin, two <br>young upstarts who managed to get married thanks to Ger-<br>da and Kay’s intervention. Vegard, Iselin’s old father, did <br>not approve of the two lovers’ marriage because of some <br>debts that Magnus’ family never paid off. Thanks to a Shard <br>that Kay blasted into the man’s eye, Vegard was transformed <br>from a grumpy breadwinner into a gentle old man who <br>willingly accepted his daughter’s marriage. In exchange for <br>their help, Gerda and Kay have the two newlyweds pose <br>as the famous healers, sending those in need of a cure to <br>Reinsdyr. The thug poses as a guide, but instead, he takes <br>the unfortunate people in a carriage into the forest to be <br>attacked by Rikke’s gang. Magnus and Iselin are not evil, <br>but they agree to deceive people to protect their marriage.</p><p>212<br>The story at the arrival of the Hunters…<br>Magnus and Iselin are in charge of the Hospital’s activi-<br>ties, trying as much as possible to help those most in need. <br>Both have studied to become doctors, but their efforts only <br>contribute to Gerda and Kay’s reputation, giving the two <br>scoundrels an aura of competence far removed from reality. <br>Reinsdyr offers himself as a guide to the rich and needy that <br>the two doctors pass on to him, only to lead them into the <br>thick of the forest and have them attacked by a group of <br>brigands in Gerda and Kay’s service.</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513746054,"modifiedTime":1781513746054,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"XwjL3DAZWXV7sFaI","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>A Frozen Reflection - Scene 1</h2><p>FIRST SCENE –  The arrival at Os<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  You leave the <br>boat in the small port of Os: in front of you you <br>see a quiet little town, very different from the cha-<br>os in which Bergen, hit hard by the Frozen Mad-<br>ness, finds itself. A large sign clearly points in the <br>direction of the famous White Hospital: could it be that the <br>strange disease has really been eradicated from this town by <br>the two famous healers?<br>Place: The White Hospital, an austere and clean medical <br>facility. <br>Time: Early morning as the church bells ring. <br>Initial Situation: The Hunters will have no trouble find-<br>ing the White Hospital and getting an interview with the <br>famous healers. Magnus and Iselin are not expecting a visit <br>from the Hunters of the Order and naively introduce them-<br>selves as Gerda and Kay. Under pressure, they do not hesi-<br>tate to expose the deception of the real Gerda and Kay. The <br>following information can be gleaned from the interview <br>with the two doctors:<br> ◆ Gerda and Kay are two enterprising young people, <br>and it is easy to guess from their behavior that they are <br>accustomed to the shady dealings of the underworld. <br>Kay seems to know about magic, while Gerda shows <br>off magical and powerful objects. <br> ◆ Magnus and Iselin’s job is to refer only the wealthiest <br>patients to Reinsdyr, whose carriage will take them to <br>a mysterious woman a day’s journey from Os. Magnus <br>and Iselin do not know what will happen to the pa-<br>tients. <br> ◆ The village was once protected by a band of nomads <br>who took a liking to the locals and began a fruitful <br>partnership. After Gerda and Kay passed through, <br>young Rikke, who leads the nomads, changed dramati-<br>cally. Now, she and her companions have taken up ban-<br>1</p><p>213<br>ditry. Reinsdyr is the only one who knows the <br>safe ways through the forest, which is why his <br>customers pay him well.<br> ◆ Magnus and Iselin are aware that they are doing some-<br>thing wrong by helping Gerda and Kay, and so they <br>serve the poor and needy without asking for anything <br>in return, trying to atone for their sins. If only Vegard <br>would accept their union, there would be no problem <br>and they would stop deceiving everyone.  <br>When the interview is over, if Iselin has not been coerced <br>or threatened by the Hunters, she will say that she has spent <br>the last few months studying the Frozen Madness and dis-<br>covering its magical origins. If the Hunters wish, she will <br>teach them how to remove the Mirror Shards from those <br>affected. Unfortunately, the process also requires the use of <br>magic, which is why Iselin does not dare perform it on pa-<br>tients herself.<br>End of Scene: The Hunters decide whether to learn from <br>Iselin how to remove the Shard (go to SECOND SCENE <br>OPTION A - A Lesson in Medicine) or approach Reinsdyr <br>instead (go to SECOND SCENE OPTION B - Reinsdyr the <br>Guide.)<br>SECONDA SCENE OPTION <br>A –  A Lesson in Medicine <br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  Iselin leads you into her <br>study and unrolls a scroll of complex magical formulas, <br>saying she found the paper in her father’s great library. The <br>inscriptions reveal that the Mirror of the Other Self is an an-<br>cient and powerful object capable of completely altering the <br>souls of those reflected in it. Iselin noticed an ominous glint <br>in the eyes of those suffering from Frozen Madness, and the <br>symptoms of total behavioral change led her to believe that a <br>Shard from the Mirror might be the cause of the illness.<br>Place: Iselin’s private study.<br>Time: Late morning.    <br>Initial Situation: Iselin will help the Hunters decipher <br>the scrolls, a task that will take all day. At the end of their <br>research, all Hunters who participated will receive the Sce-<br>nario’s Exclusive Gift - Knowledge of the Mirror of the Oth-<br>er Self - without spending any XP to acquire it. <br>Gift - Knowledge of the Mirror of the Other Self:  <br>The Hunter receives 2 Additional Successes when facing <br>the Threat - Shard of the Mirror of the Other Self. <br>End of Scene: Since a whole day has passed and Reinsdyr <br>has moved away from the town, the Hunters can only fol-<br>low his trail. Go to the THIRD SCENE - The Journey.<br>2a</p><p>214</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513746054,"modifiedTime":1781513746054,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"JbWNm0aneMryPW46","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>A Frozen Reflection - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE OPTION B <br>–  Reinsdyr the Guide<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: Reinsdyr can be found <br>in the large central square of Os, his reindeer-drawn <br>carriage standing out from the crowd. Reinsdyr is a <br>tall man with a thick dark beard and a reindeer skin <br>cloak that covers him from head to toe. The headdress <br>he wears is also made from a reindeer head, and the <br>large antlers above it make the man look almost monstrous.<br>Place: The central square of Os, filled with caravans and <br>merchants. <br>Time: In the early hours of the morning, baggers and mer-<br>chants are already hard at work in the marketplace.    <br>Initial Situation: Hunters will find Reinsdyr sitting in <br>his carriage, waiting for potential customers: the man has <br>a surly demeanor, but is willing to talk if money is shown. <br>If cornered, he will fight the Hunters to the death, refusing <br>to talk while free. If the Hunters manage to subdue him <br>somehow, Reinsdyr will reveal the following information:<br> ◆ He has an agreement with Gerda and Kay to lead <br>wealthy clients to the home of Pernille, an ice witch. <br>Pernille and her sister Sinikka were banished by Lady <br>Storm for an old betrayal, but the two witches know <br>the only way to the secret castle where Gerda and Kay <br>have taken refuge.<br> ◆ Along the road Reinsdyr travels, a gang of brigands <br>has taken up residence. They are led by Rikke, a young <br>woman afflicted with the Frozen Madness that has <br>turned her into an unscrupulous thief. Rikke’s gang <br>robs Reinsdyr’s passengers of all their possessions and <br>then lets the coach continue on to Pernille’s house. <br>Reinsdyr the Guide<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a very experienced guide and know all <br>the secrets of survival in the north. I can take down any en-<br>emy with ax and pistol without making too much of a fuss.        <br>Agenda: Escort wealthy Frozen Madness victims to Pernille’s <br>house and share the proceeds of the robberies with Rikke.<br>Gift – Die Hard:  Reinsdyr is resilient and a difficult op-<br>ponent even for Hunters. The guide can act twice during <br>an Exchange, using his ax to hit an enemy in melee combat <br>and his gun to hit a target at a distance. When he suffers <br>1 Wound, Reinsdyr can immediately make an additional <br>attack against the one who wounded him.<br>End of Scene:  With or without Reinsdyr, the Hunters <br>must go to Pernille’s house, go to SCENE THREE - The <br>Journey.<br>2b</p><p>215</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513746054,"modifiedTime":1781513746054,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"oqyUxa4W7ju4dsJH","name":"Scene 3","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>A Frozen Reflection - Scene 3</h2><p>THIRD SCENE –  The Journey<br>Note: This Scene can be introduced in a number of ways, <br>depending on what the Hunters have already done.<br>The Hunters learned the cure for the Frozen <br>Madness<br>In this situation, the Hunters missed the meeting with Re-<br>insdyr, the guide has already left with a wealthy client, and <br>the Hunters must travel the road on their own. Here is a list <br>of possible contingencies:<br> ◆ Rikke and her brigands will ambush the Hunters. Al-<br>ternatively, the Hunters may arrive while the brigands <br>have stopped Reinsdyr’s carriage.<br> ◆ The Hunters reach Reinsdyr.<br> ◆ The Hunters choose an alternative route, avoiding both <br>the brigands and Reinsdyr.<br>End of Scene: The Hunters arrive at Pernille’s house, go to</p>"},"sort":300000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513746054,"modifiedTime":1781513746054,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"ruR7fHWwL2qjAryJ","name":"Scene 4","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>A Frozen Reflection - Scene 4</h2><p>FOURTH SCENE - The Lapland Woman.<br>The Hunters hired Reinsdyr for the trip<br>The Hunters travel “safely” in Reinsdyr’s carriage. Here is a <br>list of possible contingencies:<br> ◆ Rikke and her brigands will ambush the Hunters.<br> ◆ The Hunters convince or force Reinsdyr to avoid brig-<br>and territory.<br>End of Scene: The Hunters arrive at Pernille’s house, go to</p><p>FOURTH SCENE - The Lapland Woman.<br>The Hunters defeated Reinsdyr in Os.<br>The Hunters travel in Reinsdyr’s carriage. Here is a list of <br>possible contingencies:<br> ◆ Rikke and her brigands will ambush them. The Hunt-<br>ers can try to fool the brigands thanks to Reinsdyr’s <br>carriage.<br> ◆ The Hunters choose an alternative route while avoiding <br>the brigands.<br>End of Scene: The Hunters arrive at Pernille’s house, go to</p><p>FOURTH SCENE - The Lapland Woman.<br>Rikke the Nomad<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a northern nomad and have always tried <br>to lead my companions on the right path. I am used to the <br>hard life of the forest and know how to move and hunt well.<br>Agenda: To make my nomadic family prosperous.    <br>Shard Descriptor: I am a nomad from the north, <br>trying to accumulate as much wealth as possible in order to <br>move to a more hospitable climate. I hate the hard life in these <br>latitudes and to survive I exploit my faithful companions.    <br>Shard Agenda: Gather as much wealth as I can <br>through banditry and then run far away, leaving my entire <br>clan to their fate. <br>Gift - Power of the Shard: The Shard of the Mirror of the <br>Other Self reverses the Descriptor and Agenda of the person <br>it injured. The holder increases their OL by 1 if they act in ac-<br>cordance with the altered part of their Descriptor or Agenda. <br>3</p><p>216<br>Nomads<br>Easy OL 3 - Minor NPC <br>(1 Wound - 12 Nomads)<br>Descriptor: We are nomads from the north and have al-<br>ways lived by hunting and trading what we find.<br>Agenda: We want to live in peace, but our loyalty to Rikke <br>drives us to follow her in her madness. We would like to find <br>a way to cure her and return to our nomadic ways.    <br>Gift - Nomad Clan:  A Nomad increases their OL by 1 <br>when they act to defend Rikke from a threat.</p><p>FOURTH SCENE –  The Lap -<br>land Woman<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: You arrive at a small house <br>in the woods, where the river widens into a small lake. Thick <br>smoke pours out of the chimney on the roof into the icy eve-<br>ning air.    <br>Place: The house of Pernille, known as The Lapland Wom-<br>an.<br>Time: The sun is setting.<br>Initial Situation: The meeting with Pernille can vary de-<br>pending on what the Hunters have done so far. The witch is <br>only loyal to Gerda and Kay because she is being rewarded <br>for her services, and she will not hesitate to betray them if <br>the Hunters corner her. Pernille’s approach to dealing with <br>the Hunters will vary depending on the possible events pre-<br>sented at the end of this Scenario.<br>Pernille The Lapland Woman<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a fearsome ice witch who learned the art <br>of magic from the famous Lady Storm.<br>Agenda: Earn as much as possible without risking my life.<br>Gift - Ice Magic: Pernille can manipulate frost to create <br>ice at a range of sixty feet. When she acts, she can choose <br>one of the following effects:<br>1. Ice Rain: The sharp fragments can hit up to 3 targets, <br>causing 1 Wound.<br>4</p><p>217<br>2. Ice Trap: Up to 3 targets are gripped in ice, preventing <br>them from moving their legs. To break free, it is necessary <br>to pass a Defense Check.<br>3. Ice Golem:  Summon an ice creature under Pernille’s <br>control. <br>Ice Golem<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a mighty creature of pure ice and live only <br>to serve my creator. <br>Information: Pernille is the only one who knows the <br>magic formula that opens the portal located in the small <br>lake, leading to the house of Sinikka, the Finland Wom-<br>an. A Hunter who understands magic can also activate the <br>portal by studying the passage. If both of these options are <br>impractical, Hunters can ask Iselin for help.<br>Threat –  The Magic Lake Portal<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: A magical portal leading close to Lady Storm’s <br>castle. Only those who know the magic formula can plunge <br>into the lake’s waters and pass through.<br>Epilogue<br>Once they plunge into the waters of the lake, the Hunters <br>are transported to the home of Sinikka the Finland Wom-<br>an, a few miles from Lady Storm’s castle. <br>Storyteller’s Note: The Hunters’ journey continues with <br>PART THREE - The Winter Castle. <br>Scenario Events<br>There are 3 Events in this Scenario, though the Storyteller <br>should feel free to create new ones in response to the Hunt-<br>er’s actions.<br>If one of the Black Feathers or Reinsdyr can still <br>act after a fight: they will have anticipated the Hunters <br>and alerted Pernille to the danger. <br>If no one has warned Pernille of the arrival of the <br>Hunters: the witch will act as usual and tell the Hunt-<br>ers that to get to Gerda and Kay’s castle, they must pass <br>through a secret passage that only she knows. However, this <br>passage is very expensive, and Pernille will ask the Hunters <br>for a large sum of money.<br>If Miss Snow and Lady Storm are among the <br>Hunters: Pernille will take refuge in the house and try to <br>intimidate the Hunters into leaving. The old witch is afraid <br>that Lady Storm will punish her for helping Gerda and Kay.</p><p>218<br>Part Three – The Winter Castle<br>Safety keywords: Illness / Identity theft  <br>Once upon a time…<br>The Hunters emerge from the lake and find themselves in <br>front of the house of the Finland Woman. It is a small build-<br>ing, equal to Pernille’s in every way. Turning their gaze to the <br>north, the imposing silhouette of a castle is a dark shadow in <br>the middle of a snowstorm.<br>The story that led us here…<br>Gerda and Kay retired to Lady Storm’s castle to en-<br>joy the fruits of their misdeeds. In a fit of boredom, Gerda <br>began to study in Lady Storm’s library. The young wom-<br>an had always had a flair for magic and found great sat-<br>isfaction in learning the arcane art. Meanwhile, Kay took <br>to the good life, using Lady Storm’s magic sleigh to travel <br>around Europe, wasting a lot of money on revelry. A week <br>ago, however, Gerda attempted a very powerful spell and <br>lost control at the climax of the ritual. The castle’s magic <br>resonated with the power generated by the unwary Gerda, <br>awakening a malevolent consciousness in the structure that <br>took the name Ice Heart. The Ice Heart then unleashed a <br>powerful blizzard, freezing Kay in an ice shrine, while Ger-<br>da was struck by a Shard from the Mirror of the Other Self, <br>the thing that made her deception possible turning against <br>her. The ice reached Sinikka’s house and mercilessly swept <br>everything away.<br>The story at the arrival of the <br>Hunters…<br>The Hunters have arrived at Sinikka’s house, but it will not <br>be easy to find out where they really are and how far they <br>have traveled thanks to the magic of the lake. The Finland <br>Woman’s house is completely covered in a blanket of ice as <br>if a blizzard has swept over everything in its fury. In Lady <br>Storm’s castle, Gerda desperately tries to save Kay: now that <br>her character has been changed by the Shard, the contempt <br>she felt for her partner in mischief has become a strong <br>love. Unable to thwart the will of the castle, Gerda has taken <br>refuge in Lady Storm’s great library in search of a solution.</p><p>219</p>"},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513746055,"modifiedTime":1781513746055,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"XwjL3DAZWXV7sFaI","name":"Scene 1","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>A Frozen Reflection - Scene 1</h2><p>FIRST SCENE –  The Finland <br>Woman<br>Read aloud to the Hunters:  As Pernille indicated, the <br>magic lake has led you to the home of Sinikka, her coven <br>partner. What puzzles you, however, is the total desolation <br>of the dwelling. Everything is covered in a thick layer of ice <br>as if a very powerful blizzard has been punishing the place <br>for years.    <br>Place: Sinikka’s completely frozen house.<br>Time: The sun rises as if the journey across the magic lake <br>had taken a whole night.<br>Initial Situation: Everything is covered in ice. Upon en-<br>tering the house, the Hunters will see the figure of Sinikka, <br>frozen as she was about to turn the ladle in a pot of soup <br>above the hearth. It is clear that the witch has been taken <br>by surprise. <br>Information: Observing the house, it will be easy to see <br>that the ice covering it is of magical origin. Sinikka may be <br>alive, but melting this ice will require a great deal of effort. If <br>the Hunters succeed in freeing Sinikka, the witch will thank <br>them and explain that a week ago she sensed the activation <br>of powerful magic, summoned by a strong and malevolent <br>presence that seemed to emanate from the castle itself. The <br>witch did not have time to understand what was happening <br>before she was struck by a blizzard. Sinikka is extremely <br>weak and will not follow the Hunters into the castle for any <br>reason. She has no useful information, other than that since <br>Gerda and Kay settled there, only a few people have come <br>from the lake to be cured of the Frozen Madness, and none <br>have ever returned. <br>Threat – Ice Layer<br>OL Hard 7<br>Descriptor: A thick layer of steel-hard ice. <br>End of Scene: The Hunters can head to Lady Storm’s cas-<br>tle, go to SECOND SCENE - Lady Storm’s Castle.</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513746055,"modifiedTime":1781513746055,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"JbWNm0aneMryPW46","name":"Scene 2","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>A Frozen Reflection - Scene 2</h2><p>SECOND SCENE –  Lady Storm’s <br>Castle<br>Read aloud to the Hunters: In front of you is an ancient <br>castle that appears to be made entirely of ice. The large en-<br>trance door is open, and there seems to be no guard at all. As <br>you walk across the bridge, which is also frozen, a shiver runs <br>down your spine, and you know that the cold is not to blame. <br>It may sound crazy, but you feel a gaze directed at you, as if <br>the whole structure has a malevolent will of its own.    <br>Place: Lady Storm’s Castle.<br>Time: Early morning of a clear-sky day. <br>Initial Situation: The castle is open, so it will be easy for <br>the Hunters to enter. Each room is completely covered in <br>ice, and moving around the structure takes time, consider-<br>ing there are over two hundred rooms. <br>Information: Exploration of the castle is handled by <br>Encounter Rooms, each with a different challenge for the <br>Hunters. These places represent the will of the Ice Heart <br>to eliminate unwanted guests. After each Encounter Room, <br>the Hunters will wander through other neutral rooms, <br>where they will find information about Lady Storm, the <br>true owner of the castle. These rooms are important be-<br>cause they provide vital clues as to what kind of heat can <br>scratch the Ice Heart, as explained on page 224.<br>1<br>2</p><p>220<br>Roll or choose what kind of information to give for rooms <br>without an encounter.<br>1: A huge painting depicts the figure of a beautiful woman <br>with skin as icy as snow. Her eyes are ice blue and her hair is <br>light and flowing. The plaque reads, “Lady Storm, Queen of <br>Winter, everything in her is pure frost except her heart. ”<br>2: A completely frozen old book lies open on a lectern. From <br>the few lines that can be made out, it appears to be a treatise <br>on ice magic. Among the many pages, the word “friendship” <br>is underlined. <br>3: An array of gold jewelry and bracelets lies in a completely <br>frozen display case. This is jewelry of the highest value, and <br>each has a small plaque identifying it as a gift of love from a <br>powerful European ruler. <br>4: A large painting covers the entire wall, with a beautiful <br>woman wrapped in ice in the center and a coven of witches at <br>her feet, smiling and offering her gifts in gratitude. <br>5: A huge globe is painted on the vaulted ceiling of the room. <br>Under the ice covering it, routes can be seen that seem to con-<br>nect a castle to various parts of the world. A sleigh is depicted <br>on the lines of travel, and one of the routes is clearly in the <br>shape of a heart.    <br>6: An ice sculpture stands in the center of a large bedroom. <br>The figures of two children are carved in ice, embracing each <br>other in an affectionate gesture of friendship.<br>As soon as the Hunters enter the castle behind them, a wall <br>of ice will fall and the windows will turn to frozen slabs. It <br>will be clear that there is no way out. <br>The following pages contain several Encounter Rooms, and <br>you, as the Storyteller, are free to decide which ones you <br>want to use. After at least two Encounter Rooms, the Hunt-<br>ers will find the Special Room - Library, where Gerda <br>has locked herself up, and through which it will be possible <br>to access the Special Room - Heart of the Castle  and <br>end the spell. To get there, Hunters will have to go through <br>at least one other Encounter Room.   <br>Exploration will follow this order:<br> ◆ At least 2 Encounter Rooms <br> ◆ Special Room - Library<br> ◆ At least 1 more Encounter Room<br> ◆ Special Room - Heart of the Castle<br>A room with information should be inserted between each <br>room.</p><p>221<br>ENCOUNTER ROOM –  Guard Post <br>Descriptor: A large armory with a series of ice statues de-<br>picting soldiers. <br>Information: Walking through the hall will cause the ice <br>statues to activate and move to eliminate intruders. There <br>are 16 statues in total, activated in groups of 4. The activa-<br>tion of the statues is determined by the vibrations caused by <br>the Hunters walking across the icy floor of the hall. <br>Ice Soldier<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (2 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a soldier made entirely of ice and I defend <br>Lady Storm’s castle. My priority is to always focus on the tar-<br>gets that make the most noise.<br>ENCOUNTER ROOM –  Col-umns Walk<br>Descriptor: A very long corridor leads into the heart of <br>Lady Storm’s castle. A series of ice pillars divides the corridor, <br>and in them, you can see the silhouettes of trapped people.    <br>Information: The trapped people are mostly treasure <br>seekers, but if you look closely, you can see some of the <br>Bergen nobles. It will be clear to the Hunters that the sick <br>people who made it to the castle are trapped inside the col-<br>umns. The columns are difficult to melt, and the people <br>inside them are dead. Approaching a column without an <br>occupant will activate Threat - Columns of Eternal Sleep.<br> Threat – Columns  of Eternal Sleep<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: A column of magical ice capable of absorbing <br>living things and enveloping them in a deadly frost.<br>Gift - Glacial Embrace: A target that fails a Check when <br>the column tries to absorb them is wrapped in ice and takes <br>1 Wound. During each action, the encased subject can at-<br>tempt to free themselves by making a Position Check, suf-<br>fering 1 Wound if they fail. When they run out of Wounds, <br>the target is completely absorbed by the column. An NPC <br>automatically suffers 1 Wound with each of its actions un-<br>til it has consumed all of its Wounds. At the Storyteller’s <br>discretion, a particularly skilled NPC may choose to free <br>themselves with one of their actions. <br>ENCOUNTER ROOM –  Me-morial Church<br>Descriptor: A large Gothic church made entirely of ice. <br>Small snowflakes fall from the large vault in the ceiling and <br>float gently to the ground.    <br>Information: The snowflakes are imbued with Lady <br>Storm’s power and are capable of erasing the memory of <br>those they touch. If a subject does not find a way to protect <br>themselves from contact, they will suffer the effect of the <br>Threat - Snow of Memory. In the main altar is a large shrine <br>with an object inside: this is a Treasure of the Order, which <br>the Storyteller must choose at will from those presented <br>from page 19. It takes two minutes to sprint through the <br>Church.</p><p>222<br>Threat – Snow of Memory<br>OL Medium 5<br>Descriptor: Tiny snowflakes that can freeze a person’s <br>memories forever until they forget everything. <br>Gift - Ice Oblivion:  For each minute a subject is under <br>the snowfall, it is touched by a number of flakes equal to <br>the result of a die roll. The result determines the effect to be <br>applied. If the subject does nothing to protect themselves <br>from the snow, they cannot make a Defense Check against <br>the Threat. The Storyteller must evaluate, based on protec-<br>tive measures and the subject’s clothing, whether they are <br>more exposed to snowflakes (roll 2 dice and choose the <br>higher value) or are more sheltered (roll 2 dice and choose <br>the lower value). <br>1-2: A severe headache accompanies a cherished memory <br>that slowly fades, leaving the target with the perception of <br>an event lost forever. The target loses 2 Soma. An NPC re-<br>duces their OL by 1 for the remainder of the Scenario.<br>3-4: The face of a loved one appears fleetingly in the tar -<br>get’s mind before disappearing, leaving them with the feel-<br>ing of having lost the memory of a loved one. The target <br>loses the use of one of their Descriptors (except the Dark <br>Ego) until the end of the Scenario. An NPC loses their only <br>Descriptor and replaces it with this one: I’ve lost my memo-<br>ry and have no idea where I am. <br>5-6: The target hears a phrase whispered so quietly it is <br>unintelligible, leaving them with the perception that a part <br>of themselves is lost forever. The target loses the use of one <br>Gift for the rest of the Scenario (except Dark Ego). An NPC <br>who has no Gifts to lose reduces their OL by one category. If <br>they already have OL Easy 3, they suffer 1 Wound instead.  <br>ENCOUNTER ROOM –  Troll <br>Workshop<br>Descriptor: A small room with the remains of a large bro-<br>ken mirror. Twelve more mirrors are placed in each corner, <br>creating a striking play of reflections. <br>Information: A Troll stands in the small hall. It is the cre-<br>ator of the Mirror of the Other Self. After the artifact broke, <br>the craftsman went completely insane and now tries to re-<br>produce the original, failing miserably each time. The Troll <br>hates to be interrupted, and any discussion topic other than <br>the re-creation of his beloved mirror will incur his wrath. <br>Over time, the Troll has blinded himself with splinters from <br>the many mirrors he is not satisfied with and, unaware that <br>Lady Storm is no longer in the castle, he continues his mad <br>work.<br>Troll Craftsman<br>OL Medium 5 - Minor NPC (4 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a skilled craftsman and have served Lady <br>Storm for decades, creating stunning ice mirrors for her. I can <br>manipulate the reflected images as if they were real.    <br>Agenda: Rebuilding the Mirror of the Other Self for my <br>Lady Storm.    <br>Special Agenda (Prince Trollo the Innocent): I have <br>always wanted an apprentice to pass my art on to, and he <br>seems perfect. Whether he wants to or not.    <br>Gift - The Mirrored Reality:  Although blinded, the <br>Troll can see the world around it through the mirrors scat-<br>tered throughout the room, thanks to the glare of the shards <br>in his eyes. The Troll can act against a target by striking at <br>a reflected image without the target being able to make a <br>Defense Check to avoid it.</p><p>223<br>ENCOUNTER ROOM –  Guest <br>Room<br>Descriptor: A luxurious bedroom. The ice on the walls <br>seems to have no effect on the furnishings, and even the tem-<br>perature seems decidedly milder than in the rest of the castle.    <br>Information: The room is filled with valuables and com-<br>forts. Time flows differently here, which is understandable <br>since the Hunters will feel extremely rested after a few min-<br>utes. If they stay in the room for at least an hour, they will <br>be able to call an Interlude without the Scenario Agendas <br>continuing.<br>SPECIAL ROOM –  Library<br>Descriptor: A vast library carved from the ice, with walls <br>of books stretching as far as the eye can see. A magical seal, <br>pulsing with power, is clearly visible at the library’s entrance. <br>Information: The seal is a protective spell that Gerda <br>cast to prevent the Ice Heart from reaching her. As Hunters <br>wander through the Library, they will hear Gerda mutter -<br>ing as she conducts her research. The young woman has <br>retained the memory of her misdeeds, but now her priority <br>is to save Kay, and she will not hesitate to ask the Hunters <br>for help. Gerda will give them the following information:<br> ◆ The Ice Heart is a core of magical energy that sits atop <br>Lady Storm’s throne. Through her research, Gerda dis-<br>covered that the Heart is a simulacrum of Lady Storm’s <br>consciousness that the castle has assimilated over the <br>years. <br> ◆ In an old diary hidden in the Library, Gerda has read <br>that the only thing Lady Storm fears is heat, which <br>means that the Ice Heart can be defeated if it is exposed <br>to heat. Gerda has already tried this, but even when she <br>brought a flame close to the Heart, nothing happened, <br>so Gerda is racking her brain to find out what kind of <br>heat the diary is referring to.<br> ◆ The Ice Heart has total control of the castle and will <br>not allow anyone to leave. Now even the Hunters are <br>prisoners like her.<br>The warmth referred to in the diary, as can be deduced from <br>the many scenes depicted in the rooms through which the <br>Hunters pass, is that of emotional warmth. However, Ger-<br>da, who is not a good person, is unable to intuit this truth. <br>Gerda the Swindler<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a skilled trickster, my sharp mind matched <br>only by my nerve. While studying Lady Storm’s books, I dis-<br>covered that I can also dabble in magic, and I have no qualms <br>about using it to my own advantage.    <br>Agenda: Living in luxury without working and increasing <br>my power to get my hands on more wealth / Supporting Kay <br>in his whims, because even though I think he is an idiot, I <br>need a trustworthy sidekick who will always do what I say. <br>Shard Descriptor: I am a naive girl who struggles <br>to express her feelings. Thanks to the magic I have learned, I <br>can help others. <br>Shard Agenda: Save my beloved Kay from the sad <br>fate that befell him / Defeat the Ice Heart.<br>Gift - Power of the Shard:  The Shard of the Mirror of <br>the Other Self reverses the Descriptor and Agenda of the <br>person it injured. The holder increases their OL by 1 if they <br>act in accordance with the altered part of their Descriptor <br>or Agenda.</p><p>224<br>Gift - Magician’s Apprentice: Gerda has learned the <br>rudiments of magic and can choose one of the following <br>effects as an action. <br>1. Create 3 ice darts to hit up to 3 different targets. The same <br>subject cannot be the target of more than one dart at a time.<br>2. Create a blizzard that will knock down all subjects with-<br>in a sixty-foot radius of Gerda. <br>3. Manipulate memory by touching the subject’s forehead: <br>Gerda can create a false memory or remove the memory of <br>something that happened during the Scene.  <br>SPECIAL ROOM –  Heart of the <br>Castle<br>Descriptor: Lady Storm’s throne room, where a sphere of <br>pure ice floats. The magic in this place is so powerful that <br>even ordinary people can feel it.    <br>Information: Above the great throne hovers the Ice <br>Heart, which will greet the Hunters by speaking directly <br>to their minds. The Ice Heart will ask the Hunters to turn <br>Gerda over to it so it can punish her for what she did to <br>Lady Storm. If they cooperate, the Ice Heart will be willing <br>to allow the Hunters to leave the castle, delaying their end <br>until it unleashes an eternal frost upon the world. <br>In the center of the room is an ice pillar with Kay inside, <br>trapped in a fleeing position with a terrified expression <br>on his face. To free Gerda’s accomplice, you must face the <br>Threat – Ice Layer (see page 219).<br>The Ice Heart<br>OL Medium 5 - Main NPC (6 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am a fragment of pure power and live only <br>to punish all humans guilty of hurting my Lady Storm. I am <br>the castle and within it, all is in my power. I have no human <br>malice and speak my mind without a filter. <br>Agenda: Punish Gerda for what she did to Lady Storm / <br>Punish humanity and freeze it in eternal ice.    <br>Gift - I Am Winter:  The Ice Heart is a manifestation of <br>power and can manipulate anything within the castle. As <br>an action, the Heart can inflict 1Wound from cold on any <br>subject in the castle without the ability to make a Defense <br>Check. The only safe place in the castle is the Library, where <br>the Heart’s power cannot reach because of the seal Gerda <br>created. A sincere expression of love or friendship in the <br>presence of the Ice Heart can immediately shatter and de-<br>stroy it.</p><p>225<br>Scenario Events<br>There are 3 Events in this Scenario, though the Storyteller <br>should feel free to create new ones in response to the Hunt-<br>ers’ actions.<br>If the Hunters succeed in calming the Troll:  the <br>Troll will be able to teach them the Scenario’s Exclusive Gift <br>- Knowledge of the Mirror of the Other Self. <br>If the Hunters remove the Shard from Gerda: now <br>a con artist once more, she will try to escape by using her <br>magic. <br>If the Hunters free Kay:  the scoundrel will try to help <br>Gerda, but only if doing so can help him escape. Otherwise, <br>he will just try to escape to save himself. <br>Epilogue<br>Eliminating the Ice Heart will cause the castle to collapse, <br>while leaving it active will create a threat that the Hunters <br>know they will face in the future. If Miss Snow and Lady <br>Storm were among the Hunters who participated in the <br>playthrough, a choice must be made:<br> ◆ Forgetting the Past: Miss Snow’s personality takes <br>over, forever relegating Lady Storm to the role of sec-<br>ond personality. Her Hunter Sheet remains unchanged, <br>as the memory of what happened is once again erased, <br>and Miss Snow embarks on another search for her past.<br> ◆ Remembering the Past: Lady Storm regains control of <br>her body, but, feeling indebted to Miss Snow, infuses <br>some of her magic to give her life. Her Hunter Sheet is <br>replaced with the following one.</p><p>Miss Snow<br>OL Easy 3 - (3 Wounds)<br>Descriptor: I am an apprentice ice mage, although I often cause disasters with <br>my powers. I am naive and always kind to others. <br> <br>Gift – Snow Sorceress Apprentice: Miss Snow can use the Gifts of the <br>Snow Sorceress and Winter’s Kiss, but when she does, she rolls a die, and <br>if she rolls a 4 or higher, a magical disaster (determined by the Storyteller) <br>occurs, complicating the situation.<br>Descriptors and Gifts<br>I am a powerful ice sorceress and can manipulate the weather. I want <br>Snow to learn to be a Hunter, so I limit the use of my powers to solving <br>problems for her. <br>•  Snow Sorceress: Y ou can use magic to create and manipulate the cold. <br>Describe the effects of a spell that has one of the following Keywords as a con-<br>dition: Ice, Snow, or Frost. Y ou could, for example, Create an Ice Bridge <br>to cross a crevasse or Freeze an Enemy to immobilize it. Pay a cost of 1 to 2 <br>Soma, decided by the Storyteller, to activate the spell. The effects you describe <br>last until the end of the Scene. The Soma cost is increased by 1 when environ-<br>mental conditions are not compatible with cold.<br>I am impassive and know how to assert my authority, nothing can <br>shake my heart. I have a weakness for those who show true love or <br>friendship, and it comes naturally to me to help these people, although <br>I do not want anyone to notice this weakness of mine. <br>•  Winter’s Kiss: In you lies the power of winter. When you give someone <br>a chaste kiss, you can choose one of the following effects:<br>1. Erase one of their memories. It must be the memory of an event in the Scene <br>in which you use this effect. Particularly capable Hunters and NPCs may requi-<br>re a Position Check for the effect to succeed.<br>2. Make the subject immune to cold for the rest of the Scene. This will prevent <br>them from suffering Wounds from frost and make them immune to the effects <br>of the Snow Sorceress Gift. <br>3. Make an object extremely fragile. <br>Y ou can spend 1 Soma when you use this Gift to blow a kiss to the target, thus <br>avoiding physical contact.<br>I have a special insight into understanding people and their intentions, <br>and with my magic, I can quickly create help for the weak. I dislike peo-<br>ple who talk too much and social events.  <br>•  Dark Ego - Deus Ex Machina:  When all seems lost, use your magic <br>to make truth triumph. Reduce by 1 the Soma cost of spells you cast with <br>the Gift of the Snow Sorceress when your goal is to help someone. Once per <br>Exchange, you can spend 1 Soma to prevent one of your allies from taking <br>1 Wound by protecting them with a wall of icy frost. Y ou can use the Gift of <br>Winter’s Kiss as a free action once per Exchange.<br>Activator: Step in and show your power to save a good-hearted person from the <br>danger that threatens them.<br>Equipment<br>A brooch in the shape of a sleigh / A small knife with an ice blade that never <br>melts / A scarf handmade by Miss Snow / Books of magic / A mirror fragment <br>with a strange magical aura.<br>Soma<br> 5<br>PX<br>Lady Storm and <br>Miss Snow<br>Iam a powerful witch who rules over winter and frost. Because of a betrayal, I was robbed of my <br>body for a long time and a new personality was created in me: Miss Snow. As much as I hate to admit <br>it, it is thanks to Miss Snow that I have regained my full strength, and I intend to help her find her way. Thanks to my magic, I have given her a body, and now we are like twins: identical in appearance, <br>but profoundly different in character. Snow has agreed to remain in the ranks of the Order, and until she is able to fend for herself, I will watch over her. <br>Special: Miss Snow is an NPC under the complete control of the Storyteller. Lady Storm guards over her on her missions on behalf of the Order.  <br>Wounds <br>1.<br>2.<br>3.<br>Additional <br>Wound.</p>"},"sort":200000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513746055,"modifiedTime":1781513746055,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"a-frozen-reflection","collection":"Lost Stories","sourceFile":"bt-ls-book-1-ENG-SCREEN.pdf","pages":"201-227"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513746055,"modifiedTime":1781513746055,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"ujcR3PsWSKTdhcGg","name":"The Newcomer's Crown","pages":[{"_id":"4WaBMwV1t4P3hllx","name":"Summary","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":1},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h1>The Newcomer's Crown</h1><p><strong>Collection:</strong> Standalone</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> The Newcomer's Crown [2022-06-28].pdf, pages 1-1.</p><p><img src=\"systems/broken-tales/assets/adventures/maps/the-newcomers-crown-p1-full.png\" style=\"max-width: 100%; height: auto;\" /></p>"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513746541,"modifiedTime":1781513746541,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}},{"_id":"PwRQdr5EAjt0uLD3","name":"Scenario Text","type":"text","title":{"show":true,"level":2},"text":{"format":1,"markdown":"","content":"<h2>The Newcomer's Crown - Scenario Text</h2><p>The Newcomer’s Crown<br>Once upon a time, an old and dissipated king was served by a <br>company of knights, also old and tired. Although in the past the <br>kingdom had been an example of courage and righteousness, <br>now it was nothing more than a land lost to pleasure and <br>laziness. To fight his ennui, the king called a tournament in <br>which anyone could participate. The dissolute ruler’s intent was <br>to cruelly laugh while his knights were beating on some poor <br>peasant attracted by the idea of becoming a noble. On the day <br>of the tournament, however, only the knights had entered. The <br>people were discouraged by fear, despite the fact that the grand <br>prize, nobility, could change their lives forever. However, shortly <br>before the start of the tournament, a mysterious challenger <br>appeared, a small boy with a wooden sword. The king and <br>his knights laughed heartily, warning the fool not to enter his <br>name. In response, the young man said he wanted to become a <br>knight, and what better way to achieve his dream than winning <br>a tournament?<br>Taking pity, the king sought an excuse to prevent the young <br>man’s death at the edge of some random blade. “If you don’t <br>have a helmet to protect your head, I’m afraid you can’t <br>participate. ” The young man did not lose heart. Instead, he took <br>a small wicker basket, like those used as cradles, and put it on <br>his head. “I am ready, Your Majesty, ” replied the young man.<br>The king began the tournament… and the knights fell one after <br>the other. With absolute courage, against all expectations, the <br>young man defeated all the challengers before the stunned gaze <br>of the king. “ And now that I have demonstrated my bravery, can <br>you make me a knight?”<br>The king, visibly amazed, smiled. He thought about it for a <br>moment and then shouted, “ Arrest this young man! He’s the <br>Devil himself!” The guards grabbed him. Realizing the danger, <br>the boy begged the king for mercy. But the king certainly could <br>not allow true courage and purity of heart to sprout in his <br>kingdom, proving how unworthy he was to sit at its head. <br>And so it was that the young man’s head was lopped off by the <br>headsman’s ax, leaving the small basket as the only memory of <br>his courage and his purity, soiled with blood.<br>Keywords: Purity / Attempt / Challenge / Tournament / <br>Courage / Unexpected<br>Gift - The Newcomer’s Crown:  The Hunter who wears <br>the small basket as a helmet is infused with purity and <br>courage. When facing a threat for the first time, the Hunter <br>gets 1 Additional Success at both the first Position Check and <br>the first Defense Check they must perform. Once per Scene, <br>when they take an action where they do not have a relevant <br>Descriptor, they still get 3 Base Successes. Once per Scene, <br>when the Hunter fails a Position Check, they gain back 1 <br>Soma.<br>The Newcomer’s Crown<br>Inspired by the Arthurian Myth</p>"},"sort":100000,"ownership":{"default":-1},"flags":{},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513746541,"modifiedTime":1781513746541,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"adventureSlug":"the-newcomers-crown","collection":"Standalone","sourceFile":"The Newcomer's Crown [2022-06-28].pdf","pages":"1-1"}},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"13.351","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.0","createdTime":1781513746541,"modifiedTime":1781513746541,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
